label: paraxial mesoderm
Defs: The paraxial mesoderm is the mesoderm located bilaterally adjacent to the notochord and neural tube[GO].

label: regulation of nervous system development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of nervous system development, the origin and formation of nervous tissue.

label: submucosa of small intestine
Defs: Submucosal tissue in the small intestines.

label: cation
Defs: A monoatomic or polyatomic species having one or more elementary charges of the proton.

label: arterial endothelial cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized endothelial cell acquires specialized features of an arterial endothelial cell, a thin flattened cell that lines the inside surfaces of arteries.

label: sound quality
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of vibration, as perceived by the sense of hearing.

label: cardiac neural crest cell migration involved in outflow tract morphogenesis
Defs: The orderly movement of a neural crest cell from one site to another that will contribute to the morphogenesis of the outflow tract.

label: cell fate commitment involved in formation of primary germ layer
Defs: The commitment of cells to specific cell fates of the endoderm, ectoderm, or mesoderm as a part of gastrulation.

label: wall of left ventricle
Defs: Wall of ventricle which is continuous with the wall of aorta.

label: autonomic ganglion
Defs: Ganglion that has dendrites that form a junction between autonomic nerves originating from the central nervous system and autonomic nerves innervating their target organs in the periphery. There are two subtypes, sympathetic ganglion and parasympathetic ganglion.

label: bronchus smooth muscle
Defs: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a bronchus [Automatically generated definition].

label: negative regulation of metabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways within a cell or an organism.

label: digestive tract
Defs: A tube extending from the mouth to the anus.

label: falciform
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having the shape of a scythe or sickle.

label: macrophage cytokine production
Defs: The appearance of a macrophage cytokine due to biosynthesis or secretion following a cellular stimulus, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label: conjunctival keel
Defs: The cuticular evagination constituted by conjunctiva that is elongated.

label: chemical synaptic transmission
Defs: The vesicular release of classical neurotransmitter molecules from a presynapse, across a chemical synapse, the subsequent activation of neurotransmitter receptors at the postsynapse of a target cell (neuron, muscle, or secretory cell) and the effects of this activation on the postsynaptic membrane potential and ionic composition of the postsynaptic cytosol. This process encompasses both spontaneous and evoked release of neurotransmitter and all parts of synaptic vesicle exocytosis. Evoked transmission starts with the arrival of an action potential at the presynapse.

label: pigment cell
Defs: A pigment cell is a cell that contains pigment granules.

label: premental-glossal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the labium that connects the prementum and the glossa.

label: submucosa of uterine tube
Defs: The submucous layer of the wall of the uterine tube.

label: purple
Defs: A color that falls about midway between red and blue in hue.

label: neurotransmitter receptor transport to postsynaptic membrane
Defs: The directed movement of neurotransmitter receptor to the postsynaptic membrane in transport vesicles.

label: positive regulation of compound eye photoreceptor cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of compound eye photoreceptor cell differentiation.

label: left ovary
Defs: An ovary that is part of a left side of organism [Automatically generated definition].

label: negative regulation of hemopoiesis
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of hemopoiesis.

label: adrenergic agent
Defs: Any agent that acts on an adrenergic receptor or affects the life cycle of an adrenergic transmitter.

label: cell of skeletal muscle
Defs: A somatic cell located in skeletal muscle.

label: visual system development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the visual system over time, from its formation to the mature structure, including the eye, parts of the central nervous system (CNS) involved in processing of visual inputs, and connecting nerve pathways.

label: future mouth
Defs: The primordial mouth region of the developing head.

label: epithelial cell proliferation involved in liver morphogenesis
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of epithelial cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population that contributes to the shaping of the liver.

label: acetate transmembrane transport
Defs: The process in which acetate is transported across a membrane. Acetate is the 2-carbon carboxylic acid ethanoic acid.

label: inorganic anion transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of inorganic anions from one side of a membrane to the other. Inorganic anions are atoms or small molecules with a negative charge which do not contain carbon in covalent linkage.

label: gland of tongue
Defs: Any of the mucous, serous, or mixed glands that empty their secretions onto the surface of the tongue.

label: passive
Defs: A behavioral quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s receiving or being subjected to an action without responding or initiating an action in return.

label: cuticular apophysis
Defs: The cuticular invagination that is hollow.

label: right lung endothelium
Defs: An endothelium that is part of a right lung.

label: matted
Defs: A tangled quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being not possible to unravel.

label: vitelline artery
Defs: The paired arteries that carry blood to the yolk sac from the dorsal aorta.

label: mesentery of oesophagus
Defs: A mesentery that is part of a esophagus [Automatically generated definition].

label: endocrine system
Defs: Anatomical system that consists of the glands and parts of glands that produce endocrine secretions and help to integrate and control bodily metabolic activity.

label: layer formation in cerebral cortex
Defs: The detachment of cells from radial glial fibers at the appropriate time when they cease to migrate and form distinct layer in the cerebral cortex.

label: regulation of membrane potential
Defs: Any process that modulates the establishment or extent of a membrane potential, the electric potential existing across any membrane arising from charges in the membrane itself and from the charges present in the media on either side of the membrane.

label: negative regulation of respiratory gaseous exchange
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of respiratory gaseous exchange.

label: decreased object quality
Defs: A quality of an object that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

label: positive regulation of myoblast proliferation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of myoblast proliferation.

label: increased male receptivity
Defs: A male receptivity which is relatively high.

label: photosensitive
Defs: A photosensitivity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting photosensitivity.

label: tricuspidate
Defs: A cuscpidate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer possessing three cusps.

label: permeability
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to being permeated or pervaded by a gas or liquid (as by osmosis or diffusion).

label: cystic duct development
Defs: The progression of the cystic duct over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The cystic duct runs from the gall bladder to the common bile duct.

label: cuticle of insect abdomen
Defs: The region of the cuticle that is posterior to the thorax.

label: gustatory system
Defs: The sensory system for the sense of taste.

label: bowl shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being shaped in the form of a bowl.

label: T-cell surface glycoprotein CD3 epsilon chain (mouse)
Defs: A CD3 epsilon that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: keyword textual entity
Defs: A textual entity listing keywords indicating the major theme(s) of a document.

label: hematopoietic oligopotent progenitor cell
Defs: A hematopoietic oligopotent progenitor cell that has the ability to differentiate into limited cell types but lacks lineage cell markers and self renewal capabilities.

label: nuclear microtubule
Defs: Any microtubule in the nucleus of a cell.

label: erythrocyte development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an erythrocyte over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: cicatricial
Defs: Having or resembling the characteristic of a cicatrix - a scar resulting from formation and contraction of fibrous tissue.

label: decreased cellular motility
Defs: A cellular motility which is lower relative to the normal or average.

label: regulation of endothelial tube morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of endothelial tube morphogenesis.

label: negative regulation of blood vessel morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of blood vessel morphogenesis.

label: cell
Defs: A material entity of anatomical origin (part of or deriving from an organism) that has as its parts a maximally connected cell compartment surrounded by a plasma membrane.

label: thoracic segment muscle
Defs: Any muscle organ that is part of a thorax [Automatically generated definition].

label: negative regulation of smooth muscle cell migration
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of smooth muscle cell migration.

label: variant
Defs: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits variation or change.

label: sulfur compound transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of a sulfur compound from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: primary lung bud formation
Defs: The morphogenetic process in which the foregut region specified to become the lung forms the initial left and right buds.

label: epiproct
Defs: The sclerite of the postabdomen that is attached to the posterior margin of the abdominal tergite X by the abdominal tergite X-epiproct conjunctiva.

label: carbohydrate transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of carbohydrate from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: collagenous
Defs: A composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s consisting of collagen.

label: positive regulation of protein localization
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of a protein localization.

label: cardiac atrium
Defs: Cardiac chamber in which blood enters the heart.

label: variability
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to varying or changing.

label: negative regulation of chorionic trophoblast cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of chorionic trophoblast cell proliferation.

label: pharyngeal arch artery 3
Defs: The vessels formed within the third pair of branchial arches in embryogenesis.

label: protein kinase complex
Defs: A protein complex which is capable of protein kinase activity.

label: negative regulation of chromatin organization
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of chromatin organization.

label: ascending aorta morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the ascending aorta are generated and organized. The ascending aorta is the portion of the aorta in a two-pass circulatory system that lies between the heart and the arch of aorta. In a two-pass circulatory system blood passes twice through the heart to supply the body once.

label: normal fragility
Defs: A fragility which is relatively normal or average.

label: increased permeability
Defs: A permeability which is relatively high.

label: hypoglossal nerve development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the hypoglossal nerve over time, from its formation to the mature structure. This motor nerve innervates all the intrinsic and all but one of the extrinsic muscles of the tongue.

label: cardiovascular system elastic tissue
Defs: An elastic tissue that is part of a circulatory system [Automatically generated definition].

label: alpha mating type (yeast)
Defs: A S. cerevisiae mating type cells that secrete a pheromone that stimulates a haploids.

label: regulation of lipid binding
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of lipid binding.

label: head connective tissue
Defs: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a head [Automatically generated definition].

label: outflow tract of atrium
Defs: An outflow tract that is part of a cardiac atrium.

label: intrinsic component of plasma membrane
Defs: The component of the plasma membrane consisting of the gene products and protein complexes having either part of their peptide sequence embedded in the hydrophobic region of the membrane or some other covalently attached group such as a GPI anchor that is similarly embedded in the membrane.

label: mucosa of large intestine
Defs: A mucosa that is part of a large intestine [Automatically generated definition].

label: positive regulation of oxygen metabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of oxygen metabolic process.

label: atonicity
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lack elastic tension that facilitate response to stimuli.

label: negative regulation of retrograde trans-synaptic signaling by neuropeptide
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of retrograde trans-synaptic signaling by neuropeptide.

label: arachnose
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being characterized by fine, entangled hairs giving the appearance of cobweb.

label: proximo-distal subdivision of respiratory tract
Defs: An section of a respiratory tract.

label: mesonoto-metanotal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect thorax that joins the mesonotum and the metanotum.

label: signal transduction involved in regulation of gene expression
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of gene expression as a consequence of a process in which a signal is released and/or conveyed from one location to another.

label: vestigial
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being a remnant structure from earlier development or evolution.

label: regulation of molecular function
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a molecular function, an elemental biological activity occurring at the molecular level, such as catalysis or binding.

label: tufted pyramidal morphology
Defs: A pyramidal cell morphology that inheres in neurons which have a distinct tuft formation, distal from the soma.

label: plumose
Defs: A branched quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having many fine filaments or branches that give a feathery appearance: for example, resembling a feather.

label: oviduct
Defs: A tube or collection of tubes in an animal from the ovaries to the outside of the body.

label: neuronal action potential
Defs: An action potential that occurs in a neuron.

label: digestive system gland
Defs: Any gland that is part of the digestive system.

label: positive regulation of blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation.

label: striate-angular
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being marked by narrow lines, usually parallel, with at least one salient angle on the margin

label: brachiocephalic vasculature
Defs: The vasculature consisting of brachiocephalic arteries and veins.

label: tetrapyrrole binding
Defs: Binding to a tetrapyrrole, a compound containing four pyrrole nuclei variously substituted and linked to each other through carbons at the alpha position.

label: tracheobronchial smooth muscle cell
Defs: A smooth muscle cell that is part of the tracheobronchial tree.

label: compiling software
Defs: A planned process that converts human-written or curated software into a machine-executable or interpretable set of instructions.

label: vascular endothelial growth factor receptor
Defs: A protein with core architecture consisting of a signal sequence, followed by 7 Ig-like domains (Pfam:PF00047, Pfam:PF07679, or Pfam:PF07686), a transmembrane region, and a cytoplasmic Protein tyrosine kinase domain.

label: lateral mesoderm development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the lateral mesoderm over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: protein-containing complex localization
Defs: A localization process that acts on a protein complex; the complex is transported to, or maintained in, a specific location.

label: indole alkaloid metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving an indole alkaloid, an alkaloid containing an indole skeleton.

label: positive regulation of CD4 production
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of CD4.

label: negative regulation of aortic smooth muscle cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of aortic smooth muscle cell differentiation.

label: software module
Defs: A software module is software composed of a collection of software methods.

label: postsynapse
Defs: The part of a synapse that is part of the post-synaptic cell.

label: desaturated brown
Defs: A color consisting of brown hue and low saturation.

label: venous blood
Defs: A blood that is part of a vein.

label: positive regulation of neuron apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cell death of neurons by apoptotic process.

label: neurotransmitter receptor transport
Defs: The directed movement of neurotransmitter receptors.

label: bile duct
Defs: Any of the ducts that form the biliary tree, carrying bile from the liver to the small intestine.

label: respiratory system capillary endothelium
Defs: An endothelium of capillary that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

label: proteinogenic amino-acid side-chain group
Defs: A univalent organyl group obtained by cleaving the bond from C-2 to the side chain of a proteinogenic amino-acid.

label: epithelial cell of lung
Defs: An epithelial cell of the lung.

label: increased propagation velocity
Defs: A propagation velocity that is higher than normal.

label: regulation of apoptosis involved in tissue homeostasis
Defs: Any process that modulates the occurrence or rate of cell death by apoptosis that results in the maintenance of the steady-state number of cells within a tissue.

label: steroid hormone binding
Defs: Binding to a steroid hormone.

label: regulation of gonad development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of gonad development.

label: negative regulation of anion transport
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of anion transport.

label: forebrain neuron differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a neuron that will reside in the forebrain.

label: negative regulation of smooth muscle cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of smooth muscle cell differentiation.

label: leukocyte activation involved in immune response
Defs: A change in morphology and behavior of a leukocyte resulting from exposure to a specific antigen, mitogen, cytokine, cellular ligand, or soluble factor, leading to the initiation or perpetuation of an immune response.

label: scleral cell
Defs: A cell of the sclera of the eye.

label: cilium-dependent cell motility
Defs: Cell motility due to the motion of one or more eukaryotic cilia. A eukaryotic cilium is a specialized organelle that consists of a filiform extrusion of the cell surface. Each cilium is bounded by an extrusion of the cytoplasmic (plasma) membrane, and contains a regular longitudinal array of microtubules, anchored basally in a centriole.

label: acetylcholine transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of acetylcholine from one side of a membrane to the other. Acetylcholine is an acetic acid ester of the organic base choline and functions as a neurotransmitter, released at the synapses of parasympathetic nerves and at neuromuscular junctions.

label: exopolysaccharide
Defs: A biomacromolecule composed of carbohydrate residues which is secreted by a microorganism into the surrounding environment.

label: length measurement datum
Defs: A scalar measurement datum that is the result of measurement of length quality

label: aneuploid
Defs: A ploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing a non-integral multiple of the monoploid number, due to extra or missing chromosomes.

label: granulocyte activation
Defs: The change in morphology and behavior of a granulocyte resulting from exposure to a cytokine, chemokine, cellular ligand, or soluble factor.

label: polar solvent
Defs: A solvent that is composed of polar molecules. Polar solvents can dissolve ionic compounds or ionisable covalent compounds.

label: copyright section
Defs: A document part that describes  legal restrictions on making or distributing copies of the document

label: interlobular bile duct
Defs: The canals that carry bile in the liver between the intralobular ducts and the biliary ductules; interlobular bile ducts are part of the interlobular portal triad.

label: cellular macromolecule localization
Defs: Any process in which a macromolecule is transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location at the level of a cell. Localization at the cellular level encompasses movement within the cell, from within the cell to the cell surface, or from one location to another at the surface of a cell.

label: germ cell proliferation
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of germ cells, reproductive cells in multicellular organisms, resulting in the expansion of a cell population.

label: unpaired
Defs: The bearer of this quality has_part n=1 of the indicated entity type, where n is bilaterally paired for a comparable organism..

label: mucosa of stomach
Defs: The mucosal layer that lines the stomach.

label: lower jaw region
Defs: Subdivision of head that consists of the lower jaw skeletal elements plus associated soft tissue (skin, lips, muscle)[cjm].

label: decreased sensitivity toward
Defs: A sensitivity toward an external stimulus which is lower than normal/average.

label: arthropod sensillum
Defs: Sense organ embedded in the integument and consisting of one or a cluster of sensory neurons and associated sensory structures, support cells and glial cells forming a single organised unit with a largely bona-fide boundary.[FBbt].

label: cerebral vein
Defs: The cerebral veins are divisible into external and internal groups according to the outer surfaces or the inner parts of the hemispheres they drain into. The external veins are the superior cerebral veins, inferior cerebral veins, and middle cerebral vein. [WP,unvetted].

label: rusty
Defs: A texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being covered by iron oxide as a result of oxidation.

label: shattered
Defs: A broken quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being broken into multiple contiguous wholes.

label: sensory organ development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of sensory organs over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: positive regulation of norepinephrine secretion
Defs: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of norepinephrine.

label: regulation of secretion by cell
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of secretion by cell.

label: elemental molecular entity
Defs: A molecular entity all atoms of which have the same atomic number.

label: angular
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having at least one salient angle on the margin.

label: regulation of cell projection assembly
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of cell projection assembly.

label: undamaged
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of not being harmed or injured or spoiled.

label: nuclear complex of neuraxis
Defs: Gray matter of the central nervous system which is a collection of clustered nuclei.

label: proximal-distal subdivision of colon
Defs: A section dividing a colon along a proximal-distal axis.

label: keratocyte
Defs: A keratocyte is a specialized fibroblastresiding in the cornea stroma that has a flattened, dendritic cell located between the lamellae with a large flattened nucleus and lengthy processes which communicate with neighboring cells. Thiscorneallayer, representing about 85-90% of corneal thickness, is built up from highly regular collagenous lamellae and extracellular matrix components. Keratocytes play the major role in keeping it transparent, healing its wounds, and synthesizing its components. This cell type secretes collagen I, V, VI, and keratin sulfate.

label: cranial ganglion morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structure of a cranial ganglion is generated and organized.

label: dopaminergic agent
Defs: A drug used for its effects on dopamine receptors, on the life cycle of dopamine, or on the survival of dopaminergic neurons.

label: regulation of gastro-intestinal system smooth muscle contraction
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of gastro-intestinal system smooth muscle contraction.

label: pericardial fluid
Defs: Transudate contained in the pericardial cavity.[FMA].

label: unlocalised
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s not being confined or restricted to a particular location.

label: negative regulation of iron ion transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of an iron transmembrane transporter activity.

label: regulation of programmed cell death
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of programmed cell death, cell death resulting from activation of endogenous cellular processes.

label: positive regulation of gliogenesis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of gliogenesis, the formation of mature glia.

label: cuticle of tarsomere
Defs: The cuticle of the mere that is part of the tarsus.

label: negative regulation of nucleobase-containing compound metabolic process
Defs: Any cellular process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving nucleobases, nucleosides, nucleotides and nucleic acids.

label: cytoplasmic vesicle membrane
Defs: The lipid bilayer surrounding a cytoplasmic vesicle.

label: positive regulation of T cell cytokine production
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of T cell cytokine production.

label: contractile
Defs: A contractility quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability of contracting or being contracted.

label: scutellar shield
Defs: The region of the cuticle on the posterior region of the mesoscutellum.

label: negative regulation of monocyte activation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of monocyte activation.

label: respiratory system mucosa
Defs: The mucous membrane lining the respiratory tract.

label: positive regulation of amino acid transport
Defs: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of amino acids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: intracellular non-membrane-bounded organelle
Defs: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function, not bounded by a lipid bilayer membrane and occurring within the cell. Includes ribosomes, the cytoskeleton and chromosomes.

label: regulation of acetylcholine secretion, neurotransmission
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of acetylcholine.

label: partially dislocated
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being slightly out of its usual or proper place, or position.

label: regulation of digestive system process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a digestive system process, a physical, chemical, or biochemical process carried out by living organisms to break down ingested nutrients into components that may be easily absorbed and directed into metabolism.

label: decreased diameter
Defs: A diameter which is relatively small.

label: amide transport
Defs: The directed movement of an amide, any compound containing one, two, or three acyl groups attached to a nitrogen atom, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: insect anus
Defs: The orifice on the postabdomen at the posterior margin of the digestive tract, connected to the epiproct and paraprocti.

label: superficial vein
Defs: Any of the veins carrying deoxygenated blood from the subcutaneous tissue layers.

label: muscular septum morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the muscular septum is generated and organized. The muscular septum is the lower part of the ventricular septum.

label: positive regulation of protein tyrosine kinase activity
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of protein tyrosine kinase activity.

label: prominin
Defs: A protein with core architecture consisting of one Prominin (Pfam:PF05478) domain. The prominins are an emerging family of proteins that, among the multispan membrane proteins, display a novel topology. Mouse and human prominin and prominin-like 1 are predicted to contain five membrane spanning domains, with an N-terminal domain exposed to the extracellular space followed by four, alternating small cytoplasmic and large extracellular, loops and a cytoplasmic C-terminal domain.

label: quality of a substance
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its constitution.

label: regulation of biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of substances.

label: lung elastic tissue
Defs: Elastic tissue that is part of a lung [Automatically generated definition].

label: loud
Defs: A sound amplitude which is relatively high.

label: positive regulation of lipid binding
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of lipid binding.

label: negative regulation of adipose tissue development
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of adipose tissue development.

label: pharyngeal arch artery
Defs: One of a series of paired embryological vascular structures formed within a pharyngeal arch; in the adult, some of these vessels give rise to the great vessels[MP].

label: normal solubility
Defs: A solubility which is relatively normal or average

label: articulation
Defs: Anatomical cluster that connects two or more adjacent skeletal elements or hardened body parts.

label: negative regulation of ossification
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of ossification, the formation of bone or of a bony substance or the conversion of fibrous tissue or of cartilage into bone or a bony substance.

label: leukocyte homeostasis
Defs: The process of regulating the proliferation and elimination of cells of the immune system such that the total number of cells of a particular cell type within a whole or part of an organism is stable over time in the absence of an outside stimulus.

label: brainstem nucleus
Defs: A nucleus of brain that is part of a brainstem.

label: CD34-positive, CD38-positive common myeloid progenitor
Defs: A common myeloid progenitor that is CD34-positive, CD38-positive, IL3ra-low, CD10-negative, CD7-negative, CD45RA-negative, and IL-5Ralpha-negative.

label: cell differentiation in spinal cord
Defs: The process in which relatively unspecialized cells acquire specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize the cells of the spinal cord. Differentiation includes the processes involved in commitment of a cell to a specific fate.

label: heart shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a sinus or rounded lobe at the base.

label: negative regulation of intracellular transport
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of substances within cells.

label: positive regulation of colon smooth muscle contraction
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of colon smooth muscle contraction.

label: cuticular sulcus
Defs: The cuticular depression (concavity on cuticle surface) that corresponds with a cuticular ridge (an elongate cuticular invagination).

label: embryo
Defs: Anatomical entity that comprises the organism in the early stages of growth and differentiation that are characterized by cleavage, the laying down of fundamental tissues, and the formation of primitive organs and organ systems. For example, for mammals, the process would begin with zygote formation and end with birth. For insects, the process would begin at zygote formation and end with larval hatching. For plant zygotic embryos, this would be from zygote formation to the end of seed dormancy. For plant vegetative embryos, this would be from the initial determination of the cell or group of cells to form an embryo until the point when the embryo becomes independent of the parent plant.

label: sigmoid
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s consisting of two curves, in opposite directions. S-shaped.

label: presynapse organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a presynapse.

label: Kit-negative, Ly-76 high orthochromatophilic erythroblasts
Defs: An orthochromatophilic erythroblast that is ter119-high, CD71-low, and Kit-negative.

label: posterior cranial transverse groove
Defs: The cuticular groove of the head capsule that runs parallel to the left-right axis, adjacent to the vertex and the occiput

label: His-Purkinje system
Defs: The His-Purkinje system receives signals from the AV node and is composed of the fibers that regulate cardiac muscle contraction in the ventricles.

label: negative regulation of branching morphogenesis of a nerve
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of branching morphogenesis of a nerve.

label: negative regulation of cell fate commitment
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency or rate of cell fate commitment. Cell fate commitment is the commitment of cells to specific cell fates and their capacity to differentiate into particular kinds of cells. Positional information is established through protein signals that emanate from a localized source within a cell (the initial one-cell zygote) or within a developmental field.

label: pancreas morphogenesis
Defs: Morphogenesis of the pancreas. Morphogenesis is the process in which anatomical structures are generated and organized.

label: pancreas mesenchyme
Defs: The embryonic connective tissue made up of loosely aggregated mesenchymal cells, supported by interlaminar jelly, that gives rise to the developing pancreas.

label: phototoxic
Defs: A photosensitivity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to being susceptible to damage by light.

label: positive regulation of keratinocyte proliferation
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of keratinocyte proliferation. Keratinocyte proliferation is the multiplication or reproduction of keratinocytes, resulting in the expansion of a cell population.

label: cuticle of mid leg
Defs: The cuticle of the paired appendage of the mesothorax that is posterior to the cuticle of a fore leg, anterior to the cuticle of a hind leg, and composed of cuticle of mesocoxa, cuticle of mesotrochanter, cuticle of mesofemur, cuticle of mesotibia, cuticle of mesotarsus, and cuticle of mesopretarsus.

label: insulin receptor complex
Defs: A disulfide-bonded, heterotetrameric receptor complex. The alpha chains are entirely extracellular, while each beta chain has one transmembrane domain. The ligand binds to the alpha subunit extracellular domain and the kinase is associated with the beta subunit intracellular domain.

label: compound eye
Defs: The sense organ of the insect head that is covered by the eye cuticle.

label: terminal bronchiole epithelium
Defs: An epithelium that lines a terminal bronchiole.

label: ipsilateral to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being on the same side in relation to another structure.

label: regulation of insulin secretion involved in cellular response to glucose stimulus
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of insulin that contributes to the response of a cell to glucose.

label: negative regulation of epithelial cell proliferation involved in lung morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of epithelial cell proliferation involved in lung morphogenesis.

label: superficial cervical artery
Defs: It ascends beneath the anterior margin of the trapezius, distributing branches to it, and to the neighboring muscles and lymph glands in the neck, and anastomosing with the superficial branch of the descending branch of the occipital artery.

label: muscle layer of intestine
Defs: A muscle layer that is part of an intestine.

label: extrahepatic bile duct
Defs: Passages external to the liver for the conveyance of bile. These include the common bile duct and the common hepatic duct.

label: protein-containing complex
Defs: A stable assembly of two or more macromolecules, i.e. proteins, nucleic acids, carbohydrates or lipids, in which at least one component is a protein and the constituent parts function together.

label: mislocalised anteriorly
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being positioned towards the front of an organism.

label: appendicular skeletal system
Defs: Subdivision of the skeletal system which consists of the appendicular skeleton plus associated joints.

label: base ontology module
Defs: An ontology module that comprises only of asserted axioms local to the ontology, excludes import directives, and excludes axioms or declarations from external ontologies.

label: vaporizability
Defs: A quality which inheres in a substance by virtue of the ease with which the substance can be changed into a gaseous state.

label: negative regulation of cellular component organization
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cell structures, including the plasma membrane and any external encapsulating structures such as the cell wall and cell envelope.

label: layer of smooth muscle tissue
Defs: Any organ component layer that consists of smooth muscle tissue.

label: steroid hormone secretion
Defs: The regulated release of any steroid that acts as a hormone into the circulatory system.

label: neuropeptide receptor activity
Defs: Combining with a neuropeptide to initiate a change in cell activity.

label: normal efficiency
Defs: An efficiency which is relatively normal or average.

label: central nervous system formation
Defs: The process that gives rise to the central nervous system. This process pertains to the initial formation of a structure from unspecified parts. The central nervous system is the core nervous system that serves an integrating and coordinating function. In vertebrates it consists of the brain, spinal cord and spinal nerves. In those invertebrates with a central nervous system it typically consists of a brain, cerebral ganglia and a nerve cord.

label: semi-deciduous(plant)
Defs: A quality inhering in a plant by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to being between evergeen and deciduous.

label: algorithm
Defs: A plan specification which describes the inputs and output of mathematical functions as well as workflow of execution for achieving an predefined objective. Algorithms are realized usually by means of implementation as computer programs for execution by automata.

label: acyl binding
Defs: Binding to an acyl group, any group formally derived by removal of the hydroxyl group from the acid function of a carboxylic acid.

label: smooth muscle cell migration
Defs: The orderly movement of a smooth muscle cell from one site to another, often during the development of a multicellular organism.

label: primary amino compound biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of primary amino compound.

label: mesoderm blood island
Defs: A blood island that is part of a mesoderm.

label: positive regulation of secretion by cell
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of secretion by cell.

label: coronary capillary
Defs: A capillary that is part of the coronary system.

label: myoblast maturation
Defs: A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for a myoblast to attain its fully functional state. A myoblast is a mononucleate cell type that, by fusion with other myoblasts, gives rise to the myotubes that eventually develop into skeletal muscle fibers.

label: submucosal gland
Defs: Gland of the lamina epithelialis mucosae which perforate the lamina muscularis, with their adenomeres located in the submucosal connective tissue.

label: organ
Defs: Anatomical structure that performs a specific function or group of functions [WP].

label: regulation of cerebral blood circulation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cerebral blood circulation.

label: lung epithelium development
Defs: The biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of the lung epithelium from an initial condition to its mature state. This process begins with the formation of lung epithelium and ends with the mature structure. The lung epithelium is the specialized epithelium that lines the inside of the lung.

label: interstitial cell of Cajal differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of an interstitial cell of Cajal. An interstitial cell of Cajal is an intestinal neuroepithelial cell that serves as a pacemaker to trigger gut contraction.

label: increased accumulation
Defs: An increased number of physical objects that are accumulated within another physical object usually as a result of a failure to break down or remove objects in a timely manner.

label: T Martinotti morphology
Defs: A Martinotti cell morphology that inheres in neurons which have axons that form a horizontal ramification, making it T-shaped.

label: erythroid progenitor cell
Defs: A progenitor cell committed to the erythroid lineage.

label: ocular surface region
Defs: The integrated unit (of the eye) that consists of the conjunctiva, the corneal surface, and the ocular mucosal adnexa including the lid margins and the meibomian gland openings, the lacrimal glands and the lacrimal drainage system, all which are critical to maintain ocular surface integrity and provide protection from external antigens and pathogenic microorganisms.

label: procoxal-protrochanteral conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the fore leg joining the distal margin of a procoxa and the proximal margin of a protrochanter.

label: T-shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being shaped in the form of the letter T.

label: protein localization to extracellular region
Defs: Any process in which a protein is transported from one specific location in the extracellular region to another, or maintained in a specific extracellular location.

label: leukocyte differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized hemopoietic precursor cell acquires the specialized features of a leukocyte. A leukocyte is an achromatic cell of the myeloid or lymphoid lineages capable of ameboid movement, found in blood or other tissue.

label: somite boundary epithelium
Defs: Epithelium located in the intersomitic region.

label: cuticle of femur
Defs: The cuticle of the segment of a leg attached to the distal margin of the trochanter by the trochantero-femoral conjunctiva and to the proximal margin of the tibia by the femoro-tibial conjunctiva.

label: paramero-aedeagal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the postabdomen that joins the parameres and the aedeagus.

label: oral-aboral axis
Defs: An axis that extends from the oral opening to the furthest point in an organism that is directly opposite.

label: paraxial mesoderm formation
Defs: The process that gives rise to the paraxial mesoderm. This process pertains to the initial formation of the structure from unspecified parts.

label: glossopharyngeal nerve formation
Defs: The process that gives rise to the glossopharyngeal nerve. This process pertains to the initial formation of a structure from unspecified parts. Various sensory and motor branches of the glossopharyngeal nerve supply nerve connections to the pharynx and back of the tongue. The branchial motor component contains motor fibers that innervate muscles that elevate the pharynx and larynx, and the tympanic branch supplies parasympathetic fibers to the otic ganglion.

label: physical object quality
Defs: A quality which inheres in a continuant.

label: tendon formation
Defs: The process that gives rise to a tendon. This process pertains to the initial formation of a tendon from unspecified parts.

label: continuant fiat boundary
Defs: b is a continuant fiat boundary = Def. b is an immaterial entity that is of zero, one or two dimensions and does not include a spatial region as part. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [029-001])

label: medulla oblongata sulcus limitans
Defs: A sulcus limitans of neural tube that is part of a future medulla oblongata.

label: facial bone
Defs: A bone that is part of a facial skeleton [Automatically generated definition].

label: positive regulation of signaling receptor activity
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of signaling receptor activity.

label: papillary
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling small nipple like projection.

label: gas homeostasis
Defs: A homeostatic process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of a gas within an organism or cell.

label: trilobed
Defs: A lobed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being divided into or having three lobes.

label: glutamatergic synapse
Defs: A synapse that uses glutamate as a neurotransmitter.

label: axial mesoderm morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the axial mesoderm are generated and organized.

label: gastrula
Defs: Organism at the gastrula stage.

label: organelle localization
Defs: Any process in which an organelle is transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location.

label: tripartite
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being divided into three branches.

label: negative regulation of ion transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Any process that stops or reduces the activity of an ion transporter.

label: descending thoracic aorta
Defs: The part of the aorta that extends from the arch of the aorta to the diaphragm, and from which arises numerous branches that supply oxygenated blood to the chest cage and the organs within the chest.

label: curvature
Defs: A surface shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting a degree of bending.

label: negative regulation of immune response
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the immune response, the immunological reaction of an organism to an immunogenic stimulus.

label: preference
Defs: A discrimination quality in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s liking a perceived stimulus.

label: positive regulation of chromosome organization
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of chromosome organization.

label: myeloid leukocyte mediated immunity
Defs: Any process involved in the carrying out of an immune response by a myeloid leukocyte.

label: thoracic cavity blood vessel
Defs: A blood vessel that is part of a thoracic cavity [Automatically generated definition].

label: acetylcholine receptor activity
Defs: Combining with an acetylcholine receptor ligand and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity.

label: import into cell
Defs: The directed movement of some substance from outside of a cell into a cell. This may occur via transport across the plasma membrane or via endocytosis.

label: transitional myocyte of interventricular septum
Defs: A transitional myocyte that is part of the interventricular septum.

label: organism substance
Defs: Material anatomical entity in a gaseous, liquid, semisolid or solid state; produced by anatomical structures or derived from inhaled and ingested substances that have been modified by anatomical structures as they pass through the body.

label: mandibular process mesenchyme from head mesenchyme
Defs: Mesenchyme that develops_from a head mesenchyme from mesoderm and is part of a mandibular process mesenchyme.

label: nuclear envelope organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the nuclear envelope.

label: excitatory synapse assembly
Defs: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form an excitatory synapse.

label: acetate ester transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of an acetate ester from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: submucosa of common hepatic duct
Defs: A submucosa that is part of a common hepatic duct [Automatically generated definition].

label: negative regulation of gastric mucosal blood circulation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of gastric mucosal blood circulation.

label: regulation of apical ectodermal ridge formation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of apical ectodermal ridge formation.

label: superior olivary complex
Defs: A collection of brainstem nuclei that functions in multiple aspects of hearing and is an important component of the ascending and descending auditory pathways of the auditory system.

label: negative regulation of muscle cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of muscle cell differentiation.

label: localized
Defs: A spatial pattern quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being confined or restricted to a particular location.

label: application
Defs: Intended use of the molecular entity or part thereof by humans.

label: leukosialin (mouse)
Defs: A leukosialin that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: compression-fractured
Defs: A fractured quality that is caused by a loss of bone mass (osteoporosis) that occurs as part of aging.

label: locus ceruleus morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structure of the locus ceruleus is generated and organized. In mice, the locus ceruleus is a dense cluster of neurons within the dorsorostral pons. This nucleus is the major location of neurons that release norepinephrine throughout the brain, and is responsible for physiological responses to stress and panic.

label: keratinocyte proliferation
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of keratinocytes, resulting in the expansion of a cell population. Keratinocytes are epidermal cells which synthesize keratin and undergo a characteristic change as they move upward from the basal layers of the epidermis to the cornified (horny) layer of the skin.

label: light yellow brown
Defs: A color consisting of yellow and brown hue and high brightness.

label: transmembrane transporter complex
Defs: A transmembrane protein complex which enables the transfer of a substance from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: desaturated purple
Defs: A color consisting of purple color and low saturation.

label: formation of translation initiation ternary complex
Defs: Formation of a complex between aminoacylated initiator methionine tRNA, GTP, and initiation factor 2 (either eIF2 in eukaryotes, or IF2 in prokaryotes). In prokaryotes, fMet-tRNA (initiator) is used rather than Met-tRNA (initiator).

label: anatomical gradient
Defs: Material anatomical entity defined by change in the value of some quantity per unit of distance across some spatial axis.

label: lactoferrin transport
Defs: The directed movement of lactoferrin into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: iris smooth muscle
Defs: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a iris [Automatically generated definition].

label: hepatic vein
Defs: Vein that carries blood away from the liver[ZFA].

label: regulation of anion transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of anions, atoms or small molecules with a net negative charge into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: multicellular organismal process
Defs: Any biological process, occurring at the level of a multicellular organism, pertinent to its function.

label: catecholamine
Defs: 4-(2-Aminoethyl)pyrocatechol [4-(2-aminoethyl)benzene-1,2-diol] and derivatives formed by substitution.

label: transparent eye structure
Defs: A transparent structure that is part of a visual sense organ, the function of which is to direct or focus light onto a photoreceptor array.

label: cardiac left ventricle formation
Defs: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of a left cardiac ventricle from unspecified parts.

label: regulation of macrophage differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of macrophage differentiation.

label: power
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s rate of doing work.

label: dorsal postabdomen
Defs: Dorsal part of postabdomen

label: invariant
Defs: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking or not exhibiting variation.

label: regulation of supramolecular fiber organization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of supramolecular fiber organization.

label: coxal-trochanteral conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the leg joining the distal margin of a coxa and the proximal margin of a femur.

label: regulation of collagen catabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of collagen catabolism. Collagen catabolism is the proteolytic chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of collagen in the extracellular matrix.

label: Purkinje myocyte of atrioventricular node
Defs: A Purkinje myocyte that is part of the atrioventricular node.

label: secretory cell
Defs: A cell that specializes in controlled release of one or more substances.

label: fourth maxillar palpopalpal muscle
Defs: The insect cranio-maxillar muscle that is attached to the fourth maxillar palpomere and  the fifth maxillar palpomere.

label: hepaticobiliary system development
Defs: The progression of the hepaticobiliary system over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The hepaticobiliary system is responsible for metabolic and catabolic processing of small molecules absorbed from the blood or gut, hormones and serum proteins, detoxification, storage of glycogen, triglycerides, metals and lipid soluble vitamins and excretion of bile. Included are the synthesis of albumin, blood coagulation factors, complement, and specific binding proteins.

label: linear tetrapyrrole anion
Defs: An organic anion arising from deprotonation of a acyclic tetrapyrrole compound.

label: dissolved
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s passing into solution.

label: regulation of tetrapyrrole biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of tetrapyrrole biosynthetic process.

label: negative regulation of glutamate receptor signaling pathway
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of glutamate receptor signaling pathway.

label: dermal bone morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which bone which forms superficially in the organism are generated and organized.

label: cardiotonic drug
Defs: A drug that has a strengthening effect on the heart or that can increase cardiac output.

label: symphysis
Defs: Cartilaginous joint in which the articulating bones or cartilages are connected by fibrocartilage. Examples: pubic symphysis, intervertebral symphysis, manubriosternal joint.[FMA].

label: prosternal process
Defs: The part of the prosternum that is medial to the procoxae.

label: glutamate(1-)
Defs: An alpha-amino-acid anion that is the conjugate base of glutamic acid, having anionic carboxy groups and a cationic amino group

label: elevation
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s vertical distance of a point above or below a reference surface.

label: mesothelial cell of pleura
Defs: A mesothelial cell that is part of the pleura.

label: hyperplastic
Defs: A increased size quality inhering in an organ or tissue by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting increased number of cells.

label: polyatomic anion
Defs: An anion consisting of more than one atom.

label: 2nd arch endoderm
Defs: An endoderm that is part of a pharyngeal arch 2.

label: cell growth involved in cardiac muscle cell development
Defs: The growth of a cardiac muscle cell, where growth contributes to the progression of the cell over time from its initial formation to its mature state.

label: cardiac blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a blood vessel endothelial cell of the heart. Blood vessel endothelial cells are thin flattened cells that line the inside surfaces of blood vessels.

label: carpel-like
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s similarity to the appearance of a carpel.

label: viscid
Defs: A coating quality which is sticky or clammy.

label: regulation of lipid biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of lipids.

label: width
Defs: A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance from one side of an object to another side which is opposite.

label: gastrointestinal sphincter
Defs: A sphincter muscle that is part of the gastrointestinal system.

label: actin cytoskeleton
Defs: The part of the cytoskeleton (the internal framework of a cell) composed of actin and associated proteins. Includes actin cytoskeleton-associated complexes.

label: cell leading edge
Defs: The area of a motile cell closest to the direction of movement.

label: afferent neuron
Defs: A neuron which conveys sensory information centrally from the periphery.

label: skeleton of pectoral complex
Defs: The collection of all skeletal elements in a pectoral complex - i.e. the combination of free limb or fin plus pectoral girdle.

label: aromatic compound
Defs: A cyclically conjugated molecular entity with a stability (due to delocalization) significantly greater than that of a hypothetical localized structure (e.g. Kekule structure) is said to possess aromatic character.

label: transition metal ion transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of transition metal ions from one side of a membrane to the other. A transition metal is an element whose atom has an incomplete d-subshell of extranuclear electrons, or which gives rise to a cation or cations with an incomplete d-subshell. Transition metals often have more than one valency state. Biologically relevant transition metals include vanadium, manganese, iron, copper, cobalt, nickel, molybdenum and silver.

label: monocarboxylic acid catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of monocarboxylic acids, any organic acid containing one carboxyl (-COOH) group.

label: abdominal tergite VI
Defs: Is the abdominal tergite of the preabdomen that is attached to the posterior margin of the abdominal tergite V by the abdominal tergite V-abdominal tergite VI conjunctiva and to the anterior margin of the abdominal tergite VII by the abdominal tergite VI-abdominal tergite VII conjunctiva.

label: placenta labyrinth
Defs: The placental layers where embryonic blood vessels are surrounded by trophoblast cells and maternal blood.

label: dorsal orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed dorsally.

label: stem cell division
Defs: The self-renewing division of a stem cell. A stem cell is an undifferentiated cell, in the embryo or adult, that can undergo unlimited division and give rise to one or several different cell types.

label: dicarboxylic acid
Defs: Any carboxylic acid containing two carboxy groups.

label: paired limb/fin skeleton
Defs: The collection of all skeletal elements in an individual limb or fin.

label: neural tube
Defs: In the developing vertebrate, the neural tube is the embryo\'s precursor to the central nervous system, which comprises the brain and spinal cord. The neural groove gradually deepens as the neural folds become elevated, and ultimately the folds meet and coalesce in the middle line and convert the groove into a closed tube, the neural tube or neural canal (which strictly speaking is the center of the neural tube), the ectodermal wall of which forms the rudiment of the nervous system. [WP,unvetted].

label: positive regulation of transmission of nerve impulse
Defs: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of transmission of a nerve impulse, the sequential electrochemical polarization and depolarization that travels across the membrane of a neuron in response to stimulation.

label: female pseudohermaphrodite
Defs: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population by virtue of having internal reproductive organs of female and external sexual characteristics of male.

label: negative regulation of protein depolymerization
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein depolymerization.

label: positive regulation of mononuclear cell migration
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of mononuclear cell migration. Mononuclear cell migration is the movement of a mononuclear cell within or between different tissues and organs of the body.

label: regulation of myelination
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the formation of a myelin sheath around nerve axons.

label: myeloid dendritic cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a monocyte acquires the specialized features of a dendritic cell, an immunocompetent cell of the lymphoid and hemopoietic systems and skin.

label: glioblast (sensu Vertebrata)
Defs: An early neural cell developing from the early ependymal cell of the neural tube.

label: negative regulation of compound eye retinal cell programmed cell death
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of programmed cell death that occurs in the compound eye retina.

label: orbital region
Defs: The subdivision of the face that includes the eye (eyeball plus adnexa such as eyelids) and the orbit of the skull and associated parts of the face such as the eyebrows, if present.

label: catecholamine uptake
Defs: The directed movement of catecholamine into a cell.

label: pear shaped
Defs: Having the shape of a pear; tapering near the top and bulging toward the base or bottom. From thefreedictionary.com

label: smooth muscle cell
Defs: A non-striated, elongated, spindle-shaped cell found lining the digestive tract, uterus, and blood vessels. They develop from specialized myoblasts (smooth muscle myoblast).

label: profurca-mesonotal muscle
Defs: The dorsoventral thoracic muscle that extends between the profurca and the mesonotum.

label: mouth mucosa
Defs: A mucous membrane that lines the mouth.

label: separating
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being in a position that produces a separation in, or acting to separate, another entity.

label: cuticle of procoxa
Defs: The cuticle of the segment of the fore leg that is attached to the latero-ventral region of the prothorax by the basal procoxal conjunctiva and to the protrochanter by the procoxal-protrochanteral conjunctiva.

label: cilium movement involved in cell motility
Defs: Movement of cilia mediated by motor proteins that contributes to the movement of a cell.

label: pectoral complex
Defs: Appendage girdle complex that when present, encompasses the pectoral appendicular skeleton and the pectoral girdle.

label: ventral spinal cord development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the ventral region of the spinal cord over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The neurons of the ventral region of the mature spinal cord participate in motor output.

label: ventral horn of spinal cord
Defs: The ventral grey column of the spinal cord[MP]. The neurons of the ventral region of the mature spinal cord participate in motor output[GO].

label: ventral cranio-mandibular articulation
Defs: The articular surface of the head capsule at the anterior region of the postgena

label: negative regulation of endothelial cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the rate or extent of endothelial cell proliferation.

label: skin of body
Defs: The organ covering the body that consists of the dermis and epidermis.

label: subcylindrical
Defs: A cylindrical shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being imperfectly cylindrical or approximately cylindrical.

label: positive regulation of forebrain neuron differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of forebrain neuron differentiation.

label: mesenchymal stem cell of adipose tissue
Defs: A mesenchymal stem cell of adipose tissue.

label: blastula stage
Defs: An early stage of embryonic development in animals. It is produced by cleavage of a fertilized ovum and consists of a spherical layer of around 128 cells surrounding a central fluid-filled cavity called the blastocoel. The blastula follows the morula and precedes the gastrula in the developmental sequence.

label: post-Golgi vesicle-mediated transport
Defs: The directed movement of substances from the Golgi to other parts of the cell, including organelles and the plasma membrane, mediated by small transport vesicles.

label: transmembrane receptor protein tyrosine kinase inhibitor activity
Defs: Binds to and stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a transmembrane receptor protein tyrosine kinase.

label: proximal surface
Defs: Anatomical surface that is located on the proximal side of the body or body part.

label: cellular homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state at the level of the cell.

label: glutinous
Defs: An amylose composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having negligible or no amylose content.

label: presynapse assembly
Defs: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a presynapse.

label: myeloid lineage restricted progenitor cell
Defs: A progenitor cell restricted to the myeloid lineage.

label: regionalization
Defs: The pattern specification process that results in the subdivision of an axis or axes in space to define an area or volume in which specific patterns of cell differentiation will take place or in which cells interpret a specific environment.

label: monosaccharide biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of monosaccharides, polyhydric alcohols containing either an aldehyde or a keto group and between three to ten or more carbon atoms.

label: positive regulation of ossification
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of ossification, the formation of bone or of a bony substance or the conversion of fibrous tissue or of cartilage into bone or a bony substance.

label: phosphate ion transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of phosphate (PO4 3-) ions from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: regulation of skeletal muscle fiber development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of skeletal muscle fiber development. Muscle fibers are formed by the maturation of myotubes. They can be classed as slow, intermediate/fast or fast.

label: nerve of thoracic segment

label: cuticle of scapus

label: phosphoric acids

label: ruffled
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting disturbance of its smoothness or regularity.

label: ivory

label: right uterine tube
Defs: A fallopian tube that is part of a right side of organism [Automatically generated definition].

label: defense response

label: decreased stability

label: rough

label: negative regulation of cell-cell adhesion
