label: regulation of keratinocyte apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of keratinocyte apoptotic process.

label: large intestine
Defs: A subdivision of the digestive tract that connects the small intestine to the cloaca or anus. Lacks or has few villi[Kardong].

label: ligamentous
Defs: Having the nature or characteristic of, a ligament; composed of the tissue proper to ligaments.

label: regulation of androgen secretion
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of androgen secretion.

label: regulation of sclerotome development
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the progression of the sclerotome over time, from its initial formation to the mature structure. The sclerotome is the portion of the somite that will give rise to a vertebra.

label: regulation of mesoderm formation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mesoderm formation.

label: lamina propria of mucosa of colon
Defs: A lamina propria that is part of a colonic mucosa.

label: positive regulation of striated muscle cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that increases the rate or extent of striated muscle cell apoptotic process, a form of programmed cell death induced by external or internal signals that trigger the activity of proteolytic caspases whose actions dismantle a striated muscle cell and result in its death.

label: death stage
Defs: End of the life of an organism.

label: positive regulation of biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of substances.

label: decreased contractility
Defs: A contractility which is relatively low.

label: regulation of neurogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of neurogenesis, the generation of cells in the nervous system.

label: white
Defs: An achromatic color of maximum brightness; the color of objects that reflect nearly all light of all visible wavelengths.

label: future tongue
Defs: A compound organ that has the potential to develop into a tongue.

label: dataset creating
Defs: A planned process that has a data set as its specified output.

label: migratory trunk neural crest cell
Defs: Cell that is part of the migratory trunk neural crest population. Migratory trunk neural crest cells develop from premigratory trunk neural crest cells and have undergone epithelial to mesenchymal transition and delamination.

label: institution list
Defs: A part of a document that has parts that are institution identifications associated with the authors of the document

label: regulation of vacuolar transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of vacuolar transport.

label: negative regulation of cardiac muscle contraction
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle contraction.

label: tendon development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a tendon over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A tendon is a fibrous, strong, connective tissue that connects muscle to bone or integument and is capable of withstanding tension. Tendons and muscles work together to exert a pulling force.

label: granulocyte chemotaxis
Defs: The movement of a granulocyte in response to an external stimulus.

label: regulation of pigment cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of pigmented cell differentiation.

label: cavitated compound organ
Defs: Compound organ that contains one or more macroscopic anatomical spaces.

label: iris epithelium
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a iris [Automatically generated definition].

label: regulation of intracellular lipid transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of lipids within cells.

label: regulation of hematopoietic progenitor cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of hematopoietic progenitor cell differentiation.

label: totipotent stem cell
Defs: A stem cell from which all cells of the body can form.

label: concavity
Defs: Surface shape that refers to the inward or outward curvature of the surface.

label: ectodermal digestive tract development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the ectodermal digestive tract over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The ectodermal digestive tract includes those portions that are derived from ectoderm.

label: vasculature of integument
Defs: The part of the circulatory system that lies within the subcutaneous tissue layers close to the surface of the skin.

label: hydrophilic
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to having a strong affinity for water; tending to dissolve in, mix with, or be wetted by water.

label: right ovary
Defs: An ovary that is part of a right side of organism [Automatically generated definition].

label: neural cell adhesion molecule 1 (mouse)
Defs: A neural cell adhesion molecule 1 that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: enzyme-linked receptor protein signaling pathway
Defs: The series of molecular signals initiated by an extracellular ligand binding to a receptor on the surface of the target cell, where the receptor possesses catalytic activity or is closely associated with an enzyme such as a protein kinase, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

label: decreased width and length
Defs: A width and length quality which is relatively small, where both width and length are decreased.

label: negative regulation of microtubule nucleation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of microtubule nucleation.

label: multicellular organismal homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state at the level of the multicellular organism.

label: gastrointestinal system smooth muscle
Defs: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a digestive system [Automatically generated definition].

label: regulation of oligodendrocyte apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of oligodendrocyte apoptotic process.

label: positive regulation of skeletal muscle cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of skeletal muscle cell differentiation.

label: color
Defs: A composite chromatic quality composed of hue, saturation and intensity parts.

label: blood microvessel
Defs: Any of the smallest blood vessels where blood circulates within organ tissues. Microvessels include terminal arterioles, metarterioles, capillaries, and venules (but exclude lymphatic capillaries). Arterioles carry oxygenated blood to the capillaries, and blood flows out of the capillaries through venules into veins.

label: negative regulation of epithelial tube formation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of epithelial tube formation.

label: positive regulation of cellular component biogenesis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cellular component biogenesis, a process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of a cellular component.

label: inactive
Defs: A quality of a physical object that is currently realizing none of its functions.

label: negative regulation of growth
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the rate or extent of growth, the increase in size or mass of all or part of an organism.

label: Lewis base
Defs: A molecular entity able to provide a pair of electrons and thus capable of forming a covalent bond with an electron-pair acceptor (Lewis acid), thereby producing a Lewis adduct.

label: protein metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving a protein. Includes protein modification.

label: mesodermal cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized features of a mesoderm cell.

label: G protein-coupled serotonin receptor complex
Defs: A protein complex that is capable of G protein-coupled serotonin receptor activity.

label: mislocalized adaxially
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being positioned towards the axis of an organism.

label: circular
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being such that every part of the surface or the circumference is equidistant from the center.

label: multicellular ectodermal gland
Defs: The ectodermal gland that is composed of multiple cells.

label: regulation of vesicle transport along microtubule
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of vesicle transport along microtubule.

label: positive regulation of organ growth
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of growth of an organ of an organism.

label: regulation of dendritic cell cytokine production
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of dendritic cell cytokine production.

label: submentum
Defs: The sclerite of the labium that is anteriorly attached to the mentum by the submental-mental conjunctiva.

label: reflex angle to
Defs: An angular placement quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s placement at an angle that is greater than 180 degrees but less than 360 degrees to another entity.

label: katepimeron
Defs: The region of cuticle on the ventral region of the epimeron.

label: epidermis morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the epidermis are generated and organized. The epidermis is the outer epithelial layer of an animal, it may be a single layer that produces an extracellular material (e.g. the cuticle of arthropods) or a complex stratified squamous epithelium, as in the case of many vertebrate species.

label: muscle structure development
Defs: The progression of a muscle structure over time, from its formation to its mature state. Muscle structures are contractile cells, tissues or organs that are found in multicellular organisms.

label: bicornuate
Defs: Having two horns or horn-shaped branches.

label: hexose catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of hexose, any monosaccharide with a chain of six carbon atoms in the molecule.

label: fibroblast proliferation
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of fibroblast cells, resulting in the expansion of the fibroblast population.

label: inefficient
Defs: An efficiency quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking efficiency.

label: digestive system element
Defs: Any of the organs or elements that are part of the digestive system. Examples: tongue, esophagus, spleen, crop, lunge feeding organ, tooth elements.

label: collagen type IV trimer
Defs: A collagen heterotrimer containing type IV alpha chains; [alpha1(IV)]2alpha2(IV) trimers are commonly observed, although more type IV alpha chains exist and may be present in type IV trimers; type IV collagen triple helices associate to form 3 dimensional nets within basement membranes.

label: regulation of acetylcholine biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of acetylcholine biosynthetic process.

label: wall of right ventricle
Defs: Wall of ventricle which is continuous with the wall of pulmonary trunk.

label: sympathetic ganglion
Defs: A ganglion of the sympathetic nervous system. Examples: paravertebral and the prevertebral ganglia, which include the sympathetic chain ganglia, the superior, middle, and inferior cervical ganglia, and the aorticorenal, celiac, and stellate ganglia.

label: negative regulation of protein localization to cell leading edge
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to cell leading edge.

label: increased height
Defs: A height which is relatively high.

label: decreased rate
Defs: A rate which is relatively low.

label: exclusion subset ontology module
Defs: A subset of an ontology that is intended to be excluded for some purpose. For example, a blacklist of classes.

label: positive regulation of cellular metabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways by which individual cells transform chemical substances.

label: positive regulation of protein localization to nucleus
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to nucleus.

label: vesicle-mediated transport in synapse
Defs: Any vesicle-mediated transport that occurs in a synapse.

label: conjunctival tubercle
Defs: The cuticular evagination constituted by conjunctiva that is circular.

label: apoptotic process involved in morphogenesis
Defs: Any apoptotic process that contributes to the shaping of an anatomical structure.

label: neurotransmitter secretion
Defs: The regulated release of neurotransmitter from the presynapse into the synaptic cleft via calcium-regulated exocytosis during synaptic transmission.

label: melanocyte
Defs: A pigment cell derived from the neural crest. Contains melanin-filled pigment granules, which gives a brown to black appearance.

label: lingual septum
Defs: The lingual septum consists of a vertical layer of fibrous tissue, extending throughout the entire length of the median plane of the tongue, though not quite reaching the dorsum. It is thicker behind than in front, and occasionally contains a small fibrocartilage, about 6 mm. in length. It is well displayed by making a vertical section across the organ.

label: increased linear velocity
Defs: A distance traveled in a specific time that is relatively high.

label: retinal rod cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized features of a retinal rod cell.

label: brown
Defs: A color consisting of dark orange, red, of very low intensity.

label: anaplastic
Defs: A morphology quality inhering in a neoplastic cell by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting breakdown of cell-cell interaction maintaining tissue architecture, proliferative dysregulation and bizarre modification to nucleus size and shape.

label: epibranchial placode
Defs: Focal thickenings of the embryonic ectoderm that form immediately dorsal and caudal of the clefts between the pharyngeal arches and that produce the neuroblasts that migrate and condense to form the distal cranial ganglia.

label: type B pancreatic cell proliferation
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of pancreatic B cells, resulting in the expansion of an pancreatic B cell population. Pancreatic B cell are cells of the pancreas that secrete insulin.

label: zone of hyoid bone
Defs: A zone of bone organ that is part of a hyoid bone.

label: cholangiocyte
Defs: An epithelial cell that is part of the bile duct. Cholangiocytes contribute to bile secretion via net release of bicarbonate and water. They are cuboidal epithelium in the small interlobular bile ducts, but become columnar and mucus secreting in larger bile ducts approaching the porta hepatis and the extrahepatic ducts.

label: cerebral cortex neuron
Defs: A CNS neuron of the cerebral cortex.

label: epithelial cell of small intestine
Defs: An epithelial cell of the small intestine.

label: vagal neural crest
Defs: Vagal neural crest is adjacent to the first seven somites gives rise to both ganglionic and ectomesenchymal derivatives[ZFA].

label: circumantennal ridge
Defs: The ridge of the head capsule that encircles the antennal foramen.

label: venous endothelial cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized endothelial cell acquires specialized features of a venous endothelial cell, a thin flattened cell that lines the inside surfaces of veins.

label: connected anatomical structure
Defs: Material anatomical entity that is a single connected structure with inherent 3D shape generated by coordinated expression of the organism\'s own genome.

label: cartilaginous
Defs: A composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s cartilage quantities.

label: melanocyte differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a melanocyte.

label: pancreas development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the pancreas over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The pancreas is an endoderm derived structure that produces precursors of digestive enzymes and blood glucose regulating enzymes.

label: leukocyte activation
Defs: A change in morphology and behavior of a leukocyte resulting from exposure to a specific antigen, mitogen, cytokine, cellular ligand, or soluble factor.

label: left lung endothelium
Defs: An endothelium that is part of a left lung.

label: positive regulation of neurotransmitter transport
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of a neurotransmitter into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: positive regulation of metabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways within a cell or an organism.

label: integumentary adnexa
Defs: Anatomical structure embedded in or located in the integument that is part of the integumental system. Examples: hair, follicles, skin glands, claws, nails, feathers.

label: ubiquinated
Defs: A molecular quality that pertains to the post-translational modification of a protein by the covalent attachment of one or more ubiquitin monomer.

label: regulation of melanocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of melanocyte differentiation.

label: respiratory system connective tissue
Defs: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

Defs: b is a generically dependent continuant = Def. b is a continuant that g-depends_on one or more other entities. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [074-001])

Defs: Binding to a major histocompatibility complex.

label: myeloid cell surface antigen CD33 (mouse)
Defs: A CD33 molecule that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: decreased male receptivity
Defs: A male receptivity which is relatively low.

label: white matter of telencephalon
Defs: A partion of white matter that is part of a telencephalon. This can be further subdivided in some species, for example, into hemisphere white matter and the corpus callosum.

label: metaventrite
Defs: The sclerite on the ventral region of the metathorax, limited by the pleurosternal sulci and medial to the metanepisternum and metepimeron.

label: colon epithelial cell migration
Defs: The orderly movement of a colonic epithelial cell from one site to another, often during the development of a multicellular organism.

label: multicuspidate
Defs: A cuscpidate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer possessing more than one cusp.

label: placental labyrinth villous
Defs: The vascularized and branched structures arising from the rodent trophoblast-derived epithelium that allow an increase its surface area for the efficient exchange of nutrients and wastes between the maternal and fetal circulation.

label: regulation of transepithelial transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transepithelial transport.

label: cardiac muscle tissue of interventricular septum
Defs: A portion of cardiac muscle tissue that is part of an interventricular septum [Automatically generated definition].

label: Thy-1 membrane glycoprotein
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human THY1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: embryo development ending in birth or egg hatching
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an embryo over time, from zygote formation until the end of the embryonic life stage. The end of the embryonic life stage is organism-specific and may be somewhat arbitrary; for mammals it is usually considered to be birth, for insects the hatching of the first instar larva from the eggshell.

label: hexose catabolic process to acetate

label: internal female genitalia

label: straight

label: negative regulation of macromolecule biosynthetic process

label: acinar
Defs: Pertaining to the individual parts making up an aggregate fruit like a many-lobed "berry," such as a raspberry.

label: positive regulation of oligodendrocyte apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of oligodendrocyte apoptotic process.

label: desaturated green
Defs: A color consisting of green hue and low saturation.

label: patchy
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being marked by, consisting of, or diversified with patches.

label: pancreatic A cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which relatively unspecialized cells acquire specialized structural and functional features of a pancreatic A cell. A pancreatic A cell is a cell in the pancreas that secretes glucagon.

label: monosaccharide transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of a monosaccharide from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: soluble in
Defs: A solubility quality inhering in a substance by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to dissolve in a liquid.

label: accessory XI nerve
Defs: A cranial nerve that originates from neurons in the medulla and in the cervical spinal cord.

label: variability of temperature
Defs: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits temperature variation or change.

label: positive regulation of chorionic trophoblast cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of chorionic trophoblast cell proliferation.

label: bulbus cordis
Defs: A transient fetal dilation of the distal (or cranial) heart tube located where the arterial trunk joins the ventral roots of the aortic arches.

label: respiratory system capillary
Defs: A capillary that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

label: hepatobiliary system
Defs: The part of the digestive system that contains the liver and the biliary system.

label: cranial muscle
Defs: Any skeletal muscle that is part of the head region.

label: trophoblast cell
Defs: A cell lining the outside of the blastocyst. After binding to the endometrium, trophoblast cells develop into two distinct layers, an inner layer of mononuclear cytotrophoblast cells and an outer layer of continuous multinuclear cytoplasm, the syncytiotrophoblast cells, which form the early fetal-maternal interface.

label: 5beta steroid
Defs: Any steroid that has beta-configuration at position 5.

label: increased process quality
Defs: A quality of a process that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.

label: jugal field
Defs: The insect wing region that is posterior to the jugal fold.

label: lung microvascular endothelial cell
Defs: Any lung endothelial cell that is part of a microvascular endothelium.

label: establishment of organelle localization

label: proctodeum

label: submucosa of large intestine
Defs: A submucosa that is part of a large intestine [Automatically generated definition].

label: dystonicity
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s impaired elastic tension that facilitate response to stimuli.

label: misaligned with
Defs: An alignment quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being in a improper spatial positioning with respect to an additional entity.

label: ketone biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of ketones, a class of organic compounds that contain the carbonyl group, CO, and in which the carbonyl group is bonded only to carbon atoms. The general formula for a ketone is RCOR, where R and R are alkyl or aryl groups.

label: lemon-shaped
Defs: A convex 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a quadric surface in three dimensions obtained by rotating less than half of a circular arc about an axis passing through the endpoints of the arc

label: partially dorsalized
Defs: A dorsalized quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s gross morphology containing what are normally dorsal structures and missing some but not all of what are normally ventral structures.

label: increased cellular motility
Defs: A cellular motility which is higher relative to the normal or average.

label: artery of lower lip
Defs: The inferior labial artery (inferior labial branch of facial artery) arises near the angle of the mouth; it passes upward and forward beneath the Triangularis and, penetrating the Orbicularis oris, runs in a tortuous course along the edge of the lower lip between this muscle and the mucous membrane. It supplies the labial glands, the mucous membrane, and the muscles of the lower lip; and anastomoses with the artery of the opposite side, and with the mental branch of the inferior alveolar artery.

label: syncytium formation
Defs: The formation of a syncytium, a mass of cytoplasm containing several nuclei enclosed within a single plasma membrane. Syncytia are normally derived from single cells that fuse or fail to complete cell division.

label: abaxial to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being away from or on the opposite side of the central axis.

label: normal variability of temperature
Defs: A variability of temperature which is relatively normal or average

label: response to metal ion
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a metal ion stimulus.

label: multipartite
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being divided into multiple parts.

label: vascular cord development
Defs: The progression of the vascular cord over time from its initial formation until its mature state. The vascular cord is the primordial vasculature that will develop into blood vessels by the process of tubulogenesis.

label: paraproct
Defs: The paired sclerite of the insect abdomen that is attached to the lateral margin of the abdominal tergite X by the abdominal tergite X-paraproct conjunctiva.

label: intracellular transport
Defs: The directed movement of substances within a cell.

label: lower respiratory tract
Defs: The segment of the respiratory tract that starts proximally with the trachea and includes all distal structures including the lungs[WP,modified].

label: extends to
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of some aspect of the bearer extending to the position of another entity.

label: positive regulation of aortic smooth muscle cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of aortic smooth muscle cell differentiation.

label: cardiac ventricle
Defs: Cardiac chamber through which blood leaves the heart.

label: species subset ontology module
Defs: A subset ontology that is crafted to either include or exclude a taxonomic grouping of species.

label: absence due to degeneration
Defs: Absence due to a degenerative process.

label: neutrophilic myeloblast
Defs: A myeloblast committed to the neutrophil lineage. This cell type is GATA-1 positive, C/EBPa-positive, AML-1-positive, c-myb-positive and has low expression of PU.1 transcription factor.

label: amide binding
Defs: Binding to an amide, any derivative of an oxoacid in which an acidic hydroxy group has been replaced by an amino or substituted amino group.

label: software library
Defs: A software library is software composed of a collection of software modules and/or software methods in a form that can be statically or dynamically linked to some software application.

label: regulation of T cell antigen processing and presentation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of T cell antigen processing and presentation.

label: hypoglossal canal
Defs: The hypoglossal canal is a bony canal in the occipital bone of the skull.

label: increased functionality
Defs: A functional quality held by the bearer when the latter exhibits increased ability to perform a regular function(s).

label: descending aorta morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the descending aorta are generated and organized. The descending aorta is the portion of the aorta in a two-pass circulatory system from the arch of aorta to the point where it divides into the common iliac arteries. In a two-pass circulatory system blood passes twice through the heart to supply the body once.

label: bilirubin(2-)
Defs: A dicarboxylic acid dianion obtained by deprotonation of the two carboxy groups of bilirubin; major species at pH 7.3.

label: blood vessel elastic tissue
Defs: Elastic tissue layer that lines a blood vessel layer.

label: tongue
Defs: A muscular organ in the floor of the mouth.

label: normal life span
Defs: A life span which is relatively normal or average.

label: decreased permeability
Defs: A permeability which is relatively low.

label: h minus
Defs: A S. pombe mating type determined by the mat1-Mc and mat1-Mi on the mat1 locus.

label: bicarbonate transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of bicarbonate from one side of a membrane to the other. Bicarbonate is the hydrogencarbonate ion, HCO3-.

label: negative regulation of lipid binding
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of lipid binding.

label: positive regulation of anion transport
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of anion transport.

label: elemental iron
Defs: An elemental molecular entity in which all of the atoms have atomic number 26.

label: neuropeptide signaling pathway
Defs: A G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway initiated by a neuropeptide binding to its receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process.

label: negative regulation of nervous system development
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of nervous system development, the origin and formation of nervous tissue.

label: positive regulation of smooth muscle cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of smooth muscle cell differentiation.

label: cytokine production involved in immune response
Defs: The appearance of a cytokine due to biosynthesis or secretion following a cellular stimulus contributing to an immune response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label: sigmoid colon
Defs: The part of the large intestine that is closest to the rectum and anus. It forms a loop that averages about 40 cm. in length, and normally lies within the pelvis, but on account of its freedom of movement it is liable to be displaced into the abdominal cavity.

label: regional part of nervous system
Defs: Any part or collection of parts of the central or peripheral nervous system. Parts may span both CNS and PNS.

label: regulation of excretion
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of excretion, the elimination by an organism of the waste products that arise as a result of metabolic activity.

label: negative regulation of developmental pigmentation
Defs: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of the developmental process that results in the deposition of coloring matter in an organism.

label: inorganic molecular entity
Defs: A molecular entity that contains no carbon.

label: hypostoma
Defs: The region of the head capsule that comprises the posterior region of the subgena.

label: functional
Defs: A functionality quality held by the bearer when the latter is able to perform a regular function(s).

label: untufted pyramidal morphology
Defs: A pyramidal cell morphology that inheres in neurons which lack a clear tuft formation but extend to large radial distances.

label: continuous with
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer possessing an uninterrupted or unbroken connection or spatial distribution relative to the position of another entity.

label: pseudopodium organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a pseudopodium, a temporary protrusion or retractile process of a cell, associated with cellular movement.

label: negative regulation of gastrulation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of gastrulation.

label: regulation of presynapse assembly
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of presynapse assembly.

label: anvil
Defs: A concave 3-D shape that inheres in the bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s shape that is wider at one end and narrow in the middle.

label: postcranial axial cartilage
Defs: Cartilage which is part of the axial skeleton.

label: spatulate
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being oblong, with the lower end very much attenuated.

label: carbohydrate homeostasis
Defs: A homeostatic process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of a carbohydrate within an organism or cell.

label: tergo-coxal muscle
Defs: The insect thoracic muscle that extends between the notum (or tergum) and the coxa.

label: cytoskeletal protein binding
Defs: Binding to a protein component of a cytoskeleton (actin, microtubule, or intermediate filament cytoskeleton).

label: regulation of macrophage cytokine production
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of macrophage cytokine production. Macrophage cytokine production is the appearance of a chemokine due to biosynthesis or secretion following a cellular stimulus, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label: macrophage homeostasis
Defs: The process of regulating the proliferation and elimination of macrophage cells such that the total number of myeloid cells within a whole or part of an organism is stable over time in the absence of an outside stimulus.

label: protein localization to heterochromatin
Defs: Any process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained at, a part of a chromosome that is organized into heterochromatin.

label: glutamatergic neuron differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized features of a glutamatergic neuron.

label: pharyngeal arch artery 4
Defs: The vessels formed within the fourth pair of branchial arches in embryogenesis.

label: decreased coordination
Defs: A coordination which is relatively low.

label: plasma membrane region
Defs: A membrane that is a (regional) part of the plasma membrane.

label: epithelium migration
Defs: The process in which the population of cells that make up an epithelium undergo directed movement.

label: stromal cell of lamina propria of small intestine
Defs: A stromal cell found in the lamina propria of the small intestine.

label: decreased propagation velocity
Defs: A propagation velocity that is lower than normal.

label: regulation of cell differentiation involved in tissue homeostasis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell differentiation that contributes to the maintenance of a steady state of a cell type within a tissue.

label: negative regulation of compound eye photoreceptor cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of compound eye photoreceptor cell differentiation.

label: muscle layer of sigmoid colon
Defs: A muscle layer that is part of the sigmoid colon.

label: neuroblast differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a neuroblast. There are at least four stages through which the pluripotent cells of epiblast or blastula become neuroblasts.

label: glandular
Defs: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhbiting the morphological characteristics of a gland.

label: ribonucleoprotein complex
Defs: A macromolecular complex that contains both RNA and protein molecules.

label: regulation of gluconeogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of gluconeogenesis, the formation of glucose from noncarbohydrate precursors, such as pyruvate, amino acids and glycerol.

label: gastrointestinal system mucosa
Defs: A mucosa that is part of a gastrointestinal system.

label: maturity
Defs: A quality of a single physical entity which is held by a bearer when the latter exhibits a state of growth, differentiation, or development.

label: peripheral blood stem cell
Defs: A hematopoeitic stem cell found in the blood. Normally found in very limited numbers in the peripheral circulation (less than 0.1% of all nucleated cells).

label: female reproductive system
Defs: The organs and associated structures associated with bearing offspring in a female animal.

label: pulmonary vascular system
Defs: The part of the cardiovascular system consisting of all pulmonary arteries and all pulmonary veins.

label: potable
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being suitable for use as a safe means of hydration.

label: stylus
Defs: The region of the cuticle of the postabdomen that is paired and connected to the anterior region of the gonocoxa IX.

label: mesentery of midgut
Defs: A mesentery that is part of a midgut [Automatically generated definition].

label: brain gray matter
Defs: A gray matter that is part of a brain [Automatically generated definition].

label: outflow tract morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the outflow tract are generated and organized. The outflow tract is the portion of the heart through which blood flows into the arteries.

label: pharyngeal ectoderm
Defs: The external part of the developing pharynx that is made of ectoderm. During vertebrate development, pockets form in pharyngeal ectoderm between the pharyngeal arches.

label: epithelial cell migration
Defs: The orderly movement of an epithelial cell from one site to another, often during the development of a multicellular organism.

label: prominin-1
Defs: A prominin that is a translation product of the human PROM1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: cut
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being regularly divided by deep incisions.

label: myofibril assembly
Defs: Formation of myofibrils, the repeating units of striated muscle.

label: visible light photoreceptor cell
Defs: A photoreceptor cell that detects visible light.

label: macrophage colony-stimulating factor 1 receptor (mouse)
Defs: A macrophage colony-stimulating factor 1 receptor that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: wholly ventralized
Defs: A ventralized quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s gross morphology containing only what are normally ventral structures.

label: mucosa of uterine tube
Defs: A mucosa that is part of a fallopian tube [Automatically generated definition].

label: positive regulation of iron ion transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of an iron transmembrane transporter activity.

label: distal side
Defs: Anatomical side that is distally located on an organism or structure.

label: positive regulation of programmed cell death
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of programmed cell death, cell death resulting from activation of endogenous cellular processes.

label: cellular response to carbohydrate stimulus
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a carbohydrate stimulus.

label: cytoplasmic microtubule
Defs: Any microtubule in the cytoplasm of a cell.

label: fasciated
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being abnormally flattened or coalesced.

label: entire pharyngeal arch associated mesenchyme
Defs: The sum total of mesenchymal tissue in the pharyngeal arch region. Pharyngeal mesenchyme is undifferentiated, loose connective tissue derived mostly from mesoderm, and also contains ectodermally derived neural crest cells.

label: sutural margin
Defs: The medial margin of the elytron.

label: non-contractile
Defs: A contractility quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s inability of contracting or being contracted.

label: cell proliferation involved in outflow tract morphogenesis
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population that contributes to the shaping of the outflow tract.

label: respiratory system muscle
Defs: Any muscle organ that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

label: regulation of transferase activity
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transferase activity, the catalysis of the transfer of a group, e.g. a methyl group, glycosyl group, acyl group, phosphorus-containing, or other groups, from one compound (generally regarded as the donor) to another compound (generally regarded as the acceptor). Transferase is the systematic name for any enzyme of EC class 2.

label: endocardium of right ventricle
Defs: Any endocardium that is part of the right ventricle of the heart.

label: cellular amine metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving any organic compound that is weakly basic in character and contains an amino or a substituted amino group, as carried out by individual cells. Amines are called primary, secondary, or tertiary according to whether one, two, or three carbon atoms are attached to the nitrogen atom.

label: skeletal myofibril assembly
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the skeletal myofibril over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A skeletal myofibril is a myofibril specific to skeletal muscle cells.

label: organelle lumen
Defs: The internal volume enclosed by the membranes of a particular organelle; includes the volume enclosed by a single organelle membrane, e.g. endoplasmic reticulum lumen, or the volume enclosed by the innermost of the two lipid bilayers of an organelle envelope, e.g. nuclear lumen.

label: negative regulation of T cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the rate or extent of T cell proliferation.

label: non-fragile
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to withstand great strain without tearing or breaking.

label: amide transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of an amide, any compound containing one, two, or three acyl groups attached to a nitrogen atom, from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: endothelium of venule
Defs: An endothelium that is part of a venule [Automatically generated definition].

label: regional part of brain
Defs: Anatomical divisons of the brain according to one or more criteria, e.g. cytoarchitectural, gross anatomy. Parts may be contiguous in 3D or not, e.g., basal ganglia.

label: SLAM family member 1
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human SLAMF1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: vascular associated smooth muscle cell proliferation
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of vascular smooth muscle cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population. A vascular smooth muscle cell is a non-striated, elongated, spindle-shaped cell found lining the blood vessels.

label: negative regulation of protein tyrosine kinase activity
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of protein tyrosine kinase activity.

label: autonomic nerve
Defs: The autonomic nerve is a small nerve which carries postganglionic sympathetic and parasympathetic neurons from the zygomaticotemporal nerve; a branch of the maxillary nerve, to the lacrimal nerve; a branch of the ophthalmic nerve. These neurons derive from the superior cervical ganglion and the pterygopalatine ganglion respectively. They will travel to the lacrimal gland via the lacrimal nerve. Parasympathetic will induce lacrimation and vice versa.

label: meltability
Defs: A quality which inheres in a substance by virtue of the ease with which the substance can be changed from a solid to a liquid state especially by the application of heat.

label: decreased amount
Defs: An amount which is relatively low.

label: bronchus elastic tissue
Defs: An elastic tissue that is part of a bronchus [Automatically generated definition].

label: action potential
Defs: A process in which membrane potential cycles through a depolarizing spike, triggered in response to depolarization above some threshold, followed by repolarization. This cycle is driven by the flow of ions through various voltage gated channels with different thresholds and ion specificities.

label: tube lumen cavitation
Defs: The formation of a lumen by hollowing out a solid rod or cord.

label: epithelium of bronchus
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a bronchus [Automatically generated definition].

label: abdomen connective tissue
Defs: A portion of connective tissue that is part of an abdomen [Automatically generated definition].

label: positive regulation of adipose tissue development
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of adipose tissue development.

label: KLRB1-like protein
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the KLRB1 gene or its closely related paralogs (KLRB1A-F). There are lineage-specific expansions in mouse and rat.

label: regulation of inorganic anion transmembrane transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of inorganic anion transmembrane transport.

label: phosphorescence
Defs: A fluorescence in which the emittence continues after the absorption has ceased.

label: mesenchymal stem cell of the bone marrow
Defs: A mesenchymal stem cell that is part of the bone marrow.

label: positive regulation of nucleobase-containing compound metabolic process
Defs: Any cellular process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving nucleobases, nucleosides, nucleotides and nucleic acids.

label: CD7-negative lymphoid progenitor cell
Defs: CD7-negative lymphoid progenitor cell is a lymphoid progenitor cell that is CD34-positive, CD7-negative and CD45RA-negative.

label: skeletal muscle connective tissue
Defs: A connective tissue that surrounds a skeletal muscle tissue.

label: acetate ester transport
Defs: The directed movement of an acetate ester into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: obsolete_unit of measure
Defs: a unit of measure is the quality of some material entity compared to which another quality is some multiple of.

label: negative regulation of macrophage chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of macrophage chemotaxis. Macrophage chemotaxis is the movement of a macrophage in response to an external stimulus.

label: regulation of gastric mucosal blood circulation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of gastric mucosal blood circulation.

label: germ layer
Defs: A layer of cells produced during the process of gastrulation during the early development of the animal embryo, which is distinct from other such layers of cells, as an early step of cell differentiation. The three types of germ layers are the endoderm, ectoderm, and mesoderm.

label: U-shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being shaped in the form of the letter U.

label: negative regulation of blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation.

label: postsynapse organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a postsynapse.

label: ventro-medial region
Defs: The region corresponding to the ventral region of the entity, towards the midline.

label: pharyngeal arch
Defs: One of a series of paired bulges that develop along the lateral walls of the foregut. The pharyngeal arches have developmental contributions from endoderm, mesoderm, and neural crest cells and are separated by anterior lateral endoderm out-pockets known as pharyngeal pouches.

label: negative regulation of CD4 production
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of CD4.

label: subtriangular
Defs: A triangular shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being nearly, but not perfectly, triangular.

label: software interpreter
Defs: A software interpreter is a software application that executes some specified input software.

label: developmental induction
Defs: A developmental process involving two tissues in which one tissue (the inducer) produces a signal that directs cell fate commitment of cells in the second tissue (the responder).

label: prechordal plate
Defs: A horseshoe-shaped thickening of the endoderm at the cranial (rostral) end of the primitive streak formed by the involution of Spemann\'s organizer cells which, together with the notochord, induces the formation of the neural plate from the overlying ectodermal cells and contributes mesodermal type cells to the surrounding tissue.

label: positive regulation of cell fate commitment
Defs: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency or rate of cell fate commitment. Cell fate commitment is the commitment of cells to specific cell fates and their capacity to differentiate into particular kinds of cells. Positional information is established through protein signals that emanate from a localized source within a cell (the initial one-cell zygote) or within a developmental field.

label: subcutaneous adipose tissue
Defs: A portion of adipose tissue that is part of the hypodermis, beneath the dermis.

label: branching involved in pancreas morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the branches of the pancreas are generated and organized.

label: saturated cyan
Defs: A color consisting of cyan colour and high saturation.

label: negative regulation of keratinocyte proliferation
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of keratinocyte proliferation. Keratinocyte proliferation is the multiplication or reproduction of keratinocytes, resulting in the expansion of a cell population.

label: dendritic spine development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the dendritic spine over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A dendritic spine is a protrusion from a dendrite and a specialized subcellular compartment involved in synaptic transmission.

label: organismal area to mass ratio
Defs: Quotient (or ratio) of surface area of an organism divided by the mass of the same organism

label: germ cell migration
Defs: The orderly movement of a cell specialized to produce haploid gametes through the embryo from its site of production to the place where the gonads will form.

label: organ subunit
Defs: A part of an organ that constitutes a distinct modular sub-unit. In some cases, the organ may also contain other sub-units of identical or similar types, in other cases this may be a distinct entity.

label: cuticle of hind leg
Defs: The cuticle of the paired appendage of the metathorax that is posterior to the cuticle of a mid leg and composed of cuticle of metacoxa, cuticle of metatrochanter, cuticle of metafemur, cuticle of metatibia, cuticle of metatarsus, and cuticle of metapretarsus.

label: dopamine catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of dopamine, a catecholamine neurotransmitter and a metabolic precursor of noradrenaline and adrenaline.

label: mucosa of pyloric antrum
Defs: A mucosa that is part of a pyloric antrum [Automatically generated definition].

label: smooth muscle contraction
Defs: A process in which force is generated within smooth muscle tissue, resulting in a change in muscle geometry. Force generation involves a chemo-mechanical energy conversion step that is carried out by the actin/myosin complex activity, which generates force through ATP hydrolysis. Smooth muscle differs from striated muscle in the much higher actin/myosin ratio, the absence of conspicuous sarcomeres and the ability to contract to a much smaller fraction of its resting length.

label: decreased accumulation
Defs: An accumulation which is relative low.

label: sexual reproduction
Defs: A type of reproduction that combines the genetic material of two gametes (such as a sperm or egg cell or fungal spores). The gametes have an haploid genome (with a single set of chromosomes, the product of a meiotic division) and combines with one another to produce a zygote (diploid).

label: epithelial cell of pancreas
Defs: An epithelial cell of the pancreas.

label: intercellular transport
Defs: The movement of substances between cells.

label: dendrogram
Defs:
A dendrogram is a report graph which is a tree diagram
frequently used to illustrate the arrangement of the clusters produced by a
clustering algorithm.

label: posterior vena cava
Defs: A vein that carries deoxygenated blood from the lower half of the body into the right atrium of the heart.

label: Y-shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being shaped in the form of the letter Y.

label: choroidal cell of the eye
Defs: A cell of the choroid of the eye.

label: cuticle of coxa
Defs: The cuticle of the segment of the leg that is attached to the latero-ventral region of the insect thorax by the basal coxal conjunctiva and to the trochanter by the coxal-trochanteral conjunctiva.

label: endothelial cell
Defs: An endothelial cell comprises the outermost layer or lining of anatomical structures and can be squamous or cuboidal. In mammals, endothelial cell has vimentin filaments and is derived from the mesoderm.

label: girdle skeleton
Defs: The subdivision of the skeleton of either the pectoral or pelvic girdle.

label: denotator type
Defs: A denotator type indicates how a term should be interpreted from an ontological perspective.

label: monosomy
Defs: An aneuploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing only one chromosome from a pair in a cell\'s nucleus.

label: editors ontology module
Defs: An ontology module that is intended to be directly edited, typically managed in source control, and typically not intended for direct consumption by end-users.

label: actin cytoskeleton of dendritic spine
Defs: The actin cytoskeleton that is part of a dendritic spine.

label: handedness
Defs: A behavioral quality inhering ina bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s unequal distribution of fine motor skill between its left and right hands or feet.

label: microvillus
Defs: Thin cylindrical membrane-covered projections on the surface of an animal cell containing a core bundle of actin filaments. Present in especially large numbers on the absorptive surface of intestinal cells.

label: scarred
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being fibrous tissue that replaces normal tissue destroyed by injury or disease.

label: peripheral nervous system neuron differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a neuron whose cell body resides in the peripheral nervous system.

label: response to carbohydrate
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a carbohydrate stimulus.

label: regulation of protein localization to membrane
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to membrane.

label: mononuclear cell of bone marrow
Defs: A mononuclear cell that is part_of a bone marrow.

label: flared
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being expanded laterally and or opened outward in shape.

label: regulation of response to external stimulus
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a response to an external stimulus.

label: increased sensitivity of a process
Defs: A sensitivity of a process which is higher than normal or average.

label: section of aorta
Defs: Any portion of the aorta including the ascending and descending aorta, and aortic arch or a portion of the aortic orifice of the left ventricle.

label: partially broken
Defs: A broken quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being still one contiguous whole but structurally damaged such that in danger of become two or more.

label: smooth muscle cell of sigmoid colon
Defs: A smooth muscle cell that is part of the sigmoid colon.

label: trunk region element
Defs: An organ or element that part of the trunk region. The trunk region can be further subdividied into thoracic (including chest and thoracic cavity) and abdominal (including abdomen and pelbis) regions.

label: regulation of vasculogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of vasculogenesis.

label: regulation of trophoblast cell migration
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of trophoblast cell migration.

label: neurula stage
Defs: Staged defined by the formation of a tube from the flat layer of ectodermal cells known as the neural plate. This will give rise to the central nervous system.

label: apical-basal axis relative to direction of growth
Defs: An axis of a plant structure that is determined by the direction of apical growth, either by an apical meristem or an apical cell. Apical is toward the direction of apical growth: toward the tip of a growing shoot axis, root, thallus, or non-vascular leaf. Basal is away from the direction of apical growth: toward the root-shoot junction in the case of the primary root or stem, toward the primary root or stem for higher order roots or branches, toward the point of attachment for non-vascular leaves, and toward the original point of growth (as determined in the embryo) for thalli.

label: positive regulation of cerebral blood circulation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cerebral blood circulation.

label: epithelium development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an epithelium over time, from its formation to the mature structure. An epithelium is a tissue that covers the internal or external surfaces of an anatomical structure.

label: regulation of intracellular signal transduction
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of intracellular signal transduction.

label: synapse pruning
Defs: A cellular process that results in the controlled breakdown of synapse. After it starts the process is continuous until the synapse has disappeared.

label: cellular spatiotemporal quality
Defs: A spatiotemporal quality inhering in a cell.

label: plasma membrane bounded cell projection
Defs: A prolongation or process extending from a cell and that is bounded by plasma membrane, e.g. a cilium, lamellipodium, or axon.

label: germ line cell
Defs: A cell that is within the developmental lineage of gametes and is able to pass along its genetic material to offspring.

label: negative regulation of gastro-intestinal system smooth muscle contraction
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of gastro-intestinal system smooth muscle contraction.

label: mucosa of rectum
Defs: A mucosa that is part of a rectum [Automatically generated definition].

label: mesocoxal-mesotrochanteral conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the mid leg joining the distal margin of a mesocoxa and the proximal margin of a mesotrochanter.

label: leukocyte migration involved in immune response
Defs: The movement of a leukocyte within or between different tissues and organs of the body as part of an immune response.

label: phallobasal-parameral conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the postabdomen that joins the phallobase and the parameres.

label: photoreceptor cell development
Defs: Development of a photoreceptor, a cell that responds to incident electromagnetic radiation, particularly visible light.

label: animal-vegetal axis
Defs: An axis that extends from the animal end of an egg or early embryo to the opposite, vegetal end. In animals with yolk-bearing eggs, the vegetal end is the yolk bearing pole. (pertains to animals only - both vertebrate and invertebrate embryos).

label: increased humidity
Defs: An increase in humidity.

label: midgut development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the midgut over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The midgut is the middle part of the alimentary canal from the stomach, or entrance of the bile duct, to, or including, the large intestine.

label: wavelength
Defs: A physical quality which is equal to the distance between repeating units of a wave pattern.

label: regulation of lipid localization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of lipid localization.

label: cuticle of mouthpart
Defs: The cuticle of the appendage of the insect head that is encircled by the oral foraminal conjunctiva.

label: positive regulation of muscle cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of muscle cell differentiation.

label: diaphragm
Defs: A thin musculomebranous barrier that separates the abdominal and thoracic cavities. Often used for breathing control.

label: presumptive midbrain
Defs: A presumptive structure that has the potential to develop into a midbrain.

label: skeletal muscle tissue development
Defs: The developmental sequence of events leading to the formation of adult skeletal muscle tissue. The main events are: the fusion of myoblasts to form myotubes that increase in size by further fusion to them of myoblasts, the formation of myofibrils within their cytoplasm and the establishment of functional neuromuscular junctions with motor neurons. At this stage they can be regarded as mature muscle fibers.

label: trunk bone
Defs: A bone that is part of a trunk [Automatically generated definition].

label: anal canal
Defs: The terminal part of the large intestine, continuous proximally with the rectum and distally terminates with the anus.

label: cellular localization
Defs: A cellular localization process whereby a substance or cellular entity, such as a protein complex or organelle, is transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location within a cell including the localization of substances or cellular entities to the cell membrane.

label: deep vasculature
Defs: The part of the circulatory system that lies deep beneath the subcutaneous tissue layers away from the surface of the skin.

label: ovate
Defs: A spheroid quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting a continuous convex surface with an axis of symmetry and one axis longer than the other; egg-shaped.

label: cellular glucose homeostasis
Defs: A cellular homeostatic process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of glucose within a cell or between a cell and its external environment.

label: replacement bone
Defs: Bone that forms as a replacement of another structural tissue.

label: subcutaneous abdominal adipose tissue
Defs: Subcutaneous adipose tissue that is located in the abdominal region.

label: split laterally
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being split asymmetrically on one side.

label: increased curvature
Defs: A curvature which is relatively high.

label: positive regulation of immune response
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the immune response, the immunological reaction of an organism to an immunogenic stimulus.

label: mucosa of lower lip
Defs: A mucosa that is part of a lower lip [Automatically generated definition].

label: pressure
Defs: A physical quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s amount of force per unit area it exerts.

label: eye photoreceptor cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized features of a photoreceptor cell, as found in the eye, the primary visual organ of most organisms.

label: normal speed
Defs: A speed which is relatively normal or average

label: ectodermal part of digestive tract
Defs: A portion of the gut that is derived from ectoderm.

label: deformed
Defs: A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being distorted in form.

label: medial tentorio-scapal muscle
Defs: The cranio-antennal muscle that is attached to the dorsal or anterior tentorial arm and the proximal margin of the scapus.

label: protein localization to nucleolus
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a location within a nucleolus.

label: eye gland
Defs: A gland that is part of a eye. The eye is a compound unit which depending on the species may consist of an eyeballs plus associated ducts and integumentary structures. Eye glands therefore include the various types of lacrimal gland, the various types of apocrine and sebaceous glands associated with the eyelid.

label: positive regulation of intracellular transport
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of substances within cells.

label: irregular connective tissue
Defs: Connective tissue, which consists of a population of connective tissue cells, the intercellular matrix of which contains an irregular network of collagen and elastic fiber bundles. Examples: areolar tissue, mucoid tissue, connective tissue of peritoneum, connective tissue of fibrous pericardium.

label: positive regulation of gastric mucosal blood circulation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of gastric mucosal blood circulation.

label: dopaminium(1+)
Defs: An ammonium ion that is the conjugate acid of dopamine; major species at pH 7.3.

label: fundamental particle
Defs: A particle not known to have substructure.

label: common bile duct development
Defs: The progression of the common bile duct over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The common bile duct is formed from the joining of the common hepatic duct running from the liver, and the cystic duct running from the gall bladder. The common bile duct transports bile from the liver and gall bladder to the intestine.

label: positive regulation of cation transmembrane transport
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cation transmembrane transport.

label: avulsion fractured
Defs: A fractured quality in which the fragment of bone tears away from the main mass of bone as a result of physical trauma.

label: epicranial suture
Defs: The cuticular suture composed of both the coronal suture and paired frontal sutures.

label: hyaluronan metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving hyaluronan, the naturally occurring anionic form of hyaluronic acid, any member of a group of glycosaminoglycans, the repeat units of which consist of beta-1,4 linked D-glucuronyl-beta-(1,3)-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine.

label: locus ceruleus formation
Defs: The process that gives rise to the locus ceruleus. This process pertains to the initial formation of a structure from unspecified parts. In mice, the locus ceruleus is a dense cluster of neurons within the dorsorostral pons. This nucleus is the major location of neurons that release norepinephrine throughout the brain, and is responsible for physiological responses to stress and panic.

label: chronic-active
Defs: A quality of duration having progressive course of indefinite duration with active, acute-like elements.

label: submental sulcus
Defs: The cuticular sulcus between the submentum and the postgena

label: flavourless
Defs: A flavor quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking flavour.

label: keratinized cell of the oral mucosa
Defs: A keratinized cell located in the hard palate or gingiva.

label: regulation of bone remodeling
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of bone remodeling, the processes of bone formation and resorption that combine to maintain skeletal integrity.

label: regulation of pro-T cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of pro-T cell differentiation.

label: perichordal bone
Defs: Bone element that is adjacent to the notochord.

label: membrane disassembly
Defs: The controlled breakdown of any cell membrane in the context of a normal process such as autophagy.

label: unstructured
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking distinct structure.

label: anterior-posterior gradient
Defs: Anatomical gradient that is distributed along the anterior-posterior axis.

label: ocellus
Defs: The sense organ of the insect head that is covered by eye cuticle.

label: epithelium of terminal part of digestive tract
Defs: Epithelium lining the distalmost portion of the digestive tract.

label: corymb-like
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s architecture bearing resemblence to a corymb type of inflorescence.

label: spinal cord interneuron
Defs: A CNS interneuron located in the spinal cord.

label: cardiac right ventricle formation
Defs: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of a right cardiac ventricle from unspecified parts.

label: cuticular puncture
Defs: The cuticular fovea that is small.

label: left eye
Defs: An eye that is part of a left side of organism [Automatically generated definition].

label: negative regulation of insulin secretion involved in cellular response to glucose stimulus
Defs: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of insulin that contributes to the response of a cell to glucose.

label: regulation of protein localization to cell cortex
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to cell cortex.

label: myocardium of anterior wall of left ventricle
regulation of sensory perception
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of sensory perception, the series of events required for an organism to receive a sensory stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal.

label: negative regulation of supramolecular fiber organization
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of fibril organization.

label: regulation of epithelial cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of epithelial cell apoptotic process.

label: mislocalised posteriorly
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being positioned towards the rear of an organism.

label: salivary nucleus development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a salivary nucleus over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: molecular transducer activity
Defs: A compound molecular function in which an effector function is controlled by one or more regulatory components.

label: regulation of cardiac chamber morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac chamber morphogenesis.

label: mesenchymal cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in a mesenchymal cell. A mesenchymal cell is a loosely associated cell that is part of the connective tissue in an organism. Mesenchymal cells give rise to more mature connective tissue cell types.

label: cuticle of protrochanter
Defs: The cuticle of the segment of a fore leg attached to the distal margin of the procoxa by the procoxal-protrochanteral conjunctiva and to the proximal margin of the profemur by the protrochantero-profemoral conjunctiva.

label: exocrine cell
Defs: A cell of an exocrine gland; i.e. a gland that discharges its secretion via a duct.

label: integrin alpha-IIb
Defs: An integrin alpha lacking A domain that is a translation product of the human ITGA2B gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: iris morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the iris is generated and organized. The iris is an anatomical structure in the eye whose opening forms the pupil. The iris is responsible for controlling the diameter and size of the pupil and the amount of light reaching the retina.

label: negative regulation of myelination
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the formation of a myelin sheath around nerve axons.

label: saccular
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a three dimensional cavity with a narrow or no opening, and often containing an anatomical substance.

label: ovarian artery
Defs: An artery that supplies an ovary.

label: negative regulation of tetrapyrrole biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of tetrapyrrole biosynthetic process.

label: cuticle of lacinia
Defs: The cuticle of the appendage of the insect maxilla that is attached to the cuticle of stipes by the stipito-lacinial conjunctiva.

label: normal elasticity
Defs: An elasticity which is relatively normal or average.

label: mesenchyme from somatopleure
Defs: Mesenchyme that develops_from a somatopleure.

label: nucleus of medulla oblongata
Defs: A neural nucleus that is part of a medulla oblongata.

label: synovial joint
Defs: Joint in which the articulating bones or cartilages are connected by an articular capsule which encloses a synovial membrane and a synovial cavity. Examples: Temporomandibular joint, knee joint.[FMA].

label: procoxal cavity
Defs: The concave part of the prosternum that receives the procoxa.

label: actin filament organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising actin filaments. Includes processes that control the spatial distribution of actin filaments, such as organizing filaments into meshworks, bundles, or other structures, as by cross-linking.

label: neurogenesis
Defs: Generation of cells within the nervous system.

label: balanced
Defs: A balance quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having balance.

label: increased elevation
Defs: An elevation which is relatively high.

label: dendritic spine
Defs: A small, membranous protrusion from a dendrite that forms a postsynaptic compartment, typically receiving input from a single presynapse.  They function as partially isolated biochemical and an electrical compartments. Spine morphology is variable:they can be thin, stubby, mushroom, or  branched, with a continuum of intermediate morphologies. They typically terminate in a bulb shape, linked to the dendritic shaft by a restriction. Spine remodeling is though to be involved in synaptic plasticity.

label: inferior mesenteric vein
Defs: A blood vessel that drains blood from the large intestine that usually terminates when reaching the splenic vein, which goes on to form the portal vein with the superior mesenteric vein (SMV). Anatomical variations include the IMV draining into the confluence of the SMV and splenic vein and the IMV draining in the SMV. The IMV lies to the right of the similarly name artery, the inferior mesenteric artery, which originates from the abdominal aorta. [WP,unvetted].

label: paddle shaped
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling the form of a paddle.

label: mesothelial cell of parietal pleura
Defs: A mesothelial cell that is part of the parietal pleura.

label: hypoplastic
Defs: A decreased size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting reduced number of cells within an organ or tissue.

label: 3rd arch endoderm
Defs: An endoderm that is part of a pharyngeal arch 3.

label: superior olivary nucleus maturation
Defs: A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for the superior olivary nucleus to attain its fully functional state. The superior olivary nucleus is a small cylindrical mass on the dorsal surface of the lateral part of the trapezoid body of the pons, and it is situated immediately above the inferior olivary nucleus. It receives projections from the cochlear nucleus and thus is involved in the perception of sound.

label: pelvic complex
Defs: Appendage girdle complex that when present, encompasses the pelvic appendicular skeleton and the pelvic girdle.

label: tapered
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being gradually narrower or thinner toward one end.

label: tube morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of a tube are generated and organized. Epithelial and endothelial tubes transport gases, liquids and cells from one site to another and form the basic structure of many organs and tissues, with tube shape and organization varying from the single-celled excretory organ in Caenorhabditis elegans to the branching trees of the mammalian kidney and insect tracheal system.

label: steroid hormone mediated signaling pathway
Defs: The series of molecular signals mediated by a steroid hormone binding to a receptor.

label: fan Martinotti morphology
Defs: A Martinotti cell morphology that inheres in neurons which have axons that form a fan-like plexus.

label: nerve development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a nerve over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: nucleate erythrocyte maturation
Defs: A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for a nucleate erythrocyte to attain its fully functional state. A nucleate erythrocyte is an erythrocyte with a nucleus.

label: detached from
Defs: An attachment quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking connection or association with another entity.

label: molecular entity
Defs: Any constitutionally or isotopically distinct atom, molecule, ion, ion pair, radical, radical ion, complex, conformer etc., identifiable as a separately distinguishable entity.

label: hepatic mesenchymal stem cell
Defs: A mesenchymal stem cell of liver.

label: monocyte activation involved in immune response
Defs: The change in morphology and behavior of a monocyte resulting from exposure to a cytokine, chemokine, cellular ligand, or soluble factor, leading to the initiation or perpetuation of an immune response.

label: serosa of infundibulum of uterine tube
