Defs: A serous membrane that is part of a uterine tube infundibulum.

label: regulation of small molecule metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of a small molecule metabolic process.

label: efferent neuron
Defs: A neuron which sends impulses peripherally to activate muscles or secretory cells.

label: skeleton of pelvic complex
Defs: The collection of all skeletal elements in a pelvic complex - i.e. the combination of free limb or fin plus pelvic girdle.

label: sulcus limitans of neural tube
Defs: A longitudinal groove in the neural tube wall that divides the neural tube into dorsal (alar) and ventral (basal) halves (dorsal receives input from sensory neurons, ventral effects motor functions); stretches from the mesencephalon caudad[TMD].

label: cardiac endothelial cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized structural and/or functional features of a cardiac endothelial cell.

label: abdominal tergite V-abdominal tergite VI conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect abdomen that connects the abdominal tergite V and the abdominal tergite VI.

label: regulation of catalytic activity
Defs: Any process that modulates the activity of an enzyme.

label: actin filament bundle organization
Defs: A process that results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of an actin filament bundle.

label: opaque
Defs: A optical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s not being clear; not transmitting or reflecting light or radiant energy.

label: smooth muscle cell of small intestine
Defs: A smooth muscle cell that is part of the small intestine.

label: negative regulation of apical ectodermal ridge formation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of apical ectodermal ridge formation.

label: synaptic transmission, cholinergic
Defs: The vesicular release of acetylcholine from a presynapse, across a chemical synapse, the subsequent activation of dopamine receptors at the postsynapse of a target cell (neuron, muscle, or secretory cell) and the effects of this activation on the postsynaptic membrane potential and ionic composition of the postsynaptic cytosol. This process encompasses both spontaneous and evoked release of neurotransmitter and all parts of synaptic vesicle exocytosis. Evoked transmission starts with the arrival of an action potential at the presynapse.

label: actin cytoskeleton organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising actin filaments and their associated proteins.

label: brainstem development
Defs: The progression of the brainstem from its formation to the mature structure. The brainstem is the part of the brain that connects the brain with the spinal cord.

label: caseous
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling cheese.

label: threshold
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s sensitivity towards a fixed location or value where a change is observed; upper limit.

label: fibroblast proliferation involved in heart morphogenesis
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of fibroblasts, resulting in the expansion of a fibroblast population that contributes to the shaping of the heart.

label: positive regulation of skeletal muscle fiber development
Defs: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the rate of skeletal muscle fiber development. Muscle fibers are formed by the maturation of myotubes. They can be classed as slow, intermediate/fast or fast.

label: pancreas left lobe
Defs: A pancreatic lobule that is in_the_left_side_of a exocrine pancreas.

label: positive regulation of ion transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the activity of an ion transporter.

label: insect abdominal muscle
Defs: The somatic muscle that is part of the insect abdomen.

label: glial cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized features of a glial cell.

label: anterodistal orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed anterodistally.

label: cuticle of protibia
Defs: The cuticle of the segment of a fore leg attached to the distal margin of the profemur by the profemoro-protibial conjunctiva and to the proximal margin of the protarsus by the protibio-protarsal conjunctiva.

label: neurectoderm
Defs: Embryonic ectoderm that gives rise to nervous tissue.

label: norepinephrine secretion
Defs: The regulated release of norepinephrine by a cell. Norepinephrine is a catecholamine and it acts as a hormone and as a neurotransmitter of most of the sympathetic nervous system.

label: left uterine tube
Defs: A fallopian tube that is part of a left side of organism [Automatically generated definition].

label: positive regulation of endothelial cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the rate or extent of endothelial cell proliferation.

label: cup-shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s shape form resembling the shape of a cup.

label: gastrula stage
Defs: A stage defined by complex and coordinated series of cellular movements that occurs at the end of cleavage during embryonic development of most animals. The details of gastrulation vary from species to species, but usually result in the formation of the three primary germ layers, ectoderm, mesoderm and endoderm.

label: dermatocranium
Defs: Subdivision of skeleton that includes all dermal bones in the cranial skeleton[ZFA,modified].

label: female anatomical structure
Defs: A part of the body present only in females.

label: programmed cell death involved in cell development
Defs: The activation of endogenous cellular processes that result in the death of a cell as part of its development.

label: regulation of erythrocyte apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of erythrocyte apoptotic process.

label: organelle fusion
Defs: The creation of a single organelle from two or more organelles.

label: renal sodium ion transport
Defs: The directed movement of sodium ions (Na+) by the renal system.

label: detection of light stimulus involved in sensory perception
Defs: The series of events in which a light stimulus is received by a cell and converted into a molecular signal as part of the sensory perception of light.

label: non-glutinous
Defs: An amylose composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having high amount of amylose content.

label: regulation of inflammatory response
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the inflammatory response, the immediate defensive reaction (by vertebrate tissue) to infection or injury caused by chemical or physical agents.

label: hypodermis skeletal muscle layer
Defs: Any skeletal muscle organ in the hypodermis / superficial fascia.

label: centered
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located in a position equidistant from edges.

label: small intestine smooth muscle contraction
Defs: A process in which force is generated within smooth muscle tissue, resulting in a change in muscle geometry in the intestine between the stomach and the large intestine.

label: macromolecule metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving macromolecules, any molecule of high relative molecular mass, the structure of which essentially comprises the multiple repetition of units derived, actually or conceptually, from molecules of low relative molecular mass.

label: low affinity immunoglobulin gamma Fc region receptor III (mouse)
Defs: A low affinity immunoglobulin gamma Fc region receptor III that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: mislocalised
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue the bearer\'s being changed in abnormal position.

label: placental artery endothelium
Defs: An endothelium that is part of the placental artery.

label: regulation of cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell differentiation, the process in which relatively unspecialized cells acquire specialized structural and functional features.

label: neural tube ventricular layer
Defs: The layer of undifferentiated, proliferating cells that line the neural tube lumen that is the immediate transformation of the germinal neuroepithelium.

label: obsolete relaxational quality
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in an inactive muscle or muscle fibers by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting gradual lengthening.

label: saturated red
Defs: A color consisting of red hue and high saturation.

label: fibrotic
Defs: Fibrosis is the formation of excess fibrous connective tissue in an organ or tissue in a reparative or reactive process.

label: immune system process
Defs: Any process involved in the development or functioning of the immune system, an organismal system for calibrated responses to potential internal or invasive threats.

label: cellular response to hexose stimulus
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a hexose stimulus.

label: presumptive hindbrain
Defs: The rhombencephalon (or hindbrain) is a developmental categorization of portions of the central nervous system in vertebrates. The rhombencephalon can be subdivided in a variable number of transversal swellings called rhombomeres. In the human embryo eight rhombomeres can be distinguished, from caudal to rostral: Rh7-Rh1 and the isthmus (the most rostral rhombomere). A rare disease of the rhombencephalon, \'rhombencephalosynapsis\' is characterized by a missing vermis resulting in a fused cerebellum. Patients generally present with cerebellar ataxia. The caudal rhombencephalon has been generally considered as the initiation site for neural tube closure.

label: cellular response to bile acid
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a bile acid stimulus.

label: CD7-negative lymphoid progenitor OR granulocyte monocyte progenitor
study limitations textual entity
Defs: A textual entity addressing a shortcoming or bias of a study design or execution.

label: developmental process
Defs: A biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of an integrated living unit: an anatomical structure (which may be a subcellular structure, cell, tissue, or organ), or organism over time from an initial condition to a later condition.

label: quality of a suspension
Defs: A physical quality inhering in an entity by virtue of the bearer\'s solid or liquid constituents being transiently dispersed in a solid, liquid, or gas before settling due to gravity or centrifugal forces.

label: positive regulation of cell-cell adhesion
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the rate or extent of cell adhesion to another cell.

label: notochordal fluid
Defs: Fluid contained within the notochordal canal.

label: regulation of synaptic transmission, cholinergic
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cholinergic synaptic transmission, the process of communication from a neuron to another neuron across a synapse using the neurotransmitter acetylcholine.

label: increased width and length
Defs: A width and length quality that is relatively large, where both width and length are increased.

label: epidermal cell
Defs: An epithelial cell of the integument (the outer layer of an organism).

label: lower vermilion
Defs: A vermilion that is part of a lower lip.

label: brush-like shape
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling the end of a brush with a multitude of bristles.

label: G protein-coupled receptor activity involved in regulation of postsynaptic membrane potential
Defs: A G protein-coupled receptor activity occurring in the postsynaptic membrane that is part of a GPCR signaling pathway that positively regulates ion channel activity in the postsynaptic membrane.

label: colon macrophage
Defs: A macrophage that is located in the colon.

label: negative regulation of mitotic nuclear division
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the rate or extent of mitosis. Mitosis is the division of the eukaryotic cell nucleus to produce two daughter nuclei that, usually, contain the identical chromosome complement to their mother.

label: endoderm of foregut-midgut junction
Defs: An endoderm that is part of a foregut-midgut junction.

label: negative regulation of collagen catabolic process
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of collagen catabolism. Collagen catabolism is the proteolytic chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of collagen in the extracellular matrix.

label: negative regulation of mesoderm formation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of mesoderm formation.

label: positive regulation of epithelial tube formation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of epithelial tube formation.

label: negative regulation of striated muscle cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate or extent of striated muscle cell apoptotic process, a form of programmed cell death induced by external or internal signals that trigger the activity of proteolytic caspases whose actions dismantle a striated muscle cell and result in its death.

label: constitutively active
Defs: A quality of a physical object that has been constantly realizing some of its functions.

label: trunk segmentation
Defs: Partitioning of the blastoderm embryo into trunk segmental units. In Drosophila, the trunk segments include thoracic segments and abdominal segments A1 to A8.

label: yellow
Defs: A color hue with medium wavelength of that portion of the visible spectrum lying between orange and green, evoked in the human observer by radiant energy with wavelengths of approximately 570 to 590 nanometers.

label: mesencephalic neural crest
Defs: A neural crest that has_potential_to_developmentally_contribute_to a midbrain.

label: author contributions section
Defs: A part of a publication that is about the specific contributions of each author

label: rectum glandular cell
Defs: Glandular cell of rectal epithelium. Example: Goblet cell; enterocytes or absorptive cells; enteroendocrine and M cells.

label: visceral muscle cell
Defs: A muscle cell that is part of some visceral muscle

label: thoracic spinal cord ventral horn
Defs: A ventral horn of spinal cord that is part of a thoracic spinal cord.

label: negative regulation of vacuolar transport
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of vacuolar transport.

label: optic eminence surface ectoderm
Defs: An external ectoderm that is part of a optic eminence [Automatically generated definition].

label: occiput
Defs: The region of cuticle on the posterodorsal region of the head capsule that is posterior to the occipital ridge and anterior to the postoccipital ridge.

label: negative regulation of vesicle transport along microtubule
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of vesicle transport along microtubule.

label: trabecular
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s structure resembling an irregular meshwork with cross-linking struts.

label: motor neuron
Defs: An efferent neuron that passes from the central nervous system or a ganglion toward or to a muscle and conducts an impulse that causes or inhibits movement.

label: down
Defs: A directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s direction from a higher to a lower point.

label: regulation of leukocyte cell-cell adhesion
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of leukocyte cell-cell adhesion.

label: axillary sclerite
Defs: The sclerite that is surrounded by the basal wing conjunctiva.

label: miscibility
Defs: A quality of a liquid inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to mix with (dissolve in) another liquid.

label: skin of face
Defs: A zone of skin that is part of the face.

label: cellular transition metal ion homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of transition metal ions at the level of a cell. A transition metal is an element whose atom has an incomplete d-subshell of extranuclear electrons, or which gives rise to a cation or cations with an incomplete d-subshell. Transition metals often have more than one valency state. Biologically relevant transition metals include vanadium, manganese, iron, copper, cobalt, nickel, molybdenum and silver.

label: homeostasis of number of cells
Defs: Any biological process involved in the maintenance of the steady-state number of cells within a population of cells.

label: supramolecular fiber organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a supramolecular fiber, a polymer consisting of an indefinite number of protein or protein complex subunits that have polymerised to form a fiber-shaped structure.

label: blood vessel endothelium
Defs: An endothelium that lines the blood vasculature. Other endothelia may line lymph vessels, the heart.

label: regulation of fibroblast proliferation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of multiplication or reproduction of fibroblast cells.

label: cilium disassembly
Defs: A cellular process that results in the breakdown of a cilium.

label: negative regulation of oligodendrocyte apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of oligodendrocyte apoptotic process.

label: female gamete
Defs: A mature sexual reproductive cell of the female germline.

label: musculature of body
Defs: The subdivision of the musculoskeletal system that consists of all the muscles of the body[VSAO, modified].

label: regulation of retrograde axon cargo transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of retrograde axon cargo transport.

label: positive regulation of growth
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the rate or extent of growth, the increase in size or mass of all or part of an organism.

label: postsynaptic cytoskeleton
Defs: The portion of the cytoskeleton contained within the postsynapse.

label: dopamine uptake
Defs: The directed movement of dopamine into a cell.

label: increased rate
Defs: A rate which is relatively high.

label: myotube cell migration
Defs: The orderly movement of a myotube cell from one site to another, often during the development of a multicellular organism. Myotubes are multinucleated cells that are formed when proliferating myoblasts exit the cell cycle, differentiate, and fuse.

label: cell division
Defs: The process resulting in division and partitioning of components of a cell to form more cells; may or may not be accompanied by the physical separation of a cell into distinct, individually membrane-bounded daughter cells.

label: subcircular
Defs: A circular shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being nearly, but not perfectly, circular.

label: regulation of cilium movement involved in cell motility
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate frequency or extent of cilium movement involved in ciliary motility.

label: reproductive gland
Defs: Any of the organized aggregations of cells that function as secretory or excretory organs and are associated with reproduction.

label: negative regulation of dendritic cell cytokine production
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of dendritic cell cytokine production.

label: haplodiploid
Defs: A diploidy quality inhering in a bearer in by virtue of belonging in a species whose one of the sexes has haploid cells and the other has diploid cells.

label: serotonin secreting cell
Defs: A cell type that secretes 5-Hydroxytryptamine (serotonin).

label: left cerebral hemisphere
Defs: A cerebral hemisphere that is in the left side of a brain.

label: neutrophil chemotaxis
Defs: The directed movement of a neutrophil cell, the most numerous polymorphonuclear leukocyte found in the blood, in response to an external stimulus, usually an infection or wounding.

label: system development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an organismal system over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A system is a regularly interacting or interdependent group of organs or tissues that work together to carry out a given biological process.

label: stomodeum
Defs: Anterior part of the embryonic digestive tract that develops into a mouth. The stomodeum includes as parts an invagination of the ectoderm and the stomodeal cavity.

label: glabrous
Defs: A pilosity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lack of hairs or bristles.

label: high-arched
Defs: A concave quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s forming or resembling an arch of an increased apical height.

label: Golgi to plasma membrane transport
Defs: The directed movement of substances from the Golgi to the plasma membrane in transport vesicles that move from the trans-Golgi network to the plasma membrane, where they fuse and release their contents by exocytosis.

label: bile acid and bile salt transport
Defs: The directed movement of bile acid and bile salts into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: interdigitated
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s parts or projections being interlocked; for example, the fingers of two hands that are clasped.

label: regulation of protein localization to plasma membrane
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to plasma membrane.

label: pigment epithelium of eye
Defs: Epithelial layer of the retina, ciliary body, or iris composed of cells containing pigment granules.

label: endodermal cell
Defs: A cell of the inner of the three germ layers of the embryo.

label: integral component of postsynaptic membrane
Defs: The component of the postsynaptic membrane consisting of the gene products and protein complexes having at least some part of their peptide sequence embedded in the hydrophobic region of the membrane.

label: oral lamina propria
Defs: A lamina propria that is part of a mucosa of oral region.

label: RNA localization
Defs: A process in which RNA is transported to, or maintained in, a specific location.

label: craniofacial suture
Defs: Any suture between cranial and/or facial bones.

label: monosaccharide catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of monosaccharides, polyhydric alcohols containing either an aldehyde or a keto group and between three to ten or more carbon atoms.

label: establishment of protein localization to postsynaptic membrane
Defs: The directed movement of a protein to a specific location in a postsynaptic membrane.

label: apical ectodermal ridge
Defs: Multilayered ectodermal region at the distal tip of a limb or fin bud necessary for the proper development of the underlying mesenchyme[MP,modified]. Along with the zone of polarizing activity, it is a crucial organizing region during limb development[WP].

label: negative regulation of bone resorption
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of bone resorption.

label: positive regulation of protein localization to cell leading edge
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to cell leading edge.

label: regulation of catabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of substances.

label: bile duct epithelium
Defs: Any epithelium that lines one of the bile ducts.

label: myeloid cell
Defs: A cell of the monocyte, granulocyte, mast cell, megakaryocyte, or erythroid lineage.

label: external import ontology module
Defs: An imported ontology module that is derived from an external ontology. Derivation methods include the OWLAPI SLME approach.

label: regulation of dopamine metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving dopamine.

label: regulation of cellular biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of substances, carried out by individual cells.

label: nitrated
Defs: A molecular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being combined, or impregnated, with nitric acid, or some of its compounds.

label: G-protein coupled receptor
Defs: A protein that has G protein-coupled receptor (GPCR) activity. Each GPCR consists of a single polypeptide with an extracellular N-terminus, an intracellular C-terminus and seven hydrophobic transmembrane domains (TM1-TM7) linked by three extracellular loops (ECL1-ECL3) and three intracellular loops (ICL1-ICL3). GPCRs function as part of a heterotrimeric complex to transmit an extracellular signal across the membrane by activating an associated G-protein via the exchange of GDP for GTP on the alpha subunit.

label: epithelial tube morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of a tube are generated and organized from an epithelium. Epithelial tubes transport gases, liquids and cells from one site to another and form the basic structure of many organs and tissues, with tube shape and organization varying from the single-celled excretory organ in Caenorhabditis elegans to the branching trees of the mammalian kidney and insect tracheal system.

label: vasculature of muscle organ
Defs: A vasculature that is part of a muscle organ [Automatically generated definition].

label: neural keel formation
Defs: The formation of a thickened region of the neurectoderm that is roughly triangular in cross section. The neural keel develops from the neural plate and develops into the neural rod. Neural keel formation occurs during primary neurulation in teleosts.

label: melanosome
Defs: A tissue-specific, membrane-bounded cytoplasmic organelle within which melanin pigments are synthesized and stored. Melanosomes are synthesized in melanocyte cells.

label: cellular amino acid metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving amino acids, carboxylic acids containing one or more amino groups, as carried out by individual cells.

label: orange
Defs: A color hue with high-medium wavelength that of that portion of the visible spectrum lying between red and yellow, evoked in the human observer by radiant energy with wavelengths of approximately 585 to 620 nanometers.

label: skeletal element of eye region
Defs: A skeletal element that is part of a orbital region.

label: central nervous system maturation
Defs: A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for the central nervous system to attain its fully functional state. The central nervous system is the core nervous system that serves an integrating and coordinating function. In vertebrates it consists of the brain and spinal cord. In those invertebrates with a central nervous system it typically consists of a brain, cerebral ganglia and a nerve cord.

label: regulation of neuron differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of neuron differentiation.

label: cardiogenic plate
Defs: The first recognizable structure derived from the heart field.

label: smooth
Defs: A texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s processing a surface free of roughness or irregularities.

label: sinuous
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having many curves and turns.

label: stromal cell of endometrium
Defs: Connective tissue cells of the endometrium, these cells are fibroblastic in appearance. During decidualization they tranform into decidual (stromal) cells, swellling up and adopt an epithelial cell-like appearance due to the accumulation of glycogen and lipid droplets.

label: mononuclear cell proliferation
Defs: The expansion of a mononuclear cell population by cell division. A mononuclear cell is a leukocyte with a single non-segmented nucleus in the mature form.

label: regulation of glycoprotein biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a glycoprotein, a protein that contains covalently bound glycose (i.e. monosaccharide) residues; the glycose occurs most commonly as oligosaccharide or fairly small polysaccharide but occasionally as monosaccharide.

label: postocciput
Defs: The dorsolateral region of the head capsule that is posterior to the postoccipital ridge

label: stromal cell
Defs: A connective tissue cell of an organ found in the loose connective tissue. These are most often associated with the uterine mucosa and the ovary as well as the hematopoietic system and elsewhere.

label: Ly-76 high positive erythrocyte
Defs: An enucleate erythrocyte that is Lyg-76-high.

label: Schwann cell microvillus
Defs: Small finger-like extension of a Schwann cell that contacts the nodal membrane.

label: negative regulation of androgen secretion
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of androgen secretion.

label: protein
Defs: A biological macromolecule minimally consisting of one polypeptide chain synthesized at the ribosome.

label: steroid acid anion
Defs: Any anion formed by loss of a proton from a steroid acid.

label: serosa of uterus
Defs: Outer serosa layer of the uterus.

label: ventral pancreatic duct
Defs: A duct joining the pancreas to the common bile duct to supply pancreatic juices which aid in digestion provided by the exocrine pancreas. The pancreatic duct joins the common bile duct just prior to the ampulla of Vater, after which both ducts perforate the medial side of the second portion of the duodenum at the major duodenal papilla.

label: sparse
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being scattered; spread irregularly, and at a distance from each other.

label: resistant to
Defs: A resistance quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resistance to a stimulus.

label: formation of animal organ boundary
Defs: The regionalization process that specifies animal organ primordium boundaries resulting in a restriction of organogenesis to a limited spatial domain and keeping the organ separate from surrounding tissues.

label: respiratory muscle
Defs: Muscle that is part of the respiratory system.

label: presynaptic actin cytoskeleton
Defs: The actin cytoskeleton that is part of a presynapse.

label: mesonoto-metanotal muscle
Defs: The insect thoracic muscle that extends between the mesonotum and the metanotum.

label: normal mass
Defs: A mass which is relatively normal or average.

label: broadly articulated with
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s possessing a broad surface in articulation with another entity.

label: regulation of somatostatin secretion
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, extent of the regulated release of somatostatin from secretory granules in the D cells of the pancreas.

label: negative regulation of melanocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of melanocyte differentiation.

label: trachea connective tissue
Defs: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a trachea.

label: muscle of neck
Defs: Any muscle that is part of the cervical (neck) region.

label: juvenile
Defs: A maturity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue the bearer\'s being not fully grown or developed.

label: regulation of granulocyte chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of granulocyte chemotaxis. Granulocyte chemotaxis is the movement of a granulocyte in response to an external stimulus.

label: cellular response to toxic substance
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a toxic stimulus.

label: increased object quality
Defs: A quality of an object that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.

label: luteinization
Defs: The set of processes resulting in differentiation of theca and granulosa cells into luteal cells and in the formation of a corpus luteum after ovulation.

label: disposition
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s prevailing tendency, mood, or inclination.

label: B-lymphocyte antigen CD20 (mouse)
Defs: A membrane-spanning 4-domains subfamily A member 1 that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: pointed
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a point.

label: mesanepisternum
Defs: The anepisternum on the anterior region of the mesopleuron and lateral to the mesoventrite.

label: phagocytosis
Defs: A vesicle-mediated transport process that results in the engulfment of external particulate material by phagocytes and their delivery to the lysosome. The particles are initially contained within phagocytic vacuoles (phagosomes), which then fuse with primary lysosomes to effect digestion of the particles.

label: stromal cell of lamina propria of large intestine
Defs: A stromal cell found in the lamina propria of the large intestine.

label: negative regulation of hematopoietic progenitor cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of hematopoietic progenitor cell differentiation.

label: active transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of a specific substance or related group of substances from one side of a membrane to the other, up the solute\'s concentration gradient. The transporter binds the solute and undergoes a series of conformational changes. Transport works equally well in either direction.

label: 2-D shape
Defs: A shape that inheres in a 2 dimensional entity, such as a cross section or projection of a 3 dimensional entity.

label: skeletal muscle tissue of pharynx
Defs: A portion of skeletal muscle tissue that is part of a pharynx [Automatically generated definition].

label: muscle layer of anal canal
Defs: A muscular coat that is part of a anal canal.

label: intermediate mesoderm morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the intermediate mesoderm are generated and organized.

label: papillomatous
Defs: A round or lobulated protruding form resembling a nipple.

label: nuclear division
Defs: The division of a cell nucleus into two nuclei, with DNA and other nuclear contents distributed between the daughter nuclei.

label: thoracic segment organ
Defs: An organ that part of the thoracic segment region. This region can be further subdividied chest and thoracic cavity regions.

label: great vessel of heart
Defs: Great vessels is a term used to refer collectively to the large vessels that bring blood to and from the heart.

label: obsolete bright grey
Defs: A color consisting of grey color and high saturation.

label: color hue
Defs: A chromatic scalar-circular quality inhering in an object that manifests in an observer by virtue of the dominant wavelength of the visible light; may be subject to fiat divisions, typically into 7 or 8 spectra.

label: catechol-containing compound biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of catechol-containing compounds. Catechol is a compound containing a pyrocatechol nucleus or substituent.

label: bronchus development
Defs: The biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of a bronchus from an initial condition to its mature state. This process begins with the formation of the bronchus and ends with the mature structure. The bronchus is the portion of the airway that connects to the lungs.

label: cuticle of aedeagus
Defs: The cuticular evagination of the postabdomen that is distal and attached to the cuticle of parameres by the paramero-aedeagal conjunctiva and is connected to the endophallus.

label: cellular sulfate ion homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of sulfate ions at the level of a cell.

label: insoluble in
Defs: A solubility quality inhering in a substance by virtue of the bearer\'s inability of a substance to dissolve in a liquid.

label: increased temperature
Defs: A temperature which is relatively high.

label: process efficacy
Defs: The ability of a process to produce its output.

label: regulation of glycogen catabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of glycogen.

label: obsolete_study interpretation
Defs: A study interpretation is a textual entity about the implications of a study result. Examples include discussion of whether a hypothesis is false, whether the study failed to address the hypothesis, and whether the study results have led to new hypotheses

label: membrane bone
Defs: Bone element that arises as a result of intramembranous ossification.

label: yellow bone marrow
Defs: Bone marrow in which the fat cells predominate in the meshes of the reticular network.

label: organic hydroxy compound transport
Defs: The directed movement of an organic hydroxy compound (organic alcohol) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. An organic hydroxy compound is an organic compound having at least one hydroxy group attached to a carbon atom.

label: ion binding
Defs: Binding to an ion, a charged atoms or groups of atoms.

label: epiblast cell
Defs: A cell of the outer layer of a blastula that gives rise to the ectoderm after gastrulation.

label: vagus nerve nucleus
Defs: A cranial nerve nucleus that is associated with a vagus nerve.

label: head
Defs: The head is the anterior-most division of the body [GO].

label: contractility
Defs: A physical quality that is the ability to contract or shrink.

label: cuticle of palpiger
Defs: The sclerite of the cuticle of labium that is attached to the prementum by the premental-palpigeral conjunctiva and to the cuticle of labial palpus by the palpigero-palpal conjunctiva.

label: skeletal musculature of head
Defs: Any collection of skeletal muscles that is part of a head [Automatically generated definition].

label: intrinsic component of Golgi membrane
Defs: The component of the Golgi membrane consisting of the gene products and protein complexes having either part of their peptide sequence embedded in the hydrophobic region of the membrane or some other covalently attached group such as a GPI anchor that is similarly embedded in the membrane.

label: serosa of large intestine
Defs: A serous membrane that is part of a large intestine [Automatically generated definition].

label: fatigability
Defs: A strength quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to lose strength.

label: osmolarity
Defs: A concentration quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s amount of osmoles of solute per liter of solution.

label: ketone catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of ketones, a class of organic compounds that contain the carbonyl group, CO, and in which the carbonyl group is bonded only to carbon atoms. The general formula for a ketone is RCOR, where R and R are alkyl or aryl groups.

label: lactoferrin transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of lactoferrin from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: snowman-shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having two connected parts, roughly spherical, of different sizes.

label: partially posterioralized
Defs: A posterioralized quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s gross morphology containing what are normally posterior structures and missing some but not all of what are normally anterior structures.

label: leukocyte proliferation
Defs: The expansion of a leukocyte population by cell division.

label: neuromuscular junction development
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a neuromuscular junction.

label: granulocyte
Defs: A leukocyte with abundant granules in the cytoplasm.

label: adaxial to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located on the side nearest to the axis of an organ or organism.

label: uterus
Defs: The female muscular organ of gestation in which the developing embryo or fetus is nourished until birth.

label: rhombomere
Defs: A segment of the developing hindbrain[ZFA]. In the vertebrate embryo, a rhombomere is a transiently divided segment of the developing neural tube, within the hindbrain region (a neuromere) in the area that will eventually become the rhombencephalon. The rhombomeres appear as a series of slightly constricted swellings in the neural tube, caudal to the cephalic flexure.[WP].

label: positive regulation of gastrulation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of gastrulation.

label: negative regulation of exosomal secretion
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of exosomal secretion.

label: negative regulation of acetylcholine biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of acetylcholine biosynthetic process.

label: normal velocity
Defs: A velocity which is relatively normal or average

label: response to iron ion
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an iron ion stimulus.

label: positive regulation of placenta blood vessel development
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of placenta blood vessel development.

label: cane-like
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s similarity to the appearance of a cane.

label: positive regulation of cardiac muscle adaptation
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, extent or frequency of the process in which cardiac muscle adapts, with consequent modifications to structural and/or functional phenotypes, in response to a stimulus. Stimuli include contractile activity, loading conditions, substrate supply, and environmental factors.

label: nucleobase-containing compound metabolic process
Defs: Any cellular metabolic process involving nucleobases, nucleosides, nucleotides and nucleic acids.

label: reasoned ontology module
Defs: An ontology module that contains axioms generated by a reasoner. The generated axioms are typically direct SubClassOf axioms, but other possibilities are available.

label: axon development
Defs: The progression of an axon over time. Covers axonogenesis (de novo generation of an axon) and axon regeneration (regrowth), as well as processes pertaining to the progression of the axon over time (fasciculation and defasciculation).

label: ovarian fibroblast
Defs: Any fibroblast that is part of a female gonad.

label: software application
Defs: A software application is software that can be directly executed by some processing unit.

label: endocardium of ventricle
Defs: Endocardium that is part of the cardiac ventricle.

label: fasciculated
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s forming a bundle of aligned anatomical fibers, as of muscle or nerve.

label: trophic quality
Defs: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to synthesize a particular organic compound required for its growth.

label: vitelline vein
Defs: The paired veins that carry blood from the yolk sac back to the embryo.

label: decreased linear velocity
Defs: A distance traveled in a specific time that is relatively low.

label: obsolete far red light sensitivity value
trigeminal ganglion
Defs: The cranial ganglion that is associated with and extends fibers into the trigeminal nerve.

label: bone marrow hematopoietic cell
Defs: Hematopoietic cells resident in the bone marrow. Include: hematopoietic stem cells (lymphoid stem cells and myeloid stem cells) and the precursor cells for thrombocytes, erythrocytes, basophils, neutrophils, eosinophils, monocytes and lymphocytes.

label: carbohydrate acid derivative anion
Defs: A carboxylic acid anion resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of a carbohydrate acid derivative.

label: ballooning
Defs: A volume quality inhering in a degenerating cell by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting an increase in volume associated with cytoplasmic abnormalities.

label: spatial distribution of a process
Defs: A physical quality of a process that is its spatial distribution. For example, bone mineralization follows stereotypical spatial distribution patterns during development, which may be altered in some phenotypes.

label: positive regulation of nervous system development
Defs: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of nervous system development, the origin and formation of nervous tissue.

label: neurotransmitter transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the directed movement of a neurotransmitter into, out of or within a cell, or between cells. Neurotransmitters are any chemical substance that is capable of transmitting (or inhibiting the transmission of) a nerve impulse from a neuron to another cell.

label: regulation of striated muscle cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of striated muscle cell differentiation.

label: regulation of trophectodermal cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of trophectodermal cell proliferation.

label: regulation of T cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of T cell differentiation.

label: positive regulation of developmental pigmentation
Defs: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of the developmental process that results in the deposition of coloring matter in an organism.

label: multiple
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being present in more than two copies.

label: hypostomal ridge
Defs: The ridge composing the posterior region of the subgenal ridge.

label: mucosa of common bile duct
Defs: A mucosa that is part of a common bile duct [Automatically generated definition].

label: steroid metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving steroids, compounds with a 1,2,cyclopentanoperhydrophenanthrene nucleus.

label: material anatomical entity
Defs: An anatomical entity that has mass.

label: protic solvent
Defs: A polar solvent that is capable of acting as a hydron (proton) donor.

label: pseudopodium assembly
Defs: The assembly of a pseudopodium by rearrangement of the actin cytoskeleton and overlying membrane.

label: exocrine pancreas development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the exocrine pancreas over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The exocrine pancreas produces and store zymogens of digestive enzymes, such as chymotrypsinogen and trypsinogen in the acinar cells.

label: rhomboid
Defs: A spheroid quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being oval and a little angular in the middle.

label: tergo-trochanteral muscle
Defs: The insect thoracic muscle that extends between the notum (or tergum) and the trochanter.

label: hexose metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving a hexose, any monosaccharide with a chain of six carbon atoms in the molecule.

label: arteriole
Defs: The smallest division of the artery located between the muscular arteries and the capillaries[GO].

label: negative regulation of macrophage cytokine production
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of macrophage cytokine production. Macrophage cytokine production is the appearance of a chemokine due to biosynthesis or secretion following a cellular stimulus, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label: ciliary muscle cell
Defs: A smooth muscle cell that is part of the ciliary body.

label: parietal peritoneum
Defs: The outer layer of peritoneum that is attached to the abdominal and pelvic walls.

label: lobed
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being partly divided into a determinate number of regions.

label: regulation of epithelial cell migration
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of epithelial cell migration.

label: organic anion transport
Defs: The directed movement of organic anions into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Organic anions are atoms or small molecules with a negative charge which contain carbon in covalent linkage.

label: conjugated protein
Defs: Conjugated protein is a protein that contains a non-peptide component, usually in stoichiometric proportion.

label: preganglionic autonomic fiber
Defs: Nerve fibers which project from the central nervous system to autonomic ganglia. In the sympathetic division most preganglionic fibers originate with neurons in the intermediolateral column of the spinal cord, exit via ventral roots from upper thoracic through lower lumbar segments, and project to the paravertebral ganglia; there they either terminate in synapses or continue through the splanchnic nerves to the prevertebral ganglia. In the parasympathetic division the fibers originate in neurons of the brain stem and sacral spinal cord. In both divisions the principal transmitter is acetylcholine but peptide cotransmitters may also be released.

label: nucleus of superior olivary complex
Defs: Any of the nuclei that comprise the superior olivary complex (superior olive). This includes both the primary nuclei such as the lateral and medial nuclei, as well as periolivary nuclei.

label: cytoplasmic region
Defs: Any (proper) part of the cytoplasm of a single cell of sufficient size to still be considered cytoplasm.

label: 6th arch mesenchyme from head mesenchyme
Defs: Mesenchyme that develops_from a head mesenchyme from mesoderm and is part of a 6th arch mesenchyme.

label: Golgi apparatus
Defs: A membrane-bound cytoplasmic organelle of the endomembrane system that further processes the core oligosaccharides (e.g. N-glycans) added to proteins in the endoplasmic reticulum and packages them into membrane-bound vesicles. The Golgi apparatus operates at the intersection of the secretory, lysosomal, and endocytic pathways.

label: bicarbonate binding
Defs: Binding to bicarbonate ions (CHO3-).

label: positive regulation of brood size
Defs: Any process that increases brood size. Brood size is the number of progeny that survive embryogenesis and are cared for at one time.

label: displaced
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue the bearer\'s being changed in position.

label: organelle membrane fusion
Defs: The joining of two lipid bilayers to form a single organelle membrane.

label: phosphate ion transmembrane transport
Defs: The process in which a phosphate is transported across a membrane.

label: biliary system
Defs: Organ system subdivision that consists of the organs and ducts that are involved in the production and transportation of bile. In most species this is the gallbladder and the bile ducts (biliary tree).

label: main group molecular entity
Defs: A molecular entity containing one or more atoms from any of groups 1, 2, 13, 14, 15, 16, 17, and 18 of the periodic table.

label: leukocyte migration
Defs: The movement of a leukocyte within or between different tissues and organs of the body.

label: T cell mediated immunity
Defs: Any process involved in the carrying out of an immune response by a T cell.

label: pancreatic D cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which relatively unspecialized cells acquire specialized structural and functional features that characterize a pancreatic delta cell. A delta cell is a cell of the pancreas that produces somatostatin.

label: organism subdivision
Defs: Anatomical structure which is a subdivision of a whole organism, consisting of components of multiple anatomical systems, largely surrounded by a contiguous region of integument.

label: positive regulation of biological process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of a biological process. Biological processes are regulated by many means; examples include the control of gene expression, protein modification or interaction with a protein or substrate molecule.

label: cuticle of cercomere
Defs: The cuticle of the mere that is part of the cercus.

label: morphogenesis of an epithelial fold involved in embryonic heart tube formation
Defs: The morphogenetic process in which an epithelial sheet bends along a linear axis, contributing to embryonic heart tube formation.

label: deep pink
Defs: Pink color having medium brightness and moderate saturation.

label: jugal vein
Defs: The insect wing vein in the jugal field, posterior to the jugal fold or to the anal veins.

label: nucleus of spinal cord
Defs: A neural nucleus that is part of the spinal cord.

label: genitalia development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the genitalia over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: trachea elastic tissue
Defs: An elastic tissue that is part of a trachea [Automatically generated definition].

label: positive regulation of cell development
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of the progression of the cell over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Cell development does not include the steps involved in committing a cell to a specific fate.

label: vitelline blood vessel
Defs: Blood vessel that is connected to the yolk sac.

label: mucosa of infundibulum of uterine tube
Defs: A mucosa that is part of a uterine tube infundibulum [Automatically generated definition].

label: anion
Defs: A monoatomic or polyatomic species having one or more elementary charges of the electron.

label: dorsal side
Defs: An anatomical region that is the entire part of an anatomical structure dorsal to a horizontal plane and bounded on one side by the same transverse plane.

label: CD7-positive lymphoid progenitor cell
Defs: CD7-positive lymphoid progenitor cell is a lymphoid progenitor cell that is CD34-positive, CD7-positive and is CD45RA-negative.

label: tubular
Defs: A cylindrical shape that is hollow.

label: regulation of neural crest formation
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of neural crest formation. Neural crest formation is the formation of the specialized region of ectoderm between the neural ectoderm (neural plate) and non-neural ectoderm. The neural crest gives rise to the neural crest cells that migrate away from this region as neural tube formation proceeds.

label: programming language
Defs: A language in which source code is written that is intended to be executed/run by a software interpreter. Programming languages are ways to write instructions that specify what to do, and sometimes, how to do it.

label: esophagus muscle
Defs: Any muscle organ that is part of a esophagus [Automatically generated definition].

label: pontine tegmentum
Defs: Dorsal portion of the pons, containing cranial nervee nuclei, ascending and descending tracts and reticular nuclei. It is continuous with the reticular formation of the medulla (Carpenter, A Core Text of Neuroanatomy, 3rd ed, 1985, pg 133).

label: high saturation
Defs: A color saturation which is of high purity.

label: endocardium of left ventricle
Defs: Any endocardium that is part of the left ventricle of the heart.

label: endocardial cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized structural and/or functional features of an endocardial cell. An endocardial cell is a specialized endothelial cell that makes up the endocardium portion of the heart. The endocardium is the innermost layer of tissue of the heart, and lines the heart chambers.

label: glandular columnar epithelium
Defs: Simple columnar epithelium that constitutes the secretory part of a gland. Examples: epithelium of stomach, luminal epithelium of lactiferous duct.[FMA].

label: primary circulatory organ
Defs: A hollow, muscular organ, which, by contracting rhythmically, keeps up the circulation of the blood or analogs[GO,modified].

label: progenitor cell
Defs: A precursor cell that has a tendency to differentiate into a specific type of cell. They are descendants of stem cells, only they are more constrained in their differentiation potential or capacity for self-renewal, and are often more limited in both senses.

label: regulation of cell proliferation involved in embryonic placenta development
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of cell proliferation involved in embryonic placenta development.

label: wing
Defs: Appendage that is shaped in order to produce lift for flight through the air.

label: extends beyond
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of some aspect of the bearer extending past the position of another entity.

label: Ly-76 high reticulocyte

The trigeminal nerve is composed of three large branches. They are the ophthalmic (V1, sensory), maxillary (V2, sensory) and mandibular (V3, motor and sensory) branches. The sensory ophthalmic branch travels through the superior orbital fissure and passes through the orbit to reach the skin of the forehead and top of the head. The maxillary nerve contains sensory branches that reach the pterygopalatine fossa via the inferior orbital fissure (face, cheek and upper teeth) and pterygopalatine canal (soft and hard palate, nasal cavity and pharynx). The motor part of the mandibular branch is distributed to the muscles of mastication, the mylohyoid muscle and the anterior belly of the digastric. The mandibular nerve also innervates the tensor veli palatini and tensor tympani muscles. The sensory part of the mandibular nerve is composed of branches that carry general sensory information from the mucous membranes of the mouth and cheek, anterior two-thirds of the tongue, lower teeth, skin of the lower jaw, side of the head and scalp and meninges of the anterior and middle cranial fossae.

Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of defense response to insect.

label: notched
Defs: A concave quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s shape being a V-shaped cut.

label: light blue
Defs: A color consisting of blue hue and high brightness.

label: phosphorylation
Defs: The process of introducing a phosphate group into a molecule, usually with the formation of a phosphoric ester, a phosphoric anhydride or a phosphoric amide.

label: head paraxial mesoderm
Defs: Bilateral mesenchymal mesoderm parallel and immediately adjacent to the neural tube/notochord; it generates a subset of extra-ocular, and other head, muscles.

label: polysaccharide catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a polysaccharide, a polymer of many (typically more than 10) monosaccharide residues linked glycosidically.

label: sulfate transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of sulfate ions, SO4(2-), from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: obsolete decreased action potential
Defs: An action potential which is relatively low.

label: negative regulation of skeletal muscle fiber development
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of skeletal muscle fiber development. Muscle fibers are formed by the maturation of myotubes. They can be classed as slow, intermediate/fast or fast.

label: looseness
Defs: A texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s bing full of small openings or gaps.

label: regulation of gastrulation
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate or extent of gastrulation. Gastrulation is the complex and coordinated series of cellular movements that occurs at the end of cleavage during embryonic development of most animals.

label: decreased odor
Defs: An odor quality of having decreased odor.

label: cardioblast differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized mesodermal cell acquires the specialized structural and/or functional features of a cardioblast. A cardioblast is a cardiac precursor cell. It is a cell that has been committed to a cardiac fate, but will undergo more cell division rather than terminally differentiating.

label: midgut dorsal mesentery
Defs: A dorsal mesentery that is part of a midgut.

label: small intestine venule
Defs: Venule of villus of small intestine.

label: transcription factor binding
Defs: Binding to a transcription factor, a protein required to initiate or regulate transcription.

label: mucosa of gallbladder
Defs: A mucosa that is part of a gallbladder [Automatically generated definition].

label: inflammatory response
Defs: The immediate defensive reaction (by vertebrate tissue) to infection or injury caused by chemical or physical agents. The process is characterized by local vasodilation, extravasation of plasma into intercellular spaces and accumulation of white blood cells and macrophages.

label: proepicardium
Defs: An embryonic group of progenitor cells that forms from an outpouching of the septum transversum near the venous pole of the heart and gives rise to the epicardium.

label: cilium
Defs: A specialized eukaryotic organelle that consists of a filiform extrusion of the cell surface and of some cytoplasmic parts. Each cilium is largely bounded by an extrusion of the cytoplasmic (plasma) membrane, and contains a regular longitudinal array of microtubules, anchored to a basal body.

label: regulation of bleb assembly
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of bleb assembly.

label: increased tonicity
Defs: A tonicity which is relatively high.

label: regulation of Schwann cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency or rate of multiplication or reproduction of Schwann cells, resulting in the expansion of their population. Schwann cells are a type of glial cell in the peripheral nervous system.

label: aorta development
Defs: The progression of the aorta over time, from its initial formation to the mature structure. An aorta is an artery that carries blood from the heart to other parts of the body.

label: arthropod tagma
Defs: One of the main divisions of the whole organism of arthropods formed from groups of segments.

label: organelle fission
Defs: The creation of two or more organelles by division of one organelle.

label: autogenous
Defs: Being separate or discrete from other skeletal elements.

label: RNA transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of RNA, ribonucleic acid, from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: accumulation
Defs: A structural quality of the collection or massing of one physical object within another physical object.

label: misrouted
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having mistakenly taken course, way, or passage; ill-routed.

label: regulation of cardiac muscle cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate or extent of cardiac cell apoptotic process, a form of programmed cell death induced by external or internal signals that trigger the activity of proteolytic caspases whose actions dismantle a cardiac muscle cell and result in its death.

label: female sterile
Defs: A female fertility quality inhering in a female by virtue of the bearer\'s being incapable of initiating, sustaining, or supporting reproduction.

label: negative regulation of cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cell differentiation.

label: decreased variability
Defs: A variability which is relatively low.

label: subelliptical
Defs: A shape that is almost an ellipse.

label: desaturated red
Defs: A color consisting of red hue and low saturation.

label: organelle assembly
Defs: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form an organelle. An organelle is an organized structure of distinctive morphology and function. Includes the nucleus, mitochondria, plastids, vacuoles, vesicles, ribosomes and the cytoskeleton. Excludes the plasma membrane.

label: regulation of myotube differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of myotube differentiation. Myotube differentiation is the process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a myotube cell. Myotubes are multinucleated cells that are formed when proliferating myoblasts exit the cell cycle, differentiate and fuse.

label: muscle organ morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of muscle are generated and organized.

label: organelle
Defs: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function. Includes the nucleus, mitochondria, plastids, vacuoles, vesicles, ribosomes and the cytoskeleton, and prokaryotic structures such as anammoxosomes and pirellulosomes. Excludes the plasma membrane.

label: materials section
Defs: A part of a document about the materials required to reproduce the content of the document.

label: positive regulation of cardiac muscle fiber development
Defs: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle fiber development.

label: negative regulation of leukocyte cell-cell adhesion
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of leukocyte cell-cell adhesion.

label: dendritic cell proliferation
Defs: The expansion of a dendritic cell population by cell division. A dendritic cell is a cell of hematopoietic origin, typically resident in particular tissues, specialized in the uptake, processing, and transport of antigens to lymph nodes for the purpose of stimulating an immune response via T cell activation.

label: AV node cell to bundle of His cell signaling
Defs: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from an AV node cardiac muscle cell to a bundle of His cardiomyocyte.

label: tongue squamous epithelium
Defs: A squamous epithelium that is part of a tongue.

label: positive regulation of supramolecular fiber organization
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of supramolecular fiber organization.

label: regulation of blastocyst development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of blastocyst development.

label: macrophage dendritic cell progenitor
Defs: A progenitor cell that can give rise to plasmacytoid and myeloid dendritic cells, and to monocytes and macrophages.

label: presynaptic process involved in chemical synaptic transmission
Defs: The pathway leading to secretion of a neurotransmitter from the presynapse as part of synaptic transmission.

label: endocardial endothelium
Defs: The endothelial lining of the endocardium.

label: gluconeogenesis
Defs: The formation of glucose from noncarbohydrate precursors, such as pyruvate, amino acids and glycerol.

label: glycosaminoglycan secreting cell
Defs: A cell that secretes glycosaminoglycans.

label: increased width
Defs: A width which is relatively large.

label: monosaccharide transmembrane transport
Defs: The process in which a monosaccharide is transported across a lipid bilayer, from one side of a membrane to the other. Monosaccharides are the simplest carbohydrates; they are polyhydric alcohols containing either an aldehyde or a keto group and between three to ten or more carbon atoms. They form the constitutional repeating units of oligo- and polysaccharides.

label: glial cell proliferation
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of glial cells by cell division, resulting in the expansion of their population. Glial cells exist throughout the nervous system, and include Schwann cells, astrocytes, and oligodendrocytes among others.

label: quadrangular
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having four angles and four sides.

label: D-shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a strait side and an arched side giving the bearer the form of the letter D.

label: embryonic organ development
Defs: Development, taking place during the embryonic phase, of a tissue or tissues that work together to perform a specific function or functions. Development pertains to the process whose specific outcome is the progression of a structure over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Organs are commonly observed as visibly distinct structures, but may also exist as loosely associated clusters of cells that work together to perform a specific function or functions.

label: convex
Defs: A shape quality that obtains by virtue of the bearer having inward facing edges; having a surface or boundary that curves or bulges outward, as the exterior of a sphere.

label: intrinsic component of nuclear outer membrane
Defs: The component of the nuclear outer membrane consisting of the gene products and protein complexes having either part of their peptide sequence embedded in the hydrophobic region of the membrane or some other covalently attached group such as a GPI anchor that is similarly embedded in the membrane.

label: regulation of myotube cell migration
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of myotube cell migration.

label: mesothelial cell of visceral pleura
Defs: A mesothelial cell that is part of the visceral pleura.

label: striated visceral muscle cell
Defs: A visceral muscle cell that is striated.  Examples include the visceral muscle cells of arhtropods.

label: dorsal longitudinal abdominal muscle
Defs: The insect abdominal muscle that runs along the dorsal region, parallel to the anterior-posterior axis.

label: square
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having an equal-sided rectangular form.

label: wall of large intestine
Defs: An anatomical wall that is part of a large intestine [Automatically generated definition].

label: decreased width
Defs: A width which is relatively small.

label: mixed
Defs: A composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being composed of more than one identifiable entities.

label: sensory neuron
Defs: Any neuron having a sensory function; an afferent neuron conveying sensory impulses.

label: peptidyl-amino acid modification
Defs: The alteration of an amino acid residue in a peptide.

label: left
Defs: A directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s direction that is similar to the direction of an object to the north when it faces east.

label: precoxal ridge
Defs: The ridge that is anterior to a coxa, demarcated by the anapleural sulcus.

label: gland development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a gland over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A gland is an organ specialised for secretion.

label: carbohydrate derivative binding
Defs: Binding to a carbohydrate derivative.

label: anatomical collection
Defs: A collection of anatomical structures that are alike in terms of their morphology or developmental origin.

label: ammonium
Defs: An onium cation obtained by protonation of ammonia.

label: glial cell migration
Defs: The orderly movement of a glial cell, non-neuronal cells that provide support and nutrition, maintain homeostasis, form myelin, and participate in signal transmission in the nervous system.

label: mesenchyme development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a mesenchymal tissue over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A mesenchymal tissue is made up of loosely packed stellate cells.

label: motile cilium
Defs: A cilium which may have a variable arrangement of axonemal microtubules and also contains molecular motors. It may beat with a whip-like pattern that promotes cell motility or transport of fluids and other cells across a cell surface, such as on epithelial cells that line the lumenal ducts of various tissues; or they may display a distinct twirling motion that directs fluid flow asymmetrically across the cellular surface to affect asymmetric body plan organization. Motile cilia can be found in single as well as multiple copies per cell.

label: positive regulation of fibroblast proliferation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of multiplication or reproduction of fibroblast cells.

label: paired limb/fin bud
Defs: An outgrowth on the lateral trunk of the embryo that develops into a limb or paired fin. The limb/fin bud is divided into ectoderm and mesenchyme[cjm, modified from MP].

label: anterior side
Defs: An anatomical region that is the entire part of an anatomical structure anterior to a transverse plane and bounded on one side by the same transverse plane.

label: indole-containing compound metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving compounds that contain an indole (2,3-benzopyrrole) skeleton.

label: tetrapyrrole
Defs: A natural pigment containing four pyrrole rings joined by one-carbon units linking position 2 of one pyrrole ring to position 5 of the next.

label: microtubule
Defs: Any of the long, generally straight, hollow tubes of internal diameter 12-15 nm and external diameter 24 nm found in a wide variety of eukaryotic cells; each consists (usually) of 13 protofilaments of polymeric tubulin, staggered in such a manner that the tubulin monomers are arranged in a helical pattern on the microtubular surface, and with the alpha/beta axes of the tubulin subunits parallel to the long axis of the tubule; exist in equilibrium with pool of tubulin monomers and can be rapidly assembled or disassembled in response to physiological stimuli; concerned with force generation, e.g. in the spindle.

label: haploid cell
Defs: A cell whose nucleus contains a single haploid genome.

label: excreta
Defs: A portion of organism substance that is the product of an excretion process that will be eliminated from the body. An excretion process is elimination by an organism of the waste products that arise as a result of metabolic activity.

label: negative regulation of cellular biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of substances, carried out by individual cells.

label: cadherin-5
Defs: A cadherin that is a translation product of the human CDH5 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: macromolecule localization
Defs: Any process in which a macromolecule is transported to, or maintained in, a specific location.

label: pancreas right lobe
Defs: A pancreatic lobule that is in_the_right_side_of a exocrine pancreas.

label: tendon sheath
Defs: A layer of membrane around a tendon. It has 2 layers: synovial sheath + fibrous tendon sheath.

label: vasculature of musculoskeletal system
Defs: A vasculature that is part of a musculoskeletal system [Automatically generated definition].

label: regulation of cell division
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the physical partitioning and separation of a cell into daughter cells.

label: organic molecular entity
Defs: Any molecular entity that contains carbon.

label: musculature of pelvic complex
Defs: Any collection of muscles that is part of a pelvic complex. The pelvic complex comprises the pelvic girdle and the associated limb or fin.

label: posterodistal orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed posterodistally.

label: cuticle of mesotibia
Defs: The cuticle of the segment of a mid leg attached to the distal margin of the mesofemur by the mesofemoro-mesotibial conjunctiva and to the proximal margin of the mesotarsus by the mesotibio-mesotarsal conjunctiva.

label: pointleted
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s terminating abruptly in a little point.

label: regulation of cellular amino acid metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving amino acids.

label: cellular quality
Defs: A monadic quality of continuant that exists at the cellular level of organisation.

label: noradrenergic cell
Defs: A cell capable of producting norepiniphrine. Norepiniphrine is a catecholamine with multiple roles including as a hormone and a neurotransmitter. In addition, epiniphrine is synthesized from norepiniphrine by the actions of the phenylethanolamine N-methyltransferase enzyme.

label: fallopian tube
Defs: Initial section of the oviduct through which the ova pass from the ovary to the uterus.

label: right cerebral hemisphere
Defs: A cerebral hemisphere that is in the right side of a brain.

label: neurotransmitter receptor activity
Defs: Combining with a neurotransmitter and transmitting the signal to initiate a change in cell activity.

label: muscle cell projection
Defs: A prolongation or process extending from a muscle cell. A muscle cell is a mature contractile cell, commonly known as a myocyte. This cell has as part of its cytoplasm myofibrils organized in various patterns.

label: smooth muscle layer in fatty layer of subcutaneous tissue
Defs: A smooth muscle tissue that is part of a hypodermis.

label: rectal lumen
Defs: An anatomical space that surrounded_by a rectum.

label: hairy
Defs: A pilosity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being covered with hair or hairlike projections.

label: in contact with
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s touching another entity.

label: protein kinase activator activity
Defs: Binds to and increases the activity of a protein kinase, an enzyme which phosphorylates a protein.

label: regulation of mononuclear cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mononuclear cell proliferation.

label: negative regulation of erythrocyte apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of erythrocyte apoptotic process.

label: sodium ion transport
Defs: The directed movement of sodium ions (Na+) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: splanchnic layer of lateral plate mesoderm
Defs: Layer of lateral plate mesoderm that forms the circulatory system and future gut wall - overlies endoderm[WP].
