label: negative regulation of protein localization to plasma membrane
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to plasma membrane.

label: regulation of collagen metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the metabolism of collagen, any of a group of fibrous proteins of very high tensile strength that form the main component of connective tissue in animals.

label: facial suture
Defs: Any suture between facial bones.

label: endo-epithelium
Defs: Epithelium that derives from the endoderm. Examples: urothelium, transitional epithelium of ureter, epithelium of prostatic gland.[FMA].

label: peptide catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of peptides, compounds of 2 or more (but usually less than 100) amino acids where the alpha carboxyl group of one is bound to the alpha amino group of another.

label: cerebral cortex glial cell
Defs: Glial cell of cerebral cortex.

label: regulation of exosomal secretion
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of exosomal secretion.

label: broad ligament of uterus
Defs: A broad fold of peritoneum that extends from the side of the uterus to the wall of the pelvis.

label: membrane organization
Defs: A process which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a membrane. A membrane is a double layer of lipid molecules that encloses all cells, and, in eukaryotes, many organelles; may be a single or double lipid bilayer; also includes associated proteins.

label: endometrial stroma
Defs: The layer of connective tissue comprised of the endometrial lining of the uterus which fluctuates in thickness throughout the menstrual cycle.

label: negative regulation of catabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of substances.

label: neural tube mantle layer
Defs: The layer of glia and differentiating neurons that forms as a second layer around the germinal neuroepithium; as this develops it comes to lie between the ventricular and marginal layers and includes the basal and alar plates. Develops into neurons and glia forming a gray matter layer.

label: blood plasma
Defs: The liquid component of blood, in which erythrocytes are suspended.

label: tryptaminium
Defs: An  ammonium ion that is the conjugate acid of tryptamine arising from protonation of the primary amino group; major species at pH 7.3.

label: demyelinated
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s loss of myelin sheath.

label: multi-organism reproductive process
Defs: A biological process that directly contributes to the process of producing new individuals, involving another organism.

label: negative regulation of iron ion transmembrane transport
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of iron ions from one side of a membrane to the other by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: metanepisternum
Defs: The anepisternum on the anterior region of the metapleuron and lateral to the metaventrite.

label: negative regulation of lymphocyte activation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of lymphocyte activation.

label: negative regulation of macrophage migration
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of macrophage migration.

label: dorsal to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located toward the back or upper surface of an organism relative to another entity.

label: leukocyte chemotaxis involved in inflammatory response
Defs: The movement of an immune cell in response to an external stimulus contributing to an inflammatory response.

label: negative regulation of synaptic transmission, cholinergic
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cholinergic synaptic transmission, the process of communication from a neuron to another neuron across a synapse using the neurotransmitter acetylcholine.

label: stomach glandular region mucosa
Defs: Stomach mucosa that is lined with glandular epithelium and part of a stomach glandular region.

label: negative regulation of smooth muscle contraction
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of smooth muscle contraction.

label: detoxification of inorganic compound
Defs: Any process that reduces or removes the toxicity of inorganic compounds. These include transport of such compounds away from sensitive areas and to compartments or complexes whose purpose is sequestration of inorganic compounds.

label: positive regulation of androgen secretion
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of androgen secretion.

label: localization within membrane
Defs: Any process in which a substance or cellular entity, such as a protein complex or organelle, is transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location within a membrane.

label: positive regulation of mesoderm formation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of mesoderm formation.

label: glossopharyngeal neural crest
Defs: Cranial neural crest which gives rise to the glossopharyngeal ganglion.

label: keratinocyte
Defs: An epidermal cell which synthesizes keratin and undergoes a characteristic change as it moves upward from the basal layers of the epidermis to the cornified (horny) layer of the skin. Successive stages of differentiation of the keratinocytes forming the epidermal layers are basal cell, spinous or prickle cell, and the granular cell.

label: sinusoidal space
Defs: An anatomical space that is enclosed by a sinusoid.

label: normal mass density
Defs: A density which is relatively normal or average.

label: amylose composition
Defs: A compositional quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s quantities or relative ratios of amylose of the inhering entity.

label: lipid catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of lipids, compounds soluble in an organic solvent but not, or sparingly, in an aqueous solvent.

label: biscupidate
Defs: A cuscpidate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer possessing two cusps.

label: gastric mucosal blood circulation
Defs: The flow of blood through the gastric mucosa of an animal, enabling the transport of nutrients and the removal of waste products.

label: artery
Defs: An epithelial tube or tree of tibes that transports blood away from the heart[modified from AEO definition].

label: acknowledgements section
Defs: Part of a publication that is about the contributions of people or institutions other than the authors.

label: pulmonary capillary endothelial cell
Defs: Any capillary endothelial cell that is part of a lung.

label: vitelline vasculature
Defs: Vascular network that is connected to the yolk sac.

label: positive regulation of vacuolar transport
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of vacuolar transport.

label: muscle of abdomen
Defs: Muscle (organ) which is a part of the abdomen. Examples: external oblique, rectus abdominis.

label: blastoderm cell
Defs: An undifferentiated cell produced by early cleavages of the fertilized egg (zygote).

label: negative regulation of granulocyte chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of granulocyte chemotaxis. Granulocyte chemotaxis is the movement of a granulocyte in response to an external stimulus.

label: equilateral triangular
Defs: A triangular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having all sides of the same length.

label: neurocranium bone
Defs: A bone that is part of a neurocranium [Automatically generated definition].

label: convex 3-D shape
Defs: A complete three dimensional shape in which for every line connecting pair of points on the object is within the object. Or: a shape lacking cavities. Contrast: concave.

label: scalloped
Defs: A surface feature shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having the border, edge, or outline cut into a series of segments of circles resembling a scallop-shell.

label: Purkinje myocyte differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized structural and/or functional features of a Purkinje myocyte (also known as cardiac Purkinje fiber cell). These cells are specialized cardiomyocytes that receive signals from the bundle of His and innervate the ventricular cardiac muscle.

label: pharyngeal arch mesenchymal region
Defs: A portion of mesenchymal tissue associated with an individual pharyngeal arch.

label: anterior tentorio-stipital muscle
Defs: The insect cranio-maxillar muscle that is attached to the tentorium and the stipital ridge.

label: pharynx morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the pharynx are generated and organized.

label: decreased osmolarity
Defs: A osmolarity which is relatively low.

label: transmembrane receptor protein tyrosine kinase signaling pathway
Defs: The series of molecular signals initiated by an extracellular ligand binding to a receptor on the surface of the target cell where the receptor possesses tyrosine kinase activity, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

label: partially ventralized
Defs: A ventralized quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s gross morphology containing what are normally ventral structures and missing some but not all of what are normally dorsal structures.

label: glycosaminoglycan metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving glycosaminoglycans, any of a group of polysaccharides that contain amino sugars.

label: vesicle-mediated transport to the plasma membrane
Defs: The directed movement of substances to the plasma membrane in transport vesicles that fuse with the plasma membrane by exocytosis.

label: homeostasis of number of cells within a tissue
Defs: Any biological process involved in the maintenance of the steady-state number of cells within a population of cells in a tissue.

label: collagen metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving collagen, any of a group of fibrous proteins of very high tensile strength that form the main component of connective tissue in animals. Collagen is highly enriched in glycine (some regions are 33% glycine) and proline, occurring predominantly as 3-hydroxyproline (about 20%).

label: intermediate mesoderm formation
Defs: The process that gives rise to the intermediate mesoderm. This process pertains to the initial formation of the structure from unspecified parts.

label: uterine lumen
Defs: An organ cavity that is part of a uterus.

label: telencephalon
Defs: Part of the forebrain consisting of paired olfactory bulbs and cerebral hemispheres.

label: negative regulation of retrograde axon cargo transport
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of retrograde axon cargo transport.

label: positive regulation of T cell chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of T cell chemotaxis. T cell chemotaxis is the directed movement of a T cell in response to an external stimulus.

label: color brightness
Defs: A scalar optical property that is the intensity, value or amount of perceived light.

label: bronchus morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the bronchus is generated and organized. The bronchus is the portion of the airway that connects to the lungs.

label: endophallus
Defs: The cuticular invagination of the postabdomen that is attached distally to the gonopore and basally to the aedeagus.

label: cell projection morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of a cell projection are generated and organized.

label: generated ontology module
Defs: An ontology module that is automatically generated, for example via a SPARQL query or via template and a CSV.

label: rhombomere cell migration
Defs: The movement of a cell within a rhombomere. This process is known to occur as an early step in the generation of anatomical structure from a rhombomere.

label: decreased efficacy
Defs: A decrease in the ability of a process to produce its output.

label: positive regulation of sclerotome development
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the progression of the sclerotome over time, from its initial formation to the mature structure. The sclerotome is the portion of the somite that will give rise to a vertebra.

label: epicardium of ventricle
Defs: An epicardial layer that lines a cardiac ventricle.

label: occurrence
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s occurrence.

label: hormone-mediated signaling pathway
Defs: The series of molecular signals mediated by the detection of a hormone.

label: insect cranial muscle
Defs: The somatic muscle that is attached to the head capsule.

label: cranial synchondrosis
Defs: The cartilaginous joints of the skull; these include sphenoethmoidal synchondrosis, sphenooccipital synchondrosis, sphenopetrosal synchondrosis, petrooccipital synchondrosis, anterior intraoccipital synchondrosis and posterior intraoccipital synchondrosis.

label: positive regulation of dendritic cell cytokine production
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of dendritic cell cytokine production.

label: antenniferal-scapal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the head capsule that connects the antennifer and the scapus.

label: inverted pyramidal neuron
Defs: A pyramidal neuron which has an apical tree which is oriented towards the white matter.

label: regulation of phosphate transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of phosphate transport. Phosphate transport is the directed movement of phosphate into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: dendritic cell homeostasis
Defs: The process of regulating the proliferation and elimination of dendritic cells such that the total number of dendritic cells within a whole or part of an organism is stable over time in the absence of an outside stimulus.

label: regulation of synapse assembly
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of synapse assembly, the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a synapse.

label: neuron projection bundle
Defs: A fasciculated bundle of neuron projections (GO:0043005), largely or completely lacking synapses.

label: post-embryonic notochord
Defs: A notochord that has persisted beyond the embryonic stage.

label: cell body
Defs: The portion of a cell bearing surface projections such as axons, dendrites, cilia, or flagella that includes the nucleus, but excludes all cell projections.

label: subdivision of skeletal system
Defs: Anatomical cluster consisting of the skeletal elements and articular elements that are part of an individual subdivision of the organism.

label: herniated into
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s bodily structure that has protruded through an abnormal opening in the wall that contains it into the surface or boundary of another entity.

label: occipital ridge
Defs: The ridge that runs along the posterior region of the head capsule.

label: mucous cell of stomach
Defs: A mucous cell in the epithelium of the stomach.

label: immaterial anatomical entity
Defs: An anatomical entity that has no mass.

label: positive regulation of exosomal secretion
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of exosomal secretion.

label: positive regulation of acetylcholine biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of acetylcholine biosynthetic process.

label: negative regulation of placenta blood vessel development
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of placenta blood vessel development.

label: parasympathetic ganglion
Defs: Ganglion containing neurons that receive innervation from parasympathetic neurons in the central nervous system and subserves parasympathetic functions through innervation of smooth muscle, cardiac muscle and glands.

label: oviduct smooth muscle
Defs: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a fallopian tube [Automatically generated definition].

label: pleuro-coxal muscle
Defs: The insect thoracic muscle that attaches to the pleuron and to a coxa.

label: blood vessel
Defs: A vessel through which blood circulates in the body.

label: regulation of cytoplasmic microtubule depolymerization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cytoplasmic microtubule depolymerization.

label: ovarian surface epithelial cell
Defs: Any epithelial cell that is part of a female gonad.

label: positive regulation of leukocyte chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of leukocyte chemotaxis.

label: neuroepithelial cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which epiblast cells acquire specialized features of neuroepithelial cells.

label: mesothelial cell of anterior chamber of eye
Defs: A mesothelial cell that is part of the anterior chamber of eyeball.

label: lack of fertility in offspring
Defs: A fertility quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to make its offspring sterile.

label: fractured
Defs: A broken quality where an entity is cracked or broken, usually a bone.

label: regulation of vascular associated smooth muscle cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of vascular smooth muscle cell differentiation.

label: energy derivation by oxidation of organic compounds
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways by which a cell derives energy from organic compounds; results in the oxidation of the compounds from which energy is released.

label: occipital bone
Defs: The bone at the lower, posterior part of the skull.

label: pink
Defs: Red color having medium to high brightness and low to moderate saturation.

label: positive regulation of hematopoietic progenitor cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of hematopoietic progenitor cell differentiation.

label: basophilic
Defs: An affinity inhering in an anatomical structure by virtue of the bearer exhibiting a molecular interaction for basic dyes under specific pH conditions.

label: mesothelial cell of small intestine
Defs: A mesothelial cell that is part of the small intestine.

label: negative regulation of neuron differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of neuron differentiation.

label: cell morphology
Defs: A quality of a single cell inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s size or shape or structure.

label: food packaging gas
Defs: A food additive that is a (generally inert) gas which is used to envelop foodstuffs during packing and so protect them from unwanted chemical reactions such as food spoilage or oxidation during subsequent transport and storage. The term includes propellant gases, used to expel foods from a container.

label: antero-lateral margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the antero-lateral region of the body or body part.

label: intestine smooth muscle contraction
Defs: A process in which force is generated within smooth muscle tissue, resulting in a change in muscle geometry. This process occurs in the intestine. Force generation involves a chemo-mechanical energy conversion step that is carried out by the actin/myosin complex activity, which generates force through ATP hydrolysis. The intestine is the section of the alimentary canal from the stomach to the anal canal. It includes the large intestine and small intestine.

label: negative regulation of brood size
Defs: Any process that decreases brood size. Brood size is the number of progeny that survive embryogenesis and are cared for at one time.

label: negative regulation of trophectodermal cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of trophectodermal cell proliferation.

label: extracellular vesicle biogenesis
Defs: The assembly and secretion a set of components to form an extracellular vesicule, a membrane-bounded vesicle that is released into the extracellular region. Extracellular vesicles include exosomes, microvesicles and apoptotic bodies, based on the mechanism by which they are released from cells and differentiated based on their size and content.

label: hepatic portal fibroblast
Defs: A fibroblast located in the portal triad. Hepatic portal fibroblast are a non-parenchymal cell population located adjacent to bile duct epithelia in liver and are distinct from stellate cells. They differentiate into fibrogenic myofibroblasts during chronic injury states producing high levels of collagen.

label: negative regulation of T cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of T cell differentiation.

label: hydropic
Defs: A structural quality which is held by a bearer when the latter exhibits an excessive accumulation of intracellular fluid.

label: melanosome assembly
Defs: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a melanosome, a tissue-specific, membrane-bounded cytoplasmic organelle within which melanin pigments are synthesized and stored.

label: transmembrane transport
Defs: The process in which a solute is transported across a lipid bilayer, from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: thoracic cavity artery
Defs: An artery that is part of a thoracic cavity[cjm].

label: mucosa of common hepatic duct
Defs: A mucosa that is part of a common hepatic duct [Automatically generated definition].

label: tissue morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of a tissue are generated and organized.

label: endocrine pancreas development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the endocrine pancreas over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The endocrine pancreas is made up of islet cells that produce insulin, glucagon and somatostatin.

label: composite particle
Defs: A subatomic particle known to have substructure (i.e. consisting of smaller particles).

label: hexose biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of hexose, any monosaccharide with a chain of six carbon atoms in the molecule.

label: positive regulation of somatostatin secretion
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, extent of the regulated release of somatostatin from secretory granules in the D cells of the pancreas.

label: cardiac conduction
Defs: Transfer of an organized electrical impulse across the heart to coordinate the contraction of cardiac muscles. The process begins with generation of an action potential (in the sinoatrial node (SA) in humans) and ends with a change in the rate, frequency, or extent of the contraction of the heart muscles.

label: negative regulation of cell proliferation in midbrain
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cell proliferation in midbrain.

label: endocardial cushion cell
Defs: A mesenchymal cell of the endocardial cushion.   These cells develop via an epithelial to mesenchymal transition when endocardial cells break cell-to-cell contacts and migrate into the cardiac jelly. Cells from this population form the heart septa and valves.

label: negative regulation of epithelial cell migration
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of epithelial cell migration.

label: cellular nitrogen compound catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of organic and inorganic nitrogenous compounds.

label: medial to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located toward the middle relative to another entity.

label: multi-cellular organismal disposition
Defs: A disposition inhering in a multi-cellular organism.

label: adjacent to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located near in space in relation to another entity.

label: indole skeleton
Defs: A mancude heterobicyclic organic group consisting of a benzene ring fused to a pyrrole ring.

label: glycoprotein transport
Defs: The directed movement of a glycoprotein, a protein that contains covalently bound glycose (i.e. monosaccharide) residues, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: apoptotic
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s consisting of blebbing of the nucleus and DNA fragmentation due to the cell undergoing a specific form of programmed cell death termed apoptosis.

label: regulation of myeloid dendritic cell chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of myeloid dendritic cell chemotaxis.

label: photoreceptor cell morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the structures of a photoreceptor cell are generated and organized. This process occurs while the initially relatively unspecialized cell is acquiring the specialized features of a photoreceptor cell, a sensory cell that reacts to the presence of light. An example of this is found in Drosophila melanogaster.

label: organonitrogen compound
Defs: Any heteroorganic entity containing at least one carbon-nitrogen bond.

label: postero-medial region
Defs: Anatomical region that overlaps the posterior and medial regions of the body or body part.

label: molecular quality
Defs: A quality which inheres in a molecular entity, a single molecule, atom, ion, radical etc.

label: somatostatin secretion
Defs: The regulated release of somatostatin from secretory granules in the D cells of the pancreas.

label: negative regulation of acetate catabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of acetate.

label: divergent from
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having two or more entities that extend from a common point in different directions.

label: future meninx
Defs: A developing mesenchymal capsule that covers the developing brain and spinal cord and is the precursor of the meningeal cluster. In mammals this gives rise to the arachnoid mater, pia mater and dura mater. In cyclostomes and fishes, the future meninx gives rise to a single meningeal layer, the primitive meninx.

label: increased viscosity
Defs: A viscosity which relatively high.

label: native cell
Defs: A cell that is found in a natural setting, which includes multicellular organism cells \'in vivo\' (i.e. part of an organism), and unicellular organisms \'in environment\' (i.e. part of a natural environment).

label: abdominal segment muscle
Defs: A muscle organ that is part of an abdominal segment of trunk [Automatically generated definition].

label: carbohydrate derivative
Defs: Any organooxygen compound derived from a carbohydrate by replacement of one or more hydroxy group(s) by an amino group, a thiol group or similar heteroatomic groups. The term also includes derivatives of these compounds.

label: skeletal muscle fibroblast
Defs: Any fibroblast that is part of skeletal muscle tissue.

label: pancreatic PP cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which relatively unspecialized cells acquire specialized structural and functional features of a pancreatic polypeptide-producing cell. A pancreatic polypeptide-producing cell is a cell in the pancreas that produces pancreatic polypeptide.

label: positive regulation of glycogen metabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving glycogen.

label: pancreatic acinar cell
Defs: A secretory cell found in pancreatic acini that secretes digestive enzymes and mucins. This cell is a typical zymogenic cell, have a basal nucleus and basophilic cytoplasm consisting of regular arrays of granular endoplasmic reticulum with mitochondria and dense secretory granules.

label: cellular phosphate ion homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of phosphate ions at the level of a cell.

label: endothelial cell of placenta
Defs: An endothelial cell that is part of a placenta.

label: decreased temperature
Defs: A temperature which is relatively low.

label: chromosome organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level that results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of chromosomes, structures composed of a very long molecule of DNA and associated proteins that carries hereditary information. This term covers covalent modifications at the molecular level as well as spatial relationships among the major components of a chromosome.

label: conjunctival fold
Defs: The cuticular depression constituted by conjunctiva that is elongated.

label: intestinal gland
Defs: A gland that is part of the intestinal mucosa. Examples include the intestinal crypts, duodenal gland[cjm].

label: nucleobase transport
Defs: The directed movement of a nucleobase, any nitrogenous base that is a constituent of a nucleoside, nucleotide, or nucleic acid, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: anion binding
Defs: Binding to an anion, a charged atom or group of atoms with a net negative charge.

label: dark purple
Defs: A color consisting of purple color and low brightness.

label: homeostatic
Defs: Pertaining to the ability or tendency of an organism or cell to maintain internal equilibrium by adjusting its physiological processes.

label: translation initiation ternary complex
Defs: A ribonucleoprotein complex that contains aminoacylated initiator methionine tRNA, GTP, and initiation factor 2 (either eIF2 in eukaryotes, or IF2 in prokaryotes). In prokaryotes, fMet-tRNA (initiator) is used rather than Met-tRNA (initiator).

label: media
Defs: The insect wing vein that is posterior to some radius and anterior to some cubitus.

label: aorta tunica media
Defs: The middle layer of the aorta wall, containing the smooth muscle layer and elastic fibers.

label: protein localization to cell junction
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a location within a cell junction.

label: negative regulation of cell development
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of the progression of the cell over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Cell development does not include the steps involved in committing a cell to a specific fate.

label: pelvic girdle region
Defs: The organism subdivision that includes the pelvic girdle skeleton and associated soft tissue. Note that this includes both the skeletal elements and associated tissues (integument, muscle, etc). Examples: There are only two instances in an organism, right and left pelvic girdle regions.

label: fat cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of an adipocyte, an animal connective tissue cell specialized for the synthesis and storage of fat.

label: positive regulation of inorganic anion transmembrane transport
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of inorganic anion transmembrane transport.

label: violet
Defs: A color hue with very low wavelength of that portion of the visible spectrum lying between reddish blue or bluish purple, evoked in the human observer by radiant energy with wavelengths of approximately 420 to 380 nanometers.

label: colon glandular cell
Defs: Glandular cell of colon epithelium. Example: Goblet cells; enterocytes or absorptive cells; enteroendocrine and M cells.

label: common dendritic progenitor
Defs: Common dendritic precursor is a hematopoietic progenitor cell that is CD117-low, CD135-positive, CD115-positive and lacks plasma membrane parts for hematopoietic lineage markers.

label: obsolete increased consumption
Defs: A consumption which is relatively high.

label: enteroendocrine cell of anorectum
Defs: An enteroendocrine cell that is located in the anorectum.

label: tendon sheath development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a tendon sheath over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A tendon sheath is a layer of membrane around a tendon. It permits the tendon to move.

label: monstrous
Defs: A malformed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s all-encompassing, grotesque morphological defects.

label: fat cell proliferation
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of fat cells by cell division, resulting in the expansion of their population. A fat cell is an animal connective tissue cell specialized for the synthesis and storage of fat.

label: confluent with
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer flowing or coming together with another entity.

label: negative regulation of cardiac muscle adaptation
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, extent or frequency of the process in which cardiac muscle adapts, with consequent modifications to structural and/or functional phenotypes, in response to a stimulus. Stimuli include contractile activity, loading conditions, substrate supply, and environmental factors.

label: lateral to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located toward the side relative to another entity.

label: sinoatrial node
Defs: The part of the cardiac conduction system that controls the timing of heart muscle contraction. It relays electrical signals to the AV node[GO]. Subdivision of conducting system of heart at the junction of the right atrium and the superior vena cava, around the sinoatrial nodal branch of right coronary artery and is continuous with the internodal tract[FMA].

label: alkaloid catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of alkaloids, nitrogen containing natural products not otherwise classified as peptides, nonprotein amino acids, amines, cyanogenic glycosides, glucosinolates, cofactors, phytohormones or primary metabolites (such as purine or pyrimidine bases).

label: prism shaped
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling a prism.

label: mitotic nuclear division
Defs: A mitotic cell cycle process comprising the steps by which the nucleus of a eukaryotic cell divides; the process involves condensation of chromosomal DNA into a highly compacted form. Canonically, mitosis produces two daughter nuclei whose chromosome complement is identical to that of the mother cell.

label: semicircular
Defs: A 2-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having shape or form of half a circle.

label: software script
Defs: A software script is software whose instructions can be executed using a software interpreter.

label: plasma membrane protein complex
Defs: Any protein complex that is part of the plasma membrane.

label: positive regulation of T cell antigen processing and presentation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of T cell antigen processing and presentation.

label: regulation of dendritic spine development
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of dendritic spine development, the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the dendritic spine over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: fossorial
Defs: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s morphological and physiological adaptation for digging and living underground.

label: positive regulation of Schwann cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of Schwann cell differentiation.

label: cuticle of hind wing
Defs: The cuticle of the paired insect wing that is continuous with the metanotum.

label: sequentially ordered entity
Defs: Any entity that is ordered in discrete units along a linear axis.

label: normal male fertility
Defs: A male fertility which is relatively normal or average.

label: norepinephrine catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of norepinephrine, a hormone secreted by the adrenal medulla, and a neurotransmitter in the sympathetic peripheral nervous system and in some tracts in the central nervous system. It is also the demethylated biosynthetic precursor of epinephrine.

label: abbreviation textual entity
Defs: A textual entity listing abbreviations and their expansions that are used in a document.

label: bilirubin IXalpha
Defs: A member of the class of  biladienes that is a linear tetrapyrrole with the dipyrrole units being of both exovinyl and endovinyl type. A product of heme degradation, it is produced in the reticuloendothelial system by the reduction of biliverdin and transported to the liver as a complex with serum albumin.

label: mucosa of biliary tree
Defs: A mucosa that is part of a biliary tree [Automatically generated definition].

label: F mating type
Defs: A bacterial mating type indicating the presence of F plasmid in a bacterial cell.

label: abdominal sternite VI-abdominal sternite VII conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect abdomen that connects the abdominal sternite VI and the abdominal sternite VII.

label: regulation of peptide transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of peptides, compounds of two or more amino acids where the alpha carboxyl group of one is bound to the alpha amino group of another, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: myeloid cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in a myeloid cell, a cell of the monocyte, granulocyte, mast cell, megakaryocyte, or erythroid lineage.

label: germ cell development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an immature germ cell over time, from its formation to the mature structure (gamete). A germ cell is any reproductive cell in a multicellular organism.

label: T cell cytokine production
Defs: Any process that contributes to cytokine production by a T cell.

label: punctate
Defs: A pattern inhering in a surface by virtue of the bearer\'s being marked by the presence of dots, punctures, points or pits.

label: uniparental disomy
Defs: A disomy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing two copies of the chromosome from one of the parents (with no contribution from the other parent).

label: bridge ontology module
Defs: An ontology module that consists entirely of axioms that connect or bridge two distinct ontology modules. For example, the Uberon-to-ZFA bridge module.

label: ciliary basal body-plasma membrane docking
Defs: The docking of a cytosolic centriole/basal body to the plasma membrane via the ciliary transition fibers. In some species this may happen via an intermediate step, by first docking to the ciliary vesicle via the ciliary transition fibers. The basal body-ciliary vesicle then relocates to the plasma membrane, followed by the ciliary vesicle fusing with the plasma membrane, effectively attaching the basal body to the plasma membrane.

label: incomplete structure
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking parts or having a reduced form compared to fully formed entities.

label: heterodetic cyclic peptide
Defs: A heterodetic cyclic peptide is a peptide consisting only of amino-acid residues, but in which the linkages forming the ring are not solely peptide bonds; one or more is an isopeptide, disulfide, ester, or other bond.

label: positive regulation of presynapse assembly
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of presynapse assembly.

label: extracellular matrix assembly
Defs: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of the extracellular matrix.

label: bilaterally paired
Defs: The bearer of this quality has_part n=2 of the indicated entity type, where n is unpaired for a comparable organism.

label: endomitotic cell cycle
Defs: A mitotic cell cycle in which chromosomes are replicated and sister chromatids separate, but spindle formation, nuclear membrane breakdown and nuclear division do not occur, resulting in an increased number of chromosomes in the cell.

label: increased sensitivity of a process to oxygen
Defs: A sensitivity of occurrent to oxygen which is higher than normal or average.

label: pelvic region element
Defs: An organ or element that is part of the pelvic region. Examples: reproductive organs (in some organisms), urinary bladder, bones of the pelvis.

label: obsolete post-mortem
Defs: The period after death of the organism.

label: flux
Defs: A physical quality that exists by virtue of the rate of flow of the bearer across a given surface.

label: stem cell factor receptor binding
Defs: Binding to a stem cell factor receptor (SCFR), a type III transmembrane kinase receptor.

label: skin of abdomen
Defs: A zone of skin that is part of an abdomen [Automatically generated definition].

label: pharyngeal arch artery 6
Defs: The vessels formed within the sixth pair of branchial arches in embryogenesis.

label: negative regulation of endothelial cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of endothelial cell apoptotic process.

label: T cell homeostasis
Defs: The process of regulating the proliferation and elimination of T cells such that the total number of T cells within a whole or part of an organism is stable over time in the absence of an outside stimulus.

label: diamond shaped
Defs: A superelliptic shape inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s shape resembling a diamond.

label: positive regulation of intracellular signal transduction
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of intracellular signal transduction.

label: cell junction organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a cell junction. A cell junction is a specialized region of connection between two cells or between a cell and the extracellular matrix.

label: external genitalia morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the external genitalia are generated and organized. The external genitalia are the outer sex organs, such as the penis or vulva in mammals.

label: presynaptic cytoskeleton
Defs: The portion of the cytoskeleton contained within the presynapse.

label: hormone secretion
Defs: The regulated release of hormones, substances with a specific regulatory effect on a particular organ or group of cells.

label: basal wing conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the pterothorax that surrounds the wing.

label: hematopoietic progenitor cell antigen CD34 (mouse)
Defs: A CD34 molecule that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: vein of abdomen
Defs: A vein that is part of a abdomen.

label: anepisternum
Defs: The dorsal region of the episternum that is dorsal to the anapleural sulcus.

label: abdominal segment blood vessel
Defs: A blood vessel that is part of an abdominal segment of trunk [Automatically generated definition].

label: hypoglossal nerve maturation
Defs: A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for the hypoglossal nerve to attain its fully functional state. This motor nerve innervates all the intrinsic and all but one of the extrinsic muscles of the tongue.

label: T cell antigen processing and presentation
Defs: The process in which a T cell expresses antigen (peptide or lipid) on its cell surface in association with an MHC protein complex.

label: posteriorly rotated
Defs: A rotation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of being rotated towards the rear of organism.

label: regulation of fat cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of fat cell apoptotic process.

label: hormone
Defs: Originally referring to an endogenous compound that is formed in specialized organ or group of cells and carried to another organ or group of cells, in the same organism, upon which it has a specific regulatory function, the term is now commonly used to include non-endogenous, semi-synthetic and fully synthetic analogues of such compounds.

label: regulation of cilium assembly
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cilium assembly.

label: foramen for glossopharyngeal nerve
Defs: Foramen that allows the passge of the glossopharyngeal nerve (cranial nerve IX).

label: mammalian metabolite
Defs: Any animal metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in mammals.

label: left cardiac chamber
Defs: Any chamber of the left side of the heart.

label: east
Defs: East is one of the four cardinal directions or points of the compass. It is the opposite direction from west.

label: transition element molecular entity
Defs: A molecular entity containing one or more atoms of a transition element.

label: G protein-coupled peptide receptor activity
Defs: Combining with a peptide and transmitting the signal across the membrane by activating an associated G-protein; promotes the exchange of GDP for GTP on the alpha subunit of a heterotrimeric G-protein complex.

label: cell communication
Defs: Any process that mediates interactions between a cell and its surroundings. Encompasses interactions such as signaling or attachment between one cell and another cell, between a cell and an extracellular matrix, or between a cell and any other aspect of its environment.

label: split radially
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being split along the radial axis.

label: arched
Defs: A concave quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s forming or resembling an arch.

label: viability
Defs: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer or a population by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to survive and develop normally or the number of surviving individuals in a given population.

label: regulation of morphogenesis of an epithelium
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of morphogenesis of an epithelium.

label: somitogenesis
Defs: The formation of mesodermal clusters that are arranged segmentally along the anterior posterior axis of an embryo.

label: signaling receptor regulator activity
Defs: Binds to and modulates the activity of a receptor.

label: muscle precursor cell
Defs: A non-terminally differentiated cell that is capable of developing into a muscle cell.

label: acidic amino acid transport
Defs: The directed movement of acidic amino acids, amino acids with a pH below 7, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: upper digestive tract
Defs: The region of the digestive tract extending from the mouth cavity through pharynx esophagus stomach and duodenum.

label: trivalent inorganic anion
Defs: Any inorganic anion with a valency of three.

label: lateral scapo-pedicellar muscle
Defs: The cranio-antennal muscle that is attached to the dorsal or dorsolateral regions of the scapus and the lateral or dorsolateral regions of the pedicellus.

label: curled
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having parallel chains in undulate fashion on the border.

label: statistical analysis section
Defs: A part of the document used to describe the statistical methodologies employed in the work presented in the document.

label: dense connective tissue
Defs: Dense connective tissue is mainly composed of collagen type I. Crowded between the collagen fibers are rows of fibroblasts, fiber-forming cells, that manufacture the fibers. Dense connective tissue forms strong, rope-like structures such as tendons and ligaments. Tendons attach skeletal muscles to bones; ligaments connect bones to bones at joints. Ligaments are more stretchy and contain more elastic fibers than tendons. Dense connective tissue also make up the lower layers of the skin (dermis), where it is arranged in sheets.

label: lethal (sensu genetics)
Defs: A viability quality inhering in a population by virtue of the bearer\'s long term survival inability.

label: alpha-(1,3)-fucosyltransferase 4 (mouse)
Defs: An alpha-(1,3)-fucosyltransferase 4 that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: macrophage apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in a macrophage, a mononuclear phagocyte present in a variety of tissues.

label: receptor complex
Defs: Any protein complex that undergoes combination with a hormone, neurotransmitter, drug or intracellular messenger to initiate a change in cell function.

label: biliary tree
Defs: A complex network of conduits that begins with the canals of Hering (intralobar bile duct) and progressively merges into a system of interlobular, septal, and major ducts which then coalesce to form the extrahepatic bile ducts, which finally deliver bile to the intestine, and in some species to the gallbladder.

label: increased proportionality to
Defs: A proportionality quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s increased magnitude in respect to a related entity.

label: decussate
Defs: A pattern quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s consisting of paired parts that alternately cross each other.

label: endothelial cell chemotaxis
Defs: The directed movement of an endothelial cell guided by a specific chemical concentration gradient. Movement may be towards a higher concentration (positive chemotaxis) or towards a lower concentration (negative chemotaxis).

label: insect wing region
Defs: The region of cuticle of the insect wing that contains wing veins, folds, and conjunctiva.

label: luminance
Defs: A quality that exists by virtue of the luminous intensity per unit area projected in a given direction.

label: heart capillary growth
Defs: The increase in heart capillaries that accompanies physiological hypertrophy of cardiac muscle.

label: neuron projection quality
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a neuron by virtue of the relative location of its soma and the regions to which it projects and makes synaptic contacts in.

label: positive regulation of bone remodeling
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of bone remodeling.

label: trigeminal nerve morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structure of the trigeminal nerve is generated and organized. The trigeminal nerve is composed of three large branches. They are the ophthalmic (V1, sensory), maxillary (V2, sensory) and mandibular (V3, motor and sensory) branches. The sensory ophthalmic branch travels through the superior orbital fissure and passes through the orbit to reach the skin of the forehead and top of the head. The maxillary nerve contains sensory branches that reach the pterygopalatine fossa via the inferior orbital fissure (face, cheek and upper teeth) and pterygopalatine canal (soft and hard palate, nasal cavity and pharynx). The motor part of the mandibular branch is distributed to the muscles of mastication, the mylohyoid muscle and the anterior belly of the digastric. The mandibular nerve also innervates the tensor veli palatini and tensor tympani muscles. The sensory part of the mandibular nerve is composed of branches that carry general sensory information from the mucous membranes of the mouth and cheek, anterior two-thirds of the tongue, lower teeth, skin of the lower jaw, side of the head and scalp and meninges of the anterior and middle cranial fossae.

label: regulation of protein localization to cell periphery
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to cell periphery.

label: positive regulation of pro-T cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of pro-T cell differentiation.

label: catalytic activity
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a catalyst by virtue of the amount of the catalyst\'s action.

label: conclusion textual entity
Defs: A textual entity that expresses the results of reasoning about a problem, for instance as typically found towards the end of scientific papers.

label: outer membrane
Defs: The external membrane of Gram-negative bacteria or certain organelles such as mitochondria and chloroplasts; freely permeable to most ions and metabolites.

label: normal sensitivity to irradiation
Defs: A sensitivity to irradiation which is relatively normal or average

label: cloacal epithelium
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a cloaca.

label: anatomical side
Defs: An anatomical region bounded by a plane perpendicular to an axis through the middle.

label: lacks parts or has fewer parts of type
Defs: The bearer of this quality has_part < n of the indicated entity type, where n is the normal amount for a comparable organism. Note that the bearer of the quality is the whole, not the part. Formally: If a bearer entity e has fewer parts of type X at time t, then the number of instances x of X at t such that x part_of e is < n, where n is either the normal number for comparable entities, or n is stated explicitly. This case includes the limit case, where the bearer lacks all parts of the specified type.

label: regulation of leukocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of leukocyte differentiation.

label: neurotransmitter agent
Defs: A substance used for its pharmacological action on any aspect of neurotransmitter systems. Neurotransmitter agents include agonists, antagonists, degradation inhibitors, uptake inhibitors, depleters, precursors, and modulators of receptor function.

label: monocyte activation
Defs: The change in morphology and behavior of a monocyte resulting from exposure to a cytokine, chemokine, cellular ligand, or soluble factor.

label: blood vessel smooth muscle
Defs: Smooth muscle found within, and composing the majority of the wall of blood vessels.

label: sequence bearer
Defs: Any entity that can be divided into parts such that each part is an atomical unit of a sequence

label: preabdomen
Defs: The region of cuticle of the insect abdomen that is posteriorly connected to the postabdomen.

label: polysaccharide biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a polysaccharide, a polymer of many (typically more than 10) monosaccharide residues linked glycosidically.

label: cuticular tubercle
Defs: The cuticular protrusion of a sclerite that is rounded (circular).

label: serosa of duodenum
Defs: A serous membrane that is part of a duodenum [Automatically generated definition].

label: positive regulation of protein polymerization
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the process of creating protein polymers.

label: cofactor
Defs: An organic molecule or ion (usually a metal ion) that is required by an enzyme for its activity. It may be attached either loosely (coenzyme) or tightly (prosthetic group).

label: polysaccharide derivative
Defs: A carbohydrate derivative that is any derivative of a polysaccharide.

label: composition
Defs: A single physical entity inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s quantities or relative ratios of subparts.

label: positive regulation of phosphate metabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving phosphates.

label: mislocalised medially
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being positioned towards the middle of an organism.

label: increased age
Defs: An age which is high relative to the normal or average.

label: superior salivary nucleus development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the superior salivary nucleus over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: adduction
Defs: A displaced angular placement quality inhering in a body part by virtue of the bearer\'s movement closer the medial plane of the body.

label: regulation of production of molecular mediator of immune response
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of the production of molecular mediator of immune response.

label: uncus
Defs: The spine on the distal margin of the tibia.

label: positive regulation of cellular catabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of substances, carried out by individual cells.

label: regulation of protein binding
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein binding.

label: protein localization to cell-cell junction
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained, in a location within a cell-cell junction.

label: cuticle of metatrochanter
Defs: The cuticle of the segment of a hind leg attached to the distal margin of the metacoxa by the metacoxal-metatrochanteral conjunctiva and to the proximal margin of the metafemur by the metatrochantero-metafemoral conjunctiva.

label: regulation of fibroblast migration
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of fibroblast cell migration. Fibroblast cell migration is accomplished by extension and retraction of a pseudopodium.

label: regulation of epithelial cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of epithelial cell proliferation.

label: retina blood vessel
Defs: A blood vessel that is part of a retina [Automatically generated definition].

label: endoderm
Defs: Primary germ layer that lies remote from the surface of the embryo and gives rise to internal tissues such as gut.

label: auxotrophic
Defs: A nutritional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s inability to synthesize a particular organic compound required for its growth.

label: integral component of pigment granule membrane
Defs: The component of the pigment granule membrane consisting of the gene products and protein complexes having at least some part of their peptide sequence embedded in the hydrophobic region of the membrane.

label: regulation of neural retina development
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of neural retina development, the progression of the neural retina over time from its initial formation to the mature structure. The neural retina is the part of the retina that contains neurons and photoreceptor cells.

label: myeloid progenitor cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a precursor cell type acquires the specialized features of a myeloid progenitor cell. Myeloid progenitor cells include progenitor cells for any of the myeloid lineages.

label: normal female fertility
Defs: A female fertility which is relatively normal or average.

label: decreased distance
Defs: A distance which is lesser relative to the normal or average.

label: dendritic tree
Defs: The entire complement of dendrites for a neuron, consisting of each primary dendrite and all its branches.

label: microtubule-based process
Defs: Any cellular process that depends upon or alters the microtubule cytoskeleton, that part of the cytoskeleton comprising microtubules and their associated proteins.

label: bang sensitive
Defs: A behavioral quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting paralytic behaviour when subjected to mechanical shock.

label: negative regulation of macrophage differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of macrophage differentiation.

label: regulation of acetylcholine uptake
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of the neurotransmitter acetylcholine into a cell.

label: arterial system
Defs: The part of the cardiovascular system consisting of all arteries.

label: bronchus cartilage morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the bronchus cartilage is generated and organized. The bronchus cartilage is the connective tissue of the portion of the airway that connects to the lungs.

label: left internal carotid artery
Defs: An internal carotid artery that branching_part_of a left common carotid artery plus branches.

label: asymmetric cell division
Defs: The asymmetric division of cells to produce two daughter cells with different developmental potentials. It is of fundamental significance for the generation of cell diversity.

label: respiratory tract
Defs: Anatomical structure that is part of the respiratory system. In mammals consists of upper and lower tracts.

label: type B pancreatic cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which relatively unspecialized cells acquire specialized structural and/or functional features of a type B pancreatic cell. A type B pancreatic cell is a cell located towards center of the islets of Langerhans that secretes insulin.

label: ribosome localization
Defs: A process in which a ribosome is transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location.

label: complexity
Defs: A monadic quality of continuant inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being intricate and compounded.

label: marbled
Defs: Multicolored quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being colored with a variegated pattern resembling marble,.

label: asymmetric stem cell division
Defs: Division of a stem cell during which it retains its identity and buds off a daughter cell with a new identity.

label: aerobic
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s dependence on oxygen.

label: photograph
Defs: A photograph is created by projecting an image onto a photosensitive surface such as a chemically treated plate or film, CCD receptor, etc.

label: pericardial cavity
Defs: A potential space between the visceral and parietal layers of the pericardium.

label: negative regulation of small molecule metabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of a small molecule metabolic process.

label: concavo-convex
Defs: A shape quality that obtains by virtue of the bearer being concave on one side and convex on the other.

label: mucous acinus
Defs: The secretory unit of a mucous gland. The acinar portion is composed of mucous secreting cells.

label: anapleural sulcus
Defs: The sulcus of the pleuron delimiting the dorsal region of the preepisternum and the ventral region of the anepisternum.

label: acetate
Defs: A monocarboxylic acid anion resulting from the removal of a proton from the carboxy group of acetic acid.

label: placental blood
Defs: Blood located in the placenta.

label: dislocated
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being out of its usual or proper place, or position.

label: sulfate
Defs: A sulfur oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of both OH groups of sulfuric acid.

label: cuticle of empodium
Defs: The cuticular protrusion that is part of the pretarsus, ventral to the tarsal claws.

label: negative regulation of insulin secretion
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of insulin.

label: positive regulation of response to external stimulus
Defs: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the rate of a response to an external stimulus.

label: macrophage
Defs: A mononuclear phagocyte present in variety of tissues, typically differentiated from monocytes, capable of phagocytosing a variety of extracellular particulate material, including immune complexes, microorganisms, and dead cells.

label: enzyme activator activity
Defs: Binds to and increases the activity of an enzyme.

label: sclerotome
Defs: Ventral somitic compartment that is a precursor of the axial skeleton[XAO]. Sclerotomes eventually differentiate into the vertebrae and most of the skull. The caudal (posterior) half of one sclerotome fuses with the rostral (anterior) half of the adjacent one to form each vertebra. From their initial location within the somite, the sclerotome cells migrate medially towards the notochord. These cells meet the sclerotome cells from the other side to form the vertebral body. From this vertebral body, sclerotome cells move dorsally and surround the developing spinal cord, forming the vertebral arch[WP].

label: mesoderm-derived structure
Defs: An anatomical structure that develops (entirely or partially) from the mesoderm.

label: cathepsin-like protease
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of some metazoan gene that encodes a signal peptide followed by a single Cathepsin propeptide inhibitor domain (Pfam:PF08246) followed by a single Papain family cysteine protease (Pfam:PF00112) domain at the C terminus.

label: neoplastic
Defs: A structural quality which is held by a bearer when the latter\'s disposition the presence of abnormally proliferating masses of cells.

label: liver parenchyma
Defs: The functional units of the liver including the lobules.

label: ventral longitudinal abdominal muscle
Defs: The insect abdominal muscle that runs along the ventral region, parallel to the anterior-posterior axis.

label: regulation of asymmetric cell division
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of asymmetric cell division.

label: immunoglobulin gamma Fc receptor II/III/IV
Defs: A protein with a core domain architecture consisting of an extracellular domain containing two copies of the Immunoglobulin domain (Pfam:PF00047), followed by a single-pass transmembrane region and a small intracellular domain. The active protein is a low affinity receptor for immunoglobulin gamma chain Fc region. Human II-a, II-b, and II-c represent a recent gene expansion and are equally related to mouse II, III, and IV. Human III-A and III-B are closely related and closer to mouse IV than to mouse III.

label: radial plane
Defs: Anatomical plane that follows the two dimensions specified by an apical-basal axis relative to direction of growth and a medial-lateral axis.

label: distal margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the distal side of the body or body part.

label: brochidodromous
Defs: A branched quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having secondary branches joined together in a series of prominent arches.

label: epicardium
Defs: A region of the serous membrane that forms the innermost layer of the pericardium and the outer surface of the heart.

label: cavity of bone organ
Defs: An organ cavity that surrounded_by a bone.

label: craniocervical region musculature
Defs: Musculature system of the pharyngeal and head regions.

label: subrectangular
Defs: A quadrangular shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being approximately rectangular.

label: behavior
Defs: The internally coordinated responses (actions or inactions) of animals (individuals or groups) to internal or external stimuli, via a mechanism that involves nervous system activity.

label: larynx connective tissue
Defs: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a larynx [Automatically generated definition].

label: trachea submucosa development
Defs: The progression of the trachea submucosa over time from its formation to the mature structure. The trachea submucosa is made up of the glands and elastic tissue that lie under the mucosa in the trachea.

label: pharyngeal arch 4
Defs: Contributes to development of the cartilage of the larynx, laryngeal, pharyngeal, and soft palate muscles, superior parathyroid gland, and C-cells of the thymus.

label: positive regulation of Schwann cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that increases the frequency or rate of the multiplication or reproduction of Schwann cells, resulting in the expansion of their population. Schwann cells are a type of glial cell in the peripheral nervous system.

label: increased tendency
Defs: A tendency which is relatively high.

label: negative regulation of collagen fibril organization
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of collagen fibril organization.

label: flexibility
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to being turned, bowed, or twisted without breaking.

label: subdivision of oviduct
Defs: A section through the tube or network of tubes that connects the ovaries to the outside of the body.

label: negative regulation of skeletal muscle fiber differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of skeletal muscle fiber differentiation.

label: dark blue
Defs: A color consisting of blue hue and low brightness.

label: DNA packaging complex
Defs: A protein complex that plays a role in the process of DNA packaging.

label: cellular macromolecule metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving macromolecules, any molecule of high relative molecular mass, the structure of which essentially comprises the multiple repetition of units derived, actually or conceptually, from molecules of low relative molecular mass, as carried out by individual cells.

label: lumen of epithelial sac
Defs: The space within an epithelial sphere.

label: insect wing fold
Defs: The region of cuticle of the insect wing that is more flexible than the wing conjunctiva.

label: positive regulation of cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cell differentiation.

label: negative regulation of gluconeogenesis
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of gluconeogenesis.

label: axonemal microtubule depolymerization
Defs: The removal of tubulin heterodimers from one or both ends of an axonemal microtubule. An axonemal microtubule is a microtubule in the axoneme of a cilium or flagellum; an axoneme contains nine modified doublet microtubules surrounding a pair of single microtubules.

label: cell death
Defs: Any biological process that results in permanent cessation of all vital functions of a cell. A cell should be considered dead when any one of the following molecular or morphological criteria is met: (1) the cell has lost the integrity of its plasma membrane; (2) the cell, including its nucleus, has undergone complete fragmentation into discrete bodies (frequently referred to as apoptotic bodies). The cell corpse (or its fragments) may be engulfed by an adjacent cell in vivo, but engulfment of whole cells should not be considered a strict criteria to define cell death as, under some circumstances, live engulfed cells can be released from phagosomes (see PMID:18045538).

label: regulation of neuron projection development
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of neuron projection development. Neuron projection development is the process whose specific outcome is the progression of a neuron projection over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A neuron projection is any process extending from a neural cell, such as axons or dendrites (collectively called neurites).

label: mesentery of hindgut
Defs: A mesentery that is part of a hindgut [Automatically generated definition].

label: increased odor
Defs: An odor quality of having increased odor.

label: saturated yellow
Defs: A color consisting of yellow hue and high saturation.

label: notes section
Defs: A part of a document containing typically short notes about the document itself and/or the authors. Often the notes section contains subsections related to funding, competing interests, ethical approval, etc.

label: protein catabolic process at synapse
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a protein at a synapse.

label: septum transversum
Defs: A thick plate of mesodermal tissue that occupies the space between the thoracic cavity and yolk stalk in the early embryo, forming a transverse partition partially separating the coelomic cavity into thoracic and abdominal portions. It gives rise to the central tendon of the diaphragm[VHOG].

label: immune response
Defs: Any immune system process that functions in the calibrated response of an organism to a potential internal or invasive threat.

label: radial glia-guided pyramidal neuron migration
Defs: The radial migration of a pyramidal neuron along radial glial cells.

label: regulation of immune system process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of an immune system process.

label: negative regulation of bleb assembly
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of bleb assembly.

label: decreased tonicity
Defs: A tonicity which is relatively low.

label: neuroendocrine gland
Defs: Any of the organized aggregations of cells that function as secretory or excretory organs and that release hormones in response to neural stimuli.

label: pattern recognition receptor activity
Defs: Combining with a pathogen-associated molecular pattern (PAMP), a structure conserved among microbial species to initiate an innate immune response.

label: parallelogram
Defs:
A convex quadrilateral is a parallelogram if and only if any one of the following statements are true:
1. Each diagonal divides the quadrilateral into two congruent triangles with the same orientation.
2. The opposite sides are congruent in pairs.
3. The diagonals bisect each other.
4. The opposite angles are congruent in pairs.
5. The sum of the squares of the sides equals the sum of the squares of the diagonals. (This is the parallelogram law)
6.It possesses rotational symmetry.
7.One pair of opposite sides are parallel and congruent.
8.Two pairs of adjacent angles are supplementary.

label: hyoid arch skeleton
Defs: A subdivision of skeleton that supports pharyngeal arch 2.

label: transitional myocyte
Defs: Specialized cardiac myocyte which is in the internodal tract and atrioventricular node. The cell is more slender than ordinary atrial myocytes and has more myofibrils than nodal myocytes.

label: insensitive toward
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking sensitivity toward an external stimulus.

label: pelvic complex muscle
Defs: Muscles of the pelvic girdle, hindlimb or pelvic fin.

label: glucagon
Defs: A 29-amino acid peptide hormone consisting of His, Ser, Gln, Gly, Thr, Phe, Thr, Ser, Asp, Tyr, Ser, Lys, Tyr, Leu, Asp, Ser, Arg, Arg, Ala, Gln, Asp, Phe, Val, Gln, Trp, Leu, Met, Asn and Thr residues joined in sequence.

label: mild increased temperature
Defs: A temperature which is increased by a low degree.

label: central nervous system neuron
Defs: Any neuron that is part of a central nervous system.

label: pectoral appendage
Defs: Paired appendage that consists of the anterior appendicular skeleton and associated soft and hard tissues, but excludes the pectoral girdle and its associated soft and hard tissues.

label: axon cytoplasm
Defs: Any cytoplasm that is part of a axon.

label: phragma
Defs: The internal apodeme that is continuous with the cuticle of the notum and is attached to a dorsal longitudinal muscle.

label: lipid transporter activity
Defs: Enables the directed movement of lipids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells.

label: positive regulation of cardiac muscle cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that increases the rate or extent of cardiac cell apoptotic process, a form of programmed cell death induced by external or internal signals that trigger the activity of proteolytic caspases whose actions dismantle a cardiac muscle cell and result in its death.

label: hyaluronan catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of hyaluronan, the naturally occurring anionic form of hyaluronic acid, any member of a group of glycosaminoglycans, the repeat units of which consist of beta-1,4 linked D-glucuronyl-beta-(1,3)-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine.

label: cardiac muscle cell
Defs: Cardiac muscle cells are striated muscle cells that are responsible for heart contraction. In mammals, the contractile fiber resembles those of skeletal muscle but are only one third as large in diameter, are richer in sarcoplasm, and contain centrally located instead of peripheral nuclei.

label: ciliary plasm
Defs: All of the contents of a cilium, excluding the plasma membrane surrounding the cilium.

label: integral component of nuclear outer membrane
Defs: The component of the nuclear outer membrane consisting of the gene products having at least some part of their peptide sequence embedded in the hydrophobic region of the membrane.

label: pleuroperitoneal canal
Defs: Each of the canals that links the peritoneal cavity and the caudal part of a pleural cavity.

label: transversely striated visceral muscle cell
Defs: A visceral muscle that is transversely striated.  Examples include the visceral muscle cells of arthropods.

label: positive regulation of myotube differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of myotube differentiation. Myotube differentiation is the process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a myotube cell. Myotubes are multinucleated cells that are formed when proliferating myoblasts exit the cell cycle, differentiate and fuse.

label: animal organ formation
Defs: The process pertaining to the initial formation of an animal organ from unspecified parts. The process begins with the specific processes that contribute to the appearance of the discrete structure, such as inductive events, and ends when the structural rudiment of the organ is recognizable, such as a condensation of mesenchymal cells into the organ rudiment. Organs are a natural part or structure in an animal or a plant, capable of performing some special action (termed its function), which is essential to the life or well-being of the whole. The heart and lungs are organs of animals, and the petal and leaf are organs of plants. In animals the organs are generally made up of several tissues, one of which usually predominates, and determines the principal function of the organ.

label: urokinase plasminogen activator surface receptor (mouse)
Defs: A urokinase plasminogen activator surface receptor that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: peptide biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of peptides, compounds of 2 or more (but usually less than 100) amino acids where the alpha carboxyl group of one is bound to the alpha amino group of another. This may include the translation of a precursor protein and its subsequent processing into a functional peptide.

label: positive regulation of leukocyte cell-cell adhesion
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of leukocyte cell-cell adhesion.

label: tissue-resident macrophage
