Defs: A macrophage constitutively resident in a particular tissue under non-inflammatory conditions, and capable of phagocytosing a variety of extracellular particulate material, including immune complexes, microorganisms, and dead cells.

label: chondrocyte activation
Defs: A change in the morphology or behavior of a chondrocyte resulting from exposure to an activating factor such as a cellular or soluble ligand. A chondrocyte is a polymorphic cell that forms cartilage.

label: regulation of macrophage migration
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of macrophage migration.

label: protein polypeptide chain
Defs: A naturally occurring polypeptide synthesized at the ribosome.

label: normal sensitivity of a process to oxygen
Defs: A sensitivity of occurrent to oxygen which is relatively normal.

label: positive regulation of protein localization to cell cortex
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to cell cortex.

label: cell adhesion mediator activity
Defs: The binding by a cell-adhesion protein on a cell surface to an adhesion molecule on another cell surface or an external substrate, to mediate adhesion of the cell to the external substrate or to another cell.

label: nuclear migration along microfilament
Defs: The directed movement of the nucleus along microfilaments within the cell, mediated by motor proteins.

label: proximal-distal axis
Defs: An axis that extends from the point of attachment of a structure (proximal) to the  point furthest away from the plane of attachment (distal).

label: pulmonary artery endothelium
Defs: An pulmonary artery endothelium is an epithelium that lines the pulmonary artery[GO].

label: embryonic development via the syncytial blastoderm
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the embryo over time, from zygote formation through syncytial blastoderm to the hatching of the first instar larva. An example of this process is found in Drosophila melanogaster.

label: tunica intima of artery
Defs: A tunica intima that is part of a artery.

label: negative regulation of cardiac ventricle formation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac ventricle formation.

label: multicellular organism development
Defs: The biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of a multicellular organism over time from an initial condition (e.g. a zygote or a young adult) to a later condition (e.g. a multicellular animal or an aged adult).

label: presumptive ectoderm
Defs: Presumptive structure of the blastula that will develop into ectoderm.

label: pilosity
Defs: A texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having hair or bristles.

label: serotonin binding
Defs: Binding to serotonin (5-hydroxytryptamine), a monoamine neurotransmitter occurring in the peripheral and central nervous systems, also having hormonal properties.

label: peptide receptor activity
Defs: Combining with an extracellular or intracellular peptide to initiate a change in cell activity.

label: regulation of nervous system process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a neurophysiological process, an organ system process carried out by any of the organs or tissues of the nervous system.

label: solid cuticular protrusion
Defs: The cuticular protrusion that does not correspond to an evagination.

label: misaligned away from
Defs: An alignment quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being in a improper spatial positioning away from an additional entity.

label: trinucleate
Defs: A nucleate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having three nuclei.

label: trunk somite
Defs: A somite that is part of a trunk.

label: interventricular septum muscular part
Defs: The muscular portion of the wall between the two lower chambers of the heart.

label: pleomorphic
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a cell by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to take on two or more different shapes during its life cycle.

label: granulocytopoietic cell
Defs: A cell involved in the formation of a granulocyte.

label: foregut morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the foregut are generated and organized.

label: negative regulation of neutrophil migration
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of neutrophil migration.

label: establishment of chromosome localization
Defs: The directed movement of a chromosome to a specific location.

label: endothelial cell of venule
Defs: An endothelial cell that is part of the venule.

label: unbranched
Defs: A branchiness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking branches.

label: small intestine arteriole
Defs: Arteriole of villus of small intestine.

label: regulation of sarcomere organization
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of myofibril assembly by organization of muscle actomyosin into sarcomeres. The sarcomere is the repeating unit of a myofibril in a muscle cell, composed of an array of overlapping thick and thin filaments between two adjacent Z discs.

label: abdominal tergite
Defs: The sclerite of the insect abdomen that is dorsal and medial.

label: anal region skeletal muscle
Defs: A portion of skeletal muscle tissue that is part of an anal region [Automatically generated definition].

label: skeleton of lower jaw
Defs: A subdivision of the skeleton that corresponds to the lower part of the mouth. The lower jaw skeleton includes the following elements, when present: lower jaw teeth, the mandible and other lower jaw bones, and Meckel\'s cartilage.

label: C-shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being shaped in the form of the letter C.

label: muscle cell projection membrane
Defs: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a muscle cell projection.

label: Schwann cell
Defs: A glial cell that ensheathes axons of neuron in the peripheral nervous system and are necessary for their maintainance and function.

label: intestinal epithelial cell maturation
Defs: The developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for a columna/cuboidal epithelial cell of the intestine to attain its fully functional state. A columnar/cuboidal epithelial cell of the intestine mature as they migrate from the intestinal crypt to the villus.

label: reagent

label: meninx of diencephalon

Defs: A reproductive quality inhering in the young of an animal by virtue of the bearer\'s being cared for at one time.

label: positive regulation of dendritic cell apoptotic process

label: positive regulation of cellular biosynthetic process

label: obsolete increased action potential

label: smooth muscle tissue development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of smooth muscle over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: musculature of pectoral complex
Defs: Any collection of muscles that is part of a pectoral complex. The pectoral complex comprises the pectoral girdle and the associated limb or fin.

label: epithelial tube formation
Defs: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of an epithelial tube.

label: corneal epithelial cell
Defs: An epithelial cell of the cornea.

label: cardiac pacemaker cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a pacemaker cell. Pacemaker cells are specialized cardiomyocytes that are responsible for regulating the timing of heart contractions.

label: patients textual entity

label: p-block element atom
Defs: Any main group element atom belonging to the p-block of the periodic table.

label: kinase activity
Defs: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphate group, usually from ATP, to a substrate molecule.

label: ascending aorta development
Defs: The progression of the ascending aorta over time, from its initial formation to the mature structure. The ascending aorta is the portion of the aorta in a two-pass circulatory system that lies between the heart and the arch of aorta. In a two-pass circulatory system blood passes twice through the heart to supply the body once.

label: negative regulation of mononuclear cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of mononuclear cell proliferation.

label: positive regulation of erythrocyte apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of erythrocyte apoptotic process.

label: splanchnopleure
Defs: A structure created during embryogenesis when the lateral mesoderm splits into two layers - the inner (or splanchnic) layer adheres to the endoderm, and with it forms the splanchnopleure[WP].

label: neural tube patterning
Defs: The regionalization process that regulates the coordinated growth that establishes the non-random spatial arrangement of the neural tube.

label: vacuole inheritance
Defs: The distribution of vacuoles into daughter cells after mitosis or meiosis, mediated by interactions between vacuoles and the cytoskeleton.

label: taste bud development
Defs: The progression of the taste bud over time, from its formation to the mature state. The taste bud is a specialized area of the tongue that contains taste receptors.

label: endomembrane system
Defs: A collection of membranous structures involved in transport within the cell. The main components of the endomembrane system are endoplasmic reticulum, Golgi bodies, vesicles, cell membrane and nuclear envelope. Members of the endomembrane system pass materials through each other or though the use of vesicles.

label: myb proto-oncogene protein
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human MYB gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: placental artery
Defs: An artery that is part of the placenta.

label: nervous system cell part layer
Defs: Single layer of a laminar structure, identified by different density, arrangement or size of cells and processes arranged in flattened layers or lamina[CUMBO].

label: neural tube marginal layer
Defs: The outermost layer of the neural tube that consists of axons from the developing mantle layer and will form the white matter.

label: lamina propria of bronchus
Defs: A lamina propria that is part of a bronchus [Automatically generated definition].

label: serous secreting cell
Defs: Columnar glandular cell with irregular nucleus, copious granular endoplasmic reticulum and supranuclear granules. Secretes a watery fluid containing proteins known as serous fluid.

label: positive regulation of T cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the rate or extent of T cell proliferation.

label: protein localization to chromatin
Defs: Any process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained at, a part of a chromosome that is organized into chromatin.

label: regulation of exocytic insertion of neurotransmitter receptor to postsynaptic membrane
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of exocytic fusion of neurotransmitter receptor containing vesicles into the postsynaptic membrane.

label: normal mobility
Defs: A mobility which is relatively normal or average.

label: increased variability
Defs: A variability which is relatively high.

label: cellular component organization
Defs: A process that results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a cellular component.

label: microtubule polymerization based movement
Defs: The movement of a cellular component as a result of microtubule polymerization.

label: outflow part of right ventricle
Defs: Anteriosuperior, smooth-walled portion of the cavity of the right ventricle, beginning at the supraventricular crest and terminating in the pulmonary trunk.

label: radiating
Defs: Shape quality inhering in a bearer expanding outward, or having parts expanding outward, from a center point.

label: detection of chemical stimulus involved in sensory perception of taste
Defs: The series of events involved in the perception of taste in which a gustatory chemical stimulus is received and converted into a molecular signal.

label: male fertility
Defs: A fertility quality of inhering in a male by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to initiate, sustain, or support reproduction.

label: bone of free limb or fin
Defs: A bone that is part of an appendage [Automatically generated definition].

label: positive regulation of iron ion transmembrane transport
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of iron ions from one side of a membrane to the other by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: membrane-bounded organelle
Defs: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function, bounded by a single or double lipid bilayer membrane. Includes the nucleus, mitochondria, plastids, vacuoles, and vesicles. Excludes the plasma membrane.

label: positive regulation of granulocyte chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of granulocyte chemotaxis. Granulocyte chemotaxis is the movement of a granulocyte in response to an external stimulus.

label: cellular response to glucose stimulus
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a glucose stimulus.

label: MHC class II protein complex binding

label: dicarboxylic acid biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of dicarboxylic acids, any organic acid containing two carboxyl (-COOH) groups.

label: macrophage colony-stimulating factor 1 receptor
Defs: A CSF-1/PDGF receptor-type tyrosine-protein kinase that is a translation product of the human CSF1R gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: cytoskeleton of dendritic spine
Defs: The portion of the cytoskeleton that lies within a dendritic spine.  The actin component of this cytoskeleton is involved in spine head remodelling in response to postsynaptic signalling.

label: mesepimeron
Defs: The epimeron on the posterior region of the mesopleuron.

label: unipolar neuron morphology
Defs: A cell morphology that inheres in neurons with only one process, a neurite, that extends from the cell body. The neurite then branches to form dendritic and axonal processes.

label: Mus musculus protein
Defs: A protein that is encoded in the genome of Mus musculus.

label: positive regulation of macrophage migration
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of macrophage migration.

label: mucosa
Defs: A lining of mostly endodermal origin, covered in epithelium, which is involved in absorption and secretion. They line various body cavities that are exposed to the external environment and internal organs. It is at several places continuous with skin: at the nostrils, the lips, the ears, the genital area, and the anus. The sticky, thick fluid secreted by the mucous membranes and gland is termed mucus. The term mucous membrane refers to where they are found in the body and not every mucous membrane secretes mucus[WP].

label: smooth muscle of eye
Defs: Any of the striated muscles that move the eye and include: superior rectus, inferior rectus, medial rectus, lateral rectus, superior oblique, inferior oblique, retractor bulbi.

label: stipital ridge
Defs: The ridge that is part of the stipes.

label: positive regulation of synaptic transmission, cholinergic
Defs: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cholinergic synaptic transmission, the process of communication from a neuron to another neuron across a synapse using the neurotransmitter acetylcholine.

label: bronchus submucosal gland
Defs: A submucosal gland located in a bronchus.

label: larynx morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the larynx is generated and organized. The larynx is a continuation of the pharynx that is involved in breathing, sound production, and protecting the trachea against food aspiration.

label: sonic hedgehog protein (mouse)
Defs: A sonic hedgehog protein that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: negative regulation of cardiac chamber formation

label: cardiac muscle tissue of cardiac septum
Defs: A portion of cardiac muscle tissue that is part of a cardiac septum [Automatically generated definition].

label: lipid
Defs: \'Lipids\' is a loosely defined term for substances of biological origin that are soluble in nonpolar solvents. They consist of saponifiable lipids, such as glycerides (fats and oils) and phospholipids, as well as nonsaponifiable lipids, principally steroids.

label: primary ammonium ion
Defs: An ammonium ion derivative resulting from the protonation of the nitrogen atom of a primary amino compound. Major species at pH 7.3.

label: pharyngeal gland morphogenesis

label: color saturation

label: ridged

label: cuticular spur

label: extracellular matrix disassembly
Defs: A process that results in the breakdown of the extracellular matrix.

label: cartilage element

label: footnote

label: increased osmolarity
Defs: A osmolarity which is relatively high.

Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of T cell differentiation.

label: mucosa of right hepatic duct

Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a sympathetic ganglion over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: positive regulation of catabolic process

Defs: The insect thoracic muscle that is attached to a furca and to a coxa.

label: increased length
Defs: A length quality which is relatively large.

label: extrahepatic bile duct epithelium
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a extrahepatic bile duct [Automatically generated definition].

In humans, the renal system comprises a pair of kidneys, a pair of ureters, urinary bladder, urethra, sphincter muscle and associated blood vessels.

label: regulation of striated muscle tissue development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of striated muscle development.

Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of pharynx morphogenesis.

Defs: A cell found throughout the gastrointestinal tract and in the pancreas. They secrete somatostatin in both an endocrine and paracrine manner. Somatostatin inhibits gastrin, cholecystokinin, insulin, glucagon, pancreatic enzymes, and gastric hydrochloric acid. A variety of substances which inhibit gastric acid secretion (vasoactive intestinal peptide, calcitonin gene-related peptide, cholecystokinin, beta-adrenergic agonists, and gastric inhibitory peptide) are thought to act by releasing somatostatin.

label: response to nitrogen compound
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a nitrogen compound stimulus.

label: regulation of protein catabolic process in the vacuole

label: positive regulation of neuron differentiation

label: salinity

label: epithelial cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of an epithelial cell, any of the cells making up an epithelium.

label: bone of appendage girdle complex
Defs: A bone that is part of an appendage girdle complex (i.e. any bone in a limb, fin or girdle).

label: cyclicity

label: meningeal artery

label: dorsal mesentery

label: serous membrane development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a serous membrane over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: smooth muscle cell of anorectum
Defs: A smooth muscle cell that is located in the anorectum.

label: carotid canal
Defs: On the interior surface of the temporal bone, behind the rough surface of the apex, is the large circular aperture of the carotid canal, which ascends at first vertically, and then, making a bend, runs horizontally forward and medialward. It transmits into the cranium, the internal carotid artery, and the carotid plexus of nerves. Sympathetics to the head also pass through the carotid canal. They have several motor functions: raise the eyelid (superior tarsal muscle), dilate pupil, innervate sweat glands of face and scalp and constricts blood vessels in head[WP].

label: amplitude
Defs: A physical quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the size of the bearer\'s maximum displacement from the \'normal\' position, when periodic motion is taking place.

label: skeletal muscle tissue growth

label: hadron

label: ventral orientation

label: positive regulation of acinar cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of acinar cell proliferation.

label: amine catabolic process

label: cuticle of labrum

label: vascular endothelial growth factor receptor binding
Defs: Binding to a vascular endothelial growth factor receptor.

label: lumen of trachea

Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cell proliferation in midbrain.

label: stellate neuron

Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a dopamine stimulus.

label: hyperresponsive to

Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus from a bacterium.

label: elastic tissue
Defs: Connective tissue composed of elastic fibers.

label: stem cell of gastric gland
Defs: A stomach epithelial cell that is olumnar in form with a few short apical microvilli; relatively undifferentiated mitotic cell from which other types of gland are derived; few in number, situated in the isthmus region of the gland and base of the gastric pit.

label: midbrain-hindbrain boundary
Defs: The part of the brain that is the morphological boundary between the midbrain and hindbrain and that is the location of an organizing center which patterns the midbrain and hindbrain primordia of the neural plate.

label: negative regulation of kinase activity
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of kinase activity, the catalysis of the transfer of a phosphate group, usually from ATP, to a substrate molecule.

label: rosy
Defs: A color hue consisting of red hue and yellow hue and high brightness.

label: premento-palpal muscle
Defs: The cranio-labial muscle that is attached to the prementum and the labial palpus.

label: negative regulation of myeloid dendritic cell chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of myeloid dendritic cell chemotaxis.

label: ipsilateral side
Defs: On the same side

label: insusceptible toward
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking susceptibilty toward an external stimulus.

label: positive regulation of acetate catabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of acetate.

label: actin filament
Defs: A filamentous structure formed of a two-stranded helical polymer of the protein actin and associated proteins. Actin filaments are a major component of the contractile apparatus of skeletal muscle and the microfilaments of the cytoskeleton of eukaryotic cells. The filaments, comprising polymerized globular actin molecules, appear as flexible structures with a diameter of 5-9 nm. They are organized into a variety of linear bundles, two-dimensional networks, and three dimensional gels. In the cytoskeleton they are most highly concentrated in the cortex of the cell just beneath the plasma membrane.

label: exposed
Defs: Open to view or not covered by another entity.

label: midbrain tegmentum
Defs: Ventral part of the midbrain, separated from the hindbrain by the isthmus[ISBN:0471888893]. Subdivision of the midbrain lying anterior to the tectum and posterior to the substantia nigra and cerebral peduncle[FMA] The part of the midbrain extending from the substantia nigra to the cerebral aqueduct in a horizontal section of the midbrain. It forms the floor of the midbrain that surrounds the cerebral aqueduct[WP].

label: bleb assembly
Defs: The assembly of a bleb, a cell extension caused by localized decoupling of the cytoskeleton from the plasma membrane and characterized by rapid formation, rounded shape, and scarcity of organelles within the protrusion. Plasma membrane blebbing occurs during apoptosis and other cellular processes, including cell locomotion, cell division, and as a result of physical or chemical stresses.

label: regulation of phosphate transmembrane transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of phosphate transmembrane transport.

label: thoracic segment blood vessel
Defs: A blood vessel that is part of a thorax [Automatically generated definition].

label: negative regulation of apoptotic process involved in development
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of apoptotic process involved in development.

label: positive regulation of signal transduction
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of signal transduction.

label: endocardial cell development
Defs: The progression of an endocardial cell over time, from its formation to the mature cell. An endocardial cell is a specialized endothelial cell that makes up the endocardium portion of the heart.

label: bronchiole development
Defs: The biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of a bronchiole from an initial condition to its mature state. This process begins with the formation of the bronchiole and ends with the mature structure. A bronchiole is the first airway branch that no longer contains cartilage; it is a branch of the bronchi.

label: cuticle of paramere
Defs: The cuticle of the paired cuticular evagination of the postabdomen that is attached to the cuticle of phallobase by the phallobasal-parameral conjunctiva and to the cuticle of aedeagus by the paramero-aedeagal conjunctiva.

label: dorsal-ventral polarity
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s location of features or characteristics along the dorsal-ventral axis.

label: formation of anatomical boundary
Defs: The process in which the limits of an anatomical structure are generated. An anatomical structure is any biological entity that occupies space and is distinguished from its surroundings. Anatomical structures can be macroscopic such as a carpel, or microscopic such as an acrosome.

label: keyhole shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer resembling a keyhole.

label: neuron projection development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a neuron projection over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A neuron projection is any process extending from a neural cell, such as axons or dendrites (collectively called neurites).

label: decreased variability of temperature
Defs: A variability of temperature which is relatively low.

label: increased efficacy
Defs: A increase in the ability of a process to produce its output.

label: bronchus connective tissue
Defs: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a bronchus [Automatically generated definition].

label: hepatocyte homeostasis
Defs: Any biological process involved in the maintenance of the steady-state number of hepatocytes within a population of cells. Hepatocytes are specialized epithelial cells of the liver that are organized into interconnected plates called lobules.

label: cation binding
Defs: Binding to a cation, a charged atom or group of atoms with a net positive charge.

label: lipid metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving lipids, compounds soluble in an organic solvent but not, or sparingly, in an aqueous solvent. Includes fatty acids; neutral fats, other fatty-acid esters, and soaps; long-chain (fatty) alcohols and waxes; sphingoids and other long-chain bases; glycolipids, phospholipids and sphingolipids; and carotenes, polyprenols, sterols, terpenes and other isoprenoids.

label: body proper
Defs: The region of the organism associated with the visceral organs.

label: regulation of neuron maturation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of neuron maturation, the process leading to the attainment of the full functional capacity of a neuron. This process is independent of morphogenetic change.

label: skeletal muscle cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a skeletal muscle cell, a somatic cell located in skeletal muscle.

label: genioglossus muscle
Defs: Either of a pair of lingual muscles with origin in the mandible, with insertion to the lingual fascia below the mucous membrane and epiglottis, with nerve supply from the hypoglossal nerve, and whose action depresses and protrudes the tongue.

label: irregular sleep pattern
Defs: A sleep pattern which has irregular start and/or end times.

label: embryonic eye morphogenesis
Defs: The process occurring in the embryo by which the anatomical structures of the post-embryonic eye are generated and organized.

label: normal male receptivity
Defs: A male receptivity which is relatively normal or average.

label: positive regulation of vesicle fusion
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of vesicle fusion.

label: F minus mating type
Defs: A bacterial mating type indicating the absence of F plasmid in a bacterial cell.

label: photoreceptor cell
Defs: A cell specialized to detect and transduce light.

label: curation status specification
Defs: The curation status of the term. The allowed values come from an enumerated list of predefined terms. See the specification of these instances for more detailed definitions of each enumerated value.

label: mandibular nerve
Defs: The motor and sensory nerve subdivision of the trigeminal nerve that transmits sensory information from the auricle, the external acoustic meatus, tympanic membrane, temporal region, the cheek, the skin overlying the mandible, the anterior portion of the tongue, the floor of the mouth, lower teeth and gingiva and transmits motor information from the muscles of mastication, the mylohyoid muscle and digastric muscle and the muscles tensor tympani and tensor veli palatini.

label: endocrine cell
Defs: A cell of an endocrine gland, ductless glands that secrete substances which are released directly into the circulation and which influence metabolism and other body functions.

label: duodenum glandular cell
Defs: Glandular cell of duodenal epithelium. Example: Enterocytes, Goblet cells, enteroendocrine cells; Paneth cells; M cells; Brunner\'s gland cell.

label: vein endothelial cell
Defs: An endothelial cell that is part of the vein.

label: aminoglycan catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of aminoglycans, any polymer containing amino groups that consists of more than about 10 monosaccharide residues joined to each other by glycosidic linkages.

label: external ectoderm
Defs: The surface (external) layer of ectoderm which begins to proliferate shortly after separation from the neuroectoderm.

label: negative regulation of microtubule depolymerization
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of microtubule depolymerization; prevention of depolymerization of a microtubule can result from binding by \'capping\' at the plus end (e.g. by interaction with another cellular protein of structure) or by exposing microtubules to a stabilizing drug such as taxol.

label: obsolete decreased consumption
Defs: A consumption which is relatively low.

label: endometrial microvascular endothelial cells
Defs: Any microvascular endothelial cell that is part of a endometrial blood vessel.

label: vesicle targeting, trans-Golgi to periciliary membrane compartment
Defs: The process in which vesicles formed at the trans-Golgi network are directed to the plasma membrane surrounding the base of the cilium, including the ciliary pocket, mediated by molecules at the vesicle membrane and target membrane surfaces.

label: subspherical
Defs: A spheroid shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being nearly, but not perfectly, spherical.

label: curved rostral
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved towards the front of an organism.

label: respiratory system basement membrane
Defs: A basement membrane of epithelium that is part of a respiratory system.

label: hyporesponsive to
Defs: A response quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s limited reaction to a stimulus or an agent.

label: atrioventricular node
Defs: An area of conducting tissue between the atria and the ventricles of the heart that conducts the normal electrical impulse from the atria to the ventricles.

label: foramen magnum
Defs: In anatomy, in the occipital bone, the foramen magnum is one of the several oval or circular apertures in the base of the skull, through which the medulla oblongata (an extension of the spinal cord) enters and exits the skull vault. Apart from the transmission of the medulla oblongata and its membranes, the foramen magnum transmits the Spinal Accessory nerve, vertebral arteries, the anterior and posterior spinal arteries, the membrana tectoria and alar ligaments. [WP,unvetted].

label: macromolecule modification
Defs: The covalent alteration of one or more monomeric units in a polypeptide, polynucleotide, polysaccharide, or other biological macromolecule, resulting in a change in its properties.

label: abdominal tergite X-paraproct conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the postabdomen that joins the abdominal tergite X and each paraproct.

label: mesotibial muscle
Defs: The somatic muscle that inserts in the mesotibia.

label: chronic
Defs: A duration quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having slow progressive course of indefinite duration.

label: protein binding
Defs: Binding to a protein.

label: positive regulation of dendritic spine development
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of dendritic spine development, the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the dendritic spine over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: female meiotic nuclear division
Defs: A cell cycle process by which the cell nucleus divides as part of a meiotic cell cycle in the female germline.

label: trunk mesenchyme
Defs: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing trunk.

label: catecholamine biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of any of a group of physiologically important biogenic amines that possess a catechol (3,4-dihydroxyphenyl) nucleus and are derivatives of 3,4-dihydroxyphenylethylamine.

label: abbreviations section
Defs: A part of a document where abbreviations and their long-forms used within the document are listed.

label: regulation of neutrophil apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of neutrophil apoptotic process.

label: bacterial metabolite
Defs: Any prokaryotic metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in bacteria.

label: establishment or maintenance of cytoskeleton polarity involved in ameboidal cell migration
Defs: Any cellular process that results in the specification, formation or maintenance of polarized cytoskeletal structures that contribute to the cell polarity of a migrating ameboid cell.

label: brain endothelium
Defs: Vascular endothelium found in blood vessels of the blood-brain-barrier.

label: trisomy
Defs: An aneuploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing three, instead of two, chromosomes of a particular numbered type in an organism.

label: pale pink
Defs: Pink color having high brightness and low saturation.

label: foregut-midgut junction
Defs: An anatomical junctions that overlaps the foregut and midgut.

label: electron
Defs: Elementary particle not affected by the strong force having a spin 1/2, a negative elementary charge and a rest mass of 0.000548579903(13) u, or 0.51099906(15) MeV.

label: stroma of pancreas
Defs: A stroma that is part of a pancreas.

label: normal depth
Defs: A depth quality which is relatively normal or average

label: anteriorly rotated
Defs: A rotation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of being rotated towards the front of an organism.

label: lesioned
Defs: A structural quality which is held by a bearer where a localized pathological or traumatic structural change, damage, deformity, or discontinuity of tissue, organ, or body part is present.

label: Purkinje myocyte of interventricular septum
Defs: A Purkinje myocyte that is part of the interventricular septum.

label: decreased sensitivity of a process to oxygen
Defs: A sensitivity of a process to oxygen which is lower than normal or average.

label: obsolete pre-mortem
Defs: The period before death of the organism.

label: elasticity
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to recover its size and shape after deformation in any way.

label: chorion membrane
Defs: The outermost extraembryonic membrane of amniotes.

label: positive regulation of endothelial cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of endothelial cell apoptotic process.

label: muscle adaptation
Defs: A process in which muscle adapts, with consequent modifications to structural and/or functional phenotypes, in response to a stimulus. Stimuli include contractile activity, loading conditions, substrate supply, and environmental factors. These adaptive events occur in both muscle fibers and associated structures (motoneurons and capillaries), and they involve alterations in regulatory mechanisms, contractile properties and metabolic capacities.

label: positive regulation of epithelial cell migration
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of epithelial cell migration.

label: macromolecule
Defs: A macromolecule is a molecule of high relative molecular mass, the structure of which essentially comprises the multiple repetition of units derived, actually or conceptually, from molecules of low relative molecular mass.

label: cellular nitrogen compound biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of organic and inorganic nitrogenous compounds.

label: postcubitus
Defs: The insect wing vein that is posterior to the cubitus and anterior to the anal fold or the anal vein.

label: normal rate
Defs: A rate which is relatively normal.

label: cardiac atrium development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a cardiac atrium over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A cardiac atrium receives blood from a vein and pumps it to a cardiac ventricle.

label: catecholamine binding
Defs: Binding to catecholamine.

label: signaling receptor activator activity
Defs: The function of interacting (directly or indirectly) with receptors such that the proportion of receptors in the active form is increased.

label: eye
Defs: An organ that detects light.

label: localization
Defs: Any process in which a cell, a substance, or a cellular entity, such as a protein complex or organelle, is transported, tethered to or otherwise maintained in a specific location. In the case of substances, localization may also be achieved via selective degradation.

label: degenerate
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer whose structure deteriorates or is lost over time due to an active pathological process.

label: cardiac muscle tissue
Defs: Muscle tissue composed of cardiac muscle cells, forming the muscles of the heart[ZFA,modified].

label: curved
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having or being marked by a curve or smoothly rounded bend.

label: acetate transport
Defs: The directed movement of acetate into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: conventional dendritic cell
Defs: Conventional dendritic cell is a dendritic cell that is CD11c-high.

label: mucus secretion
Defs: The regulated release of mucus by the mucosa. Mucus is a viscous slimy secretion consisting of mucins and various inorganic salts dissolved in water, with suspended epithelial cells and leukocytes. The mucosa, or mucous membrane, is the membrane covered with epithelium that lines the tubular organs of the body. Mucins are carbohydrate-rich glycoproteins that have a lubricating and protective function.

label: ictal
Defs: A physiological state which is characterized by periods of high-frequency high amplitude electrical activity in neuronal tissue.

label: tables section
Defs: A part of a document that contains one or more tables.

label: cardiac ventricle morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the cardiac ventricle is generated and organized. A cardiac ventricle receives blood from a cardiac atrium and pumps it out of the heart.

label: preepisternum
Defs: The region of cuticle on the antero-ventral region of the episternum that is anterior to the anapleural sulcus.

label: stromal cell of ovary
Defs: A stomal cell of the ovary

label: abdominal segment skin
Defs: A skin of body that is part of an abdominal segment of trunk [Automatically generated definition].

label: regulation of cell proliferation involved in heart morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell proliferation involved in heart morphogenesis.

label: submucosa of biliary tree
Defs: A submucosa that is part of a biliary tree [Automatically generated definition].

label: common bile duct
Defs: The part of the biliary tree formed by the union of the cystic duct and the common hepatic duct.

label: neuromuscular junction
Defs: The junction between the axon of a motor neuron and a muscle fiber. In response to the arrival of action potentials, the presynaptic button releases molecules of neurotransmitters into the synaptic cleft. These diffuse across the cleft and transmit the signal to the postsynaptic membrane of the muscle fiber, leading to a change in post-synaptic potential.

label: negative regulation of cilium assembly
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cilium assembly.

label: negative regulation of protein localization to cell periphery
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to cell periphery.

label: south
Defs: South is one of the four cardinal directions or compass points. South is the polar opposite of north and is perpendicular to east and west.

label: positive regulation of actin filament bundle assembly
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the assembly of actin filament bundles.

label: response to stimulus
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus. The process begins with detection of the stimulus and ends with a change in state or activity or the cell or organism.

label: metal ion transport
Defs: The directed movement of metal ions, any metal ion with an electric charge, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: protein localization to axon
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to or maintained in a location within an axon.

label: dermal melanocyte
Defs: A melanocyte that produces pigment in the dermis.

label: submucosa of cloaca
Defs: A submucosa that is part of a cloaca [Automatically generated definition].

label: endothelial cell activation
Defs: The change in morphology and behavior of an endothelial cell resulting from exposure to a cytokine, chemokine, cellular ligand, or soluble factor.

label: abdominal viscera
Defs: A viscus that is part of a abdomen.

label: embryonic tagma
Defs: Any tagma (UBERON:6000002) that is part of some embryo (UBERON:6000052).

label: gustatory organ
Defs: Any sense organ that functions in (some) detection of chemical stimulus involved in sensory perception of taste (GO:0050912).

label: enucleate erythrocyte differentiation
Defs: The process in which a myeloid precursor cell acquires specialized features of an erythrocyte without a nucleus. An example of this process is found in Mus musculus.

label: myoblast differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a myoblast. A myoblast is a mononucleate cell type that, by fusion with other myoblasts, gives rise to the myotubes that eventually develop into striated muscle fibers.

label: cuticular pit
Defs: The cuticular depression that corresponds to an apophysis.

label: amount
Defs: The number of entities of this type that are part of the whole organism.

label: regulation of cellular carbohydrate metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, extent or frequency of the chemical reactions and pathways involving carbohydrates, any of a group of organic compounds based of the general formula Cx(H2O)y, as carried out by individual cells.

label: epithelium of gonad
Defs: An epithelium surrounding a gonad.

label: negative regulation of production of molecular mediator of immune response
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of the production of molecular mediator of immune response.

label: glucan catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of glucans, polysaccharides consisting only of glucose residues.

label: space surrounding organism
Defs: The space that surrounds an organism.

label: data item
Defs: An information content entity that is intended to be a truthful statement about something (modulo, e.g., measurement precision or other systematic errors) and is constructed/acquired by a method which reliably tends to produce (approximately) truthful statements.

label: posterior communicating artery
Defs: One of a pair of right-sided and left-sided blood vessels in the circle of Willis. It connects the three cerebral arteries of the same side. Anteriorly, it is one portion of the terminal trifurcation of the internal carotid artery. The anterior cerebral artery and the middle cerebral artery are the other two branches of the trifurcation. Posteriorly, it communicates with the posterior cerebral artery.

label: gland of anal canal
Defs: A gland that is part of an anal canal [Automatically generated definition].

label: viable
Defs: A viability quality inhering in a bearer or a population by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to survive or the long term survival ability of a given population.

label: regulation of myeloid leukocyte mediated immunity
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of myeloid leukocyte mediated immunity.

label: lateral margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the lateral side of the body or body part.

label: amino acid binding
Defs: Binding to an amino acid, organic acids containing one or more amino substituents.

label: insect wing vein
Defs: The region of cuticle of the insect wing that is less flexible than the wing conjunctiva.

label: subulate
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being linear, very narrow, tapering to a very fine point from a narrow base.

label: tube
Defs: Any hollow cylindrical anatomical structure containing a lumen through which substances are transported.

label: respiratory gaseous exchange by respiratory system
Defs: The process of gaseous exchange between an organism and its environment. In plants, microorganisms, and many small animals, air or water makes direct contact with the organism\'s cells or tissue fluids, and the processes of diffusion supply the organism with dioxygen (O2) and remove carbon dioxide (CO2). In larger animals the efficiency of gaseous exchange is improved by specialized respiratory organs, such as lungs and gills, which are ventilated by breathing mechanisms.

label: far from
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located far (not close to) in space in relation to another entity.

label: wall of intestine
Defs: An anatomical wall that is part of a intestine [Automatically generated definition].

label: morbidity
Defs: A quality inhering in a population by virtue of the proportion of its members that are ill at a given time.

label: right internal carotid artery
Defs: An internal carotid artery that branching_part_of a right common carotid artery plus branches.

label: arboreal
Defs: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s morphological and physiological adaptation for living in trees.

label: cuticular seta
Defs: The unicellular cuticular evagination that constitutes a sclerite with its base surrounded by socket membrane.

label: chromatin organization
Defs: The assembly or remodeling of chromatin composed of DNA complexed with histones, other associated proteins, and sometimes RNA.

label: brainstem
Defs: Stalk-like part of the brain that includes amongst its parts the medulla oblongata of the hindbrain and the tegmentum of the midbrain[ZFA,MP,generalized].

label: abdominal sternite VII-abdominal sternite VIII conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect abdomen that connects the abdominal sternite VII and the abdominal sternite VIII.

label: photographic print
Defs: A photographic print is a material entity upon which a photograph generically depends.

label: phrenic nerve
Defs: A nerve that arises from the caudal cervical nerves and is primarily the motor nerve of the diaphragm but also sends sensory fibers to the pericardium.

label: integral component of lysosomal membrane
Defs: The component of the lysosome membrane consisting of the gene products and protein complexes having at least some part of their peptide sequence embedded in the hydrophobic region of the membrane.

label: neuroblast development
Defs: The process aimed at the progression of a neuroblast over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific state, to the mature neuroblast. It does not include processes where the neuroblast turns into a glial cell or a neuron.

label: amino acid transport
Defs: The directed movement of amino acids, organic acids containing one or more amino substituents, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: decreased age
Defs: An age which is low relative to the normal or average.

label: import ontology module
Defs: A subset ontology module that is intended to be imported from another ontology.

label: regulation of protein localization to cell-cell junction
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to cell-cell junction.

label: flight
Defs: Self-propelled movement of an organism from one location to another through the air, usually by means of active wing movement.

label: response to insulin
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an insulin stimulus. Insulin is a polypeptide hormone produced by the islets of Langerhans of the pancreas in mammals, and by the homologous organs of other organisms.

label: positive regulation of fibroblast migration
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of fibroblast cell migration. Fibroblast cell migration is accomplished by extension and retraction of a pseudopodium.

label: positive regulation of epithelial cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the rate or extent of epithelial cell proliferation.

label: neck blood vessel
Defs: A blood vessel that is part of a neck [Automatically generated definition].

label: response to hexose
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a hexose stimulus.

label: pigment granule membrane
Defs: Any membrane that is part of a pigment granule.

label: prototrophic
Defs: A nutritional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to synthesize a particular organic compound required for its growth.

label: mesenchymal cell development
Defs: The process aimed at the progression of a mesenchymal cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to its specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell.

label: positive regulation of neural retina development
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of neural retina development, the progression of the neural retina over time from its initial formation to the mature structure. The neural retina is the part of the retina that contains neurons and photoreceptor cells.

label: hepatic artery
Defs: An artery that supplies the liver.

label: normal female receptivity
Defs: A female receptivity which is relatively normal or average.

label: regulation protein catabolic process at synapse
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a protein at the synapse.

label: dorsal aorta
Defs: The dorsal aorta is a blood vessel in a single-pass circulatory system that carries oxygenated blood from the gills to the rest of the body. In a single-pass circulatory system blood passes once through the heart to supply the body once.

label: negative regulation of translational initiation in response to stress
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the rate of translation initiation as a result of a stimulus indicating the organism is under stress.

label: striated muscle tissue
Defs: Muscle tissue that contains fibers that are divided by transverse bands into striations.

label: positive regulation of macrophage differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of macrophage differentiation.

label: negative regulation of acetylcholine uptake
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of acetylcholine into a cell.

label: liver morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the liver are generated and organized.

label: cladodromous
Defs: A branched quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having secondary branches freely branching toward the margin.

label: fully formed stage
Defs: The stage of development at which the animal is fully formed, including immaturity and maturity. Includes both sexually immature stage, and adult stage.

label: abdominal aorta artery
Defs: An artery that originates from the abdominal aorta.

label: gonad morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the gonads are generated and organized. A gonad is an animal organ producing gametes, e.g. the testes or the ovary in mammals.

label: simple
Defs: A complexity quality in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having few parts or being complicated or compound.

label: mottled
Defs: Multicolored quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being dappled with spots, patches, or blotches of different colors.

label: carbohydrate metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving carbohydrates, any of a group of organic compounds based of the general formula Cx(H2O)y.

label: skeletal muscle myofibril
Defs: A myofibril of a skeletal muscle fiber.

label: Descemet's membrane
Defs: A transparent homogeneous acellular layer found between the substantia propria and the endothelial layer of the cornea[MP].

label: neutrophil activation involved in immune response
Defs: The change in morphology and behavior of a neutrophil resulting from exposure to a cytokine, chemokine, cellular ligand, or soluble factor, leading to the initiation or perpetuation of an immune response.

label: eye epithelium
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a camera-type eye.

label: trophectodermal cell proliferation
Defs: The proliferation of cells in the trophectoderm.

label: germ cell
Defs: The reproductive cell in multicellular organisms.

label: sinoatrial node cell development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a sinoatrial (SA) node cell over time, from its formation to the mature state. SA node cells are pacemaker cells that are found in the sinoatrial node.

label: ring shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a shape like a ring (a circular shape enclosing a space).

label: positive regulation of collagen fibril organization
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of collagen fibril organization.

label: tergo-trochantinal muscle
Defs: The insect thoracic muscle that attaches to the notum and to the trochantin.

label: muscle of larynx
Defs: The muscles associated with the larynx.

label: Postal delivery route
Defs: A plan specification that if realized, is realized by the delivery of mail to some facility or mailbox within some geographical region.

label: submucosa of esophagus
Defs: A submucosa that is part of a esophagus [Automatically generated definition].

label: ecdysial line
Defs: The anatomical line of weakness of the cuticle that allows molting and coincides with a suture.

label: positive regulation of skeletal muscle fiber differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of skeletal muscle fiber differentiation.

label: hydrocephalic
Defs: A structural quality which is held by a bearer when the latter exhibits an excessive accumulation of cerebral spinal fluid.

label: dark brown
Defs: A color consisting of brown hue and low brightness.

label: vascular endothelial growth factor receptor 2
Defs: A vascular endothelial growth factor receptor that is a translation product of the human KDR gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: positive regulation of gluconeogenesis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of gluconeogenesis.

label: regulation of actin cytoskeleton organization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising actin filaments and their associated proteins.

label: neuron cellular homeostasis
Defs: The cellular homeostatic process that preserves a neuron in a stable, differentiated functional and structural state.

label: protein localization to Golgi apparatus
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a location within the Golgi apparatus.

label: poorly ossified
Defs: A quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s possessing only minor levels of ossification.

label: apoptotic process
Defs: A programmed cell death process which begins when a cell receives an internal (e.g. DNA damage) or external signal (e.g. an extracellular death ligand), and proceeds through a series of biochemical events (signaling pathway phase) which trigger an execution phase. The execution phase is the last step of an apoptotic process, and is typically characterized by rounding-up of the cell, retraction of pseudopodes, reduction of cellular volume (pyknosis), chromatin condensation, nuclear fragmentation (karyorrhexis), plasma membrane blebbing and fragmentation of the cell into apoptotic bodies. When the execution phase is completed, the cell has died.

label: ectoderm-derived structure
Defs: An anatomical structure that develops (entirely or partially) from the ectoderm.

label: hepatic sinusoid
Defs: Wide thin-walled blood vessels in the liver. In mammals they have neither veinous or arterial markers.

label: phenotypic sex
Defs: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s physical expression of sexual characteristics.

label: response to organic cyclic compound
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an organic cyclic compound stimulus.

label: pharyngeal arch system
Defs: A transient embryonic complex that comprises the pharyngeal arches, bulges of tissues of mesoderm and neural crest derivation through which pass nerves and pharyngeal arch arteries. The arches are separated internally by pharyngeal pouches, evaginations of foregut endoderm, and externally by pharyngeal clefts, invaginations of surface ectoderm. The development of the system ends when the stucture it contributes to are forming, which may include (depending on species) the thymus, thyroid, parathyroids, maxilla, mandible, aortic arch, cardiac outflow tract, external and middle ear[GO,modified].

label: myocardium
Defs: The middle layer of the heart, comprised mainly of striated cardiac muscle fibers.

label: postabdomen
Defs: The region of cuticle of the insect abdomen that is anteriorly connected to the preabdomen.

label: short term hematopoietic stem cell
Defs: A hematopoietic stem cell capable of rapid replenishment of myeloerythroid progenitors and limited self renewal capability. This cell is Kit-positive, Sca1-positive, CD34-positive, CD150-positive, and is Flt3-negative.

label: depth
Defs: A 1-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s downward or backward or inward dimension.

label: ectoderm development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the ectoderm over time, from its formation to the mature structure. In animal embryos, the ectoderm is the outer germ layer of the embryo, formed during gastrulation.

label: angiogenesis
Defs: Blood vessel formation when new vessels emerge from the proliferation of pre-existing blood vessels.

label: learning or memory
Defs: The acquisition and processing of information and/or the storage and retrieval of this information over time.

label: regulation of neutrophil migration
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of neutrophil migration.

label: anterior/posterior pattern specification
Defs: The regionalization process in which specific areas of cell differentiation are determined along the anterior-posterior axis. The anterior-posterior axis is defined by a line that runs from the head or mouth of an organism to the tail or opposite end of the organism.

label: divalent inorganic anion
Defs: Any inorganic anion with a valency of two.

label: medial scapo-pedicellar muscle
Defs: The cranio-antennal muscle that is attached to the scapus and the pedicellus.

label: carboxylic acid anion
Defs: The conjugate base formed when the carboxy group of a carboxylic acid is deprotonated.

label: negative regulation of Schwann cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that decreases the frequency or extent of the multiplication or reproduction of Schwann cells, resulting in the expansion of their population. Schwann cells are a type of glial cell in the peripheral nervous system.

label: decreased tendency
Defs: A tendency which is relatively low.

label: medulla oblongata maturation
Defs: A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for the medulla oblongata to attain its fully functional state. The medulla oblongata lies directly above the spinal cord and controls vital autonomic functions such as digestion, breathing and the control of heart rate.

label: neurula embryo
Defs: An embryo at the neurula stage.

label: agenesis
Defs: Absence of a tissue or organ due to failure to develop.

label: filamentous
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having thin filamentous extensions at its edge.

label: cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which relatively unspecialized cells, e.g. embryonic or regenerative cells, acquire specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize the cells, tissues, or organs of the mature organism or some other relatively stable phase of the organism\'s life history. Differentiation includes the processes involved in commitment of a cell to a specific fate and its subsequent development to the mature state.

label: regulation of microvillus assembly
Defs: A process that modulates the formation of a microvillus.

label: celiac artery
Defs: The first major branch of the abdominal aorta.

label: epithelial bud
Defs: A bud is a protrusion that forms from an epithelial sheet by localized folding.

label: smooth muscle sphincter
Defs: A ring of smooth muscle cells whose contraction closes the opening of the ring.

label: anal field
Defs: The posterior region of the insect wing.

label: regulation of fat cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of adipocyte differentiation.

label: intratelencephalic projecting
Defs: A neuron projection quality that is a characteristic of neurons with both soma and projections entirely within the telencephalon.

label: positive regulation of neuron projection development
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of neuron projection development. Neuron projection development is the process whose specific outcome is the progression of a neuron projection over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A neuron projection is any process extending from a neural cell, such as axons or dendrites (collectively called neurites).

label: mesentery of rectum
Defs: A mesentery that is part of a rectum [Automatically generated definition].

label: normal sensitivity toward
Defs: A sensitivity toward an external stimulus which is relatively normal or average

label: sulfate transmembrane transport
Defs: The directed movement of sulfate across a membrane.

label: vascular associated smooth muscle cell migration
Defs: The orderly movement of a vascular associated smooth muscle cell from one site to another.

label: retinal cone cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized features of a retinal cone cell.

label: chemical entity
Defs: A chemical entity is a physical entity of interest in chemistry including molecular entities, parts thereof, and chemical substances.

label: negative regulation of cellular amino acid metabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving amino acid.

label: spleen smooth muscle
Defs: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a spleen [Automatically generated definition].

label: patients section
Defs: A part of a document about the patients that participated in a study.

label: brachiocephalic artery
Defs: The short first aortic arch branch and divides into the right subclavian artery and the right common carotid artery.

label: negative regulation of immune system process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of an immune system process.

label: cuticular spine
Defs: The cuticular protrusion of a sclerite that is sharp.

label: cell-cell adhesion mediator activity
Defs: The binding by a cell-adhesion protein on the cell surface to an extracellular matrix component, to mediate adhesion of the cell to another cell.

label: solvent
Defs: A liquid that can dissolve other substances (solutes) without any change in their chemical composition.

label: animal zygote
Defs: Diploid cell produced by the fusion of sperm cell nucleus and egg cell.

label: enclosed anatomical space
Defs: An anatomical space with no opening to another space or to the exterior.

label: fibrillary
Defs: A composition quaity inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing of or pertaining to fibrils, or nanoscale fibers.

label: foregut-midgut junction gland
Defs: A gland that is part of a foregut-midgut junction.

label: spiculum
Defs: The apodeme on the anterior margin of abdominal sternite VIII.

label: moderate increased temperature
Defs: A temperature which is increased by a medium degree.

label: trochantero-femoral conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that encircles the femur by joining the distal margin of the trochanter and the proximal margin of the femur.

label: cerebral cortex neuron differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a neuron residing in the cerebral cortex.

label: postoccipital phragma
Defs: The phragma that is continuous with the postocciput.

label: palpigero-palpal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the labium that connects the palpiger and the labial palpus.

label: intersomitic vessel
Defs: One of the primary blood vessel sprouts that originate from the dorsal aorta and posterior cardinal vein and align dorsoventrally at the myotomal boundaries between somites.

label: peptide binding
Defs: Binding to a peptide, an organic compound comprising two or more amino acids linked by peptide bonds.

label: skin epithelium
Defs: Any region of epithelium that is part of a skin region.

label: positive regulation of hemopoiesis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of hemopoiesis.

label: positive regulation of neutrophil migration
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of neutrophil migration.

label: trachea cartilage development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the tracheal cartilage over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Cartilage is a connective tissue dominated by extracellular matrix containing collagen type II and large amounts of proteoglycan, particularly chondroitin sulfate.

label: epithelial cell of gall bladder
Defs: An epithelial cell that is part of the gallbladder.

label: phenols
Defs: Organic aromatic compounds having one or more hydroxy groups attached to a benzene or other arene ring.

label: endothelial cell of viscerocranial mucosa
Defs: An endothelial cell found in the mucosa associated with the facial skeleton.

label: endothelium of trachea
Defs: An endothelium that is part of a trachea.

label: myeloperoxidase (mouse)
Defs: A myeloperoxidase that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: positive regulation of multicellular organismal process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of an organismal process, any of the processes pertinent to the function of an organism above the cellular level; includes the integrated processes of tissues and organs.

label: pseudostratified columnar epithelium
Defs: A simple columnar epithelium that looks stratified but is not, because its cells are arranged with their nuclei at different levels.

label: anaerobic
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s independence on oxygen.

label: surface of epithelium
Defs: An anatomical boundary that adjacent_to a epithelium.

label: chondrocyte
Defs: Skeletogenic cell that is terminally differentiated, secretes an avascular, GAG-rich matrix, is embedded in cartilage tissue matrix, retains the ability to divide, and develops from a chondroblast cell.

label: dorsal-ventral axis
Defs: An axis that is approximately perpendicular to the anterior-posterior axis and that extends through the horizontal plane of the body.

label: positive regulation of catalytic activity
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the activity of an enzyme.

label: regulation of developmental process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of development, the biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of a multicellular organism over time from an initial condition (e.g. a zygote, or a young adult) to a later condition (e.g. a multicellular animal or an aged adult).

label: response to acetylcholine
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an acetylcholine stimulus.

label: positive regulation of cardiac ventricle formation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac ventricle formation.

label: apical side
Defs: Anatomical side that is located on the apical end of an organism or structure.

label: cuticular tendon
Defs: The usually cylindircal evagination of the cuticle that is resilin rich and is continuous with somatic muscles.

label: cerebral cortex cell migration
Defs: The orderly movement of cells from one site to another in the cerebral cortex.

label: deviation
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s changed direction of position towards another entity.

label: negative regulation of establishment or maintenance of neuroblast polarity
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of establishment or maintenance of neuroblast polarity.

label: mesenchymal cell migration
Defs: The orderly movement of a mesenchymal cell from one site to another, often during the development of a multicellular organism.

label: regulation of motor neuron apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of motor neuron apoptotic process.

label: regulation of protein kinase activity
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein kinase activity.

label: regulation of protein localization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of any process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a specific location.

label: cathepsin K
Defs: A cathepsin-like protease that is a translation product of the human CTSK gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: organic sulfate
Defs: Compounds of the general formula SO3HOR where R is an organyl group

label: sinoatrial node cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a sinoatrial (SA) node cell. SA node cells are pacemaker cells that are found in the sinoatrial node.

label: dorsal margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the dorsal side of body or body part.

label: T cell homeostatic proliferation
Defs: The non-specific expansion of T cell populations within a whole or part of an organism to reach to a total number of T cells which will then remain stable over time in the absence of an external stimulus.

label: cell migration involved in vasculogenesis
Defs: The orderly movement of a cell from one site to another that will contribute to the differentiation of an endothelial cell that will form de novo blood vessels and tubes.

label: abdominal sternite
Defs: The sclerite of the insect abdomen that is ventral and medial.

label: macrophage chemotaxis
Defs: The movement of a macrophage in response to an external stimulus.

label: lip skeletal muscle
Defs: A portion of skeletal muscle tissue that is part of a lip [Automatically generated definition].

label: enucleate erythrocyte development
Defs: The process aimed at the progression of an enucleate erythrocyte over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell.

label: vesicle targeting, to, from or within Golgi
Defs: The process in which vesicles are directed to specific destination membranes during transport to, from or within the Golgi apparatus; mediated by the addition of specific coat proteins, including COPI and COPII proteins and clathrin, to the membrane during vesicle formation.

label: trachea gland development
Defs: The progression of a trachea gland over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Trachea glands are found under the mucus of the trachea and secrete mucus, and agents that help protect the lung from injury and infection.

label: intestinal epithelial cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a columnar/cuboidal epithelial cell of the intestine.

label: mesothelial cell of parietal peritoneum
Defs: A mesothelial cell that is part of the parietal peritoneum.

label: extracellular matrix binding
Defs: Binding to a component of the extracellular matrix.

label: basement membrane collagen trimer
Defs: Any collagen timer that is part of a basement membrane.

label: positive regulation of acetylcholine secretion, neurotransmission
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of acetylcholine.

label: insect region of integument
Defs: A region of cuticle and its underlying epidermis.

label: somatopleure
Defs: A structure created during embryogenesis when the lateral mesoderm splits into two layers - the outer (or somatic) layer becomes applied to the inner surface of the ectoderm, and with it forms the somatopleure.[WP].

label: germinal neuroepithelium
Defs: The single layer of epithelial cells that lines the early neural tube and develops into the nervous system and into the neural crest cells.

label: flexible
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability of being turned, bowed, or twisted without breaking.

label: single nucleate cell
Defs: A cell with a single nucleus.

label: positive regulation of collagen metabolic process
Defs: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the metabolism of collagen, any of a group of fibrous proteins of very high tensile strength that form the main component of connective tissue in animals.

label: brood viability
Defs: A reproductive quality inhering in the young of an animal by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to survive and develop normally.

label: neural cell adhesion molecule 1
Defs: A neural cell adhesion molecule NCAM that is a translation product of the human NCAM1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: heteroatomic molecular entity
Defs: A molecular entity consisting of two or more chemical elements.

label: establishment of protein localization to chromatin
Defs: The directed movement of a protein to a part of a chromosome that is organized into chromatin.

label: obsolete2_binary digital entity
Defs: A binary digital entity is a digital entity that is encoded in a way that is not easily human readable and that contains other than text characters.

label: fragility
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to being damaged or destroyed.

label: pectoral appendage cartilage tissue
Defs: A cartilage tissue that is part of a pectoral appendage.

label: blastocyst development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the blastocyst over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The mammalian blastocyst is a hollow ball of cells containing two cell types, the inner cell mass and the trophectoderm.

label: monocyte
Defs: Myeloid mononuclear recirculating leukocyte that can act as a precursor of tissue macrophages, osteoclasts and some populations of tissue dendritic cells.

label: notochord formation
