Defs: The formation of the notochord from the chordamesoderm. The notochord is composed of large cells packed within a firm connective tissue sheath and is found in all chordates at the ventral surface of the neural tube. In vertebrates, the notochord contributes to the vertebral column.

label: pre-publication history section
Defs: A part of the document about the publication history of a document. This section typically details dates of document submission to a journal and dates of any re-submissions as well as reviewer comments and responses to reviewers by the authors.

label: protein catabolic process at presynapse
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a protein at a presynapse.

label: hypodermis
Defs: Lowermost layer of the integumentary system in vertebrates. Types of cells that are found in the hypodermis are fibroblasts, adipose cells, and macrophages. It is derived from the mesoderm, but unlike the dermis, it is not derived from the dermatome region of the mesoderm. The hypodermis is used mainly for fat storage[WP].

label: alpha-adrenergic drug
Defs: Any drug that acts on an alpha-adrenergic receptor.

label: positive regulation of bleb assembly
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of bleb assembly.

label: photoreceptor cell differentiation
Defs: The specialization of organization of a photoreceptor, a cell that responds to incident electromagnetic radiation, particularly visible light. An example of this process is found in Drosophila melanogaster.

label: subdivision of digestive tract
Defs: A proximal-distal subdivision of the digestive tract.

label: superelliptic
Defs: A shape constituting a transition between a rectangle and a circle; a closed curve, of which the circle and ellipse are special cases, whose parametric equation is x = a.cos2/rt, y = b.cos2/rt

label: descending aorta development
Defs: The progression of the descending aorta over time, from its initial formation to the mature structure. The descending aorta is the portion of the aorta in a two-pass circulatory system from the arch of aorta to the point where it divides into the common iliac arteries. In a two-pass circulatory system blood passes twice through the heart to supply the body once.

label: pancreatic A cell development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a pancreatic A cell over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A pancreatic A cell is a cell in the pancreas that secretes glucagon.

label: norepinephrine metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving norepinephrine, a hormone secreted by the adrenal medulla, and a neurotransmitter in the sympathetic peripheral nervous system and in some tracts in the central nervous system. It is also the demethylated biosynthetic precursor of epinephrine.

label: heterocycle metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving heterocyclic compounds, those with a cyclic molecular structure and at least two different atoms in the ring (or rings).

label: myocardial endocrine cell
Defs: The myoendocrine cellis a specialized myocyte localized mainly in the right and left atrial appendages, and also scattered within other areas of the atria and along the conductive system in the ventricular septum. The most conspicuous feature distinguishing myoendocrine cells from other atrial myoctyes is the presence of membane-bounded secretory granules (these granules contain precursor of cardiodilatins or atrial natriuretic polypeptides).

label: stem cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a stem cell. A stem cell is a cell that retains the ability to divide and proliferate throughout life to provide progenitor cells that can differentiate into specialized cells.

label: transformed to
Defs: A morphological quality between two bearers inhering that one bearer is subject to change the nature, function, or condition of itself to become the other.

label: positive regulation of cardiac chamber formation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac chamber formation.

label: response to abiotic stimulus
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an abiotic (not derived from living organisms) stimulus.

label: indole alkaloid biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of an indole alkaloid, an alkaloid containing an indole skeleton.

label: taste bud morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the taste bud are generated and organized. The taste bud is a specialized area of the tongue that contains taste receptors.

label: acyl group
Defs: An organic group formed by removing one or more hydroxy groups from an oxoacid that has the general structure RkE(=O)l(OH)m (l =/= 0). Although the term is almost always applied to organic compounds, with carboxylic acid as the oxoacid, acyl groups can in principle be derived from other types of acids such as sulfonic acids or phosphonic acids.

label: establishment of cell polarity
Defs: The specification and formation of anisotropic intracellular organization or cell growth patterns.

label: scaly
Defs: A texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being covered or partially covered with scales.

label: placental vein
Defs: A vein that is part of the placenta.

label: negative regulation of nervous system process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of a neurophysiological process.

label: normal odor
Defs: An odor quality of having relatively normal or average odor.

label: separated from
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s not being in contact with another entity, or of no longer being connected or joined with another entity.

label: low brightness
Defs: A color brightness which is relatively low.

label: thoracic vein
Defs: A vein that is part of a thorax [Automatically generated definition].

label: axial to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located towards the central axis of the organism or an extremity.

label: metapleuro-metasternal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the metathorax that joins the metapleura and the metasternum.

label: differentiated from
Defs: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being morphologically distinguishable from another entity.

label: carbohydrate transport
Defs: The directed movement of carbohydrate into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Carbohydrates are a group of organic compounds based of the general formula Cx(H2O)y.

label: cytoplasm
Defs: The contents of a cell excluding the plasma membrane and nucleus, but including other subcellular structures.

label: supplementary material to a document
Defs: A part of a document that is segregated from the rest of the document due to its size

label: cervical spinal cord gray matter
Defs: A gray matter of spinal cord that is part of a cervical spinal cord.

label: negative regulation of myotube differentiation
Defs: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of myotube differentiation. Myotube differentiation is the process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a myotube cell. Myotubes are multinucleated cells that are formed when proliferating myoblasts exit the cell cycle, differentiate and fuse.

label: intrahepatic bile duct
Defs: Passages within the liver for the conveyance of bile. Includes right and left hepatic ducts even though these may join outside the liver to form the common hepatic duct.

label: anatomical structure formation involved in morphogenesis
Defs: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of an anatomical structure from unspecified parts. This process begins with the specific processes that contribute to the appearance of the discrete structure and ends when the structural rudiment is recognizable. An anatomical structure is any biological entity that occupies space and is distinguished from its surroundings. Anatomical structures can be macroscopic such as a carpel, or microscopic such as an acrosome.

label: glutamine family amino acid biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of amino acids of the glutamine family, comprising arginine, glutamate, glutamine and proline.

label: jaw skeleton
Defs: Subdivision of skeleton which includes upper and lower jaw skeletons.

label: postdisplaced growth
Defs: A paedomorphic growth quality which is due to a delayed onset.

label: oocyte development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an oocyte over time, from initial commitment of the cell to its specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell.

label: positive regulation of glycoprotein biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a glycoprotein, a protein that contains covalently bound glycose (i.e. monosaccharide) residues; the glycose occurs most commonly as oligosaccharide or fairly small polysaccharide but occasionally as monosaccharide.

label: non-neurogenic ectodermal placode
Defs: Ectodermal placode that does not develop into a component of the nervous system.

label: stacked
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being positioned with multiple entities of the same type above and below.

label: multipolar neuron morphology
Defs: A cell morphology that inheres in neurons which possess three or more neurites, usually a single axon and many dendrites and dendritic branches.

label: myoblast
Defs: A cell that is commited to differentiating into a muscle cell.  Embryonic myoblasts develop from the mesoderm. They undergo proliferation, migrate to their various sites, and then differentiate into the appropriate form of myocytes.  Myoblasts also occur as transient populations of cells in muscles undergoing repair.

label: Purkinje myocyte to ventricular cardiac muscle cell signaling
Defs: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from a Purkinje myocyte to a ventricular cardiac muscle cell.

label: parenchyma of spleen
Defs: A parenchyma that is part of a spleen.

label: negative regulation of pharynx morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of pharynx morphogenesis.

label: cellular response to peptide hormone stimulus
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a peptide hormone stimulus. A peptide hormone is any of a class of peptides that are secreted into the blood stream and have endocrine functions in living animals.

label: neurotransmitter receptor complex
Defs: Any protein complex that is capable of functioning as a neurotransmitter receptor.

label: cardiac muscle tissue of myocardium
Defs: A portion of cardiac muscle tissue that is part of a myocardium [Automatically generated definition].

label: velocity
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s rate of change of the position.

label: fluorescence
Defs: A luminous flux quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s emitting longer wavelength light following the absorption of shorter wavelength radiation; fluorescence is common with aromatic compounds with several rings joined together.

label: positive regulation of dendritic cell chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of dendritic cell chemotaxis.

label: eye development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the eye over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The eye is the organ of sight.

label: squama
Defs: The seta that is flat.

label: regulation of protein catabolic process at synapse, modulating synaptic transmission
Defs: Any process that modulates synaptic transmission by regulating protein degradation at the synapse.

label: pulvinate
Defs: A convex 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being shaped like a cushion or has a marked convex cushion-like form.

label: active ion transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of an ion from one side of a membrane to the other up the solute\'s concentration gradient. This is carried out by binding the solute and undergoing a series of conformational changes. Transport works equally well in either direction.

label: cellular component assembly involved in morphogenesis
Defs: The cellular component assembly that is part of the initial shaping of the component during its developmental progression.

label: regular connective tissue
Defs: Connective tissue, which consists of fibroblasts, the intercellular matrix of which contains a regular network of collagen and elastic fiber bundles. Examples: bone (tissue), cartilage (tissue), dense regular connective tissue.

label: small intestine glandular cell
Defs: A glandular cell found in the epithelium of the small intestine. Example: Enterocytes, Goblet cells, enteroendocrine cells; Paneth cells; M cells; Somatostatin-secreting Cells (D-cells) .

label: enzyme binding
Defs: Binding to an enzyme, a protein with catalytic activity.

label: role
Defs: A realizable entity  the manifestation of which brings about some result or end that is not essential to a continuant  in virtue of the kind of thing that it is but that can be served or participated in by that kind of continuant  in some kinds of natural, social or institutional contexts.

label: anatomical margin
Defs: Fiat anatomical region extending a short distance from the boundary of an object inwards.

label: intestinal lipid catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown into fatty acids and monoglycerides of lipids in the small intestine. Lipids are broken down by lipases released by the pancreas.

label: uncoiled
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being not curled or wound (especially in concentric rings or spirals).

label: negative regulation of mitotic chromosome condensation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of mitotic chromosome condensation.

label: laminar
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s processing the form of a thin plate sheet or layer.

label: regulation of insulin receptor signaling pathway
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of insulin receptor signaling.

label: stipito-lacinial conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect maxilla that connects the stipes and the lacinia.

label: tufted pyramidal neuron
Defs: A pyramidal neuron which has a distinctive tuft formation, distal from the soma.

label: cathepsin K (mouse)
Defs: A cathepsin K that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: lung epithelial cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of an epithelial cell that contributes to the epithelium of the lung.

label: drooping
Defs: To bent or hang downwards.

label: negative regulation of leukocyte proliferation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of leukocyte proliferation.

label: metencephalon sulcus limitans
Defs: A sulcus limitans of neural tube that is part of a future metencephalon.

label: meninx of hindbrain
Defs: A meninx that is part of a hindbrain [Automatically generated definition].

label: negative regulation of vascular endothelial cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of vascular endothelial cell proliferation.

label: peripheral blood mononuclear cell
Defs: A leukocyte with a single non-segmented nucleus in the mature form found in the circulatory pool of blood.

label: material information bearer
Defs: A material entity in which a concretization of an information content entity inheres.

label: cell proliferation in forebrain
Defs: The creation of greater cell numbers in the forebrain due to cell division of progenitor cells.

label: regulation of sodium ion transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of sodium ions (Na+) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: organic anion transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of organic anions from one side of a membrane to the other. Organic anions are atoms or small molecules with a negative charge which contain carbon in covalent linkage.

label: oblanceolate
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being extended along a straight line, and is shaped like a reversed lance-point, with the tapering point attached to the leafstalk.

label: positive regulation of glial cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the rate or extent of glial cell proliferation.

label: decreased length
Defs: A length quality which is relatively small.

label: intrahepatic bile duct epithelium
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a intrahepatic bile duct [Automatically generated definition].

label: trigeminal nerve muscle
Defs: Muscle innervated by the trigeminal nerve (Cranial Nerve V).

label: decreased mobility
Defs: A mobility which is relative low.

label: skeletal muscle tissue of eye
Defs: A portion of skeletal muscle tissue that is part of a eye [Automatically generated definition].

label: thickness
Defs: A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the dimension through an object as opposed to its length or width.

label: regulation of cellular catabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of substances, carried out by individual cells.

label: cardiac ventricle fibroblast
Defs: Any fibroblast that is part of a cardiac ventricle.

label: protein localization to microtubule
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained at, a microtubule.

label: main body axis
Defs: A principle subdivision of an organism that includes all structures along the primary axis, typically the anterior-posterior axis, from head to tail, including structures of the body proper where present (for example, ribs), but excluding appendages.

label: impact-fractured
Defs: A fractured quality in which one of the fragments is driven into another fragment.

label: positive regulation of vascular associated smooth muscle cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of vascular smooth muscle cell differentiation.

label: anatomical space
Defs: Non-material anatomical entity of three dimensions, that is generated by morphogenetic or other physiologic processes; is surrounded by one or more anatomical structures; contains one or more organism substances or anatomical structures.

label: self-renewal
Defs: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having the ability to go through numerous cycles of cell division while maintaining the undifferentiated state.

label: uterus development
Defs: The reproductive developmental process whose specific outcome is the progression of the uterus over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: sterile
Defs: A fertility quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being incapable of initiating, sustaining, or supporting reproduction.

label: drug
Defs: Any substance which when absorbed into a living organism may modify one or more of its functions. The term is generally accepted for a substance taken for a therapeutic purpose, but is also commonly used for abused substances.

label: submucosa of right hepatic duct
Defs: A submucosa that is part of a right hepatic duct [Automatically generated definition].

label: temporal bone
Defs: The large, irregular bone located at the base and side of the skull; consists of three parts at birth: squamous, tympanic, and petrous.

label: neoplastic, non-malignant
Defs: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition not to progress, invade surrounding tissues or metastasize.

label: sodium ion transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of sodium ions (Na+) from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: distance
Defs: A quality that is the extent of space between two entities.

label: positive regulation of cell division
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cell division.

label: postero-lateral margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the postero-lateral region of the body or body part.

label: revolute
Defs: A curled quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s edges of its surface being rolled backwards spirally on each side.

label: glucose transmembrane transport
Defs: The process in which glucose is transported across a membrane.

label: positive regulation of mononuclear cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of mononuclear cell proliferation.

label: compound eye retinal cell programmed cell death
Defs: Programmed cell death that occurs in the retina to remove excess cells between ommatidia, thus resulting in a hexagonal lattice, precise with respect to cell number and position surrounding each ommatidium.

label: bone of pectoral complex
Defs: A bone that is part of a pectoral complex. Examples: scapula, manus phalanx, any carpal bone, any bone of the pectoral fin.

label: insect articulation
Defs: The region of cuticle that is composed two articular surfaces that are adjacent to each other.

label: mucosa of left hepatic duct
Defs: A mucosa that is part of a left hepatic duct [Automatically generated definition].

label: extracellular membrane-bounded organelle
Defs: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function, bounded by a lipid bilayer membrane and occurring outside the cell.

label: negative regulation of cilium-dependent cell motility
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cilium-dependent cell motility.

label: membrane bone morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which bone which forms deep in the organism are generated and organized.

label: stromal cell of anorectum lamina propria
Defs: A stromal cell found in the lamina propria of the anorectum.

label: pancreatic lobule
Defs: A dense accumulation of exocrine glands in the pancreas often surrounding islets of Langerhans.

label: positive regulation of translational elongation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of translational elongation.

label: cilium assembly
Defs: The assembly of a cilium, a specialized eukaryotic organelle that consists of a filiform extrusion of the cell surface. Each cilium is bounded by an extrusion of the cytoplasmic membrane, and contains a regular longitudinal array of microtubules, anchored basally in a centriole.

label: fenestrated capillary
Defs: Capillary that has pores in the endothelial cells (60-80 nm in diameter) that are spanned by a diaphragm of radially oriented fibrils and allow small molecules and limited amounts of protein to diffuse.

label: adipose tissue development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of adipose tissue over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Adipose tissue is specialized tissue that is used to store fat.

label: regulation of AV node cell action potential
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of action potential creation, propagation or termination in an atrioventricular node myocyte. This typically occurs via modulation of the activity or expression of voltage-gated ion channels.

label: bitufted neuron
Defs: A type of interneuron that has two clusters of dendritic branches that originate directly from the soma and extend in opposite directions and axons that form a plexus which spreads widely. Compared to bipolar neurons, bitufted neurons have branching that occur close to the soma.

label: pterothorax
Defs: The region of cuticle of the insect thorax that contains the mesothorax and the metathorax and bears the mid legs, the hind legs and the wings.

label: catechol-containing compound catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of catechol-containing compounds. Catechol is a compound containing a pyrocatechol nucleus or substituent.

label: table of figures
Defs: A table that relates figures in a document to specific locations in that document (usually page numbers).  This is also a document part (subsumption there should be inferred).

label: cell projection membrane
Defs: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding a plasma membrane bounded cell surface projection.

label: pancreatic endocrine cell
Defs: An endocrine cell that is part of the pancreas.

label: posteroexternal cranio-mandibular muscle
Defs: The cranio-mandibular muscle that extends between the gena and the lateral margin of the insect mandible.

label: epithelium of female gonad
Defs: An epithelium surrounding an ovary.

label: negative regulation of cell activation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cell activation.

label: primiparous
Defs: A viviparous organism having given birth one time.

label: cellular response to nitrogen compound
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a nitrogen compound stimulus.

label: vasculature of retina
Defs: A vasculature that is part of a retina [Automatically generated definition].

label: metepimeron
Defs: The epimeron on the posterior region of the metapleuron and lateral to the metaventrite.

label: skeleton of right pelvic girdle
Defs: A skeleton of pelvic girdle that is part of a right pelvic girdle region.

label: regulation of cell motility
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell motility.

label: proportionality to
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s magnitude in respect to a related entity.

label: protein transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of a protein from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: negative regulation of lymphocyte chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of lymphocyte chemotaxis.

label: anterior chamber of eyeball
Defs: The space in the eye, filled with aqueous humor, and bounded anteriorly by the cornea and a small portion of the sclera and posteriorly by a small portion of the ciliary body, the iris, and part of the crystalline lens.

label: cyclic cyclicity
Defs: Cyclic cyclicity inheres in a molecule when the atoms of the molecule do contain at least one cycle in the atom-atom connection paths (through bonds).

label: increased frequency
Defs: A frequency which is relatively high.

label: scaphoid
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being shaped like a boat.

label: obsolescence reason specification
Defs: The reason for which a term has been deprecated. The allowed values come from an enumerated list of predefined terms. See the specification of these instances for more detailed definitions of each enumerated value.

label: visceral peritoneum development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a visceral peritoneum over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: bone development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of bone over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Bone is the hard skeletal connective tissue consisting of both mineral and cellular components.

label: positive regulation of apoptotic process involved in development
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of apoptotic process involved in development.

label: negative regulation of signal transduction
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of signal transduction.

label: surfactant homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of a steady-state level of the surface-active lipoprotein mixture which coats the alveoli.

label: dicarboxylic acid transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of dicarboxylic acids from one side of a membrane to the other. A dicarboxylic acid is an organic acid with two COOH groups.

label: presumptive structure
Defs: Portion of embryonic tissue determined by fate mapping to become a structure.

label: regulation of cell population proliferation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell proliferation.

label: transverse orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed transversely.

label: negative regulation of exocytosis
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of exocytosis.

label: cuticle of insect mandible
Defs: The cuticle of the mouthpart and sclerite between the cuticle of the labrum and the cuticle of the insect maxilla that is attached to the head capsule by the oral foraminal conjunctiva and the cranio-mandibular muscle.

label: heart rudiment morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the heart rudiment are generated and organized.

label: right common carotid artery plus branches
Defs: The rightmost of the two common carotid arteries, originating from in the neck from the brachiocephalic trunk.

label: translation at presynapse, modulating chemical synaptic transmission
Defs: Translation that occurs at the presynapse, and that modulates chemical synaptic transmission.

label: natural killer cell receptor 2B4 (mouse)
Defs: A natural killer cell receptor 2B4 that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: synovial membrane of synovial tendon sheath
Defs: Synovial sac which surrounds parts of one or more tendons. Examples: synovial tendon sheath of manual digit 2, radial bursa.

label: endothelial cell of hepatic portal vein
Defs: An endothelial cell that is part of a hepatic portal vein.

label: intrinsic component of organelle membrane
Defs: The component of the organelle membrane consisting of the gene products and protein complexes having either part of their peptide sequence embedded in the hydrophobic region of the membrane or some other covalently attached group such as a GPI anchor that is similarly embedded in the membrane.

label: stomach lumen
Defs: The anatomical space that is enclosed by a stomach.

label: increased variability of temperature
Defs: A variability of temperature which is relatively high.

label: graph
Defs: A diagram that presents one or more tuples of information by mapping those tuples in to a two dimensional space in a non arbitrary way.

label: hepatic portal vein
Defs: A portal vein that transports nutrients from the digestive tract to the liver[Kardong].

label: ion transmembrane transport
Defs: A process in which an ion is transported across a membrane.

label: irregular rhythm
Defs: A rhythm quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking rhythm lacking pattern.

label: multi-potent skeletal muscle stem cell
Defs: A multifate stem cell found in skeletal muscle than can differentiate into many different cell types, including muscle. Distinct cell type from satellite cell.

label: anterior chamber epithelium
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a anterior chamber of eyeball.

label: negative regulation of RNA binding
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of RNA binding.

label: anal fold
Defs: The insect wing fold that is posterior to the postcubitus and separates the costal field and the anal field.

label: oocyte maturation
Defs: A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for an oocyte to attain its fully functional state. Oocyte maturation commences after reinitiation of meiosis commonly starting with germinal vesicle breakdown, and continues up to the second meiotic arrest prior to fertilization.

label: dorsolateral orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed dorsolaterally.

label: negative regulation of extracellular matrix assembly
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of extracellular matrix assembly.

label: positive regulation of kinase activity
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of kinase activity, the catalysis of the transfer of a phosphate group, usually from ATP, to a substrate molecule.

label: maroon
Defs: A color consisting of purple and brown hue.

label: regulation of transporter activity
Defs: Any process that modulates the activity of a transporter.

label: cranio-hypopharyngeal muscle
Defs: The somatic muscle that is attached to the head capsule and the hypopharynx.

label: dorsally rotated
Defs: A rotation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of being rotated towards the back or upper surface of an organism.

label: elongated
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s length being notably higher than its width.

label: defensive cell
Defs: A cell whose primary function is to protect the organism.

label: regulation of endodermal cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of endodermal cell differentiation.

label: negative regulation of axonemal microtubule depolymerization
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the depolymerization of the specialized microtubules of the axoneme.

label: coordinated
Defs: A coordination quality of inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having skillful and effective interaction of movement.

label: negative regulation of phosphate transmembrane transport
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of phosphate transmembrane transport.

label: cuticle of metathorax
Defs: The region of the cuticle of the pterothorax that bears the hind legs and the hind wings.

label: scapal-pedicellar conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the antenna that connects the scapus and the pedicellus.

label: metencephalon
Defs: Rostral segment of the hindbrain that has as its parts the pons (where present) and the cerebellum[WP,modified].

label: cellular response to organic cyclic compound
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an organic cyclic compound stimulus.

label: cardiac neuron development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a cardiac neuron over time, from its formation to the mature state.

label: facial skeleton
Defs: Subdivision of skull that consists of the facial bones.

label: phallobase
Defs: The region of cuticle of the postabdomen that is attached to the abdominal sternite IX by the abdominal sternite IX-phallobase conjunctiva and to the paramere by the phallobasal-parameral conjunctiva.

label: increased flexibility
Defs: A flexibility which is relatively high.

label: regulation of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly.

label: lathlike
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer resembling a thin narrow strip.

label: 6th arch mesenchyme
Defs: Mesenchyme that is part of a pharyngeal arch 6.

label: somatic cell
Defs: A cell of an organism that does not pass on its genetic material to the organism\'s offspring (i.e. a non-germ line cell).

label: tendrilous
Defs: Slender and spirally coiled.

label: epidermal stem cell homeostasis
Defs: Any biological process involved in the maintenance of the steady-state number of epidermal stem cells within a population of cells.

label: skin of head
Defs: A zone of skin that is part of a head [Automatically generated definition].

label: synapse assembly
Defs: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a synapse.  This process ends when the synapse is mature (functional).

label: obsolete parental quality
Defs: A parental quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of exhibiting the characteristic of a parent.

label: positive regulation of neuron maturation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of neuron maturation.

label: cranio-mandibular muscle
Defs: The somatic muscle that is attached to the head capsule and the insect mandible.

label: taste bud
Defs: A specialized receptor organ that is a collection of cells spanning the gustatory epithelium.

label: mature
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting complete growth, differentiation, or development.

label: aldohexose
Defs: A hexose with a (potential) aldehyde group at one end.

label: ammonium ion metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving the ammonium ion.

label: high frequency recombinant
Defs: A mating type that indicates that the F plasmid has integrated into the chromosome.

label: regulation of microtubule nucleation
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of microtubule nucleation. Microtubule nucleation is the \'de novo\' formation of a microtubule, in which tubulin heterodimers form metastable oligomeric aggregates, some of which go on to support formation of a complete microtubule. Microtubule nucleation usually occurs from a specific site within a cell.

label: density plot
Defs: A density plot is a report graph which is a graphical representation of data where the tint of a particular pixel corresponds to some kind of function corresponding the the amount of data points relativelly with their distance from the the pixel.

label: regulation of blood vessel branching
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of blood vessel branching.

label: submucosal esophageal gland
Defs: One of the racemose glands in the walls of the esophagus that in humans are small and serve principally to lubricate the food but in some birds secrete a milky fluid on which the young are fed.

label: smooth muscle of trachea
Defs: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a trachea [Automatically generated definition].

label: positive regulation of synapse assembly
Defs: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of synapse assembly, the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a synapse.

label: glycosaminoglycan catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of glycosaminoglycans, any one of a group of polysaccharides that contain amino sugars.

label: secretion of serous membrane
Defs: A transudate found in the serous sac.

label: cranial neuron projection bundle
Defs: Any of the cranial nerves, or their central nervous system analogs (the optic tract, the epiphyseal tract). These analogs are not true nerves, and are instead evaginated sensory afferents emanating from the brain.

label: mixed endoderm/mesoderm-derived structure
Defs: An anatomical structure that develops from the endoderm and the mesoderm.

label: negative regulation of neurogenesis
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of neurogenesis, the generation of cells within the nervous system.

label: nucleobase-containing compound transport
Defs: The directed movement of nucleobases, nucleosides, nucleotides and nucleic acids, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: response to glucagon
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a glucagon stimulus.

label: delaminated
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking some outer layer.

label: nerve of abdominal segment
Defs: A nerve that is part of an abdominal segment of trunk [Automatically generated definition].

label: tapered size
Defs: A size quality inhering in an entity or set of entities in which size increases or decreases along the extent of the entity or set.

label: regulation of lysosome organization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of lysosome organization.

label: retinal cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in a retinal cell.

label: cellular response to amino acid stimulus
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an amino acid stimulus. An amino acid is a carboxylic acids containing one or more amino groups.

label: stroma of bone marrow
Defs: The stroma of the bone marrow is all tissue not directly involved in the primary function of hematopoiesis. The yellow bone marrow belongs here, and makes the majority of the bone marrow stroma, in addition to stromal cells located in the red bone marrow. Yellow bone marrow is found in the Medullary cavity. Still, the stroma is indirectly involved in hematopoiesis, since it provides the hematopoietic microenvironment that facilitates hematopoiesis by the parenchymal cells. For instance, they generate colony stimulating factors, affecting hematopoiesis.

label: furco-trochanteral muscle
Defs: The insect thoracic muscle that is attached to a furca and to a trochanter.

label: prechordal plate formation
Defs: The formation of the prechordal plate. The prechordal plate is a thickening of the endoderm at the cranial end of the primitive streak formed by the involution of Spemann\'s organizer cells. The prechordal plate and the notochord induce the formation of the neural plate from the overlying ectodermal cells.

label: cuticle of trochanter
Defs: The cuticle of the segment of a leg attached to the distal margin of the coxa by the coxal-trochanteral conjunctiva and to the proximal margin of the femur by the trochantero-femoral conjunctiva.

label: metatibial muscle
Defs: The somatic muscle that inserts in the metatibia.

label: hepatopancreatic ampulla
Defs: A dilation of the duodenal papilla that is the opening of the juncture of the common bile duct and the main pancreatic duct.

label: embryonic heart tube morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the embryonic heart tube are generated and organized. The embryonic heart tube is an epithelial tube that will give rise to the mature heart.

label: negative regulation of keratinocyte apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of keratinocyte apoptotic process.

label: cadherin binding involved in cell-cell adhesion
Defs: Any cadherin binding that occurs as part of the process of cell-cell adhesion.

label: positive regulation of epithelial cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of epithelial cell apoptotic process.

label: neural plate anterior/posterior regionalization
Defs: The process that regulates the coordinated growth and differentiation that establishes the non-random anterior-posterior spatial arrangement of the neural plate.

label: cyan
Defs: A color consisting of green and blue hue.

label: limb development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a limb over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A limb is an appendage of an animal used for locomotion or grasping. Examples include legs, arms or some types of fin.

label: left side of back
Defs: Left part of the organism dorsal to a horizontal plane and bounded on one side by the same transverse plane.

label: regulation of glial cell migration
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of glial cell migration.

label: oligodendrocyte apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in an oligodendrocyte. Oligodendrocytes belong to a class of large neuroglial (macroglial) cells in the central nervous system, where they form the insulating myelin sheath of axons.

label: colon endothelium
Defs: Vascular endothelium found in colon blood vessels.

label: regulation of epithelial cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of epithelial cell differentiation.

label: T-cell antigen CD7 (mouse)
Defs: A CD7 molecule that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: conical
Defs: A convex 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling a cone (a 3-D shape with a round cross section that tapers).

label: central nervous system myelination
Defs: The process in which neuronal axons and dendrites become coated with a segmented lipid-rich sheath (myelin) to enable faster and more energetically efficient conduction of electrical impulses. The sheath is formed by the cell membranes of oligodendrocytes in the central nervous system. Adjacent myelin segments are separated by a non-myelinated stretch of axon called a node of Ranvier.

label: normal height
Defs: A height which is relatively normal or average

label: version number
Defs: A version number is an information content entity which is a sequence of characters borne by part of each of a class of manufactured products or its packaging and indicates its order within a set of other products having the same name.

label: antimicrobial agent
Defs: A substance that kills or slows the growth of microorganisms, including bacteria, viruses, fungi and protozoans.

label: regulation of skeletal muscle tissue growth
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of skeletal muscle growth.

label: mucoid
Defs: A composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s consistency of mucus.

label: regulation of cilium-dependent cell motility
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cilium-dependent cell motility.

label: negative regulation of intracellular lipid transport
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of lipids within cells.

label: meninx of midbrain
Defs: A meninx that is part of a midbrain [Automatically generated definition].

label: phosphoric acid
Defs: A phosphorus oxoacid that consists of one oxo and three hydroxy groups joined covalently to a central phosphorus atom.

label: articular capsule
Defs: An articular capsule (or joint capsule) is an envelope surrounding a synovial joint. [WP,unvetted].

label: uterus or analog
Defs: A subdivision of a the reproductive tract in a female organism that is the site of embryo development.

label: interneuron migration
Defs: The orderly movement of an interneuron from one site to another.

label: west
Defs: West is one of the four cardinal directions or points of the compass. It is the opposite direction from east.

label: cellular response to dopamine
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a dopamine stimulus.

label: skeletal muscle adaptation
Defs: Any process in which skeletal muscles change their phenotypic profiles in response to altered functional demands and a variety of signals.

label: upper-lower gradient
Defs: Anatomical gradient that is distributed along the upper-lower axis.

label: sulfur compound biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of compounds that contain sulfur, such as the amino acids methionine and cysteine or the tripeptide glutathione.

label: binding
Defs: The selective, non-covalent, often stoichiometric, interaction of a molecule with one or more specific sites on another molecule.

label: radius
Defs: The insect wing vein that is posterior to the subcosta and anterior to the media.

label: anatomical structure homeostasis
Defs: A homeostatic process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state within a defined anatomical structure of an organism, including control of cellular proliferation and death and control of metabolic function. An anatomical structure is any biological entity that occupies space and is distinguished from its surroundings. Anatomical structures can be macroscopic such as a carpel, or microscopic such as an acrosome.

label: hepatoblast
Defs: Multi fate stem cell that gives rise to both hepatocytes and cholangiocytes as descendants. The term often refers to fetal precursors of hepatocytes (differently from \'hepatic stem cell\', usually applied to the self-renewing pool of hepatocyte precursors in the adult liver). Hepatoblasts may also be endogenous, as some stem cells found in the liver come from the bone marrow via blood circulation.

label: tunica media
Defs: The middle layer of an artery or vein. [WP,unvetted].

label: negative regulation of heart contraction
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of heart contraction.

label: ciliated epithelium
Defs: Epithelium bearing vibratile cilia on the free surface.

label: cardiac ventricle development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a cardiac ventricle over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A cardiac ventricle receives blood from a cardiac atrium and pumps it out of the heart.

label: efficient
Defs: An efficiency quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having efficiency.

label: signaling receptor inhibitor activity
Defs: Binds to and modulates the activity of a signaling receptor.

label: dermis blood vessel endothelial cell
Defs: Any blood vessel endothelial cell that is part of a dermis.

label: anterior tentorial pit
Defs: The tentorial pit that correspods to the anterior (dorsal in prognathous head) end of the tentorium.

label: migrating mesenchyme population
Defs: Mesenchymal cells that are migrating.

label: protein localization to euchromatin
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a location within an euchromatin.

label: negative regulation of RNA catabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of RNA catabolic process.

label: positive regulation of cellular carbohydrate metabolic process
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, extent or frequency of the chemical reactions and pathways involving carbohydrates, any of a group of organic compounds based of the general formula Cx(H2O)y, as carried out by individual cells.

label: bone of craniocervical region
Defs: A bone that is part of a craniocervical region.

label: flat
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a horizontal surface without a slope, tilt, or curvature.

label: plasma membrane acetate transport
Defs: The directed movement of acetate across a plasma membrane.

label: regulation of mucus secretion
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of mucus from a cell or a tissue.

label: non-ictal
Defs: A physiological state which is characterized by normal electrical activity in neuronal tissue.

label: large intestine smooth muscle
Defs: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a large intestine [Automatically generated definition].

label: postal code
Defs: An identifier that denotes some postal delivery route, some aggregate of postal delivery routes or a geographical region and was created for the purpose of sorting and delivering mail.

label: colored
Defs: A color quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having color.

label: obsolete_report element
Defs: A report element is a narrative object in which information is presented and consumed by a human being, and is part of a report. Examples of report elements are figure (dot plot), table, text portion (may include a movie or audio clip on a web page).

label: endocardial cushion formation
Defs: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of an endocardial cushion. The endocardial cushion is a specialized region of mesenchymal cells that will give rise to the heart septa and valves.

label: digestive tract junction
Defs: An anatomical junction between two parts of the digestive tract.

label: tracheobronchial epithelium
Defs: Epithelium pertaining to the trachea and bronchi.

label: banded collagen fibril
Defs: A supramolecular assembly of fibrillar collagen complexes in the form of a long fiber (fibril) with transverse striations (bands).

label: common hepatic duct
Defs: Predominantly extrahepatic bile duct which is formed by the junction of the right and left hepatic ducts, which are predominantly intrahepatic, and, in turn, joins the cystic duct to form the common bile duct[GAID]. The common hepatic duct is the duct formed by the convergence of the right hepatic duct (which drains bile from the right functional lobe of the liver) and the left hepatic duct (which drains bile from the left functional lobe of the liver). The common hepatic duct then joins the cystic duct coming from the gallbladder to form the common bile duct[WP].

label: embryonic cloacal lumen
Defs: An anatomical space that surrounded_by a embryonic cloaca.

label: amino acid chain
Defs: An organic amino compound that consists of amino acid residues (unmodified amino-acid residues and/or modified amino-acid residues) linked by peptide bonds or derivatives of such bonds.

label: mesenchymal stem cell of abdominal adipose tissue
Defs: Any mesenchymal stem cell of adipose tissue that is part of an abdomen.

label: positive regulation of protein localization to cell periphery
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to cell periphery.

label: cranial nerve morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structure of the cranial nerves are generated and organized. The cranial nerves are composed of twelve pairs of nerves that emanate from the nervous tissue of the hindbrain. These nerves are sensory, motor, or mixed in nature, and provide the motor and general sensory innervation of the head, neck and viscera. They mediate vision, hearing, olfaction and taste and carry the parasympathetic innervation of the autonomic ganglia that control visceral functions.

label: cellular anion homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of anions at the level of a cell.

label: neutrophil activation
Defs: The change in morphology and behavior of a neutrophil resulting from exposure to a cytokine, chemokine, cellular ligand, or soluble factor.

label: external side
Defs: Anatomical surface that is located on the distal side of the body or body part.

label: hyoglossus muscle
Defs: A muscle that attaches to the hyopid bone and to the tongue and is innervated by cranial nerve XII.

label: anterior stroma of cornea
Defs: The anterior segment of the lamellated connective tissue layer of the cornea.

label: apoptotic process involved in tube lumen cavitation
Defs: Any apoptotic process that contributes to the hollowing out of an epithelial rod or cord to form the central hole in a tube.

label: positive regulation of blood vessel branching
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of blood vessel branching.

label: enucleate erythrocyte maturation
Defs: A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for an enucleate erythrocyte to attain its fully functional state. An enucleate erythrocyte is an erythrocyte without a nucleus.

label: ganglion of peripheral nervous system
Defs: A spatially aggregated collection of nerve cell bodies in the PNS, consisting of one or more subpopulations that share cell type, chemical phenotype, and connections. (CUMBO).

label: enteroendocrine cell
Defs: An endocrine cell that is located in the epithelium of the gastrointestinal tract or in the pancreas.

label: antimicrobial humoral immune response mediated by antimicrobial peptide
Defs: An immune response against microbes mediated by anti-microbial peptides in body fluid.

label: regulation of cartilage development
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of cartilage development, the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the cartilage over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Cartilage is a connective tissue dominated by extracellular matrix containing collagen type II and large amounts of proteoglycan, particularly chondroitin sulfate.

label: negative regulation of steroid metabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving steroids.

label: obsolete cellular polarity
Defs: A cellular quality inhering in a cell by virtue of its anisotropic intracellular organization.

label: response to carbamate
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a carbamate stimulus. Carbamates are a group of insecticides and parasiticides that act by inhibiting cholinesterase.

label: positive regulation of production of molecular mediator of immune response
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of the production of molecular mediator of immune response.

label: cytoplasmic microtubule bundle
Defs: Any microtubule bundle that is part of a cytoplasm.

label: symbol
Defs: An information content entity that is a mark(s) or character(s) used as a conventional representation of another entity.

label: cartilaginous neurocranium
Defs: The primitive cartilagionous skeletal structure of the fetal skull that grows to envelop the rapidly growing embyonic brain. In humans, the chondrocranium begins forming at 28 days from mesenchymal condensations and is fully formed between week 7 and 9 of fetal development. While the majority of the chondrocranium is succeeded by the bony skull in most higher vertebrates, some components do persist into adulthood.[1] In Cartilagious fishes and Agnathans, the chondrocranium persist throughout life.[2] Embryologically, the chondrocranium represent the basal cranial structure, and lay the base for the formation of the endocranium in higher vertebrates[WP].

label: ion transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of an ion from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: curved caudal
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved towards the part of the body from which the tail arises.

label: negative regulation of myeloid leukocyte mediated immunity
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of myeloid leukocyte mediated immunity.

label: organic molecule
Defs: Any molecule that consists of at least one carbon atom as part of the electrically neutral entity.

label: medial margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the medial side of the body or body part.

label: proximal to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located more centrally than another entity.

label: appendage
Defs: Major subdivision of an organism that protrudes from the body[DOS, CARO].

label: portal system
Defs: In the circulatory system of animals, a portal venous system occurs when a capillary bed drains into another capillary bed through veins, without first going through the heart. Both capillary beds and the blood vessels that connect them are considered part of the portal venous system. They are relatively uncommon as the majority of capillary beds drain into veins which then drain into the heart, not into another capillary bed. Portal venous systems are considered venous because the blood vessels that join the two capillary beds are either veins or venules. Examples of such systems include the hepatic portal system and the hypophyseal portal system. Unqualified, \'portal venous system\' often refers to the hepatic portal system. For this reason, \'portal vein\' most commonly refers to the hepatic portal vein[WP].

label: positive regulation of osteoclast proliferation
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the multiplication or reproduction of osteoclasts, resulting in the expansion of an osteoclast cell population.

label: emarginate
Defs: A notched shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a notched tip or edge.

label: regulation of lymphocyte migration
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of lymphocyte migration.

label: pancreatic acinus
Defs: The secretory units of the exocrine pancreas, where fluid containing digestive enzymes is produced; consists of a group of secretory cells surrounding a luminal space that connects to the pancreatic duct.

label: positive regulation of acetylcholine uptake
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of acetylcholine into a cell.

label: actomyosin structure organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures containing both actin and myosin or paramyosin. The myosin may be organized into filaments.

label: crepuscular
Defs: A quality of a process that happens during dawn and dusk.

label: endothelial cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in an endothelial cell. An endothelial cell comprises the outermost layer or lining of anatomical structures and can be squamous or cuboidal.

label: catecholamine catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of any of a group of physiologically important biogenic amines that possess a catechol (3,4-dihydroxyphenyl) nucleus and are derivatives of 3,4-dihydroxyphenylethylamine.

label: author information section
Defs: A part of a document about the authors that provides biographical information and may discuss how the authors\' professional experiences are relevant to the work described in the document.

label: high contrast color pattern
Defs: A color pattern quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s color pattern in which light and dark colors (for example white and black) are codistributed to create a visual impression.

label: cholangiocyte apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in a cholangiocyte.

label: neural precursor cell proliferation
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of neural precursor cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population. A neural precursor cell is either a nervous system stem cell or a nervous system progenitor cell.

label: abdominal tergite IX
Defs: Is the abdominal tergite of the postabdomen that is attached to the posterior margin of the abdominal tergite VIII by the abdominal tergite VIII-abdominal tergite IX conjunctiva and to the anterior margin of the abdominal tergite X by the abdominal tergite IX-abdominal tergite X conjunctiva.

label: biochemical role
Defs: A biological role played by the molecular entity or part thereof within a biochemical context.

label: dentated
Defs: A surface feature shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having toothlike projections in the margin.

label: cranial blood vasculature
Defs: A blood vasculature that is part of a head.

label: His-Purkinje system cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized structural and/or functional features of a cell of the His-Purkinje system. These cells form the fibers regulate cardiac muscle contraction in the ventricles.

label: ornamentation
Defs: A surface feature shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the degree of the bearer\'s highly topographical with ridges, pits, rugosity or other surface structures.

label: subset ontology module
Defs: An ontology module that is extracted from a main ontology module and includes only a subset of entities or axioms.

label: dermis adipose tissue
Defs: An adipose tissue that is part of a dermis [Automatically generated definition].

label: katepisternum
Defs: The region of cuticle on the postero-ventral region of the episternum that is posterior to the anapleural sulcus.

label: retinal blood vessel endothelial cell
Defs: A blood vessel endothelial cell that is part of the retina.

label: cardiac muscle of right atrium
Defs: A portion of cardiac muscle tissue that is part of a right atrium [Automatically generated definition].

label: vertical
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being situated at right angles to the horizon.

label: structurally discontinuous
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being marked by interruptions or gaps.

label: regulation protein catabolic process at presynapse
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a protein at the presynapse.

label: has number of
Defs: The number of parts of a particular type that the bearer entity has. This is a relational quality, and thus holds between two entities: the bearer of the quality, and the type of parts.

label: macromolecule transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of a macromolecule from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: genitourinary system
Defs: Anatomical system that has as its parts the organs concerned with the production and excretion of urine and those concerned with reproduction.

label: brain white matter
Defs: The regions of the brain that are largely or entirely composed of myelinated nerve cell axons and contain few or no neural cell bodies or dendrites.

label: foramen of skull
Defs: Anatomical space that is an opening in a bone of the skull.

label: reticulodromous
Defs: A branched quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having secondary branches branching into a reticulum toward the margin.

label: hematopoietic tissue
Defs: Blood-forming tissue, consisting of reticular fibers and cells.

label: normal object quality
Defs: A quality of an object that has a value that is normal or average.

label: vasculogenesis
Defs: The differentiation of endothelial cells from progenitor cells during blood vessel development, and the de novo formation of blood vessels and tubes.

label: endoskeleton
Defs: Skeletal subdivision that undergoes indirect development and includes elements that develop as a replacement or substitution of other elements or tissues.

label: pubescent hair
Defs: A pilosity quality of being covered with short hairs or soft down.

label: fibrous joint
Defs: Nonsynovial joint in which the articulating bones or cartilages are connected by ligaments. Examples: sagittal suture, inferior tibiofibular syndesmosis, gomphosis.[FMA].

label: nucleolus organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the nucleolus.

label: polysaccharide metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving a polysaccharide, a polymer of many (typically more than 10) monosaccharide residues linked glycosidically.

label: localization of cell
Defs: Any process in which a cell is transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location.

label: protein localization to vacuole
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained at, a location in a vacuole.

label: tentorial pit
Defs: The cuticular pit that correspods to the tentorium.

label: ommatidium
Defs: The smallest morphological and functional unit of the compound eye that consists of a usually limited and often constant number of rhabdomeric photoreceptor cells, cornea-secreting epithelial cells, and interommatidial pigment cells, and may additionally contain crystalline cone cells.

label: sensory organ morphogenesis
Defs: Morphogenesis of a sensory organ. A sensory organ is defined as a tissue or set of tissues that work together to receive and transmit signals from external or internal stimuli. Morphogenesis is the process in which anatomical structures are generated and organized. Organs are commonly observed as visibly distinct structures, but may also exist as loosely associated clusters of cells that work together to perform a specific function or functions.

label: monocarboxylic acid anion
Defs: A carboxylic acid anion formed when the carboxy group of a monocarboxylic acid is deprotonated.

label: pronoto-protrochantinal muscle
Defs: The tergo-trochantinal muscle that is attached to the pronotum and the protrochantin.

label: zone improvement plan code
Defs: A postal code that is used in the United States for the purpose of sorting and delivering mail, and that denotes some postal delivery route or some aggregate of postal delivery routes.

label: glandular cell of endometrium
Defs: A glandular epithelial cell of the endometrium.

label: entire sense organ system
Defs: Sum of all sensory systems in an organism.

label: cardiac atrium morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the cardiac atrium is generated and organized. A cardiac atrium receives blood from a vein and pumps it to a cardiac ventricle.

label: mesoderm development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the mesoderm over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The mesoderm is the middle germ layer that develops into muscle, bone, cartilage, blood and connective tissue.

label: oral epithelium
Defs: An epithelium that is part of the mouth and lines the oral cavity, typically stratified squamous, and may be para-, ortho- or non- keratinized. Primary barrier between oral environment and deeper tissues.

label: forebrain neuron development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a neuron that resides in the forebrain, from its initial commitment to its fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell.

label: submucosa of common bile duct
Defs: A submucosa that is part of a common bile duct [Automatically generated definition].

label: cell migration involved in heart development
Defs: The orderly movement of a cell from one site to another that will contribute to the progression of the heart over time, from its initial formation, to the mature organ.

label: cellular carbohydrate metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving carbohydrates, any of a group of organic compounds based of the general formula Cx(H2O)y, as carried out by individual cells.

label: anal vein
Defs: The insect wing vein of the anal field that is posterior to the anal fold or the postcubitus and anterior to the jugal fold or the jugal veins.

label: positive regulation of hindgut contraction
Defs: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of muscle contraction of the hindgut, the posterior part of the alimentary canal, including the rectum, and the large intestine.

label: synaptic membrane
Defs: A specialized area of membrane on either the presynaptic or the postsynaptic side of a synapse, the junction between a nerve fiber of one neuron and another neuron or muscle fiber or glial cell.

label: oblique orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a slanting direction or position : neither perpendicular nor parallel.

label: establishment of neuroblast polarity
Defs: The specification and formation of the apicobasal polarity of a neuroblast cell, a progenitor of the central nervous system.

label: negative regulation of neuron projection development
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of neuron projection development. Neuron projection development is the process whose specific outcome is the progression of a neuron projection over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A neuron projection is any process extending from a neural cell, such as axons or dendrites (collectively called neurites).

label: lymphoid system
Defs: The lymphatic system in vertebrates is a network of conduits that carry a clear fluid called lymph. It also includes the lymphoid tissue through which the lymph travels. Lymphoid tissue is found in many organs, particularly the lymph nodes, and in the lymphoid follicles associated with the digestive system such as the tonsils. The system also includes all the structures dedicated to the circulation and production of lymphocytes, which includes the spleen, thymus, bone marrow and the lymphoid tissue associated with the digestive system[WP].

label: mesentery of colon
Defs: A mesentery that is part of a colon [Automatically generated definition].

label: mating type
Defs: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population that undergo sexual reproduction.

label: duodenal epithelium
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a duodenum.

label: stuff accumulating cell
Defs: A cell that is specialised to accumulate a particular substance(s).

label: increased depth
Defs: A depth quality which is relatively high.

label: signal transducer CD24
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human CD24 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: lens nucleus
Defs: The core of the crystalline lens, surrounded by the cortex.

label: Fc-gamma receptor III complex
Defs: A protein complex composed of an Fc-gamma RIII alpha chain and an Fc-epsilon RI gamma chain dimer with or without an Fc-epsilon RI beta chain and additional signaling components. The complex functions primarily as an activating receptor for IgG.

label: endothelial cell migration
Defs: The orderly movement of an endothelial cell into the extracellular matrix to form an endothelium.

label: frontolabral muscle
Defs: The cranio-labral muscle that is attached to the frons and the labrum.

label: monovalent inorganic anion
Defs: Any inorganic anion with a valency of one.

label: bile acid
Defs: Any member of a group of hydroxy-5beta-cholanic acids occuring in bile, where they are present as the sodium salts of their amides with glycine or taurine. In mammals bile acids almost invariably have 5beta-configuration.

label: pons morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structure of the pons is generated and organized. The pons lies above the medulla and next to the cerebellum. The pons conveys information about movement from the cerebral hemisphere to the cerebellum.

label: warty
Defs: A texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being covered with warts or projections that resemble warts resulting in a hard rough surface.

label: transient
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s underlying structure being capable of change.

label: monocystic
Defs: A structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s body containing one cyst - a formation of a sac-like closed membranous structure not associated with neoplasia.

label: loose connective tissue
Defs: Irregular connective tissue, the intercellular matrix of which contains a sparse irregular network of collagen and elastic fiber bundles. Examples: areolar tissue, neuroglial tissue, mucoid tissue.

label: trachea blood vessel
Defs: A blood vessel that is part of a trachea.

label: oocyte differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized immature germ cell acquires the specialized features of a mature female gamete.

label: cytoplasmic vesicle
Defs: A vesicle found in the cytoplasm of a cell.

label: striated muscle sphincter
Defs: A ring of striated muscle cells whose contraction closes the opening of the ring.

label: regulation of protein localization to lysosome
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to lysosome.

label: regulation of actin filament organization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of actin filament organization.

label: regulation of actin filament-based movement
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of actin filament-based movement.

label: cuneate
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being narrowly triangular, wider at the apex and tapering toward the base.

label: keratinocyte differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a keratinocyte.

label: digestion
Defs: The whole of the physical, chemical, and biochemical processes carried out by multicellular organisms to break down ingested nutrients into components that may be easily absorbed and directed into metabolism.

label: pyloric gastric gland
Defs: The gastric glands in the pyloric region of the stomach; the pyloric glands secrete mucin, which coats the stomach and protects it, and hormones such as gastrin and enkephalin[MP].

label: regular duration
Defs: A duration which has regular start and/or end times.

label: disoriented
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking orientation.

label: head taste bud
Defs: A taste bud that is located on the skin of the head.

label: small intestine smooth muscle
Defs: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a small intestine [Automatically generated definition].

label: anion transport
Defs: The directed movement of anions, atoms or small molecules with a net negative charge, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: establishment of protein localization to membrane
Defs: The directed movement of a protein to a specific location in a membrane.

label: glutamate secretion, neurotransmission
Defs: The controlled release of glutamate by a cell, in which the glutamate acts as a neurotransmitter.

label: rate of occurence
Defs: The number of repeated events per unit time, occurring in a repeating series. (e.g. the number of heart beats occurring over 1 minute)

label: granulated cuticle
Defs: The region of cuticle that bears an anatomical collection that is composed of granules.

label: pseudostratified ciliated columnar epithelium
Defs: Epithelium composed of a single layer of cells, appearing as layered because the column-shaped cells vary in height so the nuclei are at different levels. The basal portions of all the cells are in contact with the basement membrane. It lines the respiratory system and the male reproductive tract. The cilia in the respiratory tract are motile, while the stereocilia in the male reproductive tract are immobile.

label: collagen fibril binding
Defs: Binding to a collagen fibril.

label: left-right axis
Defs: An axis that bisects an organism from left to right sides of body, through a sagittal plane.

label: cuticle of paraglossa
Defs: The cuticle of the paired appendage of the labium, and part of the ligula, that is attached to the cuticle of prementum by the premental-paraglossal conjunctiva.
