label: negative regulation of oogenesis
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of oogenesis.

label: delayed closure
Defs: A duration quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s delay to complete the closure of the opening of an anatomical entity.

label: endoglin (mouse)
Defs: An endoglin that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: neuroblast division
Defs: The process resulting in the physical partitioning and separation of a neuroblast into daughter cells. A neuroblast is any cell that will divide and give rise to a neuron.

label: negative regulation of protein-containing complex assembly
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein complex assembly.

label: positive regulation of protein localization to cell-cell junction
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to cell-cell junction.

label: protrochantero-profemoral conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that encircles the profemur by joining the distal margin of the protrochanter and the proximal margin of the profemur.

label: cellular response to insulin stimulus
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an insulin stimulus. Insulin is a polypeptide hormone produced by the islets of Langerhans of the pancreas in mammals, and by the homologous organs of other organisms.

label: algal metabolite
Defs: Any eukaryotic metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in algae including unicellular organisms like chlorella and diatoms to multicellular organisms like giant kelps and brown algae.

label: CSF-1/PDGF receptor-type tyrosine-protein kinase
Defs: A protein with core architecture consisting of asignal sequence, 5 Ig-like domains, followed by a transmembrane sequence, followed by a Protein tyrosine kinase domain (Pfam:PF07714). However, only 1-3 of the Ig domains are detected by the Pfam HMMs in most of the sequences. Pfam:PF00047 is most common, but other members of the Ig domain clan, Pfam:PF07679 and Pfam:PF07686 can be identified instead. The fourth Ig domain lacks the disulfide-bonded cysteines.

label: positive regulation of T cell activation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of T cell activation.

label: neural crest cell development
Defs: The process aimed at the progression of a neural crest cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to its specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell.

label: regulation of phosphorylation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of addition of phosphate groups into a molecule.

label: trachea
Defs: The branching invagination of elastic cuticle that is cylindrical and contains taenidia.

label: splenic artery
Defs: An artery that supplies the spleen.

label: deviation towards the lateral side
Defs: A deviation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s changed direction of position towards the side.

label: clypeo-labral conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect maxilla that connects the clypeus and the labrum.

label: systemic vein
Defs: Any vein within the general circulation that transports blood back to the right atrium of the heart.

label: regulation of polysaccharide metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving polysaccharides.

label: abdominal sternite I
Defs: The abdominal sternite of the preabdomen that is attached to the posterior margin of the metasternum by the metasterno-abdominal sternite I conjunctiva and to the anterior margin of the abdominal sternite II by the abdominal sternite I-abdominal sternite II conjunctiva.

label: positive regulation of translational initiation in response to stress
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of translation initiation as a result of a stimulus indicating the organism is under stress.

label: uterine gland development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an uterine gland over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: trachea cartilage morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of cartilage in the trachea are generated and organized.

label: syncytium formation by plasma membrane fusion
Defs: The formation of a syncytium, a mass of cytoplasm containing several nuclei enclosed within a single plasma membrane, by the fusion of the plasma membranes of two or more individual cells.

label: peritoneal cavity mesothelium
Defs: A mesothelium that is part of a peritoneal cavity.

label: protein transport within plasma membrane
Defs: A process in which protein is transported from one region of the plasma membrane to another.

label: endothelial cell of sinusoid
Defs: An endothelial cell that lines any of the venous cavities through which blood passes in various glands and organs such as the spleen and liver.

label: carboxylic acid transport
Defs: The directed movement of carboxylic acids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Carboxylic acids are organic acids containing one or more carboxyl (COOH) groups or anions (COO-).

label: pleural membrane
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect abdomen that surrounds the spiracles.

label: catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of substances, including the breakdown of carbon compounds with the liberation of energy for use by the cell or organism.

label: unilaminar epithelium
Defs: Epithelium which consists of a single layer of epithelial cells. Examples: endothelium, mesothelium, glandular squamous epithelium.[FMA].

label: hepatic duct smooth muscle
Defs: Smooth muscle tissue in all or part of a hepatic duct.

label: positive regulation of secretory granule organization
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of secretory granule organization.

label: complex
Defs: A complexity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being intricate and compounded.

label: balance
Defs: A behavioral quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of having physical steadiness.

label: mesodermal cell migration
Defs: The orderly movement of mesodermal cells from one site to another.

label: negative regulation of multicellular organismal process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of an organismal process, the processes pertinent to the function of an organism above the cellular level; includes the integrated processes of tissues and organs.

label: conditional specification
Defs: A directive information entity that specifies what should happen if the trigger condition is fulfilled.

label: sensitivity of a process
Defs: A quality of a process inhering in bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to respond to stimulation.

label: hindgut contraction
Defs: A process in which force is generated within smooth muscle tissue, resulting in a change in muscle geometry. This process occurs in the hindgut. Force generation involves a chemo-mechanical energy conversion step that is carried out by the actin/myosin complex activity, which generates force through ATP hydrolysis. The hindgut is the posterior part of the alimentary canal, including the rectum, and the large intestine.

label: intestinal epithelial cell development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a columnar/cuboidal epithelial cell of the intestine over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: larval
Defs: A maturity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s indirect development, undergoing metamorphosis.

label: negative regulation of catalytic activity
Defs: Any process that stops or reduces the activity of an enzyme.

label: regulation of cellular process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a cellular process, any of those that are carried out at the cellular level, but are not necessarily restricted to a single cell. For example, cell communication occurs among more than one cell, but occurs at the cellular level.

label: intralobular duct
Defs: A duct that is located within a lobule, with no more connective tissue intervening between ducts and secretory units (i.e., acini or tubules) than between adjacent secretory units. Intercalated and striated ducts are intralobular.

label: sulfur compound metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving the nonmetallic element sulfur or compounds that contain sulfur, such as the amino acids methionine and cysteine or the tripeptide glutathione.

label: undulate
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a sinuate margin and rippled surface.

label: cell adhesion involved in heart morphogenesis
Defs: The attachment of a cell, either to another cell or to an underlying substrate such as the extracellular matrix, via cell adhesion molecules that contributes to the shaping of the heart.

label: mesenchymal stem cell migration
Defs: The orderly movement of a mesenchymal stem cell from one site to another.

label: cellular response to acetylcholine
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an acetylcholine stimulus.

label: basal side
Defs: Anatomical side that is located on the basal end of an organism or structure.

label: negative regulation of motor neuron apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of motor neuron apoptotic process.

label: increased solubility
Defs: A solubility which is relatively high.

label: blastula
Defs: Organism at the blastula stage - an early stage of embryonic development in animals. It is produced by cleavage of a fertilized ovum and consists of a spherical layer of around 128 cells surrounding a central fluid-filled cavity called the blastocoel. The blastula follows the morula and precedes the gastrula in the developmental sequence.

label: lysosome localization
Defs: Any process in which a lysosome is transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location.

label: blastocyst formation
Defs: The initial formation of a blastocyst from a solid ball of cells known as a morula.

label: atrioventricular node cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of an atrioventricular (AV) node cell. AV node cells are pacemaker cells that are found in the atrioventricular node.

label: negative regulation of carbohydrate metabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving carbohydrate.

label: regulation of antimicrobial peptide production
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of antimicrobial peptide production.

label: lymphocyte chemotaxis
Defs: The directed movement of a lymphocyte in response to an external stimulus.

label: pre-publication history textual entity
Defs: A textual entity that expresses the pre-publication history (submission dates, reviewer comments, etc) for a document, often including a hyperlink to a web page detailing the information.

label: long term hematopoietic stem cell
Defs: A hematopoietic stem cell with long term self renewal capability. This cell is Kit-positive, Sca1-positive, CD150-positive, CD90-low, CD34-negative and Flt3-negative.

label: nervous system development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of nervous tissue over time, from its formation to its mature state.

label: nucleate erythrocyte development
Defs: The process aimed at the progression of a nucleate erythrocyte over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell.

label: strap-shaped
Defs: A shape quality in which the bearer is shaped like a narrow band; ligulate.

label: elemental molecule
Defs: A molecule all atoms of which have the same atomic number.

label: oral gland
Defs: Gland of the epithelium lining the oral cavity. The most common are the salivary glands.

label: regulation of chromosome condensation
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of chromosome condensation, the progressive compaction of dispersed interphase chromatin into threadlike chromosomes prior to mitotic or meiotic nuclear division, or during apoptosis, in eukaryotic cells.

label: dermis connective tissue
Defs: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a dermis [Automatically generated definition].

label: endothelial tube morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of a tube are generated and organized from an endothelium. Endothelium refers to the layer of cells lining blood vessels, lymphatics, the heart, and serous cavities, and is derived from bone marrow or mesoderm. Corneal endothelium is a special case, derived from neural crest cells.

label: dorsal aorta development
Defs: The progression of the dorsal aorta over time, from its initial formation to the mature structure. The dorsal aorta is a blood vessel in a single-pass circulatory system that carries oxygenated blood from the gills to the rest of the body. In a single-pass circulatory system blood passes once through the heart to supply the body once.

label: regulation of presynapse organization
Defs: Any process that modulates the physical form of a presynapse.

label: dystrophic
Defs: A size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being abnormally developed, usually due to malnutrition.

label: stem cell development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the stem cell over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Cell development does not include the steps involved in committing a cell to its specific fate.

label: regulation of cell adhesion
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of attachment of a cell to another cell or to the extracellular matrix.

label: taste bud formation
Defs: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of the taste bud from unspecified parts. The taste bud is a specialized area of the tongue that contains taste receptors.

label: positive regulation of nervous system process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of a neurophysiological process.

label: matrix-based tissue
Defs: A tissue whose predominant feature is extracellular matrix which may or may not be highly hydrated or calcified.

label: negative regulation of fat cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of adipocyte differentiation.

label: neural tube basal plate
Defs: The region of the mantle layer of the neural tube that lies ventral to the sulcus limitans and contains primarily motor neurons and interneurons.

label: 3-D extent
Defs: A size quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s extension in three dimensions.

label: diastatic
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s separation of normally joined parts, such as the separation of adjacent bones without fracture or of certain abdominal muscles during pregnancy.

label: conus arteriosus formation
Defs: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of the conus arteriosus from unspecified parts. The conus arteriosus is a valved chamber with thick muscular walls stemming from the ventricle and connecting to the pulmonary trunk.

label: vasculature of brain
Defs: System pertaining to blood vessels in the brain.

label: response to ammonium ion
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an ammonium stimulus.

label: Mullerian duct
Defs: Paired ducts of the embryo that run down the lateral sides of the urogenital ridge and terminate at the mullerian eminence in the primitive urogenital sinus. In the female, they will develop to form the fallopian tubes, uterus, and the upper portion of the vagina; in the male, they are lost. These ducts are made of tissue of mesodermal origin[WP]. develops either by lengthwise splitting of the archinephric duct (in chondrichthyans and some amphibians) or by a elongated invagination of the coelomic epithelium (other vertebrates) In males, the oviducts regress. The cranial end of the oviduct maintains an opening into the coelom (which primitively may have been the anteriormost coelomic funnels connecting the nephrocoel with the coelom). This opening is the ostium tubae[USM].

label: degeneration
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer exhibiting deterioration of its structure.

label: hypsodont
Defs: A 3-D shape inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having dentition characterized by high-crowned teeth and enamel which extends far past the gum line, which provides extra material for wear and tear.

label: tentorio-oral muscle
Defs: The cranio-hypopharyngeal muscle that is attached to the anterior tentorial arm and the suspensorium.

label: amine
Defs: A compound formally derived from ammonia by replacing one, two or three hydrogen atoms by hydrocarbyl groups.

label: biological role
Defs: A role played by the molecular entity or part thereof within a biological context.

label: positive regulation of cellular amino acid metabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving amino acid.

label: skin of lower lip
Defs: A zone of skin that is part of a lower lip.

label: iron atom
Defs: An iron group element atom that has atomic number 26.

label: left handedness
Defs: Handedness where the organism preferentially uses the left hand or foot for tasks requiring the use of a single hand or foot or a dominant hand or foot.

label: positive regulation of immune system process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of an immune system process.

label: negative regulation of protein modification process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the covalent alteration of one or more amino acid residues within a protein.

label: introverted
Defs: An oriented quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being turned inward upon itself.

label: ionic macromolecule
Defs: A macromolecule containing ionic groups.

label: negative regulation of protein localization to membrane
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to membrane.

label: peracute
Defs: Extremely acute and aggressive onset of a pathological process.

label: type B pancreatic cell development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a type B pancreatic cell over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A type B pancreatic cell is a cell located towards center of the islets of Langerhans that secretes insulin.

label: tolerant to
Defs: A resistance quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its disposition to endure or being insensitive to a stimulus.

label: cell junction assembly
Defs: A cellular process that results in the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a cell junction.

label: dopamine biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of dopamine, a catecholamine neurotransmitter and a metabolic precursor of noradrenaline and adrenaline.

label: mesenchyme derived from head neural crest
Defs: Mesenchyme that develops_from a cranial neural crest.

label: severe increased temperature
Defs: A temperature which is increased by a high degree.

label: protein localization to ciliary transition zone
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a location within a ciliary transition zone.

label: cardiac cell development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a cardiac cell over time, from its formation to the mature state. A cardiac cell is a cell that will form part of the cardiac organ of an individual.

label: low saturation
Defs: A color saturation which is of low purity.

label: positive regulation of embryonic pattern specification
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of embryonic pattern specification.

label: table of contents
Defs: A table that relates document parts to specific locations in a document (usually page numbers).  This is also a document part (subsumption there should be inferred).

label: pancreas exocrine glandular cell
Defs: Glandular cell of exocrine pancreas epithelium. Example: pancreatic acinar cell, glandular cells in pancreatic canaliculi, glandular cells in pancreatic ducts.

label: cervical spinal cord white matter
Defs: A white matter of spinal cord that is part of a cervical spinal cord.

label: carboxylic acid metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving carboxylic acids, any organic acid containing one or more carboxyl (COOH) groups or anions (COO-).

label: nodular
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s consisting a knot-like mass.

label: negative regulation of glycoprotein biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a glycoprotein, a protein that contains covalently bound glycose (i.e. monosaccharide) residues; the glycose occurs most commonly as oligosaccharide or fairly small polysaccharide but occasionally as monosaccharide.

label: hollow
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having an empty space or cavity within.

label: bile acid secretion
Defs: The regulated release of bile acid, composed of any of a group of steroid carboxylic acids occurring in bile, by a cell or a tissue.

label: upper back muscle
Defs: A muscle of back that is part of a dorsal thoracic segment of trunk.

label: myelencephalon sulcus limitans
Defs: A sulcus limitans of neural tube that is part of a future myelencephalon.

label: fluid flow rate
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a fluid (liquid or gas) by virtue of the amount of fluid which passes through a given surface per unit time.

label: indole alkaloid
Defs: An alkaloid containing an indole skeleton.

label: responsive to
Defs: A response quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to react to a stimulus or an agent.

label: positive regulation of vascular endothelial cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of vascular endothelial cell proliferation.

label: adventitia
Defs: An outermost connective tissue covering of an organ, vessel, or other structure[WP].

label: cell motility involved in camera-type eye morphogenesis
Defs: Any process involved in the controlled self-propelled movement of a cell that results in translocation of the cell from one place to another and contributes to the physical shaping or formation of the camera-type eye.

label: visual system
Defs: The sensory system subserving the sense of vision.

label: steroid biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of steroids, compounds with a 1,2,cyclopentanoperhydrophenanthrene nucleus; includes de novo formation and steroid interconversion by modification.

label: urogenital system development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the urogenital system over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: negative regulation of glial cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that stops or decreases the rate or extent of glial cell proliferation.

label: regulation of protein catabolic process at presynapse, modulating synaptic transmission
Defs: Any process that modulates synaptic transmission by regulating a catabolic process occurring at a presynapse.

label: umbonate
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a knob or knoblike protuberance.

label: melanocyte migration
Defs: The orderly movement of melanocytes from one site to another, often during the development of a multicellular organism. A melanocyte is a pigment cell derived from the neural crest. It contains melanin-filled pigment granules, which give a brown to black appearance.

label: right side
Defs: The side of an organism that is right of the sagittal plane.

label: response to amino acid
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an amino acid stimulus. An amino acid is a carboxylic acids containing one or more amino groups.

label: serotonin production involved in inflammatory response
Defs: The synthesis or release of serotonin following a stimulus as part of an inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label: eye muscle
Defs: A muscle that is part of the eye region.

label: negative regulation of insulin receptor signaling pathway
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of insulin receptor signaling.

label: totipotent
Defs: A cellular potency that is the capacity to produce differentiated cell types of all three primary germ layers and extraembryonic cell types.

label: oviduct development
Defs: The reproductive developmental process whose specific outcome is the progression of an oviduct over time, from its formation to the mature structure. An oviduct is a tube through which an ova passes from the ovary to the uterus, or from the ovary to the outside of the organism.

label: propleuro-procoxal artiulation
Defs: The insect articulation between the propleuron and the procoxa.

label: mesothelial cell of visceral peritoneum
Defs: A mesothelial cell that is part of the visceral peritoneum.

label: submucosa of pharynx
Defs: The tissue underlying the tunica mucosa of the pharynx.

label: negative regulation of acetylcholine secretion, neurotransmission
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of acetylcholine.

label: bone of reproductive organ
Defs: A bone that is part of a reproductive organ.

label: premature closure
Defs: A duration quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s premature completion of the closure of the opening of an anatomical entity.

label: circinate
Defs: A curled quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s edges of its surface being rolled spirally downwards.

label: phosphate ion transport
Defs: The directed movement of phosphate into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: positive regulation of transport
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of substances (such as macromolecules, small molecules, ions) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: meninx of spinal cord
Defs: A meninx that is part of a spinal cord [Automatically generated definition].

label: regulation of extracellular matrix disassembly
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of extracellular matrix disassembly. Extracellular matrix disassembly is a process that results in the breakdown of the extracellular matrix.

label: adhesive
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer exhibiting molecular attraction to another entity in contact.

label: ovarian vein
Defs: A vein that carries deoxygenated blood from its corresponding ovary to inferior vena cava or one of its tributaries.

label: peptidyl-tyrosine phosphorylation
Defs: The phosphorylation of peptidyl-tyrosine to form peptidyl-O4\'-phospho-L-tyrosine.

label: alkaline
Defs: An medium acidity quality inhering in a solution by virtue of the bearer\'s a low concentration of H+ ions.

label: external female genitalia
Defs: An external genitalia that is part of a female reproductive system [Automatically generated definition].

label: normal strength
Defs: A strength which is relatively normal or average

label: positive regulation of cell activation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of activation.

label: contractile fiber
Defs: Fibers, composed of actin, myosin, and associated proteins, found in cells of smooth or striated muscle.

label: anatomical region
Defs: A 3D region in space without well-defined compartmental boundaries; for example, the dorsal region of an ectoderm.

label: oligodendrocyte precursor cell
Defs: A progenitor cell of the central nervous system that can differentiate into oligodendrocytes or type-2 astrocytes. This cell originates from multiple structures within the developing brain including the medial ganglion eminence and the lateral ganglionic eminence. These cells migrate throughout the central nervous system and persist into adulthood where they play an important role in remyelination of injured neurons.

label: ooplasm
Defs: The cytoplasm of an ovum.

label: regulation of bone development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of bone development.

label: spleen primordium
Defs: A dense syncitial-like mesenchymal thickening in the dorsal mesogastrium[ISBN]. the embryonic connective tissue made up of loosely aggregated mesenchymal cells, supported by interlaminar jelly, that gives rise to the developing spleen[MP].

label: ammonia
Defs: An azane that consists of a single nitrogen atom covelently bonded to three hydrogen atoms.

label: regulation of establishment or maintenance of cell polarity
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the specification, formation or maintenance of anisotropic intracellular organization or cell growth patterns.

label: ciliatedness
Defs: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having thin, tail-like projections extending outwards from the cell body.

label: protein transport
Defs: The directed movement of proteins into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: outer epithelium
Defs: The epidermis is the entire outer epithelial layer of an animal, it may be a single layer that produces an extracellular material (e.g. the cuticle of arthropods) or a complex stratified squamous epithelium, as in the case of many vertebrate species[GO].

label: negative regulation of cell division
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cell division.

label: sensory nerve
Defs: A nerve that transmits from sensory receptors on the surface of the body to the central nervous system.

label: cardiocyte
Defs: A cell located in the heart, including both muscle and non muscle cells.

label: positive regulation of tetrapyrrole biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of tetrapyrrole biosynthetic process.

label: sclerite
Defs: The region of the insect cuticle that is less flexible than the neighboring conjunctiva(e) (conjunctiva(e) that the sclerite is continuous with.

label: increased velocity
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s increased rate of change of the position.

label: extracellular space
Defs: That part of a multicellular organism outside the cells proper, usually taken to be outside the plasma membranes, and occupied by fluid.

label: bone morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which bones are generated and organized.

label: negative regulation of lipid metabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving lipids.

label: intermediate mesoderm
Defs: The intermediate mesoderm is located between the lateral mesoderm and the paraxial mesoderm. It develops into the kidney and gonads.

label: mesenchymal cell proliferation
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a mesenchymal cell population. A mesenchymal cell is a cell that normally gives rise to other cells that are organized as three-dimensional masses, rather than sheets.

label: neural crest cell migration involved in autonomic nervous system development
Defs: Any neural crest cell migration that is involved in autonomic nervous system development.

label: discontinuous
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being marked by breaks or interruptions.

label: persistence
Defs: A rhythm quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the repetitiveness of bearer\'s rhythm.

label: skin of back
Defs: A zone of skin that is part of a back [Automatically generated definition].

label: flaky
Defs: A texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s formed or tending to form flakes or thin, crisp fragments.

label: posterolateral orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed posterolaterally.

label: extracellular transport
Defs: The transport of substances that occurs outside cells.

label: cuticle of insect maxilla
Defs: The cuticle of the mouthpart appendage of the head capsule, between the cuticle of the insect mandible and the cuticle of the labium, composed of cuticle of cardo, which is attached to the cuticle of stipes by the cardo-stipital conjunctiva; the cuticle of stipes, which is attached to the cuticle of galea by the stipito-galeal conjunctiva, to the cuticle of lacinia by the stipito-lacinial conjunctiva, and to the cuticle of palpifer by the stipito-palpiferal conjunctiva; the cuticle of palpifer is attached to the cuticle of maxillary palpus by the palpifero-palpal conjunctiva.

label: normal osmolality
Defs: An osmolality which is relatively normal or average odor.

label: pattern specification process
Defs: Any developmental process that results in the creation of defined areas or spaces within an organism to which cells respond and eventually are instructed to differentiate.

label: G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway involved in heart process
Defs: An G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway which contributes to a circulatory system process carried out by the heart.

label: inflorescence-like
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s similarity to the appearance of an inflorescence.

label: integral component of organelle membrane
Defs: The component of the organelle membrane consisting of the gene products having at least some part of their peptide sequence embedded in the hydrophobic region of the membrane.

label: multi-multicellular organism process
Defs: A multicellular organism process which involves another multicellular organism of the same or different species.

label: running title
Defs: A shorter version of a document title

label: pectoral appendage field
Defs: A limb/fin field that has the potential to develop into a pectoral appendage bud mesenchyme.

label: anteroexternal cranio-mandibular muscle
Defs: The cranio-mandibular muscle that is attached to the gena and the insect mandible.

label: CD48 molecule
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human CD48 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: negative regulation of epithelial cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of epithelial cell apoptotic process.

label: sulfuric ester
Defs: An ester of an alcohol and sulfuric acid.

label: positive regulation of RNA binding
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of RNA binding.

label: phenol-containing compound metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving a phenol, any compound containing one or more hydroxyl groups directly attached to an aromatic carbon ring.

label: ventricular septum development
Defs: The progression of the ventricular septum over time from its formation to the mature structure.

label: mesothoracic discrimen
Defs: The discrimen of the mesoventrite.

label: skeleton of left pelvic girdle
Defs: A skeleton of pelvic girdle that is part of a left pelvic girdle region.

label: bitufted dendrite cell morphology
Defs: A cell morphology that inheres in neurons with dendrites that are bidirectional, emerging from opposite ends of the soma, with the two arbors extending in radial or tangential directions.

label: negative regulation of cell motility
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cell motility.

label: regulation of stomach neuroendocrine cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of the differentiation of a neuroendocrine cell in the stomach.

label: catecholamine secretion
Defs: The regulated release of catecholamines by a cell. The catecholamines are a group of physiologically important biogenic amines that possess a catechol (3,4-dihydroxyphenyl) nucleus and are derivatives of 3,4-dihydroxyphenylethylamine.

label: hormone binding
Defs: Binding to an hormone, a naturally occurring substance secreted by specialized cells that affect the metabolism or behavior of cells possessing functional receptors for the hormone. Hormones may be produced by the same, or different, cell as express the receptor.

label: sensory epithelium
Defs: Simple columnar epithelium made up of cells specialized to serve as sensory cells for the reception of external stimuli, as the sensory cells of the cochlea, vestibule, nasal mucosa, and tongue.

label: superior olivary nucleus development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the superior olivary nucleus over time, from its formation to the mature structure. In mice, the superior olivary nucleus is a small cylindrical mass on the dorsal surface of the lateral part of the trapezoid body of the pons, and it is situated immediately above the inferior olivary nucleus. It receives projections from the cochlear nucleus and thus is involved in the perception of sound.

label: negative regulation of endodermal cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of endodermal cell differentiation.

label: sulfate transport
Defs: The directed movement of sulfate into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: knobbled
Defs: A surface feature shape having numerous very small circular rounded projections or protuberances.

label: positive regulation of phosphate transmembrane transport
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of phosphate transmembrane transport.

label: regulation of apoptotic process involved in development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of apoptotic process involved in development.

label: color pattern
Defs: A chromatic property that is the relative position of different hues or degrees of saturation.

label: polychromatophilic erythroblast
Defs: A nucleated, immature erythrocyte in which the nucleus occupies a relatively smaller part of the cell than in its precursor, the basophilic erythroblast. The cytoplasm is beginning to acquire hemoglobin and thus is no longer a purely basophilic, but takes on acidophilic aspects, which becomes progressively more marked as the cell matures. The chromatin of the nucleus is arranged in coarse, deeply staining clumps. This cell is CD71-positive and lacks hematopoeitic lineage markers.

label: positive regulation of exocytosis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of exocytosis.

label: endophallite
Defs: The region of cuticle of the endophallus that is thicker.

label: decreased flexibility
Defs: A flexibility which is relatively low.

label: polymeric
Defs: A quality inhering in a structure by virtue of it consisting of many of repeated, similar or identical subunits, arranged in some orderly array.

label: duration
Defs: A process quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s magnitude of the temporal extent between the starting and ending point.

label: pharmacological role
Defs: A biological role which describes how a drug interacts within a biological system and how the interactions affect its medicinal properties.

label: dense regular connective tissue
Defs: Connective tissue that is dominated by collagen fibres organized into a definitive pattern (e.g., parallel to one another), with comparatively fewer cells (mostly fibroblasts).

label: actin filament bundle
Defs: An assembly of actin filaments that are on the same axis but may be oriented with the same or opposite polarities and may be packed with different levels of tightness.

label: tangled
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being entwined and difficult to unravel.

label: notochordal canal
Defs: A tubular passage that extends from the primitive pit into the head process during the early stages of embryonic development in mammals. It perforates the splanchnopleure layer so that the yolk sac and the amnion are connected temporarily.

label: regulation of skeletal muscle contraction by neural stimulation via neuromuscular junction
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of skeletal muscle contraction by variation of the pattern of stimulation by nervous system.

label: negative regulation of inflammatory response
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the inflammatory response.

label: smooth muscle fiber of duodenum
Defs: A smooth muscle cell that is part of the duodenum.

label: regulation of skeletal muscle contraction by action potential
Defs: Any action potential process that regulates skeletal muscle contraction.

label: regulation of respiratory gaseous exchange by nervous system process
Defs: A process carried out by the nervous system that is required for the proper control of respiratory gaseous exchange. This process occurs in the respiratory center of the brain in vertebrates.

label: ventrally rotated
Defs: A rotation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of being rotated towards the abdomen of an organism.

label: cranial skeletal system development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a cranial skeletal system over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The cranial skeletal system is the skeletal subdivision of the head, and includes the skull (cranium plus mandible), pharyngeal and/or hyoid apparatus.

label: mixed ectoderm/mesoderm/endoderm-derived structure
Defs: An anatomical structure that develops from the ectoderm, mesoderm and endoderm.

label: Golgi disassembly
Defs: A cellular process that results in the breakdown of a Golgi apparatus that contributes to Golgi inheritance.

label: positive regulation of leukocyte proliferation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of leukocyte proliferation.

label: acetylcholine metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving acetylcholine, the acetic acid ester of the organic base choline. Acetylcholine is a major neurotransmitter and neuromodulator both in the central and peripheral nervous systems. It also acts as a paracrine signal in various non-neural tissues.

label: cytoplasm organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the cytoplasm. The cytoplasm is all of the contents of a cell excluding the plasma membrane and nucleus, but including other subcellular structures.

label: positive regulation of cellular amine metabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving amines.

label: notum
Defs: The dorsal region of the cuticle of the insect thorax that is attached to the dorsal margin of the pleuron.

label: medulla oblongata
Defs: Organ component of neuraxis that has as its parts the medullary reticular formation, inferior olivary complex and cochlear nuclear complex, among other structures[FMA]. The medulla oblongata lies directly above the spinal cord and controls vital autonomic functions such as digestion, breathing and the control of heart rate[GO].

label: cuticle of pedicellus
Defs: The cuticle of the segment of the antenna that is attached to the scapus by the scapal-pedicellar conjunctiva and to the first flagellomere by the pedicel-first flagellomere conjunctiva.

label: textual entity
Defs: A textual entity is a part of a manifestation (FRBR sense), a generically dependent continuant whose concretizations are patterns of glyphs intended to be interpreted as words, formulas, etc.

label: regulation of oogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of oogenesis.

label: morphogenesis of a branching structure
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of branches are generated and organized. A branch is a division or offshoot from a main stem. Examples in animals would include blood vessels, nerves, lymphatics and other endothelial or epithelial tubes.

label: anterior part of tongue
Defs: The portion of the tongue in front of the terminal sulcus. At the apex, thin and narrow, it is directed forward against the lingual surfaces of the lower incisor teeth. It is derived primarily from the first pharyngeal arch.

label: exposure event or process
Defs: A process occurring within or in the vicinity of an organism that exerts some causal influence on the organism via the interaction between an exposure stimulus and an exposure receptor. The exposure stimulus may be a process, material entity or condition (for example, lack of nutrients). The exposure receptor can be an organism, organism population or a part of an organism.

label: regulation of cytokine production involved in immune response
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of cytokine production that contributes to an immune response.

label: negative regulation of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly.

label: tension
Defs: A physical quality that pertains by virtue of a pulling force that is directed away from the bearer and attempts to stretch or elongate the bearer.

label: establishment or maintenance of microtubule cytoskeleton polarity
Defs: Any cellular process that results in the specification, formation or maintenance of polarized microtubule-based cytoskeletal structures.

label: cuticle of tarsus
Defs: The cuticle of the segment of the leg that is composed of tarsomeres connected to each other by intertarsomeral conjunctiva. The first tarsomere is connected to the distal margin of the tibia by the tibio-tarsal conjunctiva and last tarsomere is connected to the proximal margin of the pretarsus by the tarso-pretarsal conjunctiva.

label: cardiac atrium fibroblast
Defs: Any fibroblast that is part of a cardiac atrium.

label: software
Defs:
Software is a plan specification composed of a series of instructions that can be 
interpreted by or directly executed by a processing unit.

label: respiratory system submucosa
Defs: A submucosa that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

label: neutrophil mediated immunity
Defs: Any process involved in the carrying out of an immune response by a neutrophil.

label: central nervous system development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the central nervous system over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The central nervous system is the core nervous system that serves an integrating and coordinating function. In vertebrates it consists of the brain and spinal cord. In those invertebrates with a central nervous system it typically consists of a brain, cerebral ganglia and a nerve cord.

label: kinase inhibitor activity
Defs: Binds to and stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a kinase.

label: skin of trunk
Defs: A zone of skin that is part of a trunk [Automatically generated definition].

label: spheroid
Defs: A convex 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a quadric surface in three dimensions obtained by rotating an ellipse about one of its principal axes. Includes spheres and oblate/prolate spheroids.

label: embryonic heart tube formation
Defs: The process that gives rise to the embryonic heart tube. This process pertains to the initial formation of a structure from unspecified parts. The embryonic heart tube is an epithelial tube that will give rise to the mature heart.

label: linearly fractured
Defs: A fractured quality where the fracture runs parallel to the long axis of a bone.

label: lysosomal membrane organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a lysosomal membrane. A lysosomal membrane is the lipid bilayer surrounding the lysosome and separating its contents from the cell cytoplasm.

label: cranio-labial muscle
Defs: The somatic muscle that is attached to the head capsule and the labium.

label: obsolete plant growth hormone sensitivity value
database extract, transform, and load process
Defs: A planned process which takes as input a database and fills another database by extracting concretizations of information entities from the first, transforming them, and loading the transformed concretizations into the second.

label: quaternary ammonium ion
Defs: A derivative of ammonium, NH4(+), in which all four of the hydrogens bonded to nitrogen have been replaced with univalent (usually organyl) groups.

label: material anatomical entity
Defs: Anatomical entity that has mass.

label: submucosa of left hepatic duct
Defs: A submucosa that is part of a left hepatic duct [Automatically generated definition].

label: negative regulation of vessel branching
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of blood vessel branching.

label: neoplastic, malignant
Defs: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to progress, invade surrounding tissues or metastasize.

label: gas molecular entity
Defs: Any main group molecular entity that is gaseous at standard temperature and pressure (STP; 0degreeC and 100 kPa).

label: mesothelium of pericardial cavity
Defs: A mesothelium that is part of a pericardium [Automatically generated definition].

label: dispersed
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being distributed or spread over a considerable extent.

label: dorso-medial margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the dorso-medial region of the body or body part.

label: zygote
Defs: A zygote in a plant or an animal.

label: positive regulation of neurogenesis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of neurogenesis, the generation of cells within the nervous system.

label: lipid homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of lipid within an organism or cell.

label: odorous
Defs: An odor quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having odour.

label: inflammatory cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in an inflammatory cell, any cell participating in the inflammatory response to a foreign substance e.g. neutrophil, macrophage.

label: villiform
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling a minute projection (villus).

label: chromatin binding
Defs: Binding to chromatin, the network of fibers of DNA, protein, and sometimes RNA, that make up the chromosomes of the eukaryotic nucleus during interphase.

label: granulocyte migration
Defs: The movement of a granulocyte within or between different tissues and organs of the body.

label: smooth muscle tissue of bronchiole
Defs: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a bronchiole [Automatically generated definition].

label: colon endothelial cell
Defs: A vascular endothelial cell found in colon blood vessels.

label: normal length
Defs: A length quality which is relatively normal or average

label: somatostatin
Defs: A fourteen-membered heterodetic cyclic peptide comprising the sequence Ala-Gly-Cys-Lys-Asn-Phe-Phe-Trp-Lys-Thr-Phe-Thr-Ser-Cys cyclised by a disulfide bridge between the two Cys residues at positions 3 and 14.

label: intracellular signal transduction involved in positive regulation of cell growth
Defs: Any intracellular signal transduction that is involved in positive regulation of cell growth.

label: exocrine gland of integumental system
Defs: An exocrine gland that is part of a integumental system.

label: presumptive sinus venosus
Defs: Portion of tissue that is part of the heart tube and will become the sinus venosus.

label: interfurcal muscle
Defs: The insect thoracic muscle that extends between two furcae.

label: epithelial tube
Defs: Epithelial tubes transport gases, liquids and cells from one site to another and form the basic structure of many organs and tissues, with tube shape and organization varying from the single-celled excretory organ in Caenorhabditis elegans to the branching trees of the mammalian kidney and insect tracheal system.

label: embryonic-extraembryonic boundary
Defs: The connection between the embryo proper and extraembryonic tissues.

label: positive regulation of intracellular lipid transport
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of lipids within cells.

label: capillary endothelial cell
Defs: An endothelial cell found in capillaries.

label: establishment of Golgi localization
Defs: The directed movement of the Golgi to a specific location.

label: epithelial cell of stratum germinativum of esophagus
Defs: A basal cell that is part of the epithelium of esophagus.

label: myocardium of anterior wall of right ventricle
trachea
Defs: The trachea is the portion of the airway that attaches to the bronchi as it branches [GO:dph].

label: network-forming collagen trimer
Defs: A collagen trimer that forms networks.

label: grand multiparous
Defs: A viviparous organism that has given birth five or more times.

label: sulfur compound catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of compounds that contain sulfur, such as the amino acids methionine and cysteine or the tripeptide glutathione.

label: subcosta
Defs: The insect wing vein that is posterior to the costa and anterior to the radius.

label: nitrogen compound metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving organic or inorganic compounds that contain nitrogen.

label: CD14-positive monocyte
Defs: A monocyte that expresses CD14 and is negative for the lineage markers CD3, CD19, and CD20.

label: regulation of antimicrobial humoral response
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of an antimicrobial humoral response.

label: aorta elastic tissue
Defs: The dense connective tissue which contains predominantly elastic fibers and is found in the tunica media of the aorta wall.

label: postsynaptic membrane
Defs: A specialized area of membrane facing the presynaptic membrane on the tip of the nerve ending and separated from it by a minute cleft (the synaptic cleft). Neurotransmitters cross the synaptic cleft and transmit the signal to the postsynaptic membrane.

label: trigeminal neural crest
Defs: Cranial neural crest which gives rise to the trigeminal ganglion.

label: low affinity immunoglobulin gamma Fc region receptor III
Defs: An immunoglobulin gamma Fc receptor II/III/IV that is a translation product of the mouse Fcgr3 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: Golgi-associated vesicle
Defs: Any vesicle associated with the Golgi complex and involved in mediating transport within the Golgi or between the Golgi and other parts of the cell.

label: smooth muscle tissue
Defs: Muscle tissue which is unstriated, composed primarily of smooth muscle fibers surrounded by a reticulum of collagen and elastic fibers. Smooth muscle differs from striated muscle in the much higher actin/myosin ratio, the absence of conspicuous sarcomeres and the ability to contract to a much smaller fraction of its resting length[GO].

label: hepatoblast differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a hepatoblast. A hepatoblast is a cell that retains the ability to divide and proliferate throughout life to provide progenitor cells that can differentiate into hepatocytes and cholangiocytes.

label: negative regulation of glial cell migration
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of glial cell migration.

label: insulin secretion involved in cellular response to glucose stimulus
Defs: The regulated release of proinsulin from secretory granules (B granules) in the B cells of the pancreas; accompanied by cleavage of proinsulin to form mature insulin, in response to a glucose stimulus.

label: negative regulation of mucus secretion
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of mucus from a cell or a tissue.

label: negative regulation of epithelial cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of epithelial cell differentiation.

label: intestine smooth muscle
Defs: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a intestine [Automatically generated definition].

label: decreased frequency
Defs: A frequency which is relatively low.

label: respiratory system venous blood vessel
Defs: A vein that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

label: developing mesenchymal condensation
Defs: A delimited region of dense mesenchyme within looser mesenchyme.

label: parietal peritoneum development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a parietal peritoneum over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: heart rudiment formation
Defs: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of the heart rudiment.

label: cuticle of gonocoxa VIII
Defs: The paired sclerite of the postabdomen that is attached to the abdominal sternite VII by the abdominal sternite VII-gonocoxa conjunctiva and is articulated with abdominal tergite IX. It is attached at the base of gonostylus VIII and adjacent to the gonopore.

label: internal carotid artery
Defs: A terminal branch of the left or right common carotid artery which supplies oxygenated blood to the brain and eyes[MP].

label: type A enteroendocrine cell
Defs: An enteroendocrine cell that produces glucagon.

label: fibrous membrane of synovial tendon sheath
refractivity
Defs: A physical quality that inheres in propagating wave (light or sound) virtue of the bearer\'s change in direction when passing from one medium to another.

label: endothelial cell of uterus
Defs: An endothelial cell that is part of a uterus.

label: meninx of telencephalon
Defs: A meninx that is part of a telencephalon [Automatically generated definition].

label: cranial nerve formation
Defs: The process that gives rise to the cranial nerves. This process pertains to the initial formation of a structure from unspecified parts. The cranial nerves are composed of twelve pairs of nerves that emanate from the nervous tissue of the hindbrain. These nerves are sensory, motor, or mixed in nature, and provide the motor and general sensory innervation of the head, neck and viscera. They mediate vision, hearing, olfaction and taste and carry the parasympathetic innervation of the autonomic ganglia that control visceral functions.

label: sensory neuron migration
Defs: The orderly movement of a sensory neuron from one site to another.

label: positive regulation of antimicrobial peptide production
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of antimicrobial peptide production.

label: lung endothelium
Defs: A blood vessel endothelium that is part of a lung [Automatically generated definition].

label: intracellular signal transduction
Defs: The process in which a signal is passed on to downstream components within the cell, which become activated themselves to further propagate the signal and finally trigger a change in the function or state of the cell.

label: deep-superficial gradient
Defs: Anatomical gradient that is distributed along the deep-superficial axis.

label: epithelial melanocyte
Defs: A melanocyte that produces pigment in the epithelium.

label: lateral orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed laterally.

label: positive regulation of extracellular matrix assembly
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of extracellular matrix assembly.

label: ribosome
Defs: An intracellular organelle, about 200 A in diameter, consisting of RNA and protein. It is the site of protein biosynthesis resulting from translation of messenger RNA (mRNA). It consists of two subunits, one large and one small, each containing only protein and RNA. Both the ribosome and its subunits are characterized by their sedimentation coefficients, expressed in Svedberg units (symbol: S). Hence, the prokaryotic ribosome (70S) comprises a large (50S) subunit and a small (30S) subunit, while the eukaryotic ribosome (80S) comprises a large (60S) subunit and a small (40S) subunit. Two sites on the ribosomal large subunit are involved in translation, namely the aminoacyl site (A site) and peptidyl site (P site). Ribosomes from prokaryotes, eukaryotes, mitochondria, and chloroplasts have characteristically distinct ribosomal proteins.

label: tunica intima
Defs: The innermost layer of a blood vessel which is a lining of endothelial cells facing the lumen[Kardong].

label: hypoglossal nerve
Defs: Cranial nerve that innervates the muscles of the tongue.

label: specific volume
Defs: A volume quality inhering in a mass of substance by virtue of the amount of 3-dimensional space it occupies.

label: vasculature of organ
Defs: A vasculature that is part of a organ.

label: posterior tentorial pit
Defs: The tentorial pit that correspods to the posterior (ventral in prognathous head) end of the tentorium.

label: compound acidity
Defs: A concentration quality inhering in compound by virtue of the bearer\'s tendency to act as a hydron donor.

label: establishment of protein localization to euchromatin
Defs: The directed movement of a protein to a specific location in an euchromatin.

label: fronto-oral muscle
Defs: The cranio-hypopharyngeal muscle that is attached to the frons and  the suspensorium.

label: negative regulation of cellular carbohydrate metabolic process
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, extent or frequency of the chemical reactions and pathways involving carbohydrates, any of a group of organic compounds based of the general formula Cx(H2O)y, as carried out by individual cells.

label: heart formation
Defs: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of the heart from unspecified parts. This process begins with the specific processes that contribute to the appearance of the heart field and the arrival of cardiac neural crest to the heart region. The process ends when the structural rudiment is recognizable.

label: anterioralized
Defs: A malformed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s gross morphology containing what are normally anterior structures and missing some or all of what are normally posterior structures.

label: frons
Defs: The region of cuticle of the head capsule that is located posterior to the clypeus and delimited by the frontal suture.

label: colorless
Defs: A color quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking color.

label: epimysium
Defs: Epimysium is a layer of connective tissue which ensheaths the entire muscle. It is composed of dense irregular connective tissue. It is continuous with fascia and other connective tissue wrappings of muscle including the endomysium, and perimysium. It is also continuous with tendons where it becomes thicker and collagenous.

label: cell migration involved in endocardial cushion formation
Defs: The orderly movement of a cell from one site to another that will contribute to the formation of an endocardial cushion. The endocardial cushion is a specialized region of mesenchymal cells that will give rise to the heart septa and valves.

label: numeral
Defs: A symbol that denotes a number.

label: amine transport
Defs: The directed movement of amines, including polyamines, organic compounds containing one or more amino groups, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: regulation of fat cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of fat cell proliferation.

label: positive regulation of myeloid leukocyte mediated immunity
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of myeloid leukocyte mediated immunity.

label: complex of collagen trimers
Defs: A complex of collagen trimers such as a fibril or collagen network.

label: ventral margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the ventral side of the body or body part.

label: fibroblast activation
Defs: A change in the morphology or behavior of a fibroblast resulting from exposure to an activating factor such as a cellular or soluble ligand.

label: keratinocyte migration
Defs: The directed movement of a keratinocyte, epidermal cells which synthesize keratin, from one site to another.

label: elastic fiber assembly
Defs: Assembly of the extracellular matrix fibers that enables the matrix to recoil after transient stretching.

label: motile cell
Defs: A cell that moves by its own activities.

label: endoderm of hindgut
Defs: An endoderm that is part of a hindgut [Automatically generated definition].

label: blade-like
Defs: A tapered shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being flat, slender, and tapering to a point.

label: cell surface receptor signaling pathway involved in heart development
Defs: The series of molecular signals initiated by a ligand the binding to its receptor on the surface of a cell, which contributes to the progression of the heart over time.

label: zymogen granule
Defs: A membrane-bounded, cytoplasmic secretory granule found in enzyme-secreting cells and visible by light microscopy. Contain zymogen, an inactive enzyme precursor, often of a digestive enzyme.

label: nocturnal
Defs: A quality of a process that happens during the hours of darkness.

label: negative regulation of neuron maturation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of neuron maturation.

label: dorsal surface
Defs: Anatomical surface that located on the dorsal side of the body or body part.

label: posterior stroma of cornea
Defs: The posterior segment of the lamellated connective tissue layer of the cornea.

label: polar amino acid
Defs: Any amino acid whose side chain is capable of forming one or more hydrogen bonds.

label: saturated violet
Defs: A color consisting of violet hue and high saturation.

label: cellular amide metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving an amide, any derivative of an oxoacid in which an acidic hydroxy group has been replaced by an amino or substituted amino group, as carried out by individual cells.

label: ciliary transition zone
Defs: A region of the cilium between the basal body and proximal segment that is characterized by Y-shaped assemblages that connect axonemal microtubules to the ciliary membrane. The ciliary transition zone appears to function as a gate that controls ciliary membrane composition and separates the cytosol from the ciliary plasm.

label: fusiform
Defs: Having a spindle-like shape that is wide in the middle and tapers at both ends.

label: abdominal tergite X
Defs: Is the abdominal tergite of the postabdomen that is attached to the posterior margin of the abdominal tergite IX by the abdominal tergite IX-abdominal tergite X conjunctiva and to the anterior margin of the epiproct and paraproct.

label: head development
Defs: The biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of a head from an initial condition to its mature state. The head is the anterior-most division of the body.

label: maxillary nerve
Defs: The sensory nerve subdivision of the trigeminal nerve that transmits sensory information from the palate, upper teeth and gingiva, the skin between the palpebral fissure and the mouth, and from the nasal cavity and maxillary sinuses.

label: liver stroma
Defs: A stroma that is part of a liver.

label: neuroendocrine cell
Defs: An endocrine cell that has the specialized function to produce and secrete hormones in response to neuronal signals.

label: ganglion of central nervous system
Defs: A ganglion that is part of a central nervous system [Automatically generated definition].

label: nucleobase-containing compound transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of nucleobases, nucleosides, nucleotides and nucleic acids from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: variable color
Defs: A color quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being uneven in color.

label: indolalkylamine biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of indolalkylamines, indole or indole derivatives containing a primary, secondary, or tertiary amine group.

label: regulation of organic acid transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of organic acids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: cranial suture morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which any suture between cranial bones is generated and organized.

label: bronchus fibroblast of lung
Defs: Any fibroblast of lung that is part of a bronchus.

label: hydridonitrate(2-)
Defs: A divalent inorganic anion resulting from the removal of two protons from ammonia.

label: curved dorsal
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved towards the back or upper surface of an organism.

label: respiratory system blood vessel
Defs: A blood vessel that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

label: negative regulation of lysosome organization
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of lysosome organization.

label: tracheobronchial tree
Defs: The structure from the trachea, bronchi, and bronchioles that forms the airways that supply air to the lungs. The lining of the tracheobronchial tree consists of ciliated columnar epithelial cells.

label: ventral to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located toward the abdomen of an organism relative to another entity.

label: spinal cord motor neuron
Defs: A motor neuron that passes from the spinal cord toward or to a muscle and conducts an impulse that causes movement.

label: cardiac Purkinje fiber
Defs: The cardiac Purkinje fiber is part of the cardiac conduction system that receives signals from the bundle of His and innervates the ventricular cardiac muscle.

label: regulation protein catabolic process at postsynapse
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a protein at the postsynapse.

label: organic cyclic compound metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving organic cyclic compound.

label: cuticular fovea
Defs: The cuticular depression that is circular.

label: epidermal cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of an epidermal cell, any of the cells making up the epidermis.

label: positive regulation of keratinocyte apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of keratinocyte apoptotic process.

label: tracheal epithelial cell
Defs: An epithelial cell found in the trachea.

label: regulation of glutamate receptor signaling pathway
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of glutamate receptor signaling pathway.

label: multicellular organism growth
Defs: The increase in size or mass of an entire multicellular organism, as opposed to cell growth.

label: hematopoietic or lymphoid organ development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of any organ involved in hematopoiesis (also known as hemopoiesis) or lymphoid cell activation over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Such development includes differentiation of resident cell types (stromal cells) and of migratory cell types dependent on the unique microenvironment afforded by the organ for their proper differentiation.

label: author information textual entity
Defs: A textual entity expression information about an author of a document. This information may include biographical information and may discuss how the authors\' professional experiences are relevant to the work described in the document.

label: 5beta-cholanic acids
Defs: Members of the class of cholanic acids based on a 5beta-cholane skeleton.

label: endochondral element
Defs: A skeletal element that has the potential to participate in endochondral ossification, and may participate in intramembranous ossification.

label: barred
Defs: A color pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of bearer\'s exhibiting vertical bars of one hue or degree of saturation crossing another.

label: hepatoblast apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in a hepatoblast.

label: obsolete pale grey
Defs: A color consisting of grey color and low saturation.

label: amino acid homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of amino acid within an organism or cell.

label: His-Purkinje system cell development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a His-Purkinje cell over time, from its formation to the mature state. These cells form the fibers that regulate cardiac muscle contraction in the ventricles.

label: G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway
Defs: The series of molecular signals initiated by a ligand binding to its receptor, in which the  activated receptor promotes the exchange of GDP for GTP on the alpha-subunit of an associated heterotrimeric G-protein complex. The GTP-bound activated alpha-G-protein then dissociates from the beta- and gamma-subunits to further transmit the signal within the cell. The pathway begins with receptor-ligand interaction, and ends with regulation of a downstream cellular process.  The pathway can start from the plasma membrane, Golgi or nuclear membrane.

label: right side of back
Defs: Right part of the organism dorsal to a horizontal plane and bounded on one side by the same transverse plane.

label: mesonoto-mesotrochantinal muscle
Defs: The tergo-trochantinal muscle that is attached to the mesonotum and the mesotrochantin.

label: negative regulation of acetylcholine metabolic process
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving acetylcholine, the acetic acid ester of the organic base choline. Acetylcholine is a major neurotransmitter and neuromodulator both in the central and peripheral nervous systems. It also acts as a paracrine signal in various non-neural tissues.

label: nonskeletal ligament
Defs: A ligament that does not connect two skeletal elements.

label: ornamented
Defs: A surface feature shape in which the bearer\'s surface is highly topographical with ridges, pits, rugosity or other surface structures.

label: anepimeron
Defs: The region of the cuticle on the dorsal region of the epimeron.

label: myelination in peripheral nervous system
Defs: The process in which neuronal axons and dendrites become coated with a segmented lipid-rich sheath (myelin) to enable faster and more energetically efficient conduction of electrical impulses. The sheath is formed by the cell membranes of Schwann cells in the peripheral nervous system. Adjacent myelin segments are separated by a non-myelinated stretch of axon called a node of Ranvier.

label: subdivision of organism along main body axis
Defs: A major subdivision of an organism that divides an organism along its main body axis (typically anterio-posterior axis). In vertebrates, this is based on the vertebral column.

label: muscular coat
Defs: A region of muscle in many organs in the vertebrate body, adjacent to the submucosa membrane. It is responsible for gut movement such as peristalsis.

label: visceral serous pericardium
Defs: Visceral serous membrane which is continuous with the parietal serous pericardium and is attached to the myocardium[FMA].

label: regulation of development, heterochronic
Defs: Any process that modulates the consistent predetermined time point at which an integrated living unit or organism progresses from an initial condition to a later condition and the rate at which this time point is reached.

label: regulation of neutrophil chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of neutrophil chemotaxis. Neutrophil chemotaxis is the directed movement of a neutrophil cell, the most numerous polymorphonuclear leukocyte found in the blood, in response to an external stimulus, usually an infection or wounding.

label: reproductive behavior
Defs: The specific behavior of an organism that is associated with reproduction.

label: horizontal
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being in the plane of the horizon.

label: food additive
Defs: Any substance which is added to food to preserve or enhance its flavour and/or appearance.

label: forebrain cell migration
Defs: The orderly movement of a cell from one site to another at least one of which is located in the forebrain.

label: doubled haploid
Defs: A ploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s haploid cells undergo chromosome doubling.

label: negative regulation of hindgut contraction
Defs: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of muscle contraction of the hindgut, the posterior part of the alimentary canal, including the rectum, and the large intestine.

label: precoxal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that coincides with the precoxal ridge.

label: bullet-shaped
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being short and wide and tapered distally.

label: inorganic ion homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of inorganic ions within an organism or cell.

label: positive regulation of microtubule nucleation
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of microtubule nucleation.
