Microtubule nucleation is the \'de novo\' formation of a microtubule, in which tubulin heterodimers form metastable oligomeric aggregates, some of which go on to support formation of a complete microtubule. Microtubule nucleation usually occurs from a specific site within a cell.

label: iron ion transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of iron (Fe) ions from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: regulation of muscle adaptation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of muscle adaptation.

label: regulation of protein depolymerization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein depolymerization.

label: anatomical conduit space
Defs: An anatomical space which is the lumen of some anatomical conduit and connects two or more spaces together[FMA,modified].

label: normal acidity
Defs: An acidity which is relatively normal.

label: fibroblast of areolar connective tissue
Defs: A fibroblast that is part of the areolar connective tissue.

label: pallium development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the pallium over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The pallium is the roof region of the telencephalon.

label: regulation of secondary metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of secondary metabolism, the chemical reactions and pathways involving compounds that are not necessarily required for growth and maintenance of cells, and are often unique to a taxon.

label: negative regulation of secretory granule organization
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of secretory granule organization.

label: regulation of aorta morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of aorta morphogenesis.

label: right angle to
Defs: An angle which is 90 degrees to another entity.

label: organic substance catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of an organic substance, any molecular entity containing carbon.

label: positive regulation of heart contraction
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of heart contraction.

label: tryptamine
Defs: An aminoalkylindole consisting of indole having a 2-aminoethyl group at the 3-position.

label: mosaicism
Defs: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having two or more cell populations that differ in genetic makeup. This situation can affect any type of cell, including blood cells, gametes (egg and sperm cells), and skin.

label: acetylcholine receptor regulator activity
Defs: Interacting (directly or indirectly) with acetylcholine receptors such that the proportion of receptors in the active form is changed.

label: muscle cell proliferation
Defs: The expansion of a muscle cell population by cell division.

label: establishment of protein localization to vacuole
Defs: The directed movement of a protein to a specific location in a vacuole.

label: arthropod foramen
Defs: Is the foramen encircled a sclerite.

label: kinase regulator activity
Defs: Modulates the activity of a kinase, an enzyme which catalyzes of the transfer of a phosphate group, usually from ATP, to a substrate molecule.

label: anterodorsal to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located toward the front and upper surface of an organism relative to another entity.

label: nuclear membrane disassembly
Defs: The controlled breakdown of the nuclear membranes, for example during  cellular division.

label: pons formation
Defs: The process that gives rise to the pons. This process pertains to the initial formation of a structure from unspecified parts. The pons lies above the medulla and next to the cerebellum. The pons conveys information about movement from the cerebral hemisphere to the cerebellum.

label: fragile
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to being easily damaged or destroyed.

label: glandular cell of esophagus
Defs: A glandular epithelial cell of the esophagus.

label: permanent
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s underlying structure not changing over time.

label: heart left ventricle
Defs: A cardiac ventricle that is in the left side of the heart.

label: auditory system
Defs: Is the sensory system for the sense of hearing.

label: apoptotic process involved in development
Defs: Any apoptotic process that is involved in anatomical structure development.

label: right hepatic duct
Defs: The duct that drains bile from the right half of the liver and joins the left hepatic duct to form the common hepatic duct.

label: dendritic spine organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a dendritic spine. A dendritic spine is a specialized protrusion from a neuronal dendrite and is involved in synaptic transmission.

label: neuron projection
Defs: A prolongation or process extending from a nerve cell, e.g. an axon or dendrite.

label: regulation of post-embryonic development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of post-embryonic development. Post-embryonic development is defined as the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the organism over time, from the completion of embryonic development to the mature structure.

label: endochondral bone
Defs: Replacement bone that forms within cartilage.

label: dendrite quality
Defs: A quality inhering in a neuron\'s dendrites by virtue of the bearer\'s physical composition.

label: sensory neuron of spinal nerve
Defs: A sensory neuron of the spinal nerve that senses body position and sends information about how much the muscle is stretched to the spinal cord.

label: melanocyte of skin of face
Defs: Any melanocyte of skin that is part of a skin of face.

label: spongy
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling a sponge in elasticity, absorbency, or porousness.

label: mesentery of duodenum
Defs: A mesentery that is part of a duodenum [Automatically generated definition].

label: intestine secretion
Defs: Clear to pale yellow watery secretions from the glands lining the small intestine walls. Secretion is stimulated by the mechanical pressure of partly digested food in the intestine.

label: basement membrane organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the basement membrane.

label: pharyngeal taste bud
Defs: A taste bud that is located in the pharynx.

label: digestive tract diverticulum
Defs: Branch or outpocketing of the digestive tract.

label: alpha-adrenergic agonist
Defs: An agent that selectively binds to and activates alpha-adrenergic receptors.

label: left lung associated mesenchyme
Defs: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing left lung.

label: cardiac muscle tissue growth
Defs: The increase in size or mass of a cardiac muscle, where the increase in size or mass has the specific outcome of the progression of the organism over time from one condition to another.

label: myoblast proliferation
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of myoblasts, resulting in the expansion of a myoblast cell population. A myoblast is a mononucleate cell type that, by fusion with other myoblasts, gives rise to the myotubes that eventually develop into skeletal muscle fibers.

label: rate of continuous process
Defs: The rate of output of a continuous process. Example include: growth rate, cell migration rate, enzyme reaction rate.

label: punctate cuticle
Defs: The region of cuticle that bears an anatomical collection that is composed of punctures.

label: pronoto-mesonotal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect thorax that joins the pronotum and the mesonotum.

label: cuticle of maxillary palpus
Defs: The cuticle of the appendage of the insect maxilla that is attached to the cuticle of palpifer by the palpifero-palpal conjunctiva.

label: radiopacity
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s relative inability of electromagnetism to pass through a particular material, particularly X-rays.

label: glycoprotein catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a glycoprotein, a protein that contains covalently bound glycose (i.e. monosaccharide) residues; the glycose occurs most commonly as oligosaccharide or fairly small polysaccharide but occasionally as monosaccharide.

label: regulation of leukocyte mediated immunity
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of leukocyte mediated immunity.

label: polycystic
Defs: A structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s body containing more than one cyst - formations of sac-like closed membranous structures not associated with neoplasia.

label: lysosome organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a lysosome. A lysosome is a cytoplasmic, membrane-bounded organelle that is found in most animal cells and that contains a variety of hydrolases.

label: mesotrochantero-mesofemoral conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that encircles the mesofemur by joining the distal margin of the mesotrochanter and the proximal margin of the mesofemur.

label: regulation of organelle organization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of an organelle.

label: positive regulation of protein localization to lysosome
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to lysosome.

label: organic acid transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of organic acids from one side of a membrane to the other. Organic acids are acidic compound containing carbon in covalent linkage.

label: positive regulation of actin filament-based movement
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of actin filament-based movement.

label: variability of size
Defs: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits size variation or change.

label: vertebrate lens cell
Defs: A cell comprising the transparent, biconvex body separating the posterior chamber and vitreous body, and constituting part of the refracting mechanism of the mammalian eye.

label: clypeus
Defs: The region of the head capsule that is anterior to the frons and is attached to the labrum by the clypeo-labral conjunctiva

label: terminal part of digestive tract
Defs: The distalmost portion of the digestive tract, derived from the hindgut, and terminating with the anus.

label: negative regulation of lymphocyte migration
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of lymphocyte migration.

label: pancreas
Defs: An endoderm derived structure that produces precursors of digestive enzymes and blood glucose regulating enzymes[GO].

label: irregular duration
Defs: A duration quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s duration which has irregular start and/or end times.

label: cartilage morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of cartilage are generated and organized.

label: oriented
Defs: A pattern where all the repeated elements are oriented in the same direction.

label: response to alkaloid
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an alkaloid stimulus. Alkaloids are a large group of nitrogenous substances found in naturally in plants, many of which have extracts that are pharmacologically active.

label: negative regulation of adaptive immune response
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of an adaptive immune response.

label: mandibular neural crest
Defs: Cranial neural crest that migrates into the mandibular arch.

label: photosensitivity
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to being sensitivity to the action of radiant energy.

label: head or neck skin
Defs: A zone of skin that is part of a craniocervical region.

label: cornea development in camera-type eye
Defs: The progression of the cornea over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The cornea is the transparent structure that covers the anterior of the eye.

label: detection of stimulus involved in sensory perception
Defs: The series of events involved in sensory perception in which a sensory stimulus is received and converted into a molecular signal.

label: sensitivity of a process to oxygen
Defs: A sensitivity of a process quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s unfolding in a location with or without oxygen.

label: allantois
Defs: A membranous sac that develops from the posterior part of the alimentary canal in the embryos of mammals, birds, and reptiles, and it is important in the formation of the umbilical cord and placenta in mammals[VHOG].

label: transverse plane
Defs: Anatomical plane that divides body into anterior and posterior parts.

label: prepubescent
Defs: A maturity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being at the age immediately before puberty.

label: immature eye
Defs: Developing anatomical structure that develops into the eyeball and associated structures.

label: oxygen homeostasis
Defs: A homeostatic process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of oxygen within an organism or cell.

label: positive regulation of melanocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of melanocyte differentiation.

label: lysosomal protein catabolic process
Defs: Any cellular protein catabolic process that takes place in a lysosome.

label: deviation (from_normal)
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the whether the bearer differs from normal or average.

label: head mesenchyme from mesoderm
Defs: A head mesenchyme that develops_from a mesoderm.

label: negative regulation of phosphorylation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or decreases the rate of addition of phosphate groups to a molecule.

label: deviation towards the medial side
Defs: A deviation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s changed direction of position towards the middle.

label: bile salt
Defs: A sodium salt of the conjugate of any bile acid with either glycine or taurine.

label: bleb
Defs: A cell extension caused by localized decoupling of the cytoskeleton from the plasma membrane and characterized by rapid formation, rounded shape, and scarcity of organelles within the protrusion. Blebs are formed during apoptosis and other cellular processes, including cell locomotion, cell division, and as a result of physical or chemical stresses.

label: erythrocyte homeostasis
Defs: Any process of regulating the production and elimination of erythrocytes within an organism.

label: cuspidate
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being tapering gradually into a rigid point.

label: positive regulation of carbohydrate metabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving carbohydrate.

label: macromolecule catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a macromolecule, any molecule of high relative molecular mass, the structure of which essentially comprises the multiple repetition of units derived, actually or conceptually, from molecules of low relative molecular mass.

label: activity (of a radionuclide)
Defs: A radiation quality inhering in a radioactive substance by virtue of its transformation (disintegration) rate.

label: regulation of cardiac ventricle development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac ventricle development.

label: behavioral quality
Defs: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s behavior aggregate of the responses or reactions or movements in a given situation.

label: postsynaptic neurotransmitter receptor activity
Defs: Neurotransmitter receptor activity occuring in the postsynaptic membrane during synaptic transmission.

label: glycogen metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving glycogen, a polydisperse, highly branched glucan composed of chains of D-glucose residues in alpha-(1->4) glycosidic linkage, joined together by alpha-(1->6) glycosidic linkages.

label: pulmonary artery endothelial tube morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of a tube are generated and organized from the pulmonary artery endothelium. An pulmonary artery endothelium is an epithelium that lines the pulmonary artery.

label: antigen processing and presentation
Defs: The process in which an antigen-presenting cell expresses antigen (peptide or lipid) on its cell surface in association with an MHC protein complex.

label: regulation of hindgut contraction
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of muscle contraction of the hindgut, the posterior part of the alimentary canal, including the rectum, and the large intestine.

label: pulmonary vein morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structure of the pulmonary venous blood vessels are generated and organized. Pulmonary veins are blood vessels that transport blood from the lungs to the heart.

label: processual entity
Defs: An occurrent [span:Occurrent] that exists in time by occurring or happening, has temporal parts and always involves and depends on some entity.

label: erythroid transcription factor
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human GATA1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: negative regulation of biological process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of a biological process. Biological processes are regulated by many means; examples include the control of gene expression, protein modification or interaction with a protein or substrate molecule.

label: supramolecular complex
Defs: A cellular component that consists of an indeterminate number of proteins or macromolecular complexes, organized into a regular, higher-order structure such as a polymer, sheet, network or a fiber.

label: telencephalon neural crest
Defs: A neural crest that has_potential_to_developmentally_contribute_to a telencephalon.

label: spherical
Defs: A spheroid quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling a ball (a sphere whose equatorial diameter is equal to the polar diameter).

label: paired limb/fin
Defs: An appendage that is part of an appendage girdle complex.

label: cell migration involved in heart formation
Defs: The orderly movement of a cell from one site to another that contribute to the formation of the heart. The initial heart structure is made up of mesoderm-derived heart progenitor cells and neural crest-derived cells.

label: cardiac muscle myoblast
Defs: A precursor cell destined to differentiate into cardiac muscle cell.

label: visceral serous membrane
Defs: Serous membrane layer that is adjacent to and lines an organ.

label: positive regulation of cilium assembly
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the formation of a cilium.

label: slit-like
Defs: Shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer exhibiting a narrow and elongate opening.

label: stroma
Defs: Connective, non-functional supportive framework of a biological cell, tissue, or organ. Contrast with parenchyma.

label: decreased solubility
Defs: A solubility which is relatively low.

label: inner cell mass cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of an inner cell mass cell.

label: nuclear membrane fusion
Defs: The joining of 2 or more lipid bilayer membranes that surround the nucleus.

label: increased fatigability
Defs: A fatigability which is relatively high.

label: obconical
Defs: A conical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling a cone, with the pointed end attached to an organism.

label: cellular catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of substances, carried out by individual cells.

label: activation of protein kinase activity
Defs: Any process that initiates the activity of an inactive protein kinase.

label: related work section
Defs: A part of a document about work in other publications that is relevant to the content of the document.

label: Slamf1-negative multipotent progenitor cell
Defs: A hematopoietic progenitor that has restricted self-renewal capability. Cell is Kit-positive, Ly6-positive, CD150-negative and Flt3-negative.

label: protein catabolic process at postsynapse
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a protein at a postsynapse.

label: anterograde trans-synaptic signaling
Defs: Cell-cell signaling from pre to post-synapse, across the synaptic cleft.

label: memory
Defs: The activities involved in the mental information processing system that receives (registers), modifies, stores, and retrieves informational stimuli. The main stages involved in the formation and retrieval of memory are encoding (processing of received information by acquisition), storage (building a permanent record of received information as a result of consolidation) and retrieval (calling back the stored information and use it in a suitable way to execute a given task).

label: trunk connective tissue
Defs: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a trunk [Automatically generated definition].

label: negative regulation of protein localization to nucleolus
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to nucleolus.

label: polysaccharide
Defs: A biomacromolecule consisting of large numbers of monosaccharide residues linked glycosidically. This term is commonly used only for those containing more than ten monosaccharide residues.

label: epithelial sheet
Defs: An epithelial sheet is a flat surface consisting of closely packed epithelial cells.

label: organ component layer
Defs: A part of a wall of an organ that forms a layer.

label: protein transporter activity
Defs: Directly binding to a specific protein and delivering it to a specific cellular location.

label: regulation of photoreceptor cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of photoreceptor cell differentiation. An example of this process is found in Drosophila melanogaster.

label: pancreas primordium
Defs: Embryonic structure that develops into pancreatic bud.

label: heterotaxic
Defs: An oriented quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being abnormally placed or arranged.

label: irregular thickness
Defs: A thickness quality which lacks pattern.

label: mesopectus
Defs: The sclerite that is continuous with the basal mesocoxal conjunctiva and the basal wing conjunctiva and contains the mesofurca.

label: regulation of postsynapse organization
Defs: Any process that modulates the physical form of a postsynapse.

label: pancreatic D cell development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a pancreatic delta cell over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A delta cell is a cell of the pancreas that produces somatostatin.

label: cellular response to chemical stimulus
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a chemical stimulus.

label: cuticle of gonapophysis
Defs: The cuticle of the appendage of the abdominal sternite VIII that is part of the ovipositor.

label: endo-epithelial cell
Defs: An epithelial cell derived from endoderm.

label: nuclear factor NF-kappa-B p100 subunit (mouse)
Defs: A nuclear factor NF-kappa-B p100 subunit that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: sensitive toward
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having sensitivity toward an external stimulus.

label: blood vessel development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a blood vessel over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The blood vessel is the vasculature carrying blood.

label: pneumatized bone
Defs: A bone that is hollow or contains many air cells, such as the mastoid process of the temporal bone[TMD].

label: absorption wavelength
Defs: The specific wavelength of radiation that can be retained by a bearer.

label: precursor cell
Defs: A cell that, by division or terminal differentiation, can give rise to other cell types.

label: taste receptor complex
Defs: A protein complex which is capable of taste receptor activity.

label: pharyngeal epithelium
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a pharynx [Automatically generated definition].

label: disrupted
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being interrupted of its normal course.

label: cell population proliferation
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population.

label: blotchy
Defs: A color pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of bearer\'s being marked with irregularly shaped spots or blots of a different hue or degree of saturation.

label: non-degenerate
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer whose structure which does not deteriorate.

label: molecular_function
Defs: A molecular process that can be carried out by the action of a single macromolecular machine, usually via direct physical interactions with other molecular entities. Function in this sense denotes an action, or activity, that a gene product (or a complex) performs. These actions are described from two distinct but related perspectives: (1) biochemical activity, and (2) role as a component in a larger system/process.

label: cytoskeleton-dependent intracellular transport
Defs: The directed movement of substances along cytoskeletal fibers such as microfilaments or microtubules within a cell.

label: brachydont
Defs: A 3-D shape inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having dentition characterized by low-crowned teeth. Human teeth are brachydont.

label: hexose transmembrane transport
Defs: The process in which hexose is transported across a membrane. Hexoses are aldoses with a chain of six carbon atoms in the molecule.

label: insect cranio-tentorial muscle
Defs: The somatic muscle that is attached to the head capsule and the tentorium.

label: negative regulation of striated muscle cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of striated muscle cell differentiation.

label: nerve fiber
Defs: A threadlike extension of a nerve cell and consists of an axon and myelin sheath (if it is myelinated) in the nervous system. There are nerve fibers in the central nervous system and peripheral nervous system. A nerve fiber may be myelinated and/or unmyelinated. In the central nervous system (CNS), myelin by oligodendroglia cells is formed. Schwann cells form myelin in the peripheral nervous system (PNS). Schwann cells also make a thin covering in an axon without myelin (in the PNS). A peripheral nerve fiber contains an axon, myelin sheath, schwann cells and its endoneurium. There are no endoneurium and schwann cells in the central nervous system.

label: protein tyrosine kinase activity
Defs: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + a protein tyrosine = ADP + protein tyrosine phosphate.

label: oxygen metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving diatomic oxygen (O2).

label: regulation of angiogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of angiogenesis.

label: pelvic cavity
Defs: The part of the ventral body cavity that is within the pelvis.

label: mast/stem cell growth factor receptor
Defs: A CSF-1/PDGF receptor-type tyrosine-protein kinase that is a translation product of the human KIT gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: Golgi organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the Golgi apparatus.

label: right handedness
Defs: Handedness where the organism preferentially uses the right hand or foot for tasks requiring the use of a single hand or foot or a dominant hand or foot.

label: regulation of leukocyte migration
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of leukocyte migration.

label: sternum
Defs: The ventral region of the cuticle of the insect thorax that is attached to the ventral margin of the pleuron.

label: positive regulation of protein modification process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the covalent alteration of one or more amino acid residues within a protein.

label: optic eminence mesenchyme
Defs: Mesenchyme that is part of a optic eminence.

label: anatomical surface
Defs: A two dimensional anatomical structure that is the boundary between an anatomical structure and an anatomical substance, an anatomical space or the organism\'s environment. Examples include the surface of your skin, the surface of the lining of your gut; the surface of the endothelium of you aorta that is in contact with blood.n.

label: concave
Defs: A shape quality in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s curving inward.

label: positive regulation of protein localization to membrane
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to membrane.

label: pedunculate
Defs: Being supported by a peduncle or stalk.

label: positive regulation of oogenesis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of oogenesis.

label: structure with developmental contribution from neural crest
Defs: An anatomical structure that has some part that develops from the neural crest.

label: indiscriminate
Defs: A discrimination quality in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being incapable perceiving differences between two or more stimuli.

label: positive regulation of vasculogenesis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of vasculogenesis.

label: positive regulation of trophoblast cell migration
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of trophoblast cell migration.

label: negative regulation of smooth muscle hypertrophy
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of smooth muscle hypertrophy.

label: mesofurca
Defs: The furca of the mesothorax that is attached to the mesocoxa via muscle.

label: microtubule cytoskeleton
Defs: The part of the cytoskeleton (the internal framework of a cell) composed of microtubules and associated proteins.

label: cortical preplate
Defs: The layer of the developing cerebral cortex that is formed from the first cohort of neurons to migrate out of the cortical ventricular zone; split by the second wave into marginal zone and subplate.

label: regulation of microtubule cytoskeleton organization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising microtubules and their associated proteins.

label: meiotic nuclear membrane disassembly
Defs: The cell cycle process in which the controlled breakdown of the nuclear membranes during meiotic cell division occurs.

label: rugose
Defs: A surface feature shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having many wrinkles or creases on the surface.

label: vesicle fusion with vacuole
Defs: The joining of the lipid bilayer membrane around a vesicle with the lipid bilayer membrane around the vacuole.

label: cardiac muscle cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a cardiac muscle precursor cell acquires specialized features of a cardiac muscle cell. Cardiac muscle cells are striated muscle cells that are responsible for heart contraction.

label: ectodermal placode formation
Defs: The developmental process in which an ectodermal placode forms. An ectodermal placode is a thickening of the ectoderm that is the primordium of many structures derived from the ectoderm.

label: socket membrane
Defs: The conjunctiva that corresponds to one epithelial cell and surrounds a sclerotized unicellular cuticular evagination.

label: pharynx
Defs: The pharynx is the part of the digestive system immediately posterior to the mouth[GO].

label: osseous
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing bone.

label: oocyte construction
Defs: The synthesis, deposition, and organization of the materials in a cell of an ovary; where the cell can then undergo meiosis and form an ovum. An example of this is found in Drosophila melanogaster.

label: one-carbon compound
Defs: An organic molecular entity containing a single carbon atom (C1).

label: appendage development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an appendage over time, from its formation to the mature structure. An appendage is an organ or part that is attached to the trunk of an organism, such as a limb or a branch.

label: autonomic nervous system
Defs: The autonomic nervous system is composed of neurons that are not under conscious control, and is comprised of two antagonistic components, the sympathetic and parasympathetic nervous systems. The autonomic nervous system regulates key functions including the activity of the cardiac (heart) muscle, smooth muscles (e.g. of the gut), and glands[GO].

label: positive regulation of lipid localization
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of lipid localization.

label: positive regulation of gene expression
Defs: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of gene expression. Gene expression is the process in which a gene\'s coding sequence is converted into a mature gene product (protein or RNA).

label: dura mater
Defs: Thick, fibrous meningeal covering surrounding the brain and spinal cord. It is the outermost of the three meningeal coverings. It consists of two layers: the periosteal dura linking the inner surface of the skull and the meningeal dura that lies above the arachnoid dural membrane. The meningeal layer draws away from the periosteal layer and certain locations to form the dural reflections.

label: dorsal mesogastrium
Defs: The portion of mesentery attached to the greater curvature of the stomach is named the dorsal mesentery (or dorsal mesogastrium, when referring to the portion at the stomach), and the part which suspends the colon is termed the mesocolon. The dorsal mesogastrium develops into the greater omentum.

label: regulation of behavior
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of behavior, the internally coordinated responses (actions or inactions) of whole living organisms (individuals or groups) to internal or external stimuli.

label: acellular anatomical structure
Defs: Anatomical structure that consists of cell parts and cell substances and together does not constitute a cell or a tissue.

label: regulation of cell adhesion involved in heart morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the extent of cell adhesion contributing to the shaping of the heart.

label: vestibulo-auditory system
Defs: Sensory system responsible for the perception of spatial orientation and auditory stimuli.

label: superolateral tentorio-mandibular muscle
Defs: The cranio-mandibular muscle that is attached to the dorsal tentorial arm and the proximal margin of the insect mandible.

label: central side
Defs: Anatomical side that is centrally located on an organism or structure.

label: postero-dorsal region
Defs: Anatomical region that overlaps the posterior and dorsal regions of the body or body part.

label: zwitterion
Defs: A neutral compound having formal unit electrical charges of opposite sign on non-adjacent atoms. Sometimes referred to as inner salts, dipolar ions (a misnomer).

label: immobile
Defs: A mobility quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being incapable to move freely.

label: positive regulation of motor neuron apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of motor neuron apoptotic process.

label: polymer
Defs: A polymer is a mixture, which is composed of macromolecules of different kinds and which may be differentiated by composition, length, degree of branching etc..

label: normal fatigability
Defs: A fatigability which is relatively normal or average

label: atom
Defs: A chemical entity constituting the smallest component of an element having the chemical properties of the element.

label: quality
Defs: A dependent entity that inheres in a bearer by virtue of how the bearer is related to other entities

label: immune organ
Defs: An organ that is part of a immune system [Automatically generated definition].

label: Cd4-negative, CD8_alpha-negative, CD11b-positive dendritic cell
Defs: Cd4-negative, CD8_alpha-negative, CD11b-positive dendritic cell is a conventional dendritic cell that is CD11b-positive, CD4-negative, CD8_alpha-negative and is CD205-positive.

label: front
Defs: A directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s direction that is similar to the direction of an object to the south when it faces north.

label: waisted
Defs: A shape quality in which the bearer possesses a gradual, yet distinct, thinning from a wide starting point.

label: elytral epipleuron
Defs: The region of cuticle on the lateral region of the elytron.

label: negative regulation of small intestine smooth muscle contraction
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of small intestine smooth muscle contraction.

label: regulation of vascular associated smooth muscle cell migration
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of vascular associated smooth muscle cell migration.

label: peripheral nervous system myelin formation
Defs: The process in which the wraps of cell membrane that constitute myelin are laid down around an axon by Schwann cells in the peripheral nervous system.

label: melanocyte of skin
Defs: A melanocyte that is part of the skin of body.

label: neuron maturation
Defs: A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for a neuron to attain its fully functional state.

label: regulation of nuclear division
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of nuclear division, the partitioning of the nucleus and its genetic information.

label: regulation of dopamine secretion
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of dopamine.

label: identifier
Defs: An identifier is an information content entity that is the outcome of a dubbing process and is used to refer to one instance of entity shared by a group of people to refer to that individual entity.

label: conjunctiva
Defs: The region of the insect cuticle that is more flexible than the neighboring sclerite(s) (sclerite(s) that the conjunctiva is continuous with).

label: dorsal pancreatic bud
Defs: Pancreatic bud that gives rise to the accessory pancreatic duct.

label: regulation of intracellular protein transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of proteins within cells.

label: preplacodal ectoderm
Defs: Non neural ectoderm that surrounds the presumptive neural plate and gives rise to neurogenic placodes.

label: sunken
Defs: Flattened from above downward; below the normal level or the level of the surrounding parts.

label: multinucleate cell
Defs: A cell with more than one nucleus.

label: cell junction disassembly
Defs: The disaggregation of a cell junction into its constituent components.

label: negative regulation of extracellular matrix disassembly
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of extracellular matrix disassembly. Extracellular matrix disassembly is a process that results in the breakdown of the extracellular matrix.

label: endometrial gland
Defs: The mucous secreting gland associated with the mucuous membrane lining the uterus.

label: adipose tissue of abdominal region
Defs: Adipose tissue that is located in the abdominal region. This includes any subcutaneous fat, visceral fat or encapsulated adipose tissue depots.

label: regulation of cell junction assembly
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell junction assembly.

label: granular
Defs: A composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing granules.

label: regulation of protein modification process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the covalent alteration of one or more amino acid residues within a protein.

label: entire extraembryonic component
Defs: The part of the conceptus that may be lost before birth or will be discarded at birth, or when the embryo becomes an independent organism.

label: growth involved in heart morphogenesis
Defs: Developmental growth that contributes to the shaping of the heart.

label: outflow part of left ventricle
Defs: Anterosuperior fibrous portion of the left ventricle that connects to the ascending aorta.

label: regulation of leukocyte apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of leukocyte apoptotic process.

label: adhesivity
Defs: An emergent molecular quality that arises by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to exhibit molecular attraction to another entity in contact.

label: negative regulation of T cell activation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of T cell activation.

label: chorionic trophoblast cell development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the chorionic trophoblast over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Cell development does not include the steps involved in committing a cell to a specific fate.

label: regulation of tetrapyrrole metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of tetrapyrrole metabolic process.

label: negative regulation of bone development
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of bone development.

label: cranial ganglion development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a cranial ganglion over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: right pelvic girdle region
Defs: A pelvic girdle region that is in the right side of a multicellular organism.

label: ascending aorta
Defs: The ascending aorta is the portion of the aorta in a two-pass circulatory system that lies between the heart and the arch of aorta[GO]. A portion of the aorta commencing at the upper part of the base of the left ventricle, on a level with the lower border of the third costal cartilage behind the left half of the sternum; it passes obliquely upward, forward, and to the right, in the direction of the heart\'s axis, as high as the upper border of the second right costal cartilage, describing a slight curve in its course, and being situated, about 6 cm behind the posterior surface of the sternum. The total length is about 5 cm in length [Wikipedia].

label: regulation of glutamine family amino acid metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving amino acids of the glutamine family, comprising arginine, glutamate, glutamine and proline.

label: positive regulation of cell motility
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cell motility.

label: pleuroperitoneal membrane
Defs: A fold of tissue which extends into the peritoneal cavity of the developing embryo and participates in the separation of the pleural and peritoneal cavities.

label: decreased depth
Defs: A depth which is relatively low.

label: amino acid transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of amino acids from one side of a membrane to the other. Amino acids are organic molecules that contain an amino group and a carboxyl group.

label: pnictogen
Defs: Any p-block element atom that is in group 15 of the periodic table: nitrogen, phosphorus, arsenic, antimony and bismuth.

label: trigeminal nerve development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the trigeminal nerve over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The trigeminal nerve is composed of three large branches. They are the ophthalmic (V1, sensory), maxillary (V2, sensory) and mandibular (V3, motor and sensory) branches. The sensory ophthalmic branch travels through the superior orbital fissure and passes through the orbit to reach the skin of the forehead and top of the head. The maxillary nerve contains sensory branches that reach the pterygopalatine fossa via the inferior orbital fissure (face, cheek and upper teeth) and pterygopalatine canal (soft and hard palate, nasal cavity and pharynx). The motor part of the mandibular branch is distributed to the muscles of mastication, the mylohyoid muscle and the anterior belly of the digastric. The mandibular nerve also innervates the tensor veli palatini and tensor tympani muscles. The sensory part of the mandibular nerve is composed of branches that carry general sensory information from the mucous membranes of the mouth and cheek, anterior two-thirds of the tongue, lower teeth, skin of the lower jaw, side of the head and scalp and meninges of the anterior and middle cranial fossae.

label: dopamine metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving dopamine, a catecholamine neurotransmitter and a metabolic precursor of noradrenaline and adrenaline.

label: regulation of neuron death
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of neuron death.

label: sulfate binding
Defs: Binding to sulfate, SO4(2-), a negatively charged small molecule.

label: regulation of mesenchymal cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mesenchymal cell proliferation. A mesenchymal cell is a cell that normally gives rise to other cells that are organized as three-dimensional masses, rather than sheets.

label: retina
Defs: The retina is the innermost layer or coating at the back of the eyeball, which is sensitive to light and in which the optic nerve terminates.

label: phase
Defs: A quality that exists by virtue of being a particular point in the time of a cycle.

label: sensitivity to irradiation
Defs: A sensitivity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exposure to radiation.

label: muscle cell migration
Defs: The orderly movement of a muscle cell from one site to another, often during the development of a multicellular organism.

label: regulation of T cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of T cell proliferation.

label: posterodorsal orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed posterodorsally.

label: normal osmolarity
Defs: An osmolarity which is relatively normal or average odor.

label: neuron projection cytoplasm
Defs: All of the contents of a plasma membrane bounded neuron projection, excluding the plasma membrane surrounding the projection.

label: glucan
Defs: A polysaccharide composed of glucose residues.

label: EC 3.* (hydrolase) inhibitor
Defs: Any enzyme inhibitor that interferes with the action of a hydrolase (EC 3.*.*.*).

label: organic cation transport
Defs: The directed movement of organic cations into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Organic cations are atoms or small molecules with a positive charge which contain carbon in covalent linkage.

label: constricted
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being drawn together, compressed or squeezed physically.

label: anatomical structure maturation
Defs: A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for an anatomical structure to attain its fully functional state.

label: carbohydrates and carbohydrate derivatives
Defs: Any organooxygen compound that is a polyhydroxy-aldehyde or -ketone, or a compound derived from one. Carbohydrates contain only carbon, hydrogen and oxygen and usually have an empirical formula Cm(H2O)n; carbohydrate derivatives may contain other elements by substitution or condensation.

label: 2nd arch ectoderm
Defs: An ectoderm that is part of a pharyngeal arch 2.

label: 24G7 epitope
Defs: An antigenic epitope recognized by an anti-bilirubin monoclonal antibody designated 24G7. A substructure of bilirubin IXalpha, it is the region containing the oxo group at C-1, the methyl group at C-2, C-(4, 5, 6, 9), and N-21 and -22.

label: abdominal tergite VI-abdominal tergite VII conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect abdomen that connects the abdominal tergite VI and the abdominal tergite VII.

label: regulation of cell growth
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, extent or direction of cell growth.

label: extratelencephalic projecting
Defs: A neuron projection quality that is a characteristic of neurons whose soma is located in the telencephalon and that project to structures outside the telencephalon

label: negative regulation of translation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of proteins by the translation of mRNA or circRNA.

label: lens development in camera-type eye
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the lens over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The lens is a transparent structure in the eye through which light is focused onto the retina. An example of this process is found in Mus musculus.

label: cell condensation
Defs: Anatomical structure that is an aggregation of similar cells from which cartilages and bones form, and from which chondrogenesis and osteogenesis are initiated during repair and/or regeneration. (Hall and Miyake 1995).

label: cellular response to glucagon stimulus
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a glucagon stimulus.

label: reclinate
Defs: A curled quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s edges of its surface being bent down upon their stalk.

label: left subclavian artery
Defs: The subclavian artery that supplies the left pectoral appendage.

label: positive regulation of endodermal cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of endodermal cell differentiation.

label: skeletal muscle tissue of diaphragm
Defs: A portion of skeletal muscle tissue that is part of a diaphragm [Automatically generated definition].

label: mass flow rate
Defs: A flow rate quality inhering in a substance by virtue of the mass of substance which passes through a given surface per unit time.

label: pleuron
Defs: The region of cuticle on the lateral region of the insect thorax that is attached to the notum and the sternum and is attached to the coxae by skeletal muscle tissue and the basal coxal conjunctiva.

label: unresponsive to
Defs: A response quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lack of reaction to a stimulus or an agent.

label: insulin binding
Defs: Binding to insulin, a polypeptide hormone produced by the islets of Langerhans of the pancreas in mammals, and by the homologous organs of other organisms.

label: dendritic cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in a dendritic cell, a cell of hematopoietic origin, typically resident in particular tissues, specialized in the uptake, processing, and transport of antigens to lymph nodes for the purpose of stimulating an immune response via T cell activation.

label: bursa copulatrix
Defs: The region of the cuticle in the postabdomen that is attached to the genital chamber.

label: monocarboxylic acid biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of monocarboxylic acids, any organic acid containing one carboxyl (-COOH) group.

label: increased strength
Defs: A strength which is relatively high.

label: author summary textual entity
Defs: A textual entity, distinct from the abstract, that describes the significance and broader context of the document content. The author summary is often written in a non-technical manner and is aimed at both scientists and non-scientist readers, e.g as described in the article submission guidelines for PLoS Genetics (http://journals.plos.org/plosgenetics/s/submission-guidelines).

label: regulation of protein catabolic process at postsynapse, modulating synaptic transmission
Defs: Any process that modulates synaptic transmission by regulating a catabolic process occurring at a postsynapse.

label: skin fibroblast
Defs: A fibroblast of skin.

label: obo basic subset ontology module
Defs:
A subset ontology that is designed for basic applications to continue to make certain simplifying assumptions; many of these simplifying assumptions were based on the initial version of the Gene Ontology, and have become enshrined in many popular and useful tools such as term enrichment tools.

Examples of such assumptions include: traversing the ontology graph ignoring relationship types using a naive algorithm will not lead to cycles (i.e. the ontology is a DAG); every referenced term is declared in the ontology (i.e. there are no dangling clauses).

An ontology is OBO Basic if and only if it has the following characteristics:
DAG
Unidirectional
No Dangling Clauses
Fully Asserted
Fully Labeled
No equivalence axioms
Singly labeled edges
No qualifier lists
No disjointness axioms
No owl-axioms header
No imports

label: paraxial mesoderm development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the paraxial mesoderm over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The paraxial mesoderm is the mesoderm located bilaterally adjacent to the notochord and neural tube.

label: regulation of postsynaptic membrane neurotransmitter receptor levels
Defs: Any process that regulates the the local concentration of neurotransmitter receptor at the postsynaptic membrane.

label: enteric smooth muscle cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a smooth muscle cell of the intestine.

label: mesenchymal cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a mesenchymal cell. A mesenchymal cell is a loosely associated cell that is part of the connective tissue in an organism. Mesenchymal cells give rise to more mature connective tissue cell types.

label: dendritic cell migration
Defs: The movement of a dendritic cell within or between different tissues and organs of the body.

label: (R)-noradrenaline(1+)
Defs: An organic cation that is the conjugate acid of (R)-noradrenaline, obtained by protonation of the priamry amino group; major species at pH 7.3.

label: neural plate development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the neural plate over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The neural plate is a flat, thickened layer of ectodermal cells. The underlying dorsal mesoderm signals the ectodermal cells above it to elongate into columnar neural plate cells. The neural plate subsequently develops into the neural tube, which gives rise to the central nervous system.

label: prophragma-tentorial muscle
Defs: The dorsoventral thoracic muscle that extends between the tentorium and the prophragma.

label: regulation of excitatory postsynaptic membrane potential involved in skeletal muscle contraction
Defs: Any process, involved in skeletal muscle contraction, that modulates the establishment or extent of the excitatory postsynaptic potential (EPSP). Excitatory postsynaptic potential (EPSP) is a temporay increase in postsynaptic potential due to the flow of positively charged ions into the postsynaptic cell. The flow of ions that causes an EPSP is an excitatory postsynaptic current (EPSC) and makes it easier for the neuron to fire an action potential.

label: parasagittal plane
Defs: Sagittal plane that divides a bilateral body into unequal left and right parts.

label: neural crest cell
Defs: A cell of the neural crest. Neural crest cells are multipotent. Premigratory neural crest cells are found at the neural plate boarder, some of which will undergo ectomesynchymal transition and delamination to form migratory neural crest cells.

label: jugular foramen
Defs: The jugular foramen is a large aperture in the base of the skull. It is located behind the carotid canal and is formed in front by the petrous portion of the temporal, and behind by the occipital; it is generally larger on the right than on the left side.

label: positive regulation of inflammatory response
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the inflammatory response.

label: catalytic activity, acting on a protein
Defs: Catalytic activity that acts to modify a protein.

label: negative regulation of protein kinase activity by protein phosphorylation
Defs: Any protein phosphorylation process that negatively regulates protein kinase activity.

label: brainstem white matter
Defs: White matter that is part of a brainstem [Automatically generated definition].

label: mesothelium of diaphragm
Defs: A mesothelium that is part of a diaphragm [Automatically generated definition].

label: basement membrane of epithelium
Defs: An acellular membrane that is part of the epithelium, lies adjacent to the epithelial cells, and is the fusion of the the basal lamina and the reticular lamina.

label: articular surface
Defs: The region of cuticle where two sclerites meet.

label: herniated out of
Defs: A protruding quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s bodily structure that has protruded out of the surface or boundary of another entity.

label: regulation of excitatory synapse pruning
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of excitatory synapse pruning.

label: body external integument structure
Defs: Dermal, epidermal, glandular and pigment structures of the body integument.

label: negative regulation of transport
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of substances (such as macromolecules, small molecules, ions) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: splanchnocranium
Defs: Subdivision of endoskeleton derived from pharyngeal arches.

label: response to steroid hormone
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a steroid hormone stimulus.

label: acetylcholine biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of acetylcholine, the acetic acid ester of the organic base choline.

label: thoracic segment bone
Defs: A bone that is part of a thorax [Automatically generated definition].

label: citation
Defs: A textual entity intended to identify a particular publication.

label: neuron-glial cell signaling
Defs: Cell-cell signaling that mediates the transfer of information from a neuron to a glial cell. This signalling has been shown to be mediated by various molecules released by different types of neurons, e.g. glutamate, gamma-amino butyric acid (GABA), noradrenaline, acetylcholine, dopamine and adenosine.

label: keratinocyte apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in a keratinocyte. A keratinocyte is an epidermal cell which synthesizes keratin and undergoes a characteristic change as it moves upward from the basal layers of the epidermis to the cornified (horny) layer of the skin.

label: non-adhesive
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer not exhibiting molecular attraction to another entity in contact.

label: profurco-mesofurcal muscle
Defs: The insect thoracic muscle that extends between the profurca and the mesofurca.

label: negative regulation of cytokine production involved in immune response
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of cytokine production contributing to an immune response.

label: increased branchiness
Defs: Branchiness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of increasing the degree to which there are subdivisions or offshoots in a bearer entity.

label: larynx submucosa
Defs: A submucosa that is part of a larynx [Automatically generated definition].

label: pericardium fibroblast
Defs: Any fibroblast that is part of a pericardium.

label: decreased occurrence
Defs: An occurrence which is relatively low.

label: collagen binding
Defs: Binding to collagen, a group of fibrous proteins of very high tensile strength that form the main component of connective tissue in animals. Collagen is highly enriched in glycine (some regions are 33% glycine) and proline, occurring predominantly as 3-hydroxyproline (about 20%).

label: prolate
Defs: A spheroid quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting a polar diameter longer than its equatorial diameter.

label: embryonic heart tube formation via epithelial folding
Defs: The process that gives rise to the embryonic heart tube by the cells of the heart field along a linear axis.

label: obliquely fractured
Defs: A fractured quality where the fracture occurs at a plane oblique to the long axis of the bone.

label: negative regulation of cell maturation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cell maturation.

label: immaterial anatomical entity
Defs: Anatomical entity that has no mass.

label: nuclear migration
Defs: The directed movement of the nucleus to a specific location within a cell.

label: neoplastic, metastatic
Defs: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to spread and invade distant tissues.

label: looking up a centrally registered identifier
Defs: A planned process in which a request to a CRID registry is made to return the information associated with a CRID symbol

label: exocrine pancreas epithelium
Defs: Epithelium lining the exocrine pancreas.

label: spindle-shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling a long tapered rod.

label: cell fate commitment
Defs: The commitment of cells to specific cell fates and their capacity to differentiate into particular kinds of cells. Positional information is established through protein signals that emanate from a localized source within a cell (the initial one-cell zygote) or within a developmental field.

label: positive regulation of glial cell migration
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of glial cell migration.

label: regulation of smooth muscle cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of smooth muscle cell proliferation.

label: ventro-medial margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the ventro-medial region of the body or body part.

label: negative regulation of protein-containing complex disassembly
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein complex disassembly, the disaggregation of a protein complex into its constituent components.

label: polar amino acid zwitterion
Defs: Zwitterionic form of a polar amino acid having an anionic carboxy group and a protonated amino group.

label: left lung morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which anatomical structures of the left lung are generated and organized.

label: positive regulation of epithelial cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of epithelial cell differentiation.

label: positive regulation of insulin secretion involved in cellular response to glucose stimulus
Defs: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of insulin that contributes to the response of a cell to glucose.

label: aspiny dendrite quality
Defs: A dendrite quality inhering in a neuron by virtue of the bearer\'s dendrite having few or no recognizable dendritic spines.

label: amorphous
Defs: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lack of distinct morphology.

label: positive regulation of lipid metabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving lipids.

label: apical-basal polarity
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s location of features or characteristics along an apical-basal axis.

label: stomach primordium
Defs: A primordium that has the potential to develop into a stomach.

label: tetrapyrrole metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving tetrapyrroles, natural pigments containing four pyrrole rings joined by one-carbon units linking position 2 of one pyrrole ring to position 5 of the next.

label: negative regulation of cardiac conduction
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac conduction.

label: smooth muscle tissue of terminal bronchiole
Defs: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a terminal bronchiole [Automatically generated definition].

label: homeostatic process
Defs: Any biological process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state.

label: normal diameter
Defs: A diameter which is relatively normal or average

label: vasodilator agent
Defs: A drug used to cause dilation of the blood vessels.

label: tartrate-resistant acid phosphatase type 5 (mouse)
Defs: A tartrate-resistant acid phosphatase type 5 that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: nuclear particle
Defs: A nucleus or any of its constituents in any of their energy states.

label: cellular response to ketone
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a ketone stimulus.

label: endothelial tube
Defs: Any endothelium that has the quality of being cylindrical [Automatically generated definition].

label: leaf-like
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s similarity to the appearance of a leaf.

label: glistening
Defs: A reflectivity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s reflecting lots of light.

label: regulation of cardiac muscle tissue growth
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle growth.

label: axo-dendritic transport
Defs: The directed movement of organelles or molecules along microtubules in neuron projections.

label: regulation of Purkinje myocyte action potential
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of action potential creation, propagation or termination in a Purkinje myocyte. This typically occurs via modulation of the activity or expression of voltage-gated ion channels.

label: lingual artery
Defs: The lingual artery arises from the external carotid between the superior thyroid and facial artery[WP].

label: ciliated columnar cell of tracheobronchial tree
Defs: A ciliated columnar cell found in the trachea and bronchus. Vary from low to tall columnar; possesses up to 300 cilia at its surface, interspersed with long irregular microvilli with the cilia varying in length from about 6um in the trachea to about 4um in the terminal bronchioles; driving force of the ciliary current in the bronchial tree.

label: surface of tongue
Defs: An anatomical surface that is part of a tongue.

label: suspensorium
Defs: The sclerite of the hypopharynx.

label: regulation of nucleus organization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of nucleus organization.

label: mediolateral polarity
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s location of features or characteristics along the mediolateral axis.

label: secretory granule organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a secretory granule. A secretory granule is a small subcellular vesicle, surrounded by a membrane, that is formed from the Golgi apparatus and contains a highly concentrated protein destined for secretion.

label: axillary region
Defs: The proximal region of the insect wing.

label: inedible
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer not being suitable for use as food.

label: gonad primordium
Defs: Portion of tissue that gives rise to the immature gonad.

label: mesofemoro-mesotibial conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that encircles the mesotibia by joining the distal margin of the mesofemur and the proximal margin of the mesotibia.

label: right pulmonary artery
Defs: The pulmonary artery that supplies the right lung.

label: periderm
Defs: A temporary epithelium that derives from the outer layer of the ectdoerm and is shed once the inner layer differentiates to form a true epidermis.

label: negative regulation of stomach neuroendocrine cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of the differentiation of a neuroendocrine cell in the stomach.

label: regulation of protein localization to chromatin
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to chromatin.

label: regulation of muscle tissue development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of muscle tissue development.

label: taxis
Defs: The directed movement of a motile cell or organism in response to an external stimulus.

label: regulation of postsynaptic membrane organization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of postsynaptic membrane organization.

label: dermomyotome
Defs: The bilaminar epithelium formed from the myotome and dermatome.

label: positive regulation of mucus secretion
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of mucus from a cell or a tissue.

label: regulation of myotome development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of myotome development.

label: accessory XI nerve nucleus
Defs: The spinal accessory nucleus lies within the cervical spinal cord (C1-C5) in the ventral horn. The nucleus ambiguus is classically said to provide the \'cranial component\' of the accessory nerve. However, the very existence of this cranial component has been recently questioned and seen as contributing exclusively to the vagus nerve. The terminology continues to be used in describing both human anatomy, and that of other animals.

label: onium cation
Defs: Mononuclear cations derived by addition of a hydron to a mononuclear parent hydride of the pnictogen, chalcogen and halogen families.

label: neuromuscular process
Defs: Any process pertaining to the functions of the nervous and muscular systems of an organism.

label: positive regulation of myotube cell migration
Defs: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of myotube cell migration.

label: regulation of protein localization to nucleolus
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to nucleolus.

label: diaphragm morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the diaphragm are generated and organized.

label: oligodendrocyte development
Defs: The process aimed at the progression of an oligodendrocyte over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell. An oligodendrocyte is a type of glial cell involved in myelinating the axons in the central nervous system.

label: cellular component biogenesis
Defs: A process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of a cellular component. Includes biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, and those macromolecular modifications that are involved in synthesis or assembly of the cellular component.

label: dermatome
Defs: A transitional population of migrating mesenchymal cells that derive from somites and that will become dermal cells.

label: subclavian artery
Defs: One of two laterally paired arteries that supplies the pectoral appendages, usually branching from the dorsal aorta.

label: Purkinje myocyte
Defs: Specialized cardiac myocyte that is subendocardially interspersed with the regular cardiac muscle cell. They are uninucleate cylindrical cells, associated end-to-end in long rows, continue from the node to the atrioventricular bundle; relatively short compared to ordinary myocytes but are nearly twice their diameter.

label: regulation of leukocyte activation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of leukocyte activation.

label: nucleus of midbrain tegmentum
Defs: A nucleus of brain that spans a midbrain tegmentum.

label: positive regulation of fertilization
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of fertilization.

label: asynchronous
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s not occurring or existing at the same time or having the same period or phase.

label: glial cell
Defs: A non-neuronal cell of the nervous system. They not only provide physical support, but also respond to injury, regulate the ionic and chemical composition of the extracellular milieu. Guide neuronal migration during development, and exchange metabolites with neurons.

label: medial orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed medially.

label: regulation of mitotic nuclear envelope disassembly
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mitotic nuclear envelope disassembly.

label: head morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the head are generated and organized. The head is the anterior-most division of the body.

label: regulation of microtubule polymerization or depolymerization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of microtubule polymerization or depolymerization by the addition or removal of tubulin heterodimers from a microtubule.

label: vasculature of liver
Defs: A vasculature that is part of a liver.

label: positive regulation of multicellular organism growth
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of growth of an organism to reach its usual body size.

label: medium acidity
Defs: A concentration quality inhering in a medium by virtue of the bearer\'s tendency to hydronate a specific reference base.

label: negative regulation of cytokine production
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the rate of production of a cytokine.

label: mesenchymal cell differentiation involved in lung development
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a mesenchymal cell of the lung. A mesenchymal cell is a loosely associated cell that is part of the connective tissue in an organism. Mesenchymal cells give rise to more mature connective tissue cell types.

label: dendritic spine cytoplasm
Defs: The region of the neuronal cytoplasm located in dendritic spines.

label: postoccipital ridge
Defs: The ridge along the dorsal and lateral regions of the head capsule that is adjacent to the foramen occipitale.

label: G protein-coupled glutamate receptor activity
Defs: Combining with glutamate and transmitting a signal from one side of the membrane to the other by activating an associated G-protein, initiating a change in cell activity.

label: Merkel cell
Defs: A modified epidermal cell located in the stratum basale. They are found mostly in areas where sensory perception is acute. Merkel cells are closely associated with an expanded terminal bulb of an afferent myelinated nerve fiber.

label: sensory perception of sound
Defs: The series of events required for an organism to receive an auditory stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. Sonic stimuli are detected in the form of vibrations and are processed to form a sound.

label: endocardial endothelium development
Defs: The progression of the endocardial endothelium over time, from its initial formation to the mature structure. The endocardium is an anatomical structure comprised of an endothelium and an extracellular matrix that forms the innermost layer of tissue of the heart, and lines the heart chambers.

label: muscle layer of oviduct
Defs: A muscle layer that is part of a fallopian tube.

label: curved ventral
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved towards the abdomen of an organism.

label: post-embryonic organism
Defs: A multicellular organism that existence_starts_with a post-embryonic stage.

label: cuticle of flagellomere
Defs: The cuticle of the mere that is part of the antenna.

label: negative regulation of fat cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that stops or decreases the rate or extent of fat cell proliferation.

label: yolk sac
Defs: A sac-like expansion of the ventral wall of the intestine, narrowed into a yolk stalk near the body[Hyman\'s]. Membranous sac attached to an embryo, providing early nourishment in the form of yolk in bony fishes, sharks, reptiles, birds, and primitive mammals. It functions as the developmental circulatory system of the human embryo, before internal circulation begins. In the mouse, the yolk sac is the first site of blood formation, generating primitive macrophages and erythrocytes[WP].

label: primary subdivision of skull
Defs: The skull can be divided into two: the neurocranium and the facial skeleton.

label: ventro-lateral margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the ventro-lateral region of the body or body part.

label: cuticle of metatibia
Defs: The cuticle of the segment of a hind leg attached to the distal margin of the metafemur by the metafemoro-metatibial conjunctiva and to the proximal margin of the metatarsus by the metatibio-metatarsal conjunctiva.

label: neuron migration
Defs: The characteristic movement of an immature neuron from germinal zones to specific positions where they will reside as they mature.

label: regulation of tetrapyrrole biosynthetic process from glutamate
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of tetrapyrrole biosynthetic process from glutamate.

label: dihydrogenphosphate
Defs: A monovalent inorganic anion that consists of phosphoric acid in which one of the three OH groups has been deprotonated.

label: microvillus organization
