label: positive regulation of fat cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of adipocyte differentiation.

label: regulation of tongue muscle cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of tongue muscle cell differentiation.

label: lamina propria of large intestine
Defs: A lamina propria that is part of a large intestine.

label: leading edge membrane
Defs: The portion of the plasma membrane surrounding the leading edge of a motile cell.

label: mobile relative to
Defs: Mobility relative to a second entity.

label: abdominal tergite VIII
Defs: Is the abdominal tergite of the postabdomen that is attached to the posterior margin of the abdominal tergite VII by the abdominal tergite VII-abdominal tergite VIII conjunctiva and to the anterior margin of the abdominal tergite IX by the abdominal tergite VIII-abdominal tergite IX conjunctiva.

label: posterior orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed posteriorly.

label: epithelium of trachea
Defs: The epithelial lining of the trachea which contains numerous ciliated cells.

label: left pulmonary artery
Defs: The pulmonary artery that supplies the left lung.

label: affinity
Defs: A molecular quality that arises from the molecular attraction exerted between two atoms or compounds.

label: basal cell of epidermis
Defs: A basally situated, mitotically active, columnar-shaped keratinocyte attached to the basement membrane.

label: pre-chordal neural plate
Defs: The portion of neural plate anterior to the mid-hindbrain junction.

label: study design
Defs: A plan specification comprised of protocols (which may specify how and what kinds of data will be gathered) that are executed as part of an investigation and is realized during a study design execution.

label: in utero embryonic development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the embryo in the uterus over time, from formation of the zygote in the oviduct, to birth. An example of this process is found in Mus musculus.

label: layer of muscle tissue
Defs: Any organ component layer that consists of muscle tissue.

label: acidic
Defs: An medium acidity quality inhering in a solution by virtue of the bearer\'s a high concentration of H+ ions.

label: negative regulation of muscle tissue development
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of muscle tissue development.

label: nucleobase-containing molecular entity
Defs: Any compound that has a nucleobase as a part.

label: convolute
Defs: A curled quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s one edge of its surface being wholly rolled up in another.

label: heart rudiment
Defs: A cone-like structure that is formed when myocardial progenitor cells of the heart field fuse at the midline. The heart rudiment is the first structure of the heart tube.

label: cuticle of insect appendage
Defs: The evagination of the cuticle that is musculated (connected to the body via muscles).

label: postsynaptic actin cytoskeleton
Defs: The actin cytoskeleton that is part of a postsynapse.

label: circumocular ridge
Defs: The ridge of the head capsule surrounding the eye cuticle.

label: extracellular matrix organization involved in endocardium development
Defs: A process which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of an extracellular matrix of the endocardium. The endocardium is an anatomical structure comprised of an endothelium and an extracellular matrix that forms the innermost layer of tissue of the heart, and lines the heart chambers.

label: cranial cavity
Defs: Anatomical cavity that is the lumen of the skull and contains the brain.

label: negative regulation of dendritic spine development
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of dendritic spine development, the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the dendritic spine over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: stomach glandular region
Defs: A region of the stomach that is lined with glandular epithelium.

label: primary subdivision of cranial skeletal system
cellular response to organic substance
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an organic substance stimulus.

label: decreased strength
Defs: A strength which is relatively low.

label: chromosome segregation
Defs: The process in which genetic material, in the form of chromosomes, is organized into specific structures and then physically separated and apportioned to two or more sets. In eukaryotes, chromosome segregation begins with the condensation of chromosomes, includes chromosome separation, and ends when chromosomes have completed movement to the spindle poles.

label: elytron
Defs: The sclerotized fore wing of beetles.

label: stromal cell of pancreas
Defs: A stromal cell of the pancreas.

label: continuous
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being uninterrupted in time, sequence, substance, or extent.

label: neural tube formation
Defs: The formation of a tube from the flat layer of ectodermal cells known as the neural plate. This will give rise to the central nervous system.

label: androgen secreting cell
Defs: A steroid hormone secreting cell that secretes androgen.

label: regulation of type B pancreatic cell development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of pancreatic B cell development.

label: Golgi to vacuole transport
Defs: The directed movement of substances from the Golgi to the vacuole.

label: transmembrane receptor protein tyrosine kinase activator activity
Defs: Binds to and increases the activity of a transmembrane receptor protein tyrosine kinase.

label: extrinsic muscle of tongue
Defs: A muscle organ that attaches the tongue to some other structure.

label: light violet
Defs: A color consisting of violet hue and high brightness.

label: cell differentiation in hindbrain
Defs: The process in which relatively unspecialized cells acquire specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize the mature cells of the hindbrain. Differentiation includes the processes involved in commitment of a cell to a specific fate.

label: nerve of trunk region
Defs: A nerve that is part of the trunk region of the body (not to be confused with a nerve trunk).

label: regulation of cell projection organization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cell projections.

label: face development
Defs: The biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of a face from an initial condition to its mature state. The face is the ventral division of the head.

label: negative regulation of microtubule polymerization or depolymerization
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of microtubule polymerization or depolymerization.

label: vesicle membrane
Defs: The lipid bilayer surrounding any membrane-bounded vesicle in the cell.

label: epithelium of stomach
Defs: The epithelial layer of the stomach .

label: positive regulation of cytokine production
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of production of a cytokine.

label: musculoskeletal movement
Defs: The movement of an organism or part of an organism using mechanoreceptors, the nervous system, striated muscle and/or the skeletal system.

label: positive regulation of T cell homeostatic proliferation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the rate or extent of resting T cell proliferation.

label: regulation of lung ciliated cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of lung ciliated cell differentiation.

label: Golgi reassembly
Defs: The reformation of the Golgi following its breakdown and partitioning contributing to Golgi inheritance.

label: regulation of epidermis development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of epidermis development.

label: positive regulation of organic acid transport
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of organic acids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: sensory perception of chemical stimulus
Defs: The series of events required for an organism to receive a sensory chemical stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. This is a neurological process.

label: negative regulation of receptor binding
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of a protein or other molecule binding to a receptor.

label: abdominal segment bone
Defs: A bone that is part of an abdominal segment of trunk [Automatically generated definition].

label: foregut
Defs: Anterior subdivision of a digestive tract.

label: cuticle of first flagellomere
Defs: The cuticle of the first flagellomere of the antenna, attached to the pedicel by the pedicel-first flagellomere conjunctiva.

label: author identification
Defs: A textual entity intended to identify a particular author

label: prophragma-occipital muscle
Defs: The dorsal longitudinal thoracic muscle that is attached to the prophragma and the postocciput.

label: imperforate
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having no opening.

label: regulation of transmembrane transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of a solute from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: hepatocyte apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in a hepatocyte, the main structural component of the liver.

label: negative regulation of tetrapyrrole biosynthetic process from glutamate
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of tetrapyrrole biosynthetic process from glutamate.

label: growth factor receptor binding
Defs: Binding to a growth factor receptor.

label: polyatomic cation
Defs: A cation consisting of more than one atom.

label: regulation of RNA metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving RNA.

label: organic cyclic compound biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of organic cyclic compound.

label: dorso-ventrally flattened
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being flattened along dorso-ventral axis.

label: obsolete2_digital entity
Defs: A digital entity is an information entity which is a collection of bits that can be interpreted by a computer. Two digital entities are the same if they are bitwise identical.

label: oxoanion
Defs: An oxoanion is an anion derived from an oxoacid by loss of hydron(s) bound to oxygen.

label: cuticular ridge
Defs: The invagination on a sclerite that is elongated.

label: rectangular
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of it being a quadrilateral polygon in which all four angles are right angles.

label: chondrocyte differentiation
Defs: The process in which a chondroblast acquires specialized structural and/or functional features of a chondrocyte. A chondrocyte is a polymorphic cell that forms cartilage.

label: peripheral nervous system
Defs: A major division of the nervous system that contains nerves which connect the central nervous system (CNS) with sensory organs, other organs, muscles, blood vessels and glands.

label: extrahepatic cholangiocyte
Defs: An epithelial cell of the extrahepatic bile ducts, including the left and right hepatic duct, common hepatic duct, and common bile duct. They are columnar in shape, and have a large nuclear-to-cytoplasmic ratio relative to small/intrahepatic cholangiocytes.

label: tegmen
Defs: The phallobase that is fused to the parameres.

label: SA node cell to atrial cardiac muscle cell communication
Defs: The process that mediates interactions between an SA node cardiomyocyte and its surroundings that contributes to the process of the SA node cardiomyocyte communicating with an atrial cardiomyocyte in cardiac conduction. Encompasses interactions such as signaling or attachment between one cell and another cell, between a cell and an extracellular matrix, or between a cell and any other aspect of its environment.

label: vestigial structure
Defs: A remnant structure from earlier development or evolution.

label: jugular vein
Defs: The jugular veins are veins that bring deoxygenated blood from the head back to the heart via the superior vena cava.

label: unipotent
Defs: A cellular potency that is the capacity to produce only one differentiated cell type.

label: smooth muscle hypertrophy
Defs: The enlargement or overgrowth of all or part of an organ due to an increase in size of its smooth muscle cells without cell division. Physiological hypertrophy is a normal process during development, and can also occur in mature structures on demand. In the uterus, smooth muscle cells undergo hypertrophy during pregnancy.

label: regulation of glucose transmembrane transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of glucose transport across a membrane. Glucose transport is the directed movement of the hexose monosaccharide glucose into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: anterior to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located toward the front of an organism relative to another entity.

label: negative regulation of cardiac muscle cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate or extent of cardiac cell apoptotic process, a form of programmed cell death induced by external or internal signals that trigger the activity of proteolytic caspases whose actions dismantle a cardiac muscle cell and result in its death.

label: Purkinje fiber network
Defs: A collection of Purkinje fibers that receives signals from the right and left bundle branches and innervates the ventricular cardiac muscle. The Purkinje fiber network creates synchronized contractions of the heart ventricles.

label: conductivity
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to transmit of an entity through a medium.

label: neuroforamen
Defs: The arthropod foramen that is part of the foramen occipitale and located below the tentorial bridge.

label: trans-synaptic signaling, modulating synaptic transmission
Defs: Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse, across the synaptic cleft, that modulates the synaptic transmission properties of the synapse.

label: varicose dendrite quality
Defs: A dendrite quality inhering in a neuron by virtue of the bearer\'s dendrite having numerous swellings or varicosities along their length.

label: hypoglossal nucleus
Defs: Nucleus forming a longitudinal cell column in the medulla, close beneath the floor of the 4th ventricle, containing motor neurons that innervate the muscles of the tongue (Brodal, Neurological Anatomy, 3rd ed., 1981, pg 453).

label: physical quality
Defs: A quality of a physical entity that exists through action of continuants at the physical level of organisation in relation to other entities.

label: future central tendon
Defs: A tendon that has the potential to develop into a central tendon.

label: negative regulation of neutrophil chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate, or extent of neutrophil chemotaxis. Neutrophil chemotaxis is the directed movement of a neutrophil cell, the most numerous polymorphonuclear leukocyte found in the blood, in response to an external stimulus, usually an infection or wounding.

label: food acidity regulator
Defs: A food additive that is used to change or otherwise control the acidity or alkalinity of foods. They may be acids, bases, neutralising agents or buffering agents.

label: normal anterior-posterior diameter
Defs: An anterior-posterior diameter which is relatively normal or average

label: fertilization
Defs: The union of gametes of opposite sexes during the process of sexual reproduction to form a zygote. It involves the fusion of the gametic nuclei (karyogamy) and cytoplasm (plasmogamy).

label: craniocervical muscle
Defs: Any muscle organ that is part of either the head or the neck.

label: non-membrane-bounded organelle
Defs: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function, not bounded by a lipid bilayer membrane. Includes ribosomes, the cytoskeleton and chromosomes.

label: genital artery
Defs: One of the laterally paired arteries that supply the gonads.

label: positive regulation of asymmetric cell division
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of asymmetric cell division.

label: left common carotid artery plus branches
Defs: The leftmost of the two common carotid arteries, originating from the aortic arch in the thorax.

label: polysaccharide transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of polysaccharides from one side of a membrane to the other. A polysaccharide is a polymer of many (typically more than 10) monosaccharide residues linked glycosidically.

label: G protein-coupled neurotransmitter receptor activity
Defs: Combining with a neurotransmitter and transmitting the signal across the membrane by activating an associated G-protein; promotes the exchange of GDP for GTP on the alpha subunit of a heterotrimeric G-protein complex.

label: negative regulation of cardiac muscle tissue growth
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle growth.

label: presumptive ganglion
Defs: A presumptive structure that has the potential to develop into a ganglion.

label: branchiness
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the degree to which there are subdivisions or offshoots in a bearer entity.

label: concentration of
Defs: A quality inhering in a substance by virtue of the amount of the bearer\'s there is mixed with another substance.

label: cranium
Defs: Upper portion of the skull that excludes the mandible (when present in the organism).

label: posterior tentorio-stipital muscle
Defs: The insect cranio-maxillar muscle that is attached to the tentorium and the stipes.

label: corneo-scleral junction
Defs: The edge of the cornea where it joins the sclera; the limbus is a common site for the occurrence of corneal epithelial neoplasm.

label: positive regulation of organelle organization
Defs: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of an organelle.

label: regulation of ion transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of charged atoms or small charged molecules into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: glossopharyngeal ganglion
Defs: The group of neuron cell bodies associated with the ninth cranial nerve.

label: cellular carbohydrate catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of carbohydrates, any of a group of organic compounds based of the general formula Cx(H2O)y, as carried out by individual cells.

label: multi-localised
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being confined or restricted to multiple locations.

label: larynx development
Defs: The biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of a larynx from an initial condition to its mature state. This process begins with the formation of the larynx and ends with the mature structure. A larynx is a continuation of the pharynx that is involved in breathing, sound production, and protecting the trachea against food aspiration.

label: chemical homeostasis within a tissue
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of the internal steady state of the amount of a chemical at the level of the tissue.

label: irregular density
Defs: A density quality which lacks pattern.

label: normal affinity
Defs: An affinity which is relatively normal or average.

label: transporter activity
Defs: Enables the directed movement of substances (such as macromolecules, small molecules, ions) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells.

label: positive regulation of aorta morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of aorta morphogenesis.

label: axoneme assembly
Defs: The assembly and organization of an axoneme, the bundle of microtubules and associated proteins that forms the core of cilia (also called flagella) in eukaryotic cells and is responsible for their movements.

label: area
Defs: A 2-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s two dimensional extent.

label: positive regulation of cell death
Defs: Any process that increases the rate or frequency of cell death. Cell death is the specific activation or halting of processes within a cell so that its vital functions markedly cease, rather than simply deteriorating gradually over time, which culminates in cell death.

label: acetylcholine secretion
Defs: The regulated release of acetylcholine by a cell.

label: neck
Defs: An organism subdivision that extends from the head to the pectoral girdle, encompassing the cervical vertebral column.

label: kinase activator activity
Defs: Binds to and increases the activity of a kinase, an enzyme which catalyzes of the transfer of a phosphate group, usually from ATP, to a substrate molecule.

label: negative regulation of cell motility involved in cerebral cortex radial glia guided migration
Defs: The intracellular signaling pathway that results in the cessation of cell movement involved in lamination of the cerebral cortex.

label: Ly-6-like protein
Defs: A protein that is the translation product of any of the LY6 genes (LY6A-LY6I).

label: phosphate ion
Defs: A phosphorus oxoanion that is the conjugate base of phosphoric acid.

label: dorsum
Defs: A major subdivision of an organism that is the entire part of the organism dorsal to a horizontal plane and bounded on one side by the same transverse plane. In vertebrares this includes the vertebral column..

label: broad
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s width being notably higher than its length.

label: anteroventral to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located toward the front and abdomen of an organism relative to another entity.

label: tentorial bridge
Defs: The apophysis of the tentorium originating from each posterior tentorial arm.

label: regulation of myoblast proliferation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of myoblast proliferation.

label: external genitalia
Defs: The external genitalia are the outer sex organs, such as the penis or vulva in mammals.

label: embryonic fibroblast
Defs: Any fibroblast that is part of a embryo.

label: negative regulation of myotube cell migration
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of myotube cell migration.

label: respiratory system development
Defs: The progression of the respiratory system over time from its formation to its mature structure. The respiratory system carries out respiratory gaseous exchange.

label: negative regulation of neural crest cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of neural crest cell differentiation.

label: visceral peritoneum
Defs: The inner layer of peritoneum that is wrapped around organs located inside the intraperitoneal space.

label: osteoclast proliferation
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of osteoclasts, resulting in the expansion of an osteoclast cell population. An osteoclast is a specialized phagocytic cell associated with the absorption and removal of the mineralized matrix of bone tissue, which typically differentiates from monocytes.

label: bipolar neuron
Defs: A type of interneuron that has two neurites, usually an axon and a dendrite, extending from opposite poles of an ovoid cell body.

label: positive regulation of post-embryonic development
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of post-embryonic development. Post-embryonic development is defined as the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the organism over time, from the completion of embryonic development to the mature structure.

label: negative regulation of myeloid dendritic cell cytokine production
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of myeloid dendritic cell cytokine production.

label: mass measurement datum
Defs: A scalar measurement datum that is the result of measurement of mass quality

label: negative regulation of leukocyte activation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of leukocyte activation.

label: secretion of exocrine pancreas
Defs: A secretion that is part of a exocrine pancreas [Automatically generated definition].

label: cranial nerve maturation
Defs: A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for a cranial nerve to attain its fully functional state. The cranial nerves are composed of twelve pairs of nerves that emanate from the nervous tissue of the hindbrain. These nerves are sensory, motor, or mixed in nature, and provide the motor and general sensory innervation of the head, neck and viscera. They mediate vision, hearing, olfaction and taste and carry the parasympathetic innervation of the autonomic ganglia that control visceral functions.

label: bronchus
Defs: The upper conducting airways of the lung; these airways arise from the terminus of the trachea.

label: negative regulation of gonad development
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of gonad development.

label: tongue muscle cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a tongue muscle cell.

label: response to insecticide
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an insecticide stimulus. Insecticides are chemicals used to kill insects.

label: apical-basal gradient
Defs: Anatomical gradient that is distributed along the apical-basal axis.

label: serotonin biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of serotonin (5-hydroxytryptamine), a monoamine neurotransmitter occurring in the peripheral and central nervous systems, also having hormonal properties.

label: multi-tissue structure
Defs: Anatomical structure that has as its parts two or more portions of tissue of at least two different types and which through specific morphogenetic processes forms a single distinct structural unit demarcated by bona-fide boundaries from other distinct structural units of different types.

label: sulfate ion homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of sulfate ions within an organism or cell.

label: organelle inheritance
Defs: The partitioning of organelles between daughter cells at cell division.

label: positive regulation of embryonic development
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of embryonic development.

label: gall bladder
Defs: An organ that aids digestion and stores bile produced by the liver[WP].

label: phlegm
Defs: Mucus produced in the respiratory tract.

label: mesenchymal cell proliferation involved in lung development
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a mesenchymal cell population that contributes to the progression of the lung over time. A mesenchymal cell is a cell that normally gives rise to other cells that are organized as three-dimensional masses, rather than sheets.

label: pectoral appendage blood vessel
Defs: A blood vessel that is part of a pectoral appendage.

label: carbohydrate binding
Defs: Binding to a carbohydrate, which includes monosaccharides, oligosaccharides and polysaccharides as well as substances derived from monosaccharides by reduction of the carbonyl group (alditols), by oxidation of one or more hydroxy groups to afford the corresponding aldehydes, ketones, or carboxylic acids, or by replacement of one or more hydroxy group(s) by a hydrogen atom. Cyclitols are generally not regarded as carbohydrates.

label: peptide metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving peptides, compounds of two or more amino acids where the alpha carboxyl group of one is bound to the alpha amino group of another.

label: mucosa of tongue
Defs: A mucosa that is part of a tongue [Automatically generated definition].

label: apoptotic process involved in outflow tract morphogenesis
Defs: Any apoptotic process that contributes to the shaping of the outflow tract. The outflow tract is the portion of the heart through which blood flows into the arteries.

label: anal canal epithelium
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a anal canal.

label: skeletal system morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the skeleton are generated and organized.

label: polynucleotide
Defs: A nucleobase-containing molecular entity with a polymeric structure comprised of a linear sequence of 13 or more nucleotide residues.

label: ketone
Defs: A compound in which a carbonyl group is bonded to two carbon atoms: R2C=O (neither R may be H).

label: neutrophillic cytoplasm
Defs: Cytoplasm that exhibits a characteristic staining and color, pale-pink, with Wright-Giemsa stain.

label: pectoral appendage muscle
Defs: Any muscle organ that is part of a pectoral appendage (forelimb or pectoral fin).

label: regulation of cardiac muscle hypertrophy
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of the enlargement or overgrowth of all or part of the heart due to an increase in size (not length) of individual cardiac muscle fibers, without cell division.

label: antero-dorsal margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the antero-dorso region of the body or body part.

label: negative regulation of keratinocyte migration
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of keratinocyte migration.

label: increased variability of size
Defs: A variability of size which is relatively high.

label: retrorse
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved backward or downward.

label: regulation of T cell migration
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of T cell migration.

label: fibroblast apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in a fibroblast, a connective tissue cell which secretes an extracellular matrix rich in collagen and other macromolecules.

label: sharp
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s terminating in a point or edge.

label: actin filament-based process
Defs: Any cellular process that depends upon or alters the actin cytoskeleton, that part of the cytoskeleton comprising actin filaments and their associated proteins.

label: generation of neurons
Defs: The process in which nerve cells are generated. This includes the production of neuroblasts and their differentiation into neurons.

label: asymmetrical
Defs: A symmetry quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking symmetry.

label: regulation of adaptive immune response based on somatic recombination of immune receptors built from immunoglobulin superfamily domains
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of an adaptive immune response based on somatic recombination of immune receptors built from immunoglobulin superfamily domains. An example of this process is found in the Gnathostomata.

label: negative regulation of neurotransmitter transport
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of a neurotransmitter into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: antimicrobial peptide production
Defs: The synthesis or release of an antimicrobial peptide during an immune response, resulting in an increase in intracellular or extracellular levels. Such peptides may have protective properties against bacteria, fungi, viruses, or protozoa.

label: endothelial cell of pericentral hepatic sinusoid
Defs: An endothelial cell found in the centrilobular region hepatic sinusoid, near the central vein. The fenestrae of these cells are smaller but more numerous compared with those of endothelial cells near the periportal region of the hepatic sinusoid.

label: heart development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the heart over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The heart is a hollow, muscular organ, which, by contracting rhythmically, keeps up the circulation of the blood.

label: chromosome
Defs: A structure composed of a very long molecule of DNA and associated proteins (e.g. histones) that carries hereditary information.

label: gustatory pore
Defs: The minute opening of a taste bud on the surface of the oral mucosa through which the gustatory hairs of the specialised neuroepithelial gustatory cells project.

label: multifocal to coalescing
Defs: Multiple lesions some interconnecting with each other.

label: detection of light stimulus involved in visual perception
Defs: The series of events involved in visual perception in which a light stimulus is received and converted into a molecular signal.

label: morphogenesis of an epithelial sheet
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of an epithelial sheet are generated and organized. An epithelial sheet is a flat surface consisting of closely packed epithelial cells.

label: white matter lamina of cerebral hemisphere
pectinate line
Defs: The pectinate line (anocutaneous line, dentate line, anorectal junction) is a line which divides the upper 2/3rds and lower 1/3rd of the anal canal. Developmentally, this line represents the hindgut-proctodeum junction. It is an important anatomical landmark, and several distinctions can be made based upon the location of a structure relative to this line:.

label: negative regulation of somatic stem cell division
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of somatic stem cell division.

label: monocyte homeostasis
Defs: The process of regulating the proliferation and elimination of monocytes such that the total number of monocytes within a whole or part of an organism is stable over time in the absence of an outside stimulus.

label: positional polarity
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s location of features or characteristics along an axis.

label: ethical approval section
Defs: A part of a document about the governance body responsible for approving the work discussed in a document on an ethical basis.

label: tube development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a tube over time, from its initial formation to a mature structure. Epithelial and endothelial tubes transport gases, liquids and cells from one site to another and form the basic structure of many organs and tissues including lung and trachea, kidney, the mammary gland, the vascular system and the gastrointestinal and urinary-genital tracts.

label: cation homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of cations within an organism or cell.

label: regulation of peptide hormone secretion
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the regulated release of a peptide hormone from secretory granules.

label: negative regulation of myeloid cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of myeloid cell differentiation.

label: positive regulation of macrophage apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of macrophage apoptotic process.

label: process boundary
Defs: p is a process boundary =Def. p is a temporal part of a process & p has no proper temporal parts. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [084-001])

label: regulation of cell migration
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell migration.

label: recurrent
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s occurring or appearing again or repeatedly.

label: peptide hormone binding
Defs: Binding to a peptide with hormonal activity in animals.

label: skeleton
Defs: Anatomical cluster that consists of all the skeletal elements (eg., bone, cartilage, and teeth) of the body.

label: layer of retina
Defs: Any of the layers that make up the retina[MP].

label: negative regulation of protein catabolic process in the vacuole
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein catabolic process in the vacuole.

label: cell cortex
Defs: The region of a cell that lies just beneath the plasma membrane and often, but not always, contains a network of actin filaments and associated proteins.

label: brain meninx
Defs: A meninx that is part of a brain [Automatically generated definition].

label: pseudopodium retraction
Defs: The myosin-based contraction and retraction of a pseudopodium.

label: positive regulation of myeloid dendritic cell chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of myeloid dendritic cell chemotaxis.

label: stipito-galeal muscle
Defs: The insect cranio-maxillar muscle that is attached to the stipes and the galea.

label: proliferating neuroepithelium
Defs: An epithelium that is undergoing proliferation to provide large numbers of neuronal cells.

label: regulation of tissue remodeling
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of tissue remodeling.

label: negative regulation of striated muscle contraction
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of striated muscle contraction.

label: unserrated
Defs: A surface feature shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking sharp straight-edged teeth pointing to the apex.

label: ocular refractive media
Defs: Body substance in a liquid or semi-solid state in the eyeball which serves to refract light.

label: positive regulation of cardiac ventricle development
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac ventricle development.

label: steroid hormone
Defs: Any steroid that acts as hormone.

label: protein modification process
Defs: The covalent alteration of one or more amino acids occurring in proteins, peptides and nascent polypeptides (co-translational, post-translational modifications). Includes the modification of charged tRNAs that are destined to occur in a protein (pre-translation modification).

label: regulation of postsynaptic neurotransmitter receptor activity
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of neurotransmitter receptor activity involved in synaptic transmission. Modulation may be via an effect on ligand affinity, or effector funtion such as ion selectivity or pore opening/closing in ionotropic receptors.

label: trigeminal placode complex
Defs: A neurogenic placode that arises at the level of the midbrain-hindbrain boundary and develops into a trigeminal ganglion.

label: ciliary muscle
Defs: The ciliary muscle is a ring of smooth muscle in the middle layer of the eye that controls the eye\'s accommodation for viewing objects at varying distances and regulates the flow of aqueous humour through Schlemm\'s canal. [WP,unvetted].

label: fibroblast neural crest derived
Defs: Any fibroblast that is deriived from the neural crest.

label: vascular endothelial growth factor receptor 2 (mouse)
Defs: A vascular endothelial growth factor receptor 2 that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: regulation of Schwann cell migration
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of Schwann cell migration.

label: aetiopathogenetic role
Defs: A role played by the molecular entity or part thereof which causes the development of a pathological process.

label: desaturated magenta
Defs: A color consisting of magenta color and low saturation.

label: embryonic epithelial tube formation
Defs: The morphogenesis of an embryonic epithelium into a tube-shaped structure.

label: cardiac fibroblast cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized structural and/or functional features of a cardiac fibroblast. A cardiac fibroblast is a connective tissue cell in the heart which secretes an extracellular matrix rich in collagen and other macromolecules.

label: pelvic appendage bud
Defs: A limb bud that develops into a hindlimb or pelvic fin.

label: hexose transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of a hexose sugar, a monosaccharide with 6 carbon atoms, from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: level with
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located at the same level as another entity.

label: phosphorus metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving the nonmetallic element phosphorus or compounds that contain phosphorus, usually in the form of a phosphate group (PO4).

label: line graph
Defs:
A line graph is a type of graph created by connecting a series of data
points together with a line.

label: negative regulation of dendritic cell antigen processing and presentation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of dendritic cell antigen processing and presentation.

label: protein localization to cell cortex
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, the cell cortex.

label: heterophilic
Defs: A cellular adhesivity quality inhering in a molecule in one cell by virtue of the bearer\'s attachment to an nonidentical molecule in an adjacent cell.

label: positive regulation of neuroblast proliferation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the rate of neuroblast proliferation.

label: subserosa
Defs: A layer of tissue between the muscularis and serosa.

label: coronary vasculature development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the blood vessels of the heart over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: skeletal muscle myoblast
Defs: A myoblast that differentiates into skeletal muscle fibers.

label: scalene triangular
Defs: A triangular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having all sides of unequal length.

label: presynaptic cytoskeleton organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures and their associated proteins in the presynaptic cytoskeleton.

label: metanoto-abdominal tergite I conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva between the insect thorax and the insect abdomen that connects the posterior margin of the metanotum to the anterior margin of the abdominal tergite I.

label: time measurement datum
Defs: A scalar measurement datum that is the result of measuring a temporal interval

label: mitotic cell cycle
Defs: Progression through the phases of the mitotic cell cycle, the most common eukaryotic cell cycle, which canonically comprises four successive phases called G1, S, G2, and M and includes replication of the genome and the subsequent segregation of chromosomes into daughter cells. In some variant cell cycles nuclear replication or nuclear division may not be followed by cell division, or G1 and G2 phases may be absent.

label: anal membrane ectodermal component
Defs: A unilaminar epithelium that develops_from a ectoderm and is part of a anal region.

label: skin epidermis development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the skin epidermis over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: progressive
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s increasing over time.

label: protein transmembrane transport
Defs: The process in which a protein is transported across a membrane.

label: basal to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located toward the base of an organism relative to another entity.

label: insect adult tagma
Defs: Any tagma (UBERON:6000002) that is part of some adult (UBERON:6003004).

label: cranio-mandibular articulation
Defs: The articulation between the mandible and the cranium.

label: cellular biogenic amine metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways occurring at the level of individual cells involving any of a group of naturally occurring, biologically active amines, such as norepinephrine, histamine, and serotonin, many of which act as neurotransmitters.

label: developmental pigmentation
Defs: The developmental process that results in the deposition of coloring matter in an organism, tissue or cell.

label: aldose
Defs: Aldehydic parent sugars (polyhydroxy aldehydes H[CH(OH)]nC(=O)H, n >= 2) and their intramolecular hemiacetals.

label: prophragma-cervical muscle
Defs: The dorsal longitudinal thoracic muscle that is attached to the prophragma and the cervical sclerite.

label: lepton
Defs: Lepton is a fermion that does not experience the strong force (strong interaction). The term is derived from the Greek lambdaepsilonpitauomicronsigma (small, thin).

label: autonomic nervous system development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the autonomic nervous system over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The autonomic nervous system is composed of neurons that are not under conscious control, and is comprised of two antagonistic components, the sympathetic and parasympathetic nervous systems. The autonomic nervous system regulates key functions including the activity of the cardiac (heart) muscle, smooth muscles (e.g. of the gut), and glands.

label: anteromedial orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed anteromedially.

label: bronchiole morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which a bronchiole is generated and organized. A bronchiole is the first airway branch that no longer contains cartilage; it is a branch of the bronchi.

label: protrochantin
Defs: The trochantin that is located on the ventro-lateral region of the prothorax and is attached to a procoxa and surrounded by the basal procoxal conjunctiva.

label: position originates from
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of some aspect of that bearer beginning from a position on another entity.

label: enteroendocrine cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized structural and/or functional features of an enteroendocrine cell. Enteroendocrine cells are hormonally active epithelial cells in the gut that constitute the diffuse neuroendocrine system.

label: glandular cell of stomach
Defs: A glandular epithelial cell that is part of the stomach.

label: rhizoidal
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having root like extensions radiating from its center.

label: metencephalon development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the metencephalon over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: outflow part of left atrium
Defs: An outflow tract of atrium that is part of a left atrium.

label: epithelium of hindgut
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a hindgut [Automatically generated definition].

label: regulation of buoyancy
Defs: Any process that modulates an organism\'s tendency or ability to rise or float in a fluid medium such as water or air, often through the use of stored gases.

label: multiporous sensillum
Defs: The seta that has multiple cuticular pores (openings of class III exocrine glands).

label: multicellular organismal reproductive process
Defs: The process, occurring above the cellular level, that is pertinent to the reproductive function of a multicellular organism. This includes the integrated processes at the level of tissues and organs.

label: nuclear outer membrane organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the nuclear outer membrane.

label: regulation of translation at synapse, modulating synaptic transmission
Defs: Any process that modulates synaptic transmission by regulating translation occurring at the synapse.

label: negative regulation of cell population proliferation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the rate or extent of cell proliferation.

label: spiny dendrite quality
Defs: A dendrite quality inhering in a neuron by virtue of the bearer\'s dendrite having spines.

label: electrically active cell
Defs: A cell whose function is determined by the generation or the reception of an electric signal.

label: nucleic acid binding
Defs: Binding to a nucleic acid.

label: prominent
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s standing out or projecting beyond a surface or line.

label: syncytial nuclear migration
Defs: The directed movement of nuclei within the syncytial embryo of insects. These precise temporal and spatial patterns of nuclear movement are coordinated with mitotic divisons and are required during blastoderm formation to reposition dividing nuclei from the interior of the syncytial embryo to the cortex.

label: intermediate epitheliocyte
Defs: An epithelial cell present in the trachea and bronchi; columnar in shape; generally lack cilia; immature forms of ciliated or secretory cells which have been formed from stem cells.

label: negative regulation of cardiac muscle fiber development
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle fiber development.

label: 1st arch mandibular mesenchyme
Defs: Mesenchyme that is part of a 1st arch mandibular component.

label: positive regulation of leukocyte migration
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of leukocyte migration.

label: pleural ridge
Defs: The ridge between the epimeron and the episternum in either the mesothorax or the metathorax.

label: parietal pleura
Defs: The outer serous membrane of the pulmonary pleural.

label: increased coordination
Defs: A coordination which is relatively high.

label: protein complex involved in cell adhesion
Defs: Any protein complex that is capable of carrying out some part of the process of cell adhesion to the cell matrix or to another cell.

label: defense response to fungus
Defs: Reactions triggered in response to the presence of a fungus that act to protect the cell or organism.

label: edibility
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to being fit to be eaten.

label: axial mesoderm formation
Defs: The process that gives rise to the axial mesoderm. This process pertains to the initial formation of the structure from unspecified parts.

label: striated muscle contraction
Defs: A process in which force is generated within striated muscle tissue, resulting in the shortening of the muscle. Force generation involves a chemo-mechanical energy conversion step that is carried out by the actin/myosin complex activity, which generates force through ATP hydrolysis. Striated muscle is a type of muscle in which the repeating units (sarcomeres) of the contractile myofibrils are arranged in registry throughout the cell, resulting in transverse or oblique striations observable at the level of the light microscope.

label: regulation of sister chromatid segregation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of sister chromatid segregation.

label: skin of thorax
Defs: A zone of skin that is part of a thorax [Automatically generated definition].

label: normal tolerance to
Defs: A tolerance to an external stimulus which is relatively normal or average

label: anatomical surface region
Defs: Material anatomical entity that forms the outermost boundary of an anatomical structure.

label: adrenergic agonist
Defs: An agent that selectively binds to and activates adrenergic receptors.

label: negative regulation of eye photoreceptor cell development
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of eye photoreceptor development.

label: blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a blood vessel endothelial cell, a thin flattened cell that lines the inside surfaces of blood vessels.

label: hyoid bone
Defs: A horseshoe shaped bone situated in the anterior midline of the neck between the chin and the thyroid cartilage. The hyoid bone provides attachment to the muscles of the floor of the mouth and the tongue above, the larynx below, and the epiglottis and pharynx behind. [WP,modified].

label: metapectus
Defs: The sclerite that is continuous with the basal metacoxal conjunctiva and the basal wing conjunctiva and contains the metafurca.

label: Golgi membrane
Defs: The lipid bilayer surrounding any of the compartments of the Golgi apparatus.

label: skeletal muscle organ development
Defs: The progression of a skeletal muscle organ over time from its initial formation to its mature state. A skeletal muscle organ includes the skeletal muscle tissue and its associated connective tissue.

label: monoamine transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of monoamines, organic compounds that contain one amino group that is connected to an aromatic ring by an ethylene group (-CH2-CH2-), from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: ovulation cycle
Defs: The type of sexual cycle seen in females, often with physiologic changes in the endometrium that recur at regular intervals during the reproductive years.

label: uvea
Defs: The pigmented middle of the three concentric layers that make up an eye, consisting of the iris, ciliary body and choroid[WP,edited].

label: one-carbon compound transport
Defs: The directed movement of one-carbon compounds into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: having decreased processual parts
Defs: A quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having fewer processual parts.

label: embryonic pattern specification
Defs: The process that results in the patterns of cell differentiation that will arise in an embryo.

label: regulation of cellular carbohydrate catabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of carbohydrates, carried out by individual cells.

label: thoracic segment connective tissue
Defs: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a thorax [Automatically generated definition].

label: publication
Defs: A document that is the output of a publishing process.

label: cellular response to ammonium ion
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an ammonium stimulus.

label: serotonin receptor signaling pathway
Defs: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of a serotonin receptor binding to one of its physiological ligands.

label: prepupal
Defs: A maturity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being in an inactive stage in the development of some insects, between the larval and the pupal stages.

label: Golgi to secretory granule transport
Defs: The directed movement of proteins from the Golgi to a secretory granule. The secretory granule is a membrane-bounded particle, usually protein, formed in the granular endoplasmic reticulum and the Golgi complex.

label: pronoto-propleural conjunctiva
Defs: The noto-pleural conjunctiva that joins the pronotum and the propleuron.

label: extraembryonic structure
Defs: A multicellular anatomical structure that is associated with an embryo and derived from the zygote from which it develops, but which does not contribute to the embryo proper or to structures that are part of the same organism after embryogenesis.

label: intracellular protein transmembrane transport
Defs: The directed movement of proteins in a cell, from one side of a membrane to another by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: chandelier cell morphology
Defs: A cell morphology that inheres in neurons which are small and round, and make highly specialized synapses with the axon initial segments of pyramidal neurons, wrapping them with candle-shaped synaptic \'cartridges\'.

label: left hepatic artery
Defs: A hepatic artery that is part of a left lobe of liver.

label: regulation of chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of a motile cell or organism in response to a specific chemical concentration gradient.

label: chemical substance
Defs: A chemical substance is a portion of matter of constant composition, composed of molecular entities of the same type or of different types.

label: liver
Defs: An exocrine gland which secretes bile and functions in metabolism of protein and carbohydrate and fat, synthesizes substances involved in the clotting of the blood, synthesizes vitamin A, detoxifies poisonous substances, stores glycogen, and breaks down worn-out erythrocytes[GO].

label: superomedial tentorio-mandibular muscle
Defs: The cranio-mandibular muscle that is attached to the anterior tentorial arm and the insect mandible.

label: central nervous system white matter layer
Defs: A layer of of the central nervous system that is composed of white matter.

label: regulation of protein-containing complex assembly
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein complex assembly.

label: mesopleuro-metapleural conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect thorax that joins the mesopleuron and the metapleuron.

label: mislocalised proximally
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being positioned towards to point of attachment or origin.

label: back nerve
Defs: A nerve that is part of a back [Automatically generated definition].

label: negative regulation of type B pancreatic cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of type B pancreatic cell apoptotic process.

label: iron ion homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of iron ions within an organism or cell.

label: basement membrane
Defs: A collagen-containing extracellular matrix consisting of a thin layer of dense material found in various animal tissues interposed between the cells and the adjacent connective tissue. It consists of the basal lamina plus an associated layer of reticulin fibers.

label: atomic nucleus
Defs: A nucleus is the positively charged central portion of an atom, excluding the orbital electrons.

label: positive regulation of catecholamine metabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving catecholamine.

label: cellular response to monosaccharide stimulus
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a monosaccharide stimulus.

label: pleurostomal ridge
Defs: The ridge of the head capsule comprising the posterior region of the subgenal ridge.

label: increased radioactivity
Defs: A radioactivity which is relatively low.

label: coordination
Defs: A behavioral quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having or lacking skillful and effective interaction of movement.

label: thoracic cavity
Defs: The part of the coelemic cavity lumen that is enclosed by the walls of the thorax.

label: elytral puncture
Defs: A puncture on an elytron.

label: increased fecundity
Defs: A fecundity which is relatively high.

label: pelvic girdle bone/zone
Defs: A bone element or fused bone that is part of pelvic girdle.

label: positive regulation of animal organ morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of animal organ morphogenesis.

label: negative regulation of cell proliferation involved in heart morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cell proliferation involved in heart morphogenesis.

label: positive regulation of vascular associated smooth muscle cell migration
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of vascular associated smooth muscle cell migration.

label: CCAAT/enhancer-binding protein alpha (mouse)
Defs: A CCAAT/enhancer-binding protein alpha that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: regulation of adaptive immune response
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of an adaptive immune response.

label: anlage
Defs: Anlagen are populations of contiguous cells, typically arranged in one plane, that are morphologically indistinct, but that already correspond in extent to a later organ/tissue.

label: nerve maturation
Defs: A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for a nerve to attain its fully functional state.

label: positive regulation of epithelial to mesenchymal transition
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of epithelial to mesenchymal transition. Epithelial to mesenchymal transition is where an epithelial cell loses apical/basolateral polarity, severs intercellular adhesive junctions, degrades basement membrane components and becomes a migratory mesenchymal cell.

label: protein localization to presynapse
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a location within a presynapse.

label: EC 3.5.* (hydrolases acting on non-peptide C-N bonds) inhibitor
Defs: Any hydrolase inhibitor that interferes with the action of a hydrolase acting on C-N bonds, other than peptide bonds (EC 3.5.*.*).

label: regulation of cell growth involved in cardiac muscle cell development
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the growth of a cardiac muscle cell, where growth contributes to the progression of the cell over time from its initial formation to its mature state.

label: positive regulation of leukocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of leukocyte differentiation.

label: serosa of cloaca
Defs: A serous membrane that is part of a cloaca [Automatically generated definition].

label: splayed caudal
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved outwards from the part of the body from which the tail arises.

label: tendon
Defs: Dense regular connective tissue that connects muscle to bone[VSAO].

label: mild intensity
Defs: An intensity which is less than moderate in type or degree or effect or force.

label: cuticle of protarsus
Defs: The cuticle of the segment of the leg that is composed of protarsomeres connected to each other by intertarsomeral conjunctiva. The first protarsomere is connected to the distal margin of the protibia by the protibio-protarsal conjunctiva and the last protarsomere is connected to the proximal margin of the propretarsus by the protarso-propretarsal conjunctiva.

label: pulmonary collagen fibril
Defs: The connective tissue bundles in the extracellular matrix of pulmonary tissue that are composed of collagen, and play a role in tissue strength and elasticity.

label: rectum smooth muscle tissue
Defs: Any portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of the rectum.

label: positive regulation of leukocyte apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of leukocyte apoptotic process.

label: endothelial cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a mesodermal, bone marrow or neural crest cell acquires specialized features of an endothelial cell, a thin flattened cell. A layer of such cells lines the inside surfaces of body cavities, blood vessels, and lymph vessels, making up the endothelium.

label: growth quality of occurrent
Defs: A quality of a single process which describes the growth of an organism, structure, or group of organisms.

label: extracellular region
Defs: The space external to the outermost structure of a cell. For cells without external protective or external encapsulating structures this refers to space outside of the plasma membrane. This term covers the host cell environment outside an intracellular parasite.

label: adventitial cell
Defs: A cell of the adventitial layer of ductal structures such as the uterer, defent duct, biliary duct, etc

label: glycoprotein biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of glycoproteins, a protein that contains covalently bound glycose (i.e. monosaccharide) residues; the glycose occurs most commonly as oligosaccharide or fairly small polysaccharide but occasionally as monosaccharide.

label: diluted
Defs: A concentration which relatively low.

label: positive regulation of tetrapyrrole metabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of tetrapyrrole metabolic process.

label: orifice
Defs: Anatomical conduit that connects two adjacent body spaces (or a body space with the space surrounding the organism)[FMA,modified].

label: ganglion morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of ganglion are generated and organized.

label: epimeron
Defs: The sclerite of the insect thorax that is part of the pleuron and posterior to the pleural ridge and attached to the posterior margin of the episternum.

label: splenic fibroblast
Defs: Any fibroblast that is part of a spleen.

label: negative regulation of fibroblast migration
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of fibroblast cell migration. Fibroblast cell migration is accomplished by extension and retraction of a pseudopodium.

label: decreased female fertility
Defs: A female fertility which is relatively low.

label: positive regulation of photoreceptor cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of photoreceptor cell differentiation. An example of this process is found in Drosophila melanogaster.

label: mucosa of terminal bronchiole
Defs: A mucosa that is part of a terminal bronchiole [Automatically generated definition].

label: 4th arch mesenchyme
Defs: Mesenchyme that is part of a pharyngeal arch 4.

label: regulation of trans-synaptic signaling
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of trans-synaptic signaling.

label: decreased intensity
Defs: An intensity which is relatively low.

label: meso-epithelial cell
Defs: Epithelial cell derived from mesoderm or mesenchyme.

label: positive regulation of neuron death
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of neuron death.

label: external encapsulating structure organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of external structures that lie outside the plasma membrane and surround the entire cell.

label: mineral
Defs: In general, a mineral is a chemical substance that is normally crystalline formed and has been formed as a result of geological processes. The term also includes metamict substances (naturally occurring, formerly crystalline substances whose crystallinity has been destroyed by ionising radiation) and can include naturally occurring amorphous substances that have never been crystalline (\'mineraloids\') such as georgite and calciouranoite as well as substances formed by the action of geological processes on bigenic compounds (\'biogenic minerals\').

label: vacuolated
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a cytoplasm that contains fluid filled cavities.

label: regulation of megakaryocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of megakaryocyte differentiation.

label: dorsolateral placode
Defs: Lateral neurogenic placodes positioned dorsal of the epibranchial placodes.

label: negative regulation of nuclear migration along microtubule
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of nuclear migration along microtubule.

label: increased sensitivity to irradiation
Defs: A sensitivity to irradiation which is relatively high.

label: meiotic cell cycle process involved in oocyte maturation
Defs: Any meiotic cell cycle process that is involved in oocyte maturation.

label: nuclear outer membrane-endoplasmic reticulum membrane network
Defs: The continuous network of membranes encompassing the nuclear outer membrane and the endoplasmic reticulum membrane.

label: repetitive
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s marked by tedious repetition.

label: positive regulation of antimicrobial humoral response
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of an antimicrobial humoral response.

label: hypostomal bridge
Defs: The lateral region of the head capsule that is adjacent to the foramen occipitale

label: collagen fibril organization
Defs: Any process that determines the size and arrangement of collagen fibrils within an extracellular matrix.

label: functionality
Defs: A quality of a single physical entity that arises by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits the ability to perform a regular function(s).

label: telencephalon cell migration
Defs: The orderly movement of a cell from one site to another at least one of which is located in the telencephalon.

label: pancreatic bud formation
Defs: The morphogenetic process in which the foregut region specified to become the pancreas forms a bud.

label: tentorio-tentorial muscle
Defs: The insect cranio-antennal muscle that is attached to the tentorial bridge and the tentorium.

label: ectodermal placode morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of an ectodermal placode are generated and organized. An ectodermal placode is a thickening of the ectoderm that is the primordium of many structures derived from the ectoderm.

label: establishment of protein localization to organelle
Defs: The directed movement of a protein to a specific location on or in an organelle. Encompasses establishment of localization in the membrane or lumen of a membrane-bounded organelle.

label: muscle of back
Defs: Any muscle organ that is part of a back [Automatically generated definition].

label: raphe nuclei
Defs: The raphe nuclei are thin plates of cells in and immediately adjacent to the sagittal plane.

label: capacitance
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to hold an electrical charge.

label: epithelial cell of lower respiratory tract
fluorescent
Defs: A fluorescence quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of emitting light during exposure to radiation from an external source.

label: regulation of microtubule binding
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of microtubule binding.

label: noto-pleural conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect thorax that joins the notum and the pleuron.

label: internal jugular vein
Defs: One of two jugular veins that collect the blood from the brain, the superficial parts of the face, and the neck. [WP,unvetted].

label: trans-synaptic signaling
Defs: Cell-cell signaling in either direction across the synaptic cleft.

label: decreased force
Defs: A force which is relative low.

label: lung macrophage
Defs: Circulating macrophages and tissue macrophages (alveolar macrophages) of lung.

label: base
Defs: A molecular entity having an available pair of electrons capable of forming a covalent bond with a hydron (Bronsted base) or with the vacant orbital of some other molecular entity (Lewis base).

label: regulation of euchromatin binding
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of euchromatin binding.

label: myeloid dendritic cell chemotaxis
Defs: The movement of a myeloid dendritic cell in response to an external stimulus.

label: chondroblast differentiation
Defs: The process in which a mesenchymal cell, acquires specialized structural and/or functional features of a chondroblast. Differentiation includes the processes involved in commitment of a cell to a chondroblast fate. A chondroblast is a precursor cell to chondrocytes.

label: pectoral appendage bud ectoderm
Defs: An unilaminar epithelium that surrounds a pectoral appendage bud.

label: lung connective tissue
Defs: The connective tissue located between the respiratory (airway and alveolar) epithelium, the capillary endothelium and pleural mesothelium; it contains basement membrane composed of collagen, elastin, proteoglycans, and fibronectin.

label: bone maturation
Defs: A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for bone to attain its fully functional state.

label: reniform
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having the shape of a kidney.

label: hematopoietic oligopotent progenitor cell, lineage-negative
Defs: A hematopoietic oligopotent progenitor cell that has the ability to differentiate into limited cell types but lacks lineage cell markers and self renewal capabilities. Cell lacks hematopoeitic lineage markers.

label: availability textual entity
Defs: A textual entity expressing the location of a resource, e.g. software, or the manner in which a resource can be obtained.

label: increased spatial extent of a process
Defs: A spatial distribution of a process in which the process occupies a greater length, area, or volume than the reference process. For example, heterochromatin may form over a shorter length of a chromosome in a mutant than in wild type.

label: atrial cardiac muscle tissue morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structure of cardiac atrium muscle is generated and organized.

label: respiratory epithelial cell
Defs: An endo-epithelial cell of the respiratory tract.

label: transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of a substance, usually a specific substance or a group of related substances, from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: dark red
Defs: A color consisting of red hue and low brightness.

label: multicellular cuticular evagination
Defs: The region of cuticle that corresponds to the evagination of the single layer epithelium.

label: rectum
Defs: The terminal portion of the intestinal tube, terminating with the anus.

label: profurca-occipital muscle
Defs: The dorsoventral thoracic muscle that extends between the posterior region (occipital region) of the head capsule and the profurca.

label: bronze
Defs: A medium brown color with a metallic sheen, resembles the actual alloy bronze.

label: serous
Defs: A quality inhering a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing or resembling serum.

label: catalytic activity, acting on RNA
Defs: Catalytic activity that acts to modify RNA, driven by ATP hydrolysis.

label: lymphocyte of large intestine lamina propria
Defs: A lymphocyte that resides in the lamina propria of the large intestine.

label: duodenal mucosa
Defs: A mucosa that is part of a duodenum [Automatically generated definition].

label: positive regulation of endothelial tube morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of endothelial tube morphogenesis.

label: metanotum
Defs: The notum or sclerite on the dorsal region of the metathorax that is posterior to the mesonotum, connected via the metanoto-metapleural conjuntiva to the dorsal margin of the metapleuron, that is not adjacent to the metacoxa, but attached to it by the metacoxal muscle.

label: cellular glucan metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving glucans, polysaccharides consisting only of glucose residues, occurring at the level of an individual cell.

label: light brown
Defs: A color consisting of brown hue and high brightness.

label: bone of jaw
Defs: A bone element that is part of a jaw region.

label: relational quality
Defs: b is a relational quality = Def. for some independent continuants c, d and for some time t: b quality_of c at t & b quality_of d at t. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [057-001])

label: exocrine gland
Defs: A gland that secretes products (excluding hormones and other chemical messengers) into ducts (duct glands) which lead directly into the external environment[WP]. Typical exocrine glands include sweat glands, salivary glands, mammary glands, stomach, liver, pancreas.

label: organic hydroxy compound catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of organic hydroxy compound.

label: structural cell
Defs: A cell whose primary function is to provide structural support, to provide strength and physical integrity to the organism.

label: tongue muscle cell
Defs: A skeletal muscle cell that is part of the tongue.

label: axonal transport
Defs: The directed movement of organelles or molecules along microtubules in axons.

label: brain macroglial cell
Defs: Any macroglial cell that is part of a brain.

label: central vein of liver
Defs: Vein that is central to a lobule in the liver.

label: Golgi localization
Defs: Any process in which the Golgi is transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location within the cell.

label: monocyte antigen processing and presentation
Defs: The process in which a monocyte expresses antigen (peptide or lipid) on its cell surface in association with an MHC protein complex.

label: myocyte of sinoatrial node
Defs: A muscle cell that is part of the sinoatrial node.

label: stubby
Defs: A size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a short, stocky build.

label: decreased adhesivity
Defs: A adhesivity which is relatively low.

label: prechondroblast
Defs: Skeletogenic cell that has the potential to develop into a chondroblast; and arises from neural crest, meseosdermal and notochordal and connective tissue cells.

label: indole-containing compound catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of compounds that contain an indole (2,3-benzopyrrole) skeleton.

label: increased elasticity
Defs: An elasticity which is relatively high.

label: prosomere
Defs: A neuromere that is part of the presumptive forebrain.

label: efficiency
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of ratio of the bearer\'s output to the bearer\'s input.

label: mononuclear cell
