The optic vesicle is the evagination of neurectoderm that precedes formation of the optic cup.

label: adipose tissue
Defs: Portion of connective tissue composed of adipocytes enmeshed in areolar tissue.

label: neurotransmitter secretion involved in regulation of skeletal muscle contraction
Defs: The regulated release of neurotransmitter into the synaptic cleft involved in skeletal muscle contraction. A neurotransmitter is any of a group of substances that are released on excitation from the axon terminal of a presynaptic neuron of the central or peripheral nervous system and travel across the synaptic cleft to either excite or inhibit the target cell. Among the many substances that have the properties of a neurotransmitter are acetylcholine, noradrenaline, adrenaline, dopamine, glycine, gamma aminobutyrate, glutamic acid, substance P, enkephalins, endorphins and serotonin.

label: negative regulation of protein catabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein catabolic process.

label: diurnal
Defs: A quality of a process that happens during the hours of daylight.

label: obsolete narcolepsy
Defs: A sleep pattern quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disrupted sleep during normal sleeping period; often accompanied by cataplexy, sleep paralysis.

label: lung cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which relatively unspecialized cells, e.g. embryonic or regenerative cells, acquire specialized structural and/or functional features of a mature cell found in the lung. Differentiation includes the processes involved in commitment of a cell to a specific fate.

label: negative regulation of dopamine metabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving dopamine.

label: blunt
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s terminating gradually in a rounded end.

label: excitatory synapse pruning
Defs: The disaggregation of an excitatory synapse into its constituent components.

label: regulation of organelle transport along microtubule
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of organelle transport along microtubule.

label: midbrain development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the midbrain over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The midbrain is the middle division of the three primary divisions of the developing chordate brain or the corresponding part of the adult brain (in vertebrates, includes a ventral part containing the cerebral peduncles and a dorsal tectum containing the corpora quadrigemina and that surrounds the aqueduct of Sylvius connecting the third and fourth ventricles).

label: lining cell
Defs: A cell within an epithelial cell sheet whose main function is to act as an internal or external covering for a tissue or an organism.

label: pelvis blood vessel
Defs: A blood vessel that is part of a pelvis [Automatically generated definition].

label: planned process
Defs: A process that realizes a plan which is the concretization of a plan specification.

label: region of cuticle
Defs: The insect region of integument that is part of the chitin-based cuticle.

label: dark grey
Defs: A color consisting of grey color and low brightness.

label: insect thoracic muscle
Defs: The somatic muscle that is part of the insect thorax.

label: pro-T cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a precursor cell type acquires the specialized features of a pro-T cell. Pro-T cells are the earliest stage of the T cell lineage but are not fully committed.

label: deep cervical artery
Defs: The deep cervical artery (Profunda cervicalis) is an artery of the neck.

label: columnar epithelium
Defs: An epithelium that consists of columnar epithelial cells. Columnar epithelia are epithelial cells whose heights are at least four times their width. Columnar epithelia are divided into simple (or unilayered), and the rarer stratified (or multi-layered).[WP, modified].

label: negative regulation of glial cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of glial cell apoptotic process.

label: analysis subset ontology module
Defs: An ontology module that is intended for usage in analysis or discovery applications.

label: epithelial cell of anal column
Defs: An epithelial cell of the anal column.

label: insertion depth
Defs: A quality that is the distance between the end of the inserted object and the surface of the object into which it penetrates.

label: narrative object
Defs: A narrative object is an information content entity that is a set of propositions.

label: sphincter pupillae
Defs: A sphincter muscle that is part of the iris.

label: forebrain dura mater
Defs: A dura mater that is part of a forebrain.

label: establishment of vesicle localization
Defs: The directed movement of a vesicle to a specific location.

label: full-spectrum EM radiation quality
Defs: An EM radiation quality that is independent of the EM wavelength range.

label: pleural cavity
Defs: The fluid-filled cavity that lies between the visceral and parietal pleurae.

label: positive regulation of microtubule binding
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of microtubule binding.

label: response to glucose
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a glucose stimulus.

label: parous
Defs: An organismal quality of having successfully reproduced.

label: bilaminar disc
Defs: A flattened, almost circular bilaminar plate of cells formed when the inner cell mass (aka embryoblast) forms two epithelial layers, each of a distinct lineage, separated by an extracellular basement membrane: the external (dorsal) layer is called the epiblast and the internal (ventral) layer is called the hypoblast (aka primitive endoderm); together, they compose the bilaminar embryonic disc.

label: CD34-positive, CD38-positive common lymphoid progenitor
Defs: A common lymphoid progenitor that is CD10-positive, CD45RA-positive, CD34-positive and CD38-positive.

label: vasoconstrictor agent
Defs: Drug used to cause constriction of the blood vessels.

label: strain
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the relative change in the bearer\'s length or the bearer\'s volume when being stretched or squashed.

label: chorionic ectoderm
Defs: An extraembryonic structure that develops_from a ectoderm and is part of a chorion.

label: choroidal blood vessel
Defs: A blood vessel that is part of a choroid [Automatically generated definition].

label: esophagus squamous epithelium
Defs: A squamous epithelium that is part of a esophagus.

label: meiotic chromosome condensation
Defs: Compaction of chromatin structure prior to meiosis in eukaryotic cells.

label: sufficiency
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer has enough functionality.

label: motile cilium assembly
Defs: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a motile cilium.

label: hematopoietic cell
Defs: A cell of a hematopoietic lineage.

label: offset quality
Defs: The temporal relation between the end of the process with respect to a reference process.

label: regulation of membrane disassembly
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of membrane disassembly.

label: cellular biogenic amine catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways occurring at the level of individual cells resulting in the breakdown of biogenic amines, any of a group of naturally occurring, biologically active amines, such as norepinephrine, histamine, and serotonin, many of which act as neurotransmitters.

label: neuromuscular junction of myotube
Defs: A neuromuscular junction in which the target muscle cell is a myotube.

label: thoracic cavity nerve
Defs: A nerve that is located in a thoracic cavity [Automatically generated definition].

label: cytoplasmic microtubule organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of structures formed of microtubules and associated proteins in the cytoplasm of a cell.

label: lumen of central nervous system
Defs: The cavity that is enclosed by the central nervous system. In vertebrates this is the cavity that includes as parts ventricular cavities and the central canal of the spinal cord that develops from the lumen of the neura tube.

label: left ventricle myocardium
Defs: A myocardium that is part of a left ventricle of a heart.

label: normal fertility
Defs: A fertility which is relatively normal or average.

label: metanoto-metatrochantinal muscle
Defs: The tergo-trochantinal muscle that is attached to the metanotum and the metatrochantin.

label: cerebral cortex pyramidal neuron
Defs: A pyramidal neuron with soma located in the cerebral cortex.

label: pigmentation
Defs: The accumulation of pigment in an organism, tissue or cell, either by increased deposition or by increased number of cells.

label: regulation of oligodendrocyte progenitor proliferation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of oligodendrocyte progenitor proliferation.

label: serosa of esophagus
Defs: A serous membrane that is part of a esophagus [Automatically generated definition].

label: muscle layer of small intestine
Defs: A muscle layer that is part of a small intestine.

label: regulation of protein metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving a protein.

label: patent
Defs: A document that has been accepted by a patent authority

label: increased male fertility
Defs: A male fertility which is relatively high.

label: G protein-coupled serotonin receptor activity
Defs: Combining with the biogenic amine serotonin and transmitting the signal across the membrane by activating an associated G-protein. Serotonin (5-hydroxytryptamine) is a neurotransmitter and hormone found in vertebrates and invertebrates.

label: positive regulation of cardiac muscle contraction
Defs: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle contraction.

label: paleopolyploid
Defs: A polyploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having an ancient polyploid ancestor.

label: fibroblast growth factor 8 (mouse)
Defs: A fibroblast growth factor 8 that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: positive regulation of glycogen catabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of glycogen.

label: fenestrated
Defs: A structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s delimited by a surface with holes.

label: atrial cardiac muscle tissue development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of cardiac muscle of the atrium over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: spiny stellate cell morphology
Defs: A cell morphology that inheres in neurons which have spiny basal dendrites and resemble pyramidal cells but lose their apical dendrites as they mature. Their axons nearly always emerge from the descending side of the soma, but often recurve and ascend with arc-like collaterals.

label: regulation of cellular amine metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways by which individual cells transform amines.

label: endocardium development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the endocardium over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The endocardium is an anatomical structure comprised of an endothelium and an extracellular matrix that forms the innermost layer of tissue of the heart, and lines the heart chambers.

label: mesentery of foregut-midgut junction
Defs: A mesentery that is part of a foregut-midgut junction.

label: insect cranio-maxillar muscle
Defs: The somatic muscle that is attached to the head capsule and the insect maxilla.

label: protruding into
Defs: A quality inhering into a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s extending out above or beyond its surface or boundary into the surface or boundary of another entity.

label: tumor necrosis factor receptor superfamily member 11A (mouse)
Defs: A tumor necrosis factor receptor superfamily member 11A that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: protruding
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s extending out above or beyond a surface or boundary.

label: refractory
Defs: An occurrence of a process during which time there is an inability to change the course, extent, or repetition of the process.

label: positive regulation of peptidyl-tyrosine phosphorylation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the phosphorylation of peptidyl-tyrosine.

label: arch of aorta
Defs: The convex portion of the aorta between the ascending and descending parts of the aorta; branches from it include the brachiocephalic trunk, the left common carotid artery, and the left subclavian artery; the brachiocephalic trunk further splits to form the right subclavian artery and the right common carotid artery.

label: decreased speed
Defs: A speed which is relatively low.

label: hepatic duct
Defs: Any portion of the ducts that carry bile from the liver to the common bile duct. This may include both intrahapetic components (parts of left and right hepatic ducts) and extrahapetic components (common hepatic duct, plus hilar portion).

label: defense response to bacterium
Defs: Reactions triggered in response to the presence of a bacterium that act to protect the cell or organism.

label: negative regulation of establishment of protein localization
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of establishment of protein localization.

label: normal threshold
Defs: A threshold which is relatively normal or average

label: ribonucleoprotein complex binding
Defs: Binding to a complex of RNA and protein.

label: tunica adventitia of artery
Defs: A tunica adventitia that is part of a artery.

label: elytral interstria
Defs: The region of the cuticle of the elytral disc that is adjacent to an elytral stria.

label: molecule
Defs: Any polyatomic entity that is an electrically neutral entity consisting of more than one atom.

label: protein localization to nuclear envelope
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained at, a location within a nuclear envelope.

label: mitotic nuclear membrane organization
Defs: A mitotic cell cycle process which results in the assembly, arrangement, or disassembly of the nuclear inner or outer membrane during mitosis.

label: pelvic girdle skeleton
Defs: Skeletal subdivision consisting of a set of bones linking the axial series to the hindlimb zeugopodium and offering anchoring areas for hindlimb and caudal musculature.

label: regulation of cardiocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cardiocyte differentiation.

label: cuticle of gonocoxa IX
Defs: The paired sclerite of the postabdomen that is attached to the abdominal tergite IX by the abdominal tergite IX-gonocoxa IX conjunctiva and is articulated with abdominal tergite IX.

label: apoptotic nuclear changes
Defs: Alterations undergone by nuclei at the molecular and morphological level as part of the execution phase of apoptosis.

label: excretion
Defs: The elimination by an organism of the waste products that arise as a result of metabolic activity. These products include water, carbon dioxide (CO2), and nitrogenous compounds.

label: one dimensional cartesian spatial coordinate datum
Defs: A cartesion spatial coordinate datum that  uses one value to specify a position along a one dimensional spatial region

label: compound eye retinal cell
Defs: Any cell in the compound eye, a light sensing organ composed of ommatidia.

label: lysosomal membrane
Defs: The lipid bilayer surrounding the lysosome and separating its contents from the cell cytoplasm.

label: synchronous
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s occurring or existing at the same time or having the same period or phase.

label: regulation of amine transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of amines into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: regulation of hepatocyte apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of hepatocyte apoptotic process.

label: splayed lateral
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved outwards from the side.

label: posterior tentorial arm
Defs: Is the apophysis of the tentorium that originates from each posterior tetorial pit.

label: severe intensity
Defs: An intensity which is extremely bad or unpleasant in type or degree or effect or force.

label: mesotarso-mesopretarsal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that encircles the mesopretarsus by joining the distal margin of the distalmost mesotarsomere and the proximal margin of the mesopretarsus.

label: cardiac muscle tissue growth involved in heart morphogenesis
Defs: The developmental growth of cardiac muscle tissue that contributes to the shaping of the heart.

label: metal atom
Defs: An atom of an element that exhibits typical metallic properties, being typically shiny, with high electrical and thermal conductivity.

label: cortical plate
Defs: The outer neural tube region in which post-mitotic neuroblasts migrate along radial glia to form the adult cortical layers[MP].

label: translation
Defs: The cellular metabolic process in which a protein is formed, using the sequence of a mature mRNA or circRNA molecule to specify the sequence of amino acids in a polypeptide chain. Translation is mediated by the ribosome, and begins with the formation of a ternary complex between aminoacylated initiator methionine tRNA, GTP, and initiation factor 2, which subsequently associates with the small subunit of the ribosome and an mRNA or circRNA. Translation ends with the release of a polypeptide chain from the ribosome.

label: muscle system process
Defs: A organ system process carried out at the level of a muscle. Muscle tissue is composed of contractile cells or fibers.

label: attachment quality
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having connection or association with another entity.

label: dorso-ventral thoracic muscle
Defs: The insect thoracic muscle that runs parallel to the dorsal-ventral axis.

label: gastroduodenal junction
Defs: An anatomical junction that connects a stomach and connects a duodenum.

label: blistered
Defs: A texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of a local accumulation of fluid underneath the surface of the bearer.

label: decreased concentration
Defs: A concentration which is lower relative to the normal or average.

label: negative regulation of tetrapyrrole catabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of tetrapyrrole catabolic process.

label: trunk neural crest cell migration
Defs: The characteristic movement of trunk neural crest cells from the neural tube to other locations in the vertebrate embryo.

label: rate
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s occurrence per unit time.

label: right cardiac atrium
Defs: A cardiac atrium that is in the left side of the heart. It receives deoxygenated blood. In mammals, this comes from the superior and inferior vena cava and the coronary sinus, and pumps it into the right ventricle through the tricuspid valve.

label: splenic endothelial cell
Defs: Any endothelial cell that is part of a spleen.

label: negative regulation of sodium ion transport
Defs: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of sodium ions (Na+) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: positive regulation of cardiac muscle cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle cell differentiation.

label: extracellular structure organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of structures in the space external to the outermost structure of a cell. For cells without external protective or external encapsulating structures this refers to space outside of the plasma membrane, and also covers the host cell environment outside an intracellular parasite.

label: chalcogen molecular entity
Defs: Any p-block molecular entity containing a chalcogen.

label: regulation of establishment of protein localization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of a protein to a specific location.

label: presumptive midbrain hindbrain boundary
Defs: Embryonic structure that gives rise to the midbrain hindbrain boundary.

label: negative regulation of pancreatic A cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of pancreatic A cell differentiation.

label: negative regulation of sodium ion transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of sodium ion transmembrane transporter activity.

label: corticothalamic-projecting glutamatergic cortical neuron
Defs: A glutamatergic neuron located in the cerebral cortex that projects to the thalamus.

label: positive regulation of megakaryocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of megakaryocyte differentiation.

label: lung bud
Defs: Structure derived from foregut that becomes a lung[GO].

label: signaling receptor activity
Defs: Receiving a signal and transmitting it in the cell to initiate a change in cell activity. A signal is a physical entity or change in state that is used to transfer information in order to trigger a response.

label: protein localization to postsynaptic membrane
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a location within a postsynaptic membrane.

label: superficial region
Defs: Anatomical region superficially located on the body or body part.

label: concealed
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being hidden from view.

label: regulation of tube lumen cavitation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of tube lumen cavitation.

label: embryonic camera-type eye formation
Defs: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of a camera-type eye from unspecified neurectoderm. This process begins with the differentiation of cells that form the optic field and ends when the optic cup has attained its shape.

label: negative regulation of cation transmembrane transport
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cation transmembrane transport.

label: type A cell of stomach
Defs: A type of enteroendocrine cell found in the stomach that secretes glucagon.

label: negative regulation of intracellular protein transport
Defs: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of proteins within cells.

label: microtubule-based transport
Defs: A microtubule-based process that results in the transport of organelles, other microtubules, or other cellular components.  Examples include motor-driven movement along microtubules and movement driven by polymerization or depolymerization of microtubules.

label: conflict of interest section
Defs: A part of a document used to declare any competing interests regarding the authors and/or funding organization for the work described in the document.

label: Kit-low proerythroblast
Defs: A proerythoblast that is Kit-low, Lyg76-positive, and CD71-positive.

label: primordial vasculature
Defs: A portion of tissue that will develop into vasculature.

label: stromal cell of lamina propria of colon
Defs: A stromal cell found in the lamina propria of the colon.

label: male genotypic sex
Defs: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual based upon genotypic composition that confers the capability for an organism to differentiate male gonads.

label: carbohydrate transmembrane transport
Defs: The process in which a carbohydrate is transported across a membrane.

label: T cell activation involved in immune response
Defs: The change in morphology and behavior of a mature or immature T cell resulting from exposure to a mitogen, cytokine, chemokine, cellular ligand, or an antigen for which it is specific, leading to the initiation or perpetuation of an immune response.

label: normal position
Defs: A position which is relatively normal or average

label: immortal
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to being capable of indefinite growth or division.

label: peptide transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of a peptide from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: size
Defs: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s physical magnitude.

label: neural cell
Defs: A cell that is part of the nervous system.

label: transport vesicle
Defs: Any of the vesicles of the constitutive secretory pathway, which carry cargo from the endoplasmic reticulum to the Golgi, between Golgi cisternae, from the Golgi to the ER (retrograde transport) or to destinations within or outside the cell.

label: endoderm-derived structure
Defs: An anatomical structure that develops (entirely or partially) from the endoderm.

label: female germ cell
Defs: Female germ cell is a germ cell that supports female gamete production.

label: regulation of mesenchymal cell proliferation involved in lung development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mesenchymal cell proliferation involved in lung development.

label: detection of stimulus
Defs: The series of events in which a stimulus is received by a cell or organism and converted into a molecular signal.

label: skin epidermis
Defs: The outer epithelial layer of the skin that is superficial to the dermis.

label: craspedodromous
Defs: A branched quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having secondary branches terminating at the margin.

label: positive regulation of microvillus assembly
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of microvillus assembly.

label: positive regulation of pigment cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of pigment cell differentiation.

label: aorta endothelium
Defs: The thin layer of flat cells that line the aorta and form a barrier between circulating blood in the lumen and the rest of the vessel wall.

label: response to external stimulus
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an external stimulus.

label: metacoxal cavity
Defs: The concave region of abdominal sternites II and III that receive the metacoxa.

label: pigmented
Defs: A degree of pigmentation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having substances produced by living organisms that have a color resulting from selective color absorption.

label: regulation of lymphocyte proliferation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of lymphocyte proliferation.

label: steroid
Defs: Any of naturally occurring compounds and synthetic analogues, based on the cyclopenta[a]phenanthrene carbon skeleton, partially or completely hydrogenated; there are usually methyl groups at C-10 and C-13, and often an alkyl group at C-17. By extension, one or more bond scissions, ring expansions and/or ring contractions of the skeleton may have occurred. Natural steroids are derived biogenetically from squalene which is a triterpene.

label: bile acid biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of bile acids, any of a group of steroid carboxylic acids occurring in bile.

label: positive regulation of response to biotic stimulus
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of a response to biotic stimulus.

label: response to amine
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an amine stimulus. An amine is a compound formally derived from ammonia by replacing one, two or three hydrogen atoms by hydrocarbyl groups.

label: amide
Defs: An amide is a derivative of an oxoacid RkE(=O)l(OH)m (l =/= 0) in which an acidic hydroxy group has been replaced by an amino or substituted amino group.

label: right hepatic vein
Defs: A hepatic vein that is part of a right lobe of liver.

label: normal concentration
Defs: A concentration which is relatively normal or average.

label: ecto-epithelium
Defs: Epithelium composed of cells that develops from the ectoderm[FMA,modified].

label: membrane-enclosed lumen
Defs: The enclosed volume within a sealed membrane or between two sealed membranes. Encompasses the volume enclosed by the membranes of a particular organelle, e.g. endoplasmic reticulum lumen, or the space between the two lipid bilayers of a double membrane surrounding an organelle, e.g. nuclear envelope lumen.

label: epithelium of bronchiole
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a bronchiole [Automatically generated definition].

label: pharyngeal arch artery 2
Defs: The vessels formed within the second pair of branchial arches in embryogenesis.

label: regulation of chondrocyte differentiation involved in endochondral bone morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the process in which a chondroblast acquires specialized structural and/or functional features of a chondrocyte that will contribute to the development of a bone. A chondrocyte is a polymorphic cell that forms cartilage.

label: intact female
Defs: Female quality of having complete, unaltered reproductive organs

label: physiological cardiac muscle hypertrophy
Defs: The enlargement or overgrowth of all or part of the heart muscle due to an increase in size of cardiac muscle cells without cell division. This process contributes to the developmental growth of the heart.

label: quality of a gas
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting the physical characteristics of an entity consisting of particles that have neither a defined volume nor defined shape.

label: supramolecular fiber
Defs: A polymer consisting of an indefinite number of protein or protein complex subunits that have polymerised to form a fiber-shaped structure.

label: small basket cell morphology
Defs: A basket cell morphology that inheres in neurons with axonal arbors composed of frequent, short, curvy axonal branches that tend to be near their somata and within the same layer.

label: positive regulation of syncytium formation by plasma membrane fusion
Defs: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of the formation of a syncytium, a mass of cytoplasm containing several nuclei enclosed within a single plasma membrane, by the fusion of the plasma membranes of two or more individual cells.

label: somatic muscle
Defs: A muscle structure of invertebrates whose origin and insertion sites are in basal side of the epidermis or structures derived from it. The simplest somatic muscles consist of a single cell and associated extracellular structures.

label: dark cyan
Defs: A color consisting of cyan hue and low brightness.

label: exosomal secretion
Defs: The process whereby a membrane-bounded vesicle is released into the extracellular region by fusion of the limiting endosomal membrane of a multivesicular body with the plasma membrane.

label: cellular polysaccharide metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving polysaccharides, polymers of more than 10 monosaccharide residues joined by glycosidic linkages, as carried out by individual cells.

label: lip taste bud
Defs: A taste bud that is located on a lip.

label: costal field
Defs: The anterior region of the insect wing.

label: organic hydroxy compound transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of organic hydroxy compound from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: regulation of acetylcholine metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving acetylcholine, the acetic acid ester of the organic base choline. Acetylcholine is a major neurotransmitter and neuromodulator both in the central and peripheral nervous systems. It also acts as a paracrine signal in various non-neural tissues.

label: negative regulation of lipid biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of lipids.

label: musculature of pelvic girdle
Defs: Any collection of muscles that is part of a pelvic girdle [Automatically generated definition].

label: respiratory system artery
Defs: An artery that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

label: crustacean metabolite
Defs: An animal metabolite produced by arthropods such as crabs, lobsters, crayfish, shrimps and krill.

label: intermediate mesoderm development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the intermediate mesoderm over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The intermediate mesoderm is located between the lateral mesoderm and the paraxial mesoderm. It develops into the kidney and gonads.

label: megakaryocyte development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a megakaryocyte cell over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Megakaryocyte development does not include the steps involved in committing a cell to a megakaryocyte fate. A megakaryocyte is a giant cell 50 to 100 micron in diameter, with a greatly lobulated nucleus, found in the bone marrow.

label: positive regulation of meiotic cell cycle
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of progression through the meiotic cell cycle.

label: univalent carboacyl group
Defs: A univalent carboacyl group is a group formed by loss of OH from the carboxy group of a carboxylic acid.

label: negative regulation of ribosome biogenesis
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of ribosome biogenesis. Ribosome biogenesis is the cellular process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of ribosome subunits.

label: nucleus localization
Defs: Any process in which the nucleus is transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location within the cell.

label: lumenized
Defs: A structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a three dimensional space surrounded by one or more anatomical structures and containing one or more anatomical substances.

label: light red brown
Defs: A color consisting of red and brown hue and high brightness.

label: mucopolysaccharide metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving mucopolysaccharide.

label: negative regulation of smooth muscle cell chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of smooth muscle cell chemotaxis.

label: positive regulation of glucagon secretion
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of glucagon.

label: antimicrobial humoral response
Defs: An immune response against microbes mediated through a body fluid. Examples of this process are seen in the antimicrobial humoral response of Drosophila melanogaster and Mus musculus.

label: hyaluronate
Defs: A carbohydrate acid derivative anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy groups of hyaluronic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

label: infiltrative
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s penetrating or permeating another substance or area.

label: setose
Defs: A hairy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being covered with setae.

label: humoral immune response
Defs: An immune response mediated through a body fluid.

label: spinal neuromere
Defs: A neuromere that is part of the presumptive spinal cord.

label: lateral plate mesoderm
Defs: Portion of the middle of the three primary germ layers of the embryo that resides on the periphery of the embryo, is continuous with the extra-embryonic mesoderm, splits into two layers enclosing the intra-embryonic coelom, and gives rise to body wall structures[MP].

label: negative regulation of humoral immune response
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of a humoral immune response.

label: maxillary artery
Defs: An artery that supplies deep structures of the face. It comes just out behind the neck of the mandible. [WP,unvetted].

label: information carrier
Defs: A quality of an information bearer that imparts the information content

label: decreased fragility
Defs: A fragility which is relatively low.

label: regulation of endothelial cell chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of endothelial cell chemotaxis.

label: membranous septum morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the membranous septum is generated and organized. The membranous septum is the upper part of ventricular septum.

label: negative regulation of macromolecule metabolic process
Defs: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving macromolecules, any molecule of high relative molecular mass, the structure of which essentially comprises the multiple repetition of units derived, actually or conceptually, from molecules of low relative molecular mass.

label: labyrinthine layer morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the labyrinthine layer of the placenta is generated and organized.

label: sympathetic nervous system
Defs: The sympathetic nervous system is one of the two divisions of the vertebrate autonomic nervous system (the other being the parasympathetic nervous system). The sympathetic preganglionic neurons have their cell bodies in the thoracic and lumbar regions of the spinal cord and connect to the paravertebral chain of sympathetic ganglia. Innervate heart and blood vessels, sweat glands, viscera and the adrenal medulla. Most sympathetic neurons, but not all, use noradrenaline as a post-ganglionic neurotransmitter [GO].

label: pyloric canal
Defs: The short narrow part of the stomach extending from the pyloric antrum to the pyloric sphincter.

label: incompatible
Defs: A compatibility quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being incapable of harmonious coexistence.

label: increased phosphorylation
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being phosphorylated to a more than normal extent, or fully saturated with phosphate groups.

label: time sampled measurement data set
Defs: A data set that is an aggregate of data recording some measurement at a number of time points. The time series data set is an ordered list of pairs of time measurement data and the corresponding measurement data acquired at that time.

label: regulation of macrophage antigen processing and presentation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of macrophage antigen processing and presentation.

label: EC 3.5.1.4 (amidase) inhibitor
Defs: An EC 3.5.1.* (non-peptide linear amide C-N hydrolase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of amidase (EC 3.5.1.4).

label: necessary (continuant)
Defs: A necessity quality (continuant) inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being essential or indispensable.

label: mesenchymal to epithelial transition
Defs: A transition where a mesenchymal cell establishes apical/basolateral polarity, forms intercellular adhesive junctions, synthesizes basement membrane components and becomes an epithelial cell.

label: mineralized bone tissue
Defs: Bone tissue mineralized with hydroxyapatite.

label: mucosa of cystic duct
Defs: A mucosa that is part of a cystic duct [Automatically generated definition].

label: anatomical structure quality
Defs: A quality of continuant that exist at the anatomical level of organisation and anything under it. This includes, but is not limited to, cells , tissues, and components.

label: obsolete unknown sex
Defs: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual whose sex is unknown.

label: chorioretinal region
Defs: The part of the eye that consists of both the retina and the optic choroid.

label: abdominal sternite II
Defs: The abdominal tergite of the preabdomen that is attached to the posterior margin of the abdominal sternite I by the abdominal sternite I-abdominal sternite II conjunctiva and to the anterior margin of the abdominal sternite III by the abdominal sternite II-abdominal sternite III conjunctiva.

label: conspicuous
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of being clearly visible.

label: beta-adrenergic drug
Defs: Any of the drugs that act on beta-adrenergic receptors.

label: oxygen binding
Defs: Binding to oxygen (O2).

label: normal thickness
Defs: A thickness which is relatively normal or average

label: lipid export from cell
Defs: The directed movement of a lipid from a cell, into the extracellular region.

label: oogenesis
Defs: The complete process of formation and maturation of an ovum or female gamete from a primordial female germ cell. Examples of this process are found in Mus musculus and Drosophila melanogaster.

label: erythrocyte apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in an erythrocyte.

label: regulation of developmental pigmentation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the developmental process that results in the deposition of coloring matter in an organism.

label: negative regulation of phosphorus metabolic process
Defs: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving phosphorus or compounds containing phosphorus.

label: polyploid
Defs: A ploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing more than two homologous sets of chromosomes.

label: dendritic microtubule
Defs: Any microtubule in a dendrite, a neuron projection.

label: positive regulation of cardiac muscle tissue development
Defs: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle tissue development.

label: nucleophilic reagent
Defs: A reagent that forms a bond to its reaction partner (the electrophile) by donating both bonding electrons.

label: epithelial cell of uterus
Defs: An epithelial cell of the uterus.

label: positive regulation of endothelial cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of endothelial cell differentiation.

label: neurotoxin
Defs: A poison that interferes with the functions of the nervous system.

label: dorsomedial orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed dorsomedially.

label: skin muscle
Defs: Any muscle organ that is part of a skin of body [Automatically generated definition].

label: increased radiopacity
Defs: A radiopacity that is relatively high.

label: retina morphogenesis in camera-type eye
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structure of the retina is generated and organized.

label: borderline intensity
Defs: An intensity which is borderline in it its effect or force as compared to baseline or normal.

label: dopamine
Defs: Catechol in which the hydrogen at position 4 is substituted by a 2-aminoethyl group.

label: avidity
Defs: A molecular quality that arises from the synergistic strength of bond affinities between multiple bond interactions.

label: presomitic mesoderm
Defs: Unsegmented field of paraxial mesoderm present posterior to the most recently formed somite pair, from which somites will form.

label: formation of primary germ layer
Defs: The formation of the ectoderm, mesoderm and endoderm during gastrulation.

label: bone foramen
Defs: Anatomical space that is an opening in a bone, usually for passage of blood vessels or nerves.

label: lung blood vessel
Defs: A blood vessel that is part of a lung [Automatically generated definition].

label: metendosternite
Defs: The furca of the metathorax that is attached to the metacoxa via muscle.

label: positive regulation of vascular associated smooth muscle cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of vascular smooth muscle cell proliferation.

label: club cell
Defs: Epithelial progenitor cell of the lung. Club cells are dome-shaped with short microvilli but no cilia. They function to protect the bronchiolar epithelium. Club cells also multiply and differentiate into ciliated cells to regenerate the bronchiolar epithelium.

label: lymphocyte antigen 6A-2/6E-1
Defs: An Ly-6-like protein that is a translation product of the mouse Ly6a gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: bicarbonate transport
Defs: The directed movement of bicarbonate into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: gigantic
Defs: A size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being many folds greater relative to the normal average.

label: cavity of pharynx
Defs: An anatomical space that is enclosed by a pharynx.

label: hard
Defs: A hardness quality of being rigid and resistant to pressure.

label: subgena
Defs: The lateral region of the head capsule that connects dorsally to the ventral side of the gena and ventrally to the mandible.

label: positive regulation of defecation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of defecation.

label: positive regulation of behavior
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of behavior, the internally coordinated responses (actions or inactions) of whole living organisms (individuals or groups) to internal or external stimuli.

label: respiratory tract epithelium
Defs: The pseudostratified ciliated epithelium that lines much of the conducting portion of the airway, including part of the nasal cavity and larynx, the trachea, and bronchi.

label: regulation of protein localization to synapse
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to synapse.

label: regulation of macrophage chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of macrophage chemotaxis. Macrophage chemotaxis is the movement of a macrophage in response to an external stimulus.

label: hydrogenphosphate
Defs: A phosphate ion that is the conjugate base of dihydrogenphosphate.

label: mixture
Defs: A mixture is a chemical substance composed of multiple molecules, at least two of which are of a different kind.

label: nucleobase biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a nucleobase, a nitrogenous base that is a constituent of a nucleic acid.

label: paracardial fat
Defs: Fat deposits in the mediastinum outside the parietal pericardium .

label: positive regulation of dendritic spine morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of dendritic spine morphogenesis, the process in which the anatomical structures of a dendritic spine are generated and organized. A dendritic spine is a protrusion from a dendrite and a specialized subcellular compartment involved in synaptic transmission.

label: venule of anorectum
Defs: A venule that is located in the anorectum.

label: corneal epithelium
Defs: The smooth stratified squamous epithelium that covers the outer surface of the cornea.

label: aromaticity
Defs: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the presence of a conjugated ring of unsaturated bonds, lone pairs, or empty orbitals that exhibit a stabilization stronger than would be expected by the stabilization of conjugation alone.

label: obsolete u v light sensitivity value
negative regulation of cardiac muscle cell myoblast differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle cell myoblast differentiation.

label: protein localization to cytoplasmic microtubule
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a location within a cytoplasmic microtubule.

label: postnotum
Defs: The sclerite of the notum that is attached to the posterior margin of the scutellum.

label: negative regulation of immune effector process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of an immune effector process.

label: accessory nerve formation
Defs: The process that gives rise to the accessory nerve. This process pertains to the initial formation of a structure from unspecified parts. The spinal branch of this motor nerve innervates the trapezius and the sternocleidomastoid muscles. The cranial branch joins the vagus nerve and innervates the same targets as the vagus nerve.

label: placental epithelial cell
Defs: An epithelial cell of the placenta.

label: protein-containing complex binding
Defs: Binding to a macromolecular complex.

label: hematopoietic precursor cell
Defs: Any hematopoietic cell that is a precursor of some other hematopoietic cell type.

label: forebrain-midbrain boundary
Defs: An anatomical boundary that adjacent_to a forebrain and adjacent_to a midbrain.

label: regulation of sodium ion transmembrane transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of sodium ion transmembrane transport.

label: submucosa of cystic duct
Defs: A submucosa that is part of a cystic duct [Automatically generated definition].

label: lytic vacuole organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a lytic vacuole.

label: cardiac muscle myoblast proliferation
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of cardiac muscle myoblasts, resulting in the expansion of a cardiac muscle myoblast cell population.  A cardiac myoblast is a precursor cell that has been committed to a cardiac muscle cell fate but retains the ability to divide and proliferate throughout life.

label: negative regulation of type B pancreatic cell development
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of pancreatic B cell development.

label: decreased thickness
Defs: A thickness which is relatively low.

label: positive regulation of apoptotic process involved in outflow tract morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of apoptotic process involved in outflow tract morphogenesis.

label: regulation of insulin secretion
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of insulin.

label: negative regulation of dendritic cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of dendritic cell apoptotic process.

label: dwarf-like
Defs: A size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being abnormally small.

label: gland of foregut
Defs: A gland that is part of a foregut [Automatically generated definition].

label: epithelium of gall bladder
Defs: The simple columnar epithelial lining of the gall bladder.

label: regulation of microtubule depolymerization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of microtubule depolymerization.

label: vacuolar membrane
Defs: The lipid bilayer surrounding the vacuole and separating its contents from the cytoplasm of the cell.

label: normal viscosity
Defs: A viscosity which is relatively normal or average

label: lip
Defs: One of the two fleshy folds which surround the opening of the mouth.

label: cellular response to catecholamine stimulus
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a catecholamine stimulus. A catecholamine is any of a group of biogenic amines that includes 4-(2-aminoethyl)pyrocatechol [4-(2-aminoethyl)benzene-1,2-diol] and derivatives formed by substitution.

label: solid configuration
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s parts having the arrangement which exhibits characteristics of solids.

label: positive regulation of muscle hypertrophy
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of muscle hypertrophy.

label: nucleobase
Defs: That part of DNA or RNA that may be involved in pairing.

label: regulation of glial cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of glia cell differentiation.

label: rhombomere boundary formation
Defs: The process that gives rise to a rhombomere boundary. This process pertains to the initial formation of a boundary delimiting a rhombomere. Rhombomeres are transverse segments of the developing rhombencephalon that are lineage restricted, express different genes from one another, and adopt different developmental fates. Rhombomeres are numbered in anterior to posterior order.

label: compound eye morphogenesis
Defs: The morphogenetic process in which the anatomical structures of the compound eye are generated and organized. The adult compound eye is a precise assembly of 700-800 ommatidia. Each ommatidium is composed of 20 cells, identified by cell type and position. An example of compound eye morphogenesis is found in Drosophila melanogaster.

label: compound eye development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the compound eye over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The compound eye is an organ of sight that contains multiple repeating units, often arranged hexagonally. Each unit has its own lens and photoreceptor cell(s) and can generate either a single pixelated image or multiple images, per eye.

label: negative regulation of endothelial cell activation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of endothelial cell activation.

label: CD59-like glycoprotein
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human CD59 gene, a 1:1 ortholog thereof, or pro-orthologs thereof.

label: positive regulation of mesoderm development
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of mesoderm development.

label: posterior region
Defs: Anatomical region posteriorly located on the body or body part.

label: basophilic cytoplasm
Defs: Cytoplasm that exhibits molecular interaction for basic dyes under specific pH conditions.

label: response to serotonin
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a serotonin stimulus.

label: dorsal second axillary sclerite
Defs: The axillary sclerite that is on the dorsal region of the basal wing conjunctiva and lateral to the first axillary sclerite.

label: back
Defs: A directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s direction that is similar to the direction of an object to the north when it faces south.

label: skeletogenic cell
Defs: Cell that has the potential to form a skeletal cell type (e.g. cells in periosteum, cells in marrow) and produce extracellular matrix (often mineralized) and skeletal tissue (often mineralized).

label: CD34-positive, CD38-negative multipotent progenitor cell
Defs: A hematopoietic multipotent progenitor cell that is CD34-positive, CD38-negative, CD45RA-negative, and CD90-negative.

label: negative regulation of cardiac muscle cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle cell proliferation.

label: spade-shaped
Defs: A shape that is in the form of a spade.

label: chorionic mesenchyme
Defs: A mesenchyme that is part of a chorion.

label: regulation of osteoclast proliferation
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the multiplication or reproduction of osteoclasts, resulting in the expansion of an osteoclast cell population.

label: negative regulation of transferase activity
Defs: Any process that stops or reduces the rate of transferase activity, the catalysis of the transfer of a group, e.g. a methyl group, glycosyl group, acyl group, phosphorus-containing, or other groups, from a donor compound to an acceptor.

label: positive regulation of cardiac muscle cell myoblast differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle cell myoblast differentiation.

label: acid secretion
Defs: The controlled release of acid by a cell or a tissue.

label: smooth muscle cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in a smooth muscle cell. Smooth muscle consists of non-striated, elongated, spindle-shaped cell found lining the digestive tract, uterus, and blood vessels.

label: brown green
Defs: A color consisting of brown and green hues.

label: mesopleuro-mesosternal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the mesothorax that joins the mesopleura and the mesosternum.

label: data transformation
Defs: A planned process that produces output data from input data.

label: anti-inflammatory agent
Defs: Any compound that has anti-inflammatory effects.

label: cuticular depression
Defs: The region of the cuticle that corresponds to a concave surface.

label: neoplastic, spontaneous
Defs: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to spontaneously arise.

label: diencephalon development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the diencephalon over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The diencephalon is the paired caudal parts of the prosencephalon from which the thalamus, hypothalamus, epithalamus and subthalamus are derived; these regions regulate autonomic, visceral and endocrine function, and process information directed to the cerebral cortex.

label: sinus venosus formation
Defs: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of the sinus venosus from unspecified parts. The sinus venosus is a heart chamber attached to the atrium on the venous side of the embryonic heart.

label: brain dura mater
Defs: The fibrous membrane forming the outer of the three coverings that surrounds the brain within the cranial cavity; consists of two layers including the periosteal layer and the meningeal layer.

label: decreased humidity
Defs: An decrease in humidity.

label: conceptus
Defs: The embryo and its adnexa (appendages or adjunct parts) or associated membranes (i.e. the products of conception) The conceptus includes all structures that develop from the zygote, both embryonic and extraembryonic. It includes the embryo as well as the embryonic part of the placenta and its associated membranes - amnion, chorion (gestational sac), and yolk sac[WP].

label: pluripotent
Defs: A cellular potency that is the capacity to produce differentiated cell types of all three primary germ layers but not extraembryonic cell types.

label: amine binding
Defs: Binding to an amine, a weakly basic organic compound that contains an amino or a substituted amino group.

label: protein localization to plasma membrane
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a specific location in the plasma membrane.

label: chorionic trophoblast cell proliferation
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of chorionic trophoblast cells, resulting in the expansion of their population.

label: endothelial cell development
Defs: The progression of an endothelial cell over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: positive regulation of protein catabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a protein by the destruction of the native, active configuration, with or without the hydrolysis of peptide bonds.

label: normal permeability
Defs: A permeability which is relatively normal or average.

label: signaling
Defs: The entirety of a process in which information is transmitted within a biological system. This process begins with an active signal and ends when a cellular response has been triggered.

label: decreased variability of rate
Defs: A variability of rate which is relatively low.

label: monovalent inorganic anion homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of monovalent inorganic anions within an organism or cell.

label: mesenchyme of trachea
Defs: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing trachea.

label: negative regulation of monocyte chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate, or extent of monocyte chemotaxis.

label: glucagon secreting cell
Defs: A cell that secretes glucagon.

label: dry
Defs: A wetness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s not being covered by a liquid.

label: cell projection organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a prolongation or process extending from a cell, e.g. a flagellum or axon.

label: negative regulation of antigen processing and presentation of peptide or polysaccharide antigen via MHC class II
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of antigen processing and presentation of antigen (peptide or polysaccharide) via MHC class II.

label: regulation of ion transmembrane transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of ions from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: accelerated growth
Defs: A peramorphic growth quality which is due to an increased rate.

label: mesocoxal cavity
Defs: The concave part of the ventral region of the pterothorax that receives the mesocoxa.

label: corticothalamic projecting
Defs: A neuron projection quality that is a characteristic of neurons with soma in the cerebral cortex and projections to the thalamus.

label: unicuspidate
Defs: Cuspidate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s possessing a single cusp.

label: facial suture morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which any suture between facial bones is generated and organized.

label: columnar/cuboidal epithelial cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a columnar/cuboidal epithelial cell. A columnar/cuboidal epithelial cell is a cell usually found in a two dimensional sheet with a free surface. Columnar/cuboidal epithelial cells take on the shape of a column or cube.

label: cadherin
Defs: A protein that has a core domain structure of signal sequence, propeptide, five Cadherin domains (Pfam:PF00028), a transmembrane region, and a Cadherin cytoplasmic region (Pfam:PF01049). Cadherins function as adhesion molecules that mediate Ca2+-dependent cell-cell adhesion in solid tissues.

label: scute-like
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being shaped like a scute or an osteoderm.

label: common myeloid progenitor, CD34-positive
Defs: A progenitor cell committed to myeloid lineage, including the megakaryocyte and erythroid lineages. These cells are CD34-positive, and express Gata1, Gata2, C/EBPa, and Pu.1.

label: normal behavioural activity
Defs: A behavioural quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting normal or average activity.

label: pulmonary lobule
Defs: The smallest anatomical unit of the lung, measuring 0.50 to 2.00 cm in diameter. Each lobule is composed of 4-8 terminal bronchioles and their distal alveolar ducts and sacs. The lobules are separated by fibrous interlobular septa.

label: neural crest derived fat cell
Defs: A fat cell derived from a neural crest cell.

label: flat bone
Defs: A bone that is shaped as a broad flat plate and composed of two thin layers of compact tissue enclosing between them a variable quantity of cancellous tissue, which is the location of red bone marrow.

label: subcutaneous fat cell
Defs: A fat cell that is part of subcutaneous adipose tissue.

label: norepinephrine uptake
Defs: The directed movement of norepinephrine into a cell, typically presynaptic neurons or glial cells. Norepinephrine (3,4-dihydroxyphenyl-2-aminoethanol) is a hormone secreted by the adrenal medulla and a neurotransmitter in the sympathetic peripheral nervous system and in some tracts of the CNS. It is also the biosynthetic precursor of epinephrine.

label: positive regulation of blood vessel endothelial cell migration
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the migration of the endothelial cells of blood vessels.

label: lens vesicle epithelium
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a lens vesicle.

label: neural tube lateral wall
Defs: Portion of tissue on the side of the lumen of the neural tube.

label: oviduct epithelium
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a oviduct [Automatically generated definition].

label: phosphorylation
Defs: A quality inhering in a protein or a molecule by virtue of the addition of a phosphate (PO4) group to the bearer.

label: L-alpha-amino acid transmembrane transport
Defs: The directed movement of L-alpha-amino acid across a membrane.

label: skeletal tissue
Defs: A specialized form of connective tissue in which the extracellular matrix is firm, providing the tissue with resilience, and/or mineralized and that functions in mechanical and structural support.[VSAO].

label: broken
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s components no longer being in a single contiguous unit.

label: cellular polysaccharide biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of polysaccharides, polymers of many (typically more than 10) monosaccharide residues linked glycosidically, occurring at the level of an individual cell.

label: nucleobase metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving a nucleobase, a nitrogenous base that is a constituent of a nucleic acid, e.g. the purines: adenine, guanine, hypoxanthine, xanthine and the pyrimidines: cytosine, uracil, thymine.

label: inelastic
Defs: An elasticity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s inability to recover its size and shape after deformation in any way.

label: sphincter associated smooth muscle cell
Defs: A smooth muscle cell that is part of a sphincter. A sphincter is a typically circular muscle that normally maintains constriction of a natural body passage or orifice and which relaxes as required by normal physiological functioning.

label: exocrine system
Defs: Anatomical system that consists of the glands and parts of glands that produce exocrine secretions and help to integrate and control bodily metabolic activity. Exocrine glands are glands that secrete their products (hormones) into ducts (duct glands). They are the counterparts to endocrine glands, which secrete their products (hormones) directly into the bloodstream (ductless glands) or release hormones (paracrines) that affect only target cells nearby the release site. [Wikipedia].

label: negative regulation of response to stimulus
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of a response to a stimulus. Response to stimulus is a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus.

label: time unit
Defs: A unit which is a standard measure of the dimension in which events occur in sequence.

label: pectoral appendage bud mesenchyme
Defs: Mesenchyme that is part of a pectoral appendage bud.

label: exocytic process
Defs: The cellular processes that contribute to exocytosis.

label: scutum
Defs: The sclerite of the notum that is attached to the posterior margin of the prescutum and to the anterior margin of the scutellum.

label: positive regulation of cell cycle process
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of a cellular process that is involved in the progression of biochemical and morphological phases and events that occur in a cell during successive cell replication or nuclear replication events.

label: hematopoietic stem cell proliferation
Defs: The expansion of a hematopoietic stem cell population by cell division. A hematopoietic stem cell is a stem cell from which all cells of the lymphoid and myeloid lineages develop.

label: remittent intensity
Defs: An intensity which is characterized by temporary abatement in severity.

label: lipid localization
Defs: Any process in which a lipid is transported to, or maintained in, a specific location.

label: negative regulation of Golgi to plasma membrane protein transport
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the transport of proteins from the Golgi to the plasma membrane.

label: cavity of left ventricle
Defs: Luminal space of the left ventricle of the heart.

label: secretion of serous gland
Defs: Any fluid produced by a serous gland.

label: antero-dorsal region
Defs: Anatomical region that overlaps the anterior and dorsal regions of a body or body part.

label: negative regulation of defense response to bacterium
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of defense response to bacterium.

label: coiling
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being wound in a continuous series of loops.

label: preganglionic parasympathetic fiber development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a preganglionic parasympathetic fiber over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A preganglionic parasympathetic fiber is a cholinergic axonal fiber projecting from the CNS to a parasympathetic ganglion.

label: chemical homeostasis
Defs: Any biological process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of a chemical.

label: optic eminence ectoderm
Defs: An ectoderm that is part of a optic eminence [Automatically generated definition].

label: cellular biogenic amine biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways occurring at the level of individual cells resulting in the formation of any of a group of naturally occurring, biologically active amines, such as norepinephrine, histamine, and serotonin, many of which act as neurotransmitters.

label: having extra processual parts
Defs: A quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having additional processual parts.

label: negative regulation of cardiac chamber morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac chamber morphogenesis.

label: post-hyoid pharyngeal arch
Defs: A pharyngeal arch that is posterior to the hyoid arch. i.e. any pharyngeal arch with a number 3 or higher.

label: positive regulation of neurotransmitter secretion
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of a neurotransmitter.

label: vesicle targeting
Defs: The process in which vesicles are directed to specific destination membranes. Targeting involves coordinated interactions among cytoskeletal elements (microtubules or actin filaments), motor proteins, molecules at the vesicle membrane and target membrane surfaces, and vesicle cargo.

label: acinus of exocrine gland
Defs: An acinus that is part of a exocrine gland.

label: regulation of T cell homeostatic proliferation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of resting T cell proliferation.

label: regulation of neuron migration
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of neuron migration.

label: right lung bronchiole
Defs: A bronchiole that is part of a right lung [Automatically generated definition].

label: prophragma
Defs: The phragma of the mesonotum that attaches to muscles attached to the pronotum.

label: peptide
Defs: Amide derived from two or more amino carboxylic acid molecules (the same or different) by formation of a covalent bond from the carbonyl carbon of one to the nitrogen atom of another with formal loss of water. The term is usually applied to structures formed from alpha-amino acids, but it includes those derived from any amino carboxylic acid. X = OH, OR, NH2, NHR, etc.

label: pharyngeal vasculature
Defs: A vasculature that is part of a chordate pharynx.

label: regulation of multicellular organismal development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of multicellular organismal development.

label: nucleated reticulocyte
Defs: A reticulocyte that retains the nucleus and other organelles. Found in birds, fish, amphibians and reptiles.

label: motor neuron apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in a motor neuron, an efferent neuron that passes from the central nervous system or a ganglion toward or to a muscle and conducts an impulse that causes movement.

label: regulation of plasma membrane bounded cell projection organization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of plasma membrane bounded cell projections.

label: haemolymphatic fluid
Defs: Circulating fluid that is part of the hemolymphoid system. Blood, lymph, interstitial fluid or its analogs.

label: volume
Defs: A 3-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s amount of 3-dimensional space it occupies.

label: obsolete_report table
Defs: A report table is a report display element consisting of a matrix of cells layed out in a grid, some set of which are filled with some information content

label: positive regulation of hormone secretion
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of a hormone from a cell.

label: ontology module subsetted by OWL profile
lung ciliated cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a lung ciliated cell. A lung ciliated cell is a specialized lung epithelial cell that contains cilia for moving substances released from lung secretory cells.

label: mesenchyme
Defs: Portion of tissue composed of mesenchymal cells (motile cells that develop from epthelia via an epithelial to mesenchymal transition) and surrounding extracellular material. Mesenchyme has different embryological origins in different metazoan taxa - in many invertebrates it derives in whole or part from ectoderm. In vertebrates it derives largely from mesoderm, and sometimes the terms are used interchangeably, e.g. lateral plate mesoderm/mesenchyme.

label: malformed
Defs: A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being distorted during formation.

label: serotonin(1+)
Defs: An ammonium ion that is the conjugate acid of serotonin; major species at pH 7.3.

label: regulation of Schwann cell chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of Schwann cell chemotaxis.

label: negative regulation of cardiac muscle hypertrophy
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of the enlargement or overgrowth of all or part of the heart due to an increase in size (not length) of individual cardiac muscle fibers, without cell division.

label: cauline to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located toward the stalk of an organism relative to another entity.

label: regulation of neutrophil activation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of neutrophil activation.

label: mesocoxal muscle
Defs: The coxal muscle of the mesocoxa.

label: mono-colored
Defs: A color pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having one hue.

label: paired limb/fin bud mesenchyme
Defs: Mesenchyme that is part of a limb/fin bud.

label: micronutrient
Defs: Any nutrient required in small quantities by organisms throughout their life in order to orchestrate a range of physiological functions.

label: positive regulation of synaptic transmission, glutamatergic
Defs: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of glutamatergic synaptic transmission, the process of communication from a neuron to another neuron across a synapse using the neurotransmitter glutamate.

label: mesenteric vein
Defs: A vein that returns blood from the intestines.

label: cellular response to stimulus
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus. The process begins with detection of the stimulus by a cell and ends with a change in state or activity or the cell.

label: mesosterno-mesocoxal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the mesothorax that joins the mesosternum and the mesocoxa.

label: lobe of liver
Defs: Traditional gross anatomy divided the liver into four lobes based on surface features. The falciform ligament is visible on the front (anterior side) of the liver. This divides the liver into a left anatomical lobe, and a right anatomical lobe.

label: simple cuboidal epithelium
Defs: Unilaminar epithelium that consists of a single layer of cuboidal cells.

label: limaciform
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling a slug.

label: cardiac conduction system development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the cardiac conduction system over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The cardiac conduction system consists of specialized cardiomyocytes that regulate the frequency of heart beat.

label: ribonucleoprotein complex subunit organization
Defs: Any process in which macromolecules aggregate, disaggregate, or are modified, resulting in the formation, disassembly, or alteration of a ribonucleoprotein complex.

label: regulation of T cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the occurrence or rate of T cell death by apoptotic process.

label: funding source declaration section
Defs: A part of a document used to detail information regarding the source of funding used in support of the generation of the document content.

label: erythroid lineage cell
Defs: A immature or mature cell in the lineage leading to and including erythrocytes.

label: endothelium
