Defs: A layer of epithelium that lines the heart, blood vessels (endothelium, vascular), lymph vessels (endothelium, lymphatic), and the serous cavities of the body[MESH]. Simple squamous epithelium which lines blood and lymphatic vessels and the heart[FMA].

label: obsolete_establishing a CRID registry
Defs: a planned process with the objective to establish a system that allows to refer to specific entities of a certain kind and store information about them, by establishing a CRID registry and plan specifications for the process of 1) assigning a CRID and 2) looking up a CRID.

label: normal process quality
Defs: A quality of a process that has a value that is normal or average.

label: adventitia of esophagus
Defs: An adventitia that is part of a esophagus.

label: anal sphincter
Defs: A sphincter muscle that is part of a anal region.

label: left atrium endocardium
Defs: Endocardium that is part of the left atrium.

label: enkephalin secreting cell
Defs: An endorphine cell that secretes enkephalin.

label: delayed
Defs: A quality of a process which starts later than the natural start time or the reference process.

label: chorionic trophoblast cell
Defs: Cells of the uterine chorion that acquire specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize chorionic trophoblasts. These cells will migrate towards the spongiotrophoblast layer and give rise to syncytiotrophoblasts of the labyrinthine layer.

label: craniocervical region vein
Defs: A vein that is part of a craniocervical region.

label: basal coxal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that encircles the coxa and connects them to the ventral and lateral thoracic regions.

label: negative regulation of pseudopodium assembly
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the assembly of pseudopodia.

label: life span
Defs: A time quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s expected maximum age.

label: compound eye retinal cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in a compound eye retinal cell.

label: cuticle of maxillary palpomere I
Defs: The cuticle of the maxillary palpomere that is attached to the distal margin of the palpiger and to the proximal margin of the maxillary palpomere II.

label: negative regulation of cholangiocyte proliferation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cholangiocyte proliferation.

label: cell maturation
Defs: A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for a cell to attain its fully functional state.

label: negative regulation of postsynaptic membrane organization
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of postsynaptic membrane organization.

label: d-block molecular entity
Defs: A d-block molecular entity is a molecular entity containing one or more atoms of a d-block element.

label: developing mesenchymal structure
Defs: A mesenchyme-derived anatomical entity undergoing a transtion to become another structure.

label: vagus nerve morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structure of the vagus nerve is generated and organized. This nerve is primarily sensory but also has visceromotor components. It originates in the brain stem and controls many autonomic functions of the heart, lungs, stomach, pharynx, larynx, trachea, esophagus and other gastrointestinal tract components. It controls some motor functions such as speech. The sensory branches mediate sensation from the pharynx, larynx, thorax and abdomen; it also innervates taste buds in the epiglottis.

label: notochordal process
Defs: A midline cellular cord formed from the migration of mesenchymal cells from the primitive knot.

label: lens placode
Defs: A thickened portion of ectoderm which serves as the precursor to the lens. SOX2 and Pou2f1 are involved in its development[WP].

label: serosa of stomach
Defs: The outermost layer of the stomach wall, consisting of layers of connective tissue continuous with the peritoneum.

label: regulation of muscle organ development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of muscle development.

label: positive regulation of macrophage activation
Defs: Any process that stimulates, induces or increases the rate of macrophage activation.

label: prothoracic-mesothoracic conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect thorax joining the prothorax and the mesothorax.

label: phosphate-containing compound metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving the phosphate group, the anion or salt of any phosphoric acid.

label: macroglial cell
Defs: A neuroglial cell of ectodermal origin, i.e., the astrocytes and oligodendrocytes considered together.

label: meiotic cell cycle
Defs: Progression through the phases of the meiotic cell cycle, in which canonically a cell replicates to produce four offspring with half the chromosomal content of the progenitor cell via two nuclear divisions.

label: high brightness
Defs: A color brightness which is relatively high.

label: lumen of digestive tract
Defs: An anatomical space that surrounded_by a digestive tract.

label: neural tissue
Defs: Portion of tissue in the nervous system which consists of neurons and glial cells, and may also contain parts of the vasculature.

label: detection of external stimulus
Defs: The series of events in which an external stimulus is received by a cell and converted into a molecular signal.

label: alternate placement
Defs: A pattern quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being placed alternately one above the other.

label: gray matter of telencephalon
Defs: A portion of gray matter that is part of a telencephalon.

label: glutamate catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of glutamate, the anion of 2-aminopentanedioic acid.

label: white matter of myelencephalon
Defs: A white matter that is part of the myelencephalon.

label: recurved
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved backward or inward.

label: positive regulation of cell morphogenesis involved in differentiation
Defs: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of cell morphogenesis contributing to cell differentiation. Cell morphogenesis involved in differentiation is the change in form (cell shape and size) that occurs when relatively unspecialized cells acquire specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize the cells, tissues, or organs of the mature organism or some other relatively stable phase of the organism\'s life history.

label: smooth muscle cell of the pulmonary artery
Defs: A smooth muscle of the pulmonary artery.

label: cardinal direction
Defs: The four cardinal directions or cardinal points are the directions north, east, south, and west, commonly denoted by their initials, N, E, S, W. East and west are at right angles to north and south, with east being in the clockwise direction of rotation from north and west being directly opposite east.

label: positive regulation of motor neuron migration
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of motor neuron migration.

label: myeloid leukocyte cytokine production
Defs: Any process that contributes to cytokine production by a myeloid cell.

label: proerythroblast
Defs: An immature, nucleated erythrocyte occupying the stage of erythropoeisis that follows formation of erythroid progenitor cells. This cell is CD71-positive, has both a nucleus and a nucleolus, and lacks hematopoeitic lineage markers.

label: gray matter of spinal cord
Defs: The ridge-shaped grey matter of the spinal cord that extends longitudunally through the center of each half of the spinal cord, and are largely or entirely composed of nerve cell bodies and their dendrites and some supportive tissue.

label: bronchial vein
Defs: The bronchial veins are small vessels that return blood from the larger bronchi and structures at the roots of the lungs. The right side drains into the azygos vein, while the left side drains into the left superior intercostal vein or the accessory hemiazygos vein. The bronchial veins are counterparts to the bronchial arteries. The veins, however, do not return all of the blood supplied by the arteries; much of the blood that is carried in the bronchial arteries is returned to the heart via the pulmonary veins. [WP,unvetted].

label: response to lipid
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a lipid stimulus.

label: obsolete radiation absorbed dose
Defs: OBSOLETE A radiation exposure quality inhering in a substance by virtue of the radiation energy "deposited" in a kilogram of a substance.

label: x-shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being shaped in the form of the letter X.

label: primary amino compound
Defs: A compound formally derived from ammonia by replacing one hydrogen atom by an organyl group.

label: migratory cranial neural crest cell
Defs: Cell that is part of the migratory cranial neural crest population. Migratory cranial neural crest cells develop from premigratory cranial neural crest cells and have undergone epithelial to mesenchymal transition and delamination.

label: protein kinase regulator activity
Defs: Modulates the activity of a protein kinase, an enzyme which phosphorylates a protein.

label: mesenchyme of ovary
Defs: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing ovary [Automatically generated definition].

label: anterior cervico-occipital muscle
Defs: The dorsoventral thoracic muscle of the prothorax that is attached to the anterior margin of a cervical sclerite and the dorso-lateral region of the postocciput.

label: parasympathetic nervous system development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the parasympathetic nervous system over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The parasympathetic nervous system is one of the two divisions of the vertebrate autonomic nervous system. Parasympathetic nerves emerge cranially as pre ganglionic fibers from oculomotor, facial, glossopharyngeal and vagus and from the sacral region of the spinal cord. Most neurons are cholinergic and responses are mediated by muscarinic receptors. The parasympathetic system innervates, for example: salivary glands, thoracic and abdominal viscera, bladder and genitalia.

label: cleft
Defs: A concave quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resembling a groove or fissure.

label: trachea morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which a trachea is generated and organized. The trachea is the portion of the airway that attaches to the bronchi as it branches.

label: placental labyrinth vasculature
Defs: Blood vessels of the layer of the placenta where embryonic and maternal blood vessels interdigitate.

label: midbrain-hindbrain boundary maturation
Defs: A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for the midbrain-hindbrain boundary to attain its fully functional state. The midbrain-hindbrain domain of the embryonic brain is comprised of the mesencephalic vesicle and the first rhombencephalic vesicle at early somitogenesis stages. An organizing center at the boundary patterns the midbrain and hindbrain primordia of the neural plate.

label: vascular associated smooth muscle cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a vascular smooth muscle cell.

label: common myeloid progenitor
Defs: A progenitor cell committed to myeloid lineage, including the megakaryocyte and erythroid lineages.

label: distensibility
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the extent to which the bearer is capable of being stretched or swollen.

label: positive regulation of stem cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of stem cell differentiation.

label: cuticular exocrine gland duct
Defs: The branching cuticular invagination that corresponds to the invagination of the membrane of a single cell and does not contain taenidia.

label: positive regulation of Schwann cell chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of Schwann cell chemotaxis.

label: production of molecular mediator involved in inflammatory response
Defs: The synthesis or release of any molecular mediator of the inflammatory response following an inflammatory stimulus, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label: portal lobule
Defs: The triangular region on the periphery of the liver lobules that contain a bile duct and a terminal branch of the hepatic artery and portal vein, and may also include a lymphatic vessel.

label: germ cell nucleus
Defs: The nucleus of a germ cell, a reproductive cell in multicellular organisms.

label: positive regulation of dopamine metabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving dopamine.

label: cuticle of labium
Defs: The cuticle of the mouthpart appendage composed of the cuticle of submentum, which is attached by the submental-mental conjunctiva to the cuticle of mentum, which is attached by the mental-premental conjunctiva to the cuticle of prementum, which is attached to the cuticle of palpiger by the premental-palpigeral conjunctiva, the cuticle of paraglossa by the premental-paraglossal conjunctiva, and the cuticle of glossa by the premental-glossal conjunctiva; the cuticle of palpiger is attached by the palpigero-palpal conjunctiva to the cuticle of labial palpus.

label: cell morphogenesis involved in differentiation
Defs: The change in form (cell shape and size) that occurs when relatively unspecialized cells, e.g. embryonic or regenerative cells, acquire specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize the cells, tissues, or organs of the mature organism or some other relatively stable phase of the organism\'s life history.

label: Golgi-associated vesicle membrane
Defs: The lipid bilayer surrounding a vesicle associated with the Golgi apparatus.

label: hindbrain development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the hindbrain over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The hindbrain is the posterior of the three primary divisions of the developing chordate brain, or the corresponding part of the adult brain (in vertebrates, includes the cerebellum, pons, and medulla oblongata and controls the autonomic functions and equilibrium).

label: synovial cell
Defs: A cell located in the synovial joint.

label: J-shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being shaped in the form of the letter J.

label: negative regulation of mitotic nuclear envelope disassembly
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of mitotic nuclear envelope disassembly.

label: tracheal mucosa
Defs: A mucosa that is part of a respiratory airway.

label: condensed
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being thicker or more closely packed together; pressed tightly together.

label: integrin alpha-M
Defs: An integrin alpha with A domain that is a translation product of the human ITGAM gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. They constitute subunits of the integrin alpha-M/beta-2 receptor. This receptor is implicated in various adhesive interactions of monocytes, macrophages and granulocytes as well as in mediating the uptake of complement-coated particles. It is also a receptor for fibrinogen, factor X and ICAM1.

label: light grey
Defs: A color consisting of grey color and high brightness.

label: positive regulation of cardiac myofibril assembly
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac myofibril assembly.

label: fibroblast of the aortic adventitia
Defs: A fibroblast of the aortic adventitia.

label: modulation of microtubule cytoskeleton involved in cerebral cortex radial glia guided migration
Defs: Rearrangements of the microtubule cytoskeleton that contribute to the movement of cells along radial glial cells as a component of the process of cerebral cortex glial-mediated radial migration.

label: pancreatic PP cell
Defs: A PP cell located in the islets of the pancreas.

label: positive regulation of cellular amino acid biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cellular amino acid biosynthetic process.

label: macronutrient
Defs: Any nutrient required in large quantities by organisms throughout their life in order to orchestrate a range of physiological functions. Macronutrients are usually chemical elements (carbon, hydrogen, nitrogen, oxygen, phosphorus and sulfur) that humans consume in the largest quantities. Calcium, sodium, magnesium and potassium are sometimes included as macronutrients because they are required in relatively large quantities compared with other vitamins and minerals.

label: antero-posteriorly flattened
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being flattened along the antero-posterior axis.

label: action specification
Defs: A directive information entity that describes an action the bearer will take.

label: negative regulation of cellular amine catabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways leading to the breakdown of amines.

label: basisternum
Defs: The part of the sternum that is attached to the posterior margin of the presternum and to the anterior margin of the furcasternum.

label: dilatator pupillae
Defs: A smooth muscle of the eye, running radially in the iris that functions as a dilator. [WP,unvetted].

label: negative regulation of embryonic camera-type eye development
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of embryonic camera-type eye development.

label: regulation of locomotion
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of locomotion of a cell or organism.

label: neutrophilic promyelocyte
Defs: A promyelocyte committed to the neutrophil lineage. This cell type is GATA-1-positive, C/EBPa-positive, AML-1-positive, MPO-positive, has low expression of PU.1 transcription factor and lacks lactotransferrin expression.

label: saddle-shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s similarity to the appearance of a saddle.

label: post-embryonic stage
Defs: Stage succeeding embryo, including mature structure.

label: future directions section
Defs: A part of a document detailing extensions of the described work that may be implemented at some future point in time.

label: feces
Defs: Portion of semisolid bodily waste discharged through the anus[MW,modified].

label: carbohydrate derivative transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of carbohydrate derivative from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: secondary metabolite biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of secondary metabolites, the compounds that are not necessarily required for growth and maintenance of cells, and are often unique to a taxon.

label: cardiac glial cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized features of a glial cell of the heart.

label: sufficient
Defs: A wholeness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s has enough functionality.

label: regulation of synapse pruning
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of synapse pruning.

label: regulation of endothelial cell migration
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the orderly movement of an endothelial cell into the extracellular matrix to form an endothelium.

label: RNA biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of RNA, ribonucleic acid, one of the two main type of nucleic acid, consisting of a long, unbranched macromolecule formed from ribonucleotides joined in 3\',5\'-phosphodiester linkage. Includes polymerization of ribonucleotide monomers. Refers not only to transcription but also to e.g. viral RNA replication.

label: sensory perception of light stimulus
Defs: The series of events required for an organism to receive a sensory light stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. This is a neurological process.

label: sacral neural crest
Defs: One of the 5 distinct and partially overlapping functional domains of the premigratory neural crest. The vagal and sacral neural crest cells develop into the ganglia of the enteric nervous system, also known as the parasympathetic ganglia.

label: organic acid transmembrane transport
Defs: The process in which an organic acid is transported across a membrane.

label: regulation of heart morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of heart morphogenesis.

label: ammonium ion binding
Defs: Binding to ammonium ions (NH4+).

label: monocyte differentiation antigen CD14 (mouse)
Defs: A CD14 molecule that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: negative regulation of chondrocyte development
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the process whose specific outcome is the progression of a chondrocyte over time, from its commitment to its mature state. Chondrocyte development does not include the steps involved in committing a chondroblast to a chondrocyte fate.

label: receptor-type tyrosine-protein kinase FLT3 (mouse)
Defs: A receptor-type tyrosine-protein kinase FLT3 that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: myeloid leukocyte differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized myeloid precursor cell acquires the specialized features of any cell of the myeloid leukocyte lineage.

label: monandrous
Defs: A phenotypic sex quality inhering in a  plant organism or a population of plants in which the flowers have only one stamen.

label: gustatory papilla of tongue
Defs: A papilla that contain taste buds, including the fungiform, foliate, and circumvallate papillae.

label: ventricular septum morphogenesis
Defs: The developmental process in which a ventricular septum is generated and organized. A ventricular septum is an anatomical structure that separates the lower chambers (ventricles) of the heart from one another.

label: normal flexibility
Defs: A flexibility which is relatively normal or average.

label: positive regulation of glial cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of glial cell apoptotic process.

label: ossification
Defs: The formation of bone or of a bony substance, or the conversion of fibrous tissue or of cartilage into bone or a bony substance.

label: negative regulation of endothelial cell development
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of endothelial cell development.

label: hermaphrodite
Defs: A biological sex quality inhering in an organism or a population with both male and female sexual organs in one individual.

label: anterior-posterior polarity
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s location of features or characteristics along the anterior-posterior axis.

label: midbrain dura mater
Defs: A dura mater that is part of a midbrain [Automatically generated definition].

label: absorption quality
Defs: A scalar EM radiation quality which obtains by the capacity of the bearer to retain radiation.

label: negative regulation of dopamine secretion
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of dopamine.

label: regulation of intestinal epithelial cell development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of intestinal epithelial cell development.

label: median lingual swelling
Defs: During the third week of embryological development there appears, immediately behind the ventral ends of the two halves of the mandibular arch, a rounded swelling named the tuberculum impar, which was described by His as undergoing enlargement to form the buccal part of the tongue. More recent researches, however, show that this part of the tongue is mainly, if not entirely, developed from a pair of lateral swellings which rise from the inner surface of the mandibular arch and meet in the middle line. The site of their meeting remains post-embryonically as the median sulcus of the tongue. The tuberculum impar is said to form the central part of the tongue immediately in front of the foramen cecum, but Hammar insists that it is purely a transitory structure and forms no part of the adult tongue[WP, Gray\'s].

label: shaded
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of that bearer being shielded from visible light.

label: keratinocyte activation
Defs: A change in the morphology or behavior of a keratinocyte resulting from exposure to an activating factor such as a cellular or soluble ligand. Upon activation, keratinocytes become migratory and hyperproliferative, and produce growth factors and cytokines.

label: aralkylamino compound
Defs: An organic amino compound in which an aminoalkyl group is linked to an arene.

label: lacking processual parts
Defs: A quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking a processual part as specified by the additional entity.

label: ventricular cardiac muscle tissue development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of ventricular cardiac muscle over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: force
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s rate of change of momentum.

label: Purkinje myocyte action potential
Defs: An action potential that occurs in a Purkinje myocyte.

label: uterine wall growth
Defs: The regrowth of the endometrium and blood vessels in the uterus following menstruation, resulting from a rise in progesterone levels.

label: stomach squamous epithelium
Defs: A squamous epithelium that is part of a stomach.

label: leukocyte cell-cell adhesion
Defs: The attachment of a leukocyte to another cell via adhesion molecules.

label: basal fold
Defs: The insect wing fold that is distal to the axillary region.

label: cranial nerve development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the cranial nerves over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The cranial nerves are composed of twelve pairs of nerves that emanate from the nervous tissue of the hindbrain. These nerves are sensory, motor, or mixed in nature, and provide the motor and general sensory innervation of the head, neck and viscera. They mediate vision, hearing, olfaction and taste and carry the parasympathetic innervation of the autonomic ganglia that control visceral functions.

label: biliary ductule
Defs: One of the fine terminal elements of the bile duct system, leaving the portal canal, and pursuing a course at the periphery of a lobule of the liver[BTO]. the excretory ducts of the liver that connect the interlobular ductules to the right or left hepatic duct[MP].

label: metafemoro-metatibial conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that encircles the metatibia by joining the distal margin of the metafemur and the proximal margin of the metatibia.

label: tissue homeostasis
Defs: A homeostatic process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state within a defined tissue of an organism, including control of cellular proliferation and death and control of metabolic function.

label: positive regulation of cellular component organization
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cell structures, including the plasma membrane and any external encapsulating structures such as the cell wall and cell envelope.

label: right ventricle myocardium
Defs: A myocardium that is part of a right ventricle of a heart.

label: negative regulation of iron ion transport
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of iron ions into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: signal release
Defs: The process in which a signal is secreted or discharged into the extracellular medium from a cellular source.

label: regulation of lipid catabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of lipids.

label: sex differentiation
Defs: The establishment of the sex of an organism by physical differentiation.

label: negative regulation of oligodendrocyte progenitor proliferation
Defs: Any process that stops or decreases the rate or extent of oligodendrocyte progenitor proliferation.

label: mesoventrite
Defs: The sclerite on the ventral region of the mesothorax, limited by the pleurosternal sulci and medial to the mesanepisternum and mesepimeron.

label: increased photosensitivity
Defs: A photosensitivity which is relatively high.

label: document part
Defs: An information content entity that is part of a document.

label: thoracic skeleton
Defs: Subdivision of skeletal system that consists of all skeletal elements in the thoracic region of the trunk. In most vertebrates this is the rib cage and sternum.

label: adult skeletal muscle myoblast
Defs: A skeletal muscle myoblast that is part of a skeletal mucle.  These cells are formed following acivation and division of skeletal muscle satellite cells. They form a transient population that is lost when they fuse to form skeletal muscle fibers.

label: decreased male fertility
Defs: A male fertility which is relatively low.

label: nutrient
Defs: A nutrient is a food component that an organism uses to survive and grow.

label: metabolite
Defs: Any intermediate or product resulting from metabolism. The term \'metabolite\' subsumes the classes commonly known as primary and secondary metabolites.

label: regulation of establishment of T cell polarity
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of establishment of T cell polarity.

label: apoptotic chromosome condensation
Defs: The compaction of chromatin during apoptosis.

label: perforate
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a hole or holes, especially a row or array of small holes.

label: cholinergic drug
Defs: Any drug used for its actions on cholinergic systems. Included here are agonists and antagonists, drugs that affect the life cycle of acetylcholine, and drugs that affect the survival of cholinergic neurons.

label: triploid
Defs: A polyploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing three homologous sets of chromosomes.

label: neural crest cell migration involved in sympathetic nervous system development
Defs: Any neural crest cell migration that is involved in sympathetic nervous system development.

label: basalare
Defs: The epipleurite that is adjacent to the anepisternum, is attached to the pleuron via muscle, is surrounded by the noto-pleural conjunctiva, and is anterior to the first axillary sclerite.

label: star shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being arranged like rays or radii; radiating from a common center.

label: cell communication involved in cardiac conduction
Defs: Any process that mediates interactions between a cell and its surroundings that contributes to the process of cardiac conduction. Encompasses interactions such as signaling or attachment between one cell and another cell, between a cell and an extracellular matrix, or between a cell and any other aspect of its environment.

label: primary lysosome
Defs: A lysosome before it has fused with a vesicle or vacuole.

label: positive regulation of protein localization to presynapse
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to presynapse.

label: endothelium development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an endothelium over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Endothelium refers to the layer of cells lining blood vessels, lymphatics, the heart, and serous cavities, and is derived from bone marrow or mesoderm. Corneal endothelium is a special case, derived from neural crest cells.

label: cranio-cardinal muscle
Defs: The insect cranio-maxillar muscle that is attached to the gena and the cardo.

label: protruding out of
Defs: A quality inhering into a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s extending out above or beyond its surface or boundary and outwards in relation to the physical space occupied by another entity.

label: negative regulation of hepatocyte apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of hepatocyte apoptotic process.

label: muscle layer of cloaca
Defs: A muscular coat that is part of a cloaca.

label: smooth muscle adaptation
Defs: Any process in which smooth muscle adapts, with consequent modifications to structural and/or functional phenotypes, in response to a stimulus. Stimuli include contractile activity, loading conditions, substrate supply, and environmental factors. These adaptive events occur in both muscle fibers and associated structures (motoneurons and capillaries), and they involve alterations in regulatory mechanisms, contractile properties and metabolic capacities.

label: T cell secretory granule organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a secretory granule in a T cell. A secretory granule is a small subcellular vesicle, surrounded by a membrane, that is formed from the Golgi apparatus and contains a highly concentrated protein destined for secretion.

label: negative regulation of lymphocyte apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of lymphocyte death by apoptotic process.

label: ribosome assembly
Defs: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of the mature ribosome and of its subunits.

label: secondary
Defs: A quality in which the effect or outcome is not primary or the focus of the observation.

label: epiblast (generic)
Defs: In amniote animal embryology, the epiblast is a tissue type derived either from the inner cell mass in mammals or the blastodisc in birds and reptiles. It lies above the hypoblast. In mammalian embryogenesis, the columnar cells of the epiblast are adjacent to the trophoblast, while the cuboidal cells of the hypoblast are closer to the blastocoele. The epiblast, whilst referred to as the primary ectoderm, differentiates to form all three layers of the trilaminar germ disc in a process called gastrulation[WP]. The outer of the two layers of the blastoderm that form during gastrulation, corresponding to primitive ectoderm during gastrulation and to the definitive ectoderm after gastrulation[ZFA].

label: intestinal epithelial cell migration
Defs: The orderly movement of an intestinal epithelial cell from one site to another, often during the development of a multicellular organism.

label: postsynaptic membrane organization
Defs: A process which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a postsynaptic membrane, the specialized area of membrane facing the presynaptic membrane on the tip of the nerve ending and separated from it by a minute cleft (the synaptic cleft).

label: positive regulation of establishment of protein localization
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of establishment of protein localization.

label: tergo-pleural muscle
Defs: The insect thoracic muscle that extends between the notum (or tergum) and the pleura.

label: nuclear steroid receptor activity
Defs: Combining with a steroid hormone and transmitting the signal within the cell to initiate a change in cell activity or function.

label: mucosa of gastroduodenal junction
Defs: A mucosa that is part of a gastroduodenal junction.

label: ribosome binding
Defs: Binding to a ribosome.

label: divalent inorganic anion homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of divalent inorganic anions within an organism or cell.

label: dense
Defs: A physical quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting density.

label: tunica adventitia of vein
Defs: A tunica adventitia that is part of a vein.

label: positive regulation of leukocyte mediated immunity
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of leukocyte mediated immunity.

label: neural plate formation
Defs: The formation of the flat, thickened layer of ectodermal cells known as the neural plate. The underlying dorsal mesoderm signals the ectodermal cells above it to elongate into columnar neural plate cells. The neural plate subsequently develops into the neural tube, which gives rise to the central nervous system.

label: yolk sac endoderm
Defs: The portion of the yolk sac that is derived from endoderm and lines the yolk sac.

label: metal ion binding
Defs: Binding to a metal ion.

label: datum label
Defs: A label is a symbol that is part of some other datum and is used to either partially define  the denotation of that datum or to provide a means for identifying the datum as a member of the set of data with the same label

label: steroid catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of steroids, compounds with a 1,2,cyclopentanoperhydrophenanthrene nucleus.

label: intramembranous bone tissue
Defs: Bone tissue that forms directly within mesenchyme, and does not replace other tissues[TAO]. Intramembranous ossification is the formation of bone in which osteoblasts secrete a collagen-proteoglycan matrix that binds calcium salts and becomes calcified[GO]. Intramembranous ossification is the way flat bones and the shell of a turtle are formed[GO]. Unlike endochondral ossification, cartilage is not present during intramembranous ossification[WP].

label: nuclear membrane biogenesis
Defs: The process in which a nuclear membrane is synthesized, aggregates, and bonds together.

label: merocrine gland
Defs: An exocrine gland whose secretions are excreted via exocytosis from secretory cells into an epithelial-walled duct or ducts and thence onto a bodily surface or into the lumen; the gland releases its product and no part of the gland is lost or damaged.

label: immune system
Defs: Anatomical system that protects the body from foreign substances, cells, and tissues by producing the immune response and that includes especially the thymus, spleen, lymphoid tissue, lymphocytes including the B cells and T cells, and antibodies.

label: biological sex
Defs: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to undergo sexual reproduction in order to differentiate the individuals or types involved.

label: regulation of nitrogen compound metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving nitrogen or nitrogenous compounds.

label: positive regulation of fat cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the rate or extent of fat cell proliferation.

label: cellular response to organonitrogen compound
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an organonitrogen stimulus. An organonitrogen compound is formally a compound containing at least one carbon-nitrogen bond.

label: regulation of bile acid metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of bile acid metabolic process.

label: cellular component organization or biogenesis
Defs: A process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a cellular component.

label: chorionic villus
Defs: One of the minute vascular projections of the fetal chorion that combines with maternal uterine tissue to form the placenta.

label: negative regulation of cardiocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cardiocyte differentiation.

label: abdominal tergite IX-gonocoxa IX conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the postabdomen that connects the abdominal tergite IX and the gonocoxa IX.

label: cuticle of profemur
Defs: The cuticle of the segment of a fore leg attached to the distal margin of the protrochanter by the protrochantero-profemoral conjunctiva and to the proximal margin of the protibia by the profemoro-protibial conjunctiva.

label: peptide secretion
Defs: The controlled release of a peptide from a cell or a tissue.

label: lens epithelial cell
Defs: A cell of the cuboidal epithelium that covers the lens. The cells of the lens epithelium regulate most of the homeostatic functions of the lens. As ions, nutrients, and liquid enter the lens from the aqueous humor, Na+/K+ ATPase pumps in the lens epithelial cells pump ions out of the lens to maintain appropriate lens osmolarity and volume, with equatorially positioned lens epithelium cells contributing most to this current. The activity of the Na+/K+ ATPases keeps water and current flowing through the lens from the poles and exiting through the equatorial regions. The cells of the lens epithelium also serve as the progenitors for new lens fibers. It constantly lays down fibers in the embryo, fetus, infant, and adult, and continues to lay down fibers for lifelong growth.

label: split
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being divided or broken up into parts or divisions.

label: digestive system duct
Defs: A duct that is part of a digestive system [Automatically generated definition].

label: body fluid secretion
Defs: The controlled release of a fluid by a cell or tissue in an animal.

label: nuclear protein-containing complex
Defs: A stable assembly of two or more macromolecules, i.e. proteins, nucleic acids, carbohydrates or lipids, in which at least one component is a protein and the constituent parts function together in the nucleus.

label: positive regulation of pancreatic A cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of pancreatic A cell differentiation.

label: synaptic transmission, glutamatergic
Defs: The vesicular release of glutamate from a presynapse, across a chemical synapse, the subsequent activation of glutamate receptors at the postsynapse of a target cell (neuron, muscle, or secretory cell) and the effects of this activation on the postsynaptic membrane potential and ionic composition of the postsynaptic cytosol. This process encompasses both spontaneous and evoked release of neurotransmitter and all parts of synaptic vesicle exocytosis. Evoked transmission starts with the arrival of an action potential at the presynapse.

label: reproductive process
Defs: A biological process that directly contributes to the process of producing new individuals by one or two organisms. The new individuals inherit some proportion of their genetic material from the parent or parents.

label: negative regulation of amine transport
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of amines into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: lumen of midgut
Defs: An anatomical cavity that surrounded_by a midgut.

label: postero-ventral region
Defs: Anatomical region that overlaps the posterior and ventral regions of a body or body part.

label: diencephalic nucleus
Defs: A nucleus of brain that is part of a diencephalon.

label: migratory
Defs: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s morphological and physiological adaptation for participating in long-distance movement of conspecifics, usually on a seasonal basis.

label: negative regulation of tube lumen cavitation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of tube lumen cavitation.

label: splayed rostral
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved outwards the front of an organism.

label: whorled
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being in opposition round a common axis.

label: microtubule polymerization based protein transport
Defs: The transport of a protein driven by polymerization of a microtubule to which it is attached.

label: anterior tentorial arm
Defs: Is the apophysis of the tentorium that is connected to an anterior tentorial pit.

label: layer of synovial tissue
Defs: A thin, loose vascular connective tissue that makes up the membranes surrounding joints and the sheaths protecting tendons (particularly flexor tendons in the hands and feet) where they pass over bony prominences. Synovial tissue contains synovial cells, which secrete a viscous liquid called synovial fluid; this liquid contains protein and hyaluronic acid and serves as a lubricant and nutrient for the joint cartilage surfaces[BTO]. Synovial tissue can be found in tendons (tissues that connect muscle to bone), bursae (fluid-filled, cushioning sacs found in spaces between tendons, ligaments, and bones), and the cavity (hollow enclosed area) that separates the bones of a freely movable joint, such as the knee or elbow[BTO].

label: porosity
Defs: A structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to admit the passage of gas or liquid through pores or interstices.

label: circulatory system process
Defs: A organ system process carried out by any of the organs or tissues of the circulatory system. The circulatory system is an organ system that moves extracellular fluids to and from tissue within a multicellular organism.

label: T cell activation
Defs: The change in morphology and behavior of a mature or immature T cell resulting from exposure to a mitogen, cytokine, chemokine, cellular ligand, or an antigen for which it is specific.

label: variability of shape
Defs: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits shape variation or change.

label: meso-epithelium
Defs: Epithelium that derives from the mesoderm. [Automatically generated definition].

label: positive regulation of tetrapyrrole catabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of tetrapyrrole catabolic process.

label: endometrium epithelium
Defs: An epithelium that is part of an endometrium [Automatically generated definition].

label: multi-ciliated epithelial cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized features of a multi-ciliated epithelial cell.

label: single layer subset ontology module
Defs: A subset ontology that is largely comprised of a single layer or strata in an ontology class hierarchy. The purpose is typically for rolling up for visualization. The classes in the layer need not be disjoint.

label: bile acid transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of bile acid from one side of a membrane to the other. Bile acids are any of a group of steroid carboxylic acids occurring in bile, where they are present as the sodium salts of their amides with glycine or taurine.

label: gliogenesis
Defs: The process that results in the generation of glial cells. This includes the production of glial progenitors and their differentiation into mature glia.

label: positive regulation of protein metabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving a protein.

label: organic cyclic compound binding
Defs: Binding to an organic cyclic compound, any molecular entity that contains carbon arranged in a cyclic molecular structure.

label: left cardiac atrium
Defs: A cardiac atrium that is in the left side of the heart. It receives oxygenated blood from the pulmonary veins, In mammals this is pumped into the left ventricle, via the Mitral valve.

label: spoon-shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being shaped in the form of a spoon.

label: pigment granule organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a pigment granule.

label: pulmonary capillary
Defs: A capillary that is part of a lung.

label: CD115-positive monocyte
Defs: CD115-positive monocyte is a monocyte that is CD115-positive and CD11b-positive.

label: regulation of establishment of protein localization to chromosome
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of a protein to a specific location on a chromosome.

label: cardiovascular system endothelium
Defs: An endothelium that is part of the cardiovascular system.

label: sharpness
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a sharp or tapered end or point.

label: regulation of monocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of monocyte differentiation.

label: CD19 molecule
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human CD19 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. It is composed of an N-terminal extracellular domain containing two Ig-like C2-type (immunoglobulin-like) domains, followed by a single-pass transmembrane segment and a cytoplasmic C-terminal tail. CD19 expression is restricted to members of the B cell lineage. It functions as a co-receptor for B-cell antigen receptor (BCR), regulating signal transduction.

label: megakaryocyte
Defs: A giant cell 50 to 100 micron in diameter, with a greatly lobulated nucleus, found in the bone marrow; mature blood platelets are released from its cytoplasm.

label: oxidising agent
Defs: A substance that removes electrons from another reactant in a redox reaction.

label: onset quality
Defs: The temporal relation between the start of the process with respect to a reference process.

label: regulation of fibroblast apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of fibroblast apoptotic process.

label: spleen development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the spleen over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The spleen is a large vascular lymphatic organ composed of white and red pulp, involved both in hemopoietic and immune system functions.

label: branching involved in labyrinthine layer morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the branches of the fetal placental villi are generated and organized. The villous part of the placenta is called the labyrinth layer.

label: articulated with
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s participating in a joint with another entity.

label: regulation of glycogen biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of glycogen.

label: embryonic camera-type eye development
Defs: The process occurring during the embryonic phase whose specific outcome is the progression of the eye over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: odorless
Defs: An odor quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking odour.

label: morphogenesis of embryonic epithelium
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of embryonic epithelia are generated and organized.

label: mesothelium of serous pericardium
Defs: A mesothelium that is part of a serous pericardium.

label: cellularity
Defs: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s consisting cells.

label: pharyngeal arch artery morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of a pharyngeal arch artery is generated and organized. The pharyngeal arch arteries are a series of six paired embryological vascular structures, the development of which give rise to several major arteries, such as the stapedial artery, the middle meningeal artery, the internal carotid artery and the pulmonary artery.

label: cuticle of insect leg
Defs: The cuticle of the paired appendage of the insect thorax that is composed of coxa, trochanter, femur, tibia, tarsus, and pretarsus.

label: tergo-tergal muscle
Defs: The insect thoracic muscle that extends between two nota (or terga).

label: lactotransferrin
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human LTF gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: mast/stem cell growth factor receptor Kit (mouse)
Defs: A mast/stem cell growth factor receptor that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: rhombencephalon neural crest
Defs: A neural crest that has_potential_to_developmentally_contribute_to a hindbrain.

label: dark green
Defs: A color consisting of green hue and low brightness.

label: somatostatin receptor activity
Defs: Combining with somatostatin to initiate a change in cell activity. Somatostatin is a peptide hormone that regulates the endocrine system by signaling via G protein-coupled somatostatin receptors. Somatostatin has two active forms produced by proteolytic cleavage: a 14 amino acid peptide (SST-14) and a 28 amino acid peptide (SST-28).

label: regulation of gastric acid secretion
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate frequency or extent of gastric secretion. Gastric secretion is the regulated release of gastric acid (hydrochloric acid) by parietal or oxyntic cells during digestion.

label: inverted-V shaped
Defs: An angular shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a single angle in its length giving the bearer the form of an inverted letter V.

label: neural crest derived neuroblast
Defs: A neuroblast derived from a neural crest cell.

label: mitotic cell cycle process
Defs: A process that is part of the mitotic cell cycle.

label: unpigmented
Defs: A degree of pigmentation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking substances produced by living organisms that have a color resulting from selective color absorption.

label: heart layer
Defs: The laminar structure of the heart.

label: positive regulation of lymphocyte proliferation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the rate or extent of lymphocyte proliferation.

label: negative regulation of cellular amine metabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving amines.

label: trigeminal nerve fibers
Defs: A nerve fiber that is part of a trigeminal nerve.

label: vesicle localization
Defs: Any process in which a vesicle or vesicles are transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location.

label: increased circumference
Defs: A circumference which is relatively high.

label: regulation of hormone levels
Defs: Any process that modulates the levels of hormone within an organism or a tissue. A hormone is any substance formed in very small amounts in one specialized organ or group of cells and carried (sometimes in the bloodstream) to another organ or group of cells in the same organism, upon which it has a specific regulatory action.

label: neoplastic cell
Defs: An abnormal cell exhibiting dysregulation of cell proliferation or programmed cell death and capable of forming a neoplasm, an aggregate of cells in the form of a tumor mass or an excess number of abnormal cells (liquid tumor) within an organism.

label: normal contractility
Defs: A contractility which is relatively normal or average.

label: rotated
Defs: An oriented quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being relocated around an axis.

label: mucosa of bronchiole
Defs: A mucosa that is part of a bronchiole [Automatically generated definition].

label: envelope
Defs: A multilayered structure surrounding all or part of a cell; encompasses one or more lipid bilayers, and may include a cell wall layer; also includes the space between layers.

label: abdomen element
Defs: An organ or element that is in the abdomen. Examples: spleen, intestine, kidney, abdominal mammary gland.

label: pons
Defs: The part of the central nervous system lying between the medulla oblongata and the midbrain, ventral to the cerebellum.

label: negative regulation of endothelial cell chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of endothelial cell chemotaxis.

label: vascular associated smooth muscle cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in a vascular associated smooth muscle cell.

label: intact male
Defs: Male quality of having complete, unaltered reproductive organs.

label: pons maturation
Defs: A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for the pons to attain its fully functional state. The pons lies above the medulla and next to the cerebellum. The pons conveys information about movement from the cerebral hemisphere to the cerebellum.

label: modulation of excitatory postsynaptic potential
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of excitatory postsynaptic potential (EPSP). EPSP is a process that leads to a temporary increase in postsynaptic potential due to the flow of positively charged ions into the postsynaptic cell. The flow of ions that causes an EPSP is an excitatory postsynaptic current (EPSC) and makes it easier for the neuron to fire an action potential.

label: polymeric cytoskeletal fiber
Defs: A component of the cytoskeleton consisting of a homo or heteropolymeric fiber constructed from an indeterminate number of protein subunits.

label: large basket cell morphology
Defs: A basket cell morphology that inheres in neurons that are large, and typically ascend to give rise to many long horizontally and vertically projecting axon collaterals that traverse neighboring columns and can extend through all cortical layers.

label: epithelial fold
Defs: An epithelial sheet bent on a linear axis.

label: negative regulation of macrophage antigen processing and presentation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of macrophage antigen processing and presentation.

label: mobile
Defs: A mobility quality of inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to move freely.

label: regulation of serotonin biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of serotonin biosynthetic process.

label: regulation of myeloid progenitor cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of myeloid progenitor cell differentiation.

label: cellular macromolecule catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a macromolecule, any large molecule including proteins, nucleic acids and carbohydrates, as carried out by individual cells.

label: cubitus
Defs: The insect wing vein that is posterior to the media and anterior to the postcubitus.

label: positive regulation of acetylcholine metabolic process
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving acetylcholine, the acetic acid ester of the organic base choline. Acetylcholine is a major neurotransmitter and neuromodulator both in the central and peripheral nervous systems. It also acts as a paracrine signal in various non-neural tissues.

label: glial cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in a glial cell, a non-neuronal cell of the nervous system.

label: musculature of pectoral girdle
Defs: A subdivision of the musculature of the body in the pectoral girdle region. Includes pectoral and shoulder muscles.

label: yeast mating type
Defs: A yeast mating type.

label: negative regulation of meiotic cell cycle
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the rate or extent of progression through the meiotic cell cycle.

label: inconspicuous
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of not being clearly visible.

label: Schwann cell migration
Defs: The orderly movement of a Schwann cell from one site to another. A Schwann cell is a glial cell that ensheathes axons of neuron in the peripheral nervous system and is necessary for their maintainance and function.

label: inflamed
Defs: A compositional quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s infiltration by leukocytes, local edema and accumulation of plasma proteins.

label: postsynaptic actin cytoskeleton organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising actin filaments and their associated proteins in the postsynaptic actin cytoskeleton.

label: positive regulation of humoral immune response
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of a humoral immune response.

label: plasma membrane bounded cell projection cytoplasm
Defs: All of the contents of a plasma membrane bounded cell projection, excluding the plasma membrane surrounding the projection.

label: translational initiation
Defs: The process preceding formation of the peptide bond between the first two amino acids of a protein. This includes the formation of a complex of the ribosome, mRNA or circRNA, and an initiation complex that contains the first aminoacyl-tRNA.

label: phosphate
Defs: Salts and esters of phosphoric and oligophosphoric acids and their chalcogen analogues. In inorganic chemistry, the term is also used to describe anionic coordination entities with phosphorus as central atom.

label: ring conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that encircles a ring sclerite.

label: aortic sac
Defs: The dilated structure that is lined by endothelial cells and located at the arterial pole of the heart just above (distal to) the truncus arteriosus in mammalian embryos; it is the primordial vascular channel from which the aortic arches (and eventually the dorsal aortae) arise; the aortic sac is homologous to the ventral aorta of gill-bearing vertebrates.

label: protein transport within lipid bilayer
Defs: The directed movement of a protein from one location to another within a lipid bilayer.

label: embryonic camera-type eye morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the eye are generated and organized during embryonic development.

label: regulation of cytoskeleton organization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures.

label: regulation of oocyte maturation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of oocyte maturation.

label: profurca
Defs: The furca of the prothorax that is attached to the procoxa via muscle.

label: tongue development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the tongue over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The tongue is the movable, muscular organ on the floor of the mouth of most vertebrates, in many other mammals is the principal organ of taste, aids in the prehension of food, in swallowing, and in modifying the voice as in speech.

label: sarcoplasm
Defs: The cytoplasm of a muscle cell; includes the sarcoplasmic reticulum.

label: poison
Defs: Any substance that causes disturbance to organisms by chemical reaction or other activity on the molecular scale, when a sufficient quantity is absorbed by the organism.

label: positive regulation of sodium ion transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of sodium ion transmembrane transporter activity.

label: regulation of apoptotic signaling pathway
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of apoptotic signaling pathway.

label: lipid import into cell
Defs: The directed movement of a lipid from outside of a cell into a cell. This may occur via transport across the plasma membrane or via endocytosis.

label: regulation of synapse structure or activity
Defs: Any process that modulates the physical form or the activity of a synapse, the junction between a neuron and a target (neuron, muscle, or secretory cell).

label: disease
Defs: A disposition (i) to undergo pathological processes that (ii) exists in an organism because of one or more disorders in that organism.

label: type D cell of colon
Defs: A D cell located in the colon.

label: axon microtubule bundle
Defs: An arrangement of closely apposed microtubules running parallel to each other in the axon hillock and initial segment.

label: autopolyploid
Defs: A polyploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing chromosomes derived from a single species.

label: regulation of epidermal cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of epidermal cell differentiation.

label: female genotypic sex
Defs: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population based upon genotypic composition that confers the capability for an organism to differentiate female gonads.

label: regulation of sulfur metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving sulfur, the nonmetallic element sulfur or compounds that contain sulfur.

label: normal angle to
Defs: An angle which is relatively normal or average

label: band shaped
Defs: A shape that is in the form of a narrow strip encircling an object.

label: regulation of cardiac muscle cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle cell proliferation.

label: profound intensity
Defs: An intensity which is characterized by being very severe.

label: cellular carbohydrate biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of carbohydrates, any of a group of organic compounds based of the general formula Cx(H2O)y, carried out by individual cells.

label: increased avidity
Defs: An avidity which is relatively high.

label: chemoreceptor cell
Defs: A cell specialized to detect chemical substances and relay that information centrally in the nervous system. Chemoreceptors may monitor external stimuli, as in taste and olfaction, or internal stimuli, such as the concentrations of oxygen and carbon dioxide in the blood.

label: ectoderm formation
Defs: The formation of ectoderm during gastrulation.

label: mandibular symphysis
Defs: A cartilaginous joint that connects left and right mandibles/dentary bones. Mandibular symphysis is unpaired[TAO,modified].

label: respiratory system
Defs: Functional system which consists of structures involved in respiration.

label: cardiac muscle adaptation
Defs: The process in which cardiac muscle adapts, with consequent modifications to structural and/or functional phenotypes, in response to a stimulus. Stimuli include contractile activity, loading conditions, substrate supply, and environmental factors.

label: cerebral cortex radially oriented cell migration
Defs: The migration of cells in the developing cerebral cortex in which cells move from the ventricular and/or subventricular zone toward the surface of the brain.

label: gaseus configuration
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s parts having the arrangement which exhibits characteristics of gases.

label: protein localization to Golgi membrane
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a location within a Golgi membrane.

label: metakatepisternal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus of the metaventrite that is transverse (parallel to the left-right axis).

label: cerebral cortex development
Defs: The progression of the cerebral cortex over time from its initial formation until its mature state. The cerebral cortex is the outer layered region of the telencephalon.

label: positive regulation of protein localization to synapse
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to synapse.

label: positive regulation of endothelial cell activation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of endothelial cell activation.

label: nucleobase catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a nucleobase, a nitrogenous base that is a constituent of a nucleic acid.

label: regulation of embryonic development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of embryonic development.

label: activation of transmembrane receptor protein tyrosine kinase activity
Defs: Any process that initiates the activity of the inactive transmembrane receptor protein tyrosine kinase activity.

label: arteriole of anorectum
Defs: An arteriole that is located in the anorectum.

label: dicarboxylic acid transport
Defs: The directed movement of dicarboxylic acids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: sclera
Defs: Opaque fibrous outer layer of the eyeball[ZFA,Kardong,WP].

label: aromatic
Defs: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity when it possesses at least one ring that is aromatic, i.e. A conjugated ring of unsaturated bonds, lone pairs, or empty orbitals that exhibit a stabilization stronger than would be expected by the stabilization of conjugation alone.

label: unidirectional
Defs: A directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having one direction only.

label: sculpted surface
Defs: A surface feature shape marked by large amounts of relief, often with multiple ridges and grooves in close association. Topographically complex.

label: polyploid cell
Defs: A cell whose nucleus, or nuclei, each contain more than two haploid genomes.

label: prescutum
Defs: The sclerite of the notum that is attached to the anterior margin of the scutum.

label: skeletal muscle fiber
Defs: A transversely striated, synctial cell of skeletal muscle. It is formed when proliferating myoblasts exit the cell cycle, differentiate and fuse.

label: negative regulation of sodium ion transmembrane transport
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of sodium ion transmembrane transport.

label: regulation of smooth muscle cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of smooth muscle cell apoptotic process.

label: positive regulation of type B pancreatic cell development
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of pancreatic B cell development.

label: regulation of myeloid dendritic cell activation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency or rate of myeloid dendritic cell activation.

label: tunica fibrosa of eyeball
Defs: The sclera and cornea form the fibrous tunic of the bulb of the eye; the sclera is opaque, and constitutes the posterior five-sixths of the tunic; the cornea is transparent, and forms the anterior sixth.

label: quality of a liquid
Defs: A physical quality inhering in an entity exhibiting the physical characteristics of an amorphous (non-crystalline) form of matter between a gas and a solid that has a definite volume, but no definite shape.

label: telencephalon development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the telencephalon over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The telencephalon is the paired anteriolateral division of the prosencephalon plus the lamina terminalis from which the olfactory lobes, cerebral cortex, and subcortical nuclei are derived.

label: negative regulation of microtubule polymerization
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of microtubule polymerization.

label: organic acid binding
Defs: Binding to an organic acid, any acidic compound containing carbon in covalent linkage.

label: normal waxiness
Defs: A waxiness which is relatively normal or average

label: regulation of neurotransmitter receptor activity
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of neurotransmitter receptor activity. Modulation may be via an effect on ligand affinity, or effector funtion such as ion selectivity or pore opening/closing in ionotropic receptors.

label: regulation of muscle hypertrophy
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of muscle hypertrophy.

label: permeable
Defs: A permeability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being capable to be permeated or pervaded by a gas or liquid (as by osmosis or diffusion).

label: nuclear membrane
Defs: Either of the lipid bilayers that surround the nucleus and form the nuclear envelope; excludes the intermembrane space.

label: negative regulation of glial cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of glia cell differentiation.

label: midgut
Defs: Middle subdivision of a digestive tract[CJM]. In vertebrates: The middle part of the alimentary canal from the stomach, or entrance of the bile duct, to, or including, the large intestine[GO].

label: increased wetness
Defs: A wetness quality that is relatively high.

label: positive regulation of mitotic chromosome condensation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of mitotic chromosome condensation.

label: hexagonal
Defs: A 2-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having six angles and six sides.

label: positive regulation of smooth muscle cell chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of smooth muscle cell chemotaxis.

label: negative regulation of ion transmembrane transport
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of ions from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: circulatory system development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the circulatory system over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The circulatory system is the organ system that passes nutrients (such as amino acids and electrolytes), gases, hormones, blood cells, etc. to and from cells in the body to help fight diseases and help stabilize body temperature and pH to maintain homeostasis.

label: CD115-positive monocyte OR common dendritic progenitor
positive regulation of cardiac muscle cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle cell proliferation.

label: egg coat
Defs: A specialized extracellular matrix that surrounds the plasma membrane of the ovum of animals. The egg coat provides structural support and can play an essential role in oogenesis, fertilization and early development.

label: pH reduction
Defs: Any process that reduces the internal pH of an organism, part of an organism or a cell, measured by the concentration of the hydrogen ion.

label: vacuolar transport
Defs: The directed movement of substances into, out of or within a vacuole.

label: cardioblast migration
Defs: The orderly movement of a cardiac progenitor cell to form the heart field. Cardiac progenitor cells are non-terminally differentiated, mesoderm-derived cells that are committed to differentiate into cells of the heart. A cardioblast is a cardiac precursor cell. It is a cell that has been committed to a cardiac fate, but will undergo more cell division rather than terminally differentiating.

label: myotome
Defs: A transitional population of migrating mesenchymal cells that derive from somites and that will become muscle cells.

label: increased area
Defs: An area which is relatively high.

label: decreased threshold
Defs: A threshold which is relatively low.

label: oxygen transport
Defs: The directed movement of oxygen (O2) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: nucleologenesis
Defs: A cellular process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of a nucleolus, a small, dense body one or more of which are present in the nucleus of eukaryotic cells.

label: mesenteric artery
Defs: Arteries which arise from the abdominal aorta and distribute to most of the intestines.

label: funnel-shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s similarity to the appearance of a funnel.

label: zone of skin
Defs: Any portion of the organ that covers that body and consists of a layer of epidermis and a layer of dermis.

label: anterior margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the anterior side of a body or body part.

label: lilac
Defs: A purple color which has low saturation and low brightness.

label: labyrinthine layer formation
Defs: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of the labyrinthine layer of the placenta.

label: metasternum
Defs: The sclerite on the ventral region of the metathorax that bears the metafurca and is attached to the metapleuro-metasternal conjunctiva.

label: trichobothrium
Defs: The seta that is elongated.

label: bitter
Defs: A flavor quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having an acrid, sharp, or disagreeable flavor.

label: ectopic germ cell programmed cell death
Defs: Programmed cell death of an errant germ line cell that is outside the normal migratory path or ectopic to the gonad. This is an important mechanism of regulating germ cell survival within the embryo.

label: spinal dura mater
Defs: A dura mater that is part of a spinal cord [Automatically generated definition].

label: quality of a plasma
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting the physical characteristics of an entity consisting of roughly equal proportions of positively and negatively charged particles, having neither a defined volume nor defined shape, having internal magnetic fields, and being electrically conductive.

label: decreased phosphorylation
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being phosphorylated to a lesser than normal extent, or less than fully.

label: nucleate quality
Defs: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of bearer\'s number of nuclei.

label: unnecessary (continuant)
Defs: A necessity quality (continuant) inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being non-essential or dispensable.

label: negative regulation of blood vessel endothelial cell migration
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the migration of the endothelial cells of blood vessels.

label: normal phosphorylation
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being phosphorylated to a normal or average extent.

label: obsolete enhanced
Defs: Increased, intensified.

label: hindbrain maturation
