Defs: A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for the hindbrain to attain its fully functional state. The hindbrain is the region consisting of the medulla, pons and cerebellum. Areas of the hindbrain control motor and autonomic functions.

label: abdominal sternite III
Defs: The abdominal sternite of the preabdomen that is attached to the posterior margin of the abdominal sternite II by the abdominal sternite II-abdominal sternite III conjunctiva and to the anterior margin of the abdominal sternite IV by the abdominal sternite III-abdominal sternite IV conjunctiva.

label: positive regulation of antigen processing and presentation of peptide or polysaccharide antigen via MHC class II
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of antigen processing and presentation of antigen (peptide or polysaccharide) via MHC class II.

label: gastro-intestinal system smooth muscle contraction
Defs: A process in which force is generated within smooth muscle tissue, resulting in a change in muscle geometry. This process occurs in the gastro-intestinal system. Force generation involves a chemo-mechanical energy conversion step that is carried out by the actin/myosin complex activity, which generates force through ATP hydrolysis. The gastro-intestinal system generally refers to the digestive structures stretching from the mouth to anus, but does not include the accessory glandular organs (liver, pancreas and biliary tract).

label: predisplaced growth
Defs: A peramorphic growth quality which is due to an earlier onset.

label: hypoglossal nucleus development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the hypoglossal nucleus over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: regulation of cell cycle process
Defs: Any process that modulates a cellular process that is involved in the progression of biochemical and morphological phases and events that occur in a cell during successive cell replication or nuclear replication events.

label: monosaccharide binding
Defs: Binding to a monosaccharide. Monosaccharides are the simplest carbohydrates; they are polyhydroxy aldehydes H[CH(OH)]nC(=O)H or polyhydroxy ketones H[CHOH]nC(=O)[CHOH]mH with three or more carbon atoms. They form the constitutional repeating units of oligo- and polysaccharides.

label: sound amplitude
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a sound wave by virtue of the maximum magnitude (value without regard to sign) of its disturbance.

label: multicellular organism reproduction
Defs: The biological process in which new individuals are produced by one or two multicellular organisms. The new individuals inherit some proportion of their genetic material from the parent or parents.

label: negative regulation of cardiac muscle tissue development
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle tissue development.

label: endochondral bone morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which bones are generated and organized as a result of the conversion of initial cartilaginous anlage into bone.

label: uniform diameter
Defs: A diameter that remains constant throughout the extent of an entity.

label: positive regulation of Golgi to plasma membrane protein transport
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the transport of proteins from the Golgi to the plasma membrane.

label: primary neural tube formation
Defs: The formation of the neural tube from an epithelial cell sheet (the neuroepithelium or neural plate). In primary neurulation, the cells surrounding the neural plate direct the neural plate cells to proliferate, invaginate, and pinch off from the surface to form a hollow epithelial tube. Primary neurulation is the typical mechanism of formation of the anterior neural tube.

label: increased coiling
Defs: A coiling which is relatively high.

label: intramembranous ossification
Defs: Direct ossification that occurs within mesenchyme or an accumulation of relatively unspecialized cells.

label: regulation of norepinephrine uptake
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of the neurotransmitter norepinephrine into a cell.

label: chondrocyte morphogenesis involved in endochondral bone morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the structures of a chondrocyte that will contribute to bone development are generated and organized.

label: cell-cell adhesion
Defs: The attachment of one cell to another cell via adhesion molecules.

label: vessel
Defs: A tubular structure that contains, conveys body fluid, such as blood or lymph.

label: robust
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being strong, thick or sturdy.

label: cuticular suture
Defs: The region of the cuticle of the head capsule that coincides with an ecdysial line.

label: regulation of translation at postsynapse, modulating synaptic transmission
Defs: Any process that modulates synaptic transmission by regulating translation occurring at the postsynapse.

label: negative regulation of behavior
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of behavior, the internally coordinated responses (actions or inactions) of whole living organisms (individuals or groups) to internal or external stimuli.

label: response to fungus
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus from a fungus.

label: negative regulation of hormone secretion
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of a hormone from a cell.

label: dephosphorylated
Defs: A quality inhering in a protein or a molecule by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking a phosphate (PO4) group.

label: regulation of multicellular organismal process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a multicellular organismal process, the processes pertinent to the function of a multicellular organism above the cellular level; includes the integrated processes of tissues and organs.

label: positive regulation of macrophage chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of macrophage chemotaxis. Macrophage chemotaxis is the movement of a macrophage in response to an external stimulus.

label: ventricular cardiac muscle cell
Defs: Any cardiac muscle cell that is part of a cardiac ventricle.

label: dermal skeletal element
Defs: Dermis-derived entity that is made of skeletal tissue.

label: neuron spine
Defs: A small membranous protrusion, often ending in a bulbous head and attached to the neuron by a narrow stalk or neck.

label: splenic vein
Defs: A vein arising from the splenic trabecular vein in the hilum of the spleen that drains into the portal vein.

label: nucleobase transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of a nucleobase, any nitrogenous base that is a constituent of a nucleoside, nucleotide, or nucleic acidfrom one side of a membrane to the other.

label: autonomic neuron
Defs: A neuron whose cell body is within an autonomic ganglion.

label: positive regulation of immune effector process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of an immune effector process.

label: scutellum
Defs: The sclerite of the notum that is attached to the posterior margin of the scutum.

label: blood vessel layer
Defs: Any of the tissue layers that comprise a blood vessel. Examples: tunica media, tunica adventitia.

label: cardiac muscle tissue development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of cardiac muscle over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: acidity
Defs: A concentration quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing acid (hydrogen ions).

label: forebrain generation of neurons
Defs: The process in which nerve cells are generated in the forebrain. This includes the production of neuroblasts from and their differentiation into neurons.

label: regulation of cardiac muscle myoblast proliferation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle myoblast proliferation.

label: necessary (occurrent)
Defs: A necessity quality inhering in a process by virtue of the bearer\'s being essential or indispensable.

label: split medially
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being split along the median axis.

label: acylcholine
Defs: A choline ester formed from choline and a carboxylic acid.

label: simple columnar epithelium
Defs: Unilaminar epithelium, which consists of a single layer of columnar cells. Examples: ciliated columnar epithelium, gastric epithelium, microvillus columnar epithelium.[FMA].

label: monovalent inorganic cation homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of monovalent inorganic cations within an organism or cell.

label: pharyngeal gland
Defs: Racemose mucous glands beneath the mucous membrane of the pharynx.

label: negative regulation of T cell homeostatic proliferation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the rate or extent of resting T cell proliferation.

label: vacuolar lumen
Defs: The volume enclosed within the vacuolar membrane.

label: left lung bronchiole
Defs: A bronchiole that is part of a left lung [Automatically generated definition].

label: ammonium transmembrane transport
Defs: The process in which ammonium is transported across a membrane. Ammonium is the cation NH4+.

label: anatomical lobe
Defs: A portion of an organ, such as the liver, lung, breast, or brain.

label: clavate
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s gradually becoming thicker towards the end.

label: atrioventricular node development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the atrioventricular (AV) node over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The AV node is part of the cardiac conduction system that controls the timing of ventricle contraction by receiving electrical signals from the sinoatrial (SA) node and relaying them to the His-Purkinje system.

label: endoglin
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human ENG gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: appendage vasculature
Defs: A vasculature that is part of a limb/fin.

label: regulation of animal organ morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of animal organ morphogenesis.

label: enucleated reticulocyte
Defs: A reticulocyte lacking a nucleus and showing a basophilic reticulum under vital staining due to the presence of ribosomes.

label: future telencephalon
Defs: Embryonic structure that gives rise to the telencephalon.

label: cardiac chamber
Defs: A cardiac chamber surrounds an enclosed cavity within the heart.

label: sensory perception
Defs: The series of events required for an organism to receive a sensory stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. This is a neurological process.

label: primordial germ cell
Defs: A primordial germ cell is a diploid germ cell precursors that transiently exist in the embryo before they enter into close association with the somatic cells of the gonad and become irreversibly committed as germ cells.

label: myeloid dendritic cell activation involved in immune response
Defs: The change in morphology and behavior of a myeloid dendritic cell resulting from exposure to a cytokine, chemokine, cellular ligand, or soluble factor, leading to the initiation or perpetuation of an immune response.

label: arcuate ligament
Defs: A ligament that is part of a diaphragm.

label: necrotic
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s undergoing unprogrammed cell death.

label: negative regulation of Schwann cell chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of Schwann cell chemotaxis.

label: apical region
Defs: Anatomical region located on the apical end on the body or body part.

label: polychromatophilic cytoplasm
Defs: Cytoplasm that exhibits affinity for both basic and acid stains under specific pH conditions.

label: negative regulation of neutrophil activation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of neutrophil activation.

label: bicyclic compound
Defs: A molecule that features two fused rings.

label: metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways, including anabolism and catabolism, by which living organisms transform chemical substances. Metabolic processes typically transform small molecules, but also include macromolecular processes such as DNA repair and replication, and protein synthesis and degradation.

label: neural tube lumen
Defs: An anatomical space that surrounded_by a neural tube.

label: carbohydrate derivative metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving carbohydrate derivative.

label: regulation of protein-containing complex disassembly
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein complex disassembly, the disaggregation of a protein complex into its constituent components.

label: circular pouch
Defs: The pouch that is circular.

label: cuticular invagination
Defs: The region of cuticle that corresponds with an invagination of the single layer epidermis (epidermal fold). The cuticular invagination sometimes corresponds to a cuticular depression (concavity on the surface of the cuticle).

label: conus arteriosus development
Defs: The progression of the conus arteriosus over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The conus arteriosus is a valved chamber with thick muscular walls stemming from the ventricle and connecting to the pulmonary trunk.

label: muscle layer of esophagus
Defs: A muscle layer that is part of a wall of esophagus.

label: type B pancreatic cell maturation
Defs: A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for a type B pancreatic cell to attain its fully functional state. A type B pancreatic cell is a cell located towards center of the islets of Langerhans that secretes insulin.

label: negative regulation of T cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of T cell death by apoptotic process.

label: funding source declaration textual entity
Defs: A textual entity documenting the source of funding that supported some study.

label: somatodendritic compartment
Defs: The region of a neuron that includes the cell body (cell soma) and dendrite(s), but excludes the axon.

label: erythroblast
Defs: A nucleated precursor of an erythrocyte that lacks hematopoietic lineage markers.

label: rhombomere lateral wall
Defs: A neural tube lateral wall that is part of a rhombomere.

label: catalytic activity, acting on a nucleic acid
Defs: Catalytic activity that acts to modify a nucleic acid.

label: fibrillar collagen trimer
Defs: Any triple helical collagen trimer that forms fibrils.

label: pancreatic A cell
Defs: A type of enteocrine cell found in the periphery of the islets of Langerhans that secretes glucagon.

label: anal column
Defs: One of a number of vertical folds, produced by an infolding of the mucous membrane and some of the muscular tissue in the upper half of the lumen of the anal canal[WP].

label: detection of abiotic stimulus
Defs: The series of events in which an (non-living) abiotic stimulus is received by a cell and converted into a molecular signal.

label: trumpet-shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s shape form resembling the shape of a trumpet.

label: endorphin secreting cell
Defs: A peptide hormone secreting cell that secretes endorphin.

label: cellular ion homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of ions at the level of a cell.

label: mesoventral process
Defs: The postero-medial region of the mesoventrite in contact with the metaventral process.

label: negative regulation of cell morphogenesis involved in differentiation
Defs: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of cell morphogenesis contributing to cell differentiation. Cell morphogenesis involved in differentiation is the change in form (cell shape and size) that occurs when relatively unspecialized cells acquire specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize the cells, tissues, or organs of the mature organism or some other relatively stable phase of the organism\'s life history.

label: cell periphery
Defs: The part of a cell encompassing the cell cortex, the plasma membrane, and any external encapsulating structures.

label: negative regulation of neutrophil apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of neutrophil apoptotic process.

label: entire embryonic mesenchyme
Defs: Sum total of mesenchyme in the embryo.

label: positive regulation of pseudopodium assembly
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the assembly of pseudopodia.

label: excreted gas
Defs: Any gaseous product of an excretory process.

label: cuticle of maxillary palpomere II
Defs: The cuticle of the maxillary palpomere that is attached to the distal margin of the maxillary palpomere I and to the proximal margin of the maxillary palpomere III.

label: positive regulation of cholangiocyte proliferation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cholangiocyte proliferation.

label: positive regulation of postsynaptic membrane organization
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of postsynaptic membrane organization.

label: negative regulation of action potential
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of action potential creation, propagation or termination. This typically occurs via modulation of the activity or expression of voltage-gated ion channels.

label: partial trisomy
Defs: A trisomy quality inhering in a bearer when part of the bearer\'s extra chromosome is attached to one of the other chromosomes, or if one of the bearer\'s chromosomes has two copies of part of its chromosome.

label: oviduct epithelium development
Defs: The progression of the oviduct epithelium over time from its initial formation to the mature structure. An oviduct is a tube through which an ova passes from the ovary to the uterus, or from the ovary to the outside of the organism. The oviduct epithelium is the specialized epithelium that lines the oviduct.

label: regulation of endothelial cell development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of endothelial cell development.

label: systemic venous system
Defs: The part of the venous system that drains the general body tissues[Kardong].

label: mesenchyme of yolk sac
Defs: The portion of the yolk sac that is derived from mesoderm and consists of mesenchyme.

label: adaptive immune response
Defs: An immune response mediated by cells expressing specific receptors for antigen produced through a somatic diversification process, and allowing for an enhanced secondary response to subsequent exposures to the same antigen (immunological memory).

label: anterior pronoto-cervical muscle
Defs: The dorsoventral thoracic muscle that extends between the antero-lateral region of the pronotum and the medial region of the propleuron.

label: cuticle of pretarsus
Defs: The cuticle of the appendage of the insect leg that is attached to the cuticle of tarsus by the tarso-pretarsal conjunctiva.

label: glutamate receptor activity
Defs: Combining with glutamate and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity.

label: disassembled
Defs: A wholeness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being taken apart into its constituent parts.

label: splanchnic nerve
Defs: The major nerves supplying sympathetic innervation to the abdomen, including the greater, lesser, and lowest (or smallest) splanchnic nerves that are formed by preganglionic fibers from the spinal cord which pass through the paravertebral ganglia and then to the celiac ganglia and plexuses and the lumbar splanchnic nerves carry fibers which pass through the lumbar paravertebral ganglia to the mesenteric and hypogastric ganglia.

label: vascular associated smooth muscle cell
Defs: A smooth muscle cell associated with the vasculature.

label: eye cuticle
Defs: The elastic cuticle of the head capsule that is transparent and covers the eye.

label: myeloid dendritic cell
Defs: A dendritic cell of the myeloid lineage.

label: microtubule bundle
Defs: An arrangement of closely apposed microtubules running parallel to each other.

label: slender
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being small or narrow in circumference or width in proportion to length or height.

label: regulation of cell proliferation involved in compound eye morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell proliferation involved in compound eye morphogenesis.

label: epithelium of pancreatic duct
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a pancreatic duct.

label: north
Defs: North is one of the four compass points or cardinal directions. It is the opposite of south and is perpendicular to east and west.

label: myoblast division
Defs: The process resulting in the physical partitioning and separation of a myoblast into daughter cells. A myoblast is a mononucleate cell type that, by fusion with other myoblasts, gives rise to the myotubes that eventually develop into skeletal muscle fibers.

label: lumen of anal canal
Defs: An anatomical cavity that surrounded_by a anal canal.

label: positive regulation of defense response to bacterium
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of defense response to bacterium.

label: white matter
Defs: Neural tissue consisting of myelinated axons connecting grey matter areas of the central nervous system.

label: cloacal gland development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a cloacal gland over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: decreased mass
Defs: A mass which is lower than normal or average.

label: platelike
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being roundish, flattish shape, possibly with a slightly angled edge.

label: response to oxygen-containing compound
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an oxygen-containing compound stimulus.

label: bile acids
Defs: Any member of a group of hydroxy steroids occuring in bile, where they are present as the sodium salts of their amides with glycine or taurine. In mammals bile acids almost invariably have 5beta-configuration, while in lower vertebrates, some bile acids, known as allo-bile acids, have 5alpha-configuration.

label: negative regulation of neuron migration
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of neuron migration.

label: negative regulation of locomotion
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of locomotion of a cell or organism.

label: regulation of artery morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of artery morphogenesis.

label: flush
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being level or even with another surface.

label: biomacromolecule
Defs: A macromolecule formed by a living organism.

label: cell cortex region
Defs: The complete extent of cell cortex that underlies some some region of the plasma membrane.

label: endocrine system development
Defs: Progression of the endocrine system over time, from its formation to a mature structure. The endocrine system is a system of hormones and ductless glands, where the glands release hormones directly into the blood, lymph or other intercellular fluid, and the hormones circulate within the body to affect distant organs. The major glands that make up the human endocrine system are the hypothalamus, pituitary, thyroid, parathryoids, adrenals, pineal body, and the reproductive glands which include the ovaries and testes.

label: plasma membrane bounded cell projection organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a plasma membrane bounded prolongation or process extending from a cell, e.g. a cilium or axon.

label: retinal rod cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in a retinal rod cell, one of the two photoreceptor cell types of the vertebrate retina.

label: vena cava endothelium
Defs: An endothelium that is part of a vena cava [Automatically generated definition].

label: Schwann cell precursor
Defs: A giioblast cell that develops from a migratory neural crest cell. The SCP is embedded among neurons (axons) with minimal extracellular spaces separating them from nerve cell membranes and has no basal lamina. In rodents SCPs are the only cells in the Schwann cell linage that expresses Cdh19.

label: humidity
Defs: A quality inhering in air by virtue of the partial pressure exerted by the bearer\'s water vapour content.

label: myotube differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a myotube cell. Myotube differentiation starts with myoblast fusion and the appearance of specific cell markers (this is the cell development step). Then individual myotubes can fuse to form bigger myotubes and start to contract. Myotubes are multinucleated cells that are formed when proliferating myoblasts exit the cell cycle, differentiate and fuse.

label: epithelium of tongue
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a tongue [Automatically generated definition].

label: spiracle
Defs: The region of the cuticle that is continuous to the proximal region of a trachea and can be closed by muscles.

label: measurement datum
Defs: A measurement datum is an information content entity that is a recording of the output of a measurement such as produced by a device.

label: cell leading edge cell cortex
Defs: The cell cortex of the leading edge of a cell.

label: additional results section
Defs: A results section that reports analyses other than main results of the study (e.g. subgroups analyses, adjusted analyses, sensitivity analyses, etc.)

label: dopamine secretion
Defs: The regulated release of dopamine by a cell. Dopamine is a catecholamine and a precursor of adrenaline and noradrenaline. It acts as a neurotransmitter in the central nervous system but it is also produced peripherally and acts as a hormone.

label: negative regulation of synapse pruning
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of synapse pruning.

label: positive regulation of endothelial cell migration
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the orderly movement of an endothelial cell into the extracellular matrix to form an endothelium.

label: optical quality
Defs: An EM radiation quality in which the EM radiation is within the fiat range of the spectrum visible deemed to be light.

label: notochord development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the notochord over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The notochord is a mesoderm-derived structure located ventral of the developing nerve cord. In vertebrates, the notochord serves as a core around which other mesodermal cells form the vertebrae. In the most primitive chordates, which lack vertebrae, the notochord persists as a substitute for a vertebral column.

label: barrier cell
Defs: A cell whose primary function is to prevent the transport of stuff across compartments.

label: detoxification of nitrogen compound
Defs: Any process that reduces or removes the toxicity of nitrogenous compounds which are dangerous or toxic. This includes the aerobic conversion of toxic compounds to harmless substances.

label: combustibility
Defs: The propensity of a material to undergo combustion. Combustion encompasses smouldering and flaming combustion. Combustibility is usually applied to solids.

label: information content entity
Defs: A generically dependent continuant that is about some thing.

label: chronological age
Defs: An age quality that exists by virtue of the time (years and months) that the bearer has existed.

label: occipital region
Defs: Anatomical cluster that is located in the posterior region of the cranium and forms the margin of the foramen magnum and occipital condyles.

label: integrin alpha-X
Defs: An integrin alpha with A domain that is a translation product of the human ITGAX gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. Integrin alpha-X complexed with beta-2 is a receptor for fibrinogen. It recognizes the sequence GPR in fibrinogen. It mediates cell-cell interaction during inflammatory responses. It is especially important in monocyte adhesion and chemotaxis.

label: light magenta
Defs: A color consisting of magenta color and high brightness.

label: regulation of transmission of nerve impulse
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transmission of a nerve impulse, the sequential electrochemical polarization and depolarization that travels across the membrane of a neuron in response to stimulation.

label: right lobe of liver
Defs: The right lobe is much larger than the left; the proportion between them being as six to one. It occupies the right hypochondrium, and is separated from the left lobe on its upper surface by the falciform ligament; on its under and posterior surfaces by the left sagittal fossa; and in front by the umbilical notch. It is of a somewhat quadrilateral form, its under and posterior surfaces being marked by three foss: the porta and the foss for the gall-bladder and inferior vena cava, which separate its left part into two smaller lobes; the quadrate and caudate lobes. [WP,unvetted].

label: PP cell of intestine
Defs: A PP cell found in intestine.

label: positive regulation of cellular amine catabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways leading to the breakdown of amines.

label: positive regulation of receptor binding
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of a protein or other molecule binding to a receptor.

label: rhombomere boundary
Defs: A boundary delimiting a rhombomere.

label: increased resistance to
Defs: A resistance to a stimulus which is relatively high.

label: mesonoto-mesopleural conjuntiva
Defs: The noto-pleural conjunctiva that joins the mesonotum and the mesopleuron.

label: future directions textual entity
Defs: A textual entity expressing ideas regarding future work relevant to work described in a document that could be done.

label: regulation of biological process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a biological process. Biological processes are regulated by many means; examples include the control of gene expression, protein modification or interaction with a protein or substrate molecule.

label: truncus arteriosus
Defs: The truncus arteriosus and bulbus cordis are divided by the aorticopulmonary septum. The truncus arteriosus gives rise to the ascending aorta and the pulmonary trunk. The bulbus cordis gives rise to the smooth parts (outflow tract) of the left and right ventricles.

label: centrally registered identifier symbol
Defs: A symbol that is part of a CRID and that is sufficient to look up a record from the CRID\'s registry.

label: skull
Defs: Anatomical structure that is part of the head consisting entirely of cranium and mandible[WP].

label: normal variability
Defs: A variability which is relatively normal or average

label: insufficient
Defs: A wholeness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacks enough functionality.

label: detection of visible light
Defs: The series of events in which a visible light stimulus is received by a cell and converted into a molecular signal. A visible light stimulus is electromagnetic radiation that can be perceived visually by an organism; for organisms lacking a visual system, this can be defined as light with a wavelength within the range 380 to 780 nm.

label: response to other organism
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus from another living organism.

label: monocarboxylic acid transport
Defs: The directed movement of monocarboxylic acids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: light phase
Defs: A phase which occurs during the light cycle.

label: sensory perception of mechanical stimulus
Defs: The series of events required for an organism to receive a sensory mechanical stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. This is a neurological process.

label: diencephalon morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the diencephalon are generated and organized. The diencephalon is the paired caudal parts of the prosencephalon from which the thalamus, hypothalamus, epithalamus and subthalamus are derived; these regions regulate autonomic, visceral and endocrine function, and process information directed to the cerebral cortex.

label: submucosa of bronchiole
Defs: A submucosa that is part of a bronchiole [Automatically generated definition].

label: regulation of dermatome development
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the progression of the dermatome over time, from its initial formation to the mature structure. The dermatome is the portion of a somite that will form skin.

label: morphology
Defs: A quality of a single physical entity inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s size or shape or structure.

label: regulation of blood circulation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of blood circulation.

label: protogynous
Defs: A sequential hermaphroditic quality whereby organisms start out as female and change to male at a later life stage.

label: neutrophil differentiation
Defs: The process in which a myeloid precursor cell acquires the specialized features of a neutrophil.

label: negative regulation of lipid catabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of lipids.

label: normal fluid flow
Defs: A fluid flow which is relatively normal or average.

label: regulation of skeletal muscle adaptation
Defs: Any process in which skeletal muscle adapts, with consequent modifications to structural and/or functional phenotypes, in response to a stimulus. Stimuli include contractile activity, loading conditions, substrate supply, and environmental factors. These adaptive events occur in both muscle fibers and associated structures (motoneurons and capillaries), and they involve alterations in regulatory mechanisms, contractile properties and metabolic capacities.

label: positive regulation of oligodendrocyte progenitor proliferation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the rate or extent of oligodendrocyte progenitor proliferation.

label: positive regulation of endothelial cell development
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of endothelial cell development.

label: a mating type (yeast)
Defs: A S. cerevisiae mating type cells that secrete a pheromone that in alpha haploids stimulates processes that lead to mating.

label: hemopoietic organ
Defs: Organ that is part of the hematopoietic system.

label: external angle
Defs: A convex angle that is formed by one side of a polygon and a line extended from an adjacent side.

label: abstract
Defs: A summary of the entire document that is substantially smaller than the document it summarizes.  It is about the document it summarizes.

label: norepinephrine binding
Defs: Binding to norepinephrine, (3,4-dihydroxyphenyl-2-aminoethanol), a hormone secreted by the adrenal medulla and a neurotransmitter in the sympathetic peripheral nervous system and in some tracts of the CNS. It is also the biosynthetic precursor of epinephrine.

label: positive regulation of dopamine secretion
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of dopamine.

label: anterior wall of right ventricle
Defs: Region of wall of right ventricle which is continuous with the lateral and septal walls of right ventricle.

label: heteroorganic entity
Defs: A heteroorganic entity is an organic molecular entity in which carbon atoms or organic groups are bonded directly to one or more heteroatoms.

label: negative regulation of intestinal epithelial cell development
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of intestinal epithelial cell development.

label: negative regulation of muscle organ development
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of muscle development.

label: negative regulation of establishment of T cell polarity
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of establishment of T cell polarity.

label: outflow tract smooth muscle
Defs: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a outflow tract [Automatically generated definition].

label: colon
Defs: A portion of the large intestine before it becomes the rectum. In mammals, the colon is the most part of the large intestine, excluding the vermiform appendix, the rectum and the anal canal.

label: developmental cell growth
Defs: The growth of a cell, where growth contributes to the progression of the cell over time from one condition to another.

label: pyramidal family morphology
Defs: A cell morphology that inheres in neurons which have a pyramidal shaped soma, a single axon, a large apical dendrite and multiple basal dendrites.

label: crystal configuration
Defs: A solid configuration inhering in a material entity by virtue of its constituent atoms, molecules, or ions being arranged in an orderly repeating pattern extending in all three spatial dimensions.

label: choledocho-duodenal junction
Defs: Hat part of the duodenal wall traversed by the ductus choledochus, ductus pancreaticus, and ampulla.

label: bile acid catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of bile acids, any of a group of steroid carboxylic acids occurring in bile.

label: SA node cell to atrial cardiac muscle cell signaling
Defs: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from an SA node cardiomyocyte to an atrial cardiomyocyte.

label: reproductive system
Defs: Anatomical system that has as its parts the organs concerned with reproduction.

label: negative regulation of tongue muscle cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of tongue muscle cell differentiation.

label: morphogenesis of an endothelium
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structure of an endothelium is generated and organized. Endothelium refers to the layer of cells lining blood vessels, lymphatics, the heart, and serous cavities, and is derived from bone marrow or mesoderm. Corneal endothelium is a special case, derived from neural crest cells.

label: epithelial tube open at both ends
Defs: An epithelial tube open at both ends that allows fluid flow.

label: cranio-lacinial muscle
Defs: The insect cranio-maxillar muscle that is attached to the gena and the lacinia.

label: opposite
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being positioned on opposite sides on the same plane.

label: development of primary sexual characteristics
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the primary sexual characteristics over time, from their formation to the mature structures. The primary sexual characteristics are the testes in males and the ovaries in females and they develop in response to sex hormone secretion.

label: intramembranous bone growth
Defs: The increase in size or mass of an intramembranous bone that contributes to the shaping of the bone.

label: fibroblast of tunica adventitia of artery
Defs: A fibroblast that is part of the tunica adventitia of artery.

label: cellular nitrogen compound metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving various organic and inorganic nitrogenous compounds, as carried out by individual cells.

label: tibio-tarsal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that encircles the tarsus by joining the distal margin of the tibia and the proximal margin of the tarsus.

label: blood circulation
Defs: The flow of blood through the body of an animal, enabling the transport of nutrients to the tissues and the removal of waste products.

label: organic cyclic compound
Defs: Any organic molecule that consists of atoms connected in the form of a ring.

label: white matter of spinal cord
Defs: The regions of the spinal cord that are largely or entirely composed of myelinated nerve cell axons and contain few or no neural cell bodies or dendrites.

label: obsolete radiation equivalent dose
Defs: OBSOLETE A radiation exposure quality inhering in a tissue by virtue of the relation between the absorbed dose to the effective biological damage of the radiation to that tissue.

label: transporter complex
Defs: A protein complex facilitating transport of molecules (proteins, small molecules, nucleic acids) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells.

label: metal ion transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of metal ions from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: regulation of neuromuscular junction development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of neuromuscular junction development.

label: regular sleep pattern
Defs: A sleep pattern which has regular start and/or end times.

label: positive regulation of embryonic camera-type eye development
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of embryonic camera-type eye development.

label: maximally connected
Defs: A structural quality inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer consisting of a single, maximally connected structure.

label: positive regulation of cardiocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cardiocyte differentiation.

label: nuclear fragmentation involved in apoptotic nuclear change
Defs: The breakdown of the nucleus into small membrane-bounded compartments, or blebs, each of which contain compacted DNA.

label: outflow tract myocardium
Defs: A myocardium that is part of a outflow tract [Automatically generated definition].

label: cribriform
Defs: Perforated like a sieve.

label: digestive tract epithelium
Defs: An epithelium that lines the lumen of the digestive tract.

label: cadherin binding
Defs: Binding to cadherin, a type I membrane protein involved in cell adhesion.

label: cholinergic agonist
Defs: Any drug that binds to and activates cholinergic receptors.

label: meiotic cell cycle process
Defs: A process that is part of the meiotic cell cycle.

label: ciliated columnar epithelium
Defs: Simple columnar epithelium in which the luminal side of the cells bears cilia. Examples: epithelium of trachea, epithelium of uterine tube.[FMA].

label: collagen-containing extracellular matrix
Defs: An extracellular matrix consisting mainly of proteins (especially collagen) and glycosaminoglycans (mostly as proteoglycans) that provides not only essential physical scaffolding for the cellular constituents but can also initiate crucial biochemical and biomechanical cues required for tissue morphogenesis, differentiation and homeostasis. The components are secreted by cells in the vicinity and form a sheet underlying or overlying cells such as endothelial and epithelial cells.

label: positive regulation of hepatocyte apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of hepatocyte apoptotic process.

label: hepatic acinus
Defs: The functional unit of the liver, consisting of a mass of hepatocytes from adjacent liver lobules aligned around the hepatic arterioles and portal venules just as they anastomose into sinusoids.

label: splayed ventral
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved outwards the abdomen of an organism.

label: chitosome membrane
Defs: The lipid bilayer surrounding a chitosome.

label: liver lobule
Defs: The polygonal structure of the liver that consists of hepatocytes radiating outward from a hepatic vein.

label: synovial cavity of joint
Defs: An anatomical cavity that surrounded_by a synovial joint.

label: positive regulation of lipid transport
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of lipids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: length
Defs: A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance between two points.

label: regulation of secondary metabolite biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of secondary metabolite biosynthetic process.

label: positive regulation of mitotic nuclear envelope disassembly
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of mitotic nuclear envelope disassembly.

label: leukocyte activation involved in inflammatory response
Defs: A change in the morphology or behavior of a leukocyte resulting from exposure to an activating factor such as a cellular or soluble ligand, leading to the initiation or perpetuation of an inflammatory response.

label: fibroblast of cardiac tissue
Defs: A fibroblast that is part of the heart.

label: optic eminence
Defs: The embryonic structure that gives rise to the corneal ectoderm.

label: future forebrain
Defs: A presumptive structure that has the potential to develop into a forebrain.

label: collagen biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of collagen, any of a group of fibrous proteins of very high tensile strength that form the main component of connective tissue in animals. Collagen is highly enriched in glycine (some regions are 33% glycine) and proline, occurring predominantly as 3-hydroxyproline (about 20%).

label: negative regulation of lung ciliated cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of lung ciliated cell differentiation.

label: positive regulation of neural crest formation
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of neural crest formation. Neural crest formation is the formation of the specialized region of ectoderm between the neural ectoderm (neural plate) and non-neural ectoderm. The neural crest gives rise to the neural crest cells that migrate away from this region as neural tube formation procedes.

label: polyanionic macromolecule
Defs: A polymer carrying multiple negative charges.

label: regulation of lymphocyte mediated immunity
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of lymphocyte mediated immunity.

label: skeletal element
Defs: Organ consisting of skeletal tissue. Encompasses whole bones, fused bones, cartilaginious elements, teeth, dermal denticles.

label: endoderm of foregut
Defs: An endoderm that is part of a foregut [Automatically generated definition].

label: electrically signaling cell
Defs: A cell that initiates an electrical signal and passes that signal to another cell.

label: negative regulation of protein metabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of chemical reactions and pathways involving a protein.

label: decreased susceptibility toward
Defs: A susceptibility toward an external stimulus which is lower than normal/average.

label: liver dendritic cell
Defs: Any dendritic cell that is part of a liver.

label: branching morphogenesis of an epithelial tube
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of branches in an epithelial tube are generated and organized. A tube is a long hollow cylinder.

label: stomodeal lumen
Defs: An anatomical cavity that surrounded_by a stomodeum.

label: pericardial sac
Defs: A double-walled sac containing the heart and the roots of the great vessels.

label: cellular response to amine stimulus
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an amine stimulus. An amine is a compound formally derived from ammonia by replacing one, two or three hydrogen atoms by hydrocarbyl groups.

label: extracellular vesicle
Defs: Any vesicle that is part of the extracellular region.

label: negative regulation of bile acid metabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of bile acid metabolic process.

label: carbohydrate
Defs: Any member of the class of organooxygen compounds that is a polyhydroxy-aldehyde or -ketone or a lactol resulting from their intramolecular condensation (monosaccharides); substances derived from these by reduction of the carbonyl group (alditols), by oxidation of one or more hydroxy groups to afford the corresponding aldehydes, ketones, or carboxylic acids, or by replacement of one or more hydroxy group(s) by a hydrogen atom; and polymeric products arising by intermolecular acetal formation between two or more such molecules (disaccharides, polysaccharides and oligosaccharides). Carbohydrates contain only carbon, hydrogen and oxygen atoms; prior to any oxidation or reduction, most have the empirical formula Cm(H2O)n. Compounds obtained from carbohydrates by substitution, etc., are known as carbohydrate derivatives and may contain other elements. Cyclitols are generally not regarded as carbohydrates.

label: biological process involved in interspecies interaction between organisms
Defs: Any process evolved to enable an interaction with an organism of a different species.

label: serous pericardium
Defs: Serous membrane which is divided into parietal and visceral serous pericardium.

label: regulation of peptide secretion
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of peptide secretion.

label: antrorse
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved forward or upward.

label: negative regulation of monocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of monocyte differentiation.

label: lumen of hindgut
Defs: An anatomical cavity that surrounded_by a hindgut.

label: musculature
Defs: A subdivision of the muscular system corresponding to a subdisivision of an organism.

label: anecic
Defs: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to burrow more than 20 cm deep into the soil and make permanent, vertical burrows.

label: digestive system development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the digestive system over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The digestive system is the entire structure in which digestion takes place. Digestion is all of the physical, chemical, and biochemical processes carried out by multicellular organisms to break down ingested nutrients into components that may be easily absorbed and directed into metabolism.

label: midbrain nucleus
Defs: Nucleus located in the midbrain.

label: distichous
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being arranged in two opposite rows (and hence in the same plane).

label: transition metal ion homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of transition metal ions within an organism or cell. A transition metal is an element whose atom has an incomplete d-subshell of extranuclear electrons, or which gives rise to a cation or cations with an incomplete d-subshell. Transition metals often have more than one valency state. Biologically relevant transition metals include vanadium, manganese, iron, copper, cobalt, nickel, molybdenum and silver.

label: Kit-negative, Ly-76 high basophilic erythroblast
Defs: A basophilic erythroblast that is Lyg 76-high and is Kit-negative.

label: epithelial cell differentiation involved in embryonic placenta development
Defs: The process in which a trophoblast cell acquires specialized features of an epithelial cell of the placental labyrinthine layer.

label: manubrium
Defs: The apodeme on the anterior margin of the tegmen.

label: tightly articulated with
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being strongly articulated with another entity.

label: enteroendocrine cell of colon
Defs: An enteroendocrine cell that is located in the colon.

label: germline stem cell asymmetric division
Defs: The self-renewing division of a germline stem cell, to produce a daughter stem cell and a daughter germ cell which will divide to form one or more gametes.

label: aromatic compound biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of aromatic compounds, any substance containing an aromatic carbon ring.

label: atrial septum morphogenesis
Defs: The developmental process in which atrial septum is generated and organized. The atrial septum separates the upper chambers (the atria) of the heart from one another.

label: costo-cervical trunk
Defs: The costocervical trunk arises from the upper and back part of the subclavian artery, behind the scalenus anterior on the right side, and medial to that muscle on the left side. Passing backward, it splits into the deep cervical artery and the supreme intercostal artery (or the Highest intercostal artery), which descends behind the pleura in front of the necks of the first and second ribs, and anastomoses with the first aortic intercostal (3rd posterior intercostal artery). As it crosses the neck of the first rib it lies medial to the anterior division of the first thoracic nerve, and lateral to the first thoracic ganglion of the sympathetic trunk. In the first intercostal space, it gives off a branch which is distributed in a manner similar to the distribution of the aortic intercostals. The branch for the second intercostal space usually joins with one from the highest aortic intercostal artery. This branch is not constant, but is more commonly found on the right side; when absent, its place is supplied by an intercostal branch from the aorta. Each intercostal gives off a posterior branch which goes to the posterior vertebral muscles, and sends a small spinal branch through the corresponding intervertebral foramen to the medulla spinalis and its membranes. [WP,unvetted].

label: mineralized
Defs: A composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being composed of or possessing inorganic material.

label: venule
Defs: One of the minute vessels that collect deoxygenated blood from the capillary plexuses returns it to the veins.

label: incisiform
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having the shape of an incisor tooth.

label: horizontal pyramidal neuron
Defs: A pyramidal neuron which has an apical tree which is oriented parallel to the pia. This is unlike typical pyramidal neurons which have its apical dendrite aligned vertically.

label: telencephalon dura mater
Defs: A dura mater that is part of a telencephalon [Automatically generated definition].

label: oocyte
Defs: A female germ cell that has entered meiosis.

label: methods section
Defs: A part of a publication about an investigation that is about the study design of the investigation

label: smooth muscle cell of the brachiocephalic vasculature
Defs: A smooth muscle cell of the bachiocephalic vasculature.

label: radiation reflective quality
Defs: A scalar EM radiation quality which obtains by the capacity of the bearer to scatter or reflect radiation.

label: submucosa of rectum
Defs: The submucous layer of the wall of the rectum.

label: lateral lingual swelling
Defs: During the third week there appears, immediately behind the ventral ends of the two halves of the mandibular arch, a rounded swelling named the tuberculum impar, which was described by His as undergoing enlargement to form the buccal part of the tongue. More recent researches, however, show that this part of the tongue is mainly, if not entirely, developed from a pair of lateral swellings (or distal tongue bud) which rise from the inner surface of the mandibular arch and meet in the middle line.

label: having extra function
Defs: A functionality quality which is held by the bearer when the latter is able to perform additional or different function(s).

label: negative regulation of lymphocyte proliferation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the rate or extent of lymphocyte proliferation.

label: organosulfate oxoanion
Defs: An organic anion of general formula RS(=O)2O(-) where R is an organyl group.

label: ectodermal placode
Defs: An ectodermal placode is a thickening of the ectoderm that is the primordium of many structures derived from the ectoderm[GO].

label: angle
Defs: An orientation inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s placement at an angle.

label: malignant cell
Defs: A neoplastic cell that is capable of entering a surrounding tissue

label: negative regulation of G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway.

label: rhombomere development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the rhombomere over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Rhombomeres are transverse segments of the developing rhombencephalon. Rhombomeres are lineage restricted, express different genes from one another, and adopt different developmental fates.

label: castrated male
Defs: Male quality of being incapable to reproduce because of functional loss of the testicles from surgical removal or chemical means.

label: carboxylic acid transmembrane transport
Defs: The process in which carboxylic acid is transported across a membrane.

label: cuticle of antenna
Defs: The cuticle of the appendage of the head capsule that is connected by the  antenniferal-scapal conjunctiva to the cuticle of the scapus, which is connected by the scapal-pedicellar conjunctiva to the cuticle of the pedicellus; the cuticle of the pedicellus is connected by the pedicellar-first flagellomeral conjunctiva to the cuticle of the first flagellomere; the cuticle of the first flagellomere is connected by interflagellomeral conjunctiva to the next cuticle of flagellomere. Further cuticle of flagellomeres are connected to each other by interflagellomeral conjunctiva.

label: pronoto-mesonotal muscle
Defs: The insect thoracic muscle that extends between the pronotum and the mesonotum.

label: mucous gland
Defs: A gland in which the principal secretory cells are mucus secreting cells.

label: vesicle organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a vesicle.

label: neurotransmitter
Defs: An endogenous compound that is used to transmit information across the synapse between a neuron and another cell.

label: regulation of brood size
Defs: Any process that modulates brood size. Brood size is the number of progeny that survive embryogenesis and are cared for at one time.

label: regulation of motile cilium assembly
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of motile cilium assembly.

label: membrane assembly
Defs: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a membrane.

label: regulation of protein localization to microtubule
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to microtubule.

label: cervical spinal cord ventral horn
Defs: A ventral horn of spinal cord that is part of a cervical spinal cord.

label: decreased fertility
Defs: A fertility which is relatively low.

label: positive regulation of epithelial cell proliferation involved in lung morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that increases the rate or frequency of epithelial cell proliferation that results in the lung attaining its shape.

label: negative regulation of myeloid progenitor cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of myeloid progenitor cell differentiation.

label: coronary vasculature morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of blood vessels of the heart are generated and organized. The blood vessel is the vasculature carrying blood.

label: positive regulation of gastric acid secretion
Defs: Any process that increases the rate frequency or extent of gastric secretion. Gastric secretion is the regulated release of gastric acid (hydrochloric acid) by parietal or oxyntic cells during digestion.

label: parallel-sided
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s possessing two sides that are at the same continuous distance relative to each other.

label: tetraploid
Defs: A polyploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing four homologous sets of chromosomes.

label: retrograde dendritic transport
Defs: The directed movement of organelles or molecules along microtubules in a dendrite from the postsynapse towards the cell body.

label: ciliated cell
Defs: A cell that has a filiform extrusion of the cell surface.

label: insulin metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving insulin.

label: establishment of localization in cell
Defs: Any process, occuring in a cell, that localizes a substance or cellular component. This may occur via movement, tethering or selective degradation.

label: decreased circumference
Defs: A circumference which is relatively low.

label: regulation of placenta blood vessel development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of placenta blood vessel development.

label: cell-cell signaling involved in lung development
Defs: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from one cell to another and contributes to the progression of the lung, from its initial state to the mature structure.

label: layer of neocortex
Defs: One of the layers of the neocortex. These layers are defined by distinctive populations of cells based on somata size, shape, or density, that are aligned into sheets.

label: anti-inflammatory drug
Defs: A substance that reduces or suppresses inflammation.

label: positive regulation of endothelial cell chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of endothelial cell chemotaxis.

label: basal mesocoxal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that encircles the mesocoxa and connects it to the ventral and lateral regions of the mesothorax.

label: zygote asymmetric cell division
Defs: The division of the zygote into two daughter cells that will adopt developmentally distinct potentials.

label: regulation of chromosome segregation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of chromosome segregation, the process in which genetic material, in the form of chromosomes, is organized and then physically separated and apportioned to two or more sets.

label: baryon
Defs: Baryon is a fermion that does experience the strong force (strong interaction). The term is derived from the Greek betaalpharhoupsilonsigma (heavy).

label: trivalent inorganic anion homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of trivalent inorganic anions within an organism or cell.

label: vacuole fission
Defs: The division of a vacuole within a cell to form two or more separate vacuoles.

label: defense response to other organism
Defs: Reactions triggered in response to the presence of another organism that act to protect the cell or organism from damage caused by that organism.

label: positive regulation of macrophage antigen processing and presentation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of macrophage antigen processing and presentation.

label: neuroblast proliferation
Defs: The expansion of a neuroblast population by cell division. A neuroblast is any cell that will divide and give rise to a neuron.

label: negative regulation of nitrogen compound metabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving nitrogen or nitrogenous compounds.

label: glutamine family amino acid
Defs: An L-alpha-amino acid which is L-glutamic acid or any of the essential amino acids biosynthesised from it (glutamine, proline and arginine). A closed class.

label: negative regulation of serotonin biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of serotonin biosynthetic process.

label: neuron development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a neuron over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell.

label: integrin alpha-IIb (mouse)
Defs: An integrin alpha-IIb that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: hematopoietic stem cell homeostasis
Defs: Any biological process involved in the maintenance of the steady-state number of hematopoietic stem cells within a population of cells.

label: cuticle of mesofemur
Defs: The cuticle of the segment of a mid leg attached to the distal margin of the mesotrochanter by the mesotrochantero-mesofemoral conjunctiva and to the proximal margin of the mesotibia by the mesofemoro-mesotibial conjunctiva.

label: myelencephalon
Defs: The posterior part of the developing vertebrate hindbrain or the corresponding part of the adult brain composed of the medulla oblongata and a portion of the fourth ventricle; as well as the glossopharyngeal nerve (CN IX), vagus nerve (CN X), accessory nerve (CN XI), hypoglossal nerve (CN XII), and a portion of the vestibulocochlear nerve (CN VIII).[BTO,WP].

label: mixed sex
Defs: A biological sex quality inhering in a population of multiple sexes.

label: epithelial cell of stomach
Defs: An epithelial cell found in the lining of the stomach.

label: dorsal tentorial arm
Defs: Is the apophysis of the tentorium that is connected to an anterior tentorial arm.

label: lymphocyte of small intestine lamina propria
Defs: A lymphocyte that resides in the lamina propria of the small intestine. Lamina propria leukocytes and intraepithelial lymphocytes are the effector compartments of the gut mucosal immune system. Lymphocytes circulate through gut associated lymphoid tissues until recruitment by intestinal antigens. They are involved in the gut immune response.

label: negative regulation of epidermal cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of epidermal cell differentiation.

label: translational elongation
Defs: The successive addition of amino acid residues to a nascent polypeptide chain during protein biosynthesis.

label: renal system process
Defs: A organ system process carried out by any of the organs or tissues of the renal system. The renal system maintains fluid balance, and contributes to electrolyte balance, acid/base balance, and disposal of nitrogenous waste products. In humans, the renal system comprises a pair of kidneys, a pair of ureters, urinary bladder, urethra, sphincter muscle and associated blood vessels; in other species, the renal system may comprise related structures (e.g., nephrocytes and malpighian tubules in Drosophila).

label: continuant
Defs: An entity that exists in full at any time in which it exists at all, persists through time while maintaining its identity and has no temporal parts.

label: regulation of extracellular exosome assembly
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of extracellular vesicular exosome assembly.

label: tongue taste bud
Defs: A taste bud that is located on the tongue, situated on a gustatory papilla.

label: (R)-noradrenaline
Defs: The R-enantiomer of noradrenaline.

label: increased weight
Defs: A weight which is relatively high.

label: negative regulation of cytoskeleton organization
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures.

label: furca
Defs: The apophysis that is located ventromedially on the thorax and is connected to the coxa via muscles.

label: tongue morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the tongue are generated and organized. The tongue is the movable, muscular organ on the floor of the mouth of most vertebrates, in man other mammals is the principal organ of taste, aids in the prehension of food, in swallowing, and in modifying the voice as in speech.

label: old
Defs: An age which is relatively high.

label: midbrain basal plate
Defs: Portion of tissue that is dorsolateral to the floor plate and part of the midbrain.

label: regulation of polysaccharide biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of polysaccharides.

label: systemic artery
Defs: An artery of the systemic circulation, which is the part of the cardiovascular system which carries oxygenated blood away from the heart, to the body, and returns deoxygenated blood back to the heart.

label: CD34 molecule
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human CD34 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. It is a leukocyte membrane protein expressed specifically by lymphohematopoietic progenitor cells. It contains a single-pass transmembrane domain and that show distinct expression on early hematopoietic precursors and vascular-associated tissue. Acts as a scaffold that presents selectin carbohydrate ligands in a clustered, tissue specific manner to allow for higher avidity interactions between leukocytes and endothelial cells during the inflammatory process. In common with related sialomucins (endoglycan and podocalyxin), the extracellular region is dominated by an N-terminal mucin-like domain, which is densely substituted with sialylated O-linked carbohydrates. The mucin-like region is followed by a cysteine-containing and presumably globular domain. This domain may fold into an immunoglobulin-like structure as the positions of 2 of the cysteines are conserved in the C2 set of the immunoglobulin superfamily. The cytoplasmic domain is around 73-76 residues long and highly conserved.

label: intrahepatic cholangiocyte
Defs: An epithelial cell of the intrahepatic portion of the bile duct. These cells are flattened or cuboidal in shape, and have a small nuclear-to-cytoplasmic ratio relative to large/extrahepatic cholangiocytes.

label: neuroinflammatory response
Defs: The immediate defensive reaction by neural vertebrate tissue to infection or injury caused by chemical or physical agents.

label: modulation of chemical synaptic transmission
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency or amplitude of synaptic transmission, the process of communication from a neuron to a target (neuron, muscle, or secretory cell) across a synapse.  Amplitude, in this case, refers to the change in postsynaptic membrane potential due to a single instance of synaptic transmission.

label: granulocyte monocyte progenitor cell
Defs: A hematopoietic progenitor cell that is committed to the granulocyte and monocyte lineages. These cells are CD123-positive, and do not express Gata1 or Gata2 but do express C/EBPa, and Pu.1.

label: type D cell of small intestine
Defs: A type D cell of the small intestine.

label: intracellular anatomical structure
Defs: A component of a cell contained within (but not including) the plasma membrane. In eukaryotes it includes the nucleus and cytoplasm.

label: normal distribution
Defs: A distribution which is relatively normal or average

label: carbonyl compound
Defs: Any compound containing the carbonyl group, C=O. The term is commonly used in the restricted sense of aldehydes and ketones, although it actually includes carboxylic acids and derivatives.

label: positive regulation of ion transport
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of charged atoms or small charged molecules into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: adolescent
Defs: A maturity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being between the onset of puberty and maturity.

label: body morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the soma are generated and organized.

label: retinal neural layer
Defs: The part of the retina that contains neurons and photoreceptor cells[GO].

label: carbohydrate catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of carbohydrates, any of a group of organic compounds based of the general formula Cx(H2O)y.

label: lymphocyte antigen 6A-2/6E-1 (mouse)
Defs: A lymphocyte antigen 6A-2/6E-1 that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: height
Defs: A 1-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s vertical dimension of extension.

label: regulation of erythrocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of erythrocyte differentiation.

label: spinal cord neural crest
Defs: A neural crest that has_potential_to_developmentally_contribute_to a spinal cord.

label: pancreatic juice
Defs: Pancreatic juice is slightly alkaline and contains numerous enzymes and inactive enzyme precursors including alpha-amylase, chymotrypsinogen, lipase, procarboxypeptidase, proelastase, prophospholipase A2, ribonuclease, and trypsinogen. Its high concentration of bicarbonate ions helps to neutralize the acid from the stomach.

label: lower lip
Defs: Lip that covers the lower portion of the mouth.[TAO].

label: normal wetness
Defs: A wetness which is relatively normal or average

label: defense response to insect
Defs: A response to protect an organism from a directly detected or perceived external threat from an insect or insects to that organism.

label: respiratory airway
Defs: An airway through which respiratory air passes in organisms.

label: regulation of lymphoid progenitor cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of lymphoid progenitor cell differentiation.

label: killer cell lectin-like receptor subfamily B member 1C (mouse)
Defs: A killer cell lectin-like receptor subfamily B member 1C that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: striated muscle adaptation
Defs: Any process in which striated muscle adapts, with consequent modifications to structural and/or functional phenotypes, in response to a stimulus. Stimuli include contractile activity, loading conditions, substrate supply, and environmental factors. These adaptive events occur in both muscle fibers and associated structures (motoneurons and capillaries), and they involve alterations in regulatory mechanisms, contractile properties and metabolic capacities.

label: dissociated from
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking physically interaction with another entity.

label: spinal cord
Defs: Part of the central nervous system located in the vertebral canal continuous with and caudal to the brain; demarcated from brain by plane of foramen magnum. It is composed of an inner core of gray matter in which nerve cells predominate, and an outer layer of white matter in which myelinated nerve fibers predominate, and surrounds the central canal. (CUMBO).

label: response to biotic stimulus
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a biotic stimulus, a stimulus caused or produced by a living organism.

label: study design execution
Defs: a planned process that carries out a study design

label: canthus
Defs: The region of cuticle that is anterior to the compound eye

label: left ventricular cardiac muscle tissue morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of left cardiac ventricle muscle are generated and organized.

label: attached to
Defs: An attachment quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s connection or association with another entity.

label: spatial pattern
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting repetition of placement of its parts.

label: hindgut
Defs: The caudalmost subdivision of a digestive tract.

label: T cell chemotaxis
Defs: The directed movement of a T cell in response to an external stimulus. A T cell is a type of lymphocyte whose defining characteristic is the expression of a T cell receptor complex.

label: cuticle of maxillary palpomere IV
Defs: The cuticle of the maxillary palpomere that is attached to the distal margin of the maxillary palpomere III and to the proximal margin of the maxillary palpomere V.

label: anatomical cavity
Defs: Anatomical space which contains portions of one or more body substances and is bounded by the internal surface of one maximally connected anatomical structure. Examples: cranial cavity, pharyngeal recess space, nasal cavity, tooth socket, cavity of serous sac, lumen of stomach, lumen of artery, fornix of vagina.

label: cellular response to steroid hormone stimulus
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a steroid hormone stimulus.

label: neurotransmitter transport
Defs: The directed movement of a neurotransmitter into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Neurotransmitters are any chemical substance that is capable of transmitting (or inhibiting the transmission of) a nerve impulse from a neuron to another cell.

label: bi-directional
Defs: A directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having two directions.

label: perpendicular to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located at a right angle relative to another entity.

label: regulation of carbohydrate metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving carbohydrates.

label: regulation of vesicle-mediated transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of vesicle-mediated transport, the directed movement of substances, either within a vesicle or in the vesicle membrane, into, out of or within a cell.

label: regulation of female gonad development
