Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of female gonad development.

label: natural killer cell receptor 2B4
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human CD244 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: substantia propria of cornea development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a substantia propria of cornea over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: hepatocyte
Defs: The main structural component of the liver. They are specialized epithelial cells that are organized into interconnected plates called lobules. Majority of cell population of liver, polygonal in shape, arranged in plates or trabeculae between sinusoids; may have single nucleus or binucleated.

label: negative regulation of smooth muscle cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of smooth muscle cell apoptotic process.

label: insect tagmatic subdivision of integument
Defs:
Region of integument of a tagma.
http://flybase.org/cgi-bin/fbcvq.html?query=FBbt:00007289

label: negative regulation of myeloid dendritic cell activation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of myeloid dendritic cell activation.

label: pigment cell development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a pigment cell over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Cell development does not include the steps involved in committing a cell to a pigment cell fate.

label: paraphyses
Defs: The proximal apodemes of the aedeagus.

label: increased sensitivity toward
Defs: A sensitivity toward an external stimulus which is higher than normal/average.

label: interventricular septum
Defs: Cardiac septum which separates the right ventricle from the left ventricle.[FMA].

label: protein localization to cell periphery
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, the cell periphery.

label: degree of illumination
Defs: The degree to which the bearer is exposed to visible light.

label: parenchyma of central nervous system
Defs: The functional tissue of the central nervous system consisting of neurons and glial cells.

label: intramembranous bone morphogenesis
Defs: The developmental process by which an intramembranous bone is generated and organized.

label: endocrine process
Defs: The process that involves the secretion of or response to endocrine hormones. An endocrine hormone is a hormone released into the circulatory system.

label: postsynaptic membrane assembly
Defs: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a postsynaptic membrane, a specialized area of membrane facing the presynaptic membrane on the tip of the nerve ending and separated from it by a minute cleft (the synaptic cleft).

label: elastic fiber
Defs: An supramolecular fiber that consists of an insoluble core of polymerized tropoelastin monomers and a surrounding mantle of microfibrils. Elastic fibers provide elasticity and recoiling to tissues and organs, and maintain structural integrity against mechanical strain.

label: liver primordium
Defs: A small endodermal thickening in the foregut adjacent to the transverse septum. Invaginates forming the hepatic diverticulum.

label: heterochronic growth
Defs: A growth quality of a process inhering in an organism, structure, or group of organisms by virtue of the bearer\'s reduced or increased growth.

label: erythroid transcription factor (mouse)
Defs: An erythroid transcription factor that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: decreased wetness
Defs: A wetness quality that is relatively low.

label: dendrite development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the dendrite over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: mononuclear cell migration
Defs: The movement of a mononuclear cell within or between different tissues and organs of the body.

label: positive regulation of ion transmembrane transport
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of ions from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: morula
Defs: A spherical embryonic mass of blastomeres formed before the blastula and resulting from cleavage of the fertilized ovum.

label: hypermorphic growth
Defs: A peramorphic growth quality which is due to a delayed offset.

label: positive regulation of retinal cell programmed cell death
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of programmed cell death that occurs in the retina.

label: regulation of reproductive process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of reproductive process.

label: trunk neural crest
Defs: Trunk portion of the neural crest. The trunk neural crest lies between the vagal and sacral neural crest and gives rise to two groups of cells. One group migrates dorsolateral and populates the skin, forming pigment cells and the other migrates ventrolateral through the anterior sclerotome to become the epinephrine-producing cells of the adrenal gland and the neurons of the sympathetic nervous system. Some cells remain in the sclerotome to form the dorsal root ganglia [Wikipedia].

label: neocortex
Defs: An area of cerebral cortex defined on the basis of cytoarchitecture that have six layers. Starting from the cortical surface the layers are: molecular layer (I), external granular layer (II), external pyramidal layer (III), internal granular layer (IV), internal pyramidal layer (V), and multiform layer (VI). Neocortex is most prominent in the frontal lobe, the parietal lobe, the temporal lobe and the occipital lobe, less so in the cingulate gyrus, the parahippocampal gyrus and the insula. It is composed of two subdivisions: true isocortex and proisocortex (Carpenter-83)(NN).

label: postsynapse of neuromuscular junction
Defs: The postsynapse of a neuromuscular junction. In vertebrate muscles this includes the motor end-plate, consisting of postjunctional folds of the sarcolemma.

label: decreased area
Defs: An area which is relatively low.

label: intrahepatic bile duct development
Defs: The progression of the intrahepatic bile ducts over time, from their formation to the mature structure. Intrahepatic bile ducts (bile ducts within the liver) collect bile from bile canaliculi in the liver, and connect to the extrahepatic bile ducts (bile ducts outside the liver).

label: regulation of glucose metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of glucose metabolism. Glucose metabolic processes are the chemical reactions and pathways involving glucose, the aldohexose gluco-hexose.

label: model number
Defs: A model number is an information content entity specifically borne by catalogs, design specifications, advertising materials, inventory systems and similar  that is about manufactured objects of the same class. The model number is an alternative term for the class. The manufactered objects may or may not also bear the model number. Model numbers can be encoded in a variety of other information objects, such as bar codes, numerals, or patterns of dots.

label: regulation of leukocyte chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of leukocyte chemotaxis.

label: detoxification of iron ion
Defs: Any process that reduces or removes the toxicity of iron ion. These include transport of iron away from sensitive areas and to compartments or complexes whose purpose is sequestration of iron ion.

label: sphincter muscle
Defs: A structure, usually a circular muscle, that normally maintains constriction of a natural body passage or orifice and which relaxes as required by normal physiological functioning.

label: negative regulation of transporter activity
Defs: Any process that stops or reduces the activity of a transporter.

label: positive regulation of extracellular exosome assembly
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of extracellular vesicular exosome assembly.

label: thoracic nerve
Defs: The twelve spinal nerves on each side of the thorax. They include eleven INTERCOSTAL NERVES and one subcostal nerve. Both sensory and motor, they supply the muscles and skin of the thoracic and abdominal walls.

label: keel-shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having an elongate structure, similar to a ridge, that extends longitudinally along an anatomical entity.

label: posterior margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the posterior side of the body or body part.

label: neural crest
Defs: A specialized region of ectoderm found between the neural ectoderm (neural plate) and non-neural ectoderm and composed of highly migratory pluripotent cells that delaminate in early embryonic development from the dorsal neural tube and give rise to an astounding variety of differentiated cell types[MP].

label: non-material anatomical boundary
Defs: A non-material anatomical entity of two dimensions. Anatomical boundaries are contiguous structures.

label: protein localization to motile cilium
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a location within a motile cilium.

label: uncoordinated
Defs: A coordination quality of inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking skillful and effective interaction of movement.

label: hydroxyapatite binding
Defs: Binding to hydroxyapatite, the calcium phosphate mineral of formula Ca10(PO4)6(OH)2 found both in rocks of nonorganic origin and as a component of bone and dentin.

label: oxidized
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having reacted with oxygen, or been modified by oxidation (the reaction in which the atoms of an element lose electrons and the valence of the element increases).

label: negative regulation of oocyte maturation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of oocyte maturation.

label: CD2 molecule
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human CD2 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: glycogen binding
Defs: Binding to glycogen.

label: negative regulation of norepinephrine uptake
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of norepinephrine into a cell.

label: cuboid
Defs: A convex 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resemblance to a cube (a 3-D shape with a square cross section).

label: regulation of pigmentation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the deposition or modulates the distribution of coloring matter in an organism.

label: hepatic sinusoidal space
Defs: A sinusoidal space that is part of a hepatic sinusoid.

label: necessity of occurrent
Defs: A quality of single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer is essential or indispensable.

label: metapleuro-metacoxal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the metathorax that joins the metapleuron and the metacoxa.

label: primitive heart tube
Defs: Multi-tissue structure that arises from the heart rudiment and will become the heart tube.

label: ruptured
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s components being torn, typically used for soft tissues or membranes.

label: organization quality
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being arranged in a systematic fashion.

label: acetylcholine
Defs: Actylcholine is an ester of acetic acid and choline, which acts as a neurotransmitter.

label: abdominal sternite IV
Defs: The abdominal sternite of the preabdomen that is attached to the posterior margin of the abdominal sternite III by the abdominal sternite III-abdominal sternite IV conjunctiva and to the anterior margin of the abdominal sternite V by the abdominal sternite IV-abdominal sternite V conjunctiva.

label: rectal salt gland
Defs: An evagination of the terminal portion of the intestine that is capable of secreting high concentrations of excess sodium chloride.

label: negative regulation of apoptotic signaling pathway
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of apoptotic signaling pathway.

label: capillary of brain
Defs: A capillary that is part of the brain.

label: neoplastic, invasive
Defs: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to invade surrounding tissues.

label: cholinergic neuron
Defs: A neuron that uses acetylcholine as a vesicular neurotransmitter.

label: regulation of cellular ketone metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the chemical reactions and pathways involving any of a class of organic compounds that contain the carbonyl group, CO, and in which the carbonyl group is bonded only to carbon atoms. The general formula for a ketone is RCOR, where R and R are alkyl or aryl groups.

label: protein localization to cell leading edge
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a location within a cell leading edge.

label: cartilage development involved in endochondral bone morphogenesis
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the cartilage that will provide a scaffold for mineralization of endochondral bones.

label: alinotum
Defs: The sclerite that is on the lateral region of the notum and is adjacent to the wing.

label: fecundity
Defs: A reproductive quality inhering in an organism or population by virtue of the bearer\'s potential reproductive capacity ad measured by the number of gametes.

label: decreased acidity
Defs: An acidity which is relatively low.

label: trough shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s shape resembling that of a trough, being narrow, long, and boxlike in shape.

label: decreased coiling
Defs: A coiling which is relatively low.

label: third axillary sclerite
Defs: The axillary sclerite that is connected via muscle to the mesopleuron and is  posterior to the first axillary sclerite.

label: regulation of cytokine production involved in inflammatory response
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cytokine production involved in inflammatory response.

label: decreased avidity
Defs: An avidity which is relatively low.

label: anatomical conduit
Defs: Any tube, opening or passage that connects two distinct anatomical spaces.

label: endoderm formation
Defs: The formation of the endoderm during gastrulation.

label: supporting cell
Defs: A cell whose primary function is to support other cell types.

label: reproductive organ
Defs: An organ involved in reproduction.

label: temperature homeostasis
Defs: A homeostatic process in which an organism modulates its internal body temperature.

label: dermal microvascular endothelial cell
Defs: Any microvascular endothelial cell that is part of the dermis.

label: vermilion
Defs: The zone of the skin that surrounds a lip and is colored red due to thin epithelium and presence of eleidin.

label: respiratory system venous smooth muscle
Defs: A smooth muscle tissue that is part of a respiratory system venous blood vessel.

label: G protein-coupled neurotransmitter receptor activity involved in regulation of postsynaptic membrane potential
Defs: A G protein-coupled neurotransmitter receptor activity, occurring in the postsynaptic membrane, involved in regulation of postsynaptic membrane potential.

label: positive regulation of cellular process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of a cellular process, any of those that are carried out at the cellular level, but are not necessarily restricted to a single cell. For example, cell communication occurs among more than one cell, but occurs at the cellular level.

label: increased rate of occurrence
Defs: A rate of occurrence that is relatively high.

label: positive regulation of lipid biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of lipids.

label: plume-shaped
Defs: A shape that ineres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s mass being distributed in a feather-like fashion.

label: sensillum chaeticum
Defs: The hairlike seta that is short and thick walled.

label: light red
Defs: A color consisting of red hue and high brightness.

label: nuclear transport
Defs: The directed movement of substances into, out of, or within the nucleus.

label: obstructed
Defs: A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being blocked or filled with obstacles or an obstacle.

label: skeletal muscle of trunk
Defs: A skeletal muscle organ that is part of the trunk region.

label: positive regulation of neutrophil activation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of neutrophil activation.

label: positive regulation of vasculature development
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of vasculature development.

label: non-aromatic
Defs: A quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the molecule possessing no rings that are aromatic.

label: bile acid salt
Defs: A salt of a bile acid.

label: vein of lip
Defs: A vein that drains a lip.

label: green
Defs: A color hue with medium-low wavelength of that portion of the visible spectrum lying between yellow and blue, evoked in the human observer by radiant energy with wavelengths of approximately 490 to 570 nanometers.

label: nuclear chromosome
Defs: A chromosome that encodes the nuclear genome and is found in the nucleus of a eukaryotic cell during the cell cycle phases when the nucleus is intact.

label: nucleolus
Defs: A small, dense body one or more of which are present in the nucleus of eukaryotic cells. It is rich in RNA and protein, is not bounded by a limiting membrane, and is not seen during mitosis. Its prime function is the transcription of the nucleolar DNA into 45S ribosomal-precursor RNA, the processing of this RNA into 5.8S, 18S, and 28S components of ribosomal RNA, and the association of these components with 5S RNA and proteins synthesized outside the nucleolus. This association results in the formation of ribonucleoprotein precursors; these pass into the cytoplasm and mature into the 40S and 60S subunits of the ribosome.

label: oviduct glandular cell
Defs: Glandular cell of oviduct epithelium. Example: peg cells, ciliated cells.

label: multi-species collection of organisms
Defs: A collection of organisms that consists of two or more organisms from at least two species.

label: positive regulation of sodium ion transmembrane transport
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of sodium ion transmembrane transport.

label: unnecessary (occurrent)
Defs: A necessity quality inhering in a process by virtue of the bearer\'s being non-essential or dispensable.

label: negative regulation of cardiac muscle myoblast proliferation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle myoblast proliferation.

label: MHC protein complex assembly
Defs: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form an MHC protein complex.

label: membrane biogenesis
Defs: A cellular process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of a membrane.

label: multilaminar epithelium
Defs: Epithelium which consists of more than one layer of epithelial cells that may or may not be in contact with a basement membrane. Examples: keratinized stratified squamous epithelium, ciliated stratified columnar epithelium.[FMA].

label: gland of diencephalon
Defs: Any gland that is part of the diencephalon. Examples: pineal gland, neurohypophysis.

label: monocarboxylic acid binding
Defs: Binding to a monocarboxylic acid, any organic acid containing one carboxyl (COOH) group or anion (COO-).

label: cardiac atrium formation
Defs: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of a cardiac atrium from unspecified parts. A cardiac atrium receives blood from a vein and pumps it to a cardiac ventricle.

label: sinoatrial node development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the sinoatrial (SA) node over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The SA node is part of the cardiac conduction system that controls the timing of heart muscle contraction. It relays electrical signals to the AV node.

label: neurotransmitter receptor regulator activity
Defs: A molecular function that directly (via physical interaction or direct modification) activates, inhibits or otherwise modulates the activity of a neurotransmitter receptor. Modulation of activity includes changes in desensitization rate, ligand affinity, ion selectivity and pore-opening/closing.

label: negative regulation of cell adhesion
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cell adhesion.

label: glandular acinus
Defs: The many-lobed berry cluster of cells that is the terminous of a gland where the secretion is produced is acinar in form.

label: tholiform
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being dome-shaped.

label: positive regulation of T cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of T cell death by apoptotic process.

label: frontoclypeal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that coincides with the frontoclypeal ridge and separated the frons from the clypeus.

label: protein-hormone receptor activity
Defs: Combining with a protein hormone to initiate a change in cell activity.

label: positive regulation of muscle adaptation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of muscle adaptation.

label: spinal cord sulcus limitans
Defs: A sulcus limitans of neural tube that is part of a future spinal cord.

label: impermeable
Defs: A permeability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being incapable of being permeated or pervaded by a gas or liquid (as by osmosis or diffusion).

label: positive regulation of glial cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of glia cell differentiation.

label: brainstem motor neuron
Defs: Any motor neuron that is part of a brainstem.

label: superior salivatory nucleus
Defs: Nucleus containing parasympathetic neurons giving rise to the parasympathetic division of the facial nerve, innervating the salivary glands (Brodal, Neurological Anatomy, 3rd ed., 1981, pg 703).

label: submucosa of anal canal
Defs: A submucosa that is part of an anal canal [Automatically generated definition].

label: descriptive data section
Defs: A document part that lists and defines data variables, describes data characteristics (e.g. missing data information) and any assumptions and simplifications made.

label: basal region
Defs: Anatomical region located basally on the body or body part.

label: type G enteroendocrine cell
Defs: An endocrine cell found in the pyloric gland mucosa (antral mucosa) of the stomach of mammals and responsible for the secretion of gastrin and enkephalin. Most abundant in pyloric antrum, pyramidal in form with a narrow apex bearing long microvilli.

label: regulation of eye photoreceptor cell development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of eye photoreceptor development.

label: positive regulation of sarcomere organization
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of myofibril assembly by organization of muscle actomyosin into sarcomeres. The sarcomere is the repeating unit of a myofibril in a muscle cell, composed of an array of overlapping thick and thin filaments between two adjacent Z discs.

label: angular acceleration
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the rate of change of the bearer\'s angular velocity.

label: pH elevation
Defs: Any process that increases the internal pH of an organism, part of an organism or a cell, measured by the concentration of the hydrogen ion.

label: ganglion maturation
Defs: A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for ganglion to attain its fully functional state.

label: vacuolar amino acid transmembrane transport
Defs: The process in which an amino acid is transported from one side of the vacuolar membrane to the other.

label: muscle organ
Defs: Organ consisting of a tissue made up of various elongated cells that are specialized to contract and thus to produce movement and mechanical work[GO].

label: positive regulation of neutrophil apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of neutrophil apoptotic process.

label: carbohydrate derivative catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of carbohydrate derivative.

label: cuticle of maxillary palpomere III
Defs: The cuticle of the maxillary palpomere that is attached to the distal margin of the maxillary palpomere II and to the proximal margin of the maxillary palpomere IV.

label: yellow orange
Defs: A color consisting of yellow and orange hue.

label: elastic cuticle
Defs: The region of cuticle with higher content of resilin.

label: subterminal
Defs: A position quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s existing near the end of another entity.

label: mosaic trisomy
Defs: A trisomy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having extra chromosomal material in only some of it\'s cells.

label: conus arteriosus morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the conus arteriosus is generated and organized. The conus arteriosus is a valved chamber with thick muscular walls stemming from the ventricle and connecting to the pulmonary trunk.

label: outflow tract of ventricle
Defs: A ventricular outflow tract is a portion of either the left ventricle or right ventricle of the heart through which blood passes in order to enter the great arteries. The right ventricular outflow tract (RVOT) is an infundibular extension of the ventricular cavity which connects to the pulmonary artery. The left ventricular outflow tract (LVOT), which connects to the aorta, is nearly indistinguishable from the rest of the ventricle[WP].

label: gene expression
Defs: The process in which a gene\'s sequence is converted into a mature gene product (protein or RNA). This includes the production of an RNA transcript and its processing, translation and maturation for protein-coding genes.

label: developmental process involved in reproduction
Defs: A developmental process in which a progressive change in the state of some part of an organism, germline or somatic, specifically contributes to its ability to form offspring.

label: anucleate
Defs: A nucleate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having no nucleus.

label: positive regulation of RNA biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of RNA biosynthetic process.

label: sonic hedgehog protein
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human SHH gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: negative regulation of glutamate secretion
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the controlled release of glutamate.

label: regulation of organelle assembly
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of organelle assembly.

label: cuticle of ligula
Defs: The cuticle of the appendage of the cuticle of labium composed of the cuticle of glossa and cuticle of paraglossa jointly.

label: normal photosensitivity
Defs: A photosensitivity which is relatively normal or average

label: regulation of myeloid leukocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of myeloid leukocyte differentiation.

label: medulla oblongata morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structure of the medulla oblongata is generated and organized. The medulla oblongata lies directly above the spinal cord and controls vital autonomic functions such as digestion, breathing and the control of heart rate.

label: cell growth
Defs: The process in which a cell irreversibly increases in size over time by accretion and biosynthetic production of matter similar to that already present.

label: cranial salt gland
Defs: A salt gland located in the cranium or head region.

label: detection of light stimulus
Defs: The series of events in which a light stimulus (in the form of photons) is received and converted into a molecular signal.

label: negative regulation of translational initiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of translational initiation.

label: sound speed
Defs: A physical quality inhering in sound by virtue of the bearer\'s travelling speed in a given medium under specified conditions.

label: regulation of protein secretion
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the controlled release of a protein from a cell.

label: metaventral process
Defs: The antero-medial region of the metaventrite in contact with the mesoventral process.

label: obclavate
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s shape being inversely clavate.

label: parasagittal orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is in the parasagittal plane.

label: cellular monovalent inorganic anion homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of monovalent inorganic anions at the level of a cell.

label: gas excreted from digestive tract
Defs: Any excreted gas that is produced by the digestive tract.

label: basophilic erythroblast
Defs: A nucleated immature erythrocyte, having cytoplasm generally similar to that of the earlier proerythroblast but sometimes even more basophilic, and usually regular in outline. The nucleus is still relatively large, but the chromatin strands are thicker and more deeply staining, giving a coarser appearance; the nucleoli have disappeared. This cell is CD71-positive and lacks hematopoeitic lineage markers.

label: azane
Defs: Saturated acyclic nitrogen hydrides having the general formula NnHn+2.

label: diencephalic white matter
Defs: White matter that is part of a diencephalon [Automatically generated definition].

label: mitotic chromosome condensation
Defs: The cell cycle process in which chromatin structure is compacted prior to and during mitosis in eukaryotic cells.

label: orientation
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s placement which is defined by the angle between the bearer and an axis, or the angle between the bearer and another object.

label: positive regulation of neutrophil differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of neutrophil differentiation.

label: kinase binding
Defs: Binding to a kinase, any enzyme that catalyzes the transfer of a phosphate group.

label: cellular response to hormone stimulus
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a hormone stimulus.

label: glucose metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving glucose, the aldohexose gluco-hexose. D-glucose is dextrorotatory and is sometimes known as dextrose; it is an important source of energy for living organisms and is found free as well as combined in homo- and hetero-oligosaccharides and polysaccharides.

label: negative regulation of artery morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of artery morphogenesis.

label: axon ensheathment
Defs: Any process in which the axon of a neuron is insulated, and that insulation maintained, thereby preventing dispersion of the electrical signal.

label: presumptive neural retina
Defs: Portion of tissue that is the inner layer of the optic cup and will become the neural retina.

label: regulation of steroid hormone secretion
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of steroid hormone secretion.

label: mouse metabolite
Defs: Any mammalian metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in a mouse (Mus musculus).

label: regulation of cellular localization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a process in which a cell, a substance, or a cellular entity is transported to, or maintained in a specific location within or in the membrane of a cell.

label: oral epithelium from ectoderm
Defs: An epithelium that develops_from a ectoderm and is part of a oral epithelium.

label: whole
Defs: A wholeness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s including all its components.

label: ossification involved in bone maturation
Defs: The formation of bone or of a bony substance, or the conversion of fibrous tissue or of cartilage into bone, involved in the progression of the skeleton from its formation to its mature state.

label: endomembrane system organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the endomembrane system.

label: branching cuticular invagination
Defs: The cuticular ivagination that is branched into umerous branches.

label: establishment or maintenance of cytoskeleton polarity involved in gastrulation
Defs: Any cellular process that results in the specification, formation or maintenance of polarized cytoskeletal structures that contribute to the cell polarity of a migrating ameboid cell taking part in gastrulation.

label: ligament
Defs: The resilin rich region that connects two sclerites.

label: hepatic sinusoid of left of lobe of liver
Defs: A hepatic sinusoid that is part of a left lobe of liver.

label: positive regulation of cell projection organization
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cell projections.

label: muscle of pelvis
Defs: Muscle (organ) which is a part of the pelvis. Examples: levator ani,.

label: negative regulation of cell proliferation involved in compound eye morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cell proliferation involved in compound eye morphogenesis.

label: material entity in digestive tract
Defs: Any material entity that is located in the digestive tract. This includes undigested food and liquid as well as unexcreted waste products. It also includes other entities such as ingested stones used to aid digestion. Any microbial cells or cell populations are also included.

label: Golgi membrane fusion
Defs: The joining of two lipid bilayers that surround the Golgi apparatus to form a single Golgi membrane.

label: senescent
Defs: A time quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s growing old; aging.

label: epithelium of large intestine
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a large intestine [Automatically generated definition].

label: T-cell surface glycoprotein CD4 (mouse)
Defs: A CD4 molecule that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: lumen of colon
Defs: An anatomical cavity that surrounded_by a colon.

label: secondary metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in many of the chemical changes of compounds that are not necessarily required for growth and maintenance of cells, and are often unique to a taxon. In multicellular organisms secondary metabolism is generally carried out in specific cell types, and may be useful for the organism as a whole. In unicellular organisms, secondary metabolism is often used for the production of antibiotics or for the utilization and acquisition of unusual nutrients.

label: bodily gas
Defs: Any substance in the body or expelled from the body that is in a gaseous state.

label: increased mass
Defs: A mass which is higher than normal or average.

label: 1st arch mesenchyme from head mesenchyme
Defs: Mesenchyme that develops_from a head mesenchyme from mesoderm and is part of a 1st arch mesenchyme.

label: cellular response to oxygen-containing compound
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an oxygen-containing compound stimulus.

label: positive regulation of neuron migration
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of neuron migration.

label: scleral endothelium
Defs: An endothelium that is part of a sclera.

label: regulation of multicellular organism growth
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of growth of the body of an organism so that it reaches its usual body size.

label: angioblastic mesenchymal cell
Defs: A mesenchymal stem cell capable of developing into blood vessel endothelium.

label: cancellous
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having an open, latticed, or porous structure; used especially of bone.

label: negative regulation of fat cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of fat cell apoptotic process.

label: steroid binding
Defs: Binding to a steroid, any of a large group of substances that have in common a ring system based on 1,2-cyclopentanoperhydrophenanthrene.

label: establishment of lymphocyte polarity
Defs: The directed orientation of lymphocyte signaling molecules and associated membrane rafts towards a chemokine gradient or a contact point with an appropriate activating cell.

label: adipocyte of epicardial fat of right ventricle
Defs: A fat cell that is part of the epicardial fat of right ventricle.

label: medulla oblongata development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the medulla oblongata over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The medulla oblongata lies directly above the spinal cord and controls vital autonomic functions such as digestion, breathing and the control of heart rate.

label: genome announcement section
Defs: A document part announcing the publication of a novel draft genome sequence.

label: outflow tract endothelium
Defs: An endothelium that is part of a outflow tract [Automatically generated definition].

label: retinal cone cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in a retinal cone cell, one of the two photoreceptor cell types of the vertebrate retina.

label: neuron projection morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of a neuron projection are generated and organized. A neuron projection is any process extending from a neural cell, such as axons or dendrites.

label: neural tube derived brain
Defs: A brain that develops_from a neural tube.

label: alpha-amino acid
Defs: An amino acid in which the amino group is located on the carbon atom at the position alpha to the carboxy group.

label: organ system subdivision
Defs: A subdivision of an anatomical system.

label: visual perception
Defs: The series of events required for an organism to receive a visual stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. Visual stimuli are detected in the form of photons and are processed to form an image.

label: ribonucleoprotein complex assembly
Defs: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of proteins and RNA molecules to form a ribonucleoprotein complex.

label: forebrain neuroblast differentiation
Defs: The process in which neuroepithelial cells in the neural tube acquire specialized structural and/or functional features of basal progenitor cells, neuroblasts that lose their contacts with the ventricular surface. Differentiation includes the processes involved in commitment of a cell to a specific fate.

label: age
Defs: A time quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of how long the bearer has existed.

label: research participants section
Defs: A document part that describes human subject(s) that participated in a study (e.g. inclusion & exclusion criteria, recruitment methods, reasons for non-participation, grouping and randomisation, methods of follow-up, etc.).

label: negative regulation of type B pancreatic cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of type B pancreatic cell proliferation.

label: positive regulation of synapse pruning
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of synapse pruning.

label: negative regulation of endothelial cell migration
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the orderly movement of an endothelial cell into the extracellular matrix to form an endothelium.

label: forebrain morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the forebrain are generated and organized. The forebrain is the anterior of the three primary divisions of the developing chordate brain or the corresponding part of the adult brain (in vertebrates, includes especially the cerebral hemispheres, the thalamus, and the hypothalamus and especially in higher vertebrates is the main control center for sensory and associative information processing, visceral functions, and voluntary motor functions).

label: cuboidal epithelium
Defs: An epithelium consisting of cuboidal epithelial cells.

label: negative regulation of cell differentiation involved in embryonic placenta development
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of cell differentiation that contributes to the progression of the placenta over time, from its initial condition to its mature state.

label: musculature of thorax
Defs: Any collection of muscles that is part of a thorax [Automatically generated definition].

label: chromatic property
Defs: An optical quality that is the mixture, purity or pattern of wavelengths of light perceived by the observer.

label: integer numeral
Defs: A numeral that denotes an integer

label: positive regulation of dermatome development
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the progression of the dermatome over time, from its initial formation to the mature structure. The dermatome is the portion of a somite that will form skin.

label: esophageal hiatus
Defs: A hole in the diaphragm through which the esophagus passes.

label: hemopoiesis
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the myeloid and lymphoid derived organ/tissue systems of the blood and other parts of the body over time, from formation to the mature structure. The site of hemopoiesis is variable during development, but occurs primarily in bone marrow or kidney in many adult vertebrates.

label: pore canal
Defs: The orifice that is contained by the cuticle and connects the inside of the insect with the outside, is tubular, and whose diameter is smaller than 100 nm.

label: striated muscle hypertrophy
Defs: The enlargement or overgrowth of all or part of an organ due to an increase in size of muscle cells without cell division. In the case of striated muscle, this happens due to the additional synthesis of sarcomeric proteins and assembly of myofibrils.

label: organic fundamental parent
Defs: An organic fundamental parent is a structure used as a basis for substitutive names in organic nomenclature, containing, in addition to one or more hydrogen atoms, a single atom of an element, a number of atoms (alike or different) linked together to form an unbranched chain, a monocyclic or polycyclic ring system, or a ring assembly or ring/chain system.

label: anion transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of a negatively charged ion from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: protandrous
Defs: A sequential hermaphroditic quality whereby organisms start out as male and change to female at a later life stage.

label: left lobe of liver
Defs: The left lobe is smaller and more flattened than the right. It is situated in the epigastric and left hypochondriac regions. Its upper surface is slightly convex and is moulded on to the diaphragm; its under surface presents the gastric impression and omental tuberosity. [WP,unvetted].

label: mental-premental conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the labium that connects the mentum and the prementum.

label: non-progressive
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s not increasing over time.

label: ciliary transition zone assembly
Defs: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a ciliary transition zone.

label: intrinsic component of membrane
Defs: The component of a membrane consisting of the gene products having some covalently attached portion, for example part of a peptide sequence or some other covalently attached group such as a GPI anchor, which spans or is embedded in one or both leaflets of the membrane.

label: negative regulation of catecholamine secretion
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of a catecholamine.

label: decreased resistance to
Defs: A resistance to a stimulus which is relatively low.

label: bone of dorsum
Defs: A bone that is part of the dorsal region of an animal.

label: myeloid leukocyte
Defs: A cell of the monocyte, granulocyte, or mast cell lineage.

label: developmental growth
Defs: The increase in size or mass of an entire organism, a part of an organism or a cell, where the increase in size or mass has the specific outcome of the progression of the organism over time from one condition to another.

label: quality of interaction of a substance with electromagnetic radiation
Defs: A quality of a substance on which or through which electromagnetic radiation impinges or traverses with respect to radiation. This substance quality changes the quality of the incident radiation with respect to any of: intensity, direction, scatter and wavelength.

label: glutamic acid
Defs: An alpha-amino acid that is glutaric acid bearing a single amino substituent at position 2.

label: endocardial cushion
Defs: The endocardial cushion is a specialized region of mesenchymal cells that will give rise to the heart septa and valves[GO]. Swellings of tissue present between the endocardial and myocardial cell layers that will give rise to the interstitial cells of the cardiac valves[ZFA].

label: centrally registered identifier
Defs: An information content entity that consists of a CRID symbol and additional information about the CRID registry to which it belongs.

label: cell-cell signaling involved in cardiac conduction
Defs: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from one cell to another and contributes to the heart process that regulates cardiac muscle contraction; beginning with the generation of an action potential in the sinoatrial node and ending with regulation of contraction of the myocardium.

label: gonad
Defs: Reproductive organ that produces and releases eggs (ovary) or sperm (testis).

label: transmission of nerve impulse
Defs: The neurological system process in which a signal is transmitted through the nervous system by a combination of action potential propagation and synaptic transmission.

label: normal variability of color
Defs: A variability of color which is relatively normal or average

label: regulation of Golgi organization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of Golgi organization.

label: inflated
Defs: A structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being filled with air.

label: arrhythmic
Defs: A rhythm quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking rhythm.

label: negative regulation of T cell mediated immunity
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of T cell mediated immunity.

label: protibio-protarsal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that encircles the protarsus by joining the distal margin of the protibia and the proximal margin of the protarsus.

label: written name
Defs: A textual entity that denotes a particular in reality.

label: peptide hormone
Defs: Any peptide with hormonal activity in animals, whether endocrine, neuroendocrine, or paracrine.

label: sulfuric acid
Defs: A sulfur oxoacid that consists of two oxo and two hydroxy groups joined covalently to a central sulfur atom.

label: negative regulation of blood circulation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of blood circulation.

label: interleukin-5 receptor subunit alpha (mouse)
Defs: An interleukin-5 receptor subunit alpha that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: monocyte differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized myeloid precursor cell acquires the specialized features of a monocyte.

label: positive regulation of lipid catabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of lipids.

label: skeletal muscle hypertrophy
Defs: The enlargement or overgrowth of all or part of an organ due to an increase in size (not length) of individual muscle fibers without cell division. In the case of skeletal muscle cells this happens due to the additional synthesis of sarcomeric proteins and assembly of myofibrils.

label: black
Defs: A color that lacks any hues as parts.

label: vagus nerve formation
Defs: The process that gives rise to the vagus nerve. This process pertains to the initial formation of a structure from unspecified parts. This nerve is primarily sensory but also has visceromotor components. It originates in the brain stem and controls many autonomic functions of the heart, lungs, stomach, pharynx, larynx, trachea, esophagus and other gastrointestinal tract components. It controls some motor functions such as speech. The sensory branches mediate sensation from the pharynx, larynx, thorax and abdomen; it also innervates taste buds in the epiglottis.

label: aorta smooth muscle tissue
Defs: The nonstriated, involuntary muscle tissue located in the wall of the aorta.

label: neural plate
Defs: A region of embryonic ectodermal cells that lie directly above the notochord. During neurulation, they change shape and produce an infolding of the neural plate (the neural fold) that then seals to form the neural tube[XAO]. The earliest recognizable dorsal ectodermal primordium of the central nervous system present near the end of gastrulation before infolding to form the neural keel; consists of a thickened pseudostratified epithelium[ZFA].

label: regulation of retina development in camera-type eye
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of retina development in camera-type eye.

label: disconnected
Defs: A structural quality inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer consisting of multiple structures lacking any physical connection to each other.

label: venous system
Defs: The part of the cardiovascular system consisting of all venous vessels. In vertebrates with a double circulation, this can be divided into systemic and pulmonary portions.

label: introduction to a publication about an investigation
Defs: A part of a publication about an investigation that is about the objective specification (why the investigation is being done)

label: endothelial tube formation
Defs: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of an endothelial tube.

label: organ or tissue specific immune response
Defs: An immune response taking place in an organ or tissues such as the liver, brain, mucosa, or nervous system tissues.

label: agrochemical
Defs: An agrochemical is a substance that is used in agriculture or horticulture.

label: positive regulation of muscle organ development
Defs: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the rate of muscle development.

label: axo-dendritic protein transport
Defs: The directed movement of proteins along microtubules in neuron projections.

label: positive regulation of establishment of T cell polarity
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of establishment of T cell polarity.

label: fatty
Defs: A composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing excess lipid.

label: amine transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of amines, including polyamines, from one side of a membrane to the other. Amines are organic compounds that are weakly basic in character and contain an amino (-NH2) or substituted amino group.

label: multi-ciliated epithelial cell
Defs: A ciliated epithelial cell with many cilium.

label: regulation of chondrocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of chondrocyte differentiation.

label: stratification
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s layered configuration.

label: regulation of vasculature development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of vasculature development.

label: collagen catabolic process
Defs: The proteolytic chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of collagen in the extracellular matrix, usually carried out by proteases secreted by nearby cells.

label: acinar cell
Defs: A secretory cell that is grouped together with other cells of the same type to form grape shaped clusters known as acini (singular acinus).

label: positive regulation of tongue muscle cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of tongue muscle cell differentiation.

label: negative regulation of RNA biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of RNA biosynthetic process.

label: oligodendrocyte
Defs: A class of large neuroglial (macroglial) cells in the central nervous system. Form the insulating myelin sheath of axons in the central nervous system.

label: collection of organisms
Defs: A material entity that consists of two or more organisms, viruses, or viroids.

label: orbicular
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being perfectly circular.

label: pelvic appendage musculature
Defs: Any collection of muscles that is part of a pelvic appendage.

label: salt
Defs: A salt is an assembly of cations and anions.

label: bone growth
Defs: The increase in size or mass of a bone that contributes to the shaping of that bone.

label: interlobar duct
Defs: A duct that is located between lobes, within conspicuous, thick connective tissue septa that separate lobes. All interlobar ducts are excretory.

label: ovary septum
Defs: Septum that divides the ovary, the basal portion of a carpel or group of fused carpels, that encloses the ovule(s)[GO].

label: cardiac left atrium morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the left cardiac atrium is generated and organized.

label: regulation of heart contraction
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of heart contraction. Heart contraction is the process in which the heart decreases in volume in a characteristic way to propel blood through the body.

label: integrin alpha-X (mouse)
Defs: An integrin alpha-X that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: L-amino acid transport
Defs: The directed movement of L-enantiomer amino acids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: jaw region
Defs: A subdivision of the head that corresponds to the jaw skeleton, containing both soft tissue, skeleton and teeth (when present). The jaw region is divided into upper and lower regions.

label: heteroarene
Defs: A heterocyclic compound formally derived from an arene by replacement of one or more methine (-C=) and/or vinylene (-CH=CH-) groups by trivalent or divalent heteroatoms, respectively, in such a way as to maintain the continuous pi-electron system characteristic of aromatic systems and a number of out-of-plane pi-electrons corresponding to the Hueckel rule (4n+2).

label: ectomeninx
Defs: The outermost layer of the mesenchymal capsule that surrounds the developing brain, of mixed paraxial mesoderm and neural crest origin. The ectomeninx forms the dura mater (both inner layer and outer chondrogenic layer).

label: apoptotic process involved in endocardial cushion morphogenesis
Defs: Any apoptotic process that contributes to the shaping of an endocardial cushion. The endocardial cushion is a specialized region of mesenchymal cells that will give rise to the heart septa and valves.

label: negative regulation of neuromuscular junction development
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of neuromuscular junction development.

label: regulation of keratinocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of keratinocyte differentiation.

label: pericardium
Defs: The combination of pericardial sac (a double-walled sac containing the heart and the roots of the great vessels) plus fibrous pericardium.

label: table
Defs: A textual entity that contains a two-dimensional arrangement of texts repeated at regular intervals across a spatial range, such that the spatial relationships among the constituent texts expresses propositions

label: external encapsulating structure
Defs: A structure that lies outside the plasma membrane and surrounds the entire cell or cells. This does not include the periplasmic space.

label: positive regulation of lymphocyte chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of lymphocyte chemotaxis.

label: negative regulation of peptide secretion
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of peptide secretion.

label: glucan biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of glucans, polysaccharides consisting only of glucose residues.

label: pronotal disc
Defs: The medial region of the pronotum.

label: hourglass-shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape that inheres in the bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s nearly) symmetric shape wide at its ends and narrow in the middle, resembling the figure of number 8.

label: T cell differentiation involved in immune response
Defs: The process in which an antigenically naive T cell acquires the specialized features of an effector, regulatory, or memory T cell as part of an immune response. Effector T cells include cells which provide T cell help or exhibit cytotoxicity towards other cells.

label: neural retina development
Defs: The progression of the neural retina over time from its initial formation to the mature structure. The neural retina is the part of the retina that contains neurons and photoreceptor cells.

label: cytokine production involved in inflammatory response
Defs: The synthesis or release of a cytokine following a inflammatory stimulus as part of an inflammatory response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label: glutamate secretion
Defs: The controlled release of glutamate by a cell. The glutamate is the most abundant excitatory neurotransmitter in the nervous system.

label: medially rotated
Defs: A rotation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of being rotated towards the middle of an organism.

label: neurecto-epithelial cell
Defs: Epithelial cells derived from neural plate and neural crest.

label: mesentery of stomach
Defs: The portion of the primitive mesentery that encloses the stomach; from its dorsal sheet, the greater omentum develops, and from its ventral sheet, the lesser omentum.

label: segmental
Defs: Affecting a segment or segments.

label: negative regulation of secondary metabolite biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of secondary metabolite biosynthetic process.

label: increased combustibility
Defs: An increase in combustibility.

label: catalytic activity
Defs: Catalysis of a biochemical reaction at physiological temperatures. In biologically catalyzed reactions, the reactants are known as substrates, and the catalysts are naturally occurring macromolecular substances known as enzymes. Enzymes possess specific binding sites for substrates, and are usually composed wholly or largely of protein, but RNA that has catalytic activity (ribozyme) is often also regarded as enzymatic.

label: aromatic compound catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of aromatic compounds, any substance containing an aromatic carbon ring.

label: type B pancreatic cell
Defs: A cell that secretes insulin and is located towards the center of the islets of Langerhans.

label: receptor-type tyrosine-protein phosphatase C isoform CD45RABC
Defs: A receptor-type tyrosine-protein phosphatase C that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P08575-3 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: dark magenta
Defs: A color consisting of magenta with low brightness.

label: actin filament-based movement
Defs: Movement of organelles or other particles along actin filaments, or sliding of actin filaments past each other, mediated by motor proteins.

label: cell migration involved in coronary angiogenesis
Defs: The orderly movement of a cell from one site to another that will contribute to the formation of new blood vessels in the heart from pre-existing blood vessels.

label: female meiosis chromosome segregation
Defs: The cell cycle process in which genetic material, in the form of chromosomes, is organized and then physically separated and apportioned to two or more sets during the meiotic cell cycle in a female.

label: extraembryonic membrane
Defs: Intrinsic membrane that arises from embryonic germ layers and grow to surround the developing embryo.

label: protein localization
Defs: Any process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a specific location.

label: regulation of collagen biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of collagen, any of a group of fibrous proteins of very high tensile strength that form the main component of connective tissue in animals.

label: negative regulation of neural crest formation
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of neural crest formation. Neural crest formation is the formation of the specialized region of ectoderm between the neural ectoderm (neural plate) and non-neural ectoderm. The neural crest gives rise to the neural crest cells that migrate away from this region as neural tube formation procedes.

label: positive regulation of lung ciliated cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of lung ciliated cell differentiation.

label: bilirubin transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of bilirubin from one side of a membrane to the other. Bilirubin is a linear tetrapyrrole produced in the reticuloendothelial system from biliverdin and transported to the liver as a complex with serum albumin. In the liver, bilirubin is converted to bilirubin bisglucuronide, which is excreted in the bile.

label: regulation of lymphocyte activation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of lymphocyte activation.

label: increased distribution
Defs: A distribution which is relatively high.

label: regulation of cell morphogenesis involved in differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell morphogenesis contributing to cell differentiation. Cell morphogenesis involved in differentiation is the change in form (cell shape and size) that occurs when relatively unspecialized cells acquire specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize the cells, tissues, or organs of the mature organism or some other relatively stable phase of the organism\'s life history.

label: branching morphogenesis of a nerve
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of branches in a nerve are generated and organized. This term refers to an anatomical structure (nerve) not a cell (neuron).

label: epidermal cell division
Defs: Any process resulting in the physical partitioning and separation of an epidermal cell, any of the cells making up the epidermis, into daughter cells.

label: regulation of plasma membrane organization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of plasma membrane organization.

label: runt-related transcription factor 1 (mouse)
Defs: A runt-related transcription factor 1 that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: peritoneum
Defs: A serous membrane that lines the peritoneal cavity[VHOG,modified].

label: migratory neural crest cell
Defs: A cell derived from the specialized ectoderm flanking each side of the embryonic neural plate, which after the closure of the neural tube, forms masses of cells that migrate out from the dorsal aspect of the neural tube to spread throughout the body.

label: membrane organ
Defs: Nonparenchymatous organ that primarily consists of dense connective tissue organized into a sheet which interconnects two or more organs, separates two or more body spaces from one another, or surrounds an organ or body part. Examples: interosseous membrane of forearm, obturator membrane, tympanic membrane, fibrous pericardium, fascia lata, dura mater. [FMA].

label: CD34-positive, CD38-negative hematopoietic stem cell
Defs: CD133-positive hematopoietic stem cell is a hematopoietic stem cell that is CD34-positive, CD90-positive, and CD133-positive.

label: anal membrane endodermal component
Defs: An endoderm that is part of a anal region.

label: positive regulation of monocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of monocyte differentiation.

label: thoracic cavity connective tissue
Defs: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a thoracic cavity [Automatically generated definition].

label: bone cell development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a bone cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell.

label: nervous system
Defs: The nervous system is an organ system containing predominantly neuron and glial cells. In bilaterally symmetrical organism, it is arranged in a network of tree-like structures connected to a central body. The main functions of the nervous system are to regulate and control body functions, and to receive sensory input, process this information, and generate behavior [CUMBO].

label: cardiac glial cell development
Defs: The process aimed at the progression of a cardiac glial cell over time, from its formation to the fully functional mature cell.

label: aggregated
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being gathered or tending to gather into a mass or whole.

label: ocular adnexa
Defs: The parts of the orbital region that are outside of the the eyeball, including the lacrimal apparatus, the extraocular muscles and the eyelids, eyelashes, eyebrows and the conjunctiva.

label: increased angle to
Defs: An angle which is relatively high.

label: regulation of glutamate metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of glutamate metabolic process.

label: Kit-negative, Ly-76 high polychromatophilic erythroblast
Defs: A polychromatophilic erythroblast that is Lyg 76-high and is Kit-negative.

label: baculum
Defs: The sclerite of the paraproct that is elongated.

label: endothelium of capillary
Defs: An endothelium that is part of a capillary [Automatically generated definition].

label: multi cell part structure
Defs: A structure consisting of multiple cell components but which is not itself a cell and does not have (complete) cells as a part.

label: negative regulation of glucose transmembrane transport
Defs: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of glucose transport across a membrane. Glucose transport is the directed movement of the hexose monosaccharide glucose into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: meningeal cluster
Defs: The collection of all meningeal layers that line a central nervous system.

label: osteoclast development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a osteoclast from its formation to the mature structure. Cell development does not include the steps involved in committing a cell to a specific fate. An osteoclast is a specialized phagocytic cell associated with the absorption and removal of the mineralized matrix of bone tissue.

label: anterior surface
Defs: Anatomical surface that is located on the anterior side of the body or body part.

label: obsolete radiation effective dose
Defs: OBSOLETE A radiation exposure quality inhering in an organ by virtue of the multiplication of an equivalent dose to that organ multiplied by the tissue weighting factor for that organ.

label: aorta smooth muscle tissue morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the structure of the smooth muscle tissue surrounding the aorta is generated and organized. An aorta is an artery that carries blood from the heart to other parts of the body.

label: dicarboxylic acid metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving dicarboxylic acids, any organic acid containing two carboxyl (COOH) groups or anions (COO-).

label: decreased height
Defs: A height which is relatively low.

label: normal fluorescence
Defs: A fluorescence which is relatively normal or average.

label: regulation of neurotransmitter levels
Defs: Any process that modulates levels of neurotransmitter.

label: torsioned
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being twisted or turned.

label: viscosity
Defs: A physical quality of a fluid inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to internal resistance to flow.

label: keratinized epithelial cell of the anal canal
Defs: An epithelial cell of the anal canal that is keratinized. This cell type is found towards the lower, rectal end of the anal canal.

label: Saccharomyces cerevisiae mating type
Defs: A S. cerevisiae mating type.

label: organelle disassembly
Defs: The disaggregation of an organelle into its constituent components.

label: axial skeleton plus cranial skeleton
Defs: Subdivision of skeleton which consists of cranial skeleton, set of all vertebrae, set of all ribs and sternum[FMA, modified].

label: oogonial cell
Defs: An undifferentiated germ cell that proliferates rapidly and gives rise to oocytes.

label: diencephalon dura mater
Defs: A dura mater that is part of a diencephalon [Automatically generated definition].

label: cellular amino acid biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of amino acids, organic acids containing one or more amino substituents.

label: albedo
Defs: A reflective quality restricted to a particular wavelength.

label: submucosa of colon
Defs: A submucosa that is part of a colon [Automatically generated definition].

label: medial region
Defs: Anatomical region medially located on the body or body part.

label: negative regulation of gastric acid secretion
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate frequency or extent of gastric secretion. Gastric secretion is the regulated release of gastric acid (hydrochloric acid) by parietal or oxyntic cells during digestion.

label: abdominal sternite VII-gonocoxa VIII conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect abdomen that joins the abdominal sternite VIII and the gonocoxa VIII.

label: embryonic heart tube development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the embryonic heart tube over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The heart tube forms as the heart rudiment from the heart field.

label: biological regulation
Defs: Any process that modulates a measurable attribute of any biological process, quality or function.

label: horizontal pyramidal morphology
Defs: A pyramidal family morphology that inheres in neurons which have an apical tree which is oriented parallel to the pia.

label: epithelial cell proliferation
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of epithelial cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population. Epithelial cells make up the epithelium, the covering of internal and external surfaces of the body, including the lining of vessels and other small cavities. It consists of cells joined by small amounts of cementing substances.

label: anaerobic (for occurrence)
Defs: A sensitivity of a process inhering in a biological process by virtue of the process unfolding in a location without oxygen.

label: insect adult head
Defs: Head of the adult organism.

label: fibroblast of dense regular elastic tissue
Defs: A fibroblast that is part of the dense regular elastic tissue.

label: midbrain-hindbrain boundary initiation
Defs: The regionalization process that gives rise to the midbrain-hindbrain boundary. The midbrain-hindbrain domain of the embryonic brain is comprised of the mesencephalic vesicle and the first rhombencephalic vesicle at early somitogenesis stages. An organizing center at the boundary patterns the midbrain and hindbrain primordia of the neural plate.

label: acetylcholine transport
Defs: The directed movement of acetylcholine into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Acetylcholine is an acetic acid ester of the organic base choline and functions as a neurotransmitter, released at the synapses of parasympathetic nerves and at neuromuscular junctions.

label: nulliparous
Defs: A viviparous organism having never given birth.

label: protein secretion
Defs: The controlled release of proteins from a cell.

label: stomatodeum gland
Defs: A gland that is part of a stomodeum.

label: artery wall
Defs: An anatomical wall that is part of an artery [Automatically generated definition].

label: carbohydrate biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of carbohydrates, any of a group of organic compounds based of the general formula Cx(H2O)y.

label: integral component of vacuolar membrane
Defs: The component of the vacuolar membrane consisting of gene products and protein complexes that have some part that penetrates at least one leaflet of the membrane bilayer. May also refer to the state of being buried in the bilayer with no exposure outside the bilayer.

label: gastric gland
Defs: The branched tubular glands found in the mucosa of the fundus and body of the stomach which contain parietal cells that secrete hydrochloric acid and zymogenic cells that produce pepsin.

label: increased fertility
Defs: A fertility which is relatively high.

label: regulation of protein localization to cilium
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to cilium.

label: mesenchymal cell
Defs: A non-polarised cell precursor cell that is part of some mesenchyme, is associated with the cell matrix but is not connected to other cells and is capable of migration.

label: epithelial cell proliferation involved in lung morphogenesis
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of epithelial cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population that contributes to the shaping of the lung.

label: positive regulation of myeloid progenitor cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of myeloid progenitor cell differentiation.

label: distended
Defs: A size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being abnormally expanded or increased in size.

label: bipartite
Defs: A multipartite quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being divided into two parts.

label: neutrophil apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in a neutrophil, any of the immature or mature forms of a granular leukocyte that in its mature form has a nucleus with three to five lobes connected by slender threads of chromatin, and cytoplasm containing fine inconspicuous granules and stainable by neutral dyes.

label: embryonic tissue
Defs: A portion of tissue that is part of an embryo.

label: cardiopharyngeal field
Defs: An region of the mesoderm that includes anterior lateral mesoderm of the first heart field plus contiguous pharyngeal mesoderm that gives rise to second-heart-field-derived regions of the heart and branchiomeric muscles.

label: muscarinic agonist
Defs: Any drug that binds to and activates a muscarinic cholinergic receptor.

label: acetate ester metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving an acetate ester, any carboxylic ester where the carboxylic acid component is acetic acid.

label: retinal cell
Defs: Any cell in the retina, the innermost layer or coating at the back of the eyeball, which is sensitive to light and in which the optic nerve terminates.

label: insulin catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of insulin.

label: muscle layer of large intestine
Defs: A muscle layer that is part of a large intestine.

label: circumference
Defs: An 1-D extent quality which is equal to the length of the closed curve of a circle.

label: muscle layer of duodenum
Defs: A muscular coat that is part of a duodenum.

label: regulation of somitogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of somitogenesis.

label: regulation of neurotransmitter secretion
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of a neurotransmitter from a cell.

label: retina vasculature development in camera-type eye
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the vasculature of the retina over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: ribosome disassembly
Defs: The disaggregation of a ribosome into its constituent components; includes the dissociation of ribosomal subunits.

label: osteoid
Defs: Bone tissue that is an unmineralized bone matrix deposited by osteoblasts prior to the mineralization of bone tissue.

label: future hindbrain meninx
Defs: A multi-tissue structure that has the potential to develop into a meninx of hindbrain.

label: acetic acid
Defs: A simple monocarboxylic acid containing two carbons.

label: translational termination
Defs: The process resulting in the release of a polypeptide chain from the ribosome, usually in response to a termination codon (UAA, UAG, or UGA in the universal genetic code).

label: occurrent
Defs: An entity that has temporal parts and that happens, unfolds or develops through time.

label: basal metacoxal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that encircles the metacoxa and connects it to the ventral and lateral regions of the metathorax.

label: positive regulation of chromosome segregation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of chromosome segregation, the process in which genetic material, in the form of chromosomes, is organized and then physically separated and apportioned to two or more sets.

label: post-transcriptional regulation of gene expression
