Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of gene expression after the production of an RNA transcript.

label: lower respiratory tract epithelium
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a lower respiratory tract [Automatically generated definition].

label: skin development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the skin over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The skin is the external membranous integument of an animal. In vertebrates the skin generally consists of two layers, an outer nonsensitive and nonvascular epidermis (cuticle or skarfskin) composed of cells which are constantly growing and multiplying in the deeper, and being thrown off in the superficial layers, as well as an inner vascular dermis (cutis, corium or true skin) composed mostly of connective tissue.

label: endodermal-mesodermal cell signaling

label: cell morphogenesis involved in neuron differentiation

label: positive regulation of bile acid metabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of bile acid metabolic process.

label: anterior tentorio-scapal muscle

label: positive regulation of apoptotic process

label: integument

label: peritoneal fluid

label: appendage morphogenesis

label: T-cell surface glycoprotein CD8 alpha chain (mouse)

label: cytoskeleton

The cytoskeleton includes intermediate filaments, microfilaments, microtubules, the microtrabecular lattice, and other structures characterized by a polymeric filamentous nature and long-range order within the cell. The various elements of the cytoskeleton not only serve in the maintenance of cellular shape but also have roles in other cellular functions, including cellular movement, cell division, endocytosis, and movement of organelles.

label: positive regulation of epidermal cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of epidermal cell differentiation.

label: heart process
Defs: A circulatory system process carried out by the heart. The heart is a hollow, muscular organ, which, by contracting rhythmically, keeps up the circulation of the blood. The heart is a hollow, muscular organ, which, by contracting rhythmically, keeps up the circulation of the blood.

label: cardiac neural crest cell differentiation involved in heart development

Cardiac neural crest cells are specialized cells that migrate toward the heart from the third, fourth and sixth pharyngeal arches.

label: normal elevation

label: negative regulation of extracellular exosome assembly

label: Schwann cell differentiation

label: aortico-pulmonary spiral septum
Defs: The spiral septum that separates the truncus arteriosus into a ventral pulmonary trunk and the dorsal aorta[MP]. The aorticopulmonary septum is developmentally formed from neural crest, specifically the cardiac neural crest, and actively separates the aorta and pulmonary arteries and fuses with the interventricular septum within the heart during development. The actual mechanism of septation of the outflow tract is poorly understood, but is recognized as a dynamic process with contributions from contractile, hemodynamic, and extracellular matrix interactions.

label: duodenal gland

label: contractile cell

label: intercostal nerve
Defs: The intercostal nerves are the anterior divisions (rami anteriores; ventral divisions) of the thoracic spinal nerves from T1 to T11. Each nerve is connected with the adjoining ganglion of the sympathetic trunk by a gray and a white ramus communicans. The intercostal nerves are distributed chiefly to the thoracic pleura and abdominal peritoneum and differ from the anterior divisions of the other spinal nerves in that each pursues an independent course without plexus formation. The first two nerves supply fibers to the upper limb in addition to their thoracic branches; the next four are limited in their distribution to the parietes of the thorax; the lower five supply the parietes of the thorax and abdomen. The 7th intercostal nerve terminates at the xyphoid process, at the lower end of the sternum. The 10th intercostal nerve terminates at the umbilicus. The twelfth thoracic is distributed to the abdominal wall and groin. [WP,unvetted].

label: mesentery

Examples: greater omentum, broad ligament of uterus, sigmoid mesocolon.

label: fibrinogen binding

label: somatic sensory system

label: rhythmic process

label: musculature of face

label: report

A report is the output of a documenting process and has the objective to be consumed by a specific audience. Topic of the report is on something that has completed. A report is not a single figure. Examples of reports are journal article, patent application, grant progress report, case report (not patient record).

label: abdominal sternite V

label: segmentation

label: bone remodeling

The process of bone remodeling takes place in the adult skeleton at discrete foci. The process ensures the mechanical integrity of the skeleton throughout life and plays an important role in calcium homeostasis. An imbalance in the regulation of bone resorption and bone formation results in many of the metabolic bone diseases, such as osteoporosis.

label: positive regulation of oocyte maturation

label: trigeminal nerve formation
Defs: The process that gives rise to the trigeminal nerve. This process pertains to the initial formation of a structure from unspecified parts. The trigeminal nerve is composed of three large branches. They are the ophthalmic (V1, sensory), maxillary (V2, sensory) and mandibular (V3, motor and sensory) branches. The sensory ophthalmic branch travels through the superior orbital fissure and passes through the orbit to reach the skin of the forehead and top of the head. The maxillary nerve contains sensory branches that reach the pterygopalatine fossa via the inferior orbital fissure (face, cheek and upper teeth) and pterygopalatine canal (soft and hard palate, nasal cavity and pharynx). The motor part of the mandibular branch is distributed to the muscles of mastication, the mylohyoid muscle and the anterior belly of the digastric. The mandibular nerve also innervates the tensor veli palatini and tensor tympani muscles. The sensory part of the mandibular nerve is composed of branches that carry general sensory information from the mucous membranes of the mouth and cheek, anterior two-thirds of the tongue, lower teeth, skin of the lower jaw, side of the head and scalp and meninges of the anterior and middle cranial fossae.

label: salt gland

Defs: A time quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the time it elapses for the bearer to respond to a stimulus.

label: specificity to
Defs: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits the ability of a probe to react precisely with a specific target molecule.

label: regulation of embryonic pattern specification
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of embryonic pattern specification.

label: fertility
Defs: A reproductive quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s initiating, sustaining, or supporting reproduction.

label: transferase complex
Defs: A protein complex capable of catalyzing the transfer of a group, e.g. a methyl group, glycosyl group, acyl group, phosphorus-containing, or other groups, from one compound (generally regarded as the donor) to another compound (generally regarded as the acceptor).

label: organic oxo compound
Defs: Organic compounds containing an oxygen atom, =O, doubly bonded to carbon or another element.

label: positive regulation of cardiac muscle myoblast proliferation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle myoblast proliferation.

label: negative regulation of developmental growth
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of developmental growth.

label: polysaccharide transport
Defs: The directed movement of polysaccharides into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. A polysaccharide is a polymer of many (typically more than 10) monosaccharide residues linked glycosidically.

label: monocarboxylic acid metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving monocarboxylic acids, any organic acid containing one carboxyl (COOH) group or anion (COO-).

label: actin filament-based transport
Defs: The transport of organelles or other particles from one location in the cell to another along actin filaments.

label: negative regulation of cytokine production involved in inflammatory response
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cytokine production involved in inflammatory response.

label: gland of integumental system
Defs: A gland that is part of a integumental system [Automatically generated definition].

label: epithelial cell of exocrine pancreas
Defs: An epithelial cell of the exocrine pancreas.

label: negative regulation of erythrocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of erythrocyte differentiation.

label: mesoderm formation
Defs: The process that gives rise to the mesoderm. This process pertains to the initial formation of the structure from unspecified parts.

label: regulation of apoptotic process involved in morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of apoptotic process involved in morphogenesis.

label: peripheral sensory neuron
Defs: Peripheral sensory neuron.

label: ovariectomized female
Defs: A female fertility quality inhering in a female by virtue of the bearer\'s not being capable of reproducing because of surgical removal of ovaries.

label: small molecule metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving small molecules, any low molecular weight, monomeric, non-encoded molecule.

label: respiratory system blood vessel smooth muscle
Defs: A blood vessel smooth muscle that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

label: radiation quality
Defs: A quality of radiation that reflects the fluence spectrum of charged and neutral particles within the material or medium where dose is being deposited.

label: pharyngeal arch mesenchyme from neural crest
Defs: Mesenchyme that develops_from a neural crest and is part of a entire pharyngeal arch associated mesenchyme.

label: duration of temperature
Defs: A duration quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s duration of exhibition of thermal energy.

label: organonitrogen compound metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving organonitrogen compound.

label: mucopolysaccharide
Defs: Any of the group of polysaccharides composed of alternating units from uronic acids and glycosamines, and commonly partially esterified with sulfuric acid.

label: sensillum trichodeum
Defs: Hairlike seta that is long.

label: obsolete dependent continuant
Defs: A continuant  that is either dependent on one or other independent continuant  bearers or inheres in or is borne by other entities.

label: central region
Defs: Anatomical region centrally located on the body or body part.

label: neuron projection organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a prolongation or process extending from a neuron, e.g. an axon, or a dendrite.

label: back blood vessel
Defs: A blood vessel that is part of a back [Automatically generated definition].

label: ciliary body
Defs: The thickened portion of the vascular tunic, which lies between the choroid and the iris, composed of ciliary muscle and ciliary processes.

label: electric charge
Defs: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the overall electric charge of the molecule, which is due to a comparison between the total number of electrons and the total number of protons.

label: circling direction
Defs: A directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s direction approximating the shape of a circle.

label: premigratory neural crest cell
Defs: Cell that is part of the neural crest region of the neuroepithelium, prior to migration. Note that not all premigratory neural crest cells may become migratory neural crest cells.

label: abutting
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer touching another entity along a border or with a projecting part.

label: area density
Defs: A density quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of some influence exerted by the bearer\'s mass on a given area.

label: gall bladder glandular cell
Defs: Glandular cell of gall bladder epithelium.

label: positive regulation of smooth muscle cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of smooth muscle cell apoptotic process.

label: pyloric antrum
Defs: The area at the bottom of the stomach on the caudal side of the pyloric canal that contains gastrin-producing G cells, which stimulate acid production, and the luminal pH-sensitive population of somatostatin-producing D cells.

label: Schwann cell proliferation
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of Schwann cells, resulting in the expansion of their population. Schwann cells are a type of glial cell in the peripheral nervous system.

label: negative regulation of molecular function
Defs: Any process that stops or reduces the rate or extent of a molecular function, an elemental biological activity occurring at the molecular level, such as catalysis or binding.

label: regulation of collagen binding
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of collagen binding.

label: type B pancreatic cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in a type B pancreatic cell, a cell located towards center of the islets of Langerhans that secretes insulin.

label: cuticular protrusion
Defs: The region of the cuticle that corresponds to a convex surface.

label: resistance to
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to resist to a stimulus.

label: cardiac ventricle formation
Defs: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of a cardiac ventricle from unspecified parts. A cardiac ventricle receives blood from a cardiac atrium and pumps it out of the heart.

label: optic choroid fibroblast
Defs: Any fibroblast that is part of a optic choroid.

label: gastrointestinal system lamina propria
Defs: A lamina propria that is part of a gastrointestinal system.

label: establishment or maintenance of cell polarity
Defs: Any cellular process that results in the specification, formation or maintenance of anisotropic intracellular organization or cell growth patterns.

label: cibarium
Defs: The conjunctiva that is part of the head capsule and is continuous with the epipharynx and the hypopharynx.

label: marrow fibroblast
Defs: A fibroblast in the bone marrow.

label: negative regulation of muscle adaptation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of muscle adaptation.

label: porous
Defs: A porosity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being capable of admitting the passage of gas or liquid through pores or interstices.

label: organelle envelope
Defs: A double membrane structure enclosing an organelle, including two lipid bilayers and the region between them. In some cases, an organelle envelope may have more than two membranes.

label: central nervous system cell part cluster
Defs: A multi cell part structure that is part of a central nervous system.

label: glial cell activation
Defs: A change in morphology and behavior of a glial cell resulting from exposure to a cytokine, chemokine, cellular ligand, or soluble factor.

label: intralobular bile duct
Defs: The tubules located between the bile canaliculi and interlobular bile ducts near the outer edge of a classic liver lobule.

label: pancreatic D cell
Defs: A D cell located in the pancreas. Peripherally placed within the islets like type A cells; contains somatostatin.

label: fibroblast of lung
Defs: A fibroblast that is part of lung.

label: pseudohermaphrodite
Defs: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population by virtue of having internal reproductive organs of one sex and external sexual characteristics of the other sex.

label: regulation of neuroblast migration
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of neuroblast migration.

label: lens vesicle cavity
Defs: An anatomical cavity that is part of a lens vesicle.

label: gastrin secreting cell
Defs: A peptide hormone secreting cell that secretes gastrin.

label: notochord
Defs: A flexible rod-shaped body found in embryos of all chordates. It is composed of cells derived from the mesoderm and defines the primitive axis of the embryo. In some chordates, it persists throughout life as the main axial support of the body, while in most vertebrates it becomes the nucleus pulposus of the intervertebral disc. The notochord is found ventral to the neural tube.

label: response to peptide
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a peptide stimulus.

label: regulation of bile acid biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of bile acids.

label: positive regulation of axonogenesis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of axonogenesis.

label: heart contraction
Defs: The multicellular organismal process in which the heart decreases in volume in a characteristic way to propel blood through the body.

label: response to light stimulus
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a light stimulus, electromagnetic radiation of wavelengths classified as infrared, visible or ultraviolet light.

label: protein polymerization
Defs: The process of creating protein polymers, compounds composed of a large number of component monomers; polymeric proteins may be made up of different or identical monomers. Polymerization occurs by the addition of extra monomers to an existing poly- or oligomeric protein.

label: ganglion formation
Defs: The process that gives rise to ganglion. This process pertains to the initial formation of a structure from unspecified parts.

label: negative regulation of lymphocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of lymphocyte differentiation.

label: regulation of myeloid cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of myeloid cell apoptotic process.

label: male-specific
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being present in males and absent from females in members of the same species.

label: decreased position
Defs: A positional which is relatively low.

label: chromatin
Defs: The ordered and organized complex of DNA, protein, and sometimes RNA, that forms the chromosome.

label: vertical to
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located at a right angle relative to another entity and to the horizon.

label: epithelium of intestinal villus
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a intestinal villus.

label: transcription factor NF-kappa-B subunit
Defs: A protein with a core domain composition consisting of a Rel homology domain (RHD) (Pfam:PF00554), an IPT/TIG domain (Pfam:PF01833), six copies of the Ankyrin repeat (Pfam:PF00023), a Death domain (Pfam:PF00531) and a C-terminal PEST region.

label: ochre
Defs: A moderate yellow-orange to orange color.

label: B-lymphocyte antigen CD19 (mouse)
Defs: A CD19 molecule that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: cartilage element of chondrocranium
Defs: A cartilage element of chondrocranium. Example: neurocranial trabecula.

label: terminal
Defs: A position quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s forming the end of another entity.

label: cuticle of palpifer
Defs: The sclerite of the insect maxilla that is attached to the cuticle of stipes by the stipito-palpiferal conjunctiva and to the cuticle of maxillary palpus by the palpifero-palpal conjunctiva.

label: endopolyploid
Defs: A polyploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s chromosome number being increased by endomitosis and for which the degree of ploidy is proportional to the number of times that endomitosis has taken place.

label: regulation of melanosome organization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of melanosome organization.

label: mesometrium
Defs: A mesentery that is part of a uterus [Automatically generated definition].

label: protein kinase binding
Defs: Binding to a protein kinase, any enzyme that catalyzes the transfer of a phosphate group, usually from ATP, to a protein substrate.

label: pigment granule localization
Defs: Any process in which a pigment granule is transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location within the cell.

label: regulation of gene expression
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of gene expression. Gene expression is the process in which a gene\'s coding sequence is converted into a mature gene product (protein or RNA).

label: epidermis suprabasal layer
Defs: Any layer of the epidermis that is superior to the stratum basale.

label: binucleate
Defs: A nucleate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having two nuclei.

label: positive regulation of mitotic sister chromatid segregation
Defs: Any process that starts or increases the frequency, rate or extent of sister chromatid segregation during mitosis.

label: myofibril
Defs: The contractile element of skeletal and cardiac muscle; a long, highly organized bundle of actin, myosin, and other proteins that contracts by a sliding filament mechanism.

label: normal pigmentation
Defs: A degree of pigmentation quality which is relatively normal or average

label: negative regulation of myeloid leukocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of myeloid leukocyte differentiation.

label: cuticle of glossa
Defs: The cuticle of the appendage of the labium, and part of the ligula, that is attached to the prementum by the premental-glossal conjunctiva.

label: transport
Defs: The directed movement of substances (such as macromolecules, small molecules, ions) or cellular components (such as complexes and organelles) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, or within a multicellular organism by means of some agent such as a transporter or a transporter complex, a pore or a motor protein.

label: bone marrow cell
Defs: A cell found in the bone marrow. This can include fibroblasts, macrophages, adipocytes, osteoblasts, osteoclasts, endothelial cells and hematopoietic cells.

label: author role
Defs: A role inhering in a person or organization that is realized when the bearer participates in the work which is the basis of the document, in the writing of the document, and signs it with their name.

label: smooth muscle cell of trachea
Defs: A smooth muscle cell of the trachea.

label: female gamete generation
Defs: Generation of the female gamete; specialised haploid cells produced by meiosis and along with a male gamete takes part in sexual reproduction.

label: calcified
Defs: A composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being encrusted or impregnated with calcium carbonate (CHEBI:3311).

label: lamina propria of small intestine
Defs: Lamina propria that is part_of the small intestine.

label: cell differentiation involved in embryonic placenta development
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of the embryonic placenta.

label: sound wavelength
Defs: A physical quality which is equal to the quotient of the speed of a sound wave divided by its wavelength.

label: negative regulation of protein secretion
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the controlled release of a protein from a cell.

label: longitudinal orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed along the longitudinal or anterior-posterior axis.

label: 2nd arch mesenchyme from neural crest
Defs: Mesenchyme that develops_from a neural crest and is part of a 2nd arch mesenchyme.

label: integumental system
Defs: Connected anatomical system that forms a barrier between an animal and its environment. In vertebrates, the integumental system consists of the epidermis, dermis plus associated glands and adnexa such as hair and scales. In invertebrates, the integumental system may include cuticle.

label: spinal cord development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the spinal cord over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The spinal cord primarily conducts sensory and motor nerve impulses between the brain and the peripheral nervous tissues.

label: extra or missing processual parts
Defs: A quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s processual parts.

label: mitotic nuclear membrane disassembly
Defs: The mitotic cell cycle process in which the controlled partial or complete breakdown of the nuclear membranes during occurs during mitosis.

label: buccal mucosa cell
Defs: An endothelial cell that lines the oral cavitiy including the mucosa of the gums, the palate, the lip, and the cheek.

label: mesothelial cell of dura mater
Defs: A mesothelial cell that is part of the dura mater.

label: female reproductive organ
Defs: A female organ involved in reproduction.

label: glucose catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of glucose, the aldohexose gluco-hexose.

label: positive regulation of artery morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of artery morphogenesis.

label: muscle structure
Defs: Muscle structures are contractile cells, tissues or organs that are found in multicellular organisms[GO].

label: nucleic acid
Defs: A macromolecule made up of nucleotide units and hydrolysable into certain pyrimidine or purine bases (usually adenine, cytosine, guanine, thymine, uracil), D-ribose or 2-deoxy-D-ribose and phosphoric acid.

label: upper back skin
Defs: A zone of skin that is part of a dorsal thoracic segment of trunk.

label: positive regulation of fat cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of fat cell apoptotic process.

label: somato-dendritic dopamine secretion
Defs: The regulated release of dopamine from the somatodendritic compartment (cell body or dendrites) of a neuron.

label: exocrine system development
Defs: Progression of the exocrine system over time, from its formation to a mature structure. The exocrine system is a system of hormones and glands, where the glands secrete straight to a target site via ducts or tubes. The human exocrine system includes the salivary glands, sweat glands and many glands of the digestive system.

label: positive regulation of bile acid biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of bile acids.

label: central nervous system morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structure of the central nervous system is generated and organized. The central nervous system is the core nervous system that serves an integrating and coordinating function. In vertebrates it consists of the brain and spinal cord. In those invertebrates with a central nervous system it typically consists of a brain, cerebral ganglia and a nerve cord.

label: regulation of macromolecule biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a macromolecule, any molecule of high relative molecular mass, the structure of which essentially comprises the multiple repetition of units derived, actually or conceptually, from molecules of low relative molecular mass.

label: dendrite morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of a dendrite are generated and organized.

label: decreased rate of occurrence
Defs: A rate of occurrence that is relatively low.

label: integral component of membrane
Defs: The component of a membrane consisting of the gene products and protein complexes having at least some part of their peptide sequence embedded in the hydrophobic region of the membrane.

label: Saccharomyces cerevisiae metabolite
Defs: Any  fungal metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in Baker\'s yeast (Saccharomyces cerevisiae).

label: immature Schwann cell
Defs: A glial cell that develops from a Schwann cell precursor. The immature Schwann cell is embedded among neurons (axons) with minimal extracellular spaces separating them from nerve cell membranes and has a basal lamina. Cells can survive without an axon present. Immature Schwann cell can be found communally ensheathing large groups of axons.

label: magnetism
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to exert an attractive or repulsive force on other entities.

label: myotube cell development
Defs: The process aimed at the progression of a myotube cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell. Myotubes are multinucleated cells that are formed when proliferating myoblasts exit the cell cycle, differentiate and fuse.

label: ossification involved in bone remodeling
Defs: The formation or growth of bone or of a bony substance, or the conversion of fibrous tissue or of cartilage into bone, involved in response to injury or other physical, physiological or environmental stress stimuli.

label: malphigian tube
Defs: The branching cuticular invagination that is located between the mid and hindgut.

label: measurement methods section
Defs: A methods section that describes details of data assessment methods (data measurement).

label: regulation of skeletal muscle cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of skeletal muscle cell proliferation.

label: acid
Defs: An acid is a molecular entity capable of donating a hydron (Bronsted acid) or capable of forming a covalent bond with an electron pair (Lewis acid).

label: epithelial cell morphogenesis involved in gastrulation
Defs: The change in form that occurs when an epithelial cell progresses from it initial formation to its mature state, contributing to the process of gastrulation.

label: epithelial cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in an epithelial cell.

label: bone cell
Defs: A connective tissue cell found in bone.

label: tryptamines
Defs: Tryptamine and its substitution derivatives.

label: anterograde axonal transport of neurotransmitter receptor complex
Defs: The directed movement of a neurotransmitter receptor complex along microtubules from the cell body toward the cell periphery in nerve cell axons.

label: positive regulation of dendrite development
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of dendrite development.

label: cell migration involved in gastrulation
Defs: The migration of individual cells within the blastocyst to help establish the multi-layered body plan of the organism (gastrulation). For example, the migration of cells from the surface to the interior of the embryo (ingression).

label: scalar measurement datum
Defs: A scalar measurement datum is a measurement datum that is composed of two parts, numerals and a unit label.

label: regulation of cholangiocyte apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cholangiocyte apoptotic process.

label: dendritic cell antigen processing and presentation
Defs: The process in which a dendritic cell expresses antigen (peptide or lipid) on its cell surface in association with an MHC protein complex.

label: lymphocyte differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized precursor cell acquires specialized features of a lymphocyte. A lymphocyte is a leukocyte commonly found in the blood and lymph that has the characteristics of a large nucleus, a neutral staining cytoplasm, and prominent heterochromatin.

label: proteinogenic amino acid
Defs: Any of the 23 alpha-amino acids that are precursors to proteins, and are incorporated into proteins during translation. The group includes the 20 amino acids encoded by the nuclear genes of eukaryotes together with selenocysteine, pyrrolysine, and N-formylmethionine. Apart from glycine, which is non-chiral, all have L configuration.

label: anterior limiting lamina of cornea
Defs: A transparent homogeneous acellular layer, 6 to 9 um thick, lying between the basal lamina of the outer layer of stratified epithelium and the substantia propria of the cornea; it is considered to be a basement membrane.

label: variability of color
Defs: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits color variation or change.

label: right vitelline vein
Defs: A vitelline vein that is in the right side of a multicellular organism.

label: air in respiratory system
Defs: Any portion of gas located in a part of the respiratory system that is composed primarily of air.

label: lamina propria
Defs: A thin layer of loose connective tissue which lies beneath the epithelium and together with the epithelium constitutes the mucosa[WP]. The lamina propria contains capillaries and a central lacteal (lymph vessel) in the small intestine, as well as lymphoid tissue. Lamina propria also contains glands with the ducts opening on to the mucosal epithelium, that secrete mucus and serous secretions.

label: simple squamous epithelium
Defs: Unilaminar epithelium which consists of a single layer of squamous cells. Examples: pulmonary alveolar epithelium, endothelium.[FMA].

label: vesicle fusion
Defs: Fusion of the membrane of a transport vesicle with its target membrane.

label: stellate pyramidal morphology
Defs: A pyramidal cell morphology that inheres in neurons which lack a tuft formation but extend to small radial distances forming a star-like shape.

label: His-Purkinje system development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the His-Purkinje system over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The His-Purkinje system receives signals from the AV node and is composed of the fibers that regulate cardiac muscle contraction in the ventricles.

label: document title
Defs: A textual entity that names a document

label: alignment
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s spatial positioning with respect to an additional entity.

label: signal transduction
Defs: The cellular process in which a signal is conveyed to trigger a change in the activity or state of a cell. Signal transduction begins with reception of a signal (e.g. a ligand binding to a receptor or receptor activation by a stimulus such as light), or for signal transduction in the absence of ligand, signal-withdrawal or the activity of a constitutively active receptor. Signal transduction ends with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. regulation of transcription or regulation of a metabolic process. Signal transduction covers signaling from receptors located on the surface of the cell and signaling via molecules located within the cell. For signaling between cells, signal transduction is restricted to events at and within the receiving cell.

label: pyramidal
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having triangular faces that meet at a common point and containing a polygonal shaped base.

label: cellular metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways by which individual cells transform chemical substances.

label: adipocyte of epicardial fat of left ventricle
Defs: A fat cell that is part of the epicardial fat of left ventricle.

label: genome announcement textual entity
Defs: A textual entity that describes the generation and public release of a novel, draft genome sequence.

label: centrally registered identifier registry
Defs: A CRID registry is a dataset of CRID records, each consisting of a CRID symbol and additional information which was recorded in the dataset through a assigning a centrally registered identifier process.

label: regulation of chromatin binding
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of chromatin binding. Chromatin binding is the selective interaction with chromatin, the network of fibers of DNA, protein, and sometimes RNA, that make up the chromosomes of the eukaryotic nucleus during interphase.

label: positive regulation of type B pancreatic cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of type B pancreatic cell proliferation.

label: future superior salivatory nucleus
Defs: A gray matter that has the potential to develop into a superior salivatory nucleus.

label: negative regulation of sarcomere organization
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of myofibril assembly by organization of muscle actomyosin into sarcomeres. The sarcomere is the repeating unit of a myofibril in a muscle cell, composed of an array of overlapping thick and thin filaments between two adjacent Z discs.

label: positive regulation of eye photoreceptor cell development
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of eye photoreceptor development.

label: phosphate(3-)
Defs: A phosphate ion that is the conjugate base of hydrogenphosphate.

label: semi-viable
Defs: A viability quality inhering in a population by virtue of some of it\'s members\' ability to survive.

label: rhythmic
Defs: A rhythm quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having rhythm.

label: brain morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the brain are generated and organized. The brain is one of the two components of the central nervous system and is the center of thought and emotion. It is responsible for the coordination and control of bodily activities and the interpretation of information from the senses (sight, hearing, smell, etc.).

label: negative regulation of protein localization
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of a protein localization.

label: cell-cell junction organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a cell-cell junction. A cell-cell junction is a specialized region of connection between two cells.

label: regulation of protein phosphorylation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of addition of phosphate groups into an amino acid in a protein.

label: carbohydrate derivative biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of carbohydrate derivative.

label: hindbrain venous system
Defs: A venous system that is part of a hindbrain.

label: alpha-(1,3)-fucosyltransferase
Defs: A protein that is a stand alone version of the Glycosyltransferase family 10 (fucosyltransferase) (Pfam:PF00852) domain. Proteins in this class may catalyze alpha-1,3 glycosidic linkages.

label: inorganic group
Defs: Any substituent group which does not contain carbon.

label: left side
Defs: The side of an organism that is left of the sagittal plane.

label: protogynous hermaphroditism
Defs: A protogynous quality whereby organisms start out as female and change to hermaphrodite at a later life stage.

label: lower jaw opening
Defs: An anatomical space that is part of a bone of lower jaw.

label: postmentum
Defs: The sclerite of the cuticle of labium that is cmposed of the submentum and the mentum, which are connected by the submental-mental conjunctiva

label: positive regulation of melanosome organization
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of melanosome organization.

label: blue
Defs: A color hue with low wavelength of that portion of the visible spectrum lying between green and indigo, evoked in the human observer by radiant energy with wavelengths of approximately 420 to 490 nanometers.

label: outflow tract aortic component
Defs: An outflow tract that is part of a aorta.

label: osmolality
Defs: A concentration quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s amount of osmoles of solute per kilogram of solvent.

label: heart morphogenesis
Defs: The developmental process in which the heart is generated and organized. The heart is a hollow, muscular organ, which, by contracting rhythmically, keeps up the circulation of the blood.

label: postoccipitopremental muscle
Defs: The cranio-labial muscle that is attached to the postoccipital phragma and  the prementum.

label: erect
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being upright in position or posture.

label: negative regulation of organelle assembly
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of organelle assembly.

label: forebrain neural plate
Defs: A neural plate that develops_from a future forebrain.

label: serous cell of epithelium of trachea
Defs: A serous secreting cell that is part of the epithelium of trachea.

label: pharyngeal system development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the pharyngeal system over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The pharyngeal system is a transient embryonic complex that is specific to vertebrates. It comprises the pharyngeal arches, bulges of tissues of mesoderm and neural crest derivation through which pass nerves and pharyngeal arch arteries. The arches are separated internally by pharyngeal pouches, evaginations of foregut endoderm, and externally by pharyngeal clefts, invaginations of surface ectoderm. The development of the system ends when the stucture it contributes to are forming: the thymus, thyroid, parathyroids, maxilla, mandible, aortic arch, cardiac outflow tract, external and middle ear.

label: negative regulation of chondrocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of chondrocyte differentiation.

label: PP cell
Defs: A cell that stores and secretes pancreatic polypeptide hormone.

label: sister chromatid segregation
Defs: The cell cycle process in which sister chromatids are organized and then physically separated and apportioned to two or more sets.

label: ovary
Defs: The gonad of a female organism which contains germ cells.

label: collagen type II trimer
Defs: A collagen homotrimer of alpha1(II) chains; type II collagen triple helices associate to form fibrils.

label: neural crest formation
Defs: The formation of the specialized region of ectoderm between the neural ectoderm (neural plate) and non-neural ectoderm. The neural crest gives rise to the neural crest cells that migrate away from this region as neural tube formation procedes.

label: uninflated
Defs: A structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being not filed with air.

label: positive regulation of translational initiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of translational initiation.

label: obtuse
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being roundish, a little inclining to be oblong.

label: cellular metal ion homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of metal ions at the level of a cell.

label: count
Defs: A measurement datum that is the output of counting.

label: appendage musculature
Defs: Any collection of muscles that is part of an appendage.

label: positive regulation of T cell mediated immunity
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of T cell mediated immunity.

label: extraembryonic epithelium
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a extraembryonic structure.

label: microtubule binding
Defs: Binding to a microtubule, a filament composed of tubulin monomers.

label: mesotibio-mesotarsal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that encircles the mesotarsus by joining the distal margin of the mesotibia and the proximal margin of the mesotarsus.

label: placental villous trophoblast
Defs: A trophoblast of placental villi.  These cells fuse to form synctial  trophoplast - the placental side of the interface between the placenta and maternal blood sinusoids in the decidua.

label: articular system
Defs: Anatomical system that consists of all the joints of the body.

label: somatic stem cell division
Defs: The self-renewing division of a somatic stem cell, a stem cell that can give rise to cell types of the body other than those of the germ-line.

label: gas in respiratory system
Defs: Any portion of gas located in a part of the respiratory system.

label: obsolete paternal
Defs: A parental quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of exhibiting the characteristic of a father.

label: serosa of uterine tube
Defs: A serous membrane that is part of a fallopian tube.

label: bone of pelvic complex
Defs: A bone that is part of a pelvic complex. Examples: pubis, ischium, fot phalanx, any tarsal bone, any bone of the pelvic fin or girdle.

label: positive regulation of neuromuscular junction development
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of neuromuscular junction development.

label: anchoring junction
Defs: A cell junction that mechanically attaches a cell (and its cytoskeleton) to neighboring cells or to the extracellular matrix.

label: organonitrogen heterocyclic compound
Defs: Any organonitrogen compound containing a cyclic component with nitrogen and at least one other element as ring member atoms.

label: adenomatous
Defs: A morphology quality inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting the morphological characteristics of a glandular epithelial cell.

label: regulation of myoblast differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of myoblast differentiation. A myoblast is a mononucleate cell type that, by fusion with other myoblasts, gives rise to the myotubes that eventually develop into skeletal muscle fibers.

label: negative regulation of retina development in camera-type eye
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of retina development in camera-type eye.

label: protein kinase inhibitor activity
Defs: Binds to and stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a protein kinase, an enzyme which phosphorylates a protein.

label: propagation velocity
Defs: The velocity of spatial propagation of a process. Examples include the velocity of propagation of an action potential along an axon.

label: immune effector process
Defs: Any process of the immune system that executes a component of an immune response. An effector immune process takes place after its activation.

label: anterograde axonal protein transport
Defs: The directed movement of proteins along microtubules from the cell body toward the cell periphery in nerve cell axons.

label: transferase activity, transferring phosphorus-containing groups
Defs: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphorus-containing group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).

label: lens vesicle
Defs: Portion of tissue that gives rise to the lens.

label: fibrinoid
Defs: A composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing fibrin.

label: food storage organ
Defs: An organ of the digestive tract that is capable of retaining and storing food.

label: negative regulation of vasculature development
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of vasculature development.

label: population of organisms
Defs: A collection of organisms, all of the same species, that live in the same place.

label: regulation of defense response
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a defense response.

label: positive regulation of cell proliferation involved in compound eye morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cell proliferation involved in compound eye morphogenesis.

label: cardiac right atrium morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the right cardiac atrium is generated and organized.

label: portal triad
Defs: A multi-organ-part structure that consists of three vessels of the portal lobule including the bile duct, a terminal branch of the hepatic artery and portal vein, and may also include a lymphatic vessel.

label: frontoepypharyngeal muscle
Defs: The cranio-labral muscle that is attached to the frons and the tormae.

label: alkaloid
Defs: Any of the naturally occurring, basic nitrogen compounds (mostly heterocyclic) occurring mostly in the plant kingdom, but also found in bacteria, fungi, and animals. By extension, certain neutral compounds biogenetically related to basic alkaloids are also classed as alkaloids. Amino acids, peptides, proteins, nucleotides, nucleic acids, amino sugars and antibiotics are not normally regarded as alkaloids. Compounds in which the nitrogen is  exocyclic (dopamine, mescaline, serotonin, etc.) are usually classed as amines rather than alkaloids.

label: ligament of larynx
Defs: A ligament that is part of a larynx and connexts the cartilages of the larynx.

label: negative regulation of collagen biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of collagen, any of a group of fibrous proteins of very high tensile strength that form the main component of connective tissue in animals.

label: neprilysin (mouse)
Defs: A neprilysin that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: salt transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of salt from one side of a membrane to the other.

label: gall bladder primordium
Defs: A sac-like cavity ventral to the liver, lying in the sub-mesodermal space and closed by a thin sheet of ectodermal cells, from which the future gall bladder develops.

label: negative regulation of keratinocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of keratinocyte differentiation.

label: substantia propria of sclera
Defs: A stroma that is part of a sclera.

label: positive regulation of catecholamine secretion
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of a catecholamine.

label: negative regulation of multicellular organism growth
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of growth of an organism to reach its usual body size.

label: parietal serous pericardium
Defs: Parietal serous membrane which is part of the pericardium and forms the outer layer of the pericardial sac.

label: table of abbreviations
Defs: A table where the constituent texts are abbreviations and their expansions

label: embryo development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an embryo from its formation until the end of its embryonic life stage. The end of the embryonic stage is organism-specific. For example, for mammals, the process would begin with zygote formation and end with birth. For insects, the process would begin at zygote formation and end with larval hatching. For plant zygotic embryos, this would be from zygote formation to the end of seed dormancy. For plant vegetative embryos, this would be from the initial determination of the cell or group of cells to form an embryo until the point when the embryo becomes independent of the parent plant.

label: negative regulation of cellular response to insulin stimulus
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cellular response to insulin stimulus.

label: postero-ventral margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the postero-ventral region of the body or body part.

label: auriculate
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a shape resembling an ear.

label: fibrous pericardium
Defs: Membrane organ which is attached to the pericardial sac proper and the central tendon of diaphragm and is continuous with the pretracheal fascia.[FMA].

label: establishment of T cell polarity
Defs: The directed orientation of T cell signaling molecules and associated membrane rafts towards a chemokine gradient or a contact point with antigen presenting cell.

label: positive regulation of peptide secretion
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of peptide secretion.

label: cellular amino acid catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of amino acids, organic acids containing one or more amino substituents.

label: motor neuron migration
Defs: The orderly movement of a motor neuron from one site to another. A motor neuron is an efferent neuron that passes from the central nervous system or a ganglion toward or to a muscle and conducts an impulse that causes movement.

label: regulation of microtubule-based movement
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of microtubule-based movement, the movement of organelles, other microtubules and other particles along microtubules, mediated by motor proteins.

label: hypomeron
Defs: The lateral region of the pronotum that is deflexed and laterally limited by the lateral pronotal carina.

label: pelvis connective tissue
Defs: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a pelvis [Automatically generated definition].

label: multinuclear osteoclast differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized monocyte acquires the specialized features of a multinuclear osteoclast. An osteoclast is a specialized phagocytic cell associated with the absorption and removal of the mineralized matrix of bone tissue.

label: central nervous system
Defs: The central nervous system is the core nervous system that serves an integrating and coordinating function. In vertebrates it consists of the neural tube derivatives: the brain and spinal cord. In invertebrates it includes central ganglia plus nerve cord.

label: sulfur compound binding
Defs: Binding to a sulfur compound.

label: regulation of glutamate secretion
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the controlled release of glutamate.

label: negative regulation of synapse organization
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of synapse organization.

label: carotid artery segment
Defs: One of: the common carotid artery, or its branches, the external and internal carotid arteries.

label: behavioural active
Defs: A behavioral quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting marked activity.

label: main group element atom
Defs: An atom belonging to one of the main groups (found in the s- and p- blocks) of the periodic table.

label: musculature of neck
Defs: Any collection of muscles that is part of a neck [Automatically generated definition].

label: endothelium of arteriole
Defs: An endothelium that is part of an arteriole [Automatically generated definition].

label: friability
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to be reduced to smaller pieces with little effort.

label: single fertilization
Defs: The union of male and female gametes to form a zygote.

label: untufted pyramidal neuron
Defs: A pyramidal neuron which lacks a clear tuft formation but extends to large radial distances.

label: dorsal lobe of eye
Defs: The dorsal region of the eye cuticle.

label: vermilion
Defs: A color consisting of red and orange hue with a slight amount of gray.

label: regulation of chorionic trophoblast cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of chorionic trophoblast cell proliferation.

label: receptor-type tyrosine-protein phosphatase C isoform CD45RA
Defs: A receptor-type tyrosine-protein phosphatase C isoform CD45R that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P08575-8 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: light orange
Defs: A color consisting of orange hue and high brightness.

label: oxide
Defs: An oxide is a chemical compound of oxygen with other chemical elements.

label: posterior surface
Defs: Anatomical surface that is located on the posterior side of the body or body part.

label: invaginated
Defs: A shape quality in which a portion of the outermost boundary of an entity folds in space such that a portion that was originally convex is now concave.

label: muscle tissue morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of muscle tissue are generated and organized. Muscle tissue consists of a set of cells that are part of an organ and carry out a contractive function.

label: hydroxides
Defs: Hydroxides are chemical compounds containing a hydroxy group or salts containing hydroxide (OH(-)).

label: anterior orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed anteriorly.

label: neutrophil progenitor cell
Defs: A progenitor cell of the neutrophil lineage.

label: protein localization to somatodendritic compartment
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to or maintained in a location within the somatodendritic compartment.

label: regulation of epidermal cell division
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the physical partitioning and separation of an epidermal cell into daughter cells. An epidermal cell is any of the cells that make up the epidermis.

label: interleukin-3 receptor class 2 alpha chain
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human IL3RA gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: buoyancy
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to rise or float in a fluid medium such as water or air.

label: luminous flux
Defs: A scalar optical quality which obtains by the magnitude of the light emitted by the bearer.

label: regulation of dendritic cell dendrite assembly
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of dendritic cell dendrite assembly.

label: cardiac neural crest
Defs: Portion of neural crest that develops from the dorsal neural tube. It overlaps the vagal neural crest and migrates to populate the pharyngeal arches 3, 4 and 6 (producing structures in the head) and to the heart, forming connective tissue that separates the great vessels of the heart. [Wikipedia].

label: anatomical structure morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which anatomical structures are generated and organized. Morphogenesis pertains to the creation of form.

label: sinus venosus
Defs: The sinus venosus is a large cardiac chamber at the inflow tract that receives venous blood from systemic circulation. precedes the atrium on the venous side of the chordate heart.

label: lateral lingual swelling epithelium
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a lateral lingual swelling.

label: surface tension
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a liquid by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to attraction of molecules at its surface as a result of unbalanced molecular cohesive forces.

label: stomach glandular epithelium
Defs: A glandular epithelium that lines the stomach. The stomach\'s glandular epithelium is characterized by the presence of gastric glands.

label: decreased angle to
Defs: An angle which is relatively low.

label: pons development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the pons over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The pons lies above the medulla and next to the cerebellum. The pons conveys information about movement from the cerebral hemisphere to the cerebellum.

label: bone marrow development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the bone marrow over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: negative regulation of glutamate metabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of glutamate metabolic process.

label: brain
Defs: The brain is the center of the nervous system in all vertebrate, and most invertebrate, animals. Some primitive animals such as jellyfish and starfish have a decentralized nervous system without a brain, while sponges lack any nervous system at all. In vertebrates, the brain is located in the head, protected by the skull and close to the primary sensory apparatus of vision, hearing, balance, taste, and smell[WP].

label: positive regulation of blood circulation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of blood circulation.

label: neuron
Defs: The basic cellular unit of nervous tissue. Each neuron consists of a body, an axon, and dendrites. Their purpose is to receive, conduct, and transmit impulses in the nervous system.

label: macrophage differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized monocyte acquires the specialized features of a macrophage.

label: yolk sac cavity
Defs: An anatomical cavity that is part of a yolk sac [Automatically generated definition].

label: increased amount
Defs: An amount which is relatively high.

label: endothelial cell of vascular tree
Defs: An endothelial cell of the vascular tree, which includes blood vessels and lymphatic vessels.

label: response to monosaccharide
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a monosaccharide stimulus.

label: right atrium endocardium
Defs: Endocardium that is part of the right atrium.

label: congested
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer with some kind of aperture or opening that is blocked or clogged.

label: fertilizer
Defs: A fertilizer is any substance that is added to soil or water to assist the growth of plants.

label: heterocyclic compound
Defs: A cyclic compound having as ring members atoms of at least two different elements.

label: retina layer formation
Defs: The process in which the vertebrate retina is organized into three laminae: the outer nuclear layer (ONL), which contains photoreceptor nuclei; the inner nuclear layer (INL), which contains amacrine, bipolar and horizontal cells; and the retinal ganglion cell (RGC) layer. Between the inner and outer nuclear layers, the outer plexiform layer (OPL) contains connections between the photoreceptors and bipolar and horizontal cells. The inner plexiform layer (IPL) is positioned between the INL and the ganglion cell layer and contains the dendrites of RGCs and processes of bipolar and amacrine cells. Spanning all layers of the retina are the radially oriented Mueller glia.

label: positive regulation of digestive system process
Defs: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of a digestive system process, a physical, chemical, or biochemical process carried out by living organisms to break down ingested nutrients into components that may be easily absorbed and directed into metabolism.

label: abdominal tergite II
Defs: Is the abdominal tergite of the preabdomen that is attached to the posterior margin of the abdominal tergite I by the abdominal tergite I-abdominal tergite II conjunctiva and to the anterior margin of the abdominal tergite III by the abdominal tergite II-abdominal tergite III conjunctiva.

label: stratified
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting a layered configuration.

label: curved lateral
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved towards the side.

label: negative regulation of neurotransmitter secretion
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of a neurotransmitter.

label: decreased combustibility
Defs: An decrease in combustibility.

label: lysed
Defs: The breakdown, disintegration, destruction of an entity due to the breaking of cell membranes by any means.

label: lacks all parts of type
Defs: A quality of physical entities inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking a physical part as specified by the additional entity.

label: response to
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the whether the bearer\'s disposition to react to a stimulus or an agent.

label: negative regulation of chromosome segregation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of chromosome segregation, the process in which genetic material, in the form of chromosomes, is organized and then physically separated and apportioned to two or more sets.

label: myoblast development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the myoblast over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A myoblast is a mononucleate cell type that, by fusion with other myoblasts, gives rise to the myotubes that eventually develop into skeletal muscle fibers.

label: neuronal cell body
Defs: The portion of a neuron that includes the nucleus, but excludes cell projections such as axons and dendrites.

label: acyclic cyclicity
Defs: Acyclic cyclicity inheres in a molecule when the atoms within the molecule do not contain at least one cycle in the atom-atom connection paths (through the bonds).

label: larynx epithelium
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a larynx [Automatically generated definition].

label: chemical synaptic transmission, postsynaptic
Defs: The part of synaptic transmission occurring in the post-synapse: a signal transduction pathway consisting of neurotransmitter receptor activation and its effects on postsynaptic membrane potential and the ionic composition of the postsynaptic cytosol.

label: lobate
Defs: A surface feature shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having deeply undulating edges forming lobes.

label: regulation of vesicle fusion with Golgi apparatus
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of vesicle fusion with Golgi apparatus.

label: apoptotic process involved in heart morphogenesis
Defs: Any apoptotic process that contributes to the shaping of the heart.

label: alpha-(1,3)-fucosyltransferase 4
Defs: An alpha-(1,3)-fucosyltransferase that is a translation product of the human FUT4 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: regulation of phosphorus metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving phosphorus or compounds containing phosphorus.

label: negative regulation of protein localization to cilium
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to cilium.

label: chromosome localization
Defs: Any process in which a chromosome is transported to, or maintained in, a specific location.

label: arteriole of colon
Defs: An arteriole located in the colon.

label: back connective tissue
Defs: A portion of connective tissue that is part of a back [Automatically generated definition].

label: extraembryonic tissue
Defs: Portion of tissue that is contiguous with the embryo and is comprised of portions of tissue or cells that will not contribute to the embryo.

label: endocardial cushion morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structure of the endocardial cushion is generated and organized. The endocardial cushion is a specialized region of mesenchymal cells that will give rise to the heart septa and valves.

label: regulation of metal ion transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of metal ion transport. Metal ion transport is the directed movement of metal ions, any metal ion with an electric charge, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: glucose binding
Defs: Binding to D- or L-enantiomers of glucose.

label: nerve fasciculus
Defs: A slender neuron projection bundle[FBbt]; A bundle of anatomical fibers, as of muscle or nerve (American Heritage Dictionary 4th ed).

label: crowded
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being overfilled.

label: inorganic anion transmembrane transport
Defs: The process in which an inorganic anion is transported across a membrane.

label: muscle layer of colon
Defs: A muscular coat that is part of a colon.

label: laterally rotated
Defs: A rotation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of being rotated towards the side of an organism.

label: regulation of system process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a system process, a multicellular organismal process carried out by any of the organs or tissues in an organ system.

label: iron ion transport
Defs: The directed movement of iron (Fe) ions into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: retina vasculature morphogenesis in camera-type eye
Defs: The process in which the vasculature of the retina is generated and organized.

label: regulation of glutamatergic neuron differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of glutamatergic neuron differentiation.

label: future metencephalon
Defs: A developing anatomical structure that has the potential to develop into a metencephalon.

label: potability
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to being fit to be used as a safe means of hydration.

label: blastoderm segmentation
Defs: The hierarchical steps resulting in the progressive subdivision of the anterior/posterior axis of the embryo.

label: positive regulation of secondary metabolite biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of secondary metabolite biosynthetic process.

label: postsynapse assembly
Defs: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a postsynapse.

label: hypoglossal nerve formation
Defs: The process that gives rise to the hypoglossal nerve. This process pertains to the initial formation of a structure from unspecified parts. This motor nerve innervates all the intrinsic and all but one of the extrinsic muscles of the tongue.

label: respiratory system process
Defs: A process carried out by the organs or tissues of the respiratory system. The respiratory system is an organ system responsible for respiratory gaseous exchange.

label: independent continuant
Defs: b is an independent continuant = Def. b is a continuant which is such that there is no c and no t such that b s-depends_on c at t. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [017-002])

label: ammonium homeostasis
Defs: Any biological process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of ammonium.

label: plasma membrane
Defs: The membrane surrounding a cell that separates the cell from its external environment. It consists of a phospholipid bilayer and associated proteins.

label: positive regulation of lymphocyte mediated immunity
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of lymphocyte mediated immunity.

label: time
Defs: A quality in which events occur in sequence.

label: vasculature of trunk
Defs: A vasculature that is part of a trunk [Automatically generated definition].

label: negative regulation of vesicle fusion
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of vesicle fusion.

label: decreased distribution
Defs: A distribution which is relatively low.

label: anterior-posterior diameter
Defs: A diameter that is along the anterior-posterior axis.

label: actin filament bundle assembly
Defs: The assembly of actin filament bundles; actin filaments are on the same axis but may be oriented with the same or opposite polarities and may be packed with different levels of tightness.

label: regulation of establishment of cell polarity
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of establishment of cell polarity.

label: skin morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the skin are generated and organized. The skin is the external membranous integument of an animal. In vertebrates the skin generally consists of two layers, an outer nonsensitive and nonvascular epidermis (cuticle or skarfskin) composed of cells which are constantly growing and multiplying in the deeper, and being thrown off in the superficial layers, as well as an inner, sensitive and vascular dermis (cutis, corium or true skin) composed mostly of connective tissue.

label: posterior tentorio-scapal muscle
Defs: The cranio-antennal muscle that is attached to the dorsal or anterior tentorial arm and the proximo-dorsal margin of the scapus.

label: regulation of Schwann cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of Schwann cell differentiation.

label: yolk sac blood island
Defs: Masses of developing blood cells attached to endothelium in the yolk sac.

label: related work textual entity
Defs: A textual entity that discusses work from other publications and expresses their relevancy to the content of a document.

label: irregular spatial pattern
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s magnitude of or the relationships between its repeated parts lack consistency.

label: neuroblast migration
Defs: The orderly movement of a neuroblast from one site to another, often during the development of a multicellular organism or multicellular structure. A neuroblast is any cell that will divide and give rise to a neuron.

label: (S)-noradrenaline
Defs: The S-enantiomer of noradrenaline.

label: central nervous system neuron development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a neuron whose cell body is located in the central nervous system, from initial commitment of the cell to a neuronal fate, to the fully functional differentiated neuron.

label: future cardiac ventricle
Defs: Multi-tissue structure that is part of the heart tube and will become the cardiac ventricle.

label: regulation of neutrophil differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of neutrophil differentiation.

label: enzyme inhibitor activity
Defs: Binds to and stops, prevents or reduces the activity of an enzyme.

label: extracellular negative regulation of signal transduction
Defs: Any negative regulation of signal transduction that takes place in extracellular region.

label: phenol-containing compound biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a phenol, any compound containing one or more hydroxyl groups directly attached to an aromatic carbon ring.

label: integrin alpha with A domain
Defs: An integrin alpha that contains an A domain. A hallmark of this class is the presence of a von Willebrand factor type A domain (Pfam:PF00092) (I-domain) of approximately 200 amino acid residues at the N terminus, which confers divalent cation binding properties. Unlike other integrin alpha proteins, they do not undergo proteolytic cleavage.

label: turgor
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a cell or blood vessel or capillary by virtue of the bearer\'s being in a rigid state of fullness resulting from pressure of the contents against the wall or membrane.

label: morphogenesis of an epithelium
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of epithelia are generated and organized. An epithelium consists of closely packed cells arranged in one or more layers, that covers the outer surfaces of the body or lines any internal cavity or tube.

label: positive regulation of synaptic transmission
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of synaptic transmission, the process of communication from a neuron to a target (neuron, muscle, or secretory cell) across a synapse.

label: intracellular membrane-bounded organelle
Defs: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function, bounded by a single or double lipid bilayer membrane and occurring within the cell. Includes the nucleus, mitochondria, plastids, vacuoles, and vesicles. Excludes the plasma membrane.

label: triradiate
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having three rays or radiating branches.

label: protein transport along microtubule
Defs: The directed movement of a protein along a microtubule, mediated by motor proteins.

label: synovial joint of pectoral girdle
Defs: A synovial joint that is part of a pectoral girdle region.

label: sodium ion homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of sodium ions within an organism or cell.

label: negative regulation of hematopoietic stem cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of hematopoietic stem cell differentiation.

label: cell-cell signaling involved in placenta development
Defs: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from one cell to another.

label: glutamate homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of glutamate within an organism or cell.

label: skeletal system
Defs: Anatomical system that is a multi-element, multi-tissue anatomical cluster that consists of the skeleton and the articular system.

label: striated
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being marked by narrow lines or grooves, usually parallel.

label: setting datum
Defs: A settings datum is a datum that denotes some configuration of an instrument.

label: normal pressure
Defs: A pressure which is relatively normal or average

label: antioxidant
Defs: A substance that opposes oxidation or inhibits reactions brought about by dioxygen or peroxides.

label: RNA polymerase II-specific DNA-binding transcription factor binding
Defs: Binding to a sequence-specific DNA binding RNA polymerase II transcription factor, any of the factors that interact selectively and non-covalently with a specific DNA sequence in order to modulate transcription.

label: cell-cell signaling via exosome
Defs: Cell-cell signaling in which the ligand is carried between cells by an exosome.

label: dicarboxylic acid catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of dicarboxylic acids, any organic acid containing two carboxyl (-COOH) groups.

label: anchor-shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a shape resembling an anchor.

label: organic acid catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of organic acids, any acidic compound containing carbon in covalent linkage.

label: negative regulation of lipid transport
