Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of lipids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: ventricular cardiac muscle tissue morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of cardiac ventricle muscle is generated and organized.

label: gonad mesenchyme
Defs: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing gonad [Automatically generated definition].

label: egg cell
Defs: A female gamete where meiosis has progressed to metaphase II and is able to participate in fertilization.

label: surrounded by
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being enclosed on all sides by another entity.

label: negative regulation of myeloid dendritic cell antigen processing and presentation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of myeloid dendritic cell antigen processing and presentation.

label: submucosa of duodenum
Defs: A submucosa that is part of a duodenum [Automatically generated definition].

label: digestive system
Defs: Anatomical system that has as its parts the organs devoted to the ingestion, digestion, and assimilation of food and the discharge of residual wastes.

label: compatibility
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to harmonious coexistence.

label: positive regulation of lymphoid progenitor cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of lymphoid progenitor cell differentiation.

label: ventral region
Defs: Anatomical region ventrally located on the body or body part.

label: response to monoamine
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a monoamine stimulus. A monoamine is any of a group of molecular messengers that contain one amino group that is connected to an aromatic ring by ethylene group (-CH2-CH2-). Monoamines are derived from the aromatic amino acids phenylalanine, tyrosine, histidine and tryptophan.

label: anterior segment of eyeball
Defs: Any of the parts of the eye that lie in front of, or ventral to, the lens (inclusive).

label: artery morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of arterial blood vessels are generated and organized. Arteries are blood vessels that transport blood from the heart to the body and its organs.

label: negative regulation of glutamate secretion, neurotransmission
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of glutamate secretion, neurotransmission.

label: subantennal groove
Defs: The concave region of the cuticle on the lateral or ventral region of the head capsule that is adjacent to the antennal foramen.

label: positive regulation of cilium-dependent cell motility
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cilium-dependent cell motility.

label: aplastic growth
Defs: A growth quality of occurrent in which the growth of an organism, structure or group of organisms does not occur.

label: pharyngeal mucosa
Defs: A mucosa that is part of a pharynx [Automatically generated definition].

label: first maxillar palpopalpal muscle
Defs: The insect cranio-maxillar muscle that is attached to the first maxillar palpomere and  the second maxillar palpomere.

label: head-cervical articulation
Defs: The articulation between the head and the neck.

label: positive regulation of protein localization to chromatin
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to chromatin.

label: multicellular anatomical structure
Defs: An anatomical structure that has more than one cell as a part.

label: bile acid binding
Defs: Binding to a bile acid, a steroid carboxylic acids occurring in bile.

label: regulation of protein transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of a protein into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: positive regulation of lipid transporter activity
Defs: Any process that increases the frequency, rate, or extent of lipid transporter activity.

label: melanosome localization
Defs: Any process in which a melanosome is transported to, and/or maintained in, a specific location within the cell.

label: multiparous
Defs: A viviparous organism that has given birth two or more times.

label: immature neutrophil
Defs: Any of the immature forms of a neutrophil in which neutrophilic specific granules are present but other phenotypic features of the mature form may be lacking.

label: glossopharyngeal nerve
Defs: Cranial nerve that branches into the ramus communicans (to the skin), the pretrematic (to the walls of the pharynx and mouth, viscero-sensory fibers), and the larval post-trematic branch (lost in the adult).

label: increased behavioural activity
Defs: A behavioral quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting increased activity.

label: positive regulation of motile cilium assembly
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of motile cilium assembly.

label: carboxylic acid catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of carboxylic acids, any organic acid containing one or more carboxyl (-COOH) groups.

label: obsolete edematous (sensu botany)
Defs: An extended swelling in plant organs caused primarily by an excessive accumulation of water.

label: Venn diagram
Defs:
A Venn diagram is a report graph showing all hypothetically possible
logical relations between a finite collection of sets.

label: detection of chemical stimulus
Defs: The series of events in which a chemical stimulus is received by a cell and converted into a molecular signal.

label: vasculogenesis involved in coronary vascular morphogenesis
Defs: The differentiation of endothelial cells from progenitor cells that contributes to blood vessel development in the heart, and the de novo formation of blood vessels and tubes.

label: somite development
Defs: The progression of a somite from its initial formation to the mature structure. Somites are mesodermal clusters that are arranged segmentally along the anterior posterior axis of an embryo.

label: increased life span
Defs: A life span which is relatively high.

label: plowshare shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being shaped like a plowshare.

label: epicardium morphogenesis
Defs: The developmental process by which an epicardium is generated and organized.

label: organelle transport along microtubule
Defs: The directed movement of an organelle along a microtubule, mediated by motor proteins. This process begins with the attachment of an organelle to a microtubule, and ends when the organelle reaches its final destination.

label: transepithelial transport
Defs: The directed movement of a substance from one side of an epithelium to the other.

label: single organismal process quality
Defs: A quality inhering in a process by virtue of that process having exactly one organism as a participant.

label: intrinsic component of postsynaptic membrane
Defs: The component of the postsynaptic membrane consisting of the gene products and protein complexes having either part of their peptide sequence embedded in the hydrophobic region of the membrane or some other covalently attached group such as a GPI anchor that is similarly embedded in the membrane.

label: epithelial cell
Defs: A cell that is usually found in a two-dimensional sheet with a free surface. The cell has a cytoskeleton that allows for tight cell to cell contact and for cell polarity where apical part is directed towards the lumen and the basal part to the basal lamina.

label: growth
Defs: The increase in size or mass of an entire organism, a part of an organism or a cell.

label: stomach
Defs: An expanded region of the vertebrate alimentary tract that serves as a food storage compartment and digestive organ. A stomach is lined, in whole or in part by a glandular epithelium.

label: promonocyte
Defs: A precursor in the monocytic series, being a cell intermediate in development between the monoblast and monocyte. This cell is CD11b-positive and has fine azurophil granules.

label: negative regulation of mononuclear cell migration
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of mononuclear cell migration. Mononuclear cell migration is the movement of a mononuclear cell within or between different tissues and organs of the body.

label: bone marrow
Defs: The soft tissue that fills the cavities of bones.

label: negative regulation of excitatory synapse assembly
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of excitatory synapse assembly.

label: ligament
Defs: Dense regular connective tissue connecting two or more adjacent skeletal elements or supporting an organ.

label: positive regulation of reproductive process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of reproductive process.

label: stipito-palpiferal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect maxilla that connects the stipes and the palpifer.

label: regulation of osteoclast differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of osteoclast differentiation.

label: epipharynx
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect head that is connected to the oral foraminal conjunctiva and to the distal margin of the labrum.

label: azurophil granule membrane
Defs: The lipid bilayer surrounding an azurophil granule, a primary lysosomal granule found in neutrophil granulocytes that contains a wide range of hydrolytic enzymes and is released into the extracellular fluid.

label: basal margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the basal side of the body or body part.

label: prepectus
Defs: The sclerite that is posterior to the pronotum and receives the site of attachment of the dilutor muscle of the first thoracic spiracle.

label: cerebral blood circulation
Defs: The flow of blood through the network of arteries and veins supplying the cerebrum, enabling the transport of nutrients to the tissues and the removal of waste products.

label: chorion development
Defs: The biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of a chorion from an initial condition to its mature state. This process begins with the formation of the structure and ends with the mature structure. The chorion is an extraembryonic membrane.

label: posteroventral orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed posteroventrally.

label: cervical spinal cord
Defs: A spinal cord segment that adjacent_to a cervical region.

label: L-shaped
Defs: An angular shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a single angle in its length giving the bearer the form of the letter L.

label: negative regulation of mitotic sister chromatid segregation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of sister chromatid segregation during mitosis.

label: neuroblast activation
Defs: A change in the morphology or behavior of a neuroblast resulting from exposure to an activating factor such as a cellular or soluble ligand.

label: monoatomic entity
Defs: A monoatomic entity is a molecular entity consisting of a single atom.

label: defecation
Defs: The expulsion of feces from the rectum.

label: G protein-coupled acetylcholine receptor activity
Defs: Combining with acetylcholine and transmitting the signal across the membrane by activating an associated G-protein; promotes the exchange of GDP for GTP on the alpha subunit of a heterotrimeric G-protein complex.

label: oral foraminal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect head that connects the head capsule and the mouthparts.

label: larynx
Defs: A continuation of the pharynx that is involved in breathing, sound production, and protecting the trachea against food aspiration.

label: bulbus cordis myocardium
Defs: A myocardium that is part of a bulbus cordis [Automatically generated definition].

label: pelvis nerve
Defs: A nerve that is part of a pelvis [Automatically generated definition].

label: regulation of mitotic nuclear division
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mitosis.

label: abdominal sternite VI
Defs: The abdominal sternite of the preabdomen that is attached to the posterior margin of the abdominal sternite V by the abdominal sternite V-abdominal sternite VI conjunctiva and to the anterior margin of the abdominal sternite VII by the abdominal sternite VI-abdominal sternite VII conjunctiva.

label: present
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s existence.

label: negative regulation of cardiac neural crest cell migration involved in outflow tract morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac neural crest cell migration involved in outflow tract morphogenesis.

label: regulation of response to stress
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a response to stress. Response to stress is a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a disturbance in organismal or cellular homeostasis, usually, but not necessarily, exogenous (e.g. temperature, humidity, ionizing radiation).

label: uterine tube infundibulum
Defs: The funnel-like expansion of the abdominal extremity of the uterine tube[MP].

label: isometrical
Defs: A symmetry quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having equal dimensions or measurements.

label: regulation of ketone catabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a ketone, carried out by individual cells.

label: rostrocaudal neural tube patterning
Defs: The process in which the neural tube is divided into specific regions along the rostrocaudal axis.

label: cardiac neural crest cell development involved in heart development
Defs: The process aimed at the progression of a cardiac neural crest cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to its specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell that contributes to the development of the heart.

label: mesothelium of pleural cavity
Defs: A mesothelium that is part of a pleural cavity [Automatically generated definition].

label: prostrate
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being stretched out and lying at full length along the ground.

label: positive regulation of cartilage development
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of cartilage development, the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the cartilage over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Cartilage is a connective tissue dominated by extracellular matrix containing collagen type II and large amounts of proteoglycan, particularly chondroitin sulfate.

label: hispidulous
Defs: A quality of being minutely hispid.

label: hypertrophic
Defs: An increased size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting enlargement of a cell or constituent group of cells (for example, organ).

label: mesophragma
Defs: The phragma of the metanotum that attaches to muscles attached to the mesonotum.

label: keywords section
Defs: A part of a document where keywords selected by the author to categorize the major theme(s) of a document are listed.

label: hematopoietic stem cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a hematopoietic stem cell. A stem cell is a cell that retains the ability to divide and proliferate throughout life to provide progenitor cells that can differentiate into specialized cells.

label: translation at postsynapse
Defs: Translation that occurs at the postsynapse.

label: positive regulation of cytokine production involved in inflammatory response
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cytokine production involved in inflammatory response.

label: embryonic cardiovascular system
Defs: A cardiovascular system that is part of a conceptus.

label: metacoxal muscle
Defs: The coxal muscle of the metacoxa.

label: mural cell
Defs: Mural cells are pericytes and the vascular smooth muscle cells (vSMCs) of the microcirculation.

label: closure incomplete
Defs: A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s affording not completed blocked passage or view.

label: negative regulation of apoptotic process involved in morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of apoptotic process involved in morphogenesis.

label: response to organic substance
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an organic substance stimulus.

label: waxiness
Defs: A composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the presence of long chain aliphatic lipids on the surface of an organism.

label: T cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a precursor cell type acquires characteristics of a more mature T-cell. A T cell is a type of lymphocyte whose definin characteristic is the expression of a T cell receptor complex.

label: decreased duration of temperature
Defs: A duration of temperature which is lesser relative to the normal or average enduring or continuing in time.

label: increased contamination
Defs: An increase in contamination.

label: nerve of cervical vertebra
Defs: The cervical nerves are the spinal nerves from the cervical vertebrae. Although there are seven cervical vertebrae (C1-C7), there are eight cervical nerves (C1-C8). All nerves except C8 emerge above their corresponding vertebrae, while the C8 nerve emerges below the C7 vertebra. (In the other portions of the spine, the nerve emerges below the vertebra with the same name. Dorsal (posterior) distribution includes the greater occipital (C2) and third occipital (C3). Ventral (anterior) distribution includes the cervical plexus (C1-C4) and brachial plexus (C5-C8) [WP,unvetted].

label: light yellow
Defs: A color consisting of yellow hue and high brightness.

label: sensillum coeloconicum
Defs: Seta that is located in the middle of a depression with narrowed external opening.

label: positive regulation of neuroinflammatory response
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of neuroinflammatory response.

label: hematopoietic progenitor cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which precursor cell type acquires the specialized features of a hematopoietic progenitor cell, a class of cell types including myeloid progenitor cells and lymphoid progenitor cells.

label: third maxillar palpopalpal muscle
Defs: The insect cranio-maxillar muscle that is attached to the third maxillar palpomere and  the fourth maxillar palpomere.

label: abdominopelvic cavity
Defs: The part of the ventral body cavity that is within the abdominal segment of the trunk, which encompasses the abdomen proper plus pelvic cavity.

label: serotonin
Defs: A primary amino compound that is the 5-hydroxy derivative of tryptamine.

label: hepaticobiliary system process
Defs: An system process carried out by any of the organs or tissues of the hepaticobiliary system. The hepaticobiliary system is responsible for metabolic and catabolic processing of small molecules absorbed from the blood or gut, hormones and serum proteins, detoxification, storage of glycogen, triglycerides, metals and lipid soluble vitamins and excretion of bile. Included are the synthesis of albumin, blood coagulation factors, complement, and specific binding proteins.

label: hematopoietic system
Defs: Anatomical system that is involved in the production of hematopoietic cells.

label: optic choroid
Defs: Vascular layer containing connective tissue, of the eye lying between the retina and the sclera. The choroid provides oxygen and nourishment to the outer layers of the retina. Along with the ciliary body and iris, the choroid forms the uveal tract[WP].

label: neutral charge
Defs: A quality which inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the molecular entity possessing the same amount of electrons overall as protons, thus having an overall neutral charge.

label: hepatic diverticulum
Defs: An out-pocket of thickened ventral foregut epithelium adjacent to the developing heart. Constitutes the first morphological sign of the embryonic liver. The anterior portion of the hepatic diverticulum gives rise to the liver and intrahepatic biliary tree, while the posterior portion forms the gall bladder and extrahepatic bile ducts.

label: red
Defs: A color hue with high wavelength of the long-wave end of the visible spectrum, evoked in the human observer by radiant energy with wavelengths of approximately 630 to 750 nanometers.

label: establishment of protein localization to chromosome
Defs: The directed movement of a protein to a specific location on a chromosome.

label: negative regulation of embryonic pattern specification
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of embryonic pattern specification.

label: G protein-coupled acetylcholine receptor signaling pathway
Defs: A G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway initiated by a ligand binding to an acetylcholine receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ends with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

label: regulation of skeletal muscle tissue development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of skeletal muscle tissue development.

label: positive regulation of molecular function
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the rate or extent of a molecular function, an elemental biological activity occurring at the molecular level, such as catalysis or binding.

label: regulation of oocyte development
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate or extent of the process whose specific outcome is the progression of an oocyte over time, from initial commitment of the cell to its specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell.

label: glycogen
Defs: A polydisperse, highly branched glucan composed of chains of D-glucopyranose residues in alpha(1->4) glycosidic linkage, joined together by alpha(1->6) glycosidic linkages. A small number of alpha(1->3) glycosidic linkages and some cumulative alpha(1->6) links also may occur. The branches in glycogen typically contain 8 to 12 glucose residues.

label: notochord morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the notochord are generated and organized. The notochord is a mesoderm-derived structure located ventral of the developing nerve cord. In vertebrates, the notochord serves as a core around which other mesodermal cells form the vertebrae. In the most primitive chordates, which lack vertebrae, the notochord persists as a substitute for a vertebral column.

label: response to chemical
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a chemical stimulus.

label: intrinsic component of vacuolar membrane
Defs: The component of the vacuolar membrane consisting of the gene products and protein complexes having either part of their peptide sequence embedded in the hydrophobic region of the membrane or some other covalently attached group such as a GPI anchor that is similarly embedded in the membrane.

label: microvascular endothelial cell
Defs: Any blood vessel endothelial cell that is part of a microvascular endothelium.

label: intestinal mucosa
Defs: Mucosal layer that lines the intestine.

label: normal duration of temperature
Defs: A duration quality of temperature quality of a process which is relatively normal.

label: defense response to nematode
Defs: A response to protect an organism from a directly detected or perceived external threat from a nematode or nematodes, which results in restriction of damage to the organism attacked or prevention/recovery from the infection caused by the attack.

label: neurectodermal cell
Defs: Ectoderm destined to be nervous tissue.

label: upper-lower axis
Defs: An anatomical axis determined by gravity.

label: pharyngeal pouch 2
Defs: A pharyngeal puch that is between the pharyngeal arches 2 and 3.

label: basal layer of endometrium
Defs: The layer of endometrial epithelium adjacent to the uterine cavity.

label: epistoma
Defs: The region of cuticle that is posterior to the cuticle of the labrum.

label: negative regulation of peptidyl-tyrosine phosphorylation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the phosphorylation of peptidyl-tyrosine.

label: organonitrogen compound catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of organonitrogen compound.

label: monopoietic cell
Defs: A cell involved in the formation of a monocyte (monopoiesis).

label: increased susceptibility toward
Defs: A susceptibility toward an external stimulus which is higher than normal/average.

label: sessile (sensu botany)
Defs: An attachment quality inhering in a flower by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking a stalk, as in flowers or leaves that grow directly from the stem.

label: sleep pattern
Defs: A sleep quality defined by the mathematic properties of the relative time frames of the sleep cycle.

label: enzyme regulator activity
Defs: Binds to and modulates the activity of an enzyme.

label: has normal numbers of parts of type
Defs: The bearer of this quality has_part = n, where n is the normal amount for a comparable organism. Note that the bearer of the quality is the whole, not the part.

label: negative regulation of bile acid biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of bile acids.

label: ionic polymer
Defs: An ionic polymer is a polymer, composed of ionic macromolecules.

label: aorta wall
Defs: An anatomical wall that is part of an aorta, enclosing the luminal space.

label: offset
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s position being displaced from a reference point.

label: cardiac muscle contraction
Defs: Muscle contraction of cardiac muscle tissue.

label: linear density
Defs: A density quality which is equal to the mass exerting an influence on a one-dimensional object.

label: positive regulation of female gonad development
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of female gonad development.

label: areolar connective tissue
Defs: Loose connective tissue located at the outer and inner layers of organs. Examples: submucosal connective tissue, tunica adventitia of artery, papillary dermis, superficial fascia of dorsum of hand.

label: neprilysin
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human MME gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: intestinal villus
Defs: The tiny hair-like projections that protrude from the inside of the small intestine that contain blood vessels that capture digested nutrients that are absorbed through the intestinal wall; the villi increase the absorptive surface area of the small intestine by approximately 30-fold.

label: alkali metal molecular entity
Defs: A molecular entity containing one or more atoms of an alkali metal.

label: myocyte of atrioventricular node
Defs: A muscle cell that is part of the atrioventricular node.

label: lumen of esophagus
Defs: An anatomical cavity that is part of a esophagus.

label: liver serosa
Defs: Hepatic serous coat; peritoneal covering of the liver, enclosing almost all except for a triangular area on its posterior surface (the \'bare area of the liver\') and a smaller area where the liver and gallbladder are in direct contact.

label: pylorus
Defs: The stomach tissue region surrounding and controlling the distal outlet of the stomach, which opens into the duodenum.

label: negative regulation of mitotic cell cycle
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the rate or extent of progression through the mitotic cell cycle.

label: negative regulation of collagen binding
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of collagen binding.

label: banded
Defs: A color pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of bearer\'s exhibiting transverse stripes of one hue or degree of saturation crossing another.

label: gonopore
Defs: The orifice in the postabdomen that marks the opening of the reproductive system.

label: presumptive segmental plate
Defs: A presumptive structure that has the potential to develop into a presomitic mesoderm.

label: brittle
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to breaks without significant deformation (strain) when subjected to stress.

label: two dimensional cartesian spatial coordinate datum
Defs: A cartesion spatial coordinate datum that  uses two values to specify a position within a two dimensional spatial region

label: xenobiotic metabolite
Defs: Any metabolite produced by metabolism of a xenobiotic compound.

label: taste receptor cell
Defs: A cell type found in the spherical or ovoid clusters of receptor cells found mainly in the epithelium of the tongue and constituting the end organs of the sense of taste.

label: gall bladder lamina propria
Defs: A lamina propria that is part of a gallbladder [Automatically generated definition].

label: decreased degree of illumination
Defs: An decrease in illumination.

label: choroidal melanocyte
Defs: A melanocyte located in the vascular uvea and involved in photoprotection, regulation of oxidative damage and immune responses.

label: monocarboxylic acid transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of monocarboxylic acids from one side of a membrane to the other. A monocarboxylic acid is an organic acid with one COOH group.

label: pigment granule
Defs: A small, subcellular membrane-bounded vesicle containing pigment and/or pigment precursor molecules. Pigment granule biogenesis is poorly understood, as pigment granules are derived from multiple sources including the endoplasmic reticulum, coated vesicles, lysosomes, and endosomes.

label: mononucleate
Defs: A nucleate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having one nucleus.

label: regulation of skeletal muscle contraction via regulation of action potential
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of skeletal muscle contraction by depolarization of muscle membrane and ionic fluxes.

label: ion transport
Defs: The directed movement of charged atoms or small charged molecules into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: perimeter
Defs: An 1-D extent quality inhering in two-dimensional bearer by virtue of being equal to the distance around it.

label: positive regulation of myeloid leukocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of myeloid leukocyte differentiation.

label: data item extraction from journal article
Defs: A planned process in which journal articles are read or processed and data items are extracted, typically for further analysis or indexing

label: ectodermal cell
Defs: A cell of the outer of the three germ layers of the embryo.

label: metatarso-metapretarsal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that encircles the metapretarsus by joining the distal margin of the distalmost metatarsomere and the proximal margin of the metapretarsus.

label: uterine smooth muscle cell
Defs: A smooth muscle cell of the uterus.

label: 2nd arch mesenchyme
Defs: Mesenchyme that is part of a pharyngeal arch 2.

label: basement membrane disassembly
Defs: The controlled breakdown of the basement membrane in the context of a normal process such as imaginal disc eversion.

label: somite
Defs: Somites are spheres of epithelial cells that form sequentially along the anterior-posterior axis of the embryo through mesenchymal to epithelial transition of the presomitic mesoderm.

label: inner cell mass
Defs: A mass of cells that develop into the body of the embryo and some extraembryonic tissues.

label: cellular response to peptide
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a peptide stimulus.

label: ipsilateral surface
Defs: Anatomical surface that is located on the same side of an organism or structure.

label: dipolar compound
Defs: An  organic molecule that is electrically neutral carrying a positive and a negative charge in one of its major canonical descriptions. In most dipolar compounds the charges are delocalized; however the term is also applied to species where this is not the case.

label: electrical conductivity
Defs: A conductivity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to convey electricity.

label: eukaryotic protein
Defs: A protein that is encoded in the genome of some Eukaryota.

label: intrasonic
Defs: A sound frequency in the range of 0-20 Hz.

label: female-specific
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being present in females and absent from males in members of the same species.

label: retracted
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being drawn in or pulled back from any given point.

label: mesiolateral orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed mesiolaterally.

label: negative regulation of melanosome organization
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of melanosome organization.

label: Schwann cell chemotaxis
Defs: The directed movement of a Schwann cell guided by a specific chemical concentration gradient. Movement may be towards a higher concentration (positive chemotaxis) or towards a lower concentration (negative chemotaxis).

label: femoro-tibial conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that encircles the tibia by joining the distal margin of the femur and the proximal margin of the tibia.

label: regulation of lysosomal protein catabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of lysosomal protein catabolic process.

label: sarcomere
Defs: The repeating unit of a myofibril in a muscle cell, composed of an array of overlapping thick and thin filaments between two adjacent Z discs.

label: discoid
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being cylindrical, in which the height is less than the diameter.

label: nerve
Defs: An enclosed, cable-like bundle of axons in the peripheral nervous system originating in a nerve root in the central nervous system (or a condensed nervous structure) connecting with peripheral structures.

label: sex-specific anatomical structure
Defs: A part of the body present only in a specific gender.

label: cilium movement
Defs: The directed, self-propelled movement of a cilium.

label: conflict of interest textual entity
Defs: A textual entity that expresses a situation involving one or more of the authors, or the funding source of a document whereby the authors or funding source stand to potentially gain (typically financially) from the results reported in the document.

label: non-porous
Defs: A porosity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being incapable of admitting the passage of gas or liquid through pores or interstices.

label: outflow tract septum
Defs: The outflow tract septum is a partition in the outflow tract.

label: germarium-derived egg chamber formation
Defs: Construction of a stage-1 egg chamber in the anterior part of the germarium, from the progeny of germ-line and somatic stem cells. An example of this is found in Drosophila melanogaster.

label: protein-containing complex organization
Defs: Any process in which macromolecules aggregate, disaggregate, or are modified, resulting in the formation, disassembly, or alteration of a protein complex.

label: cornea
Defs: The transparent anterior portion of the fibrous coat of the eye that serves as the chief refractory structure.

label: hepatocyte differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized features of a hepatocyte. A hepatocyte is specialized epithelial cell that is organized into interconnected plates called lobules, and is the main structural component of the liver.

label: melanosome organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a melanosome. A melanosome is a tissue-specific, membrane-bounded cytoplasmic organelle within which melanin pigments are synthesized and stored.

label: response to glycoprotein
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a glycoprotein stimulus.

label: epithelial cell morphogenesis
Defs: The change in form that occurs when an epithelial cell progresses from its initial formation to its mature state.

label: ciliary epithelium
Defs: A double layer covering the ciliary body that produces aqueous humor.

label: laryngeal joint
Defs: A skeletal joint that connects a laryngeal cartilage.

label: urokinase plasminogen activator surface receptor
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human PLAUR gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: prealar bridge
Defs: The region of cuticle of the dorso-lateral region of the pterothorax that is surrounded by the noto-pleural conjunctiva and articulated with the episternum.

label: upturned
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved or tilted such that the tip points upwards.

label: negative regulation of mesenchymal cell proliferation involved in lung development
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of mesenchymal cell proliferation involved in lung development.

label: abdominal segment of trunk
Defs: The abdominal segment of the torso.

label: endocrine gland
Defs: Endocrine glands are glands of the endocrine system that secrete their products directly into the circulatory system rather than through a duct.[WP, modified].

label: increased variability of color
Defs: A variability of color which is relatively high.

label: regulation of compound eye retinal cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of compound eye retinal cell apoptotic process.

label: kinked
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having multiple angles in its length.

label: laryngeal nerve
Defs: Any nerve that innervates the larynx.

label: epicardial fat
Defs: Visceral intrapericardial fat contiguous with the myocardial surface.

label: small molecule catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of small molecules, any low molecular weight, monomeric, non-encoded molecule.

label: cell surface receptor signaling pathway
Defs: The series of molecular signals initiated by activation of a receptor on the surface of a cell. The pathway begins with binding of an extracellular ligand to a cell surface receptor, or for receptors that signal in the absence of a ligand, by ligand-withdrawal or the activity of a constitutively active receptor. The pathway ends with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

label: ribonucleic acid
Defs: High molecular weight, linear polymers, composed of nucleotides containing ribose and linked by phosphodiester bonds; RNA is central to the synthesis of proteins.

label: positive regulation of chondrocyte development
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of chondrocyte development.

label: positive regulation of signaling
Defs: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of a signaling process.

label: dorsal cranio-mandibular articulation
Defs: The cranio-mandibular articulation that is part of the subgena and lateral to the clypeus.

label: axonal dopamine secretion
Defs: The regulated release of dopamine from an axon.

label: deciduous (generic)
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to shed body parts.

label: plasma membrane bounded cell projection morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of a plasma membrane bounded cell projection are generated and organized.

label: regulation of dendrite morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of dendrite morphogenesis.

label: increased rate of continuous process
Defs: A rate of output of a continuous process that is relatively high.

label: smooth muscle cell of colon
Defs: A smooth muscle cell that is part of the colon.

label: regulation of lipid metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving lipids.

label: research settings section
Defs: A document part that describes the physical/social/cultural conditions around a research trial.

label: regulation of glycoprotein metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of glycoprotein metabolic process.

label: placental labyrinth blood vessel
Defs: The embryonic vessels grow through the layer to come in close contact with the maternal blood supply.

label: stem cell
Defs: A relatively undifferentiated cell that retains the ability to divide and proliferate throughout life to provide progenitor cells that can differentiate into specialized cells.

label: directive information entity
Defs: An information content entity whose concretizations indicate to their bearer how to realize them in a process.

label: negative regulation of cholangiocyte apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cholangiocyte apoptotic process.

label: myeloid dendritic cell antigen processing and presentation
Defs: The process in which a myeloid dendritic cell expresses antigen (peptide or lipid) on its cell surface in association with an MHC protein complex.

label: myeloid cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized myeloid precursor cell acquires the specialized features of any cell of the myeloid leukocyte, megakaryocyte, thrombocyte, or erythrocyte lineages.

label: regulation of axo-dendritic protein transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of axo-dendritic protein transport.

label: epistoepipharyngeal muscle
Defs: The cranio-labral muscle that is attached to the frontoclypeal ridge and the labrum.

label: skin secretion
Defs: A portion of organism substance that secreted_by a zone of skin.

label: lamina propria of trachea
Defs: A lamina propria that is part of a respiratory airway.

label: mentum
Defs: The sclerite of the labium that is anterior to the submentum and posterior to the prementum, and attached to the prementum by the mental-premental conjunctiva.

label: acetate ester
Defs: Any carboxylic ester where the carboxylic acid component is acetic acid.

label: negative regulation of receptor localization to synapse
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of receptor localization to synapse.

label: Purkinje myocyte development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a Purkinje myocyte over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The Purkinje myocyte (also known as cardiac Purkinje fiber) is part of the cardiac conduction system that receives signals from the bundle of His and innervates the ventricular cardiac muscle.

label: regulation of cellular response to insulin stimulus
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cellular response to insulin stimulus.

label: lance-ovate
Defs: A spheroid quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting a continuous convex surface with an axis of symmetry and one axis longer than the other; characterized with an egg-shaped form crossed with a lance-head shaped form.

label: aligned with
Defs: An alignment quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being in a proper spatial positioning with respect to an additional entity.

label: primary metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving those compounds which are formed as a part of the normal anabolic and catabolic processes. These processes take place in most, if not all, cells of the organism.

label: EC 3.5.1.* (non-peptide linear amide C-N hydrolase) inhibitor
Defs: An EC 3.5.* (hydrolases acting on non-peptide C-N bonds) inhibitor that interferes with the action of any non-peptide linear amide C-N hydrolase (EC 3.5.1.*).

label: midbrain neural plate
Defs: A neural plate that develops_from a presumptive midbrain.

label: transmembrane signaling receptor activity
Defs: Combining with an extracellular or intracellular signal and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity or state as part of signal transduction.

label: inner cell mass cell
Defs: Any native cell that is part of a inner cell mass.

label: forebrain
Defs: The most anterior region of the brain including both the telencephalon and diencephalon.

label: negative regulation of chromatin binding
Defs: Any process that stops or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of chromatin binding. Chromatin binding is the selective interaction with chromatin, the network of fibers of DNA, protein, and sometimes RNA, that make up the chromosomes of the eukaryotic nucleus during interphase.

label: photon
Defs: Particle of zero charge, zero rest mass, spin quantum number 1, energy hnu and momentum hnu/c (h is the Planck constant, nu the frequency of radiation and c the speed of light), carrier of electromagnetic force.

label: positive regulation of neuroblast migration
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of neuroblast migration.

label: acinus
Defs: Having a shape that resembles a many-lobed "berry," such as a raspberry.

label: regulation of dendrite development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of dendrite development.

label: placental amniotic mesenchymal stromal cell
Defs: Any mesenchymal stem cell that is part of a placenta.

label: normal amount
Defs: An amount which normal.

label: positive regulation of lymphocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of lymphocyte differentiation.

label: negative regulation of myeloid cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of a myeloid cell apoptotic process.

label: neutrophil migration
Defs: The movement of a neutrophil within or between different tissues and organs of the body.

label: production of molecular mediator of immune response
Defs: The synthesis or release of any molecular mediator of the immune response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label: plant metabolite
Defs: Any eukaryotic metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in plants, the kingdom that include flowering plants, conifers and other gymnosperms.

label: pharynx development
Defs: The biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of a pharynx from an initial condition to its mature state. The pharynx is the part of the digestive system immediately posterior to the mouth.

label: angioblast cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized structural and/or functional features of an angioblast cell. Angioblasts are one of the two products formed from hemangioblast cells (the other being pluripotent hemopoietic stem cells).

label: outflow tract pericardium
Defs: A pericardium that is part of a outflow tract [Automatically generated definition].

label: pro-resilin (fruit fly)
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the resilin gene in fruit fly.

label: soft
Defs: A hardness quality of giving little resistance to pressure.

label: euploid
Defs: A ploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing an integral multiple of the monoploid number, possibly excluding the sex-determining chromosomes.

label: nucleobase-containing compound biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of nucleobases, nucleosides, nucleotides and nucleic acids.

label: columnar/cuboidal epithelial cell
Defs: A columnar/cuboidal epithelial cell is a cell usually found in a two dimensional sheet with a free surface. Columnar/cuboidal epithelial cells take on the shape of a column or cube.

label: future coelemic cavity lumen
Defs: An anatomical cavity that has the potential to develop into a coelemic cavity lumen.

label: subacute
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having an onset and time course between acute and chronic.

label: system process
Defs: A multicellular organismal process carried out by any of the organs or tissues in an organ system. An organ system is a regularly interacting or interdependent group of organs or tissues that work together to carry out a biological objective.

label: regulation of signaling receptor activity
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a signaling receptor activity. Receptor activity is when a molecule combines with an extracellular or intracellular messenger to initiate a change in cell activity.

label: exserted
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s protruding or projecting from the body.

label: regulation of developmental growth
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of developmental growth.

label: positive regulation of organelle assembly
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of organelle assembly.

label: phosphotransferase activity, alcohol group as acceptor
Defs: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphorus-containing group from one compound (donor) to an alcohol group (acceptor).

label: developmental maturation
Defs: A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for an anatomical structure, cell or cellular component to attain its fully functional state.

label: serous cell of epithelium of bronchus
Defs: A serous secreting cell that is part of the epithelium of bronchus.

label: cardiac muscle cell proliferation
Defs: The expansion of a cardiac muscle cell population by cell division.

label: microtubule nucleation
Defs: The process in which tubulin alpha-beta heterodimers begin aggregation to form an oligomeric tubulin structure (a microtubule seed). Microtubule nucleation is the initiating step in the formation of a microtubule in the absence of any existing microtubules (\'de novo\' microtubule formation).

label: positive regulation of chondrocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of chondrocyte differentiation.

label: abdominal tergite X-epiproct conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the postabdomen that joins the abdominal tergite X and the epiproct.

label: cell surface receptor signaling pathway involved in cell-cell signaling
Defs: Any cell surface receptor signaling pathway that is involved in cell-cell signaling.

label: ecological community
Defs: A multi-species collection of organisms of at least two different species, living in a particular area. Must have at least two populations of different species as members.

label: dendritic cell cytokine production
Defs: Any process that contributes to cytokine production by a dendritic cell.

label: obovate
Defs: A spheroid quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being egg-shaped and flat, with the narrow end attached to the base.

label: regulation of protein localization to cell leading edge
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to cell leading edge.

label: counting
Defs: The planned process of finding the number of elements in a finite set of objects.

label: pectoral appendage skeleton
Defs: Skeletal subdivision consisting of the anterior appendicular limb skeleton, excluding the pectoral girdle.

label: bronchus basement membrane
Defs: A basement membrane that is part of a bronchus.

label: future nervous system
Defs: Primordium that develops into the nervous system.

label: cardiac left ventricle morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the left cardiac ventricle is generated and organized.

label: regulation of localization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of any process in which a cell, a substance, or a cellular entity is transported to, or maintained in, a specific location.

label: damage
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer has been harmed or injured or spoiled.

label: 3rd arch mesenchyme from neural crest
Defs: Mesenchyme that develops_from a neural crest and is part of a 3rd arch mesenchyme.

label: trunk blood vessel
Defs: A blood vessel that is part of a trunk [Automatically generated definition].

label: developmental growth involved in morphogenesis
Defs: The increase in size or mass of an anatomical structure that contributes to the structure attaining its shape.

label: smooth muscle cell of the subclavian artery
Defs: A smooth muscle cell of the subclavian artery.

label: obsolete maternal
Defs: A parental quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of exhibiting the characteristic of a mother.

label: intestinal junction
Defs: An anatomical junction between two parts of the intestine.

label: positive regulation of compound eye retinal cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of compound eye retinal cell apoptotic process.

label: pontine raphe nucleus
Defs: The pontine raphe nucleus is one of the raphe nuclei. It is located in the pontine tegmentum. [WP,unvetted].

label: negative regulation of myoblast differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of myoblast differentiation. A myoblast is a mononucleate cell type that, by fusion with other myoblasts, gives rise to the myotubes that eventually develop into skeletal muscle fibers.

label: process
Defs: p is a process = Def. p is an occurrent that has temporal proper parts and for some time t, p s-depends_on some material entity at t. (axiom label in BFO2 Reference: [083-003])

label: figure
Defs: An information content entity consisting of a two dimensional arrangement of information content entities such that the arrangement itself is about something.

label: post-embryonic development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the organism over time, from the completion of embryonic development to the mature structure. See embryonic development.

label: attenuate
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s gradually tapering to a slender point.

label: granulocyte differentiation
Defs: The process in which a myeloid precursor cell acquires the specialized features of a granulocyte. Granulocytes are a class of leukocytes characterized by the presence of granules in their cytoplasm. These cells are active in allergic immune reactions such as arthritic inflammation and rashes. This class includes basophils, eosinophils and neutrophils.

label: corneal primordium
Defs: Portion of tissue that is part of the eye and gives rise to the mature, fully layered cornea.

label: positive regulation of macromolecule biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a macromolecule, any molecule of high relative molecular mass, the structure of which essentially comprises the multiple repetition of units derived, actually or conceptually, from molecules of low relative molecular mass.

label: basement membrane assembly
Defs: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a basement membrane, a part of the extracellular region that consists of a thin layer of dense material found in various animal tissues interposed between the cells and the adjacent connective tissue.

label: cytoskeleton organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures.

label: increased magnetism
Defs: A magnetism which is relatively high.

label: endocardium
Defs: The endocardium is an anatomical structure comprised of an endothelium and an extracellular matrix that forms the innermost layer of tissue of the heart, and lines the heart chambers[GO].

label: dysplastic
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting an alteration in size, shape or organization of its constituent cells.

label: positive regulation of skeletal muscle cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of skeletal muscle cell proliferation.

label: hindbrain-spinal cord boundary
Defs: An anatomical boundary that adjacent_to a hindbrain and adjacent_to a spinal cord.

label: positive regulation of glutamate secretion
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the controlled release of glutamate.

label: fermion
Defs: Particle of half-integer spin quantum number following Fermi-Dirac statistics. Fermions are named after Enrico Fermi.

label: 1-D extent
Defs: A size quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s extension in one dimension.

label: firm
Defs: A hardness quality of giving significant resistance to pressure.

label: negative regulation of defense response
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of a defense response.

label: myelinating Schwann cell
Defs: A neuroglial cell of the peripheral nervous system which forms the insulating myelin sheaths of peripheral axons.

label: skin mucous gland
Defs: A mucous gland that is part of the skin.

label: dark orange
Defs: A color consisting of orange color and low brightness.

label: tormae
Defs: The apodeme at either side of the proximal margin of the labrum.

label: regulation of skeletal muscle hypertrophy
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of skeletal muscle hypertrophy.

label: organochalcogen compound
Defs: An organochalcogen compound is a compound containing at least one carbon-chalcogen bond.

label: acetate catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of acetate, the anion of acetic acid.

label: positive regulation of collagen biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of collagen, any of a group of fibrous proteins of very high tensile strength that form the main component of connective tissue in animals.

label: reproductive gland secretion
Defs: A portion of organism substance that is secreted by a reproductive gland.

label: anterodorsal orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed anterodorsally.

label: 2nd arch mesenchyme from head mesenchyme
Defs: Mesenchyme that develops_from a head mesenchyme from mesoderm and is part of a 2nd arch mesenchyme.

label: neck cartilage
Defs: A cartilage that is part of a neck [Automatically generated definition].

label: regulation of hyaluronan biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of hyaluronan biosynthetic process.

label: embryonic cleavage
Defs: The first few specialized divisions of an activated animal egg.

label: alive
Defs: A viability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s condition before death.

label: cytokine production
Defs: The appearance of a cytokine due to biosynthesis or secretion following a cellular stimulus, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label: positive regulation of cellular response to insulin stimulus
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cellular response to insulin stimulus.

label: mesenchyme condensation cell
Defs: A mesenchymal cell in embryonic development found in a contracting mass and that gives rise to osteoprogenitors.

label: abdominal tergite I
Defs: Is the abdominal tergite of the preabdomen that is attached to the posterior margin of the tergum by the metanoto-abdominal tergite I conjunctiva and to the anterior margin of the abdominal tergite II by the abdominal tergite I-abdominal tergite II conjunctiva.

label: glutamine family amino acid metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving amino acids of the glutamine family, comprising arginine, glutamate, glutamine and proline.

label: spinal cord motor neuron migration
Defs: The orderly movement of a spinal cord motor neuron from one site to another. A spinal cord motor neuron is a motor neuron that passes from the spinal cord toward or to a muscle and conducts an impulse that causes movement.

label: cellular detoxification
Defs: Any process carried out at the cellular level that reduces or removes the toxicity of a toxic substance. These may include transport of the toxic substance away from sensitive areas and to compartments or complexes whose purpose is sequestration of the toxic substance.

label: thoracic segment of trunk
Defs: Subdivision of trunk that lies between the head and the abdomen.

label: columnar/cuboidal epithelial cell development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a columnar/cuboidal epithelial cell over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A columnar/cuboidal epithelial cell is a cell usually found in a two dimensional sheet with a free surface. Columnar/cuboidal epithelial cells take on the shape of a column or cube.

label: midbrain morphogenesis
Defs: The developmental process by which a midbrain is generated and organized.

label: rhombomere morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structure of the rhombomere is generated and organized. Rhombomeres are transverse segments of the developing rhombencephalon. Rhombomeres are lineage restricted, express different genes from one another, and adopt different developmental fates.

label: regulation of secretion
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the controlled release of a substance from a cell or a tissue.

label: positive regulation of glutamate metabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of glutamate metabolic process.

label: ventral lobe of eye
Defs: The ventral region of the eye cuticle.

label: endothelium of artery
Defs: An endothelium that is part of an artery [Automatically generated definition].

label: negative regulation of protein phosphorylation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the rate of addition of phosphate groups to amino acids within a protein.

label: alkali metal ion binding
Defs: Binding to an alkali metal ion; alkali metals are those elements in group Ia of the periodic table, with the exception of hydrogen.

label: endothelial cell morphogenesis
Defs: The change in form (cell shape and size) that occurs during the differentiation of an endothelial cell.

label: negative regulation of vascular associated smooth muscle cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of vascular associated smooth muscle cell apoptotic process.

label: regulation of antigen processing and presentation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of antigen processing and presentation.

label: organic group
Defs: Any substituent group or skeleton containing carbon.

label: protandrous hermaphroditism
Defs: A protandrous quality whereby organisms start out as male and change to hermaphrodite at a later life stage.

label: establishment of cell polarity involved in gastrulation cell migration
Defs: The specification and formation of anisotropic intracellular organization that contributes to the self-propelled directed movement of an ameboid cell taking part in gastrulation.

label: cellular response to lipid
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a lipid stimulus.

label: apical surface
Defs: Anatomical surface that is located on the apical side of the body or body part.

label: paedomorphic growth
Defs: A heterochronic growth quality inhering in an organism, structure, or group of organisms by virtue of the bearer\'s reduced growth.

label: dendritic cell dendrite assembly
Defs: Formation of dendrites, branched cellular projections (or cytoplasmic extension) that are extended from the surface of a dendritic immune cell, and which enable the cell to sample luminal pathogens and increase the surface area for antigen presentation to T cells.

label: anatomical histological quality
Defs: A quality inhering in an anotomical structure by virtue of its capacity to be stained by specific histological dyes.

label: decreased osmolality
Defs: An osmolality which is relatively low.

label: myeloblast
Defs: The most primitive precursor in the granulocytic series, having fine, evenly distributed chromatin, several nucleoli, a high nuclear-to-cytoplasmic ration (5:1-7:1), and a nongranular basophilic cytoplasm. They reside in the bone marrow.

label: regulation of cardioblast differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cardioblast differentiation, the process in which a relatively unspecialized mesodermal cell acquires the specialized structural and/or functional features of a cardioblast. A cardioblast is a cardiac precursor cell. It is a cell that has been committed to a cardiac fate, but will undergo more cell division rather than terminally differentiating.

label: translation regulator activity
Defs: Any molecular function involved in the initiation, activation, perpetuation, repression or termination of polypeptide synthesis at the ribosome.

label: reflectivity
Defs: A radiation reflective quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the ratio of the energy of a wave reflected from its surface to the energy possessed by the wave striking the bearer\'s surface.

label: negative regulation of dendritic cell dendrite assembly
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of dendritic cell dendrite assembly.

label: melanocyte apoptotic process
Defs: Any apoptotic process in a melanocyte, the main structural component of the epidermis.

label: aminoglycan metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving aminoglycans, any polymer containing amino groups that consists of more than about 10 monosaccharide residues joined to each other by glycosidic linkages.

label: tentorio-premental muscle
Defs: The cranio-labial muscle that is attached to the posterior tentorial arm and the prementum.

label: cell projection assembly
Defs: Formation of a prolongation or process extending from a cell, e.g. a flagellum or axon.

label: interleukin-3 receptor subunit alpha (mouse)
Defs: An interleukin-3 receptor class 2 alpha chain that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: pigment granule transport
Defs: The directed movement of pigment granules into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: transcription factor PU.1 (mouse)
Defs: A transcription factor PU.1 that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: protein-containing complex disassembly
Defs: The disaggregation of a protein-containing macromolecular complex into its constituent components.

label: embryonic organ morphogenesis
Defs: Morphogenesis, during the embryonic phase, of a tissue or tissues that work together to perform a specific function or functions. Morphogenesis is the process in which anatomical structures are generated and organized. Organs are commonly observed as visibly distinct structures, but may also exist as loosely associated clusters of cells that work together to perform a specific function or functions.

label: foregut duodenum mesentery
Defs: A mesentery of duodenum that is part of a foregut.

label: membrane potential
Defs: A quality inhering in a cell\'s plasma membrane by virtue of the electrical potential difference across it.

label: peptide hormone secretion
Defs: The regulated release of a peptide hormone from a cell.

label: consistency
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s density, firmness, or viscosity.

label: quality of an ecological community
Defs: A quality that inheres in a community.

label: multi-unit eye
Defs: An eye consisting of multiple light-sensing organs.

label: cuticle of labial palpomere
Defs: The cuticle of the mere that is part of the labial palpus.

label: normal cellular motility
Defs: A cellular motility which is normal or average.

label: decreased radiopacity
Defs: A radiopacity that is relatively low.

label: epicardial adipocyte
Defs: A fat cell that is part of the epicardial fat.

label: cystic artery
Defs: An artery that supplies oxygenated blood to the cystic duct.

label: increased porosity
Defs: An increase in porosity.

label: zygomorphic
Defs: A symmetry quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being capable of division into symmetrical halves by only one longitudinal plane passing through the axis.

label: metatibio-metatarsal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that encircles the metatarsus by joining the distal margin of the metatibia and the proximal margin of the metatarsus.

label: dopamine transport
Defs: The directed movement of dopamine into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Dopamine is a catecholamine neurotransmitter and a metabolic precursor of noradrenaline and adrenaline.

label: cerebral cortex
Defs: The thin layer of gray matter on the surface of the cerebral hemisphere that develops from the telencephalon. It consists of the neocortex (6 layered cortex or isocortex), the hippocampal formation and the olfactory cortex.

label: lung vasculature
Defs: The lung vasculature is composed of the tubule structures that carry blood or lymph in the lungs[GO].

label: melanoblast
Defs: A cell that originates from the neural crest and differentiates into a pigment cell.

label: radius
Defs: A length quality which is equal to the length of any straight line segment that passes from the center of a circle to any endpoint on the circular boundary. The radius is half of the diameter.

label: amine metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving any organic compound that is weakly basic in character and contains an amino or a substituted amino group. Amines are called primary, secondary, or tertiary according to whether one, two, or three carbon atoms are attached to the nitrogen atom.

label: data format specification
Defs:
A data format specification is the information content borne by the document published defining the specification.
Example: The ISO document specifying what encompasses an XML document; The instructions in a XSD file

label: abdominal sternite VIII
Defs: The abdominal sternite of the postabdomen that is attached to the posterior margin of the abdominal sternite VII by the abdominal sternite VII-abdominal sternite VIII conjunctiva. In males it is attached to the anterior margin of the abdominal sternite IX by the abdominal sternite VIII-abdominal sternite IX conjunctiva. In females it is attached to the anterior margin of the gonocoxa.

label: positive regulation of retina development in camera-type eye
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of retina development in camera-type eye.

label: genitalia morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of genitalia are generated and organized. The genitalia are the organs of reproduction or generation, external and internal.

label: positive regulation of protein localization to cilium
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to cilium.

label: regulation of steroid biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of steroids, compounds with a 1,2,cyclopentanoperhydrophenanthrene nucleus.

label: retinal rod cell development
Defs: Development of a rod cell, one of the sensory cells in the eye that reacts to the presence of light. Rod cells contain the photopigment rhodopsin or porphyropsin and are responsible for vision in dim light.

label: retrograde axonal protein transport
Defs: The directed movement of proteins along microtubules from the cell periphery toward the cell body in nerve cell axons.

label: left pulmonary vein
Defs: Vein that drains left lung and returns blood to the heart.

label: fibrinopurulent
Defs: A composition quality inhering in exudate by virtue of the bearer\'s containing fibrin.

label: respiratory system venule
Defs: A venule that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

label: tumor necrosis factor receptor superfamily member 11A
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human TNFRSF11A gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: mucosa of dorsum of tongue
Defs: A mucosa that is part of a dorsum of tongue.

label: unstratified
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking a layered configuration.

label: truncated
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s terminating abruptly by having or as if having an end or point cut off.

label: enteroendocrine cell of small intestine
Defs: An enteroendocrine cell that is located in the small intestine.

label: cellular pigmentation
Defs: The deposition or aggregation of coloring matter in a cell.

label: sensory ganglion
Defs: The clusters of neurons in the somatic peripheral nervous system which contain the cell bodies of sensory nerve axons, interneurons and non-neuronal supporting cells.

label: antero-ventral region
Defs: Anatomical region that overlaps the anterior and ventral regions of a body or body part.

label: peristalsis
Defs: A wavelike sequence of involuntary muscular contraction and relaxation that passes along a tubelike structure, such as the intestine, impelling the contents onwards.

label: beta-adrenergic agonist
Defs: An agent that selectively binds to and activates beta-adrenergic receptors.

label: non-potable
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer not being suitable for use as a safe means of hydration.

label: mass
Defs: A physical quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the proportion of the bearer\'s amount of matter.

label: patchy pigmentation
Defs: A degree of pigmentation quality that is diversified with patches, or irregularity.

label: has fewer parts of type
Defs: The bearer of this quality has_part < n AND has_part > 0 of the indicated entity type, where n is the normal amount for a comparable organism. Note that the bearer of the quality is the whole, not the part. Formally: If a bearer entity e has fewer parts of type X at time t, then the number of instances x of X at t such that x part_of e is < n, where n is either the normal number for comparable entities, or n is stated explicitly.

label: rhythm quality
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s movement or variation characterized by the regular recurrence or alternation of different quantities or conditions.

label: duodenum
Defs: The first part of the small intestine. At the junction of the stomach and the duodenum the alimentary canal is inflected. The duodenum first goes anteriorly for a short distance, turns dorsally, and eventually caudally, thus it is a U-shaped structure with two horizontal sections (a ventral and a dorsal one).

label: regulation of kinase activity
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of kinase activity, the catalysis of the transfer of a phosphate group, usually from ATP, to a substrate molecule.

label: ventral side
Defs: An anatomical region that is the entire part of an anatomical structure ventral to a horizontal plane and bounded on one side by the same horizontal plane.

label: polarity
Defs: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of whether or not the molecular entity has a separation of electric charge which leads to the molecule having an electric dipole.

label: stomach smooth muscle
Defs: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a stomach [Automatically generated definition].

label: integral component of plasma membrane
Defs: The component of the plasma membrane consisting of the gene products and protein complexes having at least some part of their peptide sequence embedded in the hydrophobic region of the membrane.

label: regulation of T cell mediated immunity
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of T cell mediated immunity.

label: hyaluronic acid
Defs: A mucopolysaccharide composed of N-acetylglucosamine and glucuronic acid subunits. It is found in the connective tissues of vertebrates. A principal constituent of the extracellular matrix (ECM), it mediates the growth and metastasis of tumour cells.

label: negative regulation of vesicle fusion with Golgi apparatus
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of vesicle fustion with Golgi apparatus.

label: cardiac septum development
Defs: The progression of a cardiac septum over time, from its initial formation to the mature structure.

label: positive regulation of protein transport
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of a protein into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: bone of lower jaw
Defs: Any bone that is part of the lower jaw skeleton. This includes (when present): the dentary/mandible, the articular, the splenial, the suprangular.

label: positive regulation of keratinocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of keratinocyte differentiation.

label: oligodendrocyte differentiation
