Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized features of an oligodendrocyte. An oligodendrocyte is a type of glial cell involved in myelinating the axons of neurons in the central nervous system.

label: regulation of mesenchymal stem cell migration
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mesenchymal stem cell migration.

label: colonic mucosa
Defs: Mucosa that is part of a colon. The mucosa of the colon is lined by a simple columnar epithelium with a thin brush border and numerous goblet cells.

label: mesenchymal cell differentiation involved in renal system development
Defs: The process in which relatively unspecialized cells acquire specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize the mesenchymal cells of the renal system as it progresses from its formation to the mature state.

label: negative regulation of sulfur metabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving sulfur or compounds containing sulfur.

label: regulation of ectoderm development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of ectoderm development.

label: fleshy
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer resembling or containing flesh.

label: regulation of antimicrobial peptide secretion
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of antimicrobial peptide secretion.

label: genital chamber
Defs: The region of cuticle that is connected to the oviduct, the bursa copulatrix and the gonocoxa VIII, and is adjacent to the gonopore.

label: requirements section
Defs: A part of a document about a resource described in the document, e.g. software, that describes the requirements necessary to use the resource, e.g. operating systems, hardware, etc. in the case of a software resource.

label: secretion of exocrine gland
Defs: A portion of organism substance that is produced by exocrine glands.

label: cleaving embryo
Defs: Organism at the cleavage stage.

label: cardiac skeleton development
Defs: The progression of the cardiac skeleton over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The cardiac skeleton is a specialized extracellular matrix that separates the atria from the ventricles and provides physical support for the heart.

label: protein phosphorylation
Defs: The process of introducing a phosphate group on to a protein.

label: multicellular organismal iron ion homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of the distribution of iron stores within tissues and organs of a multicellular organism.

label: data set
Defs: A data item that is an aggregate of other data items of the same type that have something in common. Averages and distributions can be determined for data sets.

label: inorganic cation transmembrane transport
Defs: A process in which an inorganic cation is transported from one side of a membrane to the other by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: diagonal to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located on a sloping line joining two nonconsecutive points of an entity relative to another entity.

label: protein localization to synapse
Defs: Any process in which a protein is transported to, and/or maintained at the synapse, the junction between a nerve fiber of one neuron and another neuron or muscle fiber or glial cell.

label: friable
Defs: Easily reduced to powder or easily fragmentable or crumbly.

label: acute angle to
Defs: An angle which is less than 90 degrees.

label: transcriptional activator Myb (mouse)
Defs: A myb proto-oncogene protein that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: nuclear migration along microtubule
Defs: The directed movement of the nucleus along microtubules within the cell, mediated by motor proteins.

label: neuropeptide binding
Defs: Interacting selectively and non-covalently and stoichiometrically with neuropeptides, peptides with direct synaptic effects (peptide neurotransmitters) or indirect modulatory effects on the nervous system (peptide neuromodulators).

label: pectoral appendage musculature
Defs: Any collection of muscles that is part of a pectoral appendage.

label: female receptivity
Defs: A behavioral quality which holds by virtue of extent of the receptiveness of a female to male advances.

label: head blood vessel
Defs: A blood vessel that is part of a head [Automatically generated definition].

label: submucosa of trachea
Defs: A submucosa that is part of a trachea.

label: cystic
Defs: Structure quality that is the presence of at least one sac-like closed membranous structure containing one or more liquid or solid organism substances.

label: posterior segment of eyeball
Defs: Any of the parts of the eye that lie in back of, or dorsal to, the lens (but not inclusive).

label: paraxial cell
Defs: A cell in the area of mesoderm in the neurulating embryo that flanks and forms simultaneously with the neural tube. The cells of this region give rise to somites.

label: negative regulation of Schwann cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of Schwann cell differentiation.

label: cranial nerve
Defs: Cranial nerves are nerves that emerge directly from the brain, in contrast to spinal nerves, which emerge from segments of the spinal cord.

label: secretory granule maturation
Defs: Steps required to transform an immature secretory vesicle into a mature secretory vesicle. Typically proceeds through homotypic membrane fusion and membrane remodelling.

label: discolored
Defs: A color quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being altered or spoiled in color.

label: positive regulation of glycoprotein metabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of glycoprotein metabolic process.

label: regulation of hematopoietic stem cell migration
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of hematopoietic stem cell migration.

label: negative regulation of neutrophil differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of neutrophil differentiation.

label: regulation of execution phase of apoptosis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of execution phase of apoptosis.

label: regulation of mesenchymal cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mesenchymal cell apoptotic process.

label: receptor-type tyrosine-protein phosphatase C
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human PTPRC gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. It is composed of an extracellular domain, a single transmembrane segment and two tandem intracytoplasmic protein-tyrosine phosphatase domains. Contains 1 to 3 copies of the Fibronectin type III domain (Pfam:PF00041) followed by two copies of the Protein-tyrosine phosphatase (Pfam:PF00102) domain. Receptor-type tyrosine-protein phosphatase C (CD45) regulates signal transduction and lymphocyte activation by specific association with receptor molecules on T and B cells. Multiple isoforms of CD45 (180-235 kDa) can be generated asa result of alternative splicing of three variable exons 4(A), 5(B) and 6(C), encoding sequences at the N-terminal extracellular domain of the molecule.

label: submucosa of sigmoid colon
Defs: A submucosa that is part of a sigmoid colon [Automatically generated definition].

label: amino acid transmembrane transport
Defs: The process in which an amino acid is transported across a membrane.

label: hyponastic
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting a upward bending of its leaves or other plant parts.

label: positive regulation of hematopoietic stem cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of hematopoietic stem cell differentiation.

label: skeletal muscle fiber differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a skeletal muscle fiber cell. Skeletal muscle fiber differentiation starts with myoblast fusion and the appearance of specific cell markers (this is the cell development step). Then individual skeletal muscle fibers fuse to form bigger myotubes and start to contract.

label: placenta blood vessel development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a blood vessel of the placenta over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: regulation of bile acid secretion
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the controlled release of bile acid from a cell or a tissue.

label: structured
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having distinct structure.

label: azurophil granule
Defs: Primary lysosomal granule found in neutrophil granulocytes. Contains a wide range of hydrolytic enzymes and is released into the extracellular fluid.

label: establishment of melanosome localization
Defs: The directed movement of a melanosome to a specific location.

label: trans-synaptic signalling via exosome
Defs: Transynaptic signaling in which the ligand is carried across the synapse by an exosome.

label: protein localization to nucleus
Defs: A process in which a protein transports or maintains the localization of another protein to the nucleus.

label: islet of Langerhans
Defs: The clusters of hormone-producing cells that are scattered throughout the pancreas.

label: quadripartite
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being divided into four parts.

label: abdominal sternite III-abdominal sternite IV conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect abdomen that connects the abdominal sternite III and the abdominal sternite IV.

label: decreased behavioural activity
Defs: A behavioral quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting reduced activity.

label: labiolingually compressed
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being compressed from the side facing the lips to the side facing the tongue.

label: positive regulation of myeloid dendritic cell antigen processing and presentation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of myeloid dendritic cell antigen processing and presentation.

label: obsolete_survival curve
Defs: A survival curve is a report graph which is a graphical representation of data where the percentage of survival is plotted as a function of time.

label: regulation of vascular associated smooth muscle cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of vascular associated smooth muscle cell apoptotic process.

label: ventro-lateral region
Defs: Anatomical region that overlaps the ventral and lateral regions of a body or body part.

label: extracellular matrix
Defs: A structure lying external to one or more cells, which provides structural support, biochemical or biomechanical cues for cells or tissues.

label: negative regulation of digestive system process
Defs: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of a digestive system process, a physical, chemical, or biochemical process carried out by living organisms to break down ingested nutrients into components that may be easily absorbed and directed into metabolism.

label: venous blood vessel morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of venous blood vessels are generated and organized. Veins are blood vessels that transport blood from the body and its organs to the heart.

label: abdominal tergite I-abdominal tergite II conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect abdomen that connects the abdominal tergite I and the abdominal tergite II.

label: transepithelial ammonium transport
Defs: The directed movement of ammonium ions from one side of an epithelium to the other.

label: overlapping
Defs: Overlap with quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being positioned over another entity so as to cover some portion of it.

label: anterograde dendritic transport
Defs: The directed movement of organelles or molecules along microtubules from the cell body toward the postsynapse in dendrites.

label: ciliated epithelial cell
Defs: An epithelial cell that has a cilia.

label: regulation of ribosome biogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of ribosome biogenesis. Ribosome biogenesis is the cellular process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of ribosome subunits.

label: second maxillar palpopalpal muscle
Defs: The insect cranio-maxillar muscle that is attached to the second maxillar palpomere and  the third maxillar palpomere.

label: cuticle of cardo
Defs: The sclerite of the insect maxilla that is attached to the head capsule by the oral foraminal conjunctiva and to the cuticle of stipes by the stipito-cardinal conjunctiva.

label: organ growth
Defs: The increase in size or mass of an organ. Organs are commonly observed as visibly distinct structures, but may also exist as loosely associated clusters of cells that function together as to perform a specific function.

label: stipito-galeal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect maxilla that connects the stipes and the galea.

label: regulation of RNA biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of RNA biosynthetic process.

label: transmembrane receptor protein kinase activity
Defs: Combining with a signal and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity by catalysis of the reaction: a protein + ATP = a phosphoprotein + ADP.

label: cell cluster organ
Defs: A small cluster of cells of various types which form a discrete structure, largely delimited by a morphological boundary and whose components work together to make the whole structure capable of a specific function.

label: erythrocyte
Defs: A red blood cell. In mammals, mature erythrocytes are biconcave disks containing hemoglobin whose function is to transport oxygen.

label: axoneme
Defs: The bundle of microtubules and associated proteins that forms the core of cilia (also called flagella) in eukaryotic cells and is responsible for their movements.

label: colonic epithelium
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a colon [Automatically generated definition].

label: regulation of norepinephrine secretion
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of norepinephrine.

label: pronotum
Defs: The notum or sclerite on the dorsal region of the prothorax that is attached to cranial muscles, procoxal muscles, contiuous posterioirly with the neck membrane and with pronoto-propleural conjunctiva and not adjacent (not touching) to the procoxa.

label: crown like
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a shape like a crown.

label: acetylcholine receptor signaling pathway
Defs: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of an acetylcholine receptor binding to one of its physiological ligands.

label: aortic smooth muscle cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a smooth muscle cell surrounding the aorta.

label: erose
Defs: A surface feature shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having an irregularly toothed edge.

label: raphe nuclei neuron
Defs: A neuron of the raphe nuclei.

label: intestinal epithelial cell
Defs: An epithelial cell of the intestine.

label: sagittal plane
Defs: Anatomical plane that divides a bilateral body into left and right parts, not necessarily of even size.

label: neural groove
Defs: The median dorsal longitudinal groove formed in the embryo by the neural plate after the appearance of the neural folds.

label: decreased life span
Defs: A life span which is relatively low.

label: peg-like
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a short and stout cylindrical shape.

label: regulation of pH
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium of hydrogen ions, thereby modulating the internal pH, within an organism or cell.

label: multi-colored
Defs: A color pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of bearer\'s having two or more hues or degrees of saturation.

label: spinal cord motor neuron differentiation
Defs: The process in which neuroepithelial cells in the ventral neural tube acquire specialized structural and/or functional features of motor neurons. Motor neurons innervate an effector (muscle or glandular) tissue and are responsible for transmission of motor impulses from the brain to the periphery. Differentiation includes the processes involved in commitment of a cell to a specific fate.

label: response to peptide hormone
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a peptide hormone stimulus. A peptide hormone is any of a class of peptides that are secreted into the blood stream and have endocrine functions in living animals.

label: animal organ development
Defs: Development of a tissue or tissues that work together to perform a specific function or functions. Development pertains to the process whose specific outcome is the progression of a structure over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Organs are commonly observed as visibly distinct structures, but may also exist as loosely associated clusters of cells that work together to perform a specific function or functions.

label: epithelium of mucosa
Defs: A layer of epithelial cells on the surface of the mucosa.

label: increased quality
Defs: A quality that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.

label: regulation of cilium movement
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of cilium movement, the directed, self-propelled movement of a cilium.

label: negative regulation of glutamatergic neuron differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of glutamatergic neuron differentiation.

label: negative regulation of osteoclast differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of osteoclast differentiation.

label: regulation of translation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of proteins by the translation of mRNA or circRNA.

label: basal procoxal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that encircles the procoxa and connects it to the ventral and lateral regions of the prothorax.

label: regulation of germ cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of germ cell proliferation.

label: wrinkled
Defs: A grooved texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being marked by one or more creases in a normally smooth surface.

label: tomentose
Defs: A quality of being covered with short, dense, matted hairs.

label: common hepatic artery
Defs: In anatomy, the common hepatic artery is a short blood vessel that supplies oxygenated blood to the liver, pylorus (a part of the stomach), duodenum (a part of the small intestine) and pancreas. It arises from the celiac artery and has the following branches:.

label: dorsalized
Defs: A malformed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s gross morphology containing what are normally dorsal structures and missing some or all of what are normally ventral structures.

label: hypotrophic
Defs: A decreased size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting reduced size of a cell or constituent group of cells (for example, organ).

label: scrobiculate
Defs: A texture that is uniformly covered in short, oblong, or trench-like depressions.

label: Golgi vesicle transport
Defs: The directed movement of substances into, out of or within the Golgi apparatus, mediated by vesicles.

label: decreased anterior-posterior diameter
Defs: An anterior-posterior diameter quality which is relatively small.

label: femoral muscle
Defs: The somatic muscle that inserts in the femur.

label: cardiovascular system
Defs: Anatomical system that has as its parts the heart and blood vessels.

label: response to acetate
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an acetate stimulus.

label: regulation of defense response to insect
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of defense response to insect.

label: lateral tentorio-scapal muscle
Defs: The cranio-antennal muscle that extends between the dorsal or anterior tentorial arm and the proximo-lateral margin of the scapus.

label: fragmented
Defs: Existing or functioning as though broken into separate parts; disorganized; disunified.

label: secretion
Defs: The controlled release of a substance by a cell or a tissue.

label: regulation of microvillus organization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a microvillus.

label: arterial system endothelium
Defs: An endothelium that is part of an arterial system [Automatically generated definition].

label: positive regulation of cardiac neural crest cell migration involved in outflow tract morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac neural crest cell migration involved in outflow tract morphogenesis.

label: negative regulation of neuroinflammatory response
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of neuroinflammatory response.

label: decreased turgor
Defs: A turgor which is relatively low.

label: regulation of synapse organization
Defs: Any process that modulates the physical form of a synapse, the junction between a neuron and a target (neuron, muscle, or secretory cell).

label: negative regulation of muscle cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate or frequency of muscle cell apoptotic process, a form of programmed cell death induced by external or internal signals that trigger the activity of proteolytic caspases whose actions dismantle a muscle cell and result in its death.

label: capillary of colon
Defs: A capillary that is part of the colon.

label: oocyte morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the structures of an oocyte are generated and organized. This process occurs while the initially relatively unspecialized cell is acquiring the specialized features of an oocyte.

label: liver blood vessel
Defs: A blood vessel that is part of a liver.

label: preganglionic parasympathetic fiber
Defs: A cholinergic axonal fibers projecting from the CNS to a parasympathetic ganglion.

label: male sterile
Defs: A male fertility quality inhering in a male by virtue of the bearer\'s being incapable of initiating, sustaining, or supporting reproduction.

label: flow rate
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s motion characteristic.

label: glossopharyngeal nerve development
Defs: Various sensory and motor branches of the glossopharyngeal nerve supply nerve connections to the pharynx and back of the tongue. The branchial motor component contains motor fibers that innervate muscles that elevate the pharynx and larynx, and the tympanic branch supplies parasympathetic fibers to the otic ganglion.

label: carbamoyl group
Defs: The univalent carboacyl group formed by loss of -OH from the carboxy group of carbamic acid.

label: heart elastic tissue
Defs: The type of heart connective tissue found in the endocardial layer that consists mainly of elastic fibers.

label: near projecting
Defs: A neuron projection quality that is a characteristic of neurons with projections that terminate locally rather than distantly.

label: negative regulation of striated muscle tissue development
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of striated muscle development.

label: cardiac neural crest cell development involved in outflow tract morphogenesis
Defs: The process aimed at the progression of a cardiac neural crest cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to its specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell that contributes to the shaping of the outflow tract.

label: pyloric sphincter
Defs: A strong ring of smooth muscle at the end of the pyloric canal which lets food pass from the stomach to the duodenum. It receives sympathetic innervation from the celiac ganglion[WP].

label: normal radioactivity
Defs: A radioactivity which is relatively normal or average

label: visceral abdominal adipose tissue
Defs: Subcutaneous adipose tissue that is located in the peritoneal cavity.

label: symmetrical
Defs: A symmetry quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being capable of division by a longitudinal plane into similar halves.

label: negative regulation of cartilage development
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of cartilage development, the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the cartilage over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Cartilage is a connective tissue dominated by extracellular matrix containing collagen type II and large amounts of proteoglycan, particularly chondroitin sulfate.

label: positive regulation of oocyte development
Defs: Any process that increases the rate or extent of the process whose specific outcome is the progression of an oocyte over time, from initial commitment of the cell to its specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell.

label: study limitations section
Defs: A part of a document about biases or short comings related to the study design and execution.

label: striated muscle tissue development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a striated muscle over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Striated muscle contain fibers that are divided by transverse bands into striations, and cardiac and skeletal muscle are types of striated muscle. Skeletal muscle myoblasts fuse to form myotubes and eventually multinucleated muscle fibers. The fusion of cardiac cells is very rare and can only form binucleate cells.

label: metatrochantero-metafemoral conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that encircles the metafemur by joining the distal margin of the metatrochanter and the proximal margin of the metafemur.

label: positive regulation of apoptotic process involved in morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of apoptotic process involved in morphogenesis.

label: cellular response to monoamine stimulus
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a monoamine stimulus. A monoamine is any of a group of molecular messengers that contain one amino group that is connected to an aromatic ring by ethylene group (-CH2-CH2-). Monoamines are derived from the aromatic amino acids phenylalanine, tyrosine, histidine and tryptophan.

label: nervous system process
Defs: A organ system process carried out by any of the organs or tissues of neurological system.

label: increased waxiness
Defs: A waxiness which is relatively high.

label: cloacal lumen
Defs: An anatomical space that is enclosed by a cloaca.

label: neoplastic, deeply invasive
Defs: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to invade surrounding tissues to a large extend.

label: positive regulation of glutamate secretion, neurotransmission
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of glutamate secretion, where glutamate acts as a neurotransmitter.

label: rostrum
Defs: The region of cuticle of the insect head that is proximal to the mouthparts and composed of frons and clypeus.

label: increased duration of temperature
Defs: A duration of temperature which is greater relative to the normal or average in respect to the quality of temperature of enduring or continuing in time.

label: myeloid cell development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a myeloid cell over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: dendritic cell dendrite
Defs: A branched cellular projection (or cytoplasmic extension) that is extended from the surface of a dendritic immune cell, and which enables the cell to sample luminal pathogens and increase the surface area for antigen presentation to T cells.

label: apodeme
Defs: The solid cuticular invagination of a sclerite.

label: primary amide
Defs: A derivative of an oxoacid RkE(=O)l(OH)m (l =/= 0) in which an acidic hydroxy group has been replaced by an amino or substituted amino group.

label: positive regulation of iron ion transport
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of iron ions into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: substantia propria of cornea
Defs: The lamellated connective tissue of the cornea between the Bowman and Descemet membranes.

label: positive charge
Defs: A quality which inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the molecular entity possessing more protons overall than electrons, thus having an overall positive charge.

label: movement quality
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s participation in movement.

label: biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of substances; typically the energy-requiring part of metabolism in which simpler substances are transformed into more complex ones.

label: submental-mental conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the labium that connects the submentum and the mentum.

label: tunica intima of vein
Defs: A tunica intima that is part of a vein.

label: interlocked with
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being locked together or interconnected to another entity.

label: negative regulation of protein transport
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of a protein into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: monovalent inorganic cation
Defs: An atom or small molecule with a positive charge that does not contain carbon in covalent linkage, with a valency of one.

label: negative regulation of lipid transporter activity
Defs: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate, or extent of lipid transporter activity.

label: carbohydrate acid derivative
Defs: A carbohydrate derivative that is formally obtained from a carbohydrate acid.

label: phasic smooth muscle contraction
Defs: A process in which force is generated within phasic smooth muscle tissue, resulting in a change in muscle geometry. Force generation involves a chemo-mechanical energy conversion step that is carried out by the actin/myosin complex activity, which generates force through ATP hydrolysis. In the phasic smooth muscle, the muscle contraction occurs without an ordered sarcomeric structure. Phasic smooth muscle contraction occurs in a series of discrete contractions and relaxations.

label: wall of stomach
Defs: The layered structure that makes up the stomach, typiclly consists of a serous coat, a muscular coat, a mucous membrane, and other tissue layers in between.

label: positive regulation of mitotic cell cycle
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the rate or extent of progression through the mitotic cell cycle.

label: positive regulation of collagen binding
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of collagen binding.

label: cartilage of respiratory system
Defs: A cartilage element that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

label: three dimensional cartesian spatial coordinate datum
Defs: A cartesion spatial coordinate datum that  uses three values to specify a position within a three dimensional spatial region

label: adipose microvascular endothelial cell
Defs: Any microvascular endothelial cell that is part of a adipose tissue.

label: gastrointestinal system serosa
Defs: A serous membrane that is part of a digestive system [Automatically generated definition].

label: serosa of intestine
Defs: A serous membrane that is part of a wall of intestine [Automatically generated definition].

label: normal occurrence
Defs: An occurrence which is relatively normal.

label: mesenchymal stem cell
Defs: A connective tissue cell that normally gives rise to other cells that are organized as three-dimensional masses. In humans, this cell type is CD73-positive, CD90-positive, CD105-positive, CD45-negative, CD34-negative, and MHCII-negative. They may further differentiate into osteoblasts, adipocytes, myocytes, neurons, or chondroblasts in vitro. Originally described as residing in the bone marrow, this cell type is now known to reside in many, if not all, adult organs.

label: RNA binding
Defs: Binding to an RNA molecule or a portion thereof.

label: dermatome development
Defs: The progression of the dermatome over time, from its initial formation to the mature structure. The dermatome is the portion of a somite that will form skin.

label: deep-superficial axis
Defs: An axis that extends from an internal position to a more external position in the body or body part.

label: pharyngeal pouch 3
Defs: A pharyngeal pouch that between pharyngeal arches 3 and 4.

label: subgenal sulcus
Defs: The cuticular sulcus that is adjacent to the subgena and coincides with the subgenal ridge.

label: simple eye
Defs: An eye with one concave chamber. Note that \'simple\' does not imply a reduced level of complexity or acuity.

label: nucleate cell
Defs: A cell containing at least one nucleus.

label: cuticle of propretarsus
Defs: The cuticle of the appendage of the fore leg that is attached to the protarsus by the protarso-propretarsal conjunctiva.

label: axial muscle
Defs: One of the skeletal muscles of the head and neck, spine, and ribs.

label: brain development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the brain over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Brain development begins with patterning events in the neural tube and ends with the mature structure that is the center of thought and emotion. The brain is responsible for the coordination and control of bodily activities and the interpretation of information from the senses (sight, hearing, smell, etc.).

label: sessile (sensu zoology)
Defs: A attachment quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s inability to move about.

label: regulation of growth
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the growth of all or part of an organism so that it occurs at its proper speed, either globally or in a specific part of the organism\'s development.

label: pleural sac
Defs: A serous sac that has the pleura and the pleural cavity as parts.

label: sterno-pleural muscle
Defs: The insect thoracic muscle that extends between the sternum and the pleura.

label: positive regulation of excitatory synapse assembly
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of excitatory synapse assembly.

label: aorta tunica adventitia
Defs: The outermost layer of the aorta wall, containing connective tissue and collagen and elastic fibers.

label: mouth
Defs: The proximal portion of the digestive tract, containing the oral cavity and bounded by the oral opening. In vertebrates, this extends to the pharynx and includes gums, lips, tongue and parts of the palate. Typically also includes the teeth, except where these occur elsewhere (e.g. pharyngeal jaws) or protrude from the mouth (tusks).

label: trigeminal ganglion morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structure of a trigeminal ganglion is generated and organized.

label: furcasternum
Defs: The part of the sternum that is attached to the posterior margin of the basisternum and to the anterior margin of the spinasternum.

label: regulation of meiotic nuclear division
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of meiotic nuclear division, the process in which the nucleus of a diploid cell divides twice forming four haploid cells, one or more of which usually function as gametes.

label: myeloid cell homeostasis
Defs: The process of regulating the proliferation and elimination of myeloid cells such that the total number of myeloid cells within a whole or part of an organism is stable over time in the absence of an outside stimulus.

label: cloacal muscle
Defs: Any muscle organ that is part of a cloaca.

label: chorionic trophoblast cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which relatively unspecialized cells of the ectoplacental cone acquire specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize chorionic trophoblasts. These cells will migrate towards the spongiotrophoblast layer and give rise to syncytiotrophoblasts of the labyrinthine layer.

label: myeloid dendritic cell activation
Defs: The change in morphology and behavior of a dendritic cell resulting from exposure to a cytokine, chemokine, cellular ligand, or soluble factor.

label: netted
Defs: A color pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of bearer\'s being covered with reticulated lines of a different hue or degree of saturation.

label: cuticle of gonostylus VIII
Defs: The region of the cuticle of the postabdomen that is paired and connected to the anterior region of the gonocoxa VIII.

label: rotational curvature
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved around an axis.

label: transversely striated
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being marked by narrow lines or grooves, usually parallel, that are oriented transversely relative to the long axis of the bearer.

label: 1st arch mesenchyme
Defs: Mesenchyme that is part of a pharyngeal arch 1.

label: epinastic
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting a downward bending of its leaves or other plant parts.

label: supramolecular polymer
Defs: A polymeric supramolecular structure.

label: stepped
Defs: Having a shape or form that resembles a step of a stairway (e.g., a ledge or offset margin).

label: tissue remodeling
Defs: The reorganization or renovation of existing tissues. This process can either change the characteristics of a tissue such as in blood vessel remodeling, or result in the dynamic equilibrium of a tissue such as in bone remodeling.

label: regulation of receptor localization to synapse
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of receptor localization to synapse.

label: morphogenesis of an epithelial fold
Defs: The morphogenetic process in which an epithelial sheet bends along a linear axis.

label: fibroblast of upper back skin
Defs: A fibroblast that is part of upper back skin.

label: proepicardium development
Defs: The progression of the proepicardium from its formation to the mature structure. The proepicardium is an outpouching of the septum transversum.

label: cation transport
Defs: The directed movement of cations, atoms or small molecules with a net positive charge, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: increased perimeter
Defs: A perimeter which is relatively high.

label: publishing process
Defs: A planned process of making information, such as literature, music, and software etc., available to the public for sale or for free.

label: egg activation
Defs: The process in which the egg becomes metabolically active, initiates protein and DNA synthesis and undergoes structural changes to its cortex and/or cytoplasm.

label: mesodermal cell
Defs: A cell of the middle germ layer of the embryo.

label: abdominal sternite VII
Defs: The abdominal sternite of the preabdomen that is attached to the posterior margin of the abdominal sternite VI by the abdominal sternite VI-abdominal sternite VII conjunctiva and to the anterior margin of the abdominal sternite VIII by the abdominal sternite VII-abdominal sternite VIII conjunctiva.

label: regulation of hepatocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of hepatocyte differentiation.

label: multicellular
Defs: A cellularity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s consisting of more than one cell.

label: trophoblast
Defs: The mesectodermal cell layer arising from the trophectoderm that erodes the uterine mucosa and contributes to the formation of the placenta.

label: ester
Defs: A compound formally derived from an oxoacid RkE(=O)l(OH)m (l > 0) and an alcohol, phenol, heteroarenol, or enol by linking with formal loss of water from an acidic hydroxy group of the former and a hydroxy group of the latter.

label: nerve conductivity
Defs: A conductivity quality inhering in motor and sensory nerves by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to convey electricity.

label: sonic
Defs: A sound frequency in the range of 20 to 20.000 Hz.

label: cartilage tissue
Defs: Skeletal tissue that is avascular, rich in glycosaminoglycans (GAGs) and typically includes chondrocytes within isolated lacunae. Cartilage tissue is deposited by chondroblasts.

label: ovulation cycle process
Defs: A process involved in the sexual cycle seen in females, often with physiologic changes in the endometrium that recur at regular intervals during the reproductive years.

label: positive regulation of mesenchymal cell proliferation involved in lung development
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of mesenchymal cell proliferation involved in lung development.

label: respiratory tube development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the respiratory tube over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The respiratory tube is assumed to mean any tube in the respiratory tract.

label: serotonin secretion
Defs: The regulated release of serotonin by a cell. Serotonin (5-hydroxytryptamine, or 5-HT) is a monoamine synthesised in serotonergic neurons in the central nervous system, enterochromaffin cells in the gastrointestinal tract and some immune system cells.

label: mesophragmo-abdominal tergite I muscle
Defs: The insect thoracic muscle that extends between the mesophragma and the abdominal tergite I.

label: response to bile acid
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a bile acid stimulus.

label: camera-type eye photoreceptor cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized features of a photoreceptor cell in a camera-type eye.

label: trachea gland
Defs: A tubuloacinar seromucous gland that is located principally in the submucosa of the trachea. Excretory ducts from this gland pass through the lamina propria to the tracheal lumen.

label: regulation of translation at synapse
Defs: Any process that regulates translation occurring at the synapse.

label: hyaline cartilage tissue
Defs: Cartilage tissue primarily composed of type II collagen (thin fibrils) and a glassy appearance.

label: profemoro-protibial conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that encircles the protibia by joining the distal margin of the profemur and the proximal margin of the protibia.

label: midbrain-hindbrain boundary development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the midbrain-hindbrain boundary over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The midbrain-hindbrain domain of the embryonic brain is comprised of the mesencephalic vesicle and the first rhombencephalic vesicle at early somitogenesis stages.

label: triangular
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having three angles.

label: erythrocyte differentiation
Defs: The process in which a myeloid precursor cell acquires specializes features of an erythrocyte.

label: future dermis
Defs: Mesenchyme that has the potential to develop into a dermis.

label: serous gland
Defs: A gland in which the principal secretory cells are serous secreting cells.

label: decreased rate of continuous process
Defs: A rate of output of a continuous process that is relatively low.

label: decreased contamination
Defs: A decrease in contamination.

label: saturated blue
Defs: A color consisting of blue hue and high saturation.

label: lens of camera-type eye
Defs: Transparent part of camera-type eye that helps to refract light to be focused on the retina.

label: water composition
Defs: A composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the quantities or relative ratios of water of the inhering entity.

label: cellular response to glycoprotein
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a glycoprotein stimulus.

label: hexose
Defs: Any six-carbon monosaccharide which in its linear form contains either an aldehyde group at position 1 (aldohexose) or a ketone group at position 2 (ketohexose).

label: response to external biotic stimulus
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an external biotic stimulus, an external stimulus caused by, or produced by living things.

label: iris stroma
Defs: The delicate vascular connective tissue that lies between the anterior surface of the iris and the pars iridica retinae.

label: ligament of liver
Defs: A nonskeletal ligament that is part of a liver.

label: pre-cartilage condensation
Defs: A delimited region of dense mesenchyme within looser mesenchyme whose cells are committed to become chondroblasts.

label: chemotaxis
Defs: The directed movement of a motile cell or organism, or the directed growth of a cell guided by a specific chemical concentration gradient. Movement may be towards a higher concentration (positive chemotaxis) or towards a lower concentration (negative chemotaxis).

label: mucosa of sigmoid colon
Defs: A mucosa that is part of a sigmoid colon [Automatically generated definition].

label: gonadal vein
Defs: In medicine, gonadal vein refers to the blood vessel that carrying blood away from the gonad (testis, ovary) toward the heart. Females : ovarian vein Males : testicular vein [WP,unvetted].

label: forward scatter
Defs: A reflectivity quality inhering in light by virtue of the bearer\'s scattering occurring at small angle to the incident beam.

label: vacuole fusion
Defs: Merging of two or more vacuoles, or of vacuoles and vesicles within a cell to form a single larger vacuole.

label: brood size
Defs: A reproductive quality inhering in the young of an animal by virtue of their number.

label: microtubule polymerization
Defs: The addition of tubulin heterodimers to one or both ends of a microtubule.

label: negative regulation of skeletal muscle tissue development
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of skeletal muscle tissue development.

label: decreased variability of color
Defs: A variability of color which is relatively low.

label: negative regulation of compound eye retinal cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of compound eye retinal cell apoptotic process.

label: myelinating glial cell
Defs: A glial cell that myelinates axonal processes.

label: regulation of mesodermal cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mesodermal cell differentiation.

label: cerebral cortex radial glia-guided migration
Defs: The radial migration of neuronal or glial precursor cells along radial glial cells during the development of the cerebral cortex.

label: regulation of cell communication
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell communication. Cell communication is the process that mediates interactions between a cell and its surroundings. Encompasses interactions such as signaling or attachment between one cell and another cell, between a cell and an extracellular matrix, or between a cell and any other aspect of its environment.

label: small molecule biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of small molecules, any low molecular weight, monomeric, non-encoded molecule.

label: lanceolate-triangular
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being shaped like a lance-head, considerably longer than wide, tapering towards the tip from below the middle together forming three angles; attached at the broad end.

label: postoccipital sulcus
Defs: The cuticular sulcus that coincides with the postoccipital ridge and is posterior to the occiput and anterior to the postocciput

label: negative regulation of signaling
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of a signaling process.

label: organonitrogen compound biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of organonitrogen compound.

label: hepatic stem cell
Defs: A stem cell that can give rise to the cells of the liver. The term usually refers to the self-renewing pool of hepatocyte precursors in the adult liver (differently from \'hepatoblast\', often used for fetal precursors of hepatocytes).

label: abdominal segment element
Defs: An organ or element that is part of the adbominal segment of the organism. This region can be further subdivided into the abdominal cavity and the pelvic region.

label: neuromere
Defs: A transverse unitary subdivision of the neural tube that shares a common dorsoventral structure (floor, basal, alar, and roof plates), but each having differential molecular identities and fates; they comprise the secondary prosencephalon, diencephalon (prosomeres), the midbrain (mesomeres), and the hindbrain (rhombomeres).

label: proximal region
Defs: Anatomical region proximally located on the body or body part.

label: catechol-containing compound metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving a compound containing a pyrocatechol (1,2-benzenediol) nucleus or substituent.

label: lateral surface
Defs: Anatomical surface that located on the lateral side of the body or body part.

label: lung morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the lung are generated and organized.

label: positive regulation of cell adhesion
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cell adhesion.

label: anal region smooth muscle
Defs: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of an anal region [Automatically generated definition].

label: Daphnia magna metabolite
Defs: A Daphnia metabolite produced by the species Daphnia magna.

label: volumetric density
Defs: A density quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of some influence exerted by the bearer\'s mass on a given volume.

label: muscle cell development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a muscle cell over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Muscle cell development does not include the steps involved in committing an unspecified cell to the muscle cell fate.

label: negative regulation of glycoprotein metabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of glycoprotein metabolic process.

label: single fate stem cell
Defs: A stem cell that self-renews as well as give rise to a single mature cell type.

label: investigation
Defs: a planned process that consists of parts: planning, study design execution, documentation and which produce conclusion(s).

label: increased occurrence
Defs: An occurrence which is relatively high.

label: mucosa of anal canal
Defs: A mucosa that is part of an anal canal [Automatically generated definition].

label: negative regulation of axo-dendritic protein transport
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of axo-dendritic protein transport.

label: propleuro-procoxal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the prothorax that joins the propleuron and the procoxa.

label: hardness
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s resistance to pressure, being broken, or pierced

label: MHC class II protein complex assembly
Defs: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form an MHC class II protein complex.

label: axon
Defs: The long process of a neuron that conducts nerve impulses, usually away from the cell body to the terminals and varicosities, which are sites of storage and release of neurotransmitter.

label: suppurative
Defs: A quality inhering a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to generate pus.

label: adaxial-abaxial axis
Defs: An anatomical axis that extends from the side of the anatomical entity that is closer to an axis (adaxial) to the side that is further from the same axis (abaxial).

label: L-amino acid transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of an L-amino acid from one side of a membrane to the other. L-amino acids are the L-enantiomers of amino acids.

label: skeletal muscle contraction
Defs: A process in which force is generated within skeletal muscle tissue, resulting in a change in muscle geometry. Force generation involves a chemo-mechanical energy conversion step that is carried out by the actin/myosin complex activity, which generates force through ATP hydrolysis. In the skeletal muscle, the muscle contraction takes advantage of an ordered sarcomeric structure and in most cases it is under voluntary control.

label: intersomitic artery
Defs: The small branching sprouts of the dorsal aorta that grow across the medial surface of the somite, turn right angles to grow over that surface and then fuse with other sprouts and form the vertebral arteries adjacent to the neural tube; the intersomitic arteries supply the body wall and persist in the adult as the posterior intercostal, subcostal and the lumbar arteries.

label: positive regulation of receptor localization to synapse
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of receptor localization to synapse.

label: positive regulation of amine transport
Defs: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of amines into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: regulation of postsynapse assembly
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of postsynapse assembly, the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a postsynapse.

label: smooth muscle cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a smooth muscle cell; smooth muscle lacks transverse striations in its constituent fibers and are almost always involuntary.

label: negative regulation of excitatory postsynaptic potential
Defs: Any process that prevents the establishment or decreases the extent of the excitatory postsynaptic potential (EPSP) which is a temporary increase in postsynaptic potential due to the flow of positively charged ions into the postsynaptic cell. The flow of ions that causes an EPSP is an excitatory postsynaptic current (EPSC) and makes it easier for the neuron to fire an action potential.

label: runt-related transcription factor 1
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human RUNX1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: regulation of binding
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of binding, the selective interaction of a molecule with one or more specific sites on another molecule.

label: indoles
Defs: Any compound containing an indole skeleton.

label: negative regulation of fibroblast apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of fibroblast apoptotic process.

label: abdominal tergite VIII-abdominal tergite IX conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect abdomen that connects the abdominal tergite VIII and the abdominal tergite IX.

label: dendrite cytoplasm
Defs: All of the contents of a dendrite, excluding the surrounding plasma membrane.

label: microtubule cytoskeleton organization involved in mitosis
Defs: Any microtubule cytoskeleton organization that is involved in mitosis.

label: female germ cell nucleus
Defs: The nucleus of the female germ cell, a reproductive cell in females.

label: negative regulation of neuroblast migration
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of neuroblast migration.

label: ovariohysterectomized female
Defs: A female fertility quality inhering in a female by virtue of the bearer\'s not being capable of reproducing because of surgical removal of ovaries and uterus.

label: regulation of branching involved in lung morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the process in which a highly ordered sequence of patterning events generates the branched structures of the lung, consisting of reiterated combinations of bud outgrowth, elongation, and dichotomous subdivision of terminal units.

label: response to ketone
Defs: A response that results in a state of tolerance to ketone.

label: communicating artery
Defs: An artery that connects two larger arteries.

label: negative regulation of dendrite morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of dendrite morphogenesis.

label: negative regulation of stem cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of stem cell proliferation.

label: placental villus capillary endothelial cell
Defs: Any capillary endothelial cell that is part of a placenta.

label: energy
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s capacity to do work.

label: positive regulation of myeloid cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of myeloid cell apoptotic process.

label: regulation of oligodendrocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of oligodendrocyte differentiation.

label: collapsed
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being broken down; caved in.

label: surface of bone
Defs: An anatomical surface that is part of a bone.

label: regulation of anion transmembrane transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of anion transmembrane transport.

label: coelom
Defs: The aggregate of the coelemic cavity lumen plus the membranes that line the lumen.

label: tracheobronchial serous cell
Defs: Any serous secreting cell that is part of the tracheobronchial epithelium.

label: diploid
Defs: A ploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having two copies (homologs) of each chromosome, usually one from the mother and one from the father.

label: neck nerve
Defs: A nerve that is part of a neck [Automatically generated definition].

label: nucleobase-containing compound catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of nucleobases, nucleosides, nucleotides and nucleic acids.

label: inorganic cation transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of inorganic cations from one side of a membrane to the other. Inorganic cations are atoms or small molecules with a positive charge that do not contain carbon in covalent linkage.

label: closure
Defs: A morphological quality pertaining to the degree to which an object contains an opening, aperture, orifice or vent.

label: intraembryonic coelom
Defs: The part of the coelom in the embryo between the somatopleuric and splanchnopleuric mesoderm; the principal body cavities of the trunk (thoracic, abdominal, and pelvic) arise from this embryonic part of the coelom.

label: positive regulation of myoblast differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of myoblast differentiation. A myoblast is a mononucleate cell type that, by fusion with other myoblasts, gives rise to the myotubes that eventually develop into skeletal muscle fibers.

label: negative regulation of lysosomal protein catabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of lysosomal protein catabolic process.

label: positive regulation of steroid biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of steroids, compounds with a 1,2,cyclopentanoperhydrophenanthrene nucleus.

label: consent section
Defs: A part of a document about the consent process that was used to enroll patients in a study.

label: beige
Defs: A colour that is very pale yellowish brown.

label: pharmaceutical
Defs: Any substance introduced into a living organism with therapeutic or diagnostic purpose.

label: quality of a population
Defs: A quality that inheres in a population of organisms.

label: neural plate pattern specification
Defs: The developmental process that results in the creation of defined areas or spaces within the neural plate to which cells respond and eventually are instructed to differentiate.

label: sexually dimorphic
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting a phenotypic difference between males and females of the same species.

label: positive regulation of defense response
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of a defense response.

label: sexually immature organism
Defs: A multicellular organism that is at the juvenile stage.

label: cardiac right ventricle morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the right cardiac ventricle is generated and organized.

label: regulation of action potential
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of action potential creation, propagation or termination. This typically occurs via modulation of the activity or expression of voltage-gated ion channels.

label: negative regulation of protein binding
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein binding.

label: septum
Defs: A wall, dividing a cavity or structure into smaller ones[WP].

label: 4th arch mesenchyme from neural crest
Defs: Mesenchyme that develops_from a neural crest and is part of a 4th arch mesenchyme.

label: central tendon of diaphragm
Defs: The three-lobed cloverleaf-shaped aponeurosis situated at the center of the diaphragm; the central tendon is fused with the fibrous pericardium that provides attachment for the muscle fibers.

label: smooth muscle cell of the carotid artery
Defs: Smooth muscle cell of the carotid artery.

label: transversal labral muscle
Defs: The cranio-labral muscle that extends betwen the sides of  the labrum.

label: regulation of osteoclast development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of osteoclast development.

label: organooxygen compound
Defs: An organochalcogen compound containing at least one carbon-oxygen bond.

label: prechordal mesoderm
Defs: The area of axial mesoderm that develops into the prechordal plate.

label: regulation of chromatin organization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of chromatin organization.

label: distributed
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being spread out or scattered about or divided up.

label: gastrulation
Defs: A complex and coordinated series of cellular movements that occurs at the end of cleavage during embryonic development of most animals. The details of gastrulation vary from species to species, but usually result in the formation of the three primary germ layers, ectoderm, mesoderm and endoderm.

label: lung
Defs: Respiration organ that develops as an outpocketing of the esophagus.

label: lung neuroendocrine cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a neuroendocrine cell of the lung epithelium.

label: positive regulation of locomotion
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of locomotion of a cell or organism.

label: diagram
Defs: A figure that expresses one or more propositions

label: perfoliate
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s two basal lobes being united together.

label: first axillary sclerite
Defs: The axillary sclerite that is part of the dorsal region of the basal wing conjunctiva and is anterior to the third axillary sclerite.

label: glutamine family amino acid catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of amino acids of the glutamine family, comprising arginine, glutamate, glutamine and proline.

label: normal coordination
Defs: A coordination which is relatively normal or average.

label: deciduous (plant)
Defs: A quality inhering in a plant by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to shed foliage.

label: nucleus
Defs: A membrane-bounded organelle of eukaryotic cells in which chromosomes are housed and replicated. In most cells, the nucleus contains all of the cell\'s chromosomes except the organellar chromosomes, and is the site of RNA synthesis and processing. In some species, or in specialized cell types, RNA metabolism or DNA replication may be absent.

label: cartilaginous joint
Defs: Nonsynovial joint in which the articulating bones or cartilages are connected by cartilage. Examples: Spheno-occipital synchondrosis, first sternocostal joint, pubic symphysis.[FMA].

label: notopleural sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that separates the dorsal region of the pleuron from the lateral region of the notum.

label: decreased magnetism
Defs: A magnetism which is relatively low.

label: lymphocyte migration
Defs: The movement of a lymphocyte within or between different tissues and organs of the body.

label: T-cell acute lymphocytic leukemia protein 1
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human TAL1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: pyramidal neuron
Defs: Pyramidal neurons have a pyramid-shaped soma with a single axon, a large apical dendrite and multiple basal dendrites. The apex and an apical dendrite typically point toward the pial surface and other dendrites and an axon emerging from the base. The axons may have local collaterals but also project outside their region. Pyramidal neurons are found in the cerebral cortex, the hippocampus, and the amygdala.

label: negative regulation of skeletal muscle cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of skeletal muscle cell proliferation.

label: study bias section
Defs: A study limitations section that describes systematic error introduced into sampling or testing by selecting or encouraging one outcome or answer over others.

label: trophoblast cell migration
Defs: Trophoblast cell migration that is accomplished by extension and retraction of a pseudopodium. Trophoblast cells line the outside of the blastocyst.

label: 2-D extent
Defs: A size quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s extension in two dimensions.

label: regulation of glycogen metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving glycogen.

label: female reproductive gland
Defs: A sex gland that is part of a female reproductive system.

label: nest basket cell morphology
Defs: A basket cell morphology that inheres in neurons which have simpler dendritic arbors (compared to small or large basket cell morphology), and an axonal plexus of intermediate density, composed of a few long, smooth axonal branches.

label: positive regulation of collagen catabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of collagen catabolism. Collagen catabolism is the proteolytic chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of collagen in the extracellular matrix.

label: positive regulation of cholangiocyte apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cholangiocyte apoptotic process.

label: light deep pink
Defs: Pink color having high brightness and moderate saturation.

label: establishment of protein localization to extracellular region
Defs: The directed movement of a protein to a specific location within the extracellular region.

label: regulation of dendritic cell chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of dendritic cell chemotaxis.

label: positive regulation of vascular associated smooth muscle cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of vascular associated smooth muscle cell apoptotic process.

label: organic anion
Defs: Any organic ion with a net negative charge.

label: negative regulation of skeletal muscle hypertrophy
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of skeletal muscle hypertrophy.

label: trigeminal nucleus
Defs: A nucleus of brain that is part of a trigeminal nuclear complex.

label: regulation of acetate catabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of acetate, the anion of acetic acid.

label: extracellular exosome
Defs: A vesicle that is released into the extracellular region by fusion of the limiting endosomal membrane of a multivesicular body with the plasma membrane. Extracellular exosomes, also simply called exosomes, have a diameter of about 40-100 nm.

label: abdominal tergite IV
Defs: Is the abdominal tergite of the preabdomen that is attached to the posterior margin of the abdominal tergite III by the abdominal tergite III-abdominal tergite IV conjunctiva and to the anterior margin of the abdominal tergite V by the abdominal tergite IV-abdominal tergite V conjunctiva.

label: anterolateral orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed anterolaterally.

label: 3rd arch mesenchyme from head mesenchyme
Defs: Mesenchyme that develops_from a head mesenchyme from mesoderm and is part of a 3rd arch mesenchyme.

label: negative regulation of hyaluronan biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of hyaluronan biosynthetic process.

label: positive regulation of cellular amide metabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving amides.

label: interleukin-5 receptor subunit alpha
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human IL5RA gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: peritoneal mesentery
Defs: Mesentery that is located in the peritoneum.

label: dead
Defs: A viability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the cessation of the bearer\'s life.

label: regulation of cytokine production
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of production of a cytokine.

label: cardiac mesenchymal cell
Defs: A mesenchymal cell found in the developing heart and that develops into some part of the heart.  These cells derive from intra- and extra-cardiac sources, including the endocardium, epicardium, neural crest, and second heart field.

label: establishment of pigment granule localization
Defs: The directed movement of a pigment granule to a specific location.

label: transudate
Defs: Any bodily fluid that has passed through a membrane such as the capillary wall, as a result of unbalanced hydrostatic and osmotic forces.

label: catecholamine metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving any of a group of physiologically important biogenic amines that possess a catechol (3,4-dihydroxyphenyl) nucleus and are derivatives of 3,4-dihydroxyphenylethylamine.

label: hemorrhagic
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting excessive discharge of blood from the blood vessels.

label: respiratory system arterial blood vessel
Defs: An arterial blood vessel that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

label: anterior uvea
Defs: Front (ventral) portion of the vascular, pigmentary, or middle coat of the eye, including the ciliary body and the iris.

label: abdominal sternite VIII-abdominal sternite IX conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect abdomen that connects the abdominal sternite VIII and the abdominal sternite IX.

label: midbrain
Defs: The midbrain is the middle division of the three primary divisions of the developing chordate brain or the corresponding part of the adult brain (in vertebrates, includes a ventral part containing the cerebral peduncles and a dorsal tectum containing the corpora quadrigemina and that surrounds the aqueduct of Sylvius connecting the third and fourth ventricles)[GO].

label: cardo-stipital conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect maxilla that connects the cardo and the stipes.

label: positive regulation of chromatin binding
Defs: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of chromatin binding. Chromatin binding is the selective interaction with chromatin, the network of fibers of DNA, protein, and sometimes RNA, that make up the chromosomes of the eukaryotic nucleus during interphase.

label: abdomen
Defs: The subdivision of the vertebrate body between the thorax and pelvis. The ventral part of the abdomen contains the abdominal cavity and visceral organs. The dorsal part includes the abdominal section of the vertebral column.

label: glandular epithelial cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a glandular epithelial cell. A glandular epithelial cell is a columnar/cuboidal epithelial cell found in a two dimensional sheet with a free surface exposed to the lumen of a gland.

label: T cell proliferation involved in immune response
Defs: The expansion of a T cell population by cell division as part of an immune response.

label: surrounding
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being extended on all sides of another entity simultaneously.

label: rhombomere formation
Defs: The process that gives rise to the rhombomere. This process pertains to the initial formation of a structure from unspecified parts. Rhombomeres are transverse segments of the developing rhombencephalon. Rhombomeres are lineage restricted, express different genes from one another, and adopt different developmental fates.

label: positive regulation of secretion
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the controlled release of a substance from a cell or a tissue.

label: anatomical structure development
Defs: The biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of an anatomical structure from an initial condition to its mature state. This process begins with the formation of the structure and ends with the mature structure, whatever form that may be including its natural destruction. An anatomical structure is any biological entity that occupies space and is distinguished from its surroundings. Anatomical structures can be macroscopic such as a carpel, or microscopic such as an acrosome.

label: positive regulation of protein phosphorylation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of addition of phosphate groups to amino acids within a protein.

label: heteropolycyclic compound
Defs: A polycyclic compound in which at least one of the rings contains at least one non-carbon atom.

label: neutrophillic
Defs: An affinity inhering in an anatomical structure by virtue of the bearer exhibiting a molecular interaction that stains and colors, pale-pink, with Wright-Giemsa stain.

label: increased osmolality
Defs: An osmolality which is relatively high.

label: positive regulation of nuclear migration along microtubule
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of nuclear migration along microtubule.

label: aminoglycan biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of aminoglycans, any polymer containing amino groups that consists of more than about 10 monosaccharide residues joined to each other by glycosidic linkages.

label: fundamental metabolite
Defs: Any metabolite produced by all living cells.

label: tentorio-paraglossal muscle
Defs: The cranio-labial muscle that is attached to the posterior tentorial arm and the paraglossa.

label: inserted into
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s becoming joined together with an additional entity.

label: positive regulation of developmental growth
Defs: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the rate of developmental growth.

label: pericardium development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the pericardium over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The pericardium is a double-walled sac that contains the heart and the roots of the aorta, vena cava and the pulmonary artery.

label: regulation of phagocytosis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of phagocytosis, the process in which phagocytes engulf external particulate material.

label: serous cell of epithelium of terminal bronchiole
Defs: A serous secreting cell that is part of the epithelium of terminal bronchiole.

label: respiratory system arteriole
Defs: An arteriole that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

label: allopolyploidy
Defs: A polyploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing chromosomes derived from different species.

label: endocardial cell
Defs: An endothelial cell that lines the intracavitary lumen of the heart, separating the circulating blood from the underlying myocardium. This cell type releases a number of vasoactive substances including prostacyclin, nitrous oxide and endothelin.

label: regulation of formation of translation initiation ternary complex
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of formation of translation initiation ternary complex.

label: insulin secretion
Defs: The regulated release of proinsulin from secretory granules accompanied by cleavage of proinsulin to form mature insulin. In vertebrates, insulin is secreted from B granules in the B cells of the vertebrate pancreas and from insulin-producing cells in insects.

label: postero-lateral region
Defs: Anatomical region that overlaps the posterior and lateral regions of the body or body part.
