label: myeloid dendritic cell cytokine production
Defs: Any process that contributes to cytokine production by a myeloid dendritic cell.

label: prosternum
Defs: The sclerite on the ventral region of the prothorax that bears the profurca and is attached to the propleuro-prosternal conjunctiva.

label: trachea basement membrane
Defs: A basement membrane that is part of a trachea.

label: pelvic appendage skeleton
Defs: The collection of all skeletal elements in a pelvic appendage region.

label: virulence
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the severity of infectious disease caused by the bearer in a target organism.

label: cellular macromolecule biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a macromolecule, any molecule of high relative molecular mass, the structure of which essentially comprises the multiple repetition of units derived, actually or conceptually, from molecules of low relative molecular mass, carried out by individual cells.

label: decreased porosity
Defs: An decrease in porosity.

label: mesopleuron
Defs: The region of the cuticle on the lateral region of the mesothorax that is attached to the mesonotum and the mesosternum, and is attached to the mesocoxa by the mesocoxal muscle and the basal mesocoxal conjunctiva.

label: fimbriated
Defs: Having a fringe or border of hairlike or fingerlike projections.

label: amine biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of any organic compound that is weakly basic in character and contains an amino or a substituted amino group. Amines are called primary, secondary, or tertiary according to whether one, two, or three carbon atoms are attached to the nitrogen atom.

label: polar polarity
Defs: Polar polarity is a quality that inheres in a molecular entity when the molecular entity is polar, i.e. does possess an electric dipole.

label: frontal suture
Defs: The cuticular suture that surrounds the frons and is connected to the coronal suture.

label: trachea cartilage
Defs: The ring-shaped cartilaginous structures that support the trachea.

label: neural tube development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the neural tube over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The mature structure of the neural tube exists when the tube has been segmented into the forebrain, midbrain, hindbrain and spinal cord regions. In addition neural crest has budded away from the epithelium.

label: abdominal sternite II-abdominal sternite III conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect abdomen that connects the abdominal sternite II and the abdominal sternite III.

label: cadherin-5 (mouse)
Defs: A cadherin-5 that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: zygomaticotemporal nerve
Defs: The zygomaticotemporal nerve or zygomaticotemporal branch (temporal branch) is derived from the maxillary branch of the trigeminal nerve (Cranial nerve V). It runs along the lateral wall of the orbit in a groove in the zygomatic bone, receives a branch of communication from the lacrimal, and passes through zygomaticotemporal foramen in the zygomatic bone to enter the temporal fossa. It ascends between the bone, and substance of the Temporalis muscle, pierces the temporal fascia about 2.5 cm. above the zygomatic arch, and is distributed to the skin of the side of the forehead, and communicates with the facial nerve and with the auriculotemporal branch of the mandibular nerve. As it pierces the temporal fascia, it gives off a slender twig, which runs between the two layers of the fascia to the lateral angle of the orbit.

label: regulation of protein localization to ciliary membrane
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to ciliary membrane.

label: regulation of muscle cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate or frequency of muscle cell apoptotic process, a form of programmed cell death induced by external or internal signals that trigger the activity of proteolytic caspases whose actions dismantle a muscle cell and result in its death.

label: signal release from synapse
Defs: Any signal release from a synapse.

label: herbaceous
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s upper parts die back to the rootstock at the end of the growing season.

label: regulation of granulocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of granulocyte differentiation.

label: regulation of renal system process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a system process, a multicellular organismal process carried out by the renal system.

label: retinal ganglion cell
Defs: The set of neurons that receives neural inputs via bipolar, horizontal and amacrine cells. The axons of these cells make up the optic nerve.

label: disorganized
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking organisation.

label: detoxification
Defs: Any process that reduces or removes the toxicity of a toxic substance. These may include transport of the toxic substance away from sensitive areas and to compartments or complexes whose purpose is sequestration of the toxic substance.

label: endocardium of atrium
Defs: Endocardium that is part of the atrium.

label: right ovarian vein
Defs: Ovarian vein, each instance of which is a tributary  of some inferior vena cava that drains the right pampiniform plexus of some broad ligament.

label: boson
Defs: Particle of integer spin quantum number following Bose-Einstein statistics. Bosons are named after Satyendra Nath Bose.

label: ectodermal gland
Defs: The region of cuticle that is continuous with glandular epithelial cells.

label: alpha-amino acid metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving an alpha-amino acid.

label: MHC protein complex
Defs: A transmembrane protein complex composed of an MHC alpha chain and, in most cases, either an MHC class II beta chain or an invariant beta2-microglobin chain, and with or without a bound peptide, lipid, or polysaccharide antigen.

label: positive regulation of microtubule polymerization
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of microtubule polymerization.

label: adaptive immune response based on somatic recombination of immune receptors built from immunoglobulin superfamily domains
Defs: An immune response mediated by lymphocytes expressing specific receptors for antigen produced through a somatic diversification process that includes somatic recombination of germline gene segments encoding immunoglobulin superfamily domains. Recombined receptors for antigen encoded by immunoglobulin superfamily domains include T cell receptors and immunoglobulins (antibodies) produced by B cells. The first encounter with antigen elicits a primary immune response that is slow and not of great magnitude. T and B cells selected by antigen become activated and undergo clonal expansion. A fraction of antigen-reactive T and B cells become memory cells, whereas others differentiate into effector cells. The memory cells generated during the primary response enable a much faster and stronger secondary immune response upon subsequent exposures to the same antigen (immunological memory). An example of this is the adaptive immune response found in Mus musculus.

label: hydrophobicity
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue the bearer\'s disposition to being water-repellent; tending to repel and not absorb water.

label: dorso-medial region
Defs: Anatomical region that overlaps the dorsal and medial regions of the body or body part.

label: obsolete bouts
Defs: A limited, often assigned period of activity.

label: acetate ester biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of an acetate esteran acetate ester, any carboxylic ester where the carboxylic acid component is acetic acid.

label: response to acid chemical
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus by the chemical structure of the anion portion of a dissociated acid (rather than the acid acting as a proton donor). The acid chemical may be in gaseous, liquid or solid form.

label: catalytic (activity) concentration
Defs: A concentration quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s catalytic activity divided by the volume of the system.

label: regulation of muscle system process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a muscle system process, a multicellular organismal process carried out by any of the organs or tissues in a muscle system.

label: regulation of lymphocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of lymphocyte differentiation.

label: negative regulation of mesenchymal stem cell migration
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of mesenchymal stem cell migration.

label: antennifer
Defs: The cuticular protrusion (process, protuberace) that bears the cranial articular surface of the cranio-antennal articulation.

label: girdle bone/zone
Defs: A bone that is part of a appendage girdle region.

label: negative regulation of ectoderm development
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of ectoderm development.

label: increased nucleus size
Defs: A nucleus size quality which is relatively high compared to the amount of cytoplasm present in the same cell.

label: negative regulation of antimicrobial peptide secretion
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of antimicrobial peptide secretion.

label: folded
Defs: A surface feature shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s one part being layered over another connected part.

label: requirements textual entity
Defs: A textual entity that expresses the requirements necessary to use a resource, e.g. software.

label: regulation of dendritic cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of dendritic cell differentiation.

label: cavernous artery
Defs: Any of several small branches of the internal carotid artery that supply the trigeminal ganglion and the walls of the cavernous and petrosal sinuses.

label: postsynaptic signal transduction
Defs: Signal transduction in which the initial step occurs in a postsynapse.

label: negative regulation of protein kinase activity
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein kinase activity.

label: endoderm development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the endoderm over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The endoderm is the innermost germ layer that develops into the gastrointestinal tract, the lungs and associated tissues.

label: protein localization to microvillus
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a location within a microvillus.

label: thoracic spinal cord white matter
Defs: A white matter of spinal cord that is part of a thoracic spinal cord.

label: image
Defs: An image is an affine projection to a two dimensional surface, of measurements of some quality of an entity or entities repeated at regular intervals across a spatial range, where the measurements are represented as color and luminosity on the projected on surface.

label: increased tolerance to
Defs: A tolerance quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s increased ability to endure a stimulus.

label: genoclypeal sulcus
Defs: The cuticular sulcus that is the lateral region of the frontoclypeal sulcus.

label: indurated
Defs: Having become firm or hard especially by increase of fibrous elements.

label: negative regulation of antigen processing and presentation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of antigen processing and presentation.

label: basal surface
Defs: Anatomical surface that is located on the basal side of the body or body part.

label: female sex differentiation
Defs: The establishment of the sex of a female organism by physical differentiation.

label: axial skeletal system
Defs: Subdivision of the skeletal system which consists of the axial skeleton plus associated joints.

label: male receptivity
Defs: A behavioral quality which holds by virtue of extent of the receptiveness of a male to female advances.

label: dorsal trunk
Defs: The part of the trunk that is in the dorsum[cjm].

label: artery development
Defs: The progression of the artery over time, from its initial formation to the mature structure. An artery is a blood vessel that carries blood away from the heart to a capillary bed.

label: focused
Defs: An optical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having focus.

label: oriented towards
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being aligned or positioned towards another entity.

label: promyelocyte
Defs: A precursor in the granulocytic series, being a cell intermediate in development between a myeloblast and myelocyte, that has distinct nucleoli, a nuclear-to-cytoplasmic ratio of 5:1 to 3:1, and containing a few primary cytoplasmic granules. Markers for this cell are fucosyltransferase FUT4-positive, CD33-positive, integrin alpha-M-negative, low affinity immunoglobulin gamma Fc region receptor III-negative, and CD24-negative.

label: positive regulation of cardioblast differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cardioblast differentiation, the process in which a relatively unspecialized mesodermal cell acquires the specialized structural and/or functional features of a cardioblast. A cardioblast is a cardiac precursor cell. It is a cell that has been committed to a cardiac fate, but will undergo more cell division rather than terminally differentiating.

label: smooth muscle cell neural crest derived
Defs: A smooth muscle cell derived from the neural crest.

label: mesiodistally compressed
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being compressed from the side facing the midline of the jaw to the side opposite the midline.

label: serosa of rectum
Defs: A serous membrane that is part of a rectum [Automatically generated definition].

label: positive regulation of dendritic cell dendrite assembly
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of dendritic cell dendrite assembly.

label: donor
Defs: A molecular entity that can transfer ("donate") an electron, a pair of electrons, an atom or a group to another molecular entity.

label: epithelium of lens
Defs: A layer of epithelial cells that is part of the eye.

label: recurrent laryngeal nerve
Defs: A branch of the vagus nerve that supplies motor function and sensation to the larynx (voice box). It travels within the endoneurium. It is the nerve of the 6th Branchial Arch.

label: gall bladder smooth muscle
Defs: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a gallbladder [Automatically generated definition].

label: animal organ maturation
Defs: A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for an animal organ to attain its fully functional state. An organ is a tissue or set of tissues that work together to perform a specific function or functions.

label: negative regulation of hematopoietic stem cell migration
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of hematopoietic stem cell migration.

label: action potential
Defs: A quality inhering in a cell\'s plasma membrane by virtue of a brief fluctuation in the bearer\'s potential caused by the rapid opening and closing of voltage-gated ion channels.

label: midgut duodenum mesentery
Defs: A mesentery of duodenum that is part of a midgut.

label: euchromatin
Defs: A dispersed and relatively uncompacted form of chromatin that is in a transcription-competent conformation.

label: professional antigen presenting cell
Defs: A cell capable of processing and presenting lipid and protein antigens to T cells in order to initiate an immune response.

label: capillary of anorectum
Defs: A capillary that is part of the anorectum.

label: keratinocyte development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a keratinocyte over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: positive regulation of steroid metabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving steroids.

label: cell proliferation involved in embryonic placenta development
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of the population in the embryonic placenta.

label: regulation of response to acetate
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of response to acetate.

label: head capsule
Defs: The sclerite of the insect head that is attached to the neck membrane and the oral foraminal conjunctiva, bears the eye cuticle and surrounds the brain

label: specialized cardiac myocyte
Defs: A cardiac myocyte that is an excitable cells in the myocardium, specifically in the conducting system of heart.

label: alkaloid metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving alkaloids, nitrogen containing natural products which are not otherwise classified as peptides, nonprotein amino acids, amines, cyanogenic glycosides, glucosinolates, cofactors, phytohormones or primary metabolites (such as purine or pyrimidine bases).

label: abdominal cavity
Defs: The part of the ventral body cavity that is within the abdomen proper (excluding the pelvic cavity).

label: normal coiling
Defs: A coiling which is normal or average.

label: microtubule bundle formation
Defs: A process that results in a parallel arrangement of microtubules.

label: neuromuscular junction development, skeletal muscle fiber
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a neuromuscular junction that targets a skeletal muscle fiber.

label: uterine epithelium development
Defs: The progression of an epithelium of the uterus over time from its initial formation to the mature structure. An epithelium is a tissue that covers the internal or external surfaces of an anatomical structure.

label: ADP-ribosyl cyclase/cyclic ADP-ribose hydrolase 1 (mouse)
Defs: An ADP-ribosyl cyclase/cyclic ADP-ribose hydrolase 1 that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: actinomorphic
Defs: A symmetry quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being capable of division into symmetrical halves by any longitudinal plane passing through the axis.

label: positive regulation of bile acid secretion
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the controlled release of bile acid from a cell or a tissue.

label: exocytic insertion of neurotransmitter receptor to postsynaptic membrane
Defs: The exocytic fusion of neurotransmitter receptor containing vesicles with the postsynaptic membrane resulting in the integration of NT receptors, enabling them to participate in neurotransmitter reception.  This process includes tethering and docking steps that prepare vesicles for fusion.

label: acetate biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of acetate, the anion of acetic acid.

label: protein localization to vacuolar membrane
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a location within a vacuolar membrane.

label: negative regulation of meiotic cell cycle process involved in oocyte maturation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of meiotic cell cycle process involved in oocyte maturation.

label: lamina
Defs: Any thin layer or plate.

label: melanosome transport
Defs: The directed movement of melanosomes into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: lymphocyte
Defs: A lymphocyte is a leukocyte commonly found in the blood and lymph that has the characteristics of a large nucleus, a neutral staining cytoplasm, and prominent heterochromatin.

label: epithelial cell of alimentary canal
Defs: An epithelial cell of the musculomembranous digestive tube extending from the mouth to the anus.

label: nucleic acid metabolic process
Defs: Any cellular metabolic process involving nucleic acids.

label: head mesenchyme
Defs: Portion of primordial embryonic connective tissue of the developing head, consisting of mesenchymal cells supported in interlaminar jelly, that derive mostly from the mesoderm and contribute to head connective tissue, bone and musculature in conjunction with cranial neural crest cells.

label: organic cation transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of organic cations from one side of a membrane to the other. Organic cations are atoms or small molecules with a positive charge that contain carbon in covalent linkage.

label: cell cycle
Defs: The progression of biochemical and morphological phases and events that occur in a cell during successive cell replication or nuclear replication events. Canonically, the cell cycle comprises the replication and segregation of genetic material followed by the division of the cell, but in endocycles or syncytial cells nuclear replication or nuclear division may not be followed by cell division.

label: anatomical entity
Defs: Biological entity that is either an individual member of a biological species or constitutes the structural organization of an individual member of a biological species.

label: abdominal sternite IV-abdominal sternite V conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect abdomen that connects the abdominal sternite IV and the abdominal sternite V.

label: obsolete impaired
Defs: Diminished, damaged, or weakened.

label: protein localization to cytoskeleton
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a location within the cytoskeleton.

label: decreased fluid flow
Defs: A flow that is relatively low.

label: retinal cone cell development
Defs: Development of a cone cell, one of the sensory cells in the eye that reacts to the presence of light. Cone cells contain the photopigment iodopsin or cyanopsin and are responsible for photopic (daylight) vision.

label: euchromatin binding
Defs: Binding to euchromatin, a dispersed and relatively uncompacted form of chromatin.

label: disheveled
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being in disarray; extremely disorderly.

label: boomerang shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a shape like a boomerang, with two arms connected at an angle.

label: right lung development
Defs: The biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of a right lung from an initial condition to its mature state. This process begins with the formation of the right lung and ends with the mature structure. The right lung is the lung which is on the right side of the anterior posterior axis looking from a dorsal to ventral aspect.

label: abdominal tergite III
Defs: Is the abdominal tergite of the preabdomen that is attached to the posterior margin of the abdominal tergite II by the abdominal tergite II-abdominal tergite III conjunctiva and to the anterior margin of the abdominal tergite IV by the abdominal tergite III-abdominal tergite IV conjunctiva.

label: vasculature of respiratory integument
Defs: Blood vessels in respiratory skin.

label: overlapped by
Defs: Overlap with quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being positioned under another entity so as to be covered by some portion of it.

label: mitotic sister chromatid segregation
Defs: The cell cycle process in which replicated homologous chromosomes are organized and then physically separated and apportioned to two sets during the mitotic cell cycle. Each replicated chromosome, composed of two sister chromatids, aligns at the cell equator, paired with its homologous partner. One homolog of each morphologic type goes into each of the resulting chromosome sets.

label: duct epithelial cell
Defs: An epithelial cell that is part of a duct.

label: decreased quality
Defs: A quality that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

label: positive regulation of cilium movement
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of cilium movement, the directed, self-propelled movement of a cilium.

label: palpifero-palpal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect maxilla that connects the palpifer and the maxillary palpus.

label: increased female receptivity
Defs: A female receptivity which is relatively high.

label: flattened
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s surface becoming more extended in a plane.

label: right lung terminal bronchiole
Defs: A terminal bronchiole that is part of a right lung [Automatically generated definition].

label: increased duration
Defs: A duration quality of a process which is relatively high.

label: has extra parts of type
Defs: The bearer of this quality has_part > n of the indicated entity type, where n is the normal amount for a comparable organism. Note that the bearer of the quality is the whole, not the part.

label: morphogenesis of a branching epithelium
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of a branched epithelium are generated and organized.

label: regulation of neuroblast proliferation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of neuroblast proliferation.

label: cardiac muscle of left atrium
Defs: A portion of cardiac muscle tissue that is part of a left atrium [Automatically generated definition].

label: cuticle of insect head
Defs: The cuticular region that is anterior (distal) to the neck membrane (encircled by the neck membrane) and contains the head capsule, the antenna, the eyes, mouthparts and surrounds the brain.

label: regulation of serotonin secretion
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of serotonin.

label: androgen secretion
Defs: The regulated release of an androgen into the circulatory system. Androgens are steroid hormones that stimulate or control the development and maintenance of masculine characteristics in vertebrates.

label: shell shaped
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a shape like a shell.

label: descending aorta
Defs: The descending aorta is the portion of the aorta in a two-pass circulatory system from the arch of aorta to the point where it divides into the common iliac arteries[GO]. The descending aorta is part of the aorta, the largest artery in the body. The descending aorta is the part of the aorta beginning at the aortic arch that runs down through the chest and abdomen. The descending aorta is divided into two portions, the thoracic and abdominal, in correspondence with the two great cavities of the trunk in which it is situated. Within the abdomen, the descending aorta branches into the two common iliac arteries which serve the legs. [WP,unvetted].

label: raised
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a colony by virtue of the bearer\'s appearing above the medium surface with terraced edges.

label: positive regulation of vesicle fusion with Golgi apparatus
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of vesicle fusion with Golgi apparatus.

label: transition metal ion transport
Defs: The directed movement of transition metal ions into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. A transition metal is an element whose atom has an incomplete d-subshell of extranuclear electrons, or which gives rise to a cation or cations with an incomplete d-subshell. Transition metals often have more than one valency state. Biologically relevant transition metals include vanadium, manganese, iron, copper, cobalt, nickel, molybdenum and silver.

label: axonogenesis
Defs: De novo generation of a long process of a neuron, including the terminal branched region. Refers to the morphogenesis or creation of shape or form of the developing axon, which carries efferent (outgoing) action potentials from the cell body towards target cells.

label: submucosa of digestive tract
Defs: Any portion of submucosa that lines the digestive tract.

label: positive regulation of sulfur metabolic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving sulfur or compounds containing sulfur.

label: trophectodermal cellular morphogenesis
Defs: The morphogenesis of trophectoderm cells.

label: signaling lymphocytic activation molecule (mouse)
Defs: A SLAM family member 1 that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: uterine wall
Defs: An anatomical wall that is part of a uterus [Automatically generated definition].

label: motley
Defs: A color pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of bearer\'s having 3 or more hues or degrees of saturations.

label: cardiac chamber development
Defs: The progression of a cardiac chamber over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A cardiac chamber is an enclosed cavity within the heart.

label: cell migration
Defs: The controlled self-propelled movement of a cell from one site to a destination guided by molecular cues. Cell migration is a central process in the development and maintenance of multicellular organisms.

label: medial-lateral axis
Defs: An axis that extends from the center of organism to one or other side.

label: decreased pressure
Defs: A pressure which is relatively low.

label: positive regulation of glutamatergic neuron differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of glutamatergic neuron differentiation.

label: obtuse angle to
Defs: An angle which is between 90 degrees and 180 degrees to another entity.

label: forebrain-midbrain boundary formation
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the creation of the forebrain-midbrain boundary.

label: anorectum macrophage
Defs: A macrophage that is located in the anorectum.

label: fibroblast of skin of abdomen
Defs: Any skin fibroblast that is part of a skin of abdomen.

label: stem cell proliferation
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of stem cells, resulting in the expansion of a stem cell population. A stem cell is a cell that retains the ability to divide and proliferate throughout life to provide progenitor cells that can differentiate into specialized cells.

label: craniocervical region
Defs: The anteriormost subdivision of the body that includes the head, jaws, pharyngeal region and the neck (if present). In vertebrates this is the subdivision that includes the cervical vertebrae.

label: intestinal villus of duodenum
Defs: An intestinal villus in the duodenum.

label: regulation of oxygen metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of oxygen metabolic process.

label: obsolete increased relaxation
Defs: A relaxation which is relatively high.

label: uncrowded
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being not overfilled.

label: uterus morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which anatomical structures of the uterus are generated and organized.

label: cupulate
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being a cupule, with a structure similar to a cup that also encloses the ovule in partiality.

label: posterioralized
Defs: A malformed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s gross morphology containing what are normally posterior structures and missing some or all of what are normally anterior structures.

label: layer of microvilli
Defs: A layer of microvilli, Thin cylindrical membrane-covered projections on the surface of an animal cell containing a core bundle of actin filaments[GO,modified].

label: submucosa
Defs: A layer of dense irregular connective tissue that lines organs and supports the mucosa, as well as joins the mucosa to the bulk of underlying smooth muscle. [WP,unvetted].

label: increased size
Defs: A size quality which is relatively high.

label: abdomen blood vessel
Defs: A blood vessel that is part of an abdomen [Automatically generated definition].

label: vasculature of eye
Defs: Vasculature that is part of the eye region.

label: increased anterior-posterior diameter
Defs: An anterior-posterior diameter quality which is relatively large.

label: tibial muscle
Defs: The somatic muscle that inserts in the tibia.

label: response to inorganic substance
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an inorganic substance stimulus.

label: regulation of body fluid levels
Defs: Any process that modulates the levels of body fluids.

label: cloacal vent
Defs: The opening of the cloacal chamber to the outside of the organism. Birds maintain a single cloacal opening throughout their lives.

label: nucleic acid transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of nucleic acids from one side of a membrane to the other. Nucleic acids are single or double-stranded polynucleotides involved in the storage, transmission and transfer of genetic information.

label: cranial ganglion formation
Defs: The process that gives rise to a cranial ganglion. This process pertains to the initial formation of a structure from unspecified parts.

label: telencephalon glial cell migration
Defs: The orderly movement of glial cells through the telencephalon.

label: venous system endothelium
Defs: An endothelium that is part of a venous system [Automatically generated definition].

label: negative regulation of mesenchymal cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of mesenchymal cell apoptotic process.

label: shape
Defs: A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ratios of distances between its features (points, edges, surfaces and also holes etc).

label: increased turgor
Defs: A turgor which is relatively high.

label: synapse organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a synapse, the junction between a neuron and a target (neuron, muscle, or secretory cell).

label: regulation of neuron apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the occurrence or rate of cell death by apoptotic process in neurons.

label: muscle cell apoptotic process
Defs: A form of programmed cell death induced by external or internal signals that trigger the activity of proteolytic caspases, whose actions dismantle a muscle cell and result in its death. A muscle cell is a mature contractile cell, commonly known as a myocyte, that forms one of three kinds of muscle.

label: regulation of iron ion transmembrane transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of iron ions (Fe) from one side of a membrane to the other by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: striated muscle cell
Defs: Muscle cell which has as its direct parts myofilaments organized into sarcomeres.

label: trans-synaptic signaling by neuropeptide
Defs: Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse mediated by a peptide ligand crossing the synaptic cleft.

label: corticomedulla projecting
Defs: A neuron projection quality that is a characteristic of neurons that project to the medulla oblongata from other brain regions.

label: positive regulation of striated muscle tissue development
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of striated muscle development.

label: peripheral nervous system neuron
Defs: A neuron that is part of a peripheral nervous system.

label: dentary
Defs: The dentary is a dermal bone that forms the antero-lateral part of the lower jaw in fishes and amphibians, extending to the whole lower jaw in mammals[VHOG,modified].

label: glutamate receptor signaling pathway
Defs: The series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of glutamate to its receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

label: normal radiopacity
Defs: A radiopacity which is relatively normal or average

label: lipid transport
Defs: The directed movement of lipids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Lipids are compounds soluble in an organic solvent but not, or sparingly, in an aqueous solvent.

label: negative regulation of oocyte development
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate or extent of the process whose specific outcome is the progression of an oocyte over time, from initial commitment of the cell to its specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell.

label: epithelial cell of tracheobronchial tree
Defs: An epithelial cell of the tracheobronchial tree.

label: AV node cell to bundle of His cell communication
Defs: The process that mediates interactions between an AV node cell and its surroundings that contributes to the process of the AV node cell communicating with a bundle of His cell in cardiac conduction. Encompasses interactions such as signaling or attachment between one cell and another cell, between a cell and an extracellular matrix, or between a cell and any other aspect of its environment.

label: normal frequency
Defs: A frequency which is relatively normal.

label: regulation of protein polymerization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the process of creating protein polymers.

label: tentorio-cardinal muscle
Defs: The insect cranio-maxillar muscle that is attached to the tentorium and the cardo.

label: response to catecholamine
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a catecholamine stimulus. A catecholamine is any of a group of biogenic amines that includes 4-(2-aminoethyl)pyrocatechol [4-(2-aminoethyl)benzene-1,2-diol] and derivatives formed by substitution.

label: anterior-posterior axis
Defs: An axis that extends through an organism from head end to opposite end of body or tail.

label: abduction
Defs: A displaced angular placement quality inhering in a body part by virtue of the bearer\'s movement away from the medial plane of the body.

label: female pregnancy
Defs: The set of physiological processes that allow an embryo or foetus to develop within the body of a female animal. It covers the time from fertilization of a female ovum by a male spermatozoon until birth.

label: regulation of vesicle targeting, to, from or within Golgi
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or destination of vesicle-mediated transport to, from or within the Golgi apparatus.

label: obliquely striated muscle cell
Defs: A muscle cell in which the fibers are organised into sarcomeres but in which adjacent myofibrils are offset from each other, producing an oblique banding pattern.

label: cardiac septum cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which an endocardial cushion cell becomes a cell of a cardiac septum.

label: scrobe
Defs: The subantennal groove on the rostrum that is posterior to the antennal foramen.

label: gene expression involved in extracellular matrix organization
Defs: Any gene expression that is involved in extracellular matrix organization. Gene expression includes both transcription to produce an RNA transcript, and the translation of that mRNA into protein. Protein maturation is included in gene expression when required to form an active form of a product from an inactive precursor form.

label: botryoidal
Defs: A surface feature shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being like the surface of a compact mass of grapes.

label: macromolecule biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a macromolecule, any molecule of high relative molecular mass, the structure of which essentially comprises the multiple repetition of units derived, actually or conceptually, from molecules of low relative molecular mass.

label: premental-palpigeral conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the labium that connects the prementum and the palpiger.

label: tunica media of vein
Defs: A tunica media that is part of a vein.

label: subdermal
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located or placed beneath the skin.

label: cartilage of bronchus
Defs: The hyaline cartilaginous structures that support the bronchi, present as irregular rings in the larger bronchi (and not as regular as in the trachea), and as small plates and islands in the smaller bronchi; as the branching continues through the bronchial tree, the amount of hyaline cartilage in the walls decreases until it is absent in the smallest bronchioles[MP].

label: oral opening
Defs: The orifice that connects the mouth to the exterior of the body.

label: position
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s spatial location relative to other objects in the vicinity.

label: endothelial cell of arteriole
Defs: An endothelial cell that is part of the arteriole.

label: liver subserosa
Defs: Subserosal tissue of liver. A zone of areolar connective tissue lying beneath the serous coat of the liver and distinguished with difficulty from the fibrous capsule of Glisson.

label: regulation of gliogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of gliogenesis, the formation of mature glia.

label: wall of small intestine
Defs: An anatomical wall that is part of a small intestine [Automatically generated definition].

label: negative regulation of muscle contraction
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of muscle contraction.

label: ovipositor
Defs: The region of cuticle of the postabdomen that is distal to the genital chamber.

label: regulation of Golgi inheritance
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of Golgi inheritance. Golgi inheritance is the partitioning of Golgi apparatus between daughter cells at cell division.

label: mononuclear osteoclast
Defs: A specialized mononuclear osteoclast associated with the absorption and removal of bone, precursor of multinuclear osteoclasts.

label: increased mass density
Defs: A density which is higher relative to the normal or average.

label: intracellular organelle lumen
Defs: An organelle lumen that is part of an intracellular organelle.

label: respiratory system skeletal muscle
Defs: A portion of skeletal muscle tissue that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

label: regulation of T cell cytokine production
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of T cell cytokine production.

label: retrograde trans-synaptic signaling by neuropeptide
Defs: Cell-cell signaling from postsynapse to presynapse, across the synaptic cleft, mediated by a neuropeptide.

label: quality of a colloid
Defs: A physical quality inhering in an entity by virtue of a portion of the bearer\'s molecular or polymolecular constituents present in one phase being dispersed in a portion of the bearer\'s constituents present in another phase.

label: migratory cardiac neural crest cell
Defs: Any migratory neural crest cell that is part of a cardiac neural crest.

label: gall bladder serosa
Defs: A serous membrane that is part of a gallbladder [Automatically generated definition].

label: morphogenesis of an epithelial bud
Defs: The morphogenetic process in which a bud forms from an epithelial sheet. A bud is a protrusion that forms form the sheet by localized folding.

label: neural fold
Defs: One of the two elevated edges of the neural groove[GO,MP].

label: myotome development
Defs: The progression of the myotome over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The myotome is the portion of the somite that will give rise to muscle.

label: intracellular protein transport
Defs: The directed movement of proteins in a cell, including the movement of proteins between specific compartments or structures within a cell, such as organelles of a eukaryotic cell.

label: hindbrain nucleus
Defs: Nucleus located within the hindbrain.

label: compound organ component
Defs: Multi-tissue structure that is part of a compound organ.

label: blood vessel morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of blood vessels are generated and organized. The blood vessel is the vasculature carrying blood.

label: cuticle of mesopretarsus
Defs: The cuticle of the appendage of the mid leg that is attached to the mesotarsus by the mesotarso-mesopretarsal conjunctiva.

label: pulmonary vein
Defs: Pulmonary veins are blood vessels that transport blood from the lungs to the heart[GO].

label: skeletal muscle tissue of trunk
Defs: A portion of skeletal muscle tissue in the trunk.

label: negative regulation of execution phase of apoptosis
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of execution phase of apoptosis.

label: cell proliferation involved in endocardial cushion morphogenesis
Defs: Any cell proliferation that is involved in endocardial cushion morphogenesis.

label: aorta
Defs: The main trunk of the systemic arterial system that carries blood from the heart to all the organs and other structures of the body, bringing oxygenated blood to all parts of the body in the systemic circulation.

label: animal organ morphogenesis
Defs: Morphogenesis of an animal organ. An organ is defined as a tissue or set of tissues that work together to perform a specific function or functions. Morphogenesis is the process in which anatomical structures are generated and organized. Organs are commonly observed as visibly distinct structures, but may also exist as loosely associated clusters of cells that work together to perform a specific function or functions.

label: protein catabolic process in the vacuole
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a protein in the vacuole, usually by the action of vacuolar proteases.

label: positive regulation of osteoclast differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of osteoclast differentiation.

label: spinasternum
Defs: The part of the sternum that is attached to the posterior margin of the furcasternum and to the anterior margin of the poststernite.

label: ADP-ribosyl cyclase
Defs: A protein that contains the ADP-ribosyl cyclase domain (Pfam:PF02267).

label: cell activation involved in immune response
Defs: A change in the morphology or behavior of a cell resulting from exposure to an activating factor such as a cellular or soluble ligand, leading to the initiation or perpetuation of an immune response.

label: negative regulation of germ cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of germ cell proliferation.

label: retinal cone cell
Defs: One of the two photoreceptor cell types in the vertebrate retina. In cones the photopigment is in invaginations of the cell membrane of the outer segment. Cones are less sensitive to light than rods, but they provide vision with higher spatial and temporal acuity, and the combination of signals from cones with different pigments allows color vision.

label: larynx submucosa gland
Defs: A gland that is part of a larynx submucosa [Automatically generated definition].

label: areolate
Defs: A surface feature shape inhering in a surface by virtue of the bearer\'s being divided by ridge-like structures into a number of small, irregular spaces.

label: oblong
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a somewhat elongated form with approximately parallel sides.

label: regulation of smooth muscle cell migration
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of smooth muscle cell migration.

label: wall of esophagus
Defs: An anatomical wall that is part of a esophagus [Automatically generated definition].

label: dumbbell-shaped
Defs: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having two parts, roughly spherical and of equal size, connected by a bar.

label: fibroblast of skin of back
Defs: A fibroblast that is part of skin of back.

label: erythematous
Defs: Red due to increase blood circulation in a defined area.

label: postsynaptic modulation of chemical synaptic transmission
Defs: Any process, acting in the postsynapse that results in modulation of chemical synaptic transmission.

label: septum transversum development
Defs: The progression of the septum transversum from its initial formation to the mature structure. The septum transversum is a portion of the trunk mesenchyme.

label: somatic layer of lateral plate mesoderm

label: dendrite
Defs: A neuron projection that has a short, tapering, morphology. In most neurons, the impulse is conveyed from dendrites to axon via the cell body, but in some types of unipolar neuron, the impulse does not travel via the cell body.

label: lung development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the lung over time, from its formation to the mature structure. In all air-breathing vertebrates the lungs are developed from the ventral wall of the oesophagus as a pouch which divides into two sacs. In amphibians and many reptiles the lungs retain very nearly this primitive sac-like character, but in the higher forms the connection with the esophagus becomes elongated into the windpipe and the inner walls of the sacs become more and more divided, until, in the mammals, the air spaces become minutely divided into tubes ending in small air cells, in the walls of which the blood circulates in a fine network of capillaries. In mammals the lungs are more or less divided into lobes, and each lung occupies a separate cavity in the thorax.

label: tarso-pretarsal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that encircles the pretarsus by joining the distal margin of the distalmost tarsomere and the proximal margin of the pretarsus.

label: 1st arch mesenchyme from neural crest
Defs: Mesenchyme that develops_from a neural crest and is part of a 1st arch mesenchyme.

label: serotonin secretion involved in inflammatory response
Defs: The regulated release of serotonin by a cell as part of an inflammatory response.

label: membrane docking
Defs: The initial attachment of a membrane or protein to a target membrane. Docking requires only that the proteins come close enough to interact and adhere.

label: life cycle
Defs: An entire span of an organism\'s life, commencing with the zygote stage and ending in the death of the organism.

label: invariant color
Defs: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking or not exhibiting variation of color.

label: connective tissue
Defs: Tissue with cells that deposit non-polarized extracellular matrix including connective tissue fibers and ground substance.

label: segmented
Defs: Consisting of segments or similar parts arranged in a longitudinal series.

label: acute
Defs: A quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a sudden onset, sharp rise, and short course.

label: negative regulation of cellular process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of a cellular process, any of those that are carried out at the cellular level, but are not necessarily restricted to a single cell. For example, cell communication occurs among more than one cell, but occurs at the cellular level.

label: organelle organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of an organelle within a cell. An organelle is an organized structure of distinctive morphology and function. Includes the nucleus, mitochondria, plastids, vacuoles, vesicles, ribosomes and the cytoskeleton. Excludes the plasma membrane.

label: mesothelial cell
Defs: A flattened epithelial cell of mesenchymal origin that lines the serous cavity.

label: human xenobiotic metabolite
Defs: Any human metabolite produced by metabolism of a xenobiotic compound in humans.

label: acellular membrane
Defs: An acellular anatomical structure that is the bounding layer of a anatomical structure.

label: negative regulation of steroid biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of steroids, compounds with a 1,2,cyclopentanoperhydrophenanthrene nucleus.

label: chondrocyte development involved in endochondral bone morphogenesis
Defs: The progression of a chondrocyte over time from after its commitment to its mature state where the chondrocyte will contribute to the shaping of an endochondral bone.

label: inverted
Defs: An oriented quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being reversed in position, order, or condition.

label: positive regulation of muscle cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that increases the rate or frequency of muscle cell apoptotic process, a form of programmed cell death induced by external or internal signals that trigger the activity of proteolytic caspases whose actions dismantle a muscle cell and result in its death.

label: right pulmonary vein
Defs: Vein that drains right lung and returns blood to the heart.

label: negative regulation of phagocytosis
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of phagocytosis.

label: cellular component disassembly involved in execution phase of apoptosis
Defs: The breakdown of structures such as organelles, proteins, or other macromolecular structures during apoptosis.

label: mesenchyme of tongue
Defs: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing tongue [Automatically generated definition].

label: organized
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting organisation.

label: dark pale pink
Defs: Pink color having medium brightness and low saturation.

label: normal size
Defs: A size quality which is relatively normal or average

label: endodermal cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized features of an endoderm cell, a cell of the inner of the three germ layers of the embryo.

label: antero-lateral region
Defs: Anatomical region that overlaps the anterior and lateral regions of a body or body part.

label: regulation of smooth muscle tissue development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of smooth muscle tissue development.

label: pentagonal
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having five angles and five sides.

label: trachea formation
Defs: The process pertaining to the initial formation of a trachea from unspecified parts. The process begins with the specific processes that contribute to the appearance of the discrete structure and ends when the trachea is recognizable. The trachea is the portion of the airway that attaches to the bronchi as it branches.

label: lymphocyte activation
Defs: A change in morphology and behavior of a lymphocyte resulting from exposure to a specific antigen, mitogen, cytokine, chemokine, cellular ligand, or soluble factor.

label: neural plate regionalization
Defs: The pattern specification process that results in the subdivision of an axis or axes of the neural plate in space to define an area or volume in which specific patterns of cell differentiation will take place or in which cells interpret a specific environment.

label: RNA localization to nucleus
Defs: A macromolecular localization process in which RNA is transported to and maintained in a location within the nucleus.

label: negative regulation of protein localization to cell-cell junction
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to cell-cell junction.

label: cardiac left atrium formation
Defs: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of a left cardiac atrium from unspecified parts.

label: profemoral muscle
Defs: The somatic muscle that inserts in the profemur.

label: acinar cell proliferation
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of acinar cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population. An acinar cell is a secretory cell that is grouped together with other cells of the same type to form grape-shaped clusters known as acini (singular acinus).

label: serial number
Defs: A serial number is an information content entity which is a unique sequence of characters borne by part of manufactured product or its packaging that is assigned to each individual in some class of products, and so can serve as a way to identify an individual product within the class. Serial numbers can be encoded in a variety of other information objects, such as bar codes, numerals, or patterns of dots.

label: response to norepinephrine
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a norepinephrine stimulus. Norepinephrine is a catecholamine that has the formula C8H11NO3; it acts as a hormone, and as a neurotransmitter in most of the sympathetic nervous system.

label: stratified squamous epithelium
Defs: Multilaminar epithelium which consists of more than one layer of squamous cells only one layer of which is in contact with a basement membrane. Examples: keratinized stratified squamous epithelium, epithelium of wall of esophagus.[FMA].

label: negative regulation of osteoclast development
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of osteoclast development.

label: nonpolar polarity
Defs: A molecular quality which inheres in a molecular entity when the molecular entity does not possess an electrical dipole.

label: CD34-positive, CD38-positive megakaryocyte erythroid progenitor cell
Defs: A megakaryocyte erythroid progenitor cell is CD34-positive, CD38-positive and is IL3-receptor alpha-negative and CD45RA-negative.

label: eye skin gland
Defs: A skin gland that is part of a camera-type eye [Automatically generated definition].

label: vasculature
Defs: An interconnected tubular multi-tissue structure contains fluid that is actively transported around the organism[ZFA]. Examples: vasculature of lung, vasculature of face.

label: positive regulation of mesenchymal stem cell migration
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of mesenchymal stem cell migration.

label: positive regulation of ectoderm development
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of ectoderm development.

label: decurrent
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being prolonged below the point of insertion.

label: regulation of cellular component biogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cellular component biogenesis, a process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of a cellular component.

label: activation quality
Defs: A quality that inheres in a bearer in virtue of its realizing one of its functions.

label: negative regulation of granulocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of granulocyte differentiation.

label: positive regulation of antimicrobial peptide secretion
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of antimicrobial peptide secretion.

label: plasma membrane signaling receptor complex
Defs: Any protein complex that is part of the plasma membrane and which functions as a signaling receptor.

label: negative regulation of dendritic cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of dendritic cell differentiation.

label: pleurosternal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus that separates the ventral region of the pleuron from the lateral region of the sternum.

label: gland morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of a gland are generated and organized.

label: right lung
Defs: Lung which consists of the right upper lobe, middle lobe and right lower lobe.[FMA].

label: fused with
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being merged with another entity.

label: data about an ontology part
Defs: data about an ontology part is a data item about a part of an ontology, for example a term

label: left ovarian vein
Defs: Ovarian vein, each instance of which is a tributary  of some left renal vein that drains the left pampiniform plexus of some broad ligament.

label: presumptive endoderm
Defs: Presumptive structure of the blastula that will develop into endoderm.

label: compound eye
Defs: A light sensing organ composed of ommatidia.

label: increased volume
Defs: A volume which is relatively high.

label: subatomic particle
Defs: A particle smaller than an atom.

label: regulation of acinar cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of acinar cell proliferation.

label: alpha-amino acid catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of an alpha-amino acid.

label: unicellular ectodermal gland
Defs: The ectodermal gland that is composed of one cell

label: negative regulation of glycogen metabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving glycogen.

label: inorganic molecular entity transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Enables the transfer of an inorganic molecular entity from the outside of a cell to the inside of the cell across a membrane. An inorganic molecular entity is a molecular entity that contains no carbon.

label: regulation of organ growth
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of growth of an organ of an organism.

label: cortical subplate
Defs: The transient outer neural tube region that contains the first generated post-mitotic neurons that receive synaptic input from thalamic axons and in turn project axons to the developing cortical plate.

label: regulation of cell differentiation involved in embryonic placenta development
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of cell differentiation that contributes to the progression of the placenta over time, from its initial condition to its mature state.

label: watery
Defs: Having the consistency of water.

label: positive regulation of microtubule depolymerization
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of microtubule depolymerization.

label: regulation of cell proliferation involved in outflow tract morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell proliferation involved in outflow tract morphogenesis.

label: multi organ part structure
Defs: An multicellular anatomical structure that has subparts of multiple organs as a part.

label: CD3 subunit with immunoglobulin domain
Defs: A protein with a core domain composition consisting of an extracellular N-terminal domain that adopts an immunoglobulin fold, a transmembrane domain, and an intracellular C-terminal domain with a single copy of the Immunoreceptor tyrosine-based activation motif (Pfam:PF02189) (ITAM). It constitutes the invariant subunit of the T cell antigen receptor (TCR). TCR is a surface receptor on T cells responsible for recognizing MHC-restricted antigens and initiating the cellular immune response.

label: negative regulation of dendritic cell chemotaxis
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of dendritic cell chemotaxis.

label: oocyte microtubule cytoskeleton organization
Defs: Formation and maintenance of a polarized microtubule array originating from a microtubule-organizing center (MTOC) in the oocyte. An example of this is found in Drosophila melanogaster.

label: organic cation
Defs: Any organic ion with a net positive charge.

label: positive regulation of skeletal muscle hypertrophy
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of skeletal muscle hypertrophy.

label: anteroventral orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed anteroventrally.

label: future central nervous system
Defs: Primordium that develops into the central nervous system.

label: regional part of spinal cord
Defs: A multi-tissue structure that is part of a spinal cord.

label: decreased efficiency
Defs: An efficiency which is relatively low.

label: G protein-coupled acetylcholine receptor signaling pathway involved in heart process
Defs: A G protein-coupled acetylcholine receptor signaling pathway, which contributes to a circulatory system process carried out by the heart.

label: tentorium
Defs: The solid, paired, branching cuticular invagination of the head capsule that is attached to the antenna and the mouthparts via muscles.

label: pectoral girdle bone
Defs: A bone that is part of a pectoral girdle region.

label: refractile
Defs: A reflectivity quality inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s ability to refract light.

label: integrin alpha
Defs: A protein that is composed of a long N-terminal extracellular domain, a transmembrane domain and a short cytoplasmic C-terminal domain. The N-terminal domain contains beta-propeller repeats (interrupted by an A domain in a subset of integrins alpha), while the C-terminal domain contains a GFFxR motif.

label: premento-paraglossal muscle
Defs: The cranio-labial muscle that is attached to the prementum and the paraglossa.

label: vesicle-mediated transport
Defs: A cellular transport process in which transported substances are moved in membrane-bounded vesicles; transported substances are enclosed in the vesicle lumen or located in the vesicle membrane. The process begins with a step that directs a substance to the forming vesicle, and includes vesicle budding and coating. Vesicles are then targeted to, and fuse with, an acceptor membrane.

label: spotted
Defs: A color pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of bearer\'s being marked with a round area of different hue or degree of saturation.

label: pair of lungs
Defs: The pair of anatomical structures comprised of a left lung and right lung.

label: regulation of cellular metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways by which individual cells transform chemical substances.

label: positive regulation of hematopoietic stem cell migration
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of hematopoietic stem cell migration.

label: peptide transport
Defs: The directed movement of peptides, compounds of two or more amino acids where the alpha carboxyl group of one is bound to the alpha amino group of another, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: eyeball of camera-type eye
Defs: The core globe-shaped component of the camera-type eye.

label: glandular epithelial cell development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a glandular epithelial cell over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A glandular epithelial cell is a columnar/cuboidal epithelial cell is a cell found in a two dimensional sheet with a free surface exposed to the lumen of a gland.

label: submucosa of body of stomach
Defs: A submucosa that is part of a body of stomach [Automatically generated definition].

label: dorso-lateral margin
Defs: Anatomical margin that is located on the dorso-lateral region of the body or body part.

label: cuticle of mesocoxa
Defs: The cuticle of the segment of the mid leg that is attached to the latero-ventral region of the mesothorax by the basal mesocoxal conjunctiva and to the mesotrochanter by the mesocoxal-mesotrochanteral conjunctiva.

label: negative regulation of response to acetate
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of response to acetate.

label: nongranular leukocyte
Defs: A leukocyte that lacks granules.

label: alkaloid biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of alkaloids, nitrogen-containing natural products which are not otherwise classified as nonprotein amino acids, amines, peptides, amines, cyanogenic glycosides, glucosinolates, cofactors, phytohormones, or primary metabolite (such as purine or pyrimidine bases).

label: negative regulation of secretion
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the controlled release of a substance from a cell or a tissue.

label: oviduct morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which anatomical structures of the oviduct are generated and organized. An oviduct is a tube through which an ova passes from the ovary to the uterus, or from the ovary to the outside of the organism.

label: dorsal cranio-mandibular articulation
Defs: The articular surface of the head capsule on the ventral region of the clypealia

label: cuticle of mesotarsus
Defs: The cuticle of the segment of the mid leg that is composed of mesotarsomeres connected to each other by intertarsomeral conjunctiva. The first mesotarsomere is connected to the distal margin of the mesotibia by the mesotibio-mesotarsal conjunctiva and the last mesotarsomere is connected to the proximal margin of the mesopretarsus by the mesotarso-mesopretarsal conjunctiva.

label: plasma membrane organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the plasma membrane.

label: regulation of cardiac conduction
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac conduction.

label: zygote stage
Defs: A stage at which the organism is a single cell produced by means of sexual reproduction.

label: trunk ganglion
Defs: Ganglion which is located in the trunk.

label: protein localization to actin filament bundle
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, the location of an actin filament bundle.

label: secretion by cell
Defs: The controlled release of a substance by a cell.

label: heterobicyclic compound
Defs: A bicyclic compound in which at least one of the rings contains at least one skeletal heteroatom.

label: epithelial cell of esophagus
Defs: An epithelial cell of the esophagus.

label: postcranial axial skeletal system
Defs: Subdivision of the skeletal system which consists of the postcranial axial skeleton plus associated joints.

label: dendritic cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a precursor cell type acquires the specialized features of a dendritic cell. A dendritic cell is a leukocyte of dendritic lineage specialized in the uptake, processing, and transport of antigens to lymph nodes for the purpose of stimulating an immune response via T cell activation.

label: respiratory system epithelium
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

label: blurry
Defs: An optical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking focus.

label: venous blood vessel development
Defs: The progression of the venous blood vessel over time from its initial formation to the mature structure. Venous blood vessels carry blood back to the heart after the capillary bed.

label: posteromedial to
Defs: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being located toward the rear and mid-line surface of an organism relative to another entity.

label: gray matter
Defs: A nervous system structure composed primarily of nerve cell bodies (somas). May also include dendrites and the initial unmyelinated portion of axons.

label: hematopoietic multipotent progenitor cell
Defs: A hematopoietic multipotent progenitor cell is multipotent, but not capable of long-term self-renewal. These cells are characterized as lacking lineage cell surface markers and being CD34-positive in both mice and humans.

label: negative regulation of cardioblast differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cardioblast differentiation, the process in which a relatively unspecialized mesodermal cell acquires the specialized structural and/or functional features of a cardioblast. A cardioblast is a cardiac precursor cell. It is a cell that has been committed to a cardiac fate, but will undergo more cell division rather than terminally differentiating.

label: curved lingually
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being curved towards the tongue.

label: establishment of protein localization
Defs: The directed movement of a protein to a specific location.

label: osteoclast differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized monocyte acquires the specialized features of an osteoclast. An osteoclast is a specialized phagocytic cell associated with the absorption and removal of the mineralized matrix of bone tissue.

label: glycosaminoglycan biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of glycosaminoglycans, any of a group of polysaccharides that contain amino sugars.

label: pulmonary trunk
Defs: An arterial trunk which is continuous with the heart and branches into the pulmonary arteries.

label: subdivision of skeleton
Defs: Anatomical cluster consisting of the skeletal elements (i.e. bone elements, cartilage elements, cartilage condensations) that are part of an individual subdivision of the organism. Excludes joints.

label: left lung development
Defs: The biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of a left lung from an initial condition to its mature state. This process begins with the formation of the left lung and ends with the mature structure. The left lung is the lung which is on the left side of the anterior posterior axis looking from a dorsal to ventral aspect.

label: abdominal tergite II-abdominal tergite III conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect abdomen that connects the abdominal tergite II and the abdominal tergite III.

label: central nervous system macrophage
Defs: A tissue-resident macrophage found in the central nervous system.

label: bilobed
Defs: A lobed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being divided into or having two lobes.

label: hepatic sinusoid of right of lobe of liver
Defs: A hepatic sinusoid that is part of a right lobe of liver.

label: negative regulation of formation of translation initiation ternary complex
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of formation of translation initiation ternary complex.

label: corneal blood vessel
Defs: A blood vessel that is part of a cornea [Automatically generated definition].

label: blastocyst
Defs: The mammalian blastocyst is a hollow ball of cells containing two cell types, the inner cell mass and the trophectoderm[GO].

label: autofluorescence
Defs: A fluorescence quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting fluorescence which is self-induced.

label: response to stimulus involved in regulation of muscle adaptation
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus. This occurs as part of the regulation of muscle adaptation.

label: cranial suture
Defs: Fibrous joint in which the articulating bones or cartilages of the skull are connected by sutural ligaments (scant amount of collagenous dense connective tissue). Examples: sagittal suture, frontal suture.

label: flavourful
Defs: A flavor quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having flavour.

label: stability
Defs: quality, state, or degree of being stable.

label: monoamine
Defs: An aralylamino compound which contains one amino group connected to an aromatic ring by a two-carbon chain. Monoamines are derived from aromatic amino acids like phenylalanine, tyrosine, tryptophan, and the thyroid hormones by the action of aromatic amino acid decarboxylase enzymes.

label: regulation of karyogamy
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of karyogamy, the creation of a single nucleus from multiple nuclei as a result of membrane fusion.

label: norepinephrine transport
Defs: The directed movement of norepinephrine into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore. Norepinephrine (3,4-dihydroxyphenyl-2-aminoethanol) is a hormone secreted by the adrenal medulla and a neurotransmitter in the sympathetic peripheral nervous system and in some tracts of the CNS. It is also the biosynthetic precursor of epinephrine.

label: positive regulation of meiotic cell cycle process involved in oocyte maturation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of meiotic cell cycle process involved in oocyte maturation.

label: metafemoral muscle
Defs: The somatic muscle that inserts in the metafemur.

label: acetylcholine uptake
Defs: The directed movement of acetylcholine into a cell, typically presynaptic neurons or glial cells. Acetylcholine is a major neurotransmitter and neuromodulator both in the central and peripheral nervous systems. It also acts as a paracrine signal in various non-neural tissues.

label: cardiac muscle of right ventricle
Defs: A portion of cardiac muscle tissue that is part of a right ventricle [Automatically generated definition].

label: G protein-coupled receptor activity
Defs: Combining with an extracellular signal and transmitting the signal across the membrane by activating an associated G-protein; promotes the exchange of GDP for GTP on the alpha subunit of a heterotrimeric G-protein complex.

label: ameboidal-type cell migration
Defs: Cell migration that is accomplished by extension and retraction of a pseudopodium.

label: negative regulation of serotonin secretion
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of serotonin.

label: connective tissue development
Defs: The progression of a connective tissue over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: extraembryonic membrane development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an extraembryonic membrane over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: fasciculus of spinal cord
Defs: A fascicle that is part of a spinal cord.

label: negative regulation of steroid hormone secretion
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of steroid hormone secretion.

label: neuron of the ventral spinal cord
Defs: A neuron of the ventral spinal cord.
