label: multicellular organismal signaling
Defs: The transfer of information occurring at the level of a multicellular organism.

label: desaturated cyan
Defs: A color consisting of cyan colour and low saturation.

label: increased fluid flow
Defs: A fluid flow that is relatively high.

label: negative regulation of protein localization to ciliary membrane
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to ciliary membrane.

label: blastocyst growth
Defs: An increase in size of a blastocyst due to expansion of the blastocoelic cavity cell shape changes and cell proliferation.

label: stem cell of epidermis
Defs: A somatic stem cell that is part of the epidermis.

label: greasy
Defs: A coating which is oily and slippery.

label: presynaptic actin cytoskeleton organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising actin filaments and their associated proteins in the presynaptic actin cytoskeleton.

label: respiratory system arterial endothelium
Defs: An endothelium of artery that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

label: dappled
Defs: A color pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of bearer\'s being marked with small spots, patches, or specks of hue or degree of saturation differing from that of the background.

label: extracellular exosome biogenesis
Defs: The assembly and secretion of an extracellular exosome, a membrane-bounded vesicle that is released into the extracellular region by fusion of the limiting endosomal membrane of a multivesicular body with the plasma membrane.

label: cellular motility
Defs: A cellular quality inhering in a cell by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits the ability to move spontaneously.

label: organellar ribosome
Defs: A ribosome contained within a subcellular membrane-bounded organelle.

label: glycosaminoglycan binding
Defs: Binding to a glycan (polysaccharide) containing a substantial proportion of aminomonosaccharide residues.

label: negative regulation of organelle organization
Defs: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of an organelle.

label: decreased process quality
Defs: A quality of a process that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

label: negative regulation of cilium movement
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of cilium movement, the directed, self-propelled movement of a cilium.

label: positive regulation of myotome development
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of myotome development.

label: sympathomimetic agent
Defs: A drug that mimics the effects of stimulating postganglionic adrenergic sympathetic nerves. Included in this class are drugs that directly stimulate adrenergic receptors and drugs that act indirectly by provoking the release of adrenergic transmitters.

label: photoinsensitive
Defs: A photosensitivity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking photosensitivity.

label: head bone
Defs: A bone that is part of a head [Automatically generated definition].

label: megakaryocyte-erythroid progenitor cell
Defs: A progenitor cell committed to the megakaryocyte and erythroid lineages.

label: population quality
Defs: A quality that inheres in an entire population or part of a population.

label: hydrophobic
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lacking affinity for water; tending to repel and not absorb water; tending not to dissolve in or mix with or be wetted by water.

label: cuticle of insect thorax
Defs: The region of cuticle that is connected to some muscles of the fore and hind legs and is posterior to the neck membrane and aterior to the first abdominal spiracle.

label: sensory system
Defs: Anatomical system that overlaps the nervous system and is responsible for receiving and processing sensory information.

label: cellular ammonium homeostasis
Defs: Any biological process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of ammonium at the level of the cell.

label: ventralized
Defs: A malformed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s gross morphology containing what are normally ventral structures and missing some or all of what are normally dorsal structures.

label: carbohydrate derivative transport
Defs: The directed movement of a carbohydrate derivative into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: thoracic aorta
Defs: The part of the aorta that extends from the origin at the heart to the diaphragm, and from which arises numerous branches that supply oxygenated blood to the chest cage and the organs within the chest.

label: double bouquet morphology
Defs: A cell morphology that inheres in neurons with bitufted dendritic morphology but with the special feature of a tight fascicular axonal cylinder that resembles a \'horse tail\'.

label: trapezoid
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being a quadrilateral with two parallel sides.

label: blood vasculature
Defs: A vascular network consisting of blood vessels.

label: regulation of skeletal muscle cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of skeletal muscle cell differentiation.

label: normal variability of rate
Defs: A variability of rate which is relatively normal or average

label: CD11b-positive dendritic cell
Defs: A conventional dendritic cell that expresses CD11b (ITGAM).

label: circling
Defs: A behavioral quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s exhibiting movement in a circular course.

label: Bronsted base
Defs: A molecular entity capable of accepting a hydron from a donor (Bronsted acid).

label: sodium ion transmembrane transport
Defs: A process in which a sodium ion is transported from one side of a membrane to the other by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: statistical analysis textual entity
Defs: A textual entity documenting statistical analysis tools and techniques employed.

label: vesicle fusion to plasma membrane
Defs: Fusion of the membrane of a vesicle with the plasma membrane, thereby releasing its contents into the extracellular space.

label: cardiac chamber morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which a cardiac chamber is generated and organized. A cardiac chamber is an enclosed cavity within the heart.

label: heart right ventricle
Defs: A cardiac ventricle that is in the right side of the heart.

label: negative regulation of dermatome development
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the progression of the dermatome over time, from its initial formation to the mature structure. The dermatome is the portion of a somite that will form skin.

label: respiratory system blood vessel endothelium
Defs: A blood vessel endothelium that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

label: polysaccharide immune receptor activity
Defs: Combining with a polysaccharide and transmitting the signal to initiate an innate immune response. A polysaccharide is a polymer of many (typically more than 10) monosaccharide residues linked glycosidically.

label: submucosa of pyloric antrum
Defs: A submucosa that is part of a pyloric antrum [Automatically generated definition].

label: G protein-coupled serotonin receptor signaling pathway
Defs: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of a G protein-coupled serotonin receptor binding to one of its physiological ligands.

label: atrophied
Defs: A size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of a part or parts of the bearer\'s being decreased in size due to reduction in tissue mass through wasting.

label: striated muscle cell apoptotic process
Defs: A form of programmed cell death induced by external or internal signals that trigger the activity of proteolytic caspases, whose actions dismantle a striated muscle cell and result in its death. Striated muscle cells make up striated muscle fibers which are divided by transverse bands into striations.

label: decreased tolerance to
Defs: A tolerance quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s decreased ability to endure a stimulus.

label: endothelial cell of hepatic sinusoid
Defs: An endothelial cell that is part of the hepatic sinusoid. These cells possess flattened areas containing perforations about 0.1 micrometers in diameter, known as fenestrae. The fenestrae are arranged in groups known as sieve plates.

label: Golgi to plasma membrane protein transport
Defs: The directed movement of proteins from the Golgi to the plasma membrane in transport vesicles that move from the trans-Golgi network to the plasma membrane.

label: increased pressure
Defs: A pressure which is relatively high.

label: trans-synaptic signaling by lipid
Defs: Cell-cell signaling from post to pre-synapse, across the synaptic cleft, mediated by a lipid.

label: convex angle to
Defs: An angle which is less than 180 degrees to another entity.

label: mucosa of small intestine
Defs: A mucosa that is part of a small intestine [Automatically generated definition].

label: normal resistance to
Defs: A resistance to a stimulus which is relatively normal or average

label: regulation of actin filament bundle assembly
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the assembly of actin filament bundles.

label: negative regulation of oxygen metabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of oxygen metabolic process.

label: heart blood vessel
Defs: A blood vessel that is part of a heart [Automatically generated definition].

label: regulation of catecholamine metabolic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving catecholamines.

label: cardiac muscle cell development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a cardiac muscle cell over time, from its formation to the mature state.

label: musculoskeletal system
Defs: Anatomical system that consists of the muscular and skeletal systems.

label: negative regulation of protein polymerization
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the process of creating protein polymers.

label: capsule of lens
Defs: The elastic, clear, membrane-like structure, that is outer most layer of the lens.

label: multicellular organismal movement
Defs: Any physiological process involved in changing the position of a multicellular organism or an anatomical part of a multicellular organism.

label: sporadic
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s once or in or a few unpredictable instances.

label: lumen of terminal part of digestive tract
Defs: An anatomical space that is enclosed by a terminal part of digestive tract.

label: neoplastic, non-invasive
Defs: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition not to invade surrounding tissues.

label: regulation of cell maturation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell maturation.

label: embryo implantation
Defs: Attachment of the blastocyst to the uterine lining.

label: tibial spur
Defs: The spur on the distal margin of the tibia.

label: retrograde axonal transport
Defs: The directed movement of organelles or molecules along microtubules from the cell periphery toward the cell body in nerve cell axons.

label: trigeminal ganglion formation
Defs: The process that gives rise to the trigeminal ganglion. This process pertains to the initial formation of a structure from unspecified parts.

label: regulation of protein localization to nucleus
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to nucleus.

label: setose cuticle
Defs: The region of the cuticle that bears an anatomical collection that is composed of setae.

label: positive regulation of mesenchymal cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of mesenchymal cell apoptotic process.

label: cell-cell signaling
Defs: Any process that mediates the transfer of information from one cell to another. This process includes signal transduction in the receiving cell and, where applicable, release of a ligand and any processes that actively facilitate its transport and presentation to the receiving cell.  Examples include signaling via soluble ligands, via cell adhesion molecules and via gap junctions.

label: heterochromatin
Defs: A compact and highly condensed form of chromatin that is refractory to transcription.

label: cerebral hemisphere
Defs: One of two bilateral, largely symmetrical organ subdivisions within the telencephalon which contain the cerebral cortex and cerebral white matter.[FMA].

label: premental-paraglossal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the labium that connects the prementum and the paraglossa.

label: tissue migration
Defs: The process in which the population of cells that make up a tissue undergo directed movement.

label: leukocyte
Defs: An achromatic cell of the myeloid or lymphoid lineages capable of ameboid movement, found in blood or other tissue.

label: increased distance
Defs: A distance which is greater relative to the normal or average.

label: grey
Defs: A color between white and black colors.

label: structure
Defs: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s relative position, shape, arrangements and connectivity of an organism\'s various parts; the pattern underlying its form.

label: epithelium of lower jaw
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a lower jaw [Automatically generated definition].

label: regulation of compound eye photoreceptor cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of compound eye photoreceptor cell differentiation.

label: regulation of hemopoiesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of hemopoiesis.

label: bronchus cartilage development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of lung cartilage over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Cartilage is a connective tissue dominated by extracellular matrix containing collagen type II and large amounts of proteoglycan, particularly chondroitin sulfate.

label: multinuclear osteoclast
Defs: A specialized multinuclear osteoclast associated with the absorption and removal of bone.

label: gland of digestive tract
Defs: A gland that is part of a digestive tract [Automatically generated definition].

label: positive regulation of excitatory postsynaptic potential
Defs: Any process that enhances the establishment or increases the extent of the excitatory postsynaptic potential (EPSP) which is a temporary increase in postsynaptic potential due to the flow of positively charged ions into the postsynaptic cell. The flow of ions that causes an EPSP is an excitatory postsynaptic current (EPSC) and makes it easier for the neuron to fire an action potential.

label: paralysed
Defs: A behavioral quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being affected by loss of the ability to move a body part.

label: anus
Defs: Orifice at the opposite end of an animal\'s digestive tract from the mouth. Its function is to expel feces, unwanted semi-solid matter produced during digestion, which, depending on the type of animal, may be one or more of: matter which the animal cannot digest, such as bones; food material after all the nutrients have been extracted, for example cellulose or lignin; ingested matter which would be toxic if it remained in the digestive tract; and dead or excess gut bacteria and other endosymbionts.

label: sclerotome development
Defs: The progression of the sclerotome over time, from its initial formation to the mature structure. The sclerotome is the portion of the somite that will give rise to a vertebra.

label: apical-basal axis relative to substrate
Defs: An axis that extends through an organism or organism part from the part of the organism or organism part attached to a substrate (basal) to the furthest from the attachment (apical). Note that the apical-basal axis is often used for organismal parts where there is attachment via a basal lamina or other structure.

label: placenta blood vessel
Defs: A blood vessel of the placenta.

label: mesentery of heart
Defs: A mesentery that surrounds the heart.

label: fibroblast growth factor 8
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human FGF8 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: serous sac
Defs: Organ with organ cavity, which has as parts a serous membrane and a serous cavity . Examples: pleural sac, pericardial sac, tendon sheath, bursa.[FMA].

label: heart
Defs: A myogenic muscular circulatory organ found in the vertebrate cardiovascular system composed of chambers of cardiac muscle. It is the primary circulatory organ.

label: positive regulation of macrophage cytokine production
Defs: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of macrophage cytokine production. Macrophage cytokine production is the appearance of a chemokine due to biosynthesis or secretion following a cellular stimulus, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

label: decreased female receptivity
Defs: A female receptivity which is relatively low.

label: oral cavity
Defs: Anatomical cavity at the start of the digestive tract that that is enclosed by the mouth. The boundaries and contents vary depending on the species. In vertebrates, the boundaries are the oral opening, the cheeks, the palate and (if present) the palatoglossal arch - if this is not present then the mouth and pharynx form the oropharyngeal cavity. The buccal cavity contains the teeth, tongue and palate (when present).

label: grooved
Defs: Texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being marked with one or more channels.

label: phagocyte
Defs: Any cell capable of ingesting particulate matter via phagocytosis.

label: submucosa of bronchus
Defs: A submucosa that is part of a bronchus [Automatically generated definition].

label: decreased duration
Defs: A duration quality of a process which is relatively low.

label: endothelial cell activation involved in immune response
Defs: A change in the morphology or behavior of an endothelial cell resulting from exposure to an activating factor such as a cellular or soluble ligand, leading to the initiation or perpetuation of an immune response.

label: muscle cell
Defs: A mature contractile cell, commonly known as a myocyte. This cell has as part of its cytoplasm myofibrils organized in various patterns.

label: unilateral
Defs: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s involvement of only one part or side.

label: contralateral side
Defs: On the opposite side.

label: fringed
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having an ornamental border consisting of short straight or twisted threads or strips hanging from cut or raveled edges or from a separate band.

label: spermatheca
Defs: The region of the cuticle that is part of the oviduct and connected to the bursa copulatrix.

label: domed
Defs: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having a shape resembling a dome.

label: esophagus skeletal muscle
Defs: A portion of skeletal muscle tissue that is part of a esophagus [Automatically generated definition].

label: amphiphilic
Defs: Having both hydrophilic and hydrophobic (or lipophilic) groups.

label: trigeminal nuclear complex
Defs: The sensory trigeminal nerve nuclei are the largest of the cranial nerve nuclei, and extend through the whole of the midbrain, pons and medulla. There is also a distinct trigeminal motor nucleus that is medial to the chief sensory nucleus[WP].

label: retrograde trans-synaptic signaling by neuropeptide, modulating synaptic transmission
Defs: Modulation of synaptic transmittion by cell-cell signaling across the synaptic cleft from postsynapse to presynapse, mediated by a neuropeptide.

label: vagus X ganglion
Defs: The group of sensory neuron cell bodies associated with the vagus nerve.

label: quality of an aerosol
Defs: A physical quality inhering in an entity by virtue of the bearer\'s solid or liquid constituents being suspended in a gas.

label: positive regulation of smooth muscle cell migration
Defs: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of smooth muscle cell migration.

label: exocytosis
Defs: A process of secretion by a cell that results in the release of intracellular molecules (e.g. hormones, matrix proteins) contained within a membrane-bounded vesicle. Exocytosis can occur either by full fusion, when the vesicle collapses into the plasma membrane, or by a kiss-and-run mechanism that involves the formation of a transient contact, a pore, between a granule (for exemple of chromaffin cells) and the plasma membrane. The latter process most of the time leads to only partial secretion of the granule content. Exocytosis begins with steps that prepare vesicles for fusion with the membrane (tethering and docking) and ends when molecules are secreted from the cell.

label: telencephalic nucleus
Defs: A nucleus of brain that is part of a telencephalon.

label: oxoacid metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving any oxoacid; an oxoacid is a compound which contains oxygen, at least one other element, and at least one hydrogen bound to oxygen, and which produces a conjugate base by loss of positive hydrogen ion(s) (hydrons).

label: portal vein
Defs: A vein that conducts blood from the digestive organs, spleen, pancreas, and gallbladder to the liver[BTO].

label: positive regulation of execution phase of apoptosis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of execution phase of apoptosis.

label: acantha
Defs: The solid cuticular protrusion that coincides with only one epidermal cell (smaller than the diameter of the epidermal cell).

label: regulation of protein tyrosine kinase activity
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of protein tyrosine kinase activity.

label: trunk taste bud
Defs: A taste bud that is located on the skin of the trunk.

label: positive regulation of melanosome transport
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of melanosome transport.

label: polypeptide
Defs: A peptide containing ten or more amino acid residues.

label: positive regulation of chromosome condensation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of chromosome condensation.

label: tissue development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a tissue over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: hindbrain-spinal cord boundary formation
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the formation of the hindbrain-spinal cord boundary.

label: pseudopodium
Defs: A temporary protrusion or retractile process of a cell, associated with flowing movements of the protoplasm, and serving for locomotion and feeding.

label: hindbrain dura mater
Defs: A dura mater that is part of a hindbrain [Automatically generated definition].

label: regulation of cell morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell morphogenesis. Cell morphogenesis is the developmental process in which the shape of a cell is generated and organized.

label: discussion section of a publication about an investigation
Defs: A part of a publication about an investigation that is about the study interpretation of the investigation

label: pyramidal neuron differentiation
Defs: The process in which a neuroblast or one of its progeny commits to a pyramidal neuron fate, migrates from the ventricular zone to the appropriate layer in the cortex and develops into a mature neuron.

label: serosa of small intestine
Defs: A serous membrane that is part of a small intestine [Automatically generated definition].

label: obsolete decreased relaxation
Defs: A relaxation which is relatively low.

label: regulation of retrograde trans-synaptic signaling by neuropeptide
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of retrograde trans-synaptic signaling by neuropeptide.

label: decumbent
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s lying or growing on the ground but with erect or rising tips.

label: metaphragma
Defs: The phragma of the abdominal tergite I that attaches to muscles attached to the metanotum.

label: quality of a fluid
Defs: A physical quality inhering in an entity exhibiting the physical charachteristics of a material that flows under applied force.

label: decreased size
Defs: A size quality which is relatively low.

label: hematopoietic lineage restricted progenitor cell
Defs: A hematopoietic progenitor cell that is capable of developing into only one lineage of hematopoietic cells.

label: regulation of translation at postsynapse
Defs: Any process that regulates translation occurring at the postsynapse.

label: foveate
Defs: A texture quality inhering in a surface by virtue of the bearer\'s being marked by the presence of small, shallow, regular depressions called fovae.

label: cardiocyte differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized structural and/or functional features of a cell that will form part of the cardiac organ of an individual.

label: pretarsal muscle
Defs: The somatic muscle that inserts in the pretarsus.

label: lanceolate
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being shaped like a lance-head, considerably longer than wide, tapering towards the tip from below the middle; attached at the broad end.

label: regulation of blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of blood vessel endothelial cell differentiation.

label: presynaptic modulation of chemical synaptic transmission
Defs: Any process, acting in the presynapse that results in modulation of chemical synaptic transmission.

label: sense organ
Defs: An organ that is capable of transducing sensory stimulus to the nervous system.

label: protein localization to ciliary membrane
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a location within a ciliary membrane.

label: blood vessel smooth muscle cell
Defs: A smooth muscle cell that is part of any blood vessel.

label: wilty
Defs: To bend or hang downwards due to loss of water

label: regulation of CD4 production
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of CD4.

label: monoblast
Defs: A myeloid progenitor cell committed to the monocyte lineage. This cell is CD11b-positive, has basophilic cytoplasm, euchromatin, and the presence of a nucleolus.

label: software method
Defs: A software method (also called subroutine, subprogram, procedure, method, function, or routine) is software designed to execute a specific task.

label: presynapse
Defs: The part of a synapse that is part of the presynaptic cell.

label: outflow tract
Defs: The outflow tract is the portion of the heart through which blood flows into the arteries.

label: regulation of cell fate commitment
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell fate commitment. Cell fate commitment is the commitment of cells to specific cell fates and their capacity to differentiate into particular kinds of cells. Positional information is established through protein signals that emanate from a localized source within a cell (the initial one-cell zygote) or within a developmental field.

label: arterial blood
Defs: A blood that is part of a artery.

label: cardiac mesenchyme
Defs: The embryonic connective tissue made up of loosely aggregated mesenchymal cells, supported by interlaminar jelly, that gives rise to the developing cardiac structures.

label: saturated brown
Defs: A color consisting of brown hue and high saturation.

label: CD3 epsilon
Defs: A CD3 subunit with immunoglobulin domain that is a translation product of the human CD3E gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: negative regulation of neuron apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cell death by apoptotic process in neurons.

label: cuticle of fore leg
Defs: The cuticle of the paired appendage of the prothorax that is anterior to the cuticle of a mid leg and composed of cuticle of procoxa, cuticle of protrochanter, cuticle of profemur, cuticle of protibia, cuticle of protarsus, and cuticle of propretarsus.

label: normal force
Defs: A force which is relatively normal or average.

label: accessory nerve development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the accessory nerve over time, from its formation to the mature structure. In mice, the spinal branch of this motor nerve innervates the trapezius and the sternocleidomastoid muscles. The cranial branch joins the vagus nerve and innervates the same targets as the vagus nerve.

label: excitatory neuromuscular junction
Defs: The junction between the axon of a motor neuron and a muscle fiber. In response to the arrival of action potentials, the presynaptic button releases molecules of neurotransmitters into the synaptic cleft. These diffuse across the cleft and transmit the signal to the postsynaptic membrane of the muscle fiber, leading to a post-synaptic potential responsible for muscle contraction.

label: regulation of muscle contraction
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of muscle contraction.

label: mucosa of body of stomach
Defs: A mucosa that is part of a body of stomach [Automatically generated definition].

label: Schizosaccharomyces pombe mating type
Defs: A S. pombe mating type determined by the gene configuration on the mat1 locus.

label: blood cell
Defs: A cell found predominately in the blood.

label: undivided
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being unseparated into parts or divisions.

label: G protein-coupled glutamate receptor signaling pathway
Defs: A G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway initiated by glutamate binding to its receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process.

label: cellular response to metal ion
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a metal ion stimulus.

label: regulation of smooth muscle cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of smooth muscle cell differentiation.

label: polyatomic ion
Defs: An ion consisting of more than one atom.

label: somatostatin receptor signaling pathway
Defs: A G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway initiated by somatostatin binding to the somatostatin receptor (SSTR) on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process.

label: regulation of cell development
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of the progression of the cell over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Cell development does not include the steps involved in committing a cell to a specific fate.

label: protein localization to lysosome
Defs: A process in which a protein is transported to, or maintained in, a location within a lysosome.

label: oxoacid
Defs: A compound which contains oxygen, at least one other element, and at least one hydrogen bound to oxygen, and which produces a conjugate base by loss of positive hydrogen ion(s) (hydrons).

label: regulation of biological quality
Defs: Any process that modulates a qualitative or quantitative trait of a biological quality. A biological quality is a measurable attribute of an organism or part of an organism, such as size, mass, shape, color, etc.

label: hexaploid
Defs: A polyploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s containing six homologous sets of chromosomes.

label: musculature of trunk
Defs: Any collection of muscles that is part of a trunk [Automatically generated definition].

label: standard pyramidal morphology
Defs: A pyramidal family morphology that inheres in neurons which have a standard pyramidal shape with its apical dendrite aligned vertically.

label: Purkinje myocyte to ventricular cardiac muscle cell communication
Defs: The process that mediates interactions between a Purkinje myocyte and its surroundings that contributes to the process of the Purkinje myocyte communicating with a ventricular cardiac muscle cell in cardiac conduction. Encompasses interactions such as signaling or attachment between one cell and another cell, between a cell and an extracellular matrix, or between a cell and any other aspect of its environment.

label: regulation of cellular component organization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cell structures, including the plasma membrane and any external encapsulating structures such as the cell wall and cell envelope.

label: epithelial cell maturation
Defs: The developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for an epithelial cell to attain its fully functional state. An epithelial cell is a cell usually found in a two-dimensional sheet with a free surface.

label: facial mesenchyme
Defs: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing face.

label: negative regulation of cell communication
Defs: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of cell communication. Cell communication is the process that mediates interactions between a cell and its surroundings. Encompasses interactions such as signaling or attachment between one cell and another cell, between a cell and an extracellular matrix, or between a cell and any other aspect of its environment.

label: waxy
Defs: Presence of long chain aliphatic lipids on the surface of an organism.

label: spayed female
Defs: Female quality of being incapable to reproduce because of functional loss of the ovaries and/or uterus from surgical removal.

label: liver left lobe parenchyma
Defs: A parenchyma that is part of a left lobe of liver [Automatically generated definition].

label: receptor-type tyrosine-protein phosphatase C isoform CD45R
Defs: A receptor-type tyrosine-protein phosphatase C that is a translation product of a transcript that minimally includes the region encoded by the variable exon 4(A).

label: vasculature development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the vasculature over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The vasculature is an interconnected tubular multi-tissue structure that contains fluid that is actively transported around the organism.

label: variant temperature
Defs: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having or exhibiting variation of temperature.

label: broken into two pieces
Defs: A broken quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being separated into two contiguous wholes.

label: embryonic cell (metazoa)
Defs: A cell of the embryo.

label: primary amino compound catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of primary amino compound.

label: negative regulation of norepinephrine secretion
Defs: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of norepinephrine.

label: negative regulation of cell growth
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, extent or direction of cell growth.

label: vascular cord
Defs: The vascular cord is the primordial vasculature that will develop into blood vessels by the process of tubulogenesis[GO]. The vascular cord is composed of angioblast or vascular endothelial cells in a solid linear mass called a cord. The cord then undergoes tubulogenesis to form the lumen of the vessels[ZFA].

label: ventral surface
Defs: Anatomical surface that is located on the ventral side of the body or body part.

label: lung connective tissue development
Defs: The biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of lung connective tissue from an initial condition to its mature state. This process begins with the formation of lung connective tissue and ends with the mature structure. The lung connective tissue is a material made up of fibers forming a framework and support structure for the lungs.

label: multinucleate
Defs: A nucleate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having more than one nucleus.

label: lower respiratory tract smooth muscle
Defs: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a lower respiratory tract [Automatically generated definition].

label: somatostatin binding
Defs: Binding to somatostatin, a polypeptide hormone involved in regulating pancreatic alpha and pancreatic beta cells and controlling growth hormone secretion as well as many other functions. Somatostatin is produced by several cell types including pancreatic delta cells. There are several different mature forms of somatostatin.

label: w-shaped
Defs: An angular shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having two angles in its length giving the bearer the form of the letter W.

label: cardiac myofibril assembly
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the cardiac myofibril over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A cardiac myofibril is a myofibril specific to cardiac muscle cells.

label: regulation of cell proliferation involved in tissue homeostasis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell proliferation resulting in the maintenance of a steady-state number of cells within a tissue.

label: positive regulation of germ cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of germ cell proliferation.

label: endothelial cell of artery
Defs: A blood vessel endothelial cell that is part of an arterial endothelium.

label: muscle cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a muscle cell.

label: negative regulation of gliogenesis
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of gliogenesis, the formation of mature glia.

label: somite border
Defs: A region of somite adjacent to presomitic mesoderm.

label: cuticle of mere
Defs: The ring sclerite that is part of an appendage and is not attached to somatic muscle.

label: positive regulation of muscle contraction
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of muscle contraction.

label: chondrocyte morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the structures of a chondrocyte are generated and organized. This process occurs while the initially relatively unspecialized cell is acquiring the specialized features of a chondrocyte.

label: medial-radial axis
Defs: An anatomical axis that is perpendicular to an apical/basal axis or proximal/distal axis and extends from the center of an axis (shoot axis or root in the case of plants) to any point on the exterior of the axis.

label: transport vesicle membrane
Defs: The lipid bilayer surrounding a transport vesicle.

label: negative regulation of T cell cytokine production
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of T cell cytokine production.

label: lateral mesoderm morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the lateral mesoderm are generated and organized.

label: paraxial mesoderm morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of the paraxial mesoderm are generated and organized.

label: splenocyte
Defs: Any leukocyte that is part of a spleen.

label: glossopharyngeal nerve morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structure of the glossopharyngeal nerve is generated and organized. Various sensory and motor branches of the glossopharyngeal nerve supply nerve connections to the pharynx and back of the tongue. The branchial motor component contains motor fibers that innervate muscles that elevate the pharynx and larynx, and the tympanic branch supplies parasympathetic fibers to the otic ganglion.

label: heart ventricle wall
Defs: An anatomical wall that is part of a cardiac ventricle [Automatically generated definition].

label: fat cell
Defs: A fat-storing cell found mostly in the abdominal cavity and subcutaneous tissue of mammals. Fat is usually stored in the form of triglycerides.

label: negative regulation of amino acid transport
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of amino acids into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: transferase activity
Defs: Catalysis of the transfer of a group, e.g. a methyl group, glycosyl group, acyl group, phosphorus-containing, or other groups, from one compound (generally regarded as the donor) to another compound (generally regarded as the acceptor). Transferase is the systematic name for any enzyme of EC class 2.

label: negative regulation of signaling receptor activity
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of a signaling receptor activity.

label: ammonium ion derivative
Defs: A derivative of ammonium, NH4(+), in which one (or more) of the hydrogens bonded to the nitrogen have been replaced with univalent organyl groups. The substituting carbon of the organyl group must not itself be directly attached to a heteroatom (thereby excluding protonated amides, hemiaminals, etc).

label: cuticle of metapretarsus
Defs: The cuticle of the appendage of the hind leg that is attached to the metatarsus by the metatarso-metapretarsal conjunctiva.

label: cartilage development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a cartilage element over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Cartilage elements are skeletal elements that consist of connective tissue dominated by extracellular matrix containing collagen type II and large amounts of proteoglycan, particularly chondroitin sulfate.

label: peripheral nervous system development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the peripheral nervous system over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The peripheral nervous system is one of the two major divisions of the nervous system. Nerves in the PNS connect the central nervous system (CNS) with sensory organs, other organs, muscles, blood vessels and glands.

label: tonicity
Defs: A contractile quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s elastic tension that facilitate response to stimuli.

label: fibroblast of pulmonary artery
Defs: A fibroblast of pulmonary artery.

label: positive regulation of chromatin organization
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of chromatin organization.

label: damaged
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being harmed or injured or spoiled, such that its functionality is impaired.

label: overlap with
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s coinciding spatially, partially or wholly with another entity.

label: regulation of immune response
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the immune response, the immunological reaction of an organism to an immunogenic stimulus.

label: vesicle transport along microtubule
Defs: The directed movement of a vesicle along a microtubule, mediated by motor proteins. This process begins with the attachment of a vesicle to a microtubule, and ends when the vesicle reaches its final destination.

label: cranial ganglion maturation
Defs: A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for a cranial ganglion to attain its fully functional state.

label: negative regulation of chromosome organization
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of chromosome organization.

label: negative regulation of oligodendrocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of oligodendrocyte differentiation.

label: organic acid transport
Defs: The directed movement of organic acids, any acidic compound containing carbon in covalent linkage, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: pharyngeal arch 1
Defs: The first of the series of pharyngeal arches that develop into jaw bones or their homologs, and their associated nerves and arteries.

label: normal width
Defs: A width which is relatively normal or average

label: neuron projection bundle connecting eye with brain
Defs: A neuron projection bundle that connects the retina or its analog in the eye with the brain. This includes the vertebrate optic nerve (not truly a nerve) as well as analogous structures such as the Bolwig nerve in Drosophila.

label: regulation of iron ion transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of an iron transmembrane transporter activity.

label: positive regulation of retrograde trans-synaptic signaling by neuropeptide
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of retrograde trans-synaptic signaling by neuropeptide.

label: negative regulation of apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cell death by apoptotic process.

label: regulation of ossification
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of ossification, the formation of bone or of a bony substance or the conversion of fibrous tissue or of cartilage into bone or a bony substance.

label: cell activation
Defs: A change in the morphology or behavior of a cell resulting from exposure to an activating factor such as a cellular or soluble ligand.

label: presumptive paraxial mesoderm
Defs: The part of the blastula that has the potential to develop into a paraxial mesoderm.

label: carboxylic ester
Defs: An ester of a carboxylic acid, R(1)C(=O)OR(2), where R(1) = H or organyl and R(2) = organyl.

label: elliptic
Defs: A spheroid quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being oval with two axes of symmetry, as produced by a conical section.

label: regulation of intracellular transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of substances within cells.

label: mesoscutellum
Defs: The scutellum of the mesothorax.

label: cell proliferation involved in heart morphogenesis
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population that contributes to the shaping of the heart.

label: discrimenal lamella
Defs: The ridge that is in the sagittal line of the ventral part thorax.

label: carbon oxoanion
Defs: A negative ion consisting solely of carbon and oxygen  atoms, and therefore having the general formula CxOy(n-) for some integers x, y and n.

label: acetylcholine secretion, neurotransmission
Defs: The regulated release of acetylcholine by a cell. The acetylcholine acts as a neurotransmitter that acts in both the peripheral nervous system (PNS) and central nervous system (CNS).

label: pericardium morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structure of the pericardium is generated and organized.

label: increased diameter
Defs: A diameter which is relatively large.

label: locus ceruleus development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the locus ceruleus over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The locus ceruleus is a dense cluster of neurons within the dorsorostral pons. This nucleus is the major location of neurons that release norepinephrine throughout the brain, and is responsible for physiological responses to stress and panic.

label: supraorbital crest
Defs: The cuticular carina that is parallel to the medial margin of the eye

label: dark yellow brown
Defs: A color consisting of yellow and brown hue and low brightness.

label: regulation of branching morphogenesis of a nerve
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of branching morphogenesis of a nerve.

label: positive regulation of hepatocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the rate or extent of hepatocyte differentiation.

label: capillary blood
Defs: A blood that is part of a capillary.

label: neural cell adhesion molecule
Defs: A protein with a domain composition consisting of a large extracellular domain, including five Ig-like C2-type domains followed by two copies of the Fibronectin type-III domain (Pfam:PF00041), a single-pass transmembrane domain and a short cytoplasmic C-terminal domain.

label: dorsal region
Defs: Anatomical region dorsally located on the body or body part.

label: antero-medial region
Defs: Anatomical region that overlaps the anterior and medial regions of the body or body part.

label: electronegativity
Defs: A quality that describes the power of an atom to attract electrons to itself .

label: organismal quality
Defs: A quality that inheres in an entire organism or part of an organism.

label: clypeolabrum
Defs: The region of the cuticle that is composed of the clypeus and the labrum.

label: quiet
Defs: A sound amplitude which is relatively low.

label: adult organism
Defs: A multicellular organism that existence_ends_with a post-juvenile adult stage and existence_starts_with a post-juvenile adult stage.

label: photoreceptor array
Defs: An array of photoreceptors and any supporting cells found in an eye.

label: anatomical boundary
Defs: A non-material anatomical entity of two dimensions. Anatomical boundaries are contiguous structures.

label: regulation of adipose tissue development
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of adipose tissue development.

label: gut wall
Defs: The wall of the digestive tract. This encompasses all parts of the digestive tract with the exception of the lumen (cavity).

label: hydroxyindoles
Defs: Any member of the class of  indoles carrying at least one hydroxy group.

label: regulation of epithelial cell proliferation involved in lung morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of epithelial cell proliferation involved in lung morphogenesis.

label: mesenchyme from rhombencephalic neural crest
Defs: Mesenchyme that develops_from a rhombencephalon neural crest.

label: mislocalised ventrally
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being positioned towards the abdomen of an organism.

label: regulation of bone resorption
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of bone tissue loss (resorption).

label: extracellular amino acid transport
Defs: The directed extracellular movement of amino acids.

label: ventral spinal cord interneuron differentiation
Defs: The process in which neuroepithelial cells in the neural tube acquire specialized structural and/or functional features of ventral spinal cord interneurons. Ventral spinal cord interneurons are cells located in the ventral portion of the spinal cord that transmit signals between sensory and motor neurons and are required for reflexive responses. Differentiation includes the processes involved in commitment of a cell to a specific fate.

label: muscle fibroblast
Defs: Fibroblast from muscle organ.

label: negative regulation of colon smooth muscle contraction
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of colon smooth muscle contraction.

label: transitional myocyte of sinoatrial node
Defs: A transitional myocyte that is part of the sinoatrial node.

label: optic cup morphogenesis involved in camera-type eye development
Defs: The invagination of the optic vesicle to form two-walled indentations, the optic cups, that will go on to form the retina. This process begins with the optic vesicle becoming a two-walled structure and its subsequent shape changes. It does not include the fate commitment of cells to become the pigmented retina and the neural retina. An example of this process is found in Mus musculus.

label: epithelium of biliary system
Defs: The epithelial layer covering the biliary system. This includes the epithelium of the gallbladder (when present) as well as the intrahepatic and extrahepatic bile ducts.

label: small molecule binding
Defs: Binding to a small molecule, any low molecular weight, monomeric, non-encoded molecule.

label: CD48 antigen (mouse)
Defs: A CD48 molecule that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: normal distance
Defs: A distance which is relatively normal or average.

label: erythroid progenitor cell, mammalian
Defs: A progenitor cell committed to the erythroid lineage. This cell is ter119-positive but lacks expression of other hematopoietic lineage markers (lin-negative).

label: midbrain-hindbrain boundary morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structure of the midbrain-hindbrain boundary is generated and organized. The midbrain-hindbrain domain of the embryonic brain is comprised of the mesencephalic vesicle and the first rhombencephalic vesicle at early somitogenesis stages. An organizing center at the boundary patterns the midbrain and hindbrain primordia of the neural plate.

label: regulation of generation of precursor metabolites and energy
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of precursor metabolites, substances from which energy is derived, and the processes involved in the liberation of energy from these substances.

label: evergreen (plant)
Defs: A quality inhering in a plant by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to retain foliage.

label: regulation of cardiac chamber formation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac chamber formation.

label: non-magnetic
Defs: A magnetic quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s inability to exert magnitism.

label: blood island
Defs: Blood islands are structures in the developing embryo which lead to many different parts of the circulatory system. They primarily derive from plexuses formed from angioblasts. Within them, vacuoles appear through liquefaction of the central part of the syncytium into plasma. The lumen of the blood vessels thus formed is probably intracellular. The flattened cells at the periphery form the endothelium. The nucleated red blood corpuscles develop either from small masses of the original angioblast left attached to the inner wall of the lumen or directly from the flat endothelial cells. In either case the syncytial mass thus formed projects from and is attached to the wall of the vessel. Such a mass is known as a blood island and hemoglobin gradually accumulates within it. Later the cells on the surface round up, giving the mass a mulberry-like appearance. Then the red blood cells break loose and are carried away in the plasma. Such free blood cells continue to divide. Blood islands have been seen in the area vasculosa in the omphalomesenteric vein and arteries, and in the dorsal aorta[WP, unvetted].

label: regulation of nucleobase-containing compound metabolic process
Defs: Any cellular process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving nucleobases, nucleosides, nucleotides and nucleic acids.

label: loose
Defs: A pattern quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s not being compact or dense in arrangement.

label: negative regulation of secretion by cell
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of secretion by cell.

label: regulation of keratinocyte proliferation
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of keratinocyte proliferation. Keratinocyte proliferation is the multiplication or reproduction of keratinocytes, resulting in the expansion of a cell population.

label: myelin sheath
Defs: An electrically insulating fatty layer that surrounds the axons of many neurons. It is an outgrowth of glial cells: Schwann cells supply the myelin for peripheral neurons while oligodendrocytes supply it to those of the central nervous system.

label: ventrolaterally orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed ventrolaterally.

label: anatomical structure
Defs: Material anatomical entity that is a single connected structure with inherent 3D shape generated by coordinated expression of the organism\'s own genome.

label: superior olivary nucleus formation
Defs: The process that gives rise to the superior olivary nucleus. This process pertains to the initial formation of a structure from unspecified parts. In mice, the superior olivary nucleus is a small cylindrical mass on the dorsal surface of the lateral part of the trapezoid body of the pons, and it is situated immediately above the inferior olivary nucleus. It receives projections from the cochlear nucleus and thus is involved in the perception of sound.

label: germ-line stem cell division
Defs: The self-renewing division of a germline stem cell to produce a daughter stem cell and a daughter germ cell, which will divide to form the gametes.

label: Martinotti morphology
Defs: A cell morphology that inheres in neurons which are large and non-spiny, with dendrites radiating in a multipolar or bitufted pattern, often favouring the descending side, and axons that ascend directly from the superficial side of the soma, and travel upward without branching.

label: external carotid artery
Defs: A terminal branch of the left or right common carotid artery which supplies oxygenated blood to to the throat, neck glands, tongue, face, mouth, ear, scalp and dura mater of the meninges[MP].

label: squamous epithelium
Defs: An epithelium characterised by its most superficial layer consisting of squamous epithelial cells.

label: cell part morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which the anatomical structures of a cell part are generated and organized.

label: cuticle of tibia
Defs: The cuticle of the segment of a leg attached to the distal margin of the femur by the femoro-tibial conjunctiva and to the proximal margin of the tarsus by the tibio-tarsal conjunctiva.

label: abdominal tergite IV-abdominal tergite V conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect abdomen that connects the abdominal tergite IV and the abdominal tergite V.

label: NF-kappaB binding
Defs: Binding to NF-kappaB, a transcription factor for eukaryotic RNA polymerase II promoters.

label: positive regulation of mesodermal cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of mesodermal cell differentiation.

label: positive regulation of compound eye retinal cell programmed cell death
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of programmed cell death that occurs in the compound eye retina.

label: peripheral
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being at the edge or boundary of a related entity.

label: cardiac muscle tissue of interatrial septum
Defs: A portion of cardiac muscle tissue that is part of a interatrial septum [Automatically generated definition].

label: transferrin receptor protein 1
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human TFRC gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: teardrop-shaped
Defs: A convex 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s shape resembling falling drop.

label: amino acid
Defs: A carboxylic acid containing one or more amino groups.

label: axial mesoderm development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the axial mesoderm over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The axial mesoderm includes the prechordal mesoderm and the chordamesoderm. It gives rise to the prechordal plate and to the notochord.

label: cuticle of prothorax
Defs: The region of the cuticle of the insect thorax that is anteriorly connected to the head by the neck membrane, posteriorly connected to the mesothorax by the prothorax-mesothorax conjunctiva, and contains the pronotum, the propeluron, the prosternum and one pair of legs.

label: segmental subdivision of hindbrain
Defs: An organ subunit that is part of a hindbrain [Automatically generated definition].

label: regulation of ion transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Any process that modulates the activity of an ion transporter.

label: jaw mesenchyme
Defs: Mesenchyme that is part of a developing jaw [Automatically generated definition].

label: positive regulation of cell cycle
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the rate or extent of progression through the cell cycle.

label: exocrine pancreas
Defs: The part of the pancreas that is part of the exocrine system and which produces and store zymogens of digestive enzymes, such as chymotrypsinogen and trypsinogen in the acinar cells [GO].

label: polyphasic
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having or existing in many phases.

label: catalyst
Defs: A substance that increases the rate of a reaction without modifying the overall standard Gibbs energy change in the reaction.

label: indifference
Defs: A preference quality in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having no preference to a perceived stimulus.

label: regulation of endothelial cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of endothelial cell proliferation.

label: myeloid suppressor cell
Defs: An immature myeloid leukocyte of heterogeneous phenotype found particularly in cancer and sepsis patients that is capable of suppressing activity of T cells in ex vivo assays. This cell type is CD45-positive, CD11b-positive.

label: hematopoietic stem cell
Defs: A stem cell from which all cells of the lymphoid and myeloid lineages develop, including blood cells and cells of the immune system. Hematopoietic stem cells lack cell markers of effector cells (lin-negative). Lin-negative is defined by lacking one or more of the following cell surface markers: CD2, CD3 epsilon, CD4, CD5 ,CD8 alpha chain, CD11b, CD14, CD19, CD20, CD56, ly6G, ter119.

label: colon epithelial cell
Defs: Epithelial cell that is part of the colon epithelium.

label: anion transmembrane transport
Defs: The process in which an anion is transported across a membrane.

label: immune system development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an organismal system whose objective is to provide calibrated responses by an organism to a potential internal or invasive threat, over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A system is a regularly interacting or interdependent group of organs or tissues that work together to carry out a given biological process.

label: acetylcholine binding
Defs: Binding to acetylcholine, an acetic acid ester of the organic base choline that functions as a neurotransmitter, released at the synapses of parasympathetic nerves and at neuromuscular junctions.

label: prevention of polyspermy
Defs: The negative regulation of fertilization process that takes place as part of egg activation, ensuring that only a single sperm fertilizes the egg.

label: respiratory system fluid/secretion
Defs: A portion of organism substance that secreted_by a respiratory system.

label: transitional myocyte of interatrial septum
Defs: A transitional myocyte that is part of the interatrial septum.

label: transition metal ion binding
Defs: Binding to a transition metal ions; a transition metal is an element whose atom has an incomplete d-subshell of extranuclear electrons, or which gives rise to a cation or cations with an incomplete d-subshell. Transition metals often have more than one valency state. Biologically relevant transition metals include vanadium, manganese, iron, copper, cobalt, nickel, molybdenum and silver.

label: mandibular process mesenchyme from neural crest
Defs: Mesenchyme that develops_from a neural crest and is part of a mandibular process mesenchyme.

label: discrimen
Defs: The longitudinal (parallel to antero-posterior axis) sulcus that corresponds to the discrimenal lamella.

label: neuron death
Defs: The process of cell death in a neuron.

label: submentomental muscle
Defs: The cranio-labial muscle that is attached to the submentum and the mentum.

label: regulation of muscle cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of muscle cell differentiation.

label: lateralized
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being moved or displaced to one side so as to make lateral.

label: anal region
Defs: The anus and surrounding regions. Encompasses both internal and external regions, where present.

label: bona-fide anatomical boundary
Defs: An anatomical boundary that corresponds to some physical discontinuity.

label: positive regulation of vesicle transport along microtubule
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of vesicle transport along microtubule.

label: hindbrain neural plate
Defs: A neural plate that develops_from a presumptive hindbrain.

label: gestational hematopoietic stem cell
Defs: A hematopoietic stem cell that exists during embryogenesis.

label: ganglion development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a ganglion over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

label: regulation of macrophage apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of macrophage apoptotic process.

label: saturated purple
Defs: A color consisting of purple color and high saturation.

label: osteoclast maturation
Defs: A developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for an osteoclast cell to attain its fully functional state. An osteoclast is a specialized phagocytic cell associated with the absorption and removal of the mineralized matrix of bone tissue, and which typically differentiates from monocytes.

label: myelin assembly
Defs: The process in which the wraps of cell membrane that constitute myelin are laid down around an axon in the central or peripheral nervous system.

label: regulation of dopamine biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of dopamine biosynthetic process.

label: dysplastic growth
Defs: A growth quality of occurrent in which the growth of an organism, structure or group of organisms is abnormal.

label: cuticle of appendage segment
Defs: The ring sclerite that is part of an appendage and is attached to muscle.

label: increased virulence
Defs: A virulence that is relatively high.

label: catechols
Defs: Any compound containing an o-diphenol component.

label: regulation of sodium ion transmembrane transporter activity
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of sodium ion transmembrane transporter activity.

label: cuticle of metatarsus
Defs: The cuticle of the segment of the leg that is composed of metatarsomeres connected to each other by intertarsomeral conjunctiva. The first metatarsomere is connected to the distal margin of the metatibia by the metatibio-metatarsal conjunctiva and the last metatarsomere is connected to the proximal margin of the metapretarsus by the metatarso-metapretarsal conjunctiva.

label: momentum
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s velocity multiplied by its mass.

label: leukocyte mediated immunity
Defs: Any process involved in the carrying out of an immune response by a leukocyte.

label: regulation of cell-cell adhesion
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of attachment of a cell to another cell.

label: life cycle stage
Defs: A spatiotemporal region encompassing some part of the life cycle of an organism.

label: respiratory system gland
Defs: Any gland that is part os the respiratory system.

label: circulatory system
Defs: Organ system that passes nutrients (such as amino acids and electrolytes), gases, hormones, blood cells, etc. to and from cells in the body to help fight diseases and help stabilize body temperature and pH to maintain homeostasis[WP].

label: variant color
Defs: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having or exhibiting variation of colour.

label: muscle tissue
Defs: Muscle tissue is a contractile tissue made up of actin and myosin fibers[GO].

label: telescopic
Defs: Having or resembling the shape of a telescope.

label: vesicle fusion with Golgi apparatus
Defs: The joining of the lipid bilayer membrane around a vesicle to the lipid bilayer membrane around the Golgi.

label: nucleus organization
Defs: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of the nucleus.

label: spinal cord oligodendrocyte
Defs: Any oligodendrocyte that is part of a spinal cord.

label: negative regulation of cell death
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate or frequency of cell death. Cell death is the specific activation or halting of processes within a cell so that its vital functions markedly cease, rather than simply deteriorating gradually over time, which culminates in cell death.

label: regulation of striated muscle cell apoptotic process
Defs: Any process that modulates the rate or extent of striated muscle cell apoptotic process, a form of programmed cell death induced by external or internal signals that trigger the activity of proteolytic caspases whose actions dismantle a striated muscle cell and result in its death.

label: excretory tube
Defs: A tube that is part of a excretory system.

label: positive regulation of granulocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of granulocyte differentiation.

label: replacement bone morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which bones are generated and organized as a result of the conversion of another structural tissue into bone.

label: plasma membrane fusion
Defs: The joining of the lipid bilayer membrane that surround a cell with that of another cell, producing a single cell.

label: catalytic complex
Defs: A protein complex which is capable of catalytic activity.

label: T cell of anorectum
Defs: A T cell that is located in the anorectum.

label: dermal bone
Defs: Skeletal element that forms superficially in the organism, usually in association with the ectoderm[VSAO].

label: left lung
Defs: Lung which consists of the left upper lobe and left lower lobe.[FMA].

label: normal area
Defs: An area which is relatively normal or average

label: cardiac neuron differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a neuron of the heart.

label: regulation of cardiac muscle contraction
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle contraction.

label: epithelial tube branching involved in lung morphogenesis
Defs: The process in which a highly ordered sequence of patterning events generates the branched epithelial tubes of the lung, consisting of reiterated combinations of bud outgrowth, elongation, and dichotomous subdivision of terminal units.

label: decreased volume
Defs: A volume which is relatively low.

label: eroding
Defs: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer bring gradually worn away.

label: weight
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer that has mass near a gravitational body. Important usage note: Note that this ontology has a class for a similar concept, mass (PATO:0000125). Mass and weight are not equivalent. For most use cases, the class mass is strongly preferred over weight.

label: MHC class II protein complex
Defs: A transmembrane protein complex composed of an MHC class II alpha and MHC class II beta chain, and with or without a bound peptide or polysaccharide antigen.

label: cardiac right atrium formation
Defs: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of a cardiac right atrium from unspecified parts.

label: positive regulation of erythrocyte differentiation
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of erythrocyte differentiation.

label: positive regulation of cell proliferation involved in outflow tract morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cell proliferation involved in outflow tract morphogenesis.

label: mesofemoral muscle
Defs: The somatic muscle that inserts in the mesofemur.

label: lot number
Defs: A lot number is an information content entity which is an identical sequence of character borne by part of manufactured product or its packaging for each instances of a product class in a discrete batch of an item. Lot numbers are usually assigned to each separate production run of an item. Manufacturing as a lot might be due to a variety of reasons, for example,  a single process during which many individuals are made from the same portion of source material. Lot numbers can be encoded in a pattern  of other information objects, such as bar codes, numerals, or patterns of dots.

label: cellular response to norepinephrine stimulus
Defs: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a norepinephrine stimulus. Norepinephrine is a catecholamine that has the formula C8H11NO3; it acts as a hormone, and as a neurotransmitter in most of the sympathetic nervous system.

label: positive regulation of osteoclast development
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of osteoclast development.

label: Kit-positive, CD34-negative megakaryocyte erythroid progenitor cell
Defs: A megakaryocyte erythroid progenitor cell that is Kit-positive and is Sca1-negative, CD34-negative, CD90-negative, IL7r-alpha-negative and Fcgr II/III-low.

label: mesenchymal cell differentiation involved in bone development
Defs: The process in which relatively unspecialized cells acquire specialized structural and/or functional features that characterize the mesenchymal cells of bone as it progresses from its formation to the mature state.

label: scleral mesenchyme
Defs: Mesenchyme surrounding the developing optic cup which develops into the sclera.

label: stomach neuroendocrine cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a neuroendocrine cell of the stomach epithelium.

label: primordium
Defs: Primordia are populations of contiguous cells that are morphologically distinct and already correspond in extent to a later organ/tissue[FBbt, Hartenstein, V. (2004)].

label: glandular epithelial cell
Defs: A specialized epithelial cell that is capable of synthesizing and secreting certain biomolecules.

label: negative regulation of transmission of nerve impulse
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of transmission of a nerve impulse, the sequential electrochemical polarization and depolarization that travels across the membrane of a neuron in response to stimulation.

label: capillary of small intestine
Defs: A capillary that is part of a small intestine.

label: reniform nucleus
Defs: A concave nucleus shape where the indentation is smaller than half of the distance to the farthest nuclear margin.

label: frozen
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being kept below its freezing point.

label: camera-type eye development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the camera-type eye over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The camera-type eye is an organ of sight that receives light through an aperture and focuses it through a lens, projecting it on a photoreceptor field.

label: cuticle of labial palpus
Defs: The cuticle of the paired appendage of the labium that is attached to the palpiger by the palpigero-palpal conjunctiva.

label: vena cava
Defs: Any of the veins that carries deoxygenated blood from a part of the body into the right atrium of the heart.

label: cilium or flagellum-dependent cell motility
Defs: Cell motility due to movement of eukaryotic cilia or bacterial-type flagella or archaeal-type flagella.

label: head somite
Defs: Somite located in the head region, caudal to the otic vesicle.

label: G protein-coupled amine receptor activity
Defs: Combining with an extracellular amine and transmitting the signal across the membrane by activating an associated G-protein; promotes the exchange of GDP for GTP on the alpha subunit of a heterotrimeric G-protein complex.

label: synchondrosis
Defs: Cartilaginous joint in which the articulating bones or cartilages are connected by hyaline cartilage. Examples: spheno-occipital synchondrosis, first sternocostal joint.[FMA].

label: notosternal sulcus
Defs: The sulcus separating the lateral region of the notum and the lateral region of the sternum.

label: acetylcholine receptor inhibitor activity
Defs: Binds to and stops, prevents or reduces the activity of an acetylcholine receptor.

label: T cell migration
Defs: The movement of a T cell within or between different tissues and organs of the body.

label: variability of count
Defs: A variability quality inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer having a variable number or count of an entity.

label: regulation of signal transduction
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of signal transduction.

label: mesothelial cell of peritoneum
Defs: A mesothelial cell that is part of the peritoneum.

label: herniated
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s bodily structure that has protruded through an abnormal opening in the wall that contains it.

label: ectoderm of buccopharyngeal membrane
Defs: An ectoderm that is part of a buccopharyngeal membrane.

label: negative regulation of branching involved in lung morphogenesis
Defs: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the process in which a highly ordered sequence of patterning events generates the branched structures of the lung, consisting of reiterated combinations of bud outgrowth, elongation, and dichotomous subdivision of terminal units.

label: pinnate
Defs: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having leaflets or leaflets-like structures on each side of a common axis.

label: cellular iron ion homeostasis
Defs: Any process involved in the maintenance of an internal steady state of iron ions at the level of a cell.

label: negative regulation of acinar cell proliferation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of acinar cell proliferation.

label: camera-type eye
Defs: An organ of sight that includes the camera-type eyeball and supporting structures such as the lacrimal apparatus, the conjunctiva, the eyelid.

label: appendage girdle complex
