Defs: An organism subdivision that includes both an appendage and its associated girdle region. Note that this includes both the skeletal elements and associated tissues (integument, muscle, etc).

label: negative regulation of organ growth
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of growth of an organ of an organism.

label: musculature of back
Defs: Any collection of muscles that is part of a back [Automatically generated definition].

label: clypealia
Defs: The region of the cuticle corresponding to the postero-lateral region of the postclypeus

label: fluid-filled
Defs: Bounded structure filled with fluid.

label: negative regulation of forebrain neuron differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of forebrain neuron differentiation.

label: lung parenchyma
Defs: A parenchyma that is part of a lung.

label: liver development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the liver over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The liver is an exocrine gland which secretes bile and functions in metabolism of protein and carbohydrate and fat, synthesizes substances involved in the clotting of the blood, synthesizes vitamin A, detoxifies poisonous substances, stores glycogen, and breaks down worn-out erythrocytes.

label: cell cluster
Defs: A cluster of cells, largely surrounded by a morphological boundary.

label: endocrine hormone secretion
Defs: The regulated release of a hormone into the circulatory system.

label: syncytiotrophoblast cell
Defs: A cell from the outer syncytial layer of the trophoblast of an early mammalian embryo, directly associated with the maternal blood supply. It secretes hCG in order to maintain progesterone secretion and sustain a pregnancy.

label: protein tyrosine kinase inhibitor activity
Defs: Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a protein tyrosine kinase.

label: heart growth
Defs: The increase in size or mass of the heart.

label: distal orientation
Defs: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed distally.

label: organelle outer membrane
Defs: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing in a cellular organelle, lipid bilayer of an organelle envelope.

label: lymphoid lineage restricted progenitor cell
Defs: A progenitor cell restricted to the lymphoid lineage.

label: RNA catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of RNA, ribonucleic acid, one of the two main type of nucleic acid, consisting of a long, unbranched macromolecule formed from ribonucleotides joined in 3\',5\'-phosphodiester linkage.

label: interleukin-7 receptor subunit alpha
Defs: A protein that is a translation product of the human IL7R gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label: gas transport
Defs: The directed movement of substances that are gaseous in normal living conditions into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: premento-glossal muscle
Defs: The cranio-labial muscle that is attached to the prementum and the glossa.

label: uterine epithelium
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a uterus.

label: male pseudohermaphrodite
Defs: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population by virtue of having internal reproductive organs of male and external sexual characteristics of female.

label: susceptible toward
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having susceptibilty toward an external stimulus.

label: Bronsted acid
Defs: A molecular entity capable of donating a hydron to an acceptor (Bronsted base).

label: indolalkylamine metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving indolalkylamines, indole or indole derivatives containing a primary, secondary, or tertiary amine group.

label: cerebral hemisphere gray matter
Defs: A gray matter that is part of a cerebral hemisphere.

label: texture
Defs: A morphologic quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s relative size, organization and distribution of its surface elements or the representation or invention of the appearance of its surface; visual and tactile surface characteristics.

label: dermis
Defs: The dermis is a layer of skin between the epidermis (with which it makes up the skin) and subcutaneous tissues, and is composed of two layers, the papillary and reticular dermis[WP].

label: negative regulation of cellular metabolic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways by which individual cells transform chemical substances.

label: skeletal muscle fiber development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the skeletal muscle fiber over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Muscle fibers are formed by the maturation of myotubes. They can be classed as slow, intermediate/fast or fast.

label: exocytic vesicle
Defs: A transport vesicle that mediates transport from an intracellular compartment to the plasma membrane, and fuses with the plasma membrane to release various cargo molecules, such as proteins or hormones, by exocytosis.

label: cranio-antennal conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva that encircles the base of the antenna (scape) and is encircled by the head capsule as the antennal foramen.

label: pathological
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being abnormal and having a destructive effect on living tissue.

label: columnar/cuboidal epithelial cell maturation
Defs: The developmental process, independent of morphogenetic (shape) change, that is required for a columna/cuboidal epithelial cell to attain its fully functional state. A columnar/cuboidal epithelial cell is a cell usually found in a two dimensional sheet with a free surface. Columnar/cuboidal epithelial cells take on the shape of a column or cube.

label: neural rod formation
Defs: The formation of a solid rod of neurectoderm derived from the neural keel. The neural rod is roughly circular in cross section. Neural rod formation occurs during primary neurulation in teleosts.

label: cranial cartilage
Defs: A cartilage element that is part of the cranial skeleton.

label: cuticle of metacoxa
Defs: The cuticle of the segment of the hind leg that is attached to the latero-ventral region of the metathorax by the basal metacoxal conjunctiva and to the metatrochanter by the metacoxal-metatrochanteral conjunctiva.

label: positive regulation of response to acetate
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of response to acetate.

label: interstitial cell of Cajal
Defs: This is a cell found in the gastrointestinal tract of mammals and serves as a pacemaker that triggers gut contraction. ICCs mediate inputs from the enteric nervous system to smooth muscle cells and are thought to be the cells from which gastrointestinal stromal tumors (GISTs) arise.

label: regulation of transport
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed movement of substances (such as macromolecules, small molecules, ions) into, out of or within a cell, or between cells, by means of some agent such as a transporter or pore.

label: negative regulation of syncytium formation by plasma membrane fusion
Defs: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of the formation of a syncytium, a mass of cytoplasm containing several nuclei enclosed within a single plasma membrane, by the fusion of the plasma membranes of two or more individual cells.

label: myeloid leukocyte migration
Defs: The movement of a myeloid leukocyte within or between different tissues and organs of the body.

label: hyoid apparatus
Defs: A group of bones comprised of hyoid body and two pairs of cornua (i.e. greater cornua and lesser cornua), and lies just below the tongue, above the thyroid cartilage.

label: strength
Defs: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s power or force.

label: cleavage stage
Defs: The first few specialized divisions of an activated animal egg; Stage consisting of division of cells in the early embryo. The zygotes of many species undergo rapid cell cycles with no significant growth, producing a cluster of cells the same size as the original zygote. The different cells derived from cleavage are called blastomeres and form a compact mass called the morula. Cleavage ends with the formation of the blastula.

label: neural keel
Defs: An intermediate stage (between the neural plate and neural rod) during the early segmentation period in the morphogenesis of the central nervous system primordium; the keel is roughly triangular shaped in cross section.

label: duct
Defs: A tubular structure that transports secreted or excreted substances.

label: secretion by tissue
Defs: The controlled release of a substance by a tissue.

label: epithelial cell of large intestine
Defs: An epithelial cell of the large intestine.

label: gastrointestinal system epithelium
Defs: An epithelium that is part of a digestive system [Automatically generated definition].

label: positive regulation of steroid hormone secretion
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of steroid hormone secretion.

label: 3-D shape
Defs: A shape that inheres in a 3 dimensional entity.

label: endometrium
Defs: The glandular mucous membrane lining of the uterine cavity that is hormonally responsive during the estrous/menstrual cycle and during pregnancy.

label: ossified
Defs: A composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being hardened by the deposition of calcium into bone.

label: programmed cell death
Defs: A process which begins when a cell receives an internal or external signal and activates a series of biochemical events (signaling pathway). The process ends with the death of the cell.

label: protein
Defs: An amino acid chain that is produced de novo by ribosome-mediated translation of a genetically-encoded mRNA, and any derivatives thereof.

label: positive regulation of glutamate receptor signaling pathway
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of glutamate receptor signaling pathway.

label: negative regulation of biosynthetic process
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the rate of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of substances.

label: increased contractility
Defs: A contractility which is relatively high.

label: abdominal tergite III-abdominal tergite IV conjunctiva
Defs: The conjunctiva of the insect abdomen that connects the abdominal tergite III and the abdominal tergite IV.

label: positive regulation of phagocytosis
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of phagocytosis.

label: respiratory system venous endothelium
Defs: An endothelium of vein that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

label: epithelial cell of skin gland
Defs: An epithelial cell of a skin gland.

label: positive regulation of formation of translation initiation ternary complex
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of formation of translation initiation ternary complex.

label: vascular system
Defs: Anatomical system that consists of all blood and lymph vessels.

label: pigment cell differentiation
Defs: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized features of a pigmented cell, such as a melanocyte.

label: increased stability
Defs: An increase in stability.

label: inverted pyramidal morphology
Defs: A pyramidal cell morphology that inheres in neurons which have an apical tree which is oriented towards the white matter.

label: obsolete surface shape
Defs: A shape that inheres in a part of a surface. An object can have different surface shapes on different parts of its surface.

label: protibial muscle
Defs: The somatic muscle that inserts in the protibia.

label: cardiac muscle of left ventricle
Defs: A portion of cardiac muscle tissue that is part of a left ventricle [Automatically generated definition].

label: positive regulation of serotonin secretion
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the regulated release of serotonin.

label: electric polarizability
Defs: The ease of distortion of the electron cloud of a molecular entity by an electric field.

label: respiratory system smooth muscle
Defs: A portion of smooth muscle tissue that is part of a respiratory system [Automatically generated definition].

label: cardiovascular drug
Defs: A drug that affects the rate or intensity of cardiac contraction, blood vessel diameter or blood volume.

label: fasciculus of brain
Defs: A fascicle that is part of a brain.

label: abdominal aorta
Defs: Abdominal part of aorta: the distal part of the descending aorta, which is the continuation of the thoracic part and gives rise to the inferior phrenic, lumbar, median sacral, superior and inferior mesenteric, middle suprarenal, renal, and testicular or ovarian arteries, and celiac trunk[BTO]. The abdominal aorta is the largest artery in the abdominal cavity. As part of the aorta, it is a direct continuation of descending aorta(of the thorax). [WP,unvetted].

label: pharyngeal arch mesenchyme from head mesenchyme
Defs: Mesenchyme that develops_from a head mesenchyme from mesoderm and is part of a entire pharyngeal arch associated mesenchyme.

label: organic heterobicyclic ring
Defs: A bicyclic organic group that contains both carbon and hetero atoms.

label: bronchial artery
Defs: A systemic artery that supplies the lung with with oxygenated blood.

label: saturated green
Defs: A color consisting of green hue and high saturation.

label: positive regulation of protein localization to ciliary membrane
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to ciliary membrane.

label: inner cell mass cell proliferation
Defs: The proliferation of cells in the inner cell mass.

label: regulation of epithelial tube formation
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of epithelial tube formation.

label: positive regulation of protein depolymerization
Defs: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein depolymerization.

label: regulation of vacuole organization
Defs: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a vacuole.

label: active
Defs: A quality of an physical object that is currently realizing one of its functions.

label: digestive tract development
Defs: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the digestive tract over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The digestive tract is the anatomical structure through which food passes and is processed.

label: solubility
Defs: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to dissolve in a liquid.

label: exocytic vesicle membrane
Defs: The lipid bilayer surrounding an exocytic vesicle.

label: cardiac chamber formation
Defs: The developmental process pertaining to the initial formation of a cardiac chamber from unspecified parts. A cardiac chamber is an enclosed cavity within the heart.

label: colon smooth muscle contraction
Defs: A process in which force is generated within smooth muscle tissue, resulting in a change in muscle geometry of the large intestine, exclusive of the rectum. The colon is that part of the large intestine that connects the small intestine to the rectum.

label: ribonucleoprotein complex biogenesis
Defs: A cellular process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, and arrangement of constituent parts of a complex containing RNA and proteins. Includes the biosynthesis of the constituent RNA and protein molecules, and those macromolecular modifications that are involved in synthesis or assembly of the ribonucleoprotein complex.

label: author list
Defs: A part of a document that enumerates the authors of the document

label: submucosa of pylorus
Defs: A submucosa that is part of a pylorus [Automatically generated definition].

label: serotonin receptor complex
Defs: A protein complex that is capable of serotonin receptor activity.

label: tetrapyrrole biosynthetic process from glutamate
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways leading to the formation of tetrapyrroles, natural pigments containing four pyrrole rings joined by one-carbon units linking position 2 of one pyrrole ring to position 5 of the next, from other compounds, including L-glutamate.

label: cuticular lobe
Defs: The cuticular evagination that is largely membranous.

label: alpha-amino acid biosynthetic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of an alpha-amino acid.

label: future myelencephalon
Defs: A developing anatomical structure that has the potential to develop into a myelencephalon.

label: atypical epithelium
Defs: Epithelium that consists of epithelial cells not arranged in one ore more layers.

label: neck bone
Defs: A bone that is part of a neck [Automatically generated definition].

label: protein catabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of a protein by the destruction of the native, active configuration, with or without the hydrolysis of peptide bonds.

label: internal angle
Defs: A convex angle that is inside two adjacent sides of a polygon.

label: common lymphoid progenitor
Defs: A oligopotent progenitor cell committed to the lymphoid lineage.

label: hydrophilicity
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue the bearer\'s disposition to having an affinity for water; it is readily absorbing or dissolving in water.

label: negative regulation of actin filament bundle assembly
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the assembly of actin filament bundles.

label: cell adhesion molecule binding
Defs: Binding to a cell adhesion molecule.

label: extracellular non-membrane-bounded organelle
Defs: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function, not bounded by a lipid bilayer membrane and occurring outside the cell.

label: cellular ketone metabolic process
Defs: The chemical reactions and pathways involving any of a class of organic compounds that contain the carbonyl group, CO, and in which the carbonyl group is bonded only to carbon atoms, as carried out by individual cells. The general formula for a ketone is RCOR, where R and R are alkyl or aryl groups.

label: partially anterioralized
Defs: An anterioralized quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s gross morphology containing what are normally anterior structures and missing some but not all of what are normally posterior structures.

label: cell motility
Defs: Any process involved in the controlled self-propelled movement of a cell that results in translocation of the cell from one place to another.

label: striated border microvillus layer
Defs: A microvillus layer that is striated and found in the intestine.

label: brain blood vessel
Defs: A blood vessel that is part of a brain [Automatically generated definition].

label: osteoclast
Defs: A specialized phagocytic cell associated with the absorption and removal of the mineralized matrix of bone tissue, which typically differentiates from monocytes. This cell has the following markers: tartrate-resistant acid phosphatase type 5-positive, PU.1-positive, c-fos-positive, nuclear factor NF-kappa-B p100 subunit-positive, tumor necrosis factor receptor superfamily member 11A-positive and macrophage colony-stimulating factor 1 receptor-positive.

label: increased efficiency
Defs: An efficiency which is relatively high.

label: dendritic
Defs: A branched quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s having smaller branches arising from larger branches. Resembling a tree in branching structure.

label: tentorio-antennal muscle
Defs: The insect cranial muscle that is attached to the tentorium and to the antenna.

label: integrin alpha lacking A domain
Defs: An integrin alpha that lacks an A domain. This type of integrin is often cleaved into heavy and light chains.

label: negative regulation of skeletal muscle cell differentiation
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of skeletal muscle cell differentiation.

label: bronchial lumen
Defs: An anatomical cavity that is part of a bronchus.

label: normal variability of size
Defs: A variability of size which is relatively normal or average

label: thermoplastic
Defs: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s disposition to deform by heating.

label: epidermis gland
Defs: A gland that is part of a epidermis.

label: physiological state
Defs: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the state of bearer\'s mechanical, physical, and biochemical processes.

label: respiration organ
Defs: Organ that functions in gaseous exchange between an organism and its environment. In plants, microorganisms, and many small animals, air or water makes direct contact with the organism\'s cells or tissue fluids, and the processes of diffusion supply the organism with dioxygen (O2) and remove carbon dioxide (CO2). In larger animals the efficiency of gaseous exchange is improved by specialized respiratory organs, such as lungs and gills, which are ventilated by breathing mechanisms.

label: monoamine molecular messenger
Defs: A group of neurotransmitters and neuromodulators that contain one amino group that is connected to an aromatic ring by ethylene group  (-CH2-CH2-). Monoamines are derived from the aromatic amino acids phenylalanine, tyrosine, histidine and tryptophan.

label: carboxylic acid
Defs: A carbon oxoacid acid carrying at least one -C(=O)OH group and having the structure RC(=O)OH, where R is any any monovalent functional group. Carboxylic acids are the most common type of organic acid.

label: telencephalon oligodendrocyte cell migration
Defs: The multiplication or reproduction of telencephalon oligodendrocyte cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population.

label: presynaptic signal transduction
Defs: Signal transduction in which the initial step occurs in a presynapse.

label: negative regulation of protein localization to nucleus
Defs: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein localization to nucleus.

label: paired limb/fin cartilage
Defs: A cartilage tissue that is part of a paired limb or fin.

label: transferrin receptor protein 1 (mouse)
Defs: A transferrin receptor protein 1 that is encoded in the genome of mouse.

label: decreased functionality
Defs: A functionality quality held by the bearer when the latter exhibits decreased ability to perform a regular function(s).

label: cardiac muscle cell apoptotic process
Defs: A form of programmed cell death induced by external or internal signals that trigger the activity of proteolytic caspases, whose actions dismantle a cardiac muscle cell and result in its death. Cardiac muscle cells are striated muscle cells that are responsible for heart contraction.

label: mislocalized abaxially
Defs: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer\'s being positioned away from the axis of an organism.

label: has increased age-specific mortality rate
Defs: Then percentage of organisms in a population that die during some specified age range (age-specific mortality rate), minus the percentage that die in during the same age range in a wild-type population.

label: ipsilateral to
Defs: On the same side as. For example, the left arm is ipsilateral to the left leg.

label: disease has basis in feature
Defs: A relation that holds between the disease and a feature (a phenotype or other disease) where the physical basis of the disease is the feature.

label: immediately distal to
Defs: x immediately distal to y iff x distal to y and x is contiguous with y.

label: parallel to
Defs: x is parallel t y iff x and y are lines or planes which when extended indefinitely do not cross.

label: is start sequence of
Defs: inverse of has start sequence

label: is causal somatic mutation in
Defs: Relates a gene to condition, such that a mutation in this gene is sufficient to produce the condition but that cannot be passed on to offspring[modified from orphanet].

label: has synaptic IO throughout
Defs: A relationship between a neuron and a region, where the neuron has a functionally relevant number of input and/or output synapses distributed throughout that region (rather than confined to a subregion).

label: produces
Defs: a produces b if some process that occurs_in a has_output b, where a and b are material entities. Examples: hybridoma cell line produces monoclonal antibody reagent; chondroblast produces avascular GAG-rich matrix.

label: main stem of
Defs: x main_stem_of y if y is a branching structure and x is a channel that traces a linear path through y, such that x has higher capacity than any other such path.

label: in right side of
Defs: X in right side of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two left and right portions, X is part of the right portion.

label: derives into
Defs: a relation between two distinct material entities, the old entity and the new entity, in which the new entity begins to exist when the old entity ceases to exist, and the new entity inherits the significant portion of the matter of the old entity

label: proximally connected to
Defs: x proximally_connected_to y iff the proximal part of x is connected to y. i.e. x connected_to y and x distal_to y.

label: directly positively regulates activity of
Defs:
The entity A, immediately upstream of the entity B, has an activity that positively regulates an activity performed by B. 
For example, A and B may be gene products and binding of B by A positively regulates the kinase activity of B.

label: in pseudoparalogy relationship with
Defs: Xenology that involves genes that ended up in a given genome as a result of a combination of vertical inheritance and horizontal gene transfer.

label: in orthology relationship with
Defs: Historical homology that involves genes that diverged after a speciation event.

label: contributes to severity of condition
Defs: A relationship between an entity (e.g. a genotype, genetic variation, chemical, or environmental exposure) and a condition (a phenotype or disease), where the entity influences the severity with which a condition manifests in an individual.

label: in homotopy relationship with
Defs: Structural homology that involves structures with the same or similar relative positions.

label: has eggs laid on by
Defs: inverse of lays eggs on

label: has_specified_output
Defs: A relation between a planned process and a continuant participating in that process. The presence of the continuant at the end of the process is explicitly specified in the objective specification which the process realizes the concretization of.

label: in deep part of
Defs: X superficial part of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two superficial and deep portions, X is part of the deep portion.

label: synapsed_by_via_type_Ib_bouton
Defs: Relation between a muscle and a motor neuron that synapses to it via a type Ib bouton.

label: capable of upregulating or causing pathological process
Defs: Holds between a material entity c and a pathological process p if and only if c is capable of some activity a, where a negatively regulates p.

label: supplies
Defs: Relation between an arterial structure and another structure, where the arterial structure acts as a conduit channeling fluid, substance or energy.

label: in reversal relationship with
Defs: Homoplasy that involves phenotypes similar to those seen in ancestors within the lineage.

label: in gametology relationship with
Defs: Historical homology that involves not recombining and subsequently differentiated sex chromosomes.

label: has 2D boundary
Defs: a relation between a material entity and a 2D immaterial entity (the boundary), in which the boundary delimits the material entity

label: is causal germline mutation in
Defs: Relates a gene to condition, such that a mutation in this gene is sufficient to produce the condition and that can be passed on to offspring[modified from orphanet].

label: indirectly regulates activity of
Defs: The entity A is not immediately upstream of the entity B but A has an activity that regulates an activity performed by B.

label: is about
Defs: A (currently) primitive relation that relates an information artifact to an entity.

label: in protein structural homology relationship with
Defs: Structural homology that is detected at the level of the 3D protein structure, but maybe not at the level of the amino acid sequence.

label: has part that occurs in
Defs: p has part that occurs in c if and only if there exists some p1, such that p has_part p1, and p1 occurs in c.

label: directly develops from
Defs: Candidate definition: x directly_develops from y if and only if there exists some developmental process (GO:0032502) p such that x and y both participate in p, and x is the output of p and y is the input of p, and a substantial portion of the matter of x comes from y, and the start of x is coincident with or after the end of y.

label: is carrier of
Defs: *b* is carrier of *c* at time *t* if and only if *c* *g-depends on* *b* at *t*

label: quality of
Defs: a relation between a quality and an independent continuant (the bearer), in which the quality specifically depends on the bearer for its existence

label: has active ingredient
Defs: A relationship that holds between a substance and a chemical entity, if the chemical entity is part of the substance, and the chemical entity forms the biologically active component of the substance.

label: in biological homology relationship with
Defs: Homology that is defined by sharing of a set of developmental constraints, caused by locally acting self-regulatory mechanisms of differentiation, between individualized parts of the phenotype.

label: anterior_to
Defs: x anterior_to y iff x is further along the antero-posterior axis than y, towards the head. An antero-posterior axis is an axis that bisects an organism from head end to opposite end of body or tail: bearer.

label: has allergic trigger
Defs: A relation between a condition (a phenotype or disease) of a host and a material entity, in which the material entity is not part of the host, and is considered harmless to non-allergic hosts, and the condition results in pathological processes that include an abnormally strong immune response against the material entity.

label: in progenesis relationship with
Defs: Paedomorphosis that is produced by precocious sexual maturation of an organism still in a morphologically juvenile stage.

label: myristoylates
Defs: A molecularly-interacts-with relationship between two entities, where the subject catalyzes a myristoylation activity that takes the object as input

label: determined by part of
Defs: s \'determined by part of\' w if and only if there exists some f such that (1) s \'determined by\' f and (2) f part_of w, or f=w.

label: regulates activity of
Defs: The entity A has an activity that regulates an activity of the entity B. For example, A and B are gene products where the catalytic activity of A regulates the kinase activity of B.

label: directly regulates
Defs: Process(P1) directly regulates process(P2) iff: P1 regulates P2 via direct physical interaction between an agent executing P1 (or some part of P1) and an agent executing P2 (or some part of P2).  For example, if protein A has protein binding activity(P1) that targets protein B and this binding  regulates the kinase activity (P2) of protein B then P1 directly regulates P2.

label: in in-paralogy relationship with
Defs: Paralogy that results from a lineage-specific duplication subsequent to a given speciation event.

label: obsolete different_in_magnitude_relative_to
Defs: OBSOLETE. q1 different_in_magnitude_relative_to q2 if and only if magnitude(q1) NOT =~ magnitude(q2). Here, magnitude(q) is a function that maps a quality to a unit-invariant scale.

label: biotically interacts with
Defs: An interaction relationship in which at least one of the partners is an organism and the other is either an organism or an abiotic entity with which the organism interacts.

label: has cross section
Defs: s3 has_cross_section s3 if and only if : there exists some 2d plane that intersects the bearer of s3, and the impression of s3 upon that plane has shape quality s2.

label: child nucleus of in hermaphrodite
Defs: A child nucleus relationship in which the cells are part of a hermaphroditic organism

label: expressed in
Defs: x expressed in y if and only if there is a gene expression process (GO:0010467) that occurs in y, and one of the following holds: (i) x is a gene, and x is transcribed into a transcript as part of the gene expression process (ii) x is a transcript, and the transcription of x is part of the gene expression process (iii) x is a mature gene product such as a protein, and x was translated or otherwise processes from a transcript that was transcribed as part of this gene expression process

label: results in changes to anatomical or cellular structure
Defs: p has anatomical participant c iff p has participant c, and c is an anatomical entity

label: obsolete has_cross_section
Defs: OBSOLETE. s3 has_cross_section s3 if and only if : there exists some 2d plane that intersects the bearer of s3, and the impression of s3 upon that plane has shape quality s2.

label: in deep homology relationship with
Defs: Homocracy that involves morphologically and phylogenetically disparate structures that are the result of parallel evolution.

label: directly negatively regulates quantity of
Defs: The entity A has an activity that directly negatively regulates the quantity of B.

label: is quality measurement of
Defs: m is a quality measurement of q at t. When q is a quality, there is a measurement process p that has specified output m, a measurement datum, that is about q

label: electrically_synapsed_to
Defs: A relation that holds between two neurons that are electrically coupled via gap junctions.

label: bounds sequence of
Defs: x bounds the sequence of y iff the upstream-most part of x is upstream of or coincident with the upstream-most part of y, and the downstream-most part of x is downstream of or coincident with the downstream-most part of y

label: has derived by descendant
Defs: inverse of derived by descent from

label: is autoimmune trigger for
Defs: A relation between a material entity and a condition (a phenotype or disease) of a host, in which the material entity is part of the host itself, and the condition results in pathological processes that include an abnormally strong immune response against the material entity.

label: determines
Defs: inverse of determined by

label: proper tributary of
Defs: x proper_tributary_of y iff x tributary_of y and x does not originate from y

label: skeleton of
Defs: inverse of has skeleton

label: in many to many homology relationship with
Defs: Historical homology that involves two members of a larger set of homologs.

label: ectoparasite of
Defs: A sub-relation of parasite-of in which the parasite lives on or in the integumental system of the host

label: synapsed_by_via_type_III_bouton
Defs: Relation between a muscle and a motor neuron that synapses to it via a type III bouton.

label: has model
Defs: Inverse of is-model-of

label: has symptom
Defs: A relation that holds between a disease or an organism and a phenotype

label: ubiquitously expressed in
Defs: x is ubiquitously expressed in y if and only if x is expressed in y, and the majority of cells in y express x

label: surrounds
Defs: inverse of surrounded by

label: existence ends with
Defs: x existence ends with y if and only if the time point at which x ends is equivalent to the time point at which y ends. Formally: x existence ends with y iff (x) = (y).

label: ameliorates condition
Defs: A relationship between an entity (e.g. a genotype, genetic variation, chemical, or environmental exposure) and a condition (a phenotype or disease), where the presence of the entity reduces or eliminates some or all aspects of the condition.

label: in branching relationship with
Defs: A relationship that holds between two material entities in a system of connected structures, where the branching relationship holds based on properties of the connecting network.

label: has prototype
Defs: x has prototype y if and only if x is an instance of C and y is a prototypical instance of C. For example, every instance of heart, both normal and abnormal is related by the has prototype relation to some instance of a "canonical" heart, which participates in blood circulation.

label: results in organization of
Defs: p results in organization of c iff p results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of c

label: in hypermorphosis relationship with
Defs: Peramorphosis that is produced by a delay in the offset of development.

label: indirectly negatively regulates quantity of
Defs: The entity A does not physically interact with the entity B, and A has an activity that down-regulates the quantity or abundance or concentration of B.

label: acts on population of
Defs: p acts on population of c iff c\' is a collection, has members of type c, and p has participant c

label: is causal susceptibility factor for
Defs: Relates a gene to condition, such that a mutation in this gene predisposes to the development of a condition  and that is necessary but not sufficient to develop the condition[modified from orphanet].

label: is consecutive sequence of
Defs: x is a consecutive sequence of y iff x has subsequence y, and all the parts of x are made of zero or more repetitions of y or sequences as the same type as y.

label: determined by
Defs: s determined by f if and only if s is a type of system, and f is a material entity that is part of s, such that f exerts a strong causal influence on the functioning of s, and the removal of f would cause the collapse of s.

label: results in transport to from or in
mentions
Defs: An information artifact IA mentions an entity E exactly when it has a component/part that denotes E

label: transitively provides input for
Defs: transitive form of directly_provides_input_for

label: has output
Defs: p has output c iff c is a participant in p, c is present at the end of p, and c is not present in the same state at the beginning of p.

label: has muscle antagonist
Defs: m1 has_muscle_antagonist m2 iff m1 has_muscle_insertion s, m2 has_muscle_insection s, m1 acts in opposition to m2, and m2 is responsible for returning the structure to its initial position.

label: transmitted by
Defs: A relationship that holds between a disease and organism

label: right of
Defs: Closer to the right side of the organism. Example: The dorsal fin is right of the left pectoral fin, but is left of the right eye. On the type level: X left of Y <=> every instance x of X is right of some instance y of Y, and there exists some organism o such that x part of o and y part of o.

label: has primary output
Defs: p has primary output c if (a) p has output c and (b) the goal of process is to modify, produce, or transform c.

label: has measurement datum
Defs: relates a time stamped measurement datum to the measurement datum that was measured

label: related via localization to
Defs: A relationship that holds via some process of localization

label: obsolete increased_in_magnitude_relative_to
Defs: OBSOLETE. q1 increased_in_magnitude_relative_to q2 if and only if magnitude(q1) > magnitude(q2). Here, magnitude(q) is a function that maps a quality to a unit-invariant scale.

label: results in development of
Defs: p \'results in development of\' c if and only if p is a developmental process and p results in the state of c changing from its initial state as a primordium or anlage through its mature state and to its final state.

label: in syntenic homology relationship with
Defs: Structural homology that is detected by similarity in content and organization between chromosomes.

label: derived from ancestral fusion of
Defs: x has_fused_element y iff: there exists some z : x has_part z, z homologous_to y, and y is a distinct element, the boundary between x and z is largely fiat

label: obligate parasite of
Defs: A sub-relation of parasite-of in which the parasite that cannot complete its life cycle without a host.

label: interacts with via parasite-host interaction
Defs: An interaction relationship between two organisms living together in more or less intimate association in a relationship in which association is disadvantageous or destructive to one of the organisms (GO).

label: in postdisplacement relationship with
Defs: Paedomorphosis that is produced by delayed growth of immature structures into the adult form.

label: realized in response to stimulus
Defs: A relationship between a realizable entity R (e.g. function or disposition) and a material entity M where R is realized in response to a process that has an input stimulus of M.

label: is marker for
Defs: c is marker for d iff the presence or occurrence of d is correlated with the presence of occurrence of c, and the observation of c is used to infer the presence or occurrence of d. Note that this does not imply that c and d are in a direct causal relationship, as it may be the case that there is a third entity e that stands in a direct causal relationship with c and d.

label: has exemplar data
Defs: A relation between a material entity and some data in which the data is taken as exemplifying the material entity.

label: sequentially adjacent to
Defs: x is sequentially adjacent to y iff x and y do not overlap and if there are no base units intervening between x and y

label: obsolete inversely_associated_with
Defs: OBSOLETE. q1 inversely_associated_with q2 iff q1 is dependent on q2, and the magnitude of q1 decreases if the magnitude of q2 is increased, or the magnitude of q1 increases if the magnitude of q2 is decreased. The relationship is not necessarily linear.

label: has primary input or output
Defs: p \'has primary input ot output\' c iff either (a) p \'has primary input\' c or (b) p \'has primary output\' c.

label: obsolete downstream in neural circuit with
Defs: OBSOLETE A relation that holds between a neuron that is synapsed_by another neuron or a neuron that is connected indirectly to another by a chain of neurons, each synapsed_by the next, in which the direction is from the last to the first.

label: has muscle insertion
Defs: m has_muscle_insertion s iff m is attaches_to s, and it is the case that when m contracts, s moves. Insertions are usually connections of muscle via tendon to bone.

label: ventral_to
Defs: x ventral_to y iff x is further along the dorso-ventral axis than y, towards the front. A dorso-ventral axis is an axis that bisects an organism from back (e.g. spinal column) to front (e.g. belly).

label: ubiquitinates
Defs: An interaction relation between x and y in which x catalyzes a reaction in which one or more ubiquitin groups are added to y

label: encircles
Defs: x encircles y if both x and y are regions of the 2D structure z, or 2D cross-sections of a 3D object z, and the boundary of y on z is exclusively continuous with x.

label: is evidence for
Defs:
A relationship between a piece of evidence a and some entity b, where b is  an information content entity, material entity or process, and 
the a supports either the existence of b, or the truth value of b.

label: is substance that treats
Defs: c is a substance that treats d if c is a material entity (such as a small molecule or compound) and d is a pathological process, phenotype or disease, and c is capable of some activity that negative regulates or decreases the magnitude of d.

label: is upstream of sequence of
Defs: inverse of downstream of sequence of

label: has exposure stressor
Defs: A broad relationship between an exposure event or process and any agent, stimulus, activity, or event that causes stress or tension on an organism and interacts with an exposure receptor during an exposure event.

label: has autoimmune trigger
Defs: A relation between a condition (a phenotype or disease) of a host and a material entity, in which the material entity is part of the host itself, and the condition results in pathological processes that include an abnormally strong immune response against the material entity.

label: causally downstream of
Defs: inverse of upstream of

label: receives synaptic input throughout
Defs: A relationship between a neuron and a region, where the neuron has a functionally relevant number of input synapses distributed throughout that region (rather than confined to a subregion).

label: medial_to
Defs: X medial to y if x is closer to the midsagittal plane than y.

label: participates in
Defs: a relation between a continuant and a process, in which the continuant is somehow involved in the process

label: directly positively regulated by
Defs: Process(P2) is directly postively regulated by process(P1) iff: P1 positively regulates P2 via direct physical interaction between an agent executing P1 (or some part of P1) and an agent executing P2 (or some part of P2).  For example, if protein A has protein binding activity(P1) that targets protein B and this binding positively regulates the kinase activity (P2) of protein B then P2 is directly postively regulated by P1.

label: acts upstream of, negative effect
Defs: c \'acts upstream of, negative effect\' p if c is enables f, and f is causally upstream of p, and the direction of f is negative

label: epiphyte of
Defs: An interaction relationship wherein a plant or algae is living on the outside surface of another plant.

label: disease has basis in disruption of
Defs: A relation that holds between the disease and a process where the physical basis of the disease disrupts execution of a key biological process.

label: preceded by
Defs: x is preceded by y if and only if the time point at which y ends is before or equivalent to the time point at which x starts. Formally: x preceded by y iff (y) <= (x), where  is a function that maps a process to a start point, and  is a function that maps a process to an end point.

label: innervates
Defs:
Relation between a \'neuron projection bundle\' and a region in which one or more of its component neuron projections either synapses to targets or receives synaptic input.
T innervates some R
Expands_to: T has_fasciculating_neuron_projection that synapse_in some R.

label: obsolete reciprocal_of
Defs: OBSOLETE. q1 reciprocal_of q2 if and only if : q1 and q2 are relational qualities and a phenotype e q1 e2 mutually implies a phenotype e2 q2 e.

label: location_of
Defs: a relation between two independent continuants, the location and the target, in which the target is entirely within the location

label: has primary substance added
Defs: \'has primary substance added\' indicates that an entity has had the given substance added to it in a proportion greater than any other added substance.

label: in 1 to many homology relationship with
Defs: Historical homology that involves a structure that has no other homologs in the species in which it is defined, and several homologous structures in another species.

label: ribosomal translation of
Defs: x is the ribosomal translation of y if and only if a ribosome reads x through a series of triplet codon-amino acid adaptor activities (GO:0030533) and produces y

label: branching part of
Defs: x is a branching part of y if and only if x is part of y and x is connected directly or indirectly to the main stem of y

label: has target end location
Defs: This relationship holds between p and l when p is a transport or localization process in which the outcome is to move some cargo c from a an initial location to some destination l.

label: acts upstream of, positive effect
Defs: c \'acts upstream of, positive effect\' p if c is enables f, and f is causally upstream of p, and the direction of f is positive

label: results in morphogenesis of
Defs: The relationship that links an entity with the process that results in the formation and shaping of that entity over time from an immature to a mature state.

label: in non functional homology relationship with
Defs: Structural homology that involves a pseudogenic feature and its functional ancestor.

label: regulates
Defs: process(P1) regulates process(P2) iff:P1 results in the initiation or termination of P2 OR affects the frequency of its initiation or termination OR affects the magnitude or rate of output of P2.

label: mutualistically interacts with
Defs: An interaction relationship between two organisms living together in more or less intimate association in a relationship in which both organisms benefit from each other (GO).

label: in synology relationship with
Defs: Xenology that results, not from the transfer of a gene between two species, but from a hybridization of two species.

label: fasciculates with
Defs: relationship between a neuron and a neuron projection bundle (e.g.- tract or nerve bundle) that one or more of its projections travels through.

label: in superficial part of
Defs: X superficial part of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two superficial and deep portions, X is part of the superficial portion.

label: gene product of
Defs: definition "x has gene product of y if and only if y is a gene (SO:0000704) that participates in some gene expression process (GO:0010467) where the output of that process is either y or something that is ribosomally translated from x"

label: spatially disjoint from
Defs: A is spatially_disjoint_from B if and only if they have no parts in common

label: subcluster of
Defs: A relation between a group and another group it is part of but does not fully constitute.

label: indirectly positively regulates activity of
Defs: The entity A is not immediately upstream of the entity B and has an activity that up-regulates an activity performed by B.

label: in hemiplasy relationship with
Defs: Historical homology that is characterized by topological discordance between a gene tree and a species tree attributable to the phylogenetic sorting of genetic polymorphisms across successive nodes in a species tree.

label: regulates quantity of
Defs: The entity A has an activity that regulates the quantity or abundance or concentration of the entity B.

label: obsolete_specifically denotes
Defs:
c specifically denotes r =def 
r is a portion of reality
& c is a particular quality
& c depends specifically on some independent continuant b 
& b acquired c as the result of the achievement of an objective to enable pointing to r repeatedly. 

Marked means there is a changed or additional quality of the bearer - the  quality is the information carrier.

Case 1
Memory trace as mark created when reading some description of some friend. The trace can denote.

Case 2
Pattern of ink arrayed on paper as mark when writing down a friend\'s name

Case 3
Pattern of magnetic domains on scattered pieces of a hard disk platter as mark when saving a file.

label: has branching part
Defs: inverse of branching part of

label: in paedomorphorsis relationship with
Defs: Heterochronous homology that is produced by a retention in adults of a species of traits previously seen only in juveniles.

label: transcribed from
Defs: x is transcribed from y if and only if x is synthesized from template y

label: in iterative homology relationship with
Defs: Biological homology that involves parts of the same organism.

label: has direct input
Defs: p has direct input c iff c is a participant in p, c is present at the start of p, and the state of c is modified during p.

label: starts with
Defs: x starts with y if and only if x has part y and the time point at which x starts is equivalent to the time point at which y starts. Formally: (y) = (x)  (y) < (x), where  is a function that maps a process to a start point, and  is a function that maps a process to an end point.

label: approximately perpendicular to
Defs: Crosses at an angle that is 90 degrees, or close to 90 degrees. In any non-linear organism, the main axes are rarely perpendicular when taken through the organism as a whole.

label: obsolete actively participates in
Defs: OBSOLETE x actively participates in y if and only if x participates in y and x realizes some active role

label: filtered through
Defs: Relationship between a fluid and a material entity, where the fluid is the output of a realization of a filtration role that inheres in the material entity.

label: contributes to morphology of
Defs: p contributes to morphology of w if and only if a change in the morphology of p entails a change in the morphology of w. Examples: every skull contributes to morphology of the head which it is a part of. Counter-example: nuclei do not generally contribute to the morphology of the cell they are part of, as they are buffered by cytoplasm.

label: in syngeny relationship with
Defs: Homocracy that involves recognizably corresponding characters that occurs in two or more taxa, or as a repeated unit within an individual.

label: child nucleus of in male
Defs: A child nucleus relationship in which the cells are part of a male organism

label: mereotopologically related to
Defs: A mereological relationship or a topological relationship

label: has exposure receptor
Defs: A broad relationship between an exposure event or process and any entity (e.g., an organism, organism population, or an organism part) that interacts with an exposure stimulus during the exposure event.

label: has negative regulatory component activity
Defs: A relationship that holds between a GO molecular function and a component of that molecular function that negatively regulates the activity of the whole.  More formally, A \'has regulatory component activity\' B iff :A and B are GO molecular functions (GO_0003674), A has_component B and A is negatively regulated by B.

label: in similarity relationship with
Defs: Relation between biological objects that resemble or are related to each other sufficiently to warrant a comparison.

label: has part structure that is capable of
Defs: s \'has part structure that is capable of\' p if and only if there exists some part x such that s \'has part\' x and x \'capable of\' p

label: indirectly negatively regulates activity of
Defs: The entity A is not immediately upstream of the entity B and has an activity that down-regulates an activity performed by B.

label: is treated by substance
Defs: Inverse of \'is substance that treats\'

label: has end location
Defs: x \'has end location\' y if and only if there exists some process z such that x \'ends with\' z and z \'occurs in\' y

label: in paramorphism relationship with
Defs: Iterative homology that involves two structures, one of which originated as a duplicate of the other and co-opted the expression of patterning genes of the ancestral structure.

label: has time stamp
Defs: relates a time stamped measurement datum to the time measurement datum that denotes the time when the measurement was taken

label: obsolete similar_in_magnitude_relative_to
Defs: OBSOLETE. q1 similar_in_magnitude_relative_to q2 if and only if magnitude(q1) =~ magnitude(q2). Here, magnitude(q) is a function that maps a quality to a unit-invariant scale.

label: lays eggs on
Defs: An interaction relationship in which organism a lays eggs on the outside surface of organism b. Organism b is neither helped nor harmed in the process of egg laying or incubation.

label: capable of negatively regulating
Defs: Holds between c and p if and only if c is capable of some activity a, and a negatively regulates p.

label: disposition of
Defs: inverse of has disposition

label: molecularly interacts with
Defs: An interaction relationship in which the two partners are molecular entities that directly physically interact with each other for example via a stable binding interaction or a brief interaction during which one modifies the other.

label: contains process
Defs: [copied from inverse property \'occurs in\'] b occurs_in c =def b is a process and c is a material entity or immaterial entity& there exists a spatiotemporal region r and b occupies_spatiotemporal_region r.& forall(t) if b exists_at t then c exists_at t & there exist spatial regions s and s where & b spatially_projects_onto s at t& c is occupies_spatial_region s at t& s is a proper_continuant_part_of s at t

label: disease has location
Defs: A relationship between a disease and an anatomical entity where the disease has one or more features that are located in that entity.

label: immediately superficial to
Defs: x immediately superficial to y iff x superficial to y and x is contiguous with y.

label: is downstream of sequence of
Defs: x is downstream of the sequence of y iff either (1) x and y have sequence units, and all units of x are downstream of all units of y, or (2) x and y are sequence units, and x is either immediately downstream of y, or transitively downstream of y.

label: in plesiomorphy relationship with
Defs: Historical homology that is based on distant shared ancestry.

label: is small molecule regulator of
Defs: a relation between a continuant and a process, in which the continuant is a small molecule that regulates the process

label: is immediately upstream of sequence of
Defs: inverse of immediately downstream of

label: dendrite synapsed in
Defs: Relation between a neuron and some structure  (e.g.- a brain region) in which its dendrite receives synaptic input.

label: has biological role
Defs: c has-biological-role r iff c has-role r and r is a biological role (CHEBI:24432)

label: proper distributary of
Defs: x proper_distributary_of y iff x distributary_of y and x does not flow back into y

label: is evidence with support from
Defs: A relationship between a piece of evidence and an entity that plays a role in supporting that evidence.

label: has start location
Defs: x \'has starts location\' y if and only if there exists some process z such that x \'starts with\' z and z \'occurs in\' y

label: in distal side of
Defs: x in distal side of y <=> if y is subdivided into two proximal and distal portions, y is part of the distal portion.

label: in homoeology relationship with
Defs: Synology that results from allopolyploidy.

label: has component
Defs: w \'has component\' p if w \'has part\' p and w is such that it can be directly disassembled into into n parts p, p2, p3, ..., pn, where these parts are of similar type.

label: disease has feature
Defs: A relationship between a disease and some feature of that disease, where the feature is either a phenotype or an isolated disease.

label: immediately proximal to
Defs: x immediately proximal to y iff x proximal to y and x is contiguous with y.

label: directly positively regulates quantity of
Defs: The entity A has an activity that directly positively regulates the quantity of B.

label: has small molecule inhibitor
Defs: a relation between a process and a continuant, in which the process is inhibited by the small molecule continuant

label: left of
Defs: Closer to the left side of the organism. Example: The dorsal fin is right of the left pectoral fin, but is left of the right eye. On the type level: X left of Y <=> every instance x of X is left of some instance y of Y, and there exists some organism o such that x part of o and y part of o.

label: in proximal side of
Defs: x in proximal side of y <=> if y is subdivided into two proximal and distal portions, y is part of the proximal portion.

label: surrounded by
Defs: x surrounded_by y if and only if (1) x is adjacent to y and for every region r that is adjacent to x, r overlaps y (2) the shared boundary between x and y occupies the majority of the outermost boundary of x

label: disease has inflammation site
Defs: A relationship between a disease and an anatomical entity where the disease is triggered by an inflammatory response to stimuli occurring in the anatomical entity

label: part of structure that is capable of
Defs: this relation holds between c and p when c is part of some c\', and c\' is capable of p.

label: in homoplasy relationship with
Defs: Similarity that results from independent evolution.

label: derived by descent from
Defs: d derived_by_descent_from a if d is specified by some genetic program that is sequence-inherited-from a genetic program that specifies a.

label: cell expresses
Defs: A relation that applies between a cell(c) and a gene(g) , where the process of \'transcription, DNA templated (GO_0006351)\' is occuring in in cell c and that process has input gene g.

label: in anterior side of
Defs: X anterior side of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two anterior and posterior portions, X is part of the anterior portion.

label: has characteristic
Defs: a relation between an independent continuant (the bearer) and a specifically dependent continuant (the dependent), in which the dependent specifically depends on the bearer for its existence

label: indirectly regulates quantity of
Defs: The entity A is not immediately upstream of the entity B, but A has an activity that regulates the quantity or abundance or concentration of B.

label: has positive regulatory component activity
Defs: A relationship that holds between a GO molecular function and a component of that molecular function that positively regulates the activity of the whole.  More formally, A \'has regulatory component activity\' B iff :A and B are GO molecular functions (GO_0003674), A has_component B and A is positively regulated by B.

label: causally downstream of or within
Defs: inverse of causally upstream of or within

label: helper property (not for use in curation)
has habitat
Defs: x \'has habitat\' y if and only if: x is an organism, y is a habitat, and y can sustain and allow the growth of a population of xs.

label: in many to many orthology relationship with
Defs: Orthology that involves two genes that experienced duplications more recent than the species split that created them.

label: coincident with
Defs: A relation that holds between two linear structures that are approximately parallel to each other for their entire length and where either the two structures are adjacent to each other or one is part of the other.

label: participates in a biotic-biotic interaction with
lateral_to
Defs: X lateral to y if x is further from the midsagittal plane than y.

label: has chemical role
Defs: c has-chemical-role r iff c has-role r and r is a chemical role (CHEBI:51086)

label: biomechanically related to
Defs: A relation that holds between elements of a musculoskeletal system or its analogs.

label: has input
Defs: p has input c iff: p is a process, c is a material entity, c is a participant in p, c is present at the start of p, and the state of c is modified during p.

label: has potential to develop into
Defs: x has the potential to develop into y iff x develops into y or if x is capable of developing into y

label: results in developmental progression of
Defs: p results in the developmental progression of s iff p is a developmental process and s is an anatomical structure and p causes s to undergo a change in state at some point along its natural developmental cycle (this cycle starts with its formation, through the mature structure, and ends with its loss).

label: directly negatively regulated by
Defs: Process(P2) is directly negatively regulated by process(P1) iff: P1 negatively regulates P2 via direct physical interaction between an agent executing P1 (or some part of P1) and an agent executing P2 (or some part of P2).  For example, if protein A has protein binding activity(P1) that targets protein B and this binding  negatively regulates the kinase activity (P2) of protein B then P2 directly negatively regulated by P1.

label: develops in
Defs: x develops_in y if x is located in y whilst x is developing

label: existence ends during or before
Defs: x existence ends during or before y if and only if the time point at which x ends is before or equivalent to the time point at which y ends.

label: directly regulates quantity of
Defs: The entity A, immediately upstream of B, has an activity that directly regulates the quantity of B.

label: has parasitoid
Defs: inverse of parasitoid of

label: under-expressed in
Defs: g is under-expressed in t iff g is expressed in t, and the expression level of g is decreased relative to some background.

label: has small molecule activator
Defs: a relation between a process and a continuant, in which the process is activated by the small molecule continuant

label: dorsal to
Defs: x dorsal to y iff x is further along the dorso-ventral axis than y, towards the back. A dorso-ventral axis is an axis that extends through an organism from back (e.g. spinal column) to front (e.g. belly).

label: destabilizes quantity of
Defs: An entity A directly interacts with B and A has an activity that decreases the amount of an entity B by degradating it.

label: bounding layer of
Defs:
X outer_layer_of Y iff:
. X :continuant that bearer_of some PATO:laminar
. X part_of Y
. exists Z :surface
. X has_boundary Z
. Z boundary_of Y

has_boundary: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002002
boundary_of: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002000

label: results in specification of
Defs: The relationship linking a cell and its participation in a process that results in the fate of the cell being specified. Once specification has taken place, a cell will be committed to differentiate down a specific pathway if left in its normal environment.

label: results in determination of
Defs: p \'results in determination of\' c if and only if p is a developmental process and c is a cell and p results in the state of c changing to be determined. Once a cell becomes determined, it becomes committed to differentiate down a particular pathway regardless of its environment.

label: transcribed to
Defs: inverse of transcribed from

label: in ohnology relationship with
Defs: Paralogy that results from a whole genome duplication event.

label: obsolete upstream in neural circuit with
Defs: OBSOLETE A relation that holds between a neuron that is synapsed_to another neuron or a neuron that is connected indirectly to another by a chain of neurons, each synapsed_to the next, in which the direction is from the last to the first.

label: involved in
Defs: c involved_in p if and only if c enables some process p\', and p\' is part of p

label: has muscle origin
Defs: m has_muscle_origin s iff m is attached_to s, and it is the case that when m contracts, s does not move. The site of the origin tends to be more proximal and have greater mass than what the other end attaches to.

label: develops from part of
Defs: x develops from part of y if and only if there exists some z such that x develops from z and z is part of y

label: commensually interacts with
Defs: An interaction relationship between two organisms living together in more or less intimate association in a relationship in which one benefits and the other is unaffected (GO).

label: confers susceptibility to condition
Defs: Relates a gene to condition, such that a variation in this gene predisposes to the development of a condition.

label: causal relation between material entity and a process
Defs: A relationship that holds between a material entity and a process in which causality is involved, with either the material entity or some part of the material entity exerting some influence over the process, or the process influencing some aspect of the material entity.

label: interacts with
Defs: A relationship that holds between two entities in which the processes executed by the two entities are causally connected.

label: has soma location
Defs: Relation between a neuron and an anatomical structure that its soma is part of.

label: has developmental contribution from
Defs: x has developmental contribution from y iff x has some part z such that z develops from y

label: connected to
Defs: a is connected to b if and only if a and b are discrete structure, and there exists some connecting structure c, such that c connects a and b

label: developmentally related to
Defs: A relationship that holds between entities participating in some developmental process (GO:0032502)

label: in taxon
Defs: x is in taxon y if an only if y is an organism, and the relationship between x and y is one of: part of (reflexive), developmentally preceded by, derives from, secreted by, expressed.

label: does not overlap sequence of
Defs: x does not overlaps the sequence of x if and only if there is no z such that x has a subsequence z and z is a subsequence of y.

label: has subsequence
Defs: x has subsequence y iff all of the sequence parts of x are sequence parts of y

label: in ventral side of
Defs: X ventral side of Y <=> if Y is subdivided into two dorsal and ventral portions, X is part of the ventral portion.

label: directly negatively regulates
Defs: Process(P1) directly negatively regulates process(P2) iff: P1 negatively regulates P2 via direct physical interaction between an agent executing P1 (or some part of P1) and an agent executing P2 (or some part of P2).  For example, if protein A has protein binding activity(P1) that targets protein B and this binding  negatively regulates the kinase activity (P2) of protein B then P1 directly negatively regulates P2.

label: aboral to
Defs: nearer to the aboral opening of the organism, on the oral-aboral axis.

label: has potential to developmentally contribute to
Defs: x has potential to developmentrally contribute to y iff x developmentally contributes to y or x is capable of developmentally contributing to y

label: has presynaptic terminal in
Defs: Relation between a neuron and some structure (e.g.- a brain region) in which it receives (chemical) synaptic input.

label: has host
Defs: X \'has host\' y if and only if: x is an organism, y is an organism, and x can live on the surface of or within the body of y

label: genomically related to
Defs: holds between two entities when some genome-level process such as gene expression is involved. This includes transcriptional, spliceosomal events. These relations can be used between either macromolecule entities (such as regions of nucleic acid) or between their abstract informational counterparts.

label: in functional equivalence relationship with
Defs: Similarity that is characterized by interchangeability in function.

label: occurs across
Defs: A relationship between a process and a barrier, where the process occurs in a region spanning the barrier. For cellular processes the barrier is typically a membrane. Examples include transport across a membrane and membrane depolarization.

label: hyperparasite of
Defs: x is a hyperparasite of y iff x is a parasite of a parasite of the target organism y

label: exacerbates condition
Defs: A relationship between an entity (e.g. a chemical, environmental exposure, or some form of genetic variation) and a condition (a phenotype or disease), where the presence of the entity worsens some or all aspects of the condition.

label: starts
Defs: inverse of starts with

label: distributary of
Defs: x distributary_of y if and only if x is capable of channeling the flow of a substance to y, where y channels less of the substance than x

label: capable of part of
Defs: c stands in this relationship to p if and only if there exists some p\' such that c is capable_of p\', and p\' is part_of p.

label: has driver
Defs: A relation between two entities, in which one of the entities is any natural or human-influenced factor that directly or indirectly causes a change in the other entity.

label: has connecting branch
Defs: inverse of connecting branch of

label: synapsed_via_type_Is_bouton_to
Defs: A relation between a motor neuron and a muscle that it synapses to via a type Is bouton.

label: immediately ventral to
Defs: x immediately ventral to y iff x ventral to y and x is contiguous with y.

label: has exposure stimulus
Defs: A relationship between an exposure event or process and any agent, stimulus, activity, or event that causally effects an organism and interacts with an exposure receptor during an exposure event.

label: causally upstream of or within, negative effect
causal relation between processes
Defs: p is causally related to q if and only if p or any part of p and q or any part of q are linked by a chain of events where each event pair is one of direct activation or direct inhibition. p may be upstream, downstream, part of or a container of q.

label: sends synaptic output to cell
Defs: A relationship between a neuron and a cell that it has a functionally relevant number of chemical synapses to.

label: is_specified_output_of
Defs: A relation between a planned process and a continuant participating in that process. The presence of the continuant at the end of the process is explicitly specified in the objective specification which the process realizes the concretization of.

label: acts upstream of or within, negative effect
conduit for
Defs: x is a conduit for y iff y passes through the lumen of x.

label: connecting branch of
Defs: b connecting-branch-of s iff b is connected to s, and there exists some tree-like structure t such that the mereological sum of b plus s is either the same as t or a branching-part-of t.

label: is myristoyltransferase activity
Defs: Helper relation for OWL definition of RO:0018002 myristoylates

label: obsolete related via dependence to
Defs: A relationship that holds between two entities, where the relationship holds based on the presence or absence of statistical dependence relationship. The entities may be statistical variables, or they may be other kinds of entities such as diseases, chemical entities or processes.

label: sequentially related to
Defs: A relation that holds between two entities that have the property of being sequences or having sequences.

label: indirectly activates
Defs: p indirectly activates q if and only if p is upstream of q and there is a chain of directly activates relationships connecting p and q, where the chain is of length greater than one.

label: synapsed to
Defs: Relation between a neuron and an anatomical structure (including cells) that it chemically synapses to.

label: has member
Defs: has member is a mereological relation between a collection and an item.

label: in heterochronous homology relationship with
Defs: Biological homology that is characterized by changes, over evolutionary time, in the rate or timing of developmental events of homologous structures.

label: distally connected to
Defs: x distally_connected_to y iff the distal part of x is connected to y. i.e. x connected_to y and x proximal_to y.

label: co-roosts with
Defs: Two or more individuals sharing the same roost site (cave, mine, tree or tree hollow, animal burrow, leaf tent, rock crack, space in man-made structure, etc.). Individuals that are sharing a communal roost may be said to be co-roosting. The roost may be either a day roost where the individuals rest during daytime hours, or a night roost where individuals roost to feed, groom, or rest in between flights and/or foraging bouts.  Communal roosting as thus defined is an umbrella term within which different specialized types -- which are not mutually exclusive -- may be recognized based on taxonomy and the temporal and spatial relationships of the individuals that are co-roosting.

label: in latent homology relationship with
Defs: Parallelism that involves morphologically very similar structures, occurring only within some members of a taxon and absent in the common ancestor (which possessed the developmental basis to develop this character).

label: has high plasma membrane amount
Defs: A relation between a cell and molecule or complex such that every instance of the cell has a high number of instances of that molecule expressed on the cell surface.

label: has disease
Defs: A relationship that holds between an organism and a disease. Here a disease is construed broadly as a disposition to undergo pathological processes that exists in an organism because of one or more disorders in that organism.

label: has regulatory component activity
Defs: A \'has regulatory component activity\' B if A and B are GO molecular functions (GO_0003674), A has_component B and A is regulated by B.

label: has_part
Defs: Q1 has_part Q2 if and only if: every instance of Q1 is a quality_of an entity that has_quality some Q2.

label: decreased in magnitude relative to
Defs: q1 decreased_in_magnitude_relative_to q2 if and only if magnitude(q1) < magnitude(q2). Here, magnitude(q) is a function that maps a quality to a unit-invariant scale.

label: stabilizes quantity of
Defs: An entity A physically interacts with B and A has an activity that increases the amount of an entity B by stabilizing it.

label: located in
Defs: a relation between two independent continuants, the target and the location, in which the target is entirely within the location

label: sends synaptic output to region
Defs: A relationship between a neuron and a region, where the neuron has a functionally relevant number of output synapses in that region.

label: derives from
Defs: a relation between two distinct material entities, the new entity and the old entity, in which the new entity begins to exist when the old entity ceases to exist, and the new entity inherits the significant portion of the matter of the old entity

label: in register with
existence overlaps
Defs: x existence overlaps y if and only if either (a) the start of x is part of y or (b) the end of x is part of y. Formally: x existence starts and ends during y iff ((x) >= (y) & (x) <= (y)) OR ((x) <= (y) & (x) >= (y))

label: obsolete has active participant
Defs: OBSOLETE x has participant y if and only if x realizes some active role that inheres in y

label: capable of regulating
Defs: Holds between c and p if and only if c is capable of some activity a, and a regulates p.

label: directly negatively regulates activity of
Defs:
The entity A, immediately upstream of the entity B, has an activity that negatively regulates an activity performed by B. 
For example, A and B may be gene products and binding of B by A negatively regulates the kinase activity of B.

label: disease has basis in dysfunction of
Defs: A relation that holds between the disease and a material entity where the physical basis of the disease is a disorder of that material entity that affects its function.

label: has disposition
Defs: a relation between an independent continuant (the bearer) and a disposition, in which the disposition specifically depends on the bearer for its existence

label: superficial to
Defs: Near the outer surface of the organism. Thus, skin is superficial to the muscle layer.

label: ecologically related to
Defs: A relationship that is mediated in some way by the environment or environmental feature (ENVO:00002297)

label: attached to part of
Defs: a is attached to part of b if a is attached to b, or a is attached to some p, where p is part of b.

label: in homology relationship with
Defs: Similarity that results from common evolutionary origin.

label: related via exposure to
Defs: Any relationship between an exposure event or process and any other entity.

label: different in magnitude relative to
Defs: q1 different_in_magnitude_relative_to q2 if and only if magnitude(q1) NOT =~ magnitude(q2). Here, magnitude(q) is a function that maps a quality to a unit-invariant scale.

label: characteristic of part of
